quran[6235]{c,v,t}:
  1,1,All praise is for AllahвАФLord of all worlds
  1,2,"the Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  1,3,Master of the Day of Judgment
  1,4,You ЋєaloneЋЇ we worship and You ЋєaloneЋЇ we ask for help
  1,5,Guide us along the Straight Path
  1,6,"the Path of those You have blessedвАФnot those You are displeased with, or those who are astray"
  2,1,Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m
  2,2,This is the Book! There is no doubt about itвАФa guide for those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ
  2,3,"who believe in the unseen,¬†establish prayer, and donate from what We have provided for them"
  2,4,"and who believe in what has been revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ¬†and what was revealed before you, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  2,5,"It is they who are ЋєtrulyЋЇ guided by their Lord, and it is they who will be successful"
  2,6,"As for those who persist in disbelief, it is the same whether you warn them or notвАФthey will never believe"
  2,7,"Allah has sealed their hearts and their hearing, and their sight is covered. They will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  2,8,"And there are some who say, вАЬWe believe in Allah and the Last Day,вАЭ yet they are not ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  2,9,"They seek to deceive Allah and the believers, yet they only deceive themselves, but they fail to perceive it"
  2,10,"There is sickness in their hearts, and Allah ЋєonlyЋЇ lets their sickness increase. They will suffer a painful punishment for their lies"
  2,11,"When they are told, вАЬDo not spread corruption in the land,вАЭ they reply, вАЬWe are only peace-makers!вАЭ"
  2,12,"Indeed, it is they who are the corruptors, but they fail to perceive it"
  2,13,"And when they are told, вАЬBelieve as others believe,вАЭ they reply, вАЬWill we believe as the fools believe?вАЭ Indeed, it is they who are fools, but they do not know"
  2,14,"When they meet the believers they say, вАЬWe believe.вАЭ But when alone with their evil associates they say, вАЬWe are definitely with you; we were only mocking.вАЭ"
  2,15,"Allah will throw their mockery back at them, leaving them to continue wandering blindly in their defiance"
  2,16,"They are the ones who trade guidance for misguidance. But this trade is profitless, and they are not ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  2,17,"Their example is that of someone who kindles a fire, but when it lights up all around them, Allah takes away their light, leaving them in complete darknessвАФunable to see"
  2,18,"They are ЋєwilfullyЋЇ deaf, dumb, and blind, so they will never return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ"
  2,19,"Or Ћєthose caught inЋЇ a rainstorm from the sky with darkness, thunder, and lightning. They press their fingers into their ears at the sound of every thunder-clap for fear of death. And Allah encompasses the disbelievers Ћєby His mightЋЇ"
  2,20,"It is as if the lightning were about to snatch away their sight. Whenever lightning strikes, they walk in its light, but when darkness covers them, they stand still. Had Allah willed, He could have taken away their hearing and sight. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,21,"O humanity! Worship your Lord, Who created you and those before you, so that you may become mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ"
  2,22,"ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who has made the earth a place of settlement for you and the sky a canopy; and sends down rain from the sky, causing fruits to grow as a provision for you. So do not knowingly set up equals to Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇ"
  2,23,"And if you are in doubt about what We have revealed to Our servant,¬†then produce a s√їrah¬†like it and call your helpers other than Allah, if what you say is true"
  2,24,"But if you are unable to do soвАФand you will never be able to do soвАФthen fear the Fire fuelled with people and stones, which is prepared for the disbelievers"
  2,25,"Give good news ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to those who believe and do good that they will have Gardens under which rivers flow. Whenever provided with fruit, they will say, вАЬThis is what we were given before,вАЭ for they will be served fruit that looks similar Ћєbut tastes differentЋЇ. They will have pure spouses,¬†and they will be there forever"
  2,26,"Surely Allah does not shy away from using the parable of a mosquito or what is even smaller. As for the believers, they know that it is the truth from their Lord. And as for the disbelievers, they argue, вАЬWhat does Allah mean by such a parable?вАЭ Through this ЋєtestЋЇ, He leaves many to stray, and guides many. And He leaves none to stray except the rebelliousвАФ"
  2,27,"those who violate AllahвАЩs covenant after it has been affirmed, break whatever ЋєtiesЋЇ Allah has ordered to be maintained, and spread corruption in the land. It is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ losers"
  2,28,"How can you deny Allah? You were lifeless and He gave you life, then He will cause you to die and again bring you to life, and then to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  2,29,"He is the One Who created everything in the earth for you. Then He turned towards the heaven, forming it into seven heavens. And He has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  2,30,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when your Lord said to the angels, вАЬI am going to place a successive ЋєhumanЋЇ authority on earth.вАЭ They asked ЋєAllahЋЇ, вАЬWill You place in it someone who will spread corruption there and shed blood while we glorify Your praises and proclaim Your holiness?вАЭ Allah responded, вАЬI know what you do not know.вАЭ"
  2,31,"He taught Adam the names of all things, then He presented them to the angels and said, вАЬTell Me the names of these, if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  2,32,"They replied, вАЬGlory be to You! We have no knowledge except what You have taught us. You are truly the All-Knowing, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  2,33,"Allah said, вАЬO Adam! Inform them of their names.вАЭ Then when Adam did, Allah said, вАЬDid I not tell you that I know the secrets of the heavens and the earth, and I know what you reveal and what you conceal?вАЭ"
  2,34,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We said to the angels, вАЬProstrate before Adam,вАЭ¬†so they all didвАФbut not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who refused and acted arrogantly,¬†becoming unfaithful"
  2,35,"We cautioned, вАЬO Adam! Live with your wife in Paradise and eat as freely as you please, but do not approach this tree, or else you will be wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  2,36,"But Satan deceived themвАФleading to their fall from the ЋєblissfulЋЇ state they were in,¬†and We said, вАЬDescend from the heavens Ћєto the earthЋЇ as enemies to each other.¬†You will find in the earth a residence and provision for your appointed stay.вАЭ"
  2,37,"Then Adam was inspired with words Ћєof prayerЋЇ by his Lord,¬†so He accepted his repentance. Surely He is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,38,"We said, вАЬDescend all of you! Then when guidance comes to you from Me, whoever follows it, there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,39,But those who disbelieve and deny Our signs will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever.вАЭ
  2,40,"O children of Israel!¬†Remember My favours upon you. Fulfil your covenant and I will fulfil Mine, and stand in awe of Me ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  2,41,Believe in My revelations which confirm your Scriptures.¬†Do not be the first to deny them or trade them for a fleeting gain.¬†And be mindful of Me
  2,42,Do not mix truth with falsehood or hide the truth knowingly
  2,43,"Establish prayer, pay alms-tax,¬†and bow down with those who bow down"
  2,44,"Do you preach righteousness and fail to practice it yourselves, although you read the Scripture? Do you not understand"
  2,45,"And seek help through patience and prayer. Indeed, it is a burden except for the humbleвАФ"
  2,46,those who are certain that they will meet their Lord and to Him they will return
  2,47,O Children of Israel! Remember ЋєallЋЇ the favours I granted you and how I honoured you above the others
  2,48,"Guard yourselves against the Day on which no soul will be of help to another. No intercession¬†will be accepted, no ransom taken, and no help will be given"
  2,49,"ЋєRememberЋЇ how We delivered you from the people of Pharaoh, who afflicted you with dreadful torment, slaughtering your sons and keeping your women. That was a severe test from your Lord"
  2,50,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We parted the sea, rescued you, and drowned PharaohвАЩs people before your very eyes"
  2,51,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We appointed forty nights for Moses, then you worshipped the calf in his absence, acting wrongfully"
  2,52,Even then We ЋєstillЋЇ forgave you so perhaps you would be grateful
  2,53,And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We gave Moses the ScriptureвАФthe standard Ћєto distinguish between right and wrongЋЇ that perhaps you would be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  2,54,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Moses said to his people, вАЬO my people! Surely you have wronged yourselves by worshipping the calf, so turn in repentance to your Creator and execute Ћєthe calf-worshippers amongЋЇ yourselves. That is best for you in the sight of your Creator.вАЭ Then He accepted your repentance. Surely He is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,55,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when you said, вАЬO Moses! We will never believe you until we see Allah with our own eyes,вАЭ so a thunderbolt struck you while you were looking on"
  2,56,"Then We brought you back to life after your death, so that perhaps you would be grateful"
  2,57,"And Ћєremember whenЋЇ We shaded you with clouds and sent down to you manna and quails,¬†ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬEat from the good things We have provided for you.вАЭ The evildoers ЋєcertainlyЋЇ did not wrong Us, but wronged themselves"
  2,58,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We said, вАЬEnter this city and eat freely from wherever you please; enter the gate with humility, saying, вАШAbsolve us.вАЩ We will forgive your sins and multiply the reward for the good-doers.вАЭ"
  2,59,But the wrongdoers changed the words they were commanded to say. So We sent down a punishment from the heavens upon them for their rebelliousness
  2,60,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Moses prayed for water for his people, We said, вАЬStrike the rock with your staff.вАЭ Then twelve springs gushed out, ЋєandЋЇ each tribe knew its drinking place. ЋєWe then said,ЋЇ вАЬEat and drink of AllahвАЩs provisions, and do not go about spreading corruption in the land.вАЭ"
  2,61,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when you said, вАЬO Moses! We cannot endure the same meal Ћєevery dayЋЇ. So ЋєjustЋЇ call upon your Lord on our behalf, He will bring forth for us some of what the earth produces of herbs, cucumbers, garlic, lentils, and onions.вАЭ Moses scolded ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬDo you exchange what is better for what is worse? ЋєYou canЋЇ go down to any village and you will find what you have asked for.вАЭ They were stricken with disgrace and misery, and they invited the displeasure of Allah for rejecting AllahвАЩs signs and unjustly killing the prophets. This is Ћєa fair rewardЋЇ for their disobedience and violations"
  2,62,"Indeed, the believers, Jews, Christians, and SabiansвАФwhoever ЋєtrulyЋЇ believes in Allah and the Last Day and does good will have their reward with their Lord. And there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,63,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We took a covenant from you and raised the mountain above you ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬHold firmly to that ЋєScriptureЋЇ which We have given you and observe its teachings so perhaps you will become mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ.вАЭ"
  2,64,"Yet you turned away afterwards. Had it not been for AllahвАЩs grace and mercy upon you, you would have certainly been of the losers"
  2,65,"You are already aware of those of you who broke the Sabbath. We said to them, вАЬBe disgraced apes!вАЭ"
  2,66,"So We made their fate an example to present and future generations, and a lesson to the God-fearing"
  2,67,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Moses said to his people, вАЬAllah commands you to sacrifice a cow.вАЭ¬†They replied, вАЬAre you mocking us?вАЭ Moses responded, вАЬI seek refuge in Allah from acting foolishly!вАЭ"
  2,68,"They said, вАЬCall upon your Lord to clarify for us what type Ћєof cowЋЇ it should be!вАЭ He replied, вАЬAllah says, вАШThe cow should neither be old nor young but in between. So do as you are commanded!вАЩвАЭ"
  2,69,"They said, вАЬCall upon your Lord to specify for us its colour.вАЭ He replied, вАЬAllah says, вАШIt should be a bright yellow cowвАФpleasant to see.вАЩвАЭ"
  2,70,"Again they said, вАЬCall upon your Lord so that He may make clear to us which cow, for all cows look the same to us. Then, Allah willing, we will be guided Ћєto the right oneЋЇ.вАЭ"
  2,71,"He replied, вАЬAllah says, вАШIt should have been used neither to till the soil nor water the fields; wholesome and without blemish.вАЩвАЭ They said, вАЬNow you have come with the truth.вАЭ Yet they still slaughtered it hesitantly"
  2,72,"ЋєThis isЋЇ when a man was killed and you disputed who the killer was, but Allah revealed what you concealed"
  2,73,"So We instructed, вАЬStrike the dead body with a piece of the cow.вАЭ This is how ЋєeasilyЋЇ Allah brings the dead to life, showing you His signs so that you may understand"
  2,74,"Even then your hearts became hardened like a rock or even harder, for some rocks gush rivers; others split, spilling water; while others are humbled in awe of Allah. And Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,75,"Do you Ћєbelievers stillЋЇ expect them to be true to you, though a group of them would hear the word of Allah then knowingly corrupt it after understanding it"
  2,76,"When they meet the believers they say, вАЬWe believe.вАЭ But in private they say Ћєto each otherЋЇ, вАЬWill you disclose to the believers the knowledge Allah has revealed to you,¬†so that they may use it against you before your Lord? Do you not understand?вАЭ"
  2,77,Do they not know that Allah is aware of what they conceal and what they reveal
  2,78,"And among them are the illiterate who know nothing about the Scripture except lies, and ЋєsoЋЇ they ЋєwishfullyЋЇ speculate"
  2,79,"So woe¬†to those who distort the Scripture with their own hands then say, вАЬThis is from AllahвАЭвАФseeking a fleeting gain! So woe to them for what their hands have written, and woe to them for what they have earned"
  2,80,"ЋєSome ofЋЇ the Jews claim, вАЬThe Fire will not touch us except for a number of days.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHave you taken a pledge from AllahвАФfor Allah never breaks His wordвАФor are you ЋєjustЋЇ saying about Allah what you do not know?вАЭ"
  2,81,But no! Those who commit evil and are engrossed in sin will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever
  2,82,And those who believe and do good will be the residents of Paradise. They will be there forever
  2,83,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We took a covenant from the children of Israel ЋєstatingЋЇ, вАЬWorship none but Allah; be kind to parents, relatives, orphans and the needy; speak kindly to people; establish prayer; and pay alms-tax.вАЭ But you ЋєIsraelitesЋЇ turned awayвАФexcept for a few of youвАФand were indifferent"
  2,84,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We took your covenant that you would neither shed each otherвАЩs blood nor expel each other from their homes, you gave your pledge and bore witness"
  2,85,"But here you are, killing each other and expelling some of your people from their homes, aiding one another in sin and aggression; and when those ЋєexpelledЋЇ come to you as captives, you still ransom themвАФthough expelling them was unlawful for you.¬†Do you believe in some of the Scripture and reject the rest? Is there any reward for those who do so among you other than disgrace in this worldly life and being subjected to the harshest punishment on the Day of Judgment? For Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,86,"These are the ones who trade the Hereafter for the life of this world. So their punishment will not be reduced, nor will they be helped"
  2,87,"Indeed, We gave Moses the Book and sent after him successive messengers. And We gave Jesus, son of Mary, clear proofs and supported him with the holy spirit.¬†Why is it that every time a messenger comes to you ЋєIsraelitesЋЇ with something you do not like, you become arrogant, rejecting some and killing others"
  2,88,"They say, вАЬOur hearts are unreceptive!вАЭ¬†In fact, Allah has condemned them for their disbelief. They have but little faith"
  2,89,"Although they used to pray for victory Ћєby means of the ProphetЋЇ over the polytheists,¬†when there came to them a Book from Allah which they recognized,¬†confirming the Scripture they had Ћєin their handsЋЇ, they rejected it. So may AllahвАЩs condemnation be upon the disbelievers"
  2,90,Miserable is the price they have sold their souls forвАФdenying AllahвАЩs revelation and resenting Allah for granting His grace to whoever He wills of His servants! They have earned wrath upon wrath. And such disbelievers will suffer a humiliating punishment
  2,91,"When it is said to them: вАЬBelieve in what Allah has revealed,вАЭ they reply, вАЬWe only believe in what was sent down to us,вАЭ and they deny what came afterwards, though it is the truth confirming their own Scriptures! Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWhy then did you kill AllahвАЩs prophets before, if you are ЋєtrulyЋЇ believers?вАЭ"
  2,92,"Indeed, Moses came to you with clear proofs, then you worshipped the calf in his absence, acting wrongfully"
  2,93,"And when We took your covenant and raised the mountain above you ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬHold firmly to that ЋєScriptureЋЇ which We have given you and obey,вАЭ they answered, вАЬWe hear and disobey.вАЭ The love of the calf was rooted in their hearts because of their disbelief. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHow evil is what your Ћєso-calledЋЇ belief prompts you to do, if you ЋєactuallyЋЇ believe Ћєin the TorahЋЇ!вАЭ"
  2,94,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf the ЋєeternalЋЇ Home of the Hereafter with Allah is exclusively for you ЋєIsraelitesЋЇ out of all humanity, then wish for death if what you say is true!вАЭ"
  2,95,But they will never wish for that because of what their hands have done.¬†And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of the wrongdoers
  2,96,"You will surely find them clinging to life more eagerly than any other people, even more than polytheists. Each one of them wishes to live a thousand years. But even if they were to live that long, it would not save them from the punishment. And Allah is All-Seeing of what they do"
  2,97,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWhoever is an enemy of Gabriel should know that he revealed this ЋєQuranЋЇ to your heart by AllahвАЩs Will, confirming what came before itвАФa guide and good news for the believers.вАЭ"
  2,98,"Whoever is an enemy of Allah, His angels, His messengers, Gabriel, and Michael, then Ћєlet them know thatЋЇ Allah is certainly the enemy of the disbelievers"
  2,99,"Indeed, We have sent down to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ clear revelations. ЋєButЋЇ none will deny them except the rebellious"
  2,100,"Why is it that every time they make a covenant, a group of them casts it aside? In fact, most of them do not believe"
  2,101,"Now, when a messenger from Allah has come to themвАФconfirming their own ScripturesвАФsome of the People of the Book cast the Book of Allah behind their backs as if they did not know"
  2,102,"They ЋєinsteadЋЇ followed the magic promoted by the devils during the reign of Solomon. Never did Solomon disbelieve, rather the devils disbelieved. They taught magic to the people, along with what had been revealed to the two angels, H√Ґr√їt and M√Ґr√їt, in Babylon.¬†The two angels never taught anyone without saying, вАЬWe are only a test Ћєfor youЋЇ, so do not abandon ЋєyourЋЇ faith.вАЭ Yet people learned ЋєmagicЋЇ that caused a rift ЋєevenЋЇ between husband and wife; although their magic could not harm anyone except by AllahвАЩs Will. They learned what harmed them and did not benefit themвАФalthough they already knew that whoever buys into magic would have no share in the Hereafter. Miserable indeed was the price for which they sold their souls, if only they knew"
  2,103,"If only they were faithful and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, there would have been a better reward from Allah, if only they knew"
  2,104,"O believers! Do not say, вАЬR√ҐвАЩina.вАЭ [Herd us!] But say, вАЬUnбЇУurna,вАЭ [Tend to us!] and listen ЋєattentivelyЋЇ.¬†And the disbelievers will suffer a painful punishment"
  2,105,"The disbelievers from the People of the Book and the polytheists would not want you to receive any blessing from your Lord, but Allah selects whoever He wills for His mercy. And Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty"
  2,106,"If We ever abrogate¬†a verse or cause it to be forgotten, We replace it with a better or similar one. Do you not know that Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,107,"Do you not know that the kingdom of the heavens and the earth belongs ЋєonlyЋЇ to Allah, and you have no guardian or helper besides Allah"
  2,108,Or do you ЋєbelieversЋЇ intend to ask of your Messenger as Moses was asked before?¬†But whoever trades belief for disbelief has truly strayed from the Right Way
  2,109,"Many among the People of the Book wish they could turn you ЋєbelieversЋЇ back to disbelief because of their envy, after the truth has been made clear to them. Pardon and bear with them until Allah delivers His decision. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,110,"Establish prayer, and pay alms-tax. Whatever good you send forth for yourselves, you will ЋєcertainlyЋЇ find Ћєits rewardЋЇ with Allah. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,111,"The Jews and Christians each claim that none will enter Paradise except those of their own faith. These are their desires. Reply, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬShow ЋєmeЋЇ your proof if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  2,112,"But no! Whoever submits themselves to Allah and does good will have their reward with their Lord. And there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,113,"The Jews say, вАЬThe Christians have nothing to stand onвАЭ and the Christians say, вАЬThe Jews have nothing to stand on,вАЭ although both recite the Scriptures. And those ЋєpagansЋЇ who have no knowledge say the same Ћєabout people of faithЋЇ. Surely Allah will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their dispute"
  2,114,"Who does more wrong than those who prevent AllahвАЩs Name from being mentioned in His places of worship and strive to destroy them? Such people have no right to enter these places except with fear.¬†For them is disgrace in this world, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment in the Hereafter"
  2,115,"To Allah belong the east and the west, so wherever you turn you are facing ЋєtowardsЋЇ Allah.¬†Surely Allah is All-Encompassing,¬†All-Knowing"
  2,116,"They¬†say, вАЬAllah has offspring.вАЭ¬†Glory be to Him! In fact, to Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earthвАФall are subject to His Will"
  2,117,"ЋєHe isЋЇ the Originator of the heavens and the earth! When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, вАЬBe!вАЭ And it is"
  2,118,"Those who have no knowledge say, вАЬIf only Allah would speak to us or a sign would come to us!вАЭ The same was said by those who came before. Their hearts are all alike. Indeed, We have made the signs clear for people of sure faith"
  2,119,We have surely sent you with the truth ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as a deliverer of good news and a warner. And you will not be accountable for the residents of the Hellfire
  2,120,"Never will the Jews or Christians be pleased with you, until you follow their faith. Say, вАЬAllahвАЩs guidance is the only ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance.вАЭ And if you were to follow their desires after ЋєallЋЇ the knowledge that has come to you, there would be none to protect or help you against Allah"
  2,121,"Those We have given the Book follow it as it should be followed. It is they who ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in it. As for those who reject it, it is they who are the losers"
  2,122,O Children of Israel! Remember My favours upon you and how I honoured you above the others
  2,123,"And guard yourselves against the Day when no soul will be of any help to another. No ransom will be taken, no intercession accepted, and no help will be given"
  2,124,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when Abraham was tested by his Lord with ЋєcertainЋЇ commandments, which he fulfilled. Allah said, вАЬI will certainly make you into a role model for the people.вАЭ Abraham asked, вАЬWhat about my offspring?вАЭ Allah replied, вАЬMy covenant is not extended to the wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  2,125,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We made the Sacred House¬†a centre and a sanctuary for the people ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬЋєYou mayЋЇ take the standing-place of Abraham¬†as a site of prayer.вАЭ And We entrusted Abraham and Ishmael to purify My House for those who circle it, who meditate in it, and who bow and prostrate themselves Ћєin prayerЋЇ"
  2,126,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Abraham said, вАЬMy Lord, make this city Ћєof MeccaЋЇ secure and provide fruits to its peopleвАФthose among them who believe in Allah and the Last Day.вАЭ He answered, вАЬAs for those who disbelieve, I will let them enjoy themselves for a little while, then I will condemn them to the torment of the Fire. What an evil destination!вАЭ"
  2,127,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Abraham raised the foundation of the House with Ishmael, Ћєboth praying,ЋЇ вАЬOur Lord! Accept ЋєthisЋЇ from us. You are indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,128,"Our Lord! Make us both ЋєfullyЋЇ submit to You¬†and from our descendants a nation that will submit to you. Show us our rituals, and turn to us in grace. You are truly the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,129,"Our Lord! Raise from among them a messenger who will recite to them Your revelations, teach them the Book and wisdom, and purify them. Indeed, You ЋєaloneЋЇ are the Almighty, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  2,130,"And who would reject the faith of Abraham except a fool! We certainly chose him in this life, and in the Hereafter he will surely be among the righteous"
  2,131,"When his Lord ordered him, вАЬSubmit Ћєto My WillЋЇ,вАЭ he responded, вАЬI submit to the Lord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  2,132,"This was the advice of AbrahamвАФas well as JacobвАФto his children, ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬIndeed, Allah has chosen for you this faith; so do not die except in Ћєa state of fullЋЇ submission.вАЭ"
  2,133,"Or did you witness when death came to Jacob? He asked his children, вАЬWho will you worship after my passing?вАЭ They replied, вАЬWe will Ћєcontinue toЋЇ worship your God, the God of your forefathersвАФAbraham, Ishmael, and IsaacвАФthe One God. And to Him we ЋєallЋЇ submit.вАЭ"
  2,134,That was a community that had already gone before. For them is what they earned and for you is what you have earned. And you will not be accountable for what they have done
  2,135,"The Jews and Christians each say, вАЬFollow our faith to be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬNo! We follow the faith of Abraham, the uprightвАФwho was not a polytheist.вАЭ"
  2,136,"Say, ЋєO believers,ЋЇ вАЬWe believe in Allah and what has been revealed to us; and what was revealed to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants; and what was given to Moses, Jesus, and other prophets from their Lord. We make no distinction between any of them. And to Allah we all submit.вАЭ"
  2,137,"So if they believe in what you believe, then they will indeed be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided. But if they turn away, they are simply opposed Ћєto the truthЋЇ. But Allah will spare you their evil. For He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,138,This is the ЋєnaturalЋЇ Way of Allah. And who is better than Allah in ordaining a way? And we worship Ћєnone butЋЇ Him
  2,139,"Say, вАЬWould you dispute with us about Allah, while He is our Lord and your Lord? We are accountable for our deeds and you for yours. And we are devoted to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  2,140,"Do you claim that Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants were all Jews or Christians?вАЭ Say, вАЬWho is more knowledgeable: you or Allah?вАЭ Who does more wrong than those who hide the testimony they received from Allah? And Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,141,That was a community that had already gone before. For them is what they earned and for you is what you have earned. And you will not be accountable for what they have done
  2,142,"The foolish among the people will ask, вАЬWhy did they turn away from the direction of prayer they used to face?вАЭ¬†Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬThe east and west belong ЋєonlyЋЇ to Allah. He guides whoever He wills to the Straight Path.вАЭ"
  2,143,And so We have made you ЋєbelieversЋЇ an upright¬†community so that you may be witnesses over humanity and that the Messenger may be a witness over you. We assigned your former direction of prayer only to distinguish those who would remain faithful to the Messenger from those who would lose faith. It was certainly a difficult test except for those ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided by Allah. And Allah would never discount your Ћєprevious acts ofЋЇ faith. Surely Allah is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to humanity
  2,144,"Indeed, We see you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ turning your face towards heaven. Now We will make you turn towards a direction Ћєof prayerЋЇ that will please you. So turn your face towards the Sacred Mosque Ћєin MeccaЋЇвАФwherever you are, turn your faces towards it. Those who were given the Scripture certainly know this to be the truth from their Lord. And Allah is never unaware of what they do"
  2,145,"Even if you were to bring every proof to the People of the Book, they would not accept your direction Ћєof prayerЋЇ, nor would you accept theirs; nor would any of them accept the direction Ћєof prayerЋЇ of another. And if you were to follow their desires after ЋєallЋЇ the knowledge that has come to you, then you would certainly be one of the wrongdoers"
  2,146,Those We have given the Scripture recognize this ЋєProphetЋЇ as they recognize their own children. Yet a group of them hides the truth knowingly
  2,147,"ЋєThis isЋЇ the truth from your Lord, so do not ever be one of those who doubt"
  2,148,"Everyone turns to their own direction Ћєof prayerЋЇ. So compete with one another in doing good. Wherever you are, Allah will bring you all together Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,149,"Wherever you are ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, turn your face towards the Sacred Mosque. This is certainly the truth from your Lord. And Allah is never unaware of what you ЋєallЋЇ do"
  2,150,"Wherever you are ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, turn your face towards the Sacred Mosque. And wherever you ЋєbelieversЋЇ are, face towards it, so that people will have no argument against you, except the wrongdoers among them. Do not fear them; fear Me, so that I may Ћєcontinue toЋЇ perfect My favour upon you and so you may be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  2,151,"Since We have sent you a messenger from among yourselvesвАФreciting to you Our revelations, purifying you, teaching you the Book and wisdom, and teaching you what you never knewвАФ"
  2,152,"remember Me; I will remember you. And thank Me, and never be ungrateful"
  2,153,O believers! Seek comfort in patience and prayer. Allah is truly with those who are patient
  2,154,"Never say that those martyred in the cause of Allah are deadвАФin fact, they are alive! But you do not perceive it"
  2,155,"We will certainly test you with a touch of fear and famine and loss of property, life, and crops. Give good news to those who patiently endureвАФ"
  2,156,"who, when faced with a disaster, say, вАЬSurely to Allah we belong and to Him we will ЋєallЋЇ return.вАЭ"
  2,157,They are the ones who will receive AllahвАЩs blessings and mercy. And it is they who are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  2,158,"Indeed, Ћєthe hills ofЋЇ бєҐafa¬†and Marwah¬†are among the symbols of Allah. So whoever performs the pilgrimage or minor pilgrimage,¬†let them walk between Ћєthe two hillsЋЇ. And whoever does good willingly, Allah is truly Appreciative, All-Knowing"
  2,159,Those who hide the clear proofs and guidance that We have revealedвАФafter We made it clear for humanity in the BookвАФwill be condemned by Allah and ЋєallЋЇ those who condemn
  2,160,"As for those who repent, mend their ways, and let the truth be known, they are the ones to whom I will turn Ћєin forgivenessЋЇ, for I am the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,161,"Surely those who disbelieve and die as disbelievers are condemned by Allah, the angels, and all of humanity"
  2,162,"They will be in Hell forever. Their punishment will not be lightened, nor will they be delayed Ћєfrom itЋЇ"
  2,163,"Your God is ЋєonlyЋЇ One God. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except HimвАФthe Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  2,164,"Indeed, in the creation of the heavens and the earth; the alternation of the day and the night; the ships that sail the sea for the benefit of humanity; the rain sent down by Allah from the skies, reviving the earth after its death; the scattering of all kinds of creatures throughout; the shifting of the winds; and the clouds drifting between the heavens and the earthвАФЋєin all of thisЋЇ are surely signs for people of understanding"
  2,165,"Still there are some who take others as AllahвАЩs equalвАФthey love them as they should love AllahвАФbut the ЋєtrueЋЇ believers love Allah even more. If only the wrongdoers could see the ЋєhorribleЋЇ punishment Ћєawaiting themЋЇ, they would certainly realize that all power belongs to Allah and that Allah is indeed severe in punishment"
  2,166,ЋєConsider the DayЋЇ when those who misled others will disown their followersвАФwhen they face the tormentвАФand the bonds that united them will be cut off
  2,167,"The ЋєmisledЋЇ followers will cry, вАЬIf only we could have a second chance, we would disown them as they disowned us.вАЭ And so Allah will make them remorseful of their misdeeds. And they will never Ћєbe able toЋЇ leave the Fire"
  2,168,O humanity! Eat from what is lawful and good on the earth and do not follow SatanвАЩs footsteps. He is truly your sworn enemy
  2,169,"He only incites you to commit evil and indecency, and to claim against Allah what you do not know"
  2,170,"When it is said to them, вАЬFollow what Allah has revealed,вАЭ they reply, вАЬNo! We ЋєonlyЋЇ follow what we found our forefathers practicing.вАЭ ЋєWould they still do so,ЋЇ even if their forefathers had ЋєabsolutelyЋЇ no understanding or guidance"
  2,171,"The example of the disbelievers Ћєnot responding to the MessengerвАЩs warningЋЇ is like a flock not comprehending the calls and cries of the shepherd. ЋєThey are wilfullyЋЇ deaf, dumb and blind so they have no understanding"
  2,172,O believers! Eat from the good things We have provided for you. And give thanks to Allah if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ
  2,173,"He has only forbidden you Ћєto eatЋЇ carrion, blood, swine,¬†and what is slaughtered in the name of any other than Allah. But if someone is compelled by necessityвАФneither driven by desire nor exceeding immediate needвАФthey will not be sinful. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,174,"Indeed, those who hide AllahвАЩs revelations, trading them for a fleeting gain consume nothing but fire into their bellies. Allah will neither speak to them on the Day of Judgment, nor will He purify them. And they will suffer a painful punishment"
  2,175,They are the ones who trade guidance for misguidance and forgiveness for punishment. How persistent are they in pursuit of the Fire
  2,176,That is because Allah has revealed the Book in truth. And surely those who differ regarding it are totally engrossed in opposition
  2,177,"Righteousness is not in turning your faces towards the east or the west. Rather, the righteous are those who believe in Allah, the Last Day, the angels, the Books, and the prophets; who give charity out of their cherished wealth to relatives, orphans, the poor, ЋєneedyЋЇ travellers, beggars, and for freeing captives; who establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and keep the pledges they make; and who are patient in times of suffering, adversity, and in Ћєthe heat ofЋЇ battle. It is they who are true Ћєin faithЋЇ, and it is they who are mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ"
  2,178,"O believers! ЋєThe law ofЋЇ retaliation is set for you in cases of murderвАФa free man for a free man, a slave for a slave, and a female for a female.¬†But if the offender is pardoned by the victimвАЩs guardian,¬†then blood-money should be decided fairly¬†and payment should be made courteously. This is a concession and a mercy from your Lord. But whoever transgresses after that will suffer a painful punishment"
  2,179,"There is Ћєsecurity ofЋЇ life for you in Ћєthe law ofЋЇ retaliation, O people of reason, so that you may become mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ"
  2,180,It is prescribed that when death approaches any of youвАФif they leave something of valueвАФa will should be made in favour of parents and immediate family with fairness.¬†ЋєThis isЋЇ an obligation on those who are mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ
  2,181,"But whoever changes the will after hearing it,¬†the blame will only be on those who made the change. Indeed, Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,182,"Whoever suspects an error or an injustice in the will and brings about a ЋєfairЋЇ settlement among the parties will not be sinful. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,183,O believers! Fasting is prescribed for youвАФas it was for those before youвАФso perhaps you will become mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ
  2,184,"ЋєFast aЋЇ prescribed number of days.¬†But whoever of you is ill or on a journey, then Ћєlet them fastЋЇ an equal number of days Ћєafter RamaбЄН√ҐnЋЇ. For those who can only fast with extreme difficulty,¬†compensation can be made by feeding a needy person Ћєfor every day not fastedЋЇ. But whoever volunteers to give more, it is better for them. And to fast is better for you, if only you knew"
  2,185,"RamaбЄН√Ґn is the month in which the Quran was revealed as a guide for humanity with clear proofs of guidance and the standard Ћєto distinguish between right and wrongЋЇ. So whoever is present this month, let them fast. But whoever is ill or on a journey, then Ћєlet them fastЋЇ an equal number of days Ћєafter RamaбЄН√ҐnЋЇ. Allah intends ease for you, not hardship, so that you may complete the prescribed period and proclaim the greatness of Allah for guiding you, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  2,186,"When My servants ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about Me: I am truly near. I respond to oneвАЩs prayer when they call upon Me. So let them respond Ћєwith obedienceЋЇ to Me and believe in Me, perhaps they will be guided Ћєto the Right WayЋЇ"
  2,187,"It has been made permissible for you to be intimate with your wives during the nights preceding the fast. Your spouses are a garment¬†for you as you are for them. Allah knows that you were deceiving yourselves.¬†So He has accepted your repentance and pardoned you. So now you may be intimate with them and seek what Allah has prescribed for you.¬†ЋєYou mayЋЇ eat and drink until you see the light of dawn breaking the darkness of night, then complete the fast until nightfall. Do not be intimate with your spouses while you are meditating in the mosques. These are the limits set by Allah, so do not exceed them. This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to people, so they may become mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ"
  2,188,"Do not consume one anotherвАЩs wealth unjustly, nor deliberately bribe authorities in order to devour a portion of othersвАЩ property, knowing that it is a sin"
  2,189,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about the phases of the moon. Say, вАЬThey are a means for people to determine time and pilgrimage.вАЭ Righteousness is not in entering your houses from the back doors.¬†Rather, righteousness is to be mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ. So enter your homes through their ЋєproperЋЇ doors, and be mindful of Allah so you may be successful"
  2,190,"Fight in the cause of Allah ЋєonlyЋЇ against those who wage war against you, but do not exceed the limits.¬†Allah does not like transgressors"
  2,191,"Kill them wherever you come upon them¬†and drive them out of the places from which they have driven you out. For persecution¬†is far worse than killing. And do not fight them at the Sacred Mosque unless they attack you there. If they do so, then fight themвАФthat is the reward of the disbelievers"
  2,192,"But if they cease, then surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,193,"Fight against them Ћєif they persecute youЋЇ until there is no more persecution, and ЋєyourЋЇ devotion will be to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ. If they stop Ћєpersecuting youЋЇ, let there be no hostility except against the aggressors"
  2,194,"ЋєThere will be retaliation inЋЇ a sacred month for Ћєan offence inЋЇ a sacred month,¬†and all violations will bring about retaliation. So, if anyone attacks you, retaliate in the same manner. ЋєButЋЇ be mindful of Allah, and know that Allah is with those mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ"
  2,195,"Spend in the cause of Allah and do not let your own hands throw you into destruction Ћєby withholdingЋЇ. And do good, for Allah certainly loves the good-doers"
  2,196,"Complete the pilgrimage and minor pilgrimage for Allah.¬†But if prevented Ћєfrom proceedingЋЇ, then ЋєofferЋЇ whatever sacrificial animals you can afford. And do not shave your heads until the sacrificial animal reaches its destination. But if any of you is ill or has a scalp ailment Ћєrequiring shavingЋЇ, then compensate either by fasting, charity, or a sacrificial offering. In times of peace, you may combine the pilgrimage and minor pilgrimage then make the sacrificial offering you can afford. Whoever cannot afford that ЋєofferingЋЇ, let them fast three days during pilgrimage and seven after returning ЋєhomeЋЇвАФcompleting ten. These offerings are for those who do not live near the Sacred House. And be mindful of Allah, and know that Allah is severe in punishment"
  2,197,"ЋєCommitment toЋЇ pilgrimage is made in appointed months.¬†Whoever commits to ЋєperformingЋЇ pilgrimage, let them stay away from intimate relations, foul language, and arguments during pilgrimage. Whatever good you do, Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows of it. Take ЋєnecessaryЋЇ provisions Ћєfor the journeyЋЇвАФsurely the best provision is righteousness. And be mindful of Me, O people of reason"
  2,198,"There is no blame on you for seeking the bounty of your Lord Ћєduring this journeyЋЇ.¬†When you return from вАЩAraf√Ґt,¬†praise Allah near the sacred place¬†and praise Him for having guided you, for surely before this ЋєguidanceЋЇ you were astray"
  2,199,"Then go forth with the rest of the pilgrims. And seek AllahвАЩs forgiveness. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,200,"When you have fulfilled your sacred rites, praise Allah as you used to praise your forefathers Ћєbefore IslamЋЇ, or even more passionately. There are some who say, вАЬOur Lord! Grant us ЋєYour bountiesЋЇ in this world,вАЭ but they will have no share in the Hereafter"
  2,201,"Yet there are others who say, вАЬOur Lord! Grant us the good of this world and the Hereafter, and protect us from the torment of the Fire.вАЭ"
  2,202,It is they who will receive a ЋєheavenlyЋЇ reward for the good they have done. Surely Allah is swift in reckoning
  2,203,"And remember Allah during ЋєtheseЋЇ appointed days.¬†Whoever departs swiftly on the second day is not sinful, neither are those who stay behind Ћєtill the thirdвАФseeking additional rewardЋЇ, so long as they are mindful Ћєof their LordЋЇ. And be mindful of Allah, and know that to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be gathered"
  2,204,"There are some ЋєhypocritesЋЇ who impress you with their views regarding worldly affairs and openly call upon Allah to witness what is in their hearts, yet they are your worst adversaries"
  2,205,"And when they leave ЋєyouЋЇ,¬†they strive throughout the land to spread mischief in it and destroy crops and cattle. Allah does not like mischief"
  2,206,"When it is said to them, вАЬFear Allah,вАЭ pride carries them off to sin. Hell will be their proper place. What an evil place to rest"
  2,207,And there are those who would dedicate their lives to AllahвАЩs pleasure. And Allah is Ever Gracious to ЋєHisЋЇ servants
  2,208,O believers! Enter into Islam wholeheartedly and do not follow SatanвАЩs footsteps. Surely he is your sworn enemy
  2,209,"If you falter after receiving the clear proofs, then know that Allah is indeed Almighty, All-Wise"
  2,210,"Are they waiting for Allah ЋєHimselfЋЇ to come to them in the shade of clouds, along with the angels? ЋєIf He didЋЇ, then the matter would be settled Ћєat onceЋЇ. And to Allah ЋєallЋЇ matters will be returned Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ"
  2,211,Ask the Children of Israel how many clear signs We have given them. And whoever trades AllahвАЩs favourвАФafter receiving itвАФЋєfor disbeliefЋЇ should know that Allah is indeed severe in punishment
  2,212,"The life of this world has been made appealing to the disbelievers, and they mock the believers. Those who are mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ will rank above them on the Day of Judgment. And Allah provides for whoever He wills without limit"
  2,213,"Humanity had once been one community Ћєof believers before they lost faithЋЇ. Then Allah raised prophets as deliverers of good news and as warners, and revealed to them the Scriptures in truth to judge among people regarding their disputes. And no one disputed the Scriptures except the very people who received them after clear proofs had come to themвАФout of jealousy. Then Allah, by His grace, has guided the believers to the truth regarding those disputes. And Allah guides whoever He wills to the Straight Path"
  2,214,"Do you think you will be admitted into Paradise without being tested like those before you? They were afflicted with suffering and adversity and were so ЋєviolentlyЋЇ shaken that ЋєevenЋЇ the Messenger and the believers with him cried out, вАЬWhen will AllahвАЩs help come?вАЭ Indeed, AllahвАЩs help is ЋєalwaysЋЇ near"
  2,215,"They ask you ЋєO Prophet inЋЇ what ЋєwayЋЇ they should donate. Say, вАЬWhatever donations you give are for parents, relatives, orphans, the poor, and ЋєneedyЋЇ travellers. Whatever good you do is certainly well known to Allah.вАЭ"
  2,216,"Fighting has been made obligatory upon you ЋєbelieversЋЇ, though you dislike it. Perhaps you dislike something which is good for you and like something which is bad for you. Allah knows and you do not know"
  2,217,"They¬†ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about fighting in the sacred months.¬†Say, вАЬFighting during these months is a great sin. But hindering ЋєothersЋЇ from the Path of Allah, rejecting Him, and expelling the worshippers from the Sacred Mosque is ЋєaЋЇ greater ЋєsinЋЇ in the sight of Allah. For persecution¬†is far worse than killing. And they will not stop fighting you until they turn you away from your faithвАФif they can. And whoever among you renounces their own faith and dies a disbeliever, their deeds will become void in this life and in the Hereafter. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever.вАЭ"
  2,218,"Surely those who have believed, emigrated, and struggled in the Way of AllahвАФthey can hope for AllahвАЩs mercy. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,219,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about intoxicants and gambling. Say, вАЬThere is great evil in both, as well as some benefit for peopleвАФbut the evil outweighs the benefit.вАЭ¬†They ЋєalsoЋЇ ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ what they should donate. Say, вАЬWhatever you can spare.вАЭ This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you ЋєbelieversЋЇ, so perhaps you may reflect"
  2,220,"upon this world and the Hereafter. And they ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ concerning orphans. Say, вАЬImproving their condition is best. And if you partner with them, they are bonded with you Ћєin faithЋЇ.¬†And Allah knows who intends harm and who intends good. Had Allah willed, He could have made it difficult for you.¬†Surely Allah is Almighty, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  2,221,"Do not marry polytheistic women until they believe; for a believing slave-woman is better than a free polytheist, even though she may look pleasant to you. And do not marry your women to polytheistic men until they believe, for a believing slave-man is better than a free polytheist, even though he may look pleasant to you. They invite ЋєyouЋЇ to the Fire while Allah invites ЋєyouЋЇ to Paradise and forgiveness by His grace.¬†He makes His revelations clear to the people so perhaps they will be mindful"
  2,222,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about menstruation. Say, вАЬBeware of its harm! So keep away, and do not have intercourse with your wives during their monthly cycles until they are purified.¬†When they purify themselves, then you may approach them in the manner specified by Allah. Surely Allah loves those who always turn to Him in repentance and those who purify themselves.вАЭ"
  2,223,"Your wives are like farmland for you,¬†so approach them ЋєconsensuallyЋЇ as you please.¬†And send forth something good for yourselves.¬†Be mindful of Allah, and know that you will meet Him. And give good news to the believers"
  2,224,"Do not use AllahвАЩs Name in your oaths as an excuse for not doing good, not guarding against evil, or not making peace between people. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,225,"Allah will not hold you accountable for unintentional oaths, but for what you intended in your hearts. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  2,226,"Those who swear not to have intercourse with their wives must wait for four months.¬†If they change their mind, then Allah is certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  2,227,"But if they settle on divorce, then Allah is indeed All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,228,"Divorced women must wait three monthly cycles Ћєbefore they can re-marryЋЇ. It is not lawful for them to conceal what Allah has created in their wombs,¬†if they ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in Allah and the Last Day. And their husbands reserve the right to take them back within that period if they desire reconciliation. Women have rights similar to those of men equitably, although men have a degree Ћєof responsibilityЋЇ above them. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  2,229,"Divorce may be retracted twice, then the husband must retain Ћєhis wifeЋЇ with honour or separate Ћєfrom herЋЇ with grace.¬†It is not lawful for husbands to take back anything of the dowry given to their wives, unless the couple fears not being able to keep within the limits of Allah.¬†So if you fear they will not be able to keep within the limits of Allah, there is no blame if the wife compensates the husband to obtain divorce.¬†These are the limits set by Allah, so do not transgress them. And whoever transgresses the limits of Allah, they are the ЋєtrueЋЇ wrongdoers"
  2,230,"So if a husband divorces his wife Ћєthree timesЋЇ, then it is not lawful for him to remarry her until after she has married another man and then is divorced. Then it is permissible for them to reunite, as long as they feel they are able to maintain the limits of Allah. These are the limits set by Allah, which He makes clear for people of knowledge"
  2,231,"When you divorce women and they have ЋєalmostЋЇ reached the end of their waiting period, either retain them honourably or let them go honourably. But do not retain them ЋєonlyЋЇ to harm them ЋєorЋЇ to take advantage Ћєof themЋЇ. Whoever does that surely wrongs his own soul. Do not take AllahвАЩs revelations lightly. Remember AllahвАЩs favours upon you as well as the Book and wisdom¬†He has sent down for your guidance. Be mindful of Allah, and know that Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  2,232,"When you have divorced women and they have reached the end of their waiting period, do not prevent them from re-marrying their ex-husbands if they come to an honourable agreement. This is enjoined on whoever has faith in Allah and the Last Day. This is purer and more dignifying for you. Allah knows and you do not know"
  2,233,"ЋєDivorcedЋЇ mothers will breastfeed their offspring for two whole years, for those who wish to complete the nursing Ћєof their childЋЇ. The childвАЩs father will provide reasonable maintenance and clothing for the mother Ћєduring that periodЋЇ. No one will be charged with more than they can bear. No mother or father should be made to suffer for their child. The ЋєfatherвАЩsЋЇ heirs are under the same obligation. But if both sides decideвАФafter mutual consultation and consentвАФto wean a child, then there is no blame on them. If you decide to have your children nursed by a wet-nurse, it is permissible as long as you pay fairly. Be mindful of Allah, and know that Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,234,"As for those of you who die and leave widows behind, let them observe a waiting period of four months and ten days. When they have reached the end of this period, then you¬†are not accountable for what they decide for themselves in a reasonable manner. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  2,235,"There is no blame on you for subtly showing interest in Ћєdivorced or widowedЋЇ women¬†or for hiding Ћєthe intentionЋЇ in your hearts. Allah knows that you are considering them Ћєfor marriageЋЇ. But do not make a secret commitment with themвАФyou can only show interest in them appropriately. Do not commit to the bond of marriage until the waiting period expires. Know that Allah is aware of what is in your hearts, so beware of Him. And know that Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  2,236,There is no blame if you divorce women before the marriage is consummated or the dowry is settled. But give them a ЋєsuitableЋЇ compensationвАФthe rich according to his means and the poor according to his. A reasonable compensation is an obligation on the good-doers
  2,237,"And if you divorce them before consummating the marriage but after deciding on a dowry, pay half of the dowry, unless the wife graciously waives it or the husband graciously pays in full. Graciousness is closer to righteousness. And do not forget kindness among yourselves. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,238,Observe the Ћєfive obligatoryЋЇ prayersвАФespecially the middle prayerвАФand stand in true devotion to Allah
  2,239,"If you are in danger, pray on foot or while riding. But when you are safe, Ћєtake time toЋЇ remember Allah for teaching you what you did not know"
  2,240,"Those of you who die leaving widows should bequeath for them a yearвАЩs maintenance without forcing them out.¬†But if they choose to leave, you are not accountable for what they reasonably decide for themselves. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  2,241,Reasonable provisions must be made for divorced womenвАФa duty on those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ
  2,242,"This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, so perhaps you will understand"
  2,243,"Have you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not seen those who fled their homes in the thousands for fear of death?¬†Allah said to them, вАЬDie!вАЭ then He gave them life. Surely Allah is ever Bountiful to humanity, but most people are ungrateful"
  2,244,"Fight in the cause of Allah, and know that Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,245,Who will lend to Allah a good loan which Allah will multiply many times over? It is Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ who decreases and increases ЋєwealthЋЇ. And to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned
  2,246,"Have you not seen those chiefs of the Children of Israel after Moses? They said to one of their prophets, вАЬAppoint for us a king, ЋєandЋЇ we will fight in the cause of Allah.вАЭ He said, вАЬAre you not going to cower if ordered to fight?вАЭ They replied, вАЬHow could we refuse to fight in the cause of Allah, while we were driven out of our homes and Ћєseparated fromЋЇ our children?вАЭ But when they were ordered to fight, they fled, except for a few of them. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of the wrongdoers"
  2,247,"Their prophet told them, вАЬAllah has appointed Saul¬†to be your king.вАЭ They protested, вАЬHow can he be our king when some of us are more deserving of kingship than he, and he has not been blessed with vast riches?вАЭ He replied, вАЬAllah has chosen him over you and blessed him with knowledge and stature. Allah grants kingship to whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing.вАЭ"
  2,248,"Their prophet further told them, вАЬThe sign of SaulвАЩs kingship is that the Ark will come to youвАФcontaining reassurance¬†from your Lord and relics of the family of Moses and the family of Aaron,¬†which will be carried by the angels. Surely in this is a sign for you, if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe.вАЭ"
  2,249,"When Saul marched forth with his army, he cautioned: вАЬAllah will test you with a river. So whoever drinks Ћєhis fillЋЇ from it is not with me, and whoever does not taste itвАФexcept a sip from the hollow of his handsвАФis definitely with me.вАЭ They all drank Ћєtheir fillЋЇ except for a few! When he and the ЋєremainingЋЇ faithful with him crossed the river, they said, вАЬNow we are no match for Goliath and his warriors.вАЭ But those ЋєbelieversЋЇ who were certain they would meet Allah reasoned, вАЬHow many times has a small force vanquished a mighty army by the Will of Allah! And Allah is ЋєalwaysЋЇ with the steadfast.вАЭ"
  2,250,"When they advanced to face Goliath and his warriors, they prayed, вАЬOur Lord! Shower us with perseverance, make our steps firm, and give us victory over the disbelieving people.вАЭ"
  2,251,"So they defeated them by AllahвАЩs Will, and David killed Goliath. And Allah blessed David with kingship and wisdom and taught him what He willed. Had Allah not repelled a group of people by Ћєthe might ofЋЇ another, corruption would have dominated the earth, but Allah is Gracious to all"
  2,252,These are AllahвАЩs revelations which We recite to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in truth. And you are truly one of the messengers
  2,253,"We have chosen some of those messengers above others.¬†Allah spoke directly to some, and raised some high in rank. To Jesus, son of Mary, We gave clear proofs and supported him with the holy spirit.¬†If Allah had willed, succeeding generations would not have fought Ћєamong themselvesЋЇ after receiving the clear proofs. But they differedвАФsome believed while others disbelieved. Yet if Allah had willed, they would not have fought one another. But Allah does what He wills"
  2,254,"O believers! Donate from what We have provided for you before the arrival of a Day when there will be no bargaining,¬†friendship,¬†or intercession. Those who disbelieve are ЋєtrulyЋЇ the wrongdoers"
  2,255,"Allah! There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him, the Ever-Living, All-Sustaining. Neither drowsiness nor sleep overtakes Him. To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Who could possibly intercede with Him without His permission? He ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what is ahead of them and what is behind them, but no one can grasp any of His knowledgeвАФexcept what He wills Ћєto revealЋЇ. His Seat¬†encompasses the heavens and the earth, and the preservation of both does not tire Him. For He is the Most High, the Greatest"
  2,256,"Let there be no compulsion in religion, for the truth stands out clearly from falsehood.¬†So whoever renounces false gods and believes in Allah has certainly grasped the firmest, unfailing hand-hold. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,257,"Allah is the Guardian of the believersвАФHe brings them out of darkness and into light. As for the disbelievers, their guardians are false gods who lead them out of light and into darkness. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  2,258,"Are you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not aware of the one who argued with Abraham about his Lord because Allah had granted him kingship? ЋєRememberЋЇ when Abraham said, вАЬMy Lord is the One Who has power to give life and cause death.вАЭ He argued, вАЬI too have the power to give life and cause death.вАЭ Abraham challenged ЋєhimЋЇ, вАЬAllah causes the sun to rise from the east. So make it rise from the west.вАЭ And so the disbeliever was dumbstruck. And Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  2,259,"Or Ћєare you not aware ofЋЇ the one who passed by a city which was in ruins. He wondered, вАЬHow could Allah bring this back to life after its destruction?вАЭ So Allah caused him to die for a hundred years then brought him back to life. Allah asked, вАЬHow long have you remained Ћєin this stateЋЇ?вАЭ He replied, вАЬPerhaps a day or part of a day.вАЭ Allah said, вАЬNo! You have remained here for a hundred years! Just look at your food and drinkвАФthey have not spoiled. ЋєBut nowЋЇ look at Ћєthe remains ofЋЇ your donkey! And ЋєsoЋЇ We have made you into a sign for humanity. And look at the bones Ћєof the donkeyЋЇ, how We bring them together then clothe them with flesh!вАЭ¬†When this was made clear to him, he declared, вАЬЋєNowЋЇ I know that Allah is Most Capable of everything.вАЭ"
  2,260,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Abraham said, вАЬMy Lord! Show me how you give life to the dead.вАЭ Allah responded, вАЬDo you not believe?вАЭ Abraham replied, вАЬYes I do, but just so my heart can be reassured.вАЭ Allah said, вАЬThen bring four birds, train them to come to you, Ћєthen cut them into pieces,ЋЇ and scatter them on different hilltops. Then call them back, they will fly to you in haste. And Ћєso you willЋЇ know that Allah is Almighty, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  2,261,"The example of those who spend their wealth in the cause of Allah is that of a grain that sprouts into seven ears, each bearing one hundred grains. And Allah multiplies Ћєthe reward even moreЋЇ to whoever He wills. For Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing"
  2,262,"Those who spend their wealth in the cause of Allah and do not follow their charity with reminders of their generosity or hurtful wordsвАФthey will get their reward from their Lord, and there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,263,"Kind words and forgiveness are better than charity followed by injury. And Allah is Self-Sufficient, Most Forbearing"
  2,264,"O believers! Do not waste your charity with reminders Ћєof your generosityЋЇ or hurtful words, like those who donate their wealth just to show off and do not believe in Allah or the Last Day. Their example is that of a hard barren rock covered with a thin layer of soil hit by a strong rainвАФleaving it just a bare stone. Such people are unable to preserve the reward of their charity. Allah does not guide ЋєsuchЋЇ disbelieving people"
  2,265,"And the example of those who donate their wealth, seeking AllahвАЩs pleasure and believing the reward is certain,¬†is that of a garden on a fertile hill: when heavy rain falls, it yields up twice its normal produce. If no heavy rain falls, a drizzle is sufficient. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,266,"Would any of you wish to have a garden with palm trees, grapevines, and all kinds of fruits with rivers flowing underneath and as they grow very old with dependent children, a fiery whirlwind hits the garden, burning it all up? This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, so perhaps you will reflect"
  2,267,"O believers! Donate from the best of what you have earned and of what We have produced for you from the earth. Do not pick out worthless things for donation, which you yourselves would only accept with closed eyes. And know that Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  2,268,"The Devil threatens you with Ћєthe prospect ofЋЇ poverty and bids you to the shameful deed Ћєof stinginessЋЇ, while Allah promises you forgiveness and ЋєgreatЋЇ bounties from Him. And Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing"
  2,269,Allah grants wisdom to whoever He wills. And whoever is granted wisdom is certainly blessed with a great privilege. But none will be mindful Ћєof thisЋЇ except people of reason
  2,270,Whatever charities you give or vows you make are surely known to Allah. And the wrongdoers will have no helpers
  2,271,"To give charity publicly is good, but to give to the poor privately is better for you, and will absolve you of your sins. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  2,272,"You are not responsible for peopleвАЩs guidance ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФit is Allah Who guides whoever He wills. Whatever you ЋєbelieversЋЇ spend in charity, it is for your own goodвАФas long as you do so seeking the pleasure of Allah.¬†Whatever you donate will be paid back to you in full, and you will not be wronged"
  2,273,ЋєCharity isЋЇ for the needy who are too engaged in the cause of Allah to move about in the land Ћєfor workЋЇ. Those unfamiliar with their situation will think they are not in need Ћєof charityЋЇ because they do not beg. You can recognize them by their appearance. They do not beg people persistently. Whatever you give in charity is certainly well known to Allah
  2,274,"Those who spend their wealth in charity day and night, secretly and openlyвАФtheir reward is with their Lord, and there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,275,"Those who consume interest will stand Ћєon Judgment DayЋЇ like those driven to madness by SatanвАЩs touch. That is because they say, вАЬTrade is no different than interest.вАЭ But Allah has permitted trading and forbidden interest. Whoever refrainsвАФafter having received warning from their LordвАФmay keep their previous gains, and their case is left to Allah. As for those who persist, it is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  2,276,Allah has made interest fruitless and charity fruitful. And Allah does not like any ungrateful evildoer
  2,277,"Indeed, those who believe, do good, establish prayer, and pay alms-tax will receive their reward from their Lord, and there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,278,"O believers! Fear Allah, and give up outstanding interest if you are ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  2,279,"If you do not, then beware of a war with Allah and His Messenger! But if you repent, you may retain your principalвАФneither inflicting nor suffering harm"
  2,280,"If it is difficult for someone to repay a debt, postpone it until a time of ease. And if you waive it as an act of charity, it will be better for you, if only you knew"
  2,281,"Be mindful of the Day when you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned to Allah, then every soul will be paid in full for what it has done, and none will be wronged"
  2,282,"O believers! When you contract a loan for a fixed period of time, commit it to writing. Let the scribe maintain justice between the parties. The scribe should not refuse to write as Allah has taught them to write. They will write what the debtor dictates, bearing Allah in mind and not defrauding the debt. If the debtor is incompetent, weak, or unable to dictate, let their guardian dictate for them with justice. Call upon two of your men to witness. If two men cannot be found, then one man and two women of your choice will witnessвАФso if one of the women forgets the other may remind her.¬†The witnesses must not refuse when they are summoned. You must not be against writing ЋєcontractsЋЇ for a fixed periodвАФwhether the sum is small or great. This is more just Ћєfor youЋЇ in the sight of Allah, and more convenient to establish evidence and remove doubts. However, if you conduct an immediate transaction among yourselves, then there is no need for you to record it, but call upon witnesses when a deal is finalized. Let no harm come to the scribe or witnesses. If you do, then you have gravely exceeded Ћєyour limitsЋЇ. Be mindful of Allah, for Allah Ћєis the One WhoЋЇ teaches you. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  2,283,"If you are on a journey and a scribe cannot be found, then a security can be taken. If you trust one another, then Ћєthere is no need for a security, butЋЇ the debtor should honour this trust Ћєby repaying the debtЋЇвАФand let them fear Allah, their Lord. And do not conceal the testimony, for whoever conceals it, their hearts are indeed sinful. And Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what you do"
  2,284,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Whether you reveal what is in your hearts or conceal it, Allah will call you to account for it. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,285,"The Messenger ЋєfirmlyЋЇ believes in what has been revealed to him from his Lord, and so do the believers. They ЋєallЋЇ believe in Allah, His angels, His Books, and His messengers. ЋєThey proclaim,ЋЇ вАЬWe make no distinction between any of His messengers.вАЭ And they say, вАЬWe hear and obey. ЋєWe seekЋЇ Your forgiveness, our Lord! And to You ЋєaloneЋЇ is the final return.вАЭ"
  2,286,"Allah does not require of any soul more than what it can afford. All good will be for its own benefit, and all evil will be to its own loss. ЋєThe believers pray,ЋЇ вАЬOur Lord! Do not punish us if we forget or make a mistake. Our Lord! Do not place a burden on us like the one you placed on those before us. Our Lord! Do not burden us with what we cannot bear. Pardon us, forgive us, and have mercy on us. You are our ЋєonlyЋЇ Guardian. So grant us victory over the disbelieving people.вАЭ"
  3,1,Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m
  3,2,"Allah! There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except HimвАФthe Ever-Living, All-Sustaining"
  3,3,"He has revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the Book in truth, confirming what came before it, as He revealed the Torah and the Gospel"
  3,4,"previously, as a guide for people, and ЋєalsoЋЇ revealed the Standard Ћєto distinguish between right and wrongЋЇ.¬†Surely those who reject AllahвАЩs revelations will suffer a severe torment. For Allah is Almighty, capable of punishment"
  3,5,Surely nothing on earth or in the heavens is hidden from Allah
  3,6,"He is the One Who shapes you in the wombs of your mothers as He wills. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except HimвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,7,"He is the One Who has revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the Book, of which some verses are preciseвАФthey are the foundation of the BookвАФwhile others are elusive.¬†Those with deviant hearts follow the elusive verses seeking Ћєto spreadЋЇ doubt through their ЋєfalseЋЇ interpretationsвАФbut none grasps their ЋєfullЋЇ meaning except Allah. As for those well-grounded in knowledge, they say, вАЬWe believe in this ЋєQuranЋЇвАФit is all from our Lord.вАЭ But none will be mindful Ћєof thisЋЇ except people of reason"
  3,8,"ЋєThey say,ЋЇ вАЬOur Lord! Do not let our hearts deviate after you have guided us. Grant us Your mercy. You are indeed the Giver Ћєof all bountiesЋЇ"
  3,9,Our Lord! You will certainly gather all humanity for the ЋєpromisedЋЇ DayвАФabout which there is no doubt. Surely Allah does not break His promise.вАЭ
  3,10,"Indeed, neither the wealth nor children¬†of the disbelievers will be of any benefit to them against AllahвАФand they will be the fuel for the Fire"
  3,11,"Their fate will be like that of the people of Pharaoh and those before themвАФthey all rejected Our signs, so Allah seized them for their sins. And Allah is severe in punishment"
  3,12,"ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Tell the disbelievers, вАЬSoon you will be overpowered and driven to HellвАФwhat an evil place to rest!вАЭ"
  3,13,"Indeed, there was a sign for you in the two armies that met in battleвАФone fighting for the cause of Allah and the other in denial. The believers saw their enemy twice their number.¬†But Allah supports with His victory whoever He wills. Surely in this is a lesson for people of insight"
  3,14,"The enjoyment of ЋєworldlyЋЇ desiresвАФwomen, children,¬†treasures of gold and silver, fine horses, cattle, and fertile landвАФhas been made appealing to people. These are the pleasures of this worldly life, but with Allah is the finest destination"
  3,15,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬShall I inform you of what is better than Ћєall ofЋЇ this? Those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ will have Gardens with their Lord under which rivers flow, to stay there forever, and pure spouses,¬†along with AllahвАЩs pleasure.вАЭ And Allah is All-Seeing of ЋєHisЋЇ servants"
  3,16,"who pray, вАЬOur Lord! We have believed, so forgive our sins and protect us from the torment of the Fire.вАЭ"
  3,17,"ЋєIt is theyЋЇ who are patient, sincere, obedient, and charitable, and who pray for forgiveness before dawn"
  3,18,"Allah ЋєHimselfЋЇ is a Witness that there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except HimвАФand so are the angels and people of knowledge. He is the Maintainer of justice. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except HimвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,19,"Certainly, AllahвАЩs only Way is Islam.¬†Those who were given the Scripture did not dispute Ћєamong themselvesЋЇ out of mutual envy until knowledge came to them.¬†Whoever denies AllahвАЩs signs, then surely Allah is swift in reckoning"
  3,20,"So if they argue with you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, say, вАЬI have submitted myself to Allah, and so have my followers.вАЭ And ask those who were given the Scripture and the illiterate ЋєpeopleЋЇ,¬†вАЬHave you submitted yourselves Ћєto AllahЋЇ?вАЭ If they submit, they will be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided. But if they turn away, then your duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ. And Allah is All-Seeing of ЋєHisЋЇ servants"
  3,21,"Indeed, those who deny AllahвАЩs signs, kill the prophets unjustly, and kill people who stand up for justiceвАФgive them good news of a painful punishment"
  3,22,They are the ones whose deeds are wasted in this world and the Hereafter. And they will have no helpers
  3,23,"Have you not seen those who were given a portion of the Scriptures?¬†Yet when they are invited to the Book of Allah to settle their disputes, some of them turn away heedlessly"
  3,24,"This is because they say, вАЬThe Fire will not touch us except for a few days.вАЭ They have been deceived in their faith by their wishful lying"
  3,25,"But how ЋєhorribleЋЇ will it be when We gather them together on the Day about which there is no doubtвАФwhen every soul will be paid in full for what it has done, and none will be wronged"
  3,26,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO Allah! Lord over all authorities! You give authority to whoever You please and remove it from who You please; You honour whoever You please and disgrace who You pleaseвАФall good is in Your Hands. Surely You ЋєaloneЋЇ are Most Capable of everything"
  3,27,You cause the night to pass into the day and the day into the night. You bring forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living. And You provide for whoever You will without limit.вАЭ
  3,28,Believers should not take disbelievers as guardians instead of the believersвАФand whoever does so will have nothing to hope for from AllahвАФunless it is a precaution against their tyranny. And Allah warns you about Himself. And to Allah is the final return
  3,29,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWhether you conceal what is in your hearts or reveal it, it is known to Allah. For He knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And Allah is Most Capable of everything.вАЭ"
  3,30,ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day when every soul will be presented with whatever good it has done. And it will wish that its misdeeds were far off. And Allah warns you about Himself. And Allah is Ever Gracious to ЋєHisЋЇ servants
  3,31,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf you ЋєsincerelyЋЇ love Allah, then follow me; Allah will love you and forgive your sins. For Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  3,32,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬObey Allah and His Messenger.вАЭ If they still turn away, then truly Allah does not like the disbelievers"
  3,33,"Indeed, Allah chose Adam, Noah, the family of Abraham, and the family of вАЩImr√Ґn above all people Ћєof their timeЋЇ"
  3,34,"They are descendants of one another. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,35,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the wife of вАЩImr√Ґn said, вАЬMy Lord! I dedicate what is in my womb entirely to Your service,¬†so accept it from me. You ЋєaloneЋЇ are truly the All-Hearing, All-Knowing.вАЭ"
  3,36,"When she delivered, she said, вАЬMy Lord! I have given birth to a girl,вАЭвАФand Allah fully knew what she had deliveredвАФвАЬand the male is not like the female.¬†I have named her Mary, and I seek Your protection for her and her offspring from Satan, the accursed.вАЭ"
  3,37,"So her Lord accepted her graciously and blessed her with a pleasant upbringingвАФentrusting her to the care of Zachariah. Whenever Zachariah visited her in the sanctuary, he found her supplied with provisions. He exclaimed, вАЬO Mary! Where did this come from?вАЭ She replied, вАЬIt is from Allah. Surely Allah provides for whoever He wills without limit.вАЭ"
  3,38,"Then and there Zachariah prayed to his Lord, saying, вАЬMy Lord! Grant meвАФby your graceвАФrighteous offspring. You are certainly the Hearer of ЋєallЋЇ prayers.вАЭ"
  3,39,"So the angels called out to him while he stood praying in the sanctuary, вАЬAllah gives you good news of Ћєthe birth ofЋЇ John who will confirm the Word of Allah and will be a great leader, chaste, and a prophet among the righteous.вАЭ"
  3,40,"Zachariah exclaimed, вАЬMy Lord! How can I have a son when I am very old and my wife is barren?вАЭ He replied, вАЬSo will it be. Allah does what He wills.вАЭ"
  3,41,"Zachariah said, вАЬMy Lord! Grant me a sign.вАЭ He said, вАЬYour sign is that you will not Ћєbe able toЋЇ speak to people for three days except through gestures. Remember your Lord often and glorify ЋєHimЋЇ morning and evening.вАЭ"
  3,42,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when the angels said, вАЬO Mary! Surely Allah has selected you, purified you, and chosen you over all women of the world"
  3,43,"O Mary! Be devout to your Lord, prostrate yourself Ћєin prayerЋЇ and bow along with those who bow down.вАЭ"
  3,44,"This is news of the unseen that We reveal to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. You were not with them when they cast lots to decide who would be MaryвАЩs guardian, nor were you there when they argued Ћєabout itЋЇ"
  3,45,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the angels proclaimed, вАЬO Mary! Allah gives you good news of a Word¬†from Him, his name will be the Messiah,¬†Jesus, son of Mary; honoured in this world and the Hereafter, and he will be one of those nearest Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  3,46,And he will speak to people in ЋєhisЋЇ infancy and adulthood and will be one of the righteous.вАЭ
  3,47,"Mary wondered, вАЬMy Lord! How can I have a child when no man has ever touched me?вАЭ An angel replied, вАЬSo will it be. Allah creates what He wills. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, вАШBe!вАЩ And it is"
  3,48,"And Allah will teach him writing and wisdom, the Torah and the Gospel"
  3,49,"and Ћєmake himЋЇ a messenger to the Children of Israel Ћєto proclaim,ЋЇ вАШI have come to you with a sign from your Lord: I will make for you a bird from clay, breathe into it, and it will become a ЋєrealЋЇ birdвАФby AllahвАЩs Will. I will heal the blind and the leper and raise the dead to lifeвАФby AllahвАЩs Will. And I will prophesize what you eat and store in your houses. Surely in this is a sign for you if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe"
  3,50,"And I will confirm the Torah revealed before me and legalize some of what had been forbidden to you. I have come to you with a sign from your Lord, so be mindful of Allah and obey me"
  3,51,Surely Allah is my Lord and your Lord. So worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. This is the Straight Path.вАЩвАЭ
  3,52,"When Jesus sensed disbelief from his people, he asked, вАЬWho will stand up with me for Allah?вАЭ The disciples replied, вАЬWe will stand up for Allah. We believe in Allah, so bear witness that we have submitted.вАЭ"
  3,53,"ЋєThey prayed to Allah,ЋЇ вАЬOur Lord! We believe in Your revelations and follow the messenger, so count us among those who bear witness.вАЭ"
  3,54,"And the disbelievers made a plan Ћєagainst JesusЋЇ, but Allah also plannedвАФand Allah is the best of planners"
  3,55,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when Allah said, вАЬO Jesus! I will take you¬†and raise you up to Myself. I will deliver you from those who disbelieve, and elevate your followers above the disbelievers until the Day of Judgment. Then to Me you will ЋєallЋЇ return, and I will settle all your disputes"
  3,56,"As for those who disbelieve, I will subject them to a severe punishment in this life and the Hereafter, and they will have no helpers"
  3,57,"And as for those who believe and do good, they will be rewarded in full. And Allah does not like the wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  3,58,We recite ЋєallЋЇ this to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as one of the signs¬†and ЋєasЋЇ a wise reminder
  3,59,"Indeed, the example of Jesus in the sight of Allah is like that of Adam. He created him from dust, then said to him, вАЬBe!вАЭ And he was"
  3,60,"This is the truth from your Lord, so do not be one of those who doubt"
  3,61,"Now, whoever disputes with you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ concerning Jesus after full knowledge has come to you, say, вАЬCome! Let us gather our children and your children, our women and your women, ourselves and yourselvesвАФthen let us sincerely invoke AllahвАЩs curse upon the liars.вАЭ"
  3,62,"Certainly, this is the true narrative, and there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Allah. And indeed, Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  3,63,"If they turn away, then surely Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of the corruptors"
  3,64,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO People of the Book! Let us come to common terms: that we will worship none but Allah, associate none with Him, nor take one another as lords instead of Allah.вАЭ But if they turn away, then say, вАЬBear witness that we have submitted Ћєto Allah aloneЋЇ.вАЭ"
  3,65,"O People of the Book! Why do you argue about Abraham, while the Torah and the Gospel were not revealed until long after him? Do you not understand"
  3,66,"Here you are! You disputed about what you have ЋєlittleЋЇ knowledge of,¬†but why do you now argue about what you have no knowledge of?¬†Allah knows and you do not know"
  3,67,Abraham was neither a Jew nor a Christian; he submitted in all uprightness¬†and was not a polytheist
  3,68,"Indeed, those who have the best claim to Abraham are his followers, this Prophet,¬†and the believers. And Allah is the Guardian of those who believe"
  3,69,"Some of the People of the Book wish to mislead you ЋєbelieversЋЇ. They mislead none but themselves, yet they fail to perceive it"
  3,70,O People of the Book! Why do you reject the signs of Allah while you bear witness Ћєto their truthЋЇ
  3,71,O People of the Book! Why do you mix the truth with falsehood and hide the truth knowingly
  3,72,"A group among the People of the Book said Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬBelieve in what has been revealed to the believers in the morning and reject it in the evening, so they may abandon their faith"
  3,73,"And only believe those who follow your religion.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬSurely, Ћєthe onlyЋЇ true guidance is AllahвАЩs guidance.вАЭ ЋєThey also said,ЋЇ вАЬDo not believe that someone will receive ЋєrevealedЋЇ knowledge similar to yours or argue against you before your Lord.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIndeed, all bounty is in the Hands of AllahвАФHe grants it to whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing.вАЭ"
  3,74,He chooses whoever He wills to receive His mercy. And Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty
  3,75,"There are some among the People of the Book who, if entrusted with a stack of gold, will readily return it. Yet there are others who, if entrusted with a single coin, will not repay it unless you constantly demand it. This is because they say, вАЬWe are not accountable for ЋєexploitingЋЇ the Gentiles.вАЭ¬†And ЋєsoЋЇ they attribute lies to Allah knowingly"
  3,76,Absolutely! Those who honour their trusts and shun evilвАФsurely Allah loves those who are mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ
  3,77,"Indeed, those who trade AllahвАЩs covenant and their oaths for a fleeting gain will have no share in the Hereafter. Allah will neither speak to them, nor look at them, nor purify them on the Day of Judgment. And they will suffer a painful punishment"
  3,78,"There are some among them who distort the Book with their tongues to make you think this ЋєdistortionЋЇ is from the BookвАФbut it is not what the Book says. They say, вАЬIt is from AllahвАЭвАФbut it is not from Allah. And ЋєsoЋЇ they attribute lies to Allah knowingly"
  3,79,"It is not appropriate for someone who Allah has blessed with the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood to say to people, вАЬWorship me instead of Allah.вАЭ Rather, he would say, вАЬBe devoted to the worship of your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇвАЭвАФin accordance with what these prophets read in the Scripture and what they taught"
  3,80,And he would never ask you to take angels and prophets as lords. Would he ask you to disbelieve after you have submitted
  3,81,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when Allah made a covenant with the prophets, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬNow that I have given you the Book and wisdom, if there comes to you a messenger¬†confirming what you have, you must believe in him and support him.вАЭ He added, вАЬDo you affirm this covenant and accept this commitment?вАЭ They said, вАЬYes, we do.вАЭ Allah said, вАЬThen bear witness, and I too am a Witness.вАЭ"
  3,82,"Whoever turns back after this, they will be the rebellious"
  3,83,"Do they desire a way other than AllahвАЩsвАФknowing that all those in the heavens and the earth submit to His Will, willingly or unwillingly, and to Him they will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  3,84,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWe believe in Allah and what has been revealed to us and what was revealed to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants; and what was given to Moses, Jesus, and other prophets from their LordвАФwe make no distinction between any of them, and to Him we ЋєfullyЋЇ submit.вАЭ"
  3,85,"Whoever seeks a way other than Islam,¬†it will never be accepted from them, and in the Hereafter they will be among the losers"
  3,86,"How will Allah guide a people who chose to disbelieve after they had believed, acknowledged the Messenger to be true, and received clear proofs? For Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  3,87,"Their reward is that they will be condemned by Allah, the angels, and all of humanity"
  3,88,"They will be in Hell forever. Their punishment will not be lightened, nor will they be delayed Ћєfrom itЋЇ"
  3,89,"As for those who repent afterwards and mend their ways, then surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  3,90,"Indeed, those who disbelieve after having believed then increase in disbelief, their repentance will never be accepted.¬†It is they who are astray"
  3,91,"Indeed, if each of those who disbelieve then die as disbelievers were to offer a ransom of enough gold to fill the whole world, it would never be accepted from them. It is they who will suffer a painful punishment, and they will have no helpers"
  3,92,You will never achieve righteousness until you donate some of what you cherish. And whatever you give is certainly well known to Allah
  3,93,"All food was lawful for the children of Israel, except what Israel¬†made unlawful for himself before the Torah was revealed.¬†Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬBring the Torah and read it, if your claims are true.вАЭ"
  3,94,"Then whoever still fabricates lies about Allah, they will be the ЋєtrueЋЇ wrongdoers"
  3,95,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAllah has declared the truth. So follow the Way of Abraham, the uprightвАФwho was not a polytheist.вАЭ"
  3,96,Surely the first House Ћєof worshipЋЇ established for humanity is the one at BakkahвАФa blessed sanctuary and a guide for ЋєallЋЇ people
  3,97,"In it are clear signs and the standing-place of Abraham. Whoever enters it should be safe. Pilgrimage to this House is an obligation by Allah upon whoever is able among the people.¬†And whoever disbelieves, then surely Allah is not in need of Ћєany of HisЋЇ creation"
  3,98,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO People of the Book! Why do you deny the revelations of Allah, when Allah is a Witness to what you do?вАЭ"
  3,99,"Say, вАЬO People of the Book! Why do you turn the believers away from the Way of AllahвАФstriving to make it ЋєappearЋЇ crooked, while you are witnesses Ћєto its truthЋЇ? And Allah is never unaware of what you do.вАЭ"
  3,100,"O believers! If you were to yield to a group of those who were given the Scripture, they would turn you back from belief to disbelief"
  3,101,How can you disbelieve when AllahвАЩs revelations are recited to you and His Messenger is in your midst? Whoever holds firmly to Allah is surely guided to the Straight Path
  3,102,"O believers! Be mindful of Allah in the way He deserves,¬†and do not die except in Ћєa state of fullЋЇ submission Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  3,103,"And hold firmly to the rope of Allah¬†and do not be divided. Remember AllahвАЩs favour upon you when you were enemies, then He united your hearts, so youвАФby His graceвАФbecame brothers. And you were at the brink of a fiery pit and He saved you from it. This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, so that you may be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  3,104,"Let there be a group among you who call ЋєothersЋЇ to goodness, encourage what is good, and forbid what is evilвАФit is they who will be successful"
  3,105,And do not be like those who split Ћєinto sectsЋЇ and differed after clear proofs had come to them. It is they who will suffer a tremendous punishment
  3,106,"On that Day some faces will be bright while others gloomy. To the gloomy-faced it will be said, вАЬDid you disbelieve after having believed? So taste the punishment for your disbelief.вАЭ"
  3,107,"As for the bright-faced, they will be in AllahвАЩs mercy, where they will remain forever"
  3,108,These are AllahвАЩs revelations We recite to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in truth. And Allah desires no injustice to ЋєHisЋЇ creation
  3,109,To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And to Allah ЋєallЋЇ matters will be returned Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ
  3,110,"You are the best community ever raised for humanityвАФyou encourage good, forbid evil, and believe in Allah. Had the People of the Book believed, it would have been better for them. Some of them are faithful, but most are rebellious"
  3,111,"They can never inflict harm on you, except a little annoyance.¬†But if they meet you in battle, they will flee and they will have no helpers"
  3,112,"They will be stricken with disgrace wherever they go, unless they are protected by a covenant with Allah or a treaty with the people. They have invited the displeasure of Allah and have been branded with misery for rejecting AllahвАЩs revelations and murdering ЋєHisЋЇ prophets unjustly. This is Ћєa fair rewardЋЇ for their disobedience and violations"
  3,113,"Yet they are not all alike: there are some among the People of the Book who are upright, who recite AllahвАЩs revelations throughout the night, prostrating Ћєin prayerЋЇ"
  3,114,"They believe in Allah and the Last Day, encourage good and forbid evil, and race with one another in doing good. They are ЋєtrulyЋЇ among the righteous"
  3,115,They will never be denied the reward for any good they have done. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of those mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ
  3,116,"Indeed, neither the wealth nor children of the disbelievers will be of any benefit to them against Allah. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  3,117,"The good they do in this worldly life is like the harvest of an evil people struck by a bitter wind, destroying it ЋєcompletelyЋЇ. Allah never wronged them, but they wronged themselves"
  3,118,"O believers! Do not associate closely with others who would not miss a chance to harm you. Their only desire is to see you suffer. Their prejudice has become evident from what they sayвАФand what their hearts hide is far worse. We have made Our revelations clear to you, if only you understood"
  3,119,"Here you are! You love them but they do not love you, and you believe in all Scriptures. When they meet you they say, вАЬWe believe.вАЭ But when alone, they bite their fingertips in rage. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєMay youЋЇ die of your rage!вАЭ Surely Allah knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  3,120,"When you ЋєbelieversЋЇ are touched with good, they grieve; but when you are afflicted with evil, they rejoice. ЋєYet,ЋЇ if you are patient and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, their schemes will not harm you in the least. Surely Allah is Fully Aware of what they do"
  3,121,"ЋєRemember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when you left your home in the early morning to position the believers in the battlefield. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,122,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when two groups among you ЋєbelieversЋЇ were about to cower, then Allah reassured them. So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  3,123,"Indeed, Allah made you victorious at Badr when you were ЋєvastlyЋЇ outnumbered. So be mindful of Allah, perhaps you will be grateful"
  3,124,"ЋєRemember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when you said to the believers, вАЬIs it not enough that your Lord will send down a reinforcement of three thousand angels for your aid?вАЭ"
  3,125,"Most certainly, if you ЋєbelieversЋЇ are firm and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ and the enemy launches a sudden attack on you, Allah will reinforce you with five thousand angels designated Ћєfor battleЋЇ"
  3,126,"Allah ordained this ЋєreinforcementЋЇ only as good news for you and reassurance for your hearts. And victory comes only from AllahвАФthe Almighty, All-WiseвАФ"
  3,127,"to destroy a group of the disbelievers and humble the rest, causing them to withdraw in disappointment"
  3,128,"You ЋєO ProphetЋЇ have no say in the matter.¬†It is up to Allah to turn to them in mercy or punish them, for indeed they are wrongdoers"
  3,129,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  3,130,"O believers! Do not consume interest, multiplying it many times over. And be mindful of Allah, so you may prosper"
  3,131,Guard yourselves against the Fire prepared for the disbelievers
  3,132,"Obey Allah and the Messenger, so you may be shown mercy"
  3,133,"And hasten towards forgiveness from your Lord and a Paradise as vast as the heavens and the earth, prepared for those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ"
  3,134,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who donate in prosperity and adversity, control their anger, and pardon others. And Allah loves the good-doers"
  3,135,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who, upon committing an evil deed or wronging themselves, remember Allah and seek forgiveness and do not knowingly persist in sinвАФand who forgives sins except Allah"
  3,136,"Their reward is forgiveness from their Lord and Gardens under which rivers flow, staying there forever. How excellent is the reward for those who work ЋєrighteousnessЋЇ"
  3,137,"Similar situations came to pass before you, so travel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers"
  3,138,This¬†is an insight to humanityвАФa guide and a lesson to the God-fearing
  3,139,"Do not falter or grieve, for you will have the upper hand, if you are ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  3,140,"If you have suffered injuries Ћєat UбЄ•udЋЇ, they suffered similarly Ћєat BadrЋЇ. We alternate these days Ћєof victory and defeatЋЇ among people so that Allah may reveal the ЋєtrueЋЇ believers, choose martyrs from among youвАФand Allah does not like the wrongdoersвАФ"
  3,141,and distinguish the ЋєtrueЋЇ believers and destroy the disbelievers
  3,142,Do you think you will enter Paradise without Allah proving which of you ЋєtrulyЋЇ struggled Ћєfor His causeЋЇ and patiently endured
  3,143,"You certainly wished Ћєfor the opportunityЋЇ for martyrdom before encountering it, now you have seen it with your own eyes"
  3,144,"MuбЄ•ammad is no more than a messenger; other messengers have gone before him. If he were to die or to be killed, would you regress into disbelief? Those who do so will not harm Allah whatsoever. And Allah will reward those who are grateful"
  3,145,"No soul can ever die without AllahвАЩs Will at the destined time. Those who desire worldly gain, We will let them have it, and those who desire heavenly reward, We will grant it to them. And We will reward those who are grateful"
  3,146,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many devotees fought along with their prophets and never faltered despite whatever ЋєlossesЋЇ they suffered in the cause of Allah, nor did they weaken or give in! Allah loves those who persevere"
  3,147,"And all they said was, вАЬOur Lord! Forgive our sins and excesses, make our steps firm, and grant us victory over the disbelieving people.вАЭ"
  3,148,So Allah gave them the reward of this world and the excellent reward of the Hereafter. For Allah loves the good-doers
  3,149,"O believers! If you yield to the disbelievers, they will drag you back to disbeliefвАФand you will become losers"
  3,150,"But no! Allah is your Guardian, and He is the best Helper"
  3,151,We will cast horror into the hearts of the disbelievers for associating Ћєfalse godsЋЇ with AllahвАФa practice He has never authorized. The Fire will be their homeвАФwhat an evil place for the wrongdoers to stay
  3,152,"Indeed, Allah fulfilled His promise to you when you ЋєinitiallyЋЇ swept them away by His Will, then your courage weakened and you disputed about the command and disobeyed,¬†after Allah had brought victory within your reach. Some of you were after worldly gain while others desired a heavenly reward. He denied you victory over them as a test, yet He has pardoned you. And Allah is Gracious to the believers"
  3,153,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when you were running far away Ћєin panicЋЇвАФnot looking at anyoneвАФwhile the Messenger was calling to you from behind! So Allah rewarded your disobedience with distress upon distress. Now, do not grieve over the victory you were denied or the injury you suffered. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  3,154,"Then after distress, He sent down serenity in the form of drowsiness overcoming some of you, while others were disturbed by evil thoughts about AllahвАФthe thoughts of Ћєpre-IslamicЋЇ ignorance. They ask, вАЬDo we have a say in the matter?вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAll matters are destined by Allah.вАЭ They conceal in their hearts what they do not reveal to you. They say Ћєto themselvesЋЇ, вАЬIf we had any say in the matter, none of us would have come to die here.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬEven if you were to remain in your homes, those among you who were destined to be killed would have met the same fate.вАЭ Through this, Allah tests what is within you and purifies what is in your hearts. And Allah knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  3,155,"Indeed, those ЋєbelieversЋЇ who fled on the day when the two armies met were made to slip by Satan because of their misdeeds. But Allah has pardoned them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  3,156,"O believers! Do not be like the unfaithful¬†who say about their brothers who travel throughout the land or engage in battle, вАЬIf they had stayed with us, they would not have died or been killed.вАЭ Allah makes such thinking a cause of agony in their hearts. It is Allah who gives life and causes death. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  3,157,"Should you be martyred or die in the cause of Allah, then His forgiveness and mercy are far better than whatever ЋєwealthЋЇ those Ћєwho stay behindЋЇ accumulate"
  3,158,Whether you die or are martyredвАФall of you will be gathered before Allah
  3,159,"It is out of AllahвАЩs mercy that you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ have been lenient with them. Had you been cruel or hard-hearted, they would have certainly abandoned you. So pardon them, ask AllahвАЩs forgiveness for them, and consult with them in ЋєconductingЋЇ matters. Once you make a decision, put your trust in Allah. Surely Allah loves those who trust in Him"
  3,160,"If Allah helps you, none can defeat you. But if He denies you help, then who else can help you? So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  3,161,"It is not appropriate for a prophet to illegally withhold spoils of war. And whoever does so, it will be held against them on the Day of Judgment. Then every soul will be paid in full for what it has done, and none will be wronged"
  3,162,Are those who seek AllahвАЩs pleasure like those who deserve AllahвАЩs wrath? Hell is their home. What an evil destination
  3,163,They ЋєeachЋЇ have varying degrees in the sight of Allah. And Allah is All-Seeing of what they do
  3,164,"Indeed, Allah has done the believers a ЋєgreatЋЇ favour by raising a messenger from among themвАФreciting to them His revelations, purifying them, and teaching them the Book and wisdom. For indeed they had previously been clearly astray"
  3,165,"Why is it when you suffered casualties Ћєat UбЄ•udЋЇвАФalthough you had made your enemy suffer twice as much Ћєat BadrЋЇвАФyou protested, вАЬHow could this be?вАЭ? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIt is because of your disobedience.вАЭ Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  3,166,"So what you suffered on the day the two armies met was by AllahвАЩs Will, so that He might distinguish the ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  3,167,"and expose the hypocrites. When it was said to them, вАЬCome fight in the cause of Allah or Ћєat leastЋЇ defend yourselves,вАЭ they replied, вАЬIf we had known there was fighting, we would have definitely gone with you.вАЭ They were closer to disbelief than to belief on that dayвАФfor saying with their mouths what was not in their hearts. Allah is All-Knowing of what they hide"
  3,168,"Those who sat at home, saying about their brothers, вАЬHad they listened to us, they would not have been killed.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬTry not to die¬†if what you say is true!вАЭ"
  3,169,"Never think of those martyred in the cause of Allah as dead. In fact, they are alive with their Lord, well provided forвАФ"
  3,170,"rejoicing in AllahвАЩs bounties and being delighted for those yet to join them. There will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  3,171,"They are joyful for receiving AllahвАЩs grace and bounty, and that Allah does not deny the reward of the believers"
  3,172,"ЋєAs forЋЇ those who responded to the call of Allah and His Messenger after their injury,¬†those of them who did good and were mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ will have a great reward"
  3,173,"Those who were warned, вАЬYour enemies have mobilized their forces against you, so fear them,вАЭ the warning only made them grow stronger in faith and they replied, вАЬAllah ЋєaloneЋЇ is sufficient Ћєas an aidЋЇ for us and ЋєHeЋЇ is the best Protector.вАЭ"
  3,174,"So they returned with AllahвАЩs favours and grace, suffering no harm. For they sought to please Allah. And surely Allah is ЋєtheЋЇ Lord of infinite bounty"
  3,175,"That ЋєwarningЋЇ was only ЋєfromЋЇ Satan, trying to prompt you to fear his followers.¬†So do not fear them; fear Me if you are ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  3,176,"ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Do not grieve for those who race to disbelieveвАФsurely they will not harm Allah in the least. It is AllahвАЩs Will to disallow them a share in the Hereafter, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  3,177,"Those who trade belief for disbelief will never harm Allah in the least, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  3,178,"Those who disbelieve should not think that living longer is good for them. They are only given more time to increase in sin, and they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  3,179,"Allah would not leave the believers in the condition you were in, until He distinguished the good from the evil Ћєamong youЋЇ. Nor would Allah ЋєdirectlyЋЇ reveal to you the unseen,¬†but He chooses whoever He wills as a messenger. So believe in Allah and His messengers. And if you are faithful and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, you will receive a great reward"
  3,180,"And do not let those who ЋєgreedilyЋЇ withhold AllahвАЩs bounties think it is good for themвАФin fact, it is bad for them! They will be leashed Ћєby their necksЋЇ on the Day of Judgment with whatever ЋєwealthЋЇ they used to withhold. And Allah is the ЋєsoleЋЇ inheritor of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  3,181,"Indeed, Allah has heard those Ћєamong the JewsЋЇ who said, вАЬAllah is poor; we are rich!вАЭ We have certainly recorded their slurs and their killing of prophets unjustly. Then We will say, вАЬTaste the torment of burning"
  3,182,This is Ћєthe rewardЋЇ for what your hands have done. And Allah is never unjust to ЋєHisЋЇ creation.вАЭ
  3,183,"Those Ћєare the same peopleЋЇ who say, вАЬAllah has commanded us not to believe in any messenger unless he brings us an offering to be consumed by fire Ћєfrom the skyЋЇ.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬOther prophets did in fact come to you¬†before me with clear proofs and ЋєevenЋЇ what you demandedвАФwhy then did you kill them, if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  3,184,"If you are rejected by them, so too were messengers before you who came with clear proofs, divine Books, and enlightening Scriptures"
  3,185,"Every soul will taste death. And you will only receive your full reward on the Day of Judgment. Whoever is spared from the Fire and is admitted into Paradise will ЋєindeedЋЇ triumph, whereas the life of this world is no more than the delusion of enjoyment"
  3,186,"You ЋєbelieversЋЇ will surely be tested in your wealth and yourselves,¬†and you will certainly hear many hurtful words from those who were given the Scripture before you and ЋєfromЋЇ the polytheists. But if you are patient and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇвАФsurely this is a resolve to aspire to"
  3,187,"ЋєRemember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when Allah took the covenant of those who were given the Scripture to make it known to people and not hide it, yet they cast it behind their backs and traded it for a fleeting gain. What a miserable profit"
  3,188,Do not let those who rejoice in their misdeeds and love to take credit for what they have not done think they will escape torment. They will suffer a painful punishment
  3,189,To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is Most Capable of everything
  3,190,"Indeed, in the creation of the heavens and the earth and the alternation of the day and night there are signs for people of reason"
  3,191,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who remember Allah while standing, sitting, and lying on their sides, and reflect on the creation of the heavens and the earth Ћєand prayЋЇ, вАЬOur Lord! You have not created Ћєall ofЋЇ this without purpose. Glory be to You! Protect us from the torment of the Fire"
  3,192,"Our Lord! Indeed, those You commit to the Fire will be ЋєcompletelyЋЇ disgraced! And the wrongdoers will have no helpers"
  3,193,"Our Lord! We have heard the caller¬†to ЋєtrueЋЇ belief, Ћєproclaiming,ЋЇ вАШBelieve in your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ,вАЩ so we believed. Our Lord! Forgive our sins, absolve us of our misdeeds, and allow us ЋєeachЋЇ to die as one of the virtuous"
  3,194,Our Lord! Grant us what You have promised us through Your messengers and do not put us to shame on Judgment DayвАФfor certainly You never fail in Your promise.вАЭ
  3,195,"So their Lord responded to them: вАЬI will never deny any of youвАФmale or femaleвАФthe reward of your deeds. Both are equal in reward. Those who migrated or were expelled from their homes, and were persecuted for My sake and fought and ЋєsomeЋЇ were martyredвАФI will certainly forgive their sins and admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, as a reward from Allah. And with Allah is the finest reward!вАЭ"
  3,196,Do not be deceived by the prosperity of the disbelievers throughout the land
  3,197,It is only a brief enjoyment. Then Hell will be their homeвАФwhat an evil place to rest
  3,198,"But those who are mindful of their Lord will be in Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there foreverвАФas an accommodation from Allah. And what is with Allah is best for the virtuous"
  3,199,"Indeed, there are some among the People of the Book who truly believe in Allah and what has been revealed to you ЋєbelieversЋЇ and what was revealed to them. They humble themselves before AllahвАФnever trading AllahвАЩs revelations for a fleeting gain. Their reward is with their Lord. Surely Allah is swift in reckoning"
  3,200,"O believers! Patiently endure, persevere, stand on guard,¬†and be mindful of Allah, so you may be successful"
  4,1,"O humanity! Be mindful of your Lord Who created you from a single soul, and from it He created its mate,¬†and through both He spread countless men and women. And be mindful of AllahвАФin Whose Name you appeal to one anotherвАФand ЋєhonourЋЇ family ties. Surely Allah is ever Watchful over you"
  4,2,"Give orphans their wealth Ћєwhen they reach maturityЋЇ, and do not exchange your worthless possessions for their valuables, nor cheat them by mixing their wealth with your own. For this would indeed be a great sin"
  4,3,"If you fear you might fail to give orphan women their ЋєdueЋЇ rights Ћєif you were to marry themЋЇ, then marry other women of your choiceвАФtwo, three, or four. But if you are afraid you will fail to maintain justice, then Ћєcontent yourselves withЋЇ one¬†or those ЋєbondwomenЋЇ in your possession.¬†This way you are less likely to commit injustice"
  4,4,"Give women Ћєyou wedЋЇ their due dowries graciously. But if they waive some of it willingly, then you may enjoy it freely with a clear conscience"
  4,5,"Do not entrust the incapable Ћєamong your dependantsЋЇ with your wealth which Allah has made a means of support for youвАФbut feed and clothe them from it, and speak to them kindly"
  4,6,"Test Ћєthe competence ofЋЇ the orphans until they reach a marriageable age. Then if you feel they are capable of sound judgment, return their wealth to them. And do not consume it wastefully and hastily before they grow up Ћєto demand itЋЇ. If the guardian is well-off, they should not take compensation; but if the guardian is poor, let them take a reasonable provision. When you give orphans back their property, call in witnesses. And sufficient is Allah as a ЋєvigilantЋЇ Reckoner"
  4,7,"For men there is a share in what their parents and close relatives leave, and for women there is a share in what their parents and close relatives leaveвАФwhether it is little or much. ЋєThese areЋЇ obligatory shares"
  4,8,"If Ћєnon-inheritingЋЇ relatives, orphans,¬†or the needy are present at the time of distribution, offer them a ЋєsmallЋЇ provision from it and speak to them kindly"
  4,9,Let the guardians be as concerned Ћєfor the orphansЋЇ as they would if they were to Ћєdie andЋЇ leave Ћєtheir ownЋЇ helpless children behind. So let them be mindful of Allah and speak equitably
  4,10,"Indeed, those who unjustly consume orphansвАЩ wealth Ћєin factЋЇ consume nothing but fire into their bellies. And they will be burned in a blazing Hell"
  4,11,"Allah commands you regarding your children: the share of the male will be twice that of the female.¬†If you leave only two Ћєor moreЋЇ females, their share is two-thirds of the estate. But if there is only one female, her share will be one-half. Each parent is entitled to one-sixth if you leave offspring.¬†But if you are childless and your parents are the only heirs, then your mother will receive one-third.¬†But if you leave siblings, then your mother will receive one-sixthвАФafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts.¬†ЋєBe fair toЋЇ your parents and children, as you do not ЋєfullyЋЇ know who is more beneficial to you.¬†ЋєThis isЋЇ an obligation from Allah. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,12,"You will inherit half of what your wives leave if they are childless. But if they have children, then Ћєyour share isЋЇ one-fourth of the estateвАФafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts. And your wives will inherit one-fourth of what you leave if you are childless. But if you have children, then your wives will receive one-eighth of your estateвАФafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts. And if a man or a woman leaves neither parents nor children but only a brother or a sister Ћєfrom their motherвАЩs sideЋЇ, they will each inherit one-sixth, but if they are more than one, they ЋєallЋЇ will share one-third of the estateвАФafter the fulfilment of bequests and debts without harm Ћєto the heirsЋЇ.¬†ЋєThis isЋЇ a commandment from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  4,13,"These ЋєentitlementsЋЇ are the limits set by Allah. Whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger will be admitted into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  4,14,"But whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger and exceeds their limits will be cast into Hell, to stay there forever. And they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  4,15,"ЋєAs forЋЇ those of your women who commit illegal intercourseвАФcall four witnesses from among yourselves. If they testify, confine the offenders to their homes until they die or Allah ordains a ЋєdifferentЋЇ way for them"
  4,16,"And the two among you who commit this sinвАФdiscipline them. If they repent and mend their ways, relieve them. Surely Allah is ever Accepting of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  4,17,"Allah only accepts the repentance of those who commit evil ignorantly Ћєor recklesslyЋЇ then repent soon afterвАФAllah will pardon them. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,18,"However, repentance is not accepted from those who knowingly persist in sin until they start dying, and then cry, вАЬNow I repent!вАЭ nor those who die as disbelievers. For them We have prepared a painful punishment"
  4,19,"O believers! It is not permissible for you to inherit women against their will¬†or mistreat them to make them return some of the dowry Ћєas a ransom for divorceЋЇвАФunless they are found guilty of adultery.¬†Treat them fairly. If you happen to dislike them, you may hate something which Allah turns into a great blessing"
  4,20,"If you desire to replace a wife with another and you have given the former ЋєevenЋЇ a stack of gold Ћєas a dowryЋЇ, do not take any of it back. Would you ЋєstillЋЇ take it unjustly and very sinfully"
  4,21,And how could you take it back after having enjoyed each other intimately and she has taken from you a firm commitment
  4,22,"Do not marry former wives of your fathersвАФexcept what was done previously. It was indeed a shameful, despicable, and evil practice"
  4,23,"ЋєAlsoЋЇ forbidden to you for marriage are your mothers, your daughters, your sisters, your paternal and maternal aunts, your brotherвАЩs daughters, your sisterвАЩs daughters, your foster-mothers, your foster-sisters, your mothers-in-law, your stepdaughters under your guardianship if you have consummated marriage with their mothersвАФbut if you have not, then you can marry themвАФnor the wives of your own sons, nor two sisters together at the same timeвАФexcept what was done previously. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,24,"Also Ћєforbidden areЋЇ married womenвАФexcept ЋєfemaleЋЇ captives in your possession.¬†This is AllahвАЩs commandment to you. Lawful to you are all beyond theseвАФas long as you seek them with your wealth in a legal marriage, not in fornication. Give those you have consummated marriage with their due dowries. It is permissible to be mutually gracious regarding the set dowry. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,25,"But if any of you cannot afford to marry a free believing woman, then Ћєlet him marryЋЇ a believing bondwoman possessed by one of you. Allah knows best Ћєthe state ofЋЇ your faith Ћєand theirsЋЇ. You are from one another.¬†So marry them with the permission of their owners,¬†giving them their dowry in fairness, if they are chaste, neither promiscuous nor having secret affairs. If they commit indecency after marriage, they receive half the punishment of free women.¬†This is for those of you who fear falling into sin. But if you are patient, it is better for you. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,26,"It is AllahвАЩs Will to make things clear to you, guide you to the ЋєnobleЋЇ ways of those before you, and turn to you in mercy. For Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,27,"And it is AllahвАЩs Will to turn to you in grace, but those who follow their desires wish to see you deviate entirely Ћєfrom AllahвАЩs WayЋЇ"
  4,28,"And it is AllahвАЩs Will to lighten your burdens, for humankind was created weak"
  4,29,"O believers! Do not devour one anotherвАЩs wealth illegally, but rather trade by mutual consent. And do not kill Ћєeach other orЋЇ yourselves. Surely Allah is ever Merciful to you"
  4,30,"And whoever does this sinfully and unjustly, We will burn them in the Fire. That is easy for Allah"
  4,31,"If you avoid the major sins forbidden to you, We will absolve you of your ЋєlesserЋЇ misdeeds and admit you into a place of honour"
  4,32,"And do not crave what Allah has given some of you over others. Men will be rewarded according to their deeds and women ЋєequallyЋЇ according to theirs. Rather, ask Allah for His bounties. Surely Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  4,33,"And We have appointed heirs to what has been left by parents and next of kin. As for those you have made a pledge to, give them their share.¬†Surely Allah is a Witness over all things"
  4,34,"Men are the caretakers of women, as men have been provisioned by Allah over women and tasked with supporting them financially. And righteous women are devoutly obedient and, when alone, protective of what Allah has entrusted them with.¬†And if you sense ill-conduct from your women, advise them ЋєfirstЋЇ, Ћєif they persist,ЋЇ do not share their beds, Ћєbut if they still persist,ЋЇ then discipline them ЋєgentlyЋЇ.¬†But if they change their ways, do not be unjust to them. Surely Allah is Most High, All-Great"
  4,35,"If you anticipate a split between them, appoint a mediator from his family and another from hers. If they desire reconciliation, Allah will restore harmony between them. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  4,36,"Worship Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ and associate none with Him. And be kind to parents, relatives, orphans, the poor, near and distant neighbours, close friends, ЋєneedyЋЇ travellers, and those ЋєbondspeopleЋЇ in your possession. Surely Allah does not like whoever is arrogant, boastfulвАФ"
  4,37,"those who are stingy, promote stinginess among people, and withhold AllahвАЩs bounties. We have prepared for the disbelievers a humiliating punishment"
  4,38,Likewise for those who spend their wealth to show off and do not believe in Allah or the Last Day. And whoever takes Satan as an associateвАФwhat an evil associate they have
  4,39,What harm could have come to them if they had believed in Allah and the Last Day and donated from what Allah has provided for them? And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of them
  4,40,"Indeed, Allah never wrongs ЋєanyoneЋЇвАФeven by an atomвАЩs weight.¬†And if it is a good deed, He will multiply it many times over and will give a great reward out of His grace"
  4,41,So how will it be when We bring a witness from every faith-community and bring you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as a witness against yours
  4,42,"On that Day, those who denied ЋєAllahЋЇ and disobeyed the Messenger will wish they were reduced to dust. And they will never be able to hide anything from Allah"
  4,43,"O believers! Do not approach prayer while intoxicated¬†until you are aware of what you say, nor in a state of ЋєfullЋЇ impurityвАФunless you merely pass through Ћєthe mosqueЋЇвАФuntil you have bathed. But if you are ill, on a journey, or have relieved yourselves, or been intimate with your wives and cannot find water, then purify yourselves with clean earth, wiping your faces and hands.¬†And Allah is Ever-Pardoning, All-Forgiving"
  4,44,Have you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not seen those who were given a portion of the Scriptures yet trade it for misguidance and wish to see you deviate from the ЋєRightЋЇ Path
  4,45,"Allah knows best who your enemies are! And Allah is sufficient as a Guardian, and He is sufficient as a Helper"
  4,46,"Some Jews take words out of context and say, вАЬWe listen and we disobey,вАЭ вАЬHear! May you never hear,вАЭ and вАЬR√ҐвАЩina!вАЭ [Herd us!]вАФplaying with words and discrediting the faith. Had they said ЋєcourteouslyЋЇ, вАЬWe hear and obey,вАЭ вАЬListen to us,вАЭ and вАЬUnбЇУurna,вАЭ [Tend to us!] it would have been better for them and more proper. Allah has condemned them for their disbelief, so they do not believe except for a few"
  4,47,"O you who were given the Book! Believe in what We have revealedвАФconfirming your own ScripturesвАФbefore We wipe out ЋєyourЋЇ faces, turning them backwards, or We condemn the defiant as We did to the Sabbath-breakers.¬†And AllahвАЩs command is always executed"
  4,48,"Indeed, Allah does not forgive associating others with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ,¬†but forgives anything else of whoever He wills. And whoever associates others with Allah has indeed committed a grave sin"
  4,49,Have you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not seen those who ЋєfalselyЋЇ elevate themselves? It is Allah who elevates whoever He wills. And none will be wronged Ћєeven by the width ofЋЇ the thread of a date stone
  4,50,See how they fabricate lies against AllahвАФthis alone is a blatant sin
  4,51,Have you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not seen those who were given a portion of the Scriptures yet believe in idols and false gods and reassure the disbelievers¬†that they are better guided than the believers
  4,52,It is they who have been condemned by Allah. And whoever is condemned by Allah will have no helper
  4,53,"Do they have control over shares of the kingdom? If so, they would not have given anyone so much as the speck on a date stone"
  4,54,"Or do they envy the people for AllahвАЩs bounties? Indeed, We have given the descendants of Abraham the Book and wisdom, along with great authority"
  4,55,Yet some believed in him while others turned away from him.¬†Hell is sufficient as a torment
  4,56,"Surely those who reject Our signs, We will cast them into the Fire. Whenever their skin is burnt completely, We will replace it so they will ЋєconstantlyЋЇ taste the punishment. Indeed, Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  4,57,"As for those who believe and do good, We will admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. There they will have pure spouses,¬†and We will place them under a vast shade"
  4,58,"Indeed, Allah commands you to return trusts to their rightful owners;¬†and when you judge between people, judge with fairness. What a noble commandment from Allah to you! Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  4,59,"O believers! Obey Allah and obey the Messenger and those in authority among you. Should you disagree on anything, then refer it to Allah and His Messenger, if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in Allah and the Last Day. This is the best and fairest resolution"
  4,60,"Have you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not seen those who claim they believe in what has been revealed to you and what was revealed before you? They seek the judgment of false judges, which they were commanded to reject. And Satan ЋєonlyЋЇ desires to lead them farther away"
  4,61,"When it is said to them, вАЬCome to AllahвАЩs revelations and to the Messenger,вАЭ you see the hypocrites turn away from you stubbornly"
  4,62,"How ЋєhorribleЋЇ will it be if a disaster strikes them because of what their hands have done, then they come to you swearing by Allah, вАЬWe intended nothing but goodwill and reconciliation.вАЭ"
  4,63,"ЋєOnlyЋЇ Allah knows what is in their hearts. So turn away from them, caution them, and give them advice that will shake their very souls"
  4,64,"We only sent messengers to be obeyed by AllahвАЩs Will. If only those ЋєhypocritesЋЇ came to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФafter wronging themselvesвАФseeking AllahвАЩs forgiveness and the Messenger prayed for their forgiveness, they would have certainly found Allah ever Accepting of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  4,65,"But no! By your Lord, they will never be ЋєtrueЋЇ believers until they accept you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as the judge in their disputes, and find no resistance within themselves against your decision and submit wholeheartedly"
  4,66,"If We had commanded them to sacrifice themselves or abandon their homes, none would have obeyed except for a few. Had they done what they were advised to do,¬†it would have certainly been far better for them and more reassuring"
  4,67,and We would have granted them a great reward by Our grace
  4,68,and guided them to the Straight Path
  4,69,"And whoever obeys Allah and the Messenger will be in the company of those blessed by Allah: the prophets, the people of truth, the martyrs, and the righteousвАФwhat honourable company"
  4,70,"This is AllahвАЩs favour, and Allah fully knows Ћєwho deserves itЋЇ"
  4,71,O believers! Take your precautions and go forth either in groups or together
  4,72,"There will be some among you who will lag behind so that if you face a disaster, they will say, вАЬAllah has blessed us for not being there among them.вАЭ"
  4,73,"But if you return with AllahвАЩs bounties, they will sayвАФas if there had been no bond between youвАФвАЬWe wish we had been there with them to share the great gain!вАЭ"
  4,74,Let those who would sacrifice this life for the Hereafter fight in the cause of Allah. And whoever fights in AllahвАЩs causeвАФwhether they achieve martyrdom or victoryвАФWe will honour them with a great reward
  4,75,"And what is it with you? You do not fight in the cause of Allah and for oppressed men, women, and children who cry out, вАЬOur Lord! Deliver us from this land of oppressors! Appoint for us a saviour; appoint for us a helperвАФall by Your grace.вАЭ"
  4,76,"Believers fight for the cause of Allah, whereas disbelievers fight for the cause of the Devil. So fight against SatanвАЩs ЋєevilЋЇ forces. Indeed, SatanвАЩs schemes are ever weak"
  4,77,"Have you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not seen those who had been told, вАЬDo not fight! Rather, establish prayer and pay alms-tax.вАЭ? Then once the order came to fight, a group of them feared those ЋєhostileЋЇ people as Allah should be fearedвАФor even more. They said, вАЬOur Lord! Why have You ordered us to fight? If only You had delayed Ћєthe order forЋЇ us for a little while!вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬThe enjoyment of this world is so little, whereas the Hereafter is far better for those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ. And none of you will be wronged Ћєeven by the width ofЋЇ the thread of a date stone"
  4,78,"Wherever you may be, death will overcome youвАФeven if you were in fortified towers.вАЭ When something good befalls them, they say, вАЬThis is from Allah,вАЭ but when something evil befalls them, they say, вАЬThis is from you.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬBoth have been destined by Allah.вАЭ So what is the matter with these people? They can hardly comprehend anything"
  4,79,Whatever good befalls you is from Allah and whatever evil befalls you is from yourself.¬†We have sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as a messenger to ЋєallЋЇ people. And Allah is sufficient as a Witness
  4,80,"Whoever obeys the Messenger has truly obeyed Allah. But whoever turns away, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ We have not sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as a keeper over them"
  4,81,"And they say, вАЬWe obey,вАЭ but when they leave you, a group of them would spend the night contradicting what they said. Allah records all their schemes. So turn away from them, and put your trust in Allah. And Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  4,82,"Do they not then reflect on the Quran? Had it been from anyone other than Allah, they would have certainly found in it many inconsistencies"
  4,83,"And when they hear news of security or fear,¬†they publicize it. Had they referred it to the Messenger or their authorities, those with sound judgment among them would have validated it. Had it not been for AllahвАЩs grace and mercy, you would have followed SatanвАФexcept for a few"
  4,84,"So fight in the cause of Allah ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. You are accountable for none but yourself. And motivate the believers Ћєto fightЋЇ, so perhaps Allah will curb the disbelieversвАЩ might. And Allah is far superior in might and in punishment"
  4,85,"Whoever intercedes for a good cause will have a share in the reward, and whoever intercedes for an evil cause will have a share in the burden. And Allah is Watchful over all things"
  4,86,"And when you are greeted, respond with a better greeting or at least similarly. Surely Allah is a ЋєvigilantЋЇ Reckoner of all things"
  4,87,"Allah, there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. He will certainly gather Ћєall ofЋЇ you together on the Day of JudgmentвАФabout which there is no doubt. And whose word is more truthful than AllahвАЩs"
  4,88,"Why are you ЋєbelieversЋЇ divided into two groups regarding the hypocrites while Allah allowed them to regress Ћєto disbeliefЋЇ because of their misdeeds? Do you wish to guide those left by Allah to stray? And whoever Allah leaves to stray, you will never find for them a way"
  4,89,"They wish you would disbelieve as they have disbelieved, so you may all be alike. So do not take them as allies unless they emigrate in the cause of Allah. But if they turn away, then seize them and kill them wherever you find them, and do not take any of them as allies or helpers"
  4,90,"except those who are allies of a people you are bound with in a treaty or those wholeheartedly opposed to fighting either you or their own people. If Allah had willed, He would have empowered them to fight you. So if they refrain from fighting you and offer you peace, then Allah does not permit you to harm them"
  4,91,"You will find others who wish to be safe from you and their own people. Yet they cannot resist the temptation Ћєof disbelief or hostilityЋЇ. If they do not keep away, offer you peace, or refrain from attacking you, then seize them and kill them wherever you find them. We have given you full permission over such people"
  4,92,"It is not lawful for a believer to kill another except by mistake. And whoever kills a believer unintentionally must free a believing slave and pay blood-money to the victimвАЩs familyвАФunless they waive it charitably. But if the victim is a believer from a hostile people, then a believing slave must be freed. And if the victim is from a people bound with you in a treaty, then blood-money must be paid to the family along with freeing a believing slave. Those who are unable, let them fast two consecutive monthsвАФas a means of repentance to Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,93,"And whoever kills a believer intentionally, their reward will be HellвАФwhere they will stay indefinitely.¬†Allah will be displeased with them, condemn them, and will prepare for them a tremendous punishment"
  4,94,"O believers! When you struggle in the cause of Allah, be sure of who you fight. And do not say to those who offer you Ћєgreetings ofЋЇ peace, вАЬYou are no believer!вАЭвАФseeking a fleeting worldly gain.¬†Instead, Allah has infinite bounties Ћєin storeЋЇ. You were initially like them then Allah blessed you Ћєwith IslamЋЇ. So be sure! Indeed, Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  4,95,"Those who stay at homeвАФexcept those with valid excusesвАФare not equal to those who strive in the cause of Allah with their wealth and their lives. Allah has elevated in rank those who strive with their wealth and their lives above those who stay behind Ћєwith valid excusesЋЇ. Allah has promised each a fine reward, but those who strive will receive a far better reward than othersвАФ"
  4,96,"far superior ranks, forgiveness, and mercy from Him. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,97,"When the angels seize the souls of those who have wronged themselvesвАФscolding them, вАЬWhat do you think you were doing?вАЭ they will reply, вАЬWe were oppressed in the land.вАЭ The angels will respond, вАЬWas AllahвАЩs earth not spacious enough for you to emigrate?вАЭ It is they who will have Hell as their homeвАФwhat an evil destination"
  4,98,"Except helpless men, women, and children who cannot afford a way outвАФ"
  4,99,"it is right to hope that Allah will pardon them. For Allah is Ever-Pardoning, All-Forgiving"
  4,100,"Whoever emigrates in the cause of Allah will find many safe havens and bountiful resources throughout the earth. Those who leave their homes and die while emigrating to Allah and His MessengerвАФtheir reward has already been secured with Allah. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,101,"When you travel through the land, it is permissible for you to shorten the prayerвАФЋєespeciallyЋЇ if you fear an attack by the disbelievers. Indeed, the disbelievers are your sworn enemies"
  4,102,"When you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are ЋєcampaigningЋЇ with them and you lead them in prayer, let one group of them pray with youвАФwhile armed. When they prostrate themselves, let the other group stand guard behind them. Then the group that has not yet prayed will then join you in prayerвАФand let them be vigilant and armed.¬†The disbelievers would wish to see you neglect your weapons and belongings, so they could launch a sweeping assault on you. But there is no blame if you lay aside your weapons when overcome by heavy rain or illnessвАФbut take precaution. Indeed, Allah has prepared a humiliating punishment for the disbelievers"
  4,103,"When the prayers are over, remember AllahвАФwhether you are standing, sitting, or lying down. But when you are secure, establish regular prayers. Indeed, performing prayers is a duty on the believers at the appointed times"
  4,104,"Do not falter in pursuit of the enemyвАФif you are suffering, they too are suffering. But you can hope to receive from Allah what they can never hope for. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,105,"Indeed, We have sent down the Book to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in truth to judge between people by means of what Allah has shown you. So do not be an advocate for the deceitful"
  4,106,"And seek AllahвАЩs forgivenessвАФindeed, Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,107,"Do not advocate for those who wrong themselves.¬†Surely Allah does not like those who are deceitful, sinful"
  4,108,"They try to hide Ћєtheir deceptionЋЇ from people, but they can never hide it from AllahвАФin Whose presence they plot by night what is displeasing to Him. And Allah is Fully Aware of what they do"
  4,109,"Here you are! You ЋєbelieversЋЇ are advocating for them in this life, but who will Ћєdare toЋЇ advocate for them before Allah on the Day of Judgment? Or who will come to their defence"
  4,110,"Whoever commits evil or wrongs themselves then seeks AllahвАЩs forgiveness will certainly find Allah All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,111,"And whoever commits a sinвАФit is only to their own loss. Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,112,"And whoever commits an evil or sinful deed then blames it on an innocent person, they will definitely bear the guilt of slander and blatant sin"
  4,113,"Had it not been for AllahвАЩs grace and mercy, a group of them would have sought to deceive you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Yet they would deceive none but themselves, nor can they harm you in the least. Allah has revealed to you the Book and wisdom and taught you what you never knew. Great ЋєindeedЋЇ is AllahвАЩs favour upon you"
  4,114,"There is no good in most of their secret talksвАФexcept those encouraging charity, kindness, or reconciliation between people. And whoever does this seeking AllahвАЩs pleasure, We will grant them a great reward"
  4,115,"And whoever defies the Messenger after guidance has become clear to them and follows a path other than that of the believers, We will let them pursue what they have chosen, then burn them in HellвАФwhat an evil end"
  4,116,"Surely Allah does not forgive associating ЋєothersЋЇ with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ,¬†but forgives anything else of whoever He wills. Indeed, whoever associates ЋєothersЋЇ with Allah has clearly gone far astray"
  4,117,"Instead of Allah, they only invoke female gods¬†and they ЋєactuallyЋЇ invoke none but a rebellious SatanвАФ"
  4,118,"cursed by AllahвАФwho said, вАЬI will surely take hold of a certain number of Your servants"
  4,119,"I will certainly mislead them and delude them with empty hopes. Also, I will order them and they will slit the ears of cattle¬†and alter AllahвАЩs creation.вАЭ And whoever takes Satan as a guardian instead of Allah has certainly suffered a tremendous loss"
  4,120,Satan only makes them ЋєfalseЋЇ promises and deludes them with ЋєemptyЋЇ hopes. Truly Satan promises them nothing but delusion
  4,121,"It is they who will have Hell as their home, and they will find no escape from it"
  4,122,"And those who believe and do good, We will soon admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. AllahвАЩs promise is ЋєalwaysЋЇ true. And whose word is more truthful than AllahвАЩs"
  4,123,"ЋєDivine grace isЋЇ neither by your wishes nor those of the People of the Book! Whoever commits evil will be rewarded accordingly, and they will find no protector or helper besides Allah"
  4,124,But those who do goodвАФwhether male or femaleвАФand have faith will enter Paradise and will never be wronged Ћєeven as much asЋЇ the speck on a date stone
  4,125,"And who is better in faith than those who ЋєfullyЋЇ submit themselves to Allah, do good, and follow the Way of Abraham, the upright? Allah chose Abraham as a close friend"
  4,126,To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And Allah is Fully Aware of everything
  4,127,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ regarding women. Say, вАЬIt is Allah Who instructs you regarding them. Instruction has ЋєalreadyЋЇ been revealed in the Book¬†concerning the orphan women you deprive of their due rights¬†but still wish to marry, also helpless children, as well as standing up for orphansвАЩ rights. And whatever good you do is certainly well known to Allah.вАЭ"
  4,128,"If a woman fears indifference or neglect from her husband, there is no blame on either of them if they seek ЋєfairЋЇ settlement, which is best. Humans are ever inclined to selfishness.¬†But if you are gracious and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, surely Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  4,129,"You will never be able to maintain ЋєemotionalЋЇ justice between your wivesвАФno matter how keen you are. So do not totally incline towards one leaving the other in suspense.¬†And if you do what is right and are mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,130,"But if they choose to separate, Allah will enrich both of them from His bounties. And Allah is Ever-Bountiful, All-Wise"
  4,131,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Indeed, We have commanded those given the Scripture before you, as well as you, to be mindful of Allah. But if you disobey, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  4,132,To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs
  4,133,"If it is His Will, He can remove you altogether, O humanity, and replace you with others. And Allah is Most Capable to do so"
  4,134,"Whoever desires the reward of this world, then Ћєlet them know thatЋЇ with Allah are the rewards of this world and the Hereafter. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  4,135,"O believers! Stand firm for justice as witnesses for Allah even if it is against yourselves, your parents, or close relatives. Be they rich or poor, Allah is best to ensure their interests. So do not let your desires cause you to deviate Ћєfrom justiceЋЇ. If you distort the testimony or refuse to give it, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ Allah is certainly All-Aware of what you do"
  4,136,"O believers! Have faith in Allah, His Messenger, the Book He has revealed to His Messenger, and the Scriptures He revealed before. Indeed, whoever denies Allah, His angels, His Books, His messengers, and the Last Day has clearly gone far astray"
  4,137,"Indeed, those who believed then disbelieved, then believed and again disbelievedвАФЋєonlyЋЇ increasing in disbeliefвАФAllah will neither forgive them nor guide them to the ЋєRightЋЇ Way"
  4,138,Give good news of a painful punishment to hypocrites
  4,139,who choose disbelievers as allies instead of the believers. Do they seek honour and power through that company? Surely all honour and power belongs to Allah
  4,140,"He has already revealed to you in the Book that when you hear AllahвАЩs revelations being denied or ridiculed, then do not sit in that company unless they engage in a different topic, or else you will be like them.¬†Surely Allah will gather the hypocrites and disbelievers all together in Hell"
  4,141,"ЋєThe hypocrites areЋЇ those who wait to see what happens to you. So if Allah grants you victory, they say Ћєto youЋЇ, вАЬWere we not on your side?вАЭ But if the disbelievers have a share Ћєof victoryЋЇ, they say Ћєto themЋЇ, вАЬDid we not have the advantage over you, yet we protected you from the believers?вАЭ Allah will judge between Ћєall ofЋЇ you on the Day of Judgment. And Allah will never grant the disbelievers a way over the believers"
  4,142,"Surely the hypocrites seek to deceive Allah, but He outwits them. When they stand up for prayer, they do it half-heartedly only to be seen by peopleвАФhardly remembering Allah at all"
  4,143,"Torn between belief and disbeliefвАФbelonging neither to these ЋєbelieversЋЇ nor those ЋєdisbelieversЋЇ. And whoever Allah leaves to stray, you will never find for them a way"
  4,144,O believers! Do not take disbelievers as allies instead of the believers. Would you like to give Allah solid proof against yourselves
  4,145,Surely the hypocrites will be in the lowest depths of the FireвАФand you will never find for them any helperвАФ
  4,146,"except those who repent, mend their ways, hold fast to Allah, and are sincere in their devotion to Allah; they will be with the believers. And Allah will grant the believers a great reward"
  4,147,"Why should Allah punish you if you are grateful and faithful? Allah is ever Appreciative, All-Knowing"
  4,148,"Allah does not like negative thoughts to be voicedвАФexcept by those who have been wronged.¬†Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  4,149,"Whether you reveal or conceal a good or pardon an evilвАФsurely Allah is Ever-Pardoning, Most Capable"
  4,150,"Surely those who deny Allah and His messengers and wish to make a distinction between Allah and His messengers,¬†saying, вАЬWe believe in some and disbelieve in others,вАЭ desiring to forge a compromise"
  4,151,they are indeed the true disbelievers. And We have prepared for the disbelievers a humiliating punishment
  4,152,"As for those who believe in Allah and His messengersвАФaccepting all; rejecting noneвАФHe will surely give them their rewards. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  4,153,"The People of the Book demand that you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ bring down for them a revelation in writing from heaven.¬†They demanded what is even greater than this from Moses, saying, вАЬMake Allah visible to us!вАЭ So a thunderbolt struck them for their wrongdoing. Then they took the calf for worship after receiving clear signs. Still We forgave them for that Ћєafter their repentanceЋЇ and gave Moses compelling proof"
  4,154,"We raised the Mount over them Ћєas a warningЋЇ for ЋєbreakingЋЇ their covenant and said, вАЬEnter the gate Ћєof JerusalemЋЇ with humility.вАЭ We also warned them, вАЬDo not break the Sabbath,вАЭ and took from them a firm covenant"
  4,155,"ЋєThey were condemnedЋЇ for breaking their covenant, rejecting AllahвАЩs signs, killing the prophets unjustly, and for saying, вАЬOur hearts are unreceptive!вАЭвАФit is Allah Who has sealed their hearts for their disbelief, so they do not believe except for a fewвАФ"
  4,156,and for their denial and outrageous accusation against Mary
  4,157,"and for boasting, вАЬWe killed the Messiah, Jesus, son of Mary, the messenger of Allah.вАЭ But they neither killed nor crucified himвАФit was only made to appear so.¬†Even those who argue for this ЋєcrucifixionЋЇ are in doubt. They have no knowledge whatsoeverвАФonly making¬†assumptions. They certainly did not kill him"
  4,158,"Rather, Allah raised him up to Himself. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  4,159,Every one of the People of the Book will definitely believe in him before his death.¬†And on the Day of Judgment Jesus will be a witness against them
  4,160,"We forbade the Jews certain foods that had been lawful to them for their wrongdoing, and for hindering many from the Way of Allah"
  4,161,"taking interest despite its prohibition, and consuming peopleвАЩs wealth unjustly. We have prepared for the disbelievers among them a painful punishment"
  4,162,"But those of them well-grounded in knowledge, the faithful ЋєwhoЋЇ believe in what has been revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ and what was revealed before youвАФЋєespeciallyЋЇ those who establish prayerвАФand those who pay alms-tax and believe in Allah and the Last Day, to these ЋєpeopleЋЇ We will grant a great reward"
  4,163,"Indeed, We have sent revelation to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as We sent revelation to Noah and the prophets after him. We also sent revelation to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants, Ћєas well asЋЇ Jesus, Job, Jonah, Aaron, and Solomon. And to David We gave the Psalms"
  4,164,There are messengers whose stories We have told you already and others We have not. And to Moses Allah spoke directly
  4,165,"ЋєAll wereЋЇ messengers delivering good news and warnings so humanity should have no excuse before Allah after Ћєthe coming ofЋЇ the messengers. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  4,166,"Yet Ћєif you are denied, O Prophet,ЋЇ Allah bears witness to what He has sent down to youвАФHe has sent it with His knowledge. The angels too bear witness. And Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is sufficient as a Witness"
  4,167,Those who disbelieve and hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah have certainly strayed far away
  4,168,Those who disbelieve and wrong themselvesвАФsurely Allah will neither forgive them nor guide them to any path
  4,169,"except that of Hell, to stay there for ever and ever. And that is easy for Allah"
  4,170,"O humanity! The Messenger has certainly come to you with the truth from your Lord, so believe for your own good. But if you disbelieve, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  4,171,"O People of the Book! Do not go to extremes regarding your faith; say nothing about Allah except the truth.¬†The Messiah, Jesus, son of Mary, was no more than a messenger of Allah and the fulfilment of His Word through Mary and a spirit Ћєcreated by a commandЋЇ from Him.¬†So believe in Allah and His messengers and do not say, вАЬTrinity.вАЭ Stop!вАФfor your own good. Allah is only One God. Glory be to Him! He is far above having a son! To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  4,172,"The Messiah would never be too proud to be a servant of Allah, nor would the angels nearest to Allah. Those who are too proud and arrogant to worship Him will be brought before Him all together"
  4,173,"As for those who believe and do good, He will reward them in full and increase them out of His grace. But those who are too proud and arrogant, He will subject them to a painful punishment. And besides Allah they will find no protector or helper"
  4,174,O humanity! There has come to you conclusive evidence from your Lord. And We have sent down to you a brilliant light
  4,175,"As for those who believe in Allah and hold fast to Him, He will admit them into His mercy and grace and guide them to Himself through the Straight Path"
  4,176,"They ask you Ћєfor a ruling, O ProphetЋЇ. Say, вАЬAllah gives you a ruling regarding those who die without children or parents.вАЭ If a man dies childless and leaves behind a sister, she will inherit one-half of his estate, whereas her brother will inherit all of her estate if she dies childless. If this person leaves behind two sisters, they together will inherit two-thirds of the estate. But if the deceased leaves male and female siblings, a maleвАЩs share will be equal to that of two females. Allah makes ЋєthisЋЇ clear to you so you do not go astray. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  5,1,"O believers! Honour your obligations. All grazing livestock has been made lawful to youвАФexcept what is hereby announced to you and hunting while on pilgrimage. Indeed, Allah commands what He wills"
  5,2,"O believers! Do not violate AllahвАЩs rituals Ћєof pilgrimageЋЇ, the sacred months, the sacrificial animals, the Ћєofferings decorated withЋЇ garlands, nor those ЋєpilgrimsЋЇ on their way to the Sacred House seeking their LordвАЩs bounty and pleasure. When pilgrimage has ended, you are allowed to hunt. Do not let the hatred of a people who once barred you from the Sacred Mosque provoke you to transgress. Cooperate with one another in goodness and righteousness, and do not cooperate in sin and transgression. And be mindful of Allah. Surely Allah is severe in punishment"
  5,3,"Forbidden to you are carrion, blood, and swine; what is slaughtered in the name of any other than Allah; what is killed by strangling, beating, a fall, or by being gored to death; what is partly eaten by a predator unless you slaughter it; and what is sacrificed on altars. You are also forbidden to draw lots for decisions.¬†This is all evil. Today the disbelievers have given up all hope of ЋєunderminingЋЇ your faith. So do not fear them; fear Me! Today I have perfected your faith for you, completed My favour upon you, and chosen Islam as your way. But whoever is compelled by extreme hungerвАФnot intending to sinвАФthen surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  5,4,"They ask you, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ what is permissible for them Ћєto eatЋЇ. Say, вАЬWhat is good and lawful. Also what is caught by your hunting animals and birds of prey which you have trained as instructed by Allah. So eat what they catch for you, but mention the Name of Allah over it ЋєfirstЋЇ.вАЭ And be mindful of Allah. Surely Allah is swift in reckoning"
  5,5,"Today all good, pure foods have been made lawful for you. Similarly, the food of the People of the Book¬†is permissible for you and yours is permissible for them. And Ћєpermissible for you in marriageЋЇ are chaste believing women as well as chaste women of those given the Scripture before youвАФas long as you pay them their dowries in wedlock, neither fornicating nor taking them as mistresses. And whoever rejects the faith, all their good deeds will be void Ћєin this lifeЋЇ and in the Hereafter they will be among the losers"
  5,6,"O believers! When you rise up for prayer, wash your faces and your hands up to the elbows, wipe your heads, and wash your feet to the ankles. And if you are in a state of ЋєfullЋЇ impurity,¬†then take a full bath. But if you are ill, on a journey, or have relieved yourselves, or have been intimate with your wives and cannot find water, then purify yourselves with clean earth by wiping your faces and hands.¬†It is not AllahвАЩs Will to burden you, but to purify you and complete His favour upon you, so perhaps you will be grateful"
  5,7,"Remember AllahвАЩs favour upon you and the covenant He made with you when you said, вАЬWe hear and obey.вАЭ And be mindful of Allah. Surely Allah knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  5,8,O believers! Stand firm for Allah and bear true testimony. Do not let the hatred of a people lead you to injustice. Be just! That is closer to righteousness. And be mindful of Allah. Surely Allah is All-Aware of what you do
  5,9,Allah has promised those who believe and do good ЋєHisЋЇ forgiveness and a great reward
  5,10,"As for those who disbelieve and deny Our signs, they are the residents of the Hellfire"
  5,11,"O believers! Remember AllahвАЩs favour upon you: when a people sought to harm you, but He held their hands back from you. Be mindful of Allah. And in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  5,12,"Allah made a covenant with the Children of Israel and appointed twelve leaders from among them and ЋєthenЋЇ said, вАЬI am truly with you. If you establish prayer, pay alms-tax, believe in My messengers, support them, and lend to Allah a good loan, I will certainly forgive your sins and admit you into Gardens under which rivers flow. And whoever among you disbelieves afterwards has truly strayed from the Right Way.вАЭ"
  5,13,"But for breaking their covenant We condemned them and hardened their hearts. They distorted the words of the Scripture and neglected a portion of what they had been commanded to uphold. You ЋєO ProphetЋЇ will always find deceit on their part, except for a few. But pardon them and bear with them. Indeed, Allah loves the good-doers"
  5,14,"And from those who say, вАЬWe are Christians,вАЭ We took their covenant, but they neglected a portion of what they had been commanded to uphold. So We let hostility and enmity arise between them until the Day of Judgment, and soon Allah will inform them of all they have done"
  5,15,"O People of the Book! Now Our Messenger has come to you, revealing much of what you have hidden of the Scriptures and disregarding much. There certainly has come to you from Allah a light and a clear Book"
  5,16,"through which Allah guides those who seek His pleasure to the ways of peace, brings them out of darkness and into light by His Will, and guides them to the Straight Path"
  5,17,"Indeed, those who say, вАЬAllah is the Messiah, son of Mary,вАЭ have fallen into disbelief. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWho has the power to prevent Allah if He chose to destroy the Messiah, son of Mary, his mother, and everyone in the world all together?вАЭ To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between. He creates whatever He wills. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  5,18,"The Jews and the Christians each say, вАЬWe are the children of Allah and His most beloved!вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWhy then does He punish you for your sins? No! You are only humans like others of His Own making. He forgives whoever He wills and punishes whoever He wills. To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between. And to Him is the final return.вАЭ"
  5,19,"O People of the Book! Our Messenger has indeed come to you, making things clear to you after an interval between the messengers so you do not say, вАЬThere has never come to us a deliverer of good news or a warner.вАЭ Now there has come to you a deliverer of good news and a warner. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  5,20,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Moses said to his people, вАЬO my people! Remember AllahвАЩs favours upon you when He raised prophets from among you, made you sovereign,¬†and gave you what He had never given anyone in the world"
  5,21,O my people! Enter the Holy Land which Allah has destined for you Ћєto enterЋЇ. And do not turn back or else you will become losers.вАЭ
  5,22,"They replied, вАЬO Moses! There is an enormously powerful people there, so we will never Ћєbe able toЋЇ enter it until they leave. If they do, then we will enter!вАЭ"
  5,23,"Two God-fearing menвАФwho had been blessed by AllahвАФsaid, вАЬSurprise them through the gate. If you do, you will certainly prevail. Put your trust in Allah if you are ЋєtrulyЋЇ believers.вАЭ"
  5,24,"ЋєYetЋЇ they said, вАЬO Moses! ЋєStillЋЇ we will never enter as long as they remain there. So goвАФboth you and your LordвАФand fight; we are staying right here!вАЭ"
  5,25,"Moses pleaded, вАЬMy Lord! I have no control over anyone except myself and my brother. So set us apart from the rebellious people.вАЭ"
  5,26,"Allah replied, вАЬThen this land is forbidden to them for forty years, during which they will wander through the land. So do not grieve for the rebellious people.вАЭ"
  5,27,"Relate to them in truth ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the story of AdamвАЩs two sonsвАФhow each offered a sacrifice: AbelвАЩs offering was accepted while CainвАЩs was not. So Cain threatened, вАЬI will kill you!вАЭ His brother replied, вАЬAllah only accepts Ћєthe offeringЋЇ of the sincerely devout"
  5,28,"If you raise your hand to kill me, I will not raise mine to kill you, because I fear AllahвАФthe Lord of all worlds"
  5,29,"I want to let you bear your sin against me along with your other sins, then you will be one of those destined to the Fire. And that is the reward of the wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  5,30,"Yet Cain convinced himself to kill his brother, so he killed himвАФbecoming a loser"
  5,31,"Then Allah sent a crow digging Ћєa graveЋЇ in the ground Ћєfor a dead crowЋЇ, in order to show him how to bury the corpse of his brother. He cried, вАЬAlas! Have I ЋєevenЋЇ failed to be like this crow and bury the corpse of my brother?вАЭ So he became regretful"
  5,32,"That is why We ordained for the Children of Israel that whoever takes a lifeвАФunless as a punishment for murder or mischief in the landвАФit will be as if they killed all of humanity; and whoever saves a life, it will be as if they saved all of humanity.¬†ЋєAlthoughЋЇ Our messengers already came to them with clear proofs, many of them still transgressed afterwards through the land"
  5,33,"Indeed, the penalty for those who wage war against Allah and His Messenger and spread mischief in the land is death, crucifixion, cutting off their hands and feet on opposite sides, or exile from the land. This ЋєpenaltyЋЇ is a disgrace for them in this world, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment in the Hereafter"
  5,34,"As for those who repent before you seize them, then know that Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  5,35,"O believers! Be mindful of Allah and seek what brings you closer to Him and struggle in His Way, so you may be successful"
  5,36,"As for the disbelievers, even if they were to possess everything in the world twice over Ћєand offer it allЋЇ to ransom themselves from the punishment of the Day of Judgment, it would never be accepted from them. And they will suffer a painful punishment"
  5,37,They will be desperate to get out of the Fire but they will never be able to. And they will suffer an everlasting punishment
  5,38,"As for male and female thieves, cut off their hands for what they have doneвАФa deterrent from Allah. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  5,39,"But whoever repents after their wrongdoing and mends their ways, Allah will surely turn to them in forgiveness. Indeed, Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  5,40,Do you not know that the kingdom of the heavens and the earth belongs to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ? He punishes whoever He wills and forgives whoever He wills. And Allah is Most Capable of everything
  5,41,"O Messenger! Do not grieve for those who race to disbelieveвАФthose who say, вАЬWe believeвАЭ with their tongues, but their hearts are in disbelief. Nor those among the Jews who eagerly listen to lies, attentive to those who are too arrogant to come to you. They distort the Scripture, taking rulings out of context, then say, вАЬIf this is the ruling you get Ћєfrom MuбЄ•ammadЋЇ, accept it. If not, beware!вАЭ Whoever Allah allows to be deluded, you can never be of any help to them against Allah. It is not AllahвАЩs Will to purify their hearts. For them is disgrace in this world, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment in the Hereafter"
  5,42,"They eagerly listen to falsehood and consume forbidden gain.¬†So if they come to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, either judge between them or turn away from them. If you turn away from them, they cannot harm you whatsoever. But if you judge between them, then do so with justice. Surely Allah loves those who are just"
  5,43,"But why do they come to you for judgment when they ЋєalreadyЋЇ have the Torah containing AllahвАЩs judgment, then they turn away after all? They are not ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  5,44,"Indeed, We revealed the Torah, containing guidance and light, by which the prophets, who submitted themselves to Allah, made judgments for Jews. So too did the rabbis and scholars judge according to AllahвАЩs Book, with which they were entrusted and of which they were made keepers. So do not fear the people; fear Me! Nor trade my revelations for a fleeting gain. And those who do not judge by what Allah has revealed are ЋєtrulyЋЇ the disbelievers"
  5,45,"We ordained for them in the Torah, вАЬA life for a life, an eye for an eye, a nose for a nose, an ear for an ear, a tooth for a toothвАФand for wounds equal retaliation.вАЭ But whoever waives it charitably, it will be atonement for them. And those who do not judge by what Allah has revealed are ЋєtrulyЋЇ the wrongdoers"
  5,46,"Then in the footsteps of the prophets, We sent Jesus, son of Mary, confirming the Torah revealed before him. And We gave him the Gospel containing guidance and light and confirming what was revealed in the TorahвАФa guide and a lesson to the God-fearing"
  5,47,So let the people of the Gospel judge by what Allah has revealed in it. And those who do not judge by what Allah has revealed are ЋєtrulyЋЇ the rebellious
  5,48,"We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ this Book with the truth, as a confirmation of previous Scriptures and a supreme authority on them. So judge between them by what Allah has revealed, and do not follow their desires over the truth that has come to you. To each of you We have ordained a code of law and a way of life. If Allah had willed, He would have made you one community, but His Will is to test you with what He has given Ћєeach ofЋЇ you. So compete with one another in doing good. To Allah you will all return, then He will inform you Ћєof the truthЋЇ regarding your differences"
  5,49,"And judge between them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ by what Allah has revealed, and do not follow their desires. And beware, so they do not lure you away from some of what Allah has revealed to you. If they turn away Ћєfrom AllahвАЩs judgmentЋЇ, then know that it is AllahвАЩs Will to repay them for some of their sins, and that many people are indeed rebellious"
  5,50,Is it the judgment of Ћєpre-IslamicЋЇ ignorance they seek? Who could be a better judge than Allah for people of sure faith
  5,51,O believers! Take neither Jews nor Christians as guardiansвАФthey are guardians of each other.¬†Whoever does so will be counted as one of them. Surely Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people
  5,52,"You see those with sickness in their hearts racing for their guardianship, saying Ћєin justificationЋЇ, вАЬWe fear a turn of fortune will strike us.вАЭ But perhaps Allah will bring about ЋєyourЋЇ victory or another favour by His command, and they will regret what they have hidden in their hearts"
  5,53,"ЋєOnly then,ЋЇ the believers will ask Ћєone anotherЋЇ, вАЬAre these the ones who swore solemn oaths by Allah that they were with you?вАЭ Their deeds have been in vain, so they have become losers"
  5,54,"O believers! Whoever among you abandons their faith, Allah will replace them with others who love Him and are loved by Him. They will be humble with the believers but firm towards the disbelievers, struggling in the Way of Allah; fearing no blame from anyone. This is the favour of Allah. He grants it to whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing"
  5,55,"Your only guardians are Allah, His Messenger, and fellow believersвАФwho establish prayer and pay alms-tax¬†with humility"
  5,56,"Whoever allies themselves with Allah, His Messenger, and fellow believers, then it is certainly AllahвАЩs party that will prevail"
  5,57,O believers! Do not seek the guardianship of those given the Scripture before you and the disbelievers who have made your faith a mockery and amusement. And be mindful of Allah if you are ЋєtrulyЋЇ believers
  5,58,"When you call to prayer, they mock it in amusement. This is because they are a people without understanding"
  5,59,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO People of the Book! Do you resent us only because we believe in Allah and what has been revealed to us and what was revealed beforeвАФwhile most of you are rebellious?вАЭ"
  5,60,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬShall I inform you of those who deserve a worse punishment from Allah Ћєthan the rebelliousЋЇ? It is those who earned AllahвАЩs condemnation and displeasureвАФsome being reduced to apes and pigs¬†and worshippers of false gods. These are far worse in rank and farther astray from the Right Way.вАЭ"
  5,61,"When they come to you ЋєbelieversЋЇ they say, вАЬWe believe.вАЭ But they are committed to disbelief when they enter and when they leave. And Allah knows what they hide"
  5,62,"You see many of them racing towards sin, transgression, and consumption of forbidden gain. Evil indeed are their actions"
  5,63,Why do their rabbis and scholars not forbid them from saying what is sinful and consuming what is unlawful? Evil indeed is their inaction
  5,64,"ЋєSome amongЋЇ the Jews said, вАЬAllah is tight-fisted.вАЭ¬†May their fists be tied and they be condemned for what they said. Rather, He is open-handed, giving freely as He pleases. That which has been revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ from your Lord will only cause many of them to increase in wickedness and disbelief. We have stirred among them hostility and hatred until the Day of Judgment. Whenever they kindle the fire of war, Allah puts it out. And they strive to spread corruption in the land. And Allah does not like corruptors"
  5,65,"Had the People of the Book only been faithful and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, We would have certainly absolved them of their sins and admitted them into the Gardens of Bliss"
  5,66,"And had they observed the Torah, the Gospel, and what has been revealed to them from their Lord, they would have been overwhelmed with provisions from above and below. Some among them are upright, yet many do nothing but evil"
  5,67,"O Messenger! Convey everything revealed to you from your Lord. If you do not, then you have not delivered His message. Allah will ЋєcertainlyЋЇ protect you from the people. Indeed, Allah does not guide the people who disbelieve"
  5,68,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO People of the Book! You have nothing to stand on unless you observe the Torah, the Gospel, and what has been revealed to you from your Lord.вАЭ And your LordвАЩs revelation to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ will only cause many of them to increase in wickedness and disbelief. So do not grieve for the people who disbelieve"
  5,69,"Indeed, the believers, Jews, Sabians¬†and ChristiansвАФwhoever ЋєtrulyЋЇ believes in Allah and the Last Day and does good, there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  5,70,"Indeed, We took a covenant from the Children of Israel and sent them messengers. Whenever a messenger came to them with what they did not desire, they denied some and killed others"
  5,71,"They thought there would be no consequences, so they turned a blind eye and a deaf ear. Yet Allah turned to them in forgiveness Ћєafter their repentanceЋЇ, but again many became blind and deaf. And Allah is All-Seeing of what they do"
  5,72,"Those who say, вАЬAllah is the Messiah, son of Mary,вАЭ have certainly fallen into disbelief. The Messiah ЋєhimselfЋЇ said, вАЬO Children of Israel! Worship AllahвАФmy Lord and your Lord.вАЭ Whoever associates others with Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇ will surely be forbidden Paradise by Allah. Their home will be the Fire. And the wrongdoers will have no helpers"
  5,73,"Those who say, вАЬAllah is one in a Trinity,вАЭ have certainly fallen into disbelief. There is only One God. If they do not stop saying this, those who disbelieve among them will be afflicted with a painful punishment"
  5,74,"Will they not turn to Allah in repentance and seek His forgiveness? And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  5,75,"The Messiah, son of Mary, was no more than a messenger. ЋєManyЋЇ messengers had Ћєcome andЋЇ gone before him. His mother was a woman of truth. They both ate food.¬†See how We make the signs clear to them, yet see how they are deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  5,76,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHow can you worship besides Allah those who can neither harm nor benefit you? And Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing.вАЭ"
  5,77,"Say, вАЬO People of the Book! Do not go to extremes in your faith beyond the truth, nor follow the vain desires of those who went astray before ЋєyouЋЇ. They misled many and strayed from the Right Way.вАЭ"
  5,78,"The disbelievers among the Children of Israel were condemned in the revelations of David and Jesus, son of Mary. That was for their disobedience and violations"
  5,79,They did not forbid one another from doing evil. Evil indeed was what they did
  5,80,"You see many of them taking the disbelievers¬†as allies. Truly wicked are their misdeeds, which have earned them AllahвАЩs wrath. And they will be in everlasting torment"
  5,81,"Had they believed in Allah, the Prophet, and what has been revealed to him, they would have never taken those ЋєpagansЋЇ as allies. But most of them are rebellious"
  5,82,You will surely find the most bitter towards the believers to be the Jews and polytheists and the most gracious to be those who call themselves Christian. That is because there are priests and monks among them and because they are not arrogant
  5,83,"When they listen to what has been revealed to the Messenger, you see their eyes overflowing with tears for recognizing the truth. They say, вАЬOur Lord! We believe, so count us among the witnesses"
  5,84,Why should we not believe in Allah and the truth that has come to us? And we long for our Lord to include us in the company of the righteous.вАЭ
  5,85,"So Allah will reward them for what they said with Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. And that is the reward of the good-doers"
  5,86,"As for those who disbelieve and reject Our signs, they will be the residents of the Hellfire"
  5,87,"O believers! Do not forbid the good things which Allah has made lawful for you, and do not transgress. Indeed, Allah does not like transgressors"
  5,88,"Eat of the good, lawful things provided to you by Allah. And be mindful of Allah in Whom you believe"
  5,89,"Allah will not call you to account for your thoughtless oaths, but He will hold you accountable for deliberate oaths. The penalty for a broken oath is to feed ten poor people from what you normally feed your own family, or to clothe them, or to free a bondsperson. But if none of this is affordable, then you must fast three days. This is the penalty for breaking your oaths. So be mindful of your oaths. This is how Allah makes things clear to you, so perhaps you will be grateful"
  5,90,"O believers! Intoxicants, gambling, idols, and drawing lots for decisions¬†are all evil of SatanвАЩs handiwork. So shun them so you may be successful"
  5,91,SatanвАЩs plan is to stir up hostility and hatred between you with intoxicants and gambling and to prevent you from remembering Allah and praying. Will you not then abstain
  5,92,"Obey Allah and obey the Messenger and beware! But if you turn away, then know that Our MessengerвАЩs duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ clearly"
  5,93,"There is no blame on those who believe and do good for what they had consumed before Ћєthe prohibitionЋЇ, as long as they fear Allah, have faith, and do what is good; then they believe and act virtuously, then become fully mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ and do righteous deeds. For Allah loves the good-doers"
  5,94,O believers! Allah will surely test you with game within the reach of your hands and spears to distinguish those who fear Him in secret. Whoever transgresses from now on will suffer a painful punishment
  5,95,"O believers! Do not kill game while on pilgrimage. Whoever kills game intentionally must compensate by offering its equivalenceвАФas judged by two just men among youвАФto be offered at the Sacred House, or by feeding the needy, or by fasting so that they may taste the consequences of their violations. Allah has forgiven what has been done. But those who persist will be punished by Allah. And Allah is Almighty, capable of punishment"
  5,96,"It is lawful for you to hunt and eat seafood, as a provision for you and for travellers. But hunting on land is forbidden to you while on pilgrimage. Be mindful of Allah to Whom you all will be gathered"
  5,97,"Allah has made the KaвАЩbahвАФthe Sacred HouseвАФa sanctuary of well-being for all people, along with the sacred months, the sacrificial animals, and the Ћєofferings decorated withЋЇ garlands. All this so you may know that Allah knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth, and that He has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of everything"
  5,98,"Know that Allah is severe in punishment and that He is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  5,99,The MessengerвАЩs duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ. And Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what you reveal and what you conceal
  5,100,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬGood and evil are not equal, though you may be dazzled by the abundance of evil. So be mindful of Allah, O people of reason, so you may be successful.вАЭ"
  5,101,"O believers! Do not ask about any matter which, if made clear to you, may disturb you. But if you inquire about what is being revealed in the Quran, it will be made clear to you. Allah has forgiven what was done Ћєin the pastЋЇ.¬†And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Forbearing"
  5,102,Some people before you asked such questions then denied their answers
  5,103,"Allah has never ordained the Ћєso-calledЋЇ baбЄ•√Ѓrah, s√Ґ'ibah, waбє£√Ѓlah, and бЄ•√Ґm¬†camels.¬†But the disbelievers¬†just fabricate lies about Allah, and most of them lack understanding"
  5,104,"When it is said to them, вАЬCome to AllahвАЩs revelations and to the Messenger,вАЭ they reply, вАЬWhat we found our forefathers practicing is good enough for us.вАЭ ЋєWould they still do so,ЋЇ even if their forefathers had absolutely no knowledge or guidance"
  5,105,"O believers! You are accountable only for yourselves.¬†It will not harm you if someone chooses to deviateвАФas long as you are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided. To Allah you will all return, and He will inform you of what you used to do"
  5,106,"O believers! When death approaches any of you, call upon two just Muslim men to witness as you make a bequest; otherwise, two non-Muslims if you are afflicted with death while on a journey.¬†If you doubt Ћєtheir testimonyЋЇ, keep them after prayer and let them testify under oath ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬBy Allah! We would never sell our testimony for any price, even in favour of a close relative, nor withhold the testimony of Allah. Otherwise, we would surely be sinful.вАЭ"
  5,107,"If they are found guilty Ћєof false testimonyЋЇ, let the deceasedвАЩs two closest heirs affected by the bequest replace the witnesses and testify under oath ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬBy Allah! Our testimony is truer than theirs. We have not transgressed. Otherwise, we would surely be wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  5,108,In this way it is more likely that witnesses will give true testimony or else fear that their oaths could be refuted by those of the heirs. Be mindful of Allah and obey. For Allah does not guide the rebellious people
  5,109,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ the Day Allah will gather the messengers and say, вАЬWhat response did you receive?вАЭ They will reply, вАЬWe have no knowledge Ћєcompared to YouЋЇ! You ЋєaloneЋЇ are indeed the Knower of all unseen.вАЭ"
  5,110,"And Ћєon Judgment DayЋЇ Allah will say, вАЬO Jesus, son of Mary! Remember My favour upon you and your mother: how I supported you with the holy spirit¬†so you spoke to people in ЋєyourЋЇ infancy and adulthood. How I taught you writing, wisdom, the Torah, and the Gospel. How you moulded a bird from clayвАФby My WillвАФand breathed into it and it became a ЋєrealЋЇ birdвАФby My Will. How you healed the blind and the lepersвАФby My Will. How you brought the dead to lifeвАФby My Will. How I prevented the Children of Israel from harming you when you came to them with clear proofs and the disbelievers among them said, вАЬThis is nothing but pure magic.вАЭ"
  5,111,"And how I inspired the disciples, вАЬBelieve in Me and My messenger!вАЭ They declared, вАЬWe believe and bear witness that we fully submit Ћєto AllahЋЇ.вАЭ"
  5,112,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the disciples asked, вАЬO Jesus, son of Mary! Would your Lord be willing to send down to us a table spread with food from heaven?вАЭ Jesus answered, вАЬFear Allah if you are ЋєtrulyЋЇ believers.вАЭ"
  5,113,"They said, вАЬWe ЋєonlyЋЇ wish to eat from it to reassure our hearts, to verify you are indeed truthful to us, and to become its witnesses.вАЭ"
  5,114,"Jesus, son of Mary, prayed, вАЬO Allah, our Lord! Send us from heaven a table spread with food as a feast for usвАФthe first and last of usвАФand as a sign from You. Provide for us! You are indeed the Best Provider.вАЭ"
  5,115,"Allah answered, вАЬI am sending it down to you. But whoever among you denies afterwards will be subjected to a torment I have never inflicted on anyone of My creation.вАЭ"
  5,116,"And Ћєon Judgment DayЋЇ Allah will say, вАЬO Jesus, son of Mary! Did you ever ask the people to worship you and your mother as gods besides Allah?вАЭ He will answer, вАЬGlory be to You! How could I ever say what I had no right to say? If I had said such a thing, you would have certainly known it. You know what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ within me, but I do not know what is within You. Indeed, You ЋєaloneЋЇ are the Knower of all unseen"
  5,117,"I never told them anything except what You ordered me to say: вАЬWorship AllahвАФmy Lord and your Lord!вАЭ And I was witness over them as long as I remained among them. But when You took me,¬†You were the Witness over themвАФand You are a Witness over all things"
  5,118,"If You punish them, they belong to You after all.¬†But if You forgive them, You are surely the Almighty, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  5,119,"Allah will declare, вАЬThis is the Day when ЋєonlyЋЇ the faithful will benefit from their faithfulness. Theirs are Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. That is the ultimate triumph.вАЭ"
  5,120,To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything within. And He is Most Capable of everything
  6,1,All praise is for Allah Who created the heavens and the earth and made darkness and light.¬†Yet the disbelievers set up equals to their Lord Ћєin worshipЋЇ
  6,2,"He is the One Who created you from clay,¬†then appointed a term Ћєfor your deathЋЇ and another known only to Him Ћєfor your resurrectionЋЇвАФyet you continue to doubt"
  6,3,"He is the Only True God in the heavens and the earth. He knows whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal, and knows whatever you do"
  6,4,"Whenever a sign comes to them from their Lord, they turn away from it"
  6,5,"They have indeed rejected the truth when it came to them, so they will soon face the consequences of their ridicule"
  6,6,Have they not seen how many ЋєdisbelievingЋЇ peoples¬†We destroyed before them? We had made them more established in the land than you. We sent down abundant rain for them and made rivers flow at their feet. Then We destroyed them for their sins and replaced them with other peoples
  6,7,"Had We sent down to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ a revelation in writing and they were to touch it with their own hands, the disbelievers would still have said, вАЬThis is nothing but pure magic!вАЭ"
  6,8,"They say, вАЬWhy has no ЋєvisibleЋЇ angel come with him?вАЭ Had We sent down an angel, the matter would have certainly been settled Ћєat onceЋЇ,¬†and they would have never been given more time Ћєto repentЋЇ"
  6,9,"And if We had sent an angel, We would have certainly made it Ћєassume the form ofЋЇ a manвАФleaving them more confused than they already are"
  6,10,"ЋєOtherЋЇ messengers had already been ridiculed before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, but those who mocked them were overtaken by what they used to ridicule"
  6,11,"Say, вАЬTravel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers.вАЭ"
  6,12,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬTo whom belongs everything in the heavens and the earth?вАЭ Say, вАЬTo Allah!вАЭ He has taken upon Himself to be Merciful. He will certainly gather Ћєall ofЋЇ you together for the Day of JudgmentвАФabout which there is no doubt. But those who have ruined themselves will never believe"
  6,13,"To Him belongs whatever exists in the day and night. And He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  6,14,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWill I take any guardian other than Allah, the Originator of the heavens and the earth, Who provides for all and is not in need of provision?вАЭ Say, вАЬI have been commanded to be the first to submit and not be one of the polytheists.вАЭ"
  6,15,"Say, вАЬI truly fearвАФif I were to disobey my LordвАФthe torment of a tremendous Day.вАЭ"
  6,16,Whoever is spared the torment of that Day will have certainly been shown AllahвАЩs mercy. And that is the absolute triumph
  6,17,"If Allah touches you with harm, none can undo it except Him. And if He touches you with a blessing, He is Most Capable of everything"
  6,18,"He reigns supreme over His creation. And He is the All-Wise, All-Aware"
  6,19,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWho is the best witness?вАЭ Say, вАЬAllah is! He is a Witness between me and you. And this Quran has been revealed to me so that, with it, I may warn you and whoever it reaches. Do you ЋєpagansЋЇ testify that there are other gods besides Allah?вАЭ ЋєThenЋЇ say, вАЬI will never testify Ћєto thisЋЇ!вАЭ ЋєAndЋЇ say, вАЬThere is only One God. And I totally reject whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you associate with Him.вАЭ"
  6,20,Those to whom We gave the Scripture recognize him Ћєto be a true prophetЋЇ as they recognize their own children. Those who have ruined themselves will never believe
  6,21,"Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against Allah or deny His signs? Indeed, the wrongdoers will never succeed"
  6,22,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ the Day We will gather them all together then ask those who associated others Ћєwith Allah in worshipЋЇ, вАЬWhere are those gods you used to claim?вАЭ"
  6,23,"Their only argument will be: вАЬBy Allah, our Lord! We were never polytheists.вАЭ"
  6,24,See how they will lie about themselves and how those ЋєgodsЋЇ they fabricated will fail them
  6,25,"There are some of them who Ћєpretend toЋЇ listen to your recitation Ћєof the QuranЋЇ, but We have cast veils over their heartsвАФleaving them unable to comprehend itвАФand deafness in their ears. Even if they were to see every sign, they still would not believe in them. The disbelievers would ЋєevenЋЇ come to argue with you, saying, вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ is nothing but ancient fables!вАЭ"
  6,26,"They turn others away from the Prophet and distance themselves as well. They ruin none but themselves, yet they fail to perceive it"
  6,27,"If only you could see when they will be detained before the Fire! They will cry, вАЬOh! If only we could be sent back, we would never deny the signs of our Lord and we would ЋєsurelyЋЇ be of the believers.вАЭ"
  6,28,"But no! ЋєThey only say thisЋЇ because the truth they used to hide will become all too clear to them. Even if they were to be sent back, they would certainly revert to what they were forbidden. Indeed they are liars"
  6,29,"They insisted, вАЬThere is nothing beyond this worldly life and we will never be resurrected.вАЭ"
  6,30,"But if only you could see when they will be detained before their Lord! He will ask ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬIs this ЋєHereafterЋЇ not the truth?вАЭ They will cry, вАЬAbsolutely, by our Lord!вАЭ He will say, вАЬThen taste the punishment for your disbelief.вАЭ"
  6,31,"Losers indeed are those who deny the meeting with Allah until the Hour takes them by surprise, then they will cry, вАЬWoe to us for having ignored this!вАЭ They will bear Ћєthe burden ofЋЇ their sins on their backs. Evil indeed is their burden"
  6,32,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement, but far better is the ЋєeternalЋЇ Home of the Hereafter for those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ. Will you not then understand"
  6,33,We certainly know that what they say grieves you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. It is not your honesty they questionвАФit is AllahвАЩs signs that the wrongdoers deny
  6,34,"Indeed, messengers before you were rejected but patiently endured rejection and persecution until Our help came to them. And AllahвАЩs promise Ћєto helpЋЇ is never broken. And you have already received some of the narratives of these messengers"
  6,35,"If you find their denial unbearable, then buildвАФif you canвАФa tunnel through the earth or stairs to the sky to bring them a Ћєmore compellingЋЇ sign. Had Allah so willed, He could have guided them all. So do not be one of those ignorant Ћєof this factЋЇ"
  6,36,"Only the attentive will respond Ћєto your callЋЇ. As for the dead, Allah will raise them up, then to Him they will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  6,37,"They ask, вАЬWhy has no ЋєotherЋЇ sign been sent down to him from his Lord?вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAllah certainly has the power to send down a signвАЭвАФthough most of them do not know"
  6,38,All living beings roaming the earth and winged birds soaring in the sky are communities like yourselves.¬†We have left nothing out of the Record.¬†Then to their Lord they will be gathered all together
  6,39,Those who deny Our signs are ЋєwilfullyЋЇ deaf and dumbвАФlost in darkness. Allah leaves whoever He wills to stray and guides whoever He wills to the Straight Way
  6,40,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬImagine if you were overwhelmed by AllahвАЩs torment or the HourвАФwould you call upon any other than Allah Ћєfor helpЋЇ? ЋєAnswer meЋЇ if your claims are true"
  6,41,"No! He is the only One you would call. And if He willed, He could remove the affliction that made you invoke Him. Only then will you forget whatever you associate with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ.вАЭ"
  6,42,"Indeed, We have sent messengers before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to other people who We put through suffering and adversity Ћєfor their denialЋЇ, so perhaps they would be humbled"
  6,43,"Why did they not humble themselves when We made them suffer? Instead, their hearts were hardened, and Satan made their misdeeds appealing to them"
  6,44,"When they became oblivious to warnings, We showered them with everything they desired. But just as they became prideful of what they were given, We seized them by surprise, then they instantly fell into despair"
  6,45,So the wrongdoers were utterly uprooted. And all praise is for AllahвАФLord of all worlds
  6,46,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬImagine if Allah were to take away your hearing or sight, or seal your heartsвАФwho else other than Allah could restore it?вАЭ See ЋєO ProphetЋЇ how We vary the signs, yet they still turn away"
  6,47,"Ask, вАЬImagine if AllahвАЩs punishment were to overwhelm you with or without warningвАФwho would be destroyed other than the wrongdoers?вАЭ"
  6,48,"We have sent messengers only as deliverers of good news and as warners. Whoever believes and does good, there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  6,49,But those who deny Our signs will be afflicted with punishment for their rebelliousness
  6,50,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI do not say to you that I possess AllahвАЩs treasuries or know the unseen, nor do I claim to be an angel. I only follow what is revealed to me.вАЭ Say, вАЬAre those blind Ћєto the truthЋЇ equal to those who can see? Will you not then reflect?вАЭ"
  6,51,Warn with this ЋєQuranЋЇ those who are awed by the prospect of being gathered before their LordвАФwhen they will have no protector or intercessor besides HimвАФso perhaps they will be mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ
  6,52,"ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Do not dismiss those Ћєpoor believersЋЇ who invoke their Lord morning and evening, seeking His pleasure.¬†You are not accountable for them whatsoever, nor are they accountable for you. So do not dismiss them, or you will be one of the wrongdoers"
  6,53,"In this way We have tested some by means of others, so those ЋєdisbelieversЋЇ may say, вАЬHas Allah favoured these Ћєpoor believersЋЇ out of all of us?вАЭ Does Allah not best recognize the grateful"
  6,54,"When the believers in Our revelations come to you, say, вАЬPeace be upon you! Your Lord has taken upon Himself to be Merciful. Whoever among you commits evil ignorantly Ћєor recklesslyЋЇ then repents afterwards and mends their ways, then Allah is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  6,55,"This is how We make Our signs clear, so the way of the wicked may become distinct"
  6,56,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI have been forbidden to worship those you invoke besides Allah.вАЭ Say, вАЬI will not follow your desires, for I then would certainly be astray and not one of those ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided.вАЭ"
  6,57,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIndeed, I stand on a clear proof from my LordвАФyet you have denied it. That ЋєtormentЋЇ you seek to hasten is not within my power. It is only Allah Who decides Ћєits timeЋЇ. He declares the truth. And He is the Best of Judges.вАЭ"
  6,58,"Say ЋєalsoЋЇ, вАЬIf what you seek to hasten were within my power, the matter between us would have already been settled. But Allah knows the wrongdoers best.вАЭ"
  6,59,"With Him are the keys of the unseenвАФno one knows them except Him.¬†And He knows what is in the land and sea. Not even a leaf falls without His knowledge, nor a grain in the darkness of the earth or anythingвАФgreen or dryвАФbut is ЋєwrittenЋЇ in a perfect Record"
  6,60,"He is the One Who calls back your souls by night and knows what you do by day, then revives you daily to complete your appointed term. To Him is your ЋєultimateЋЇ return, then He will inform you of what you used to do"
  6,61,"He reigns supreme over all of His creation, and sends recording-angels, watching over you. When death comes to any of you, Our angels take their soul, never neglecting this duty"
  6,62,Then they are ЋєallЋЇ returned to AllahвАФtheir True Master. Judgment is His ЋєaloneЋЇ. And He is the Swiftest Reckoner
  6,63,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWho rescues you from the darkest times on land and at sea? He ЋєaloneЋЇ you call upon with humility, openly and secretly: вАЬIf You rescue us from this, we will be ever grateful.вАЭ"
  6,64,"Say, вАЬЋєOnlyЋЇ Allah rescues you from this and any other distress, yet you associate others with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ.вАЭ"
  6,65,"Say, вАЬHe ЋєaloneЋЇ has the power to unleash upon you a torment from above or below you or split you into ЋєconflictingЋЇ factions and make you taste the violence of one another.вАЭ See how We vary the signs, so perhaps they will comprehend"
  6,66,"Still your people ЋєO ProphetЋЇ have rejected this ЋєQuranЋЇ, although it is the truth. Say, вАЬI am not a keeper over you.вАЭ"
  6,67,Every ЋєdestinedЋЇ matter has a ЋєsetЋЇ time to transpire. And you will soon come to know
  6,68,"And when you come across those who ridicule Our revelations, do not sit with them unless they engage in a different topic. Should Satan make you forget, then once you remember, do not Ћєcontinue toЋЇ sit with the wrongdoing people"
  6,69,"Those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ will not be accountable for those Ћєwho ridicule itЋЇ whatsoeverвАФtheir duty is to advise, so perhaps the ridiculers will abstain"
  6,70,"And leave those who take this¬†faith Ћєof IslamЋЇ as mere play and amusement and are deluded by ЋєtheirЋЇ worldly life. Yet remind them by this ЋєQuranЋЇ, so no one should be ruined for their misdeeds. They will have no protector or intercessor other than Allah. Even if they were to offer every ЋєpossibleЋЇ ransom, none will be accepted from them. Those are the ones who will be ruined for their misdeeds. They will have a boiling drink and painful punishment for their disbelief"
  6,71,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬShould we invoke, other than Allah, those ЋєidolsЋЇ which cannot benefit or harm us, and turn back to disbelief after Allah has guided us? ЋєIf we do so, we will beЋЇ like those disoriented by devils in the wilderness, while their companions call them to guidance, ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАШCome to us!вАЩ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAllahвАЩs guidance is the ЋєonlyЋЇ true guidance. And we are commanded to submit to the Lord of all worlds"
  6,72,"establish prayer, and be mindful of Him. To Him you will all be gathered together"
  6,73,"He is the One Who created the heavens and the earth in truth. On the Day Ћєof JudgmentЋЇ He will say, вАШBe!вАЩ And there will be! His command is truth. All authority is His ЋєaloneЋЇ¬†on the Day the Trumpet will be blown.¬†He is the Knower of allвАФseen or unseen. And He is the All-Wise, All-Aware.вАЭ"
  6,74,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Abraham said to his father, »Вzar, вАЬDo you take idols as gods? It is clear to me that you and your people are entirely misguided.вАЭ"
  6,75,"We also showed Abraham the wonders of the heavens and the earth, so he would be sure in faith"
  6,76,"When the night grew dark upon him, he saw a star and said, вАЬThis is my Lord!вАЭ But when it set, he said, вАЬI do not love things that set.вАЭ"
  6,77,"Then when he saw the moon rising, he said, вАЬThis one is my Lord!вАЭ But when it disappeared, he said, вАЬIf my Lord does not guide me, I will certainly be one of the misguided people.вАЭ"
  6,78,"Then when he saw the sun shining, he said, вАЬThis must be my LordвАФit is the greatest!вАЭ But again when it set, he declared, вАЬO my people! I totally reject whatever you associate Ћєwith Allah in worshipЋЇ"
  6,79,I have turned my face towards the One Who has originated the heavens and the earthвАФbeing uprightвАФand I am not one of the polytheists.вАЭ
  6,80,"And his people argued with him. He responded, вАЬAre you arguing with me about Allah, while He has guided me? I am not afraid of whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you associate with HimвАФЋєnone can harm me,ЋЇ unless my Lord so wills. My Lord encompasses everything in ЋєHisЋЇ knowledge. Will you not be mindful"
  6,81,"And how should I fear your associate-gods, while you have no fear in associating ЋєothersЋЇ with AllahвАФa practice He has never authorized? Which side has more right to security? ЋєTell meЋЇ if you really know!вАЭ"
  6,82,It is ЋєonlyЋЇ those who are faithful and do not tarnish their faith with falsehood¬†who are guaranteed security and are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  6,83,"This was the argument We gave Abraham against his people. We elevate in rank whoever We please. Surely your Lord is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,84,"And We blessed him with Isaac and Jacob. We guided them all as We previously guided Noah and those among his descendants: David, Solomon, Job, Joseph, Moses, and Aaron. This is how We reward the good-doers"
  6,85,"Likewise, ЋєWe guidedЋЇ Zachariah, John, Jesus, and Elias, who were all of the righteous"
  6,86,"ЋєWe also guidedЋЇ Ishmael, Elisha, Jonah, and Lot, favouring each over other people Ћєof their timeЋЇ"
  6,87,"And ЋєWe favouredЋЇ some of their forefathers, their descendants, and their brothers. We chose them and guided them to the Straight Path"
  6,88,"This is AllahвАЩs guidance with which He guides whoever He wills of His servants. Had they associated others with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ, their ЋєgoodЋЇ deeds would have been wasted"
  6,89,"Those were the ones to whom We gave the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood. But if these ЋєpagansЋЇ disbelieve in this ЋєmessageЋЇ, then We have already entrusted it to a people who will never disbelieve in it"
  6,90,"These ЋєprophetsЋЇ were ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided by Allah, so follow their guidance. Say, вАЬI ask no reward of you for this ЋєQuranЋЇвАФit is a reminder to the whole world.вАЭ"
  6,91,"And they¬†have not shown Allah His proper reverence when they said, вАЬAllah has revealed nothing to any human being.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWho then revealed the Book brought forth by Moses as a light and guidance for people, which you split into separate sheetsвАФrevealing some and hiding much? You have been taught Ћєthrough this QuranЋЇ what neither you nor your forefathers knew.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAllah Ћєrevealed itЋЇ!вАЭ Then leave them to amuse themselves with falsehood"
  6,92,This is a blessed Book which We have revealedвАФconfirming what came before itвАФso you may warn the Mother of Cities¬†and everyone around it. Those who believe in the Hereafter ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in it and guard their prayers
  6,93,"Who does more wrong than the one who fabricates lies against Allah or claims, вАЬI have received revelations!вАЭвАФalthough nothing was revealed to themвАФor the one who says, вАЬI can reveal the like of AllahвАЩs revelations!вАЭ? If you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ could only see the wrongdoers in the throes of death while the angels are stretching out their hands ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬGive up your souls! Today you will be rewarded with the torment of disgrace for telling lies about Allah and for being arrogant towards His revelations!вАЭ"
  6,94,ЋєTodayЋЇ you have come back to Us all alone as We created you the first timeвАФleaving behind everything We have provided you with. We do not see your intercessors with youвАФthose you claimed were AllahвАЩs partners Ћєin worshipЋЇ. All your ties have been broken and all your claims have let you down.вАЭ
  6,95,"Indeed, Allah is the One Who causes seeds and fruit stones to sprout. He brings forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living. That is Allah! How can you then be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  6,96,"He causes the dawn to break, and has made the night for rest and ЋєmadeЋЇ the sun and the moon Ћєto travelЋЇ with precision. That is the design of the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  6,97,And He is the One Who has made the stars as your guide through the darkness of land and sea. We have already made the signs clear for people who know
  6,98,"And He is the One Who originated you all from a single soul,¬†then assigned you a place to live and another to Ћєbe laid toЋЇ rest. We have already made the signs clear for people who comprehend"
  6,99,"And He is the One Who sends down rain from the skyвАФcausing all kinds of plants to growвАФproducing green stalks from which We bring forth clustered grain. And from palm trees come clusters of dates hanging within reach. ЋєThere areЋЇ also gardens of grapevines, olives, and pomegranates, similar Ћєin shapeЋЇ but dissimilar Ћєin tasteЋЇ. Look at their fruit as it yields and ripens! Indeed, in these are signs for people who believe"
  6,100,"Yet they associate the jinn¬†with Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇ, even though He created them, and they falsely attribute to Him sons¬†and daughters¬†out of ignorance. Glorified and Exalted is He above what they claim"
  6,101,ЋєHe isЋЇ the Originator of the heavens and earth. How could He have children when He has no mate? He created all things and has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of everything
  6,102,"That is AllahвАФyour Lord! There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. ЋєHe isЋЇ the Creator of all things, so worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. And He is the Maintainer of everything"
  6,103,"No vision can encompass Him, but He encompasses all vision. For He is the Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  6,104,"Indeed, there have come to you insights from your Lord. So whoever chooses to see, it is for their own good. But whoever chooses to be blind, it is to their own loss. And I am not a keeper over you"
  6,105,"And so We vary our signs to the extent that they will say, вАЬYou have studied Ћєprevious scripturesЋЇ,вАЭ¬†and We make this ЋєQuranЋЇ clear for people who know"
  6,106,ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Follow what is revealed to you from your LordвАФthere is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except HimвАФand turn away from the polytheists
  6,107,"Had Allah willed, they would not have been polytheists. We have not appointed you as their keeper, nor are you their maintainer"
  6,108,"ЋєO believers!ЋЇ Do not insult what they invoke besides Allah or they will insult Allah spitefully out of ignorance. This is how We have made each peopleвАЩs deeds appealing to them. Then to their Lord is their return, and He will inform them of what they used to do"
  6,109,"They swear by Allah their most solemn oaths that if a sign were to come to them, they would certainly believe in it. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬSigns are only with Allah.вАЭ What will make you ЋєbelieversЋЇ realize that even if a sign were to come to them, they still would not believe"
  6,110,"We turn their hearts and eyes away Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ as they refused to believe at first, leaving them to wander blindly in their defiance"
  6,111,"Even if We had sent them the angels, made the dead speak to them, and assembled before their own eyes every sign Ћєthey demandedЋЇ, they still would not have believedвАФunless Allah so willed. But most of them are ignorant Ћєof thisЋЇ"
  6,112,"And so We have made for every prophet enemiesвАФdevilish humans and jinnвАФwhispering to one another with elegant words of deception. Had it been your LordвАЩs Will, they would not have done such a thing. So leave them and their deceit"
  6,113,"so that the hearts of those who disbelieve in the Hereafter may be receptive to it, be pleased with it, and be persistent in their evil pursuits"
  6,114,"ЋєSay, O Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬShould I seek a judge other than Allah while He is the One Who has revealed for you the Book Ћєwith the truthЋЇ perfectly explained?вАЭ Those who were given the Scripture know that it has been revealed Ћєto youЋЇ from your Lord in truth. So do not be one of those who doubt"
  6,115,"The Word of your Lord has been perfected in truth and justice. None can change His Words. And He is the All-Hearing, All- Knowing"
  6,116,"ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ If you were to obey most of those on earth, they would lead you away from AllahвАЩs Way. They follow nothing but assumptions and do nothing but lie"
  6,117,"Indeed, your Lord knows best who has strayed from His Way and who is ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  6,118,So eat only of what is slaughtered in AllahвАЩs Name if you truly believe in His revelations
  6,119,Why should you not eat of what is slaughtered in AllahвАЩs Name when He has already explained to you what He has forbidden to youвАФexcept when compelled by necessity? Many ЋєdeviantsЋЇ certainly mislead others by their whims out of ignorance. Surely your Lord knows the transgressors best
  6,120,"Shun all sinвАФopen and secret. Indeed, those who commit sin will be punished for what they earn"
  6,121,"Do not eat of what is not slaughtered in AllahвАЩs Name. For that would certainly be Ћєan act ofЋЇ disobedience. Surely the devils whisper to their ЋєhumanЋЇ associates to argue with you.¬†If you were to obey them, then you ЋєtooЋЇ would be polytheists"
  6,122,"Can those who had been dead, to whom We gave life and a light with which they can walk among people, be compared to those in complete darkness from which they can never emerge?¬†That is how the misdeeds of the disbelievers have been made appealing to them"
  6,123,"And so We have placed in every society the most wicked to conspire in it. Yet they plot only against themselves, but they fail to perceive it"
  6,124,"Whenever a sign comes to them, they say, вАЬWe will never believe until we receive what AllahвАЩs messengers received.вАЭ Allah knows best where to place His message. The wicked will soon be overwhelmed by humiliation from Allah and a severe punishment for their evil plots"
  6,125,"Whoever Allah wills to guide, He opens their heart to Islam.¬†But whoever He wills to leave astray, He makes their chest tight and constricted as if they were climbing up into the sky. This is how Allah dooms those who disbelieve"
  6,126,That is your LordвАЩs PathвАФperfectly straight. We have already made the signs clear to those who are mindful
  6,127,"They will have the Home of Peace with their Lord, Who will be their Guardian because of what they used to do"
  6,128,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ the Day He will gather them ЋєallЋЇ together and say, вАЬO assembly of jinn! You misled humans in great numbers.вАЭ And their human associates will say, вАЬOur Lord! We benefited from each otherвАЩs company,¬†but now we have reached the term which You appointed for us.вАЭ ЋєThenЋЇ He will say, вАЬThe Fire is your home, yours to stay in forever, except whoever Allah wills to spare.вАЭ¬†Surely your Lord is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,129,This is how We make the wrongdoers ЋєdestructiveЋЇ allies of one another because of their misdeeds
  6,130,"ЋєAllah will ask,ЋЇ вАЬO assembly of jinn and humans! Did messengers not come from among you, proclaiming My revelations and warning you of the coming of this Day of yours?вАЭ They will say, вАЬWe confess against ourselves!вАЭ For they have been deluded by ЋєtheirЋЇ worldly life. And they will testify against themselves that they were disbelievers"
  6,131,This Ћєsending of the messengersЋЇ is because your Lord would never destroy a society for their wrongdoing while its people are unaware Ћєof the truthЋЇ
  6,132,They will each be assigned ranks according to their deeds. And your Lord is not unaware of what they do
  6,133,"Your Lord is the Self-Sufficient, Full of Mercy. If He wills, He can do away with you and replace you with whoever He wills, just as He produced you from the offspring of other people"
  6,134,"Indeed, what you have been promised will certainly come to pass. And you will have no escape"
  6,135,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO my people! Persist in your ways, for I ЋєtooЋЇ will persist in mine. You will soon know who will fare best in the end. Indeed, the wrongdoers will never succeed.вАЭ"
  6,136,"The pagans set aside for Allah a share of the crops and cattle He created, saying, вАЬThis ЋєportionЋЇ is for Allah,вАЭ so they claim, вАЬand this ЋєoneЋЇ for our associate-gods.вАЭ Yet the portion of their associate-gods is not shared with Allah while AllahвАЩs portion is shared with their associate-gods. What unfair judgment"
  6,137,"Likewise, the pagansвАЩ evil associates have made it appealing to them to kill their own childrenвАФonly leading to their destruction as well as confusion in their faith. Had it been AllahвАЩs Will, they would not have done such a thing. So leave them and their falsehood"
  6,138,"They say, вАЬThese cattle and crops are reservedвАФnone may eat them except those we permit,вАЭ so they claim. Some other cattle are exempted from labour and others are not slaughtered in AllahвАЩs NameвАФfalsely attributing lies to Him. He will repay them for their lies"
  6,139,"They ЋєalsoЋЇ say, вАЬThe offspring of this cattle is reserved for our males and forbidden to our females; but if it is stillborn, they may all share it.вАЭ He will repay them for their falsehood. Surely He is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,140,Lost indeed are those who have murdered their own children foolishly out of ignorance and have forbidden what Allah has provided for themвАФfalsely attributing lies to Allah. They have certainly strayed and are not ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  6,141,"He is the One Who produces gardensвАФboth cultivated and wildвАФand palm trees, crops of different flavours, olives, and pomegranatesвАФsimilar Ћєin shapeЋЇ, but dissimilar Ћєin tasteЋЇ. Eat of the fruit they bear and pay the dues at harvest, but do not waste. Surely He does not like the wasteful"
  6,142,"Some cattle are fit for labour, others are too small.¬†Eat of what Allah has provided for you and do not follow SatanвАЩs footsteps. Certainly, he is your sworn enemy"
  6,143,"ЋєAllah has createdЋЇ four pairs: a pair of sheep and a pair of goatsвАФask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬHas He forbidden Ћєto youЋЇ the two males or the two females or what is in the wombs of the two females? Tell me with knowledge, if what you say is true.вАЭвАФ"
  6,144,"and a pair of camels and a pair of oxen. Ask ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬHas He forbidden Ћєto youЋЇ the two males or the two females or what is in the wombs of the two females? Or were you present when Allah gave you this commandment?вАЭ Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against Allah to mislead others without ЋєanyЋЇ knowledge? Surely Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  6,145,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI do not find in what has been revealed to me anything forbidden to eat except carrion, running blood, swineвАФwhich is impureвАФor a sinful offering in the name of any other than Allah. But if someone is compelled by necessityвАФneither driven by desire nor exceeding immediate needвАФthen surely your Lord is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  6,146,"For those who are Jewish, We forbade every animal with undivided hoofs and the fat of oxen and sheep except what is joined to their backs or intestines or mixed with bone. In this way We rewarded them for their violations. And We are certainly truthful"
  6,147,"But if they deny you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, say, вАЬYour Lord is infinite in mercy, yet His punishment will not be averted from the wicked people.вАЭ"
  6,148,"The polytheists will argue, вАЬHad it been AllahвАЩs Will, neither we nor our forefathers would have associated others with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ or made anything unlawful.вАЭ Likewise, those before them rejected the truth until they tasted Our punishment. Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬDo you have any knowledge that you can produce for us? Surely you follow nothing but ЋєfalseЋЇ assumptions and you do nothing but lie.вАЭ"
  6,149,"Say, вАЬAllah has the most conclusive argument. Had it been His Will, He would have easily imposed guidance upon all of you.вАЭ"
  6,150,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬBring your witnesses who can testify that Allah has forbidden this.вАЭ If they ЋєfalselyЋЇ testify, do not testify with them. And do not follow the desires of those who deny Our proofs, disbelieve in the Hereafter, and set up equals with their Lord"
  6,151,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬCome! Let me recite to you what your Lord has forbidden to you: do not associate others with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ. ЋєDo not fail toЋЇ honour your parents. Do not kill your children for fear of poverty. We provide for you and for them. Do not come near indecencies, openly or secretly. Do not take a ЋєhumanЋЇ lifeвАФmade sacred by AllahвАФexcept with ЋєlegalЋЇ right.¬†This is what He has commanded you, so perhaps you will understand"
  6,152,"And do not come near the wealth of the orphanвАФunless intending to enhance itвАФuntil they attain maturity. Give full measure and weigh with justice. We never require of any soul more than what it can afford. Whenever you speak,¬†maintain justiceвАФeven regarding a close relative. And fulfil your covenant with Allah. This is what He has commanded you, so perhaps you will be mindful"
  6,153,"Indeed, that is My PathвАФperfectly straight. So follow it and do not follow other ways, for they will lead you away from His Way. This is what He has commanded you, so perhaps you will be conscious Ћєof AllahЋЇ.вАЭ"
  6,154,"Additionally, We gave Moses the Scripture, completing the favour upon those who do good, detailing everything, and as a guide and a mercy, so perhaps they would be certain of the meeting with their Lord"
  6,155,"This is a blessed Book We have revealed. So follow it and be mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, so you may be shown mercy"
  6,156,"You ЋєpagansЋЇ can no longer say, вАЬScriptures were only revealed to two groups before us and we were unaware of their teachings.вАЭ"
  6,157,"Nor can you say, вАЬIf only the Scriptures had been revealed to us, we would have been better guided than they.вАЭ Now there has come to you from your Lord a clear proofвАФa guide and mercy. Who then does more wrong than those who deny AllahвАЩs revelations and turn away from them? We will reward those who turn away from Our revelations with a dreadful punishment for turning away"
  6,158,"Are they awaiting the coming of the angels, or your Lord ЋєHimselfЋЇ, or some of your LordвАЩs ЋєmajorЋЇ signs? On the Day your LordвАЩs signs arrive, belief will not benefit those who did not believe earlier or those who did no good through their faith.¬†Say, вАЬKeep waiting! We too are waiting.вАЭ"
  6,159,"Indeed, you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are not responsible whatsoever for those who have divided their faith and split into sects. Their judgment rests only with Allah. And He will inform them of what they used to do"
  6,160,Whoever comes with a good deed will be rewarded tenfold. But whoever comes with a bad deed will be punished for only one. None will be wronged
  6,161,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬSurely my Lord has guided me to the Straight Path, a perfect way, the faith of Abraham, the upright, who was not one of the polytheists.вАЭ"
  6,162,"Say, вАЬSurely my prayer, my worship, my life, and my death are all for AllahвАФLord of all worlds"
  6,163,"He has no partner. So I am commanded, and so I am the first to submit.вАЭ"
  6,164,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬShould I seek a lord other than Allah while He is the Lord of everything?вАЭ No one will reap except what they sow. No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. Then to your Lord is your return, and He will inform you of your differences"
  6,165,"He is the One Who has placed you as successors on earth and elevated some of you in rank over others, so He may test you with what He has given you. Surely your Lord is swift in punishment, but He is certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  7,1,Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m-бєҐ√£d
  7,2,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a Book sent down to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФdo not let anxiety into your heart regarding itвАФso with it you may warn Ћєthe disbelieversЋЇ, and as a reminder to the believers"
  7,3,"Follow what has been sent down to you from your Lord, and do not take others as guardians besides Him. How seldom are you mindful"
  7,4,ЋєImagineЋЇ how many societies We have destroyed! Our torment took them by surprise Ћєwhile sleepingЋЇ at night or midday
  7,5,"Their only cryвАФwhen overwhelmed by Our tormentвАФwas, вАЬWe have indeed been wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  7,6,We will surely question those who received messengers and We will question the messengers ЋєthemselvesЋЇ
  7,7,Then We will give them a full account with sure knowledgeвАФfor We were never absent
  7,8,"The weighing on that Day will be just. As for those whose scale will be heavy Ћєwith good deedsЋЇ, ЋєonlyЋЇ they will be successful"
  7,9,"But those whose scale is light, they have doomed themselves for wrongfully denying Our signs"
  7,10,We have indeed established you on earth and provided you with a means of livelihood. ЋєYetЋЇ you seldom give any thanks
  7,11,"Surely We created you,¬†then shaped you, then said to the angels, вАЬProstrate before Adam,вАЭ so they all didвАФbut not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who refused to prostrate with the others"
  7,12,"Allah asked, вАЬWhat prevented you from prostrating when I commanded you?вАЭ He replied, вАЬI am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.вАЭ"
  7,13,"Allah said, вАЬThen get down from Paradise! It is not for you to be arrogant here. So get out! You are truly one of the disgraced.вАЭ"
  7,14,"He appealed, вАЬThen delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.вАЭ"
  7,15,"Allah said, вАЬYou are delayed Ћєuntil the appointed DayЋЇ.вАЭ"
  7,16,"He said, вАЬFor leaving me to stray I will lie in ambush for them on Your Straight Path"
  7,17,"I will approach them from their front, their back, their right, their left, and then You will find most of them ungrateful.вАЭ"
  7,18,"Allah said, вАЬGet out of Paradise! You are disgraced and rejected! I will certainly fill up Hell with you and your followers all together.вАЭ"
  7,19,"ЋєAllah said,ЋЇ вАЬO Adam! Live with your wife in Paradise and eat from wherever you please, but do not approach this tree, or else you will be wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  7,20,"Then Satan tempted them in order to expose what was hidden of their nakedness. He said, вАЬYour Lord has forbidden this tree to you only to prevent you from becoming angels or immortals.вАЭ"
  7,21,"And he swore to them, вАЬI am truly your sincere advisor.вАЭ"
  7,22,"So he brought about their fall through deception. And when they tasted of the tree, their nakedness was exposed to them, prompting them to cover themselves with leaves from Paradise. Then their Lord called out to them, вАЬDid I not forbid you from that tree and Ћєdid I notЋЇ tell you that Satan is your sworn enemy?вАЭ"
  7,23,"They replied, вАЬOur Lord! We have wronged ourselves. If You do not forgive us and have mercy on us, we will certainly be losers.вАЭ"
  7,24,"Allah said, вАЬDescend as enemies to each other.¬†You will find in the earth a residence and provision for your appointed stay.вАЭ"
  7,25,"He added, вАЬThere you will live, there you will die, and from there you will be resurrected.вАЭ"
  7,26,"O children of Adam! We have provided for you clothing to cover your nakedness and as an adornment. However, the best clothing is righteousness. This is one of AllahвАЩs bounties, so perhaps you will be mindful"
  7,27,O children of Adam! Do not let Satan deceive you as he tempted your parents out of Paradise and caused their cover to be removed in order to expose their nakedness. Surely he and his soldiers watch you from where you cannot see them. We have made the devils allies of those who disbelieve
  7,28,"Whenever they commit a shameful deed,¬†they say, вАЬWe found our forefathers doing it and Allah has commanded us to do it.вАЭ Say, вАЬNo! Allah never commands what is shameful. How can you attribute to Allah what you do not know?вАЭ"
  7,29,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬMy Lord has commanded uprightness and dedication Ћєto Him aloneЋЇ in worship, calling upon Him with sincere devotion. Just as He first brought you into being, you will be brought to life again.вАЭ"
  7,30,"He has guided some, while others are destined to stray. They have taken devils as their masters instead of AllahвАФthinking they are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  7,31,"O Children of Adam! Dress properly whenever you are at worship. Eat and drink, but do not waste. Surely He does not like the wasteful"
  7,32,"Ask, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWho has forbidden the adornments and lawful provisions Allah has brought forth for His servants?вАЭ Say, вАЬThey are for the enjoyment of the believers in this worldly life, but they will be exclusively theirs on the Day of Judgment.¬†This is how We make Our revelations clear for people of knowledge.вАЭ"
  7,33,"Say, вАЬMy Lord has only forbidden open and secret indecencies, sinfulness, unjust aggression, associating ЋєothersЋЇ with Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇвАФa practice He has never authorizedвАФand attributing to Allah what you do not know.вАЭ"
  7,34,"For each community there is an appointed term. When their time arrives, they can neither delay it for a moment, nor could they advance it"
  7,35,"O children of Adam! When messengers from among yourselves come to you reciting My revelationsвАФwhoever shuns evil and mends their ways, there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  7,36,But those who receive Our revelations with denial and arrogance will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever
  7,37,"Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against Allah or deny His revelations? They will receive what is destined for them,¬†until Our messenger-angels arrive to take their souls, asking them, вАЬWhere are those Ћєfalse godsЋЇ you used to invoke besides Allah?вАЭ They will cry, вАЬThey have failed us,вАЭ and they will confess against themselves that they were indeed disbelievers"
  7,38,"Allah will say, вАЬEnter the Fire along with the ЋєevilЋЇ groups of jinn and humans that preceded you.вАЭ Whenever a group enters Hell, it will curse the preceding one until they are all gathered inside, the followers will say about their leaders, вАЬOur Lord! They have misled us, so multiply their torment in the Fire.вАЭ He will answer, вАЬIt has already been multiplied for all, but you do not know.вАЭ"
  7,39,"Then the leaders will say to their followers, вАЬYou were no better than us! So taste the torment for what you used to commit.вАЭ"
  7,40,"Surely those who receive our revelations with denial and arrogance, the gates of heaven will not be opened for them, nor will they enter Paradise until a camel passes through the eye of a needle. This is how We reward the wicked"
  7,41,Hell will be their bed; flames will be their cover. This is how We reward the wrongdoers
  7,42,As for those who believe and do goodвАФWe never require of any soul more than what it can affordвАФit is they who will be the residents of Paradise. They will be there forever
  7,43,"We will remove whatever bitterness they had in their hearts.¬†Rivers will flow under their feet. And they will say, вАЬPraise be to Allah for guiding us to this. We would have never been guided if Allah had not guided us. The messengers of our Lord had certainly come with the truth.вАЭ It will be announced to them, вАЬThis is Paradise awarded to you for what you used to do.вАЭ"
  7,44,"The residents of Paradise will call out to the residents of the Fire, вАЬWe have certainly found our LordвАЩs promise to be true. Have you too found your LordвАЩs promise to be true?вАЭ They will reply, вАЬYes, we have!вАЭ Then a caller will announce to both, вАЬMay AllahвАЩs condemnation be upon the wrongdoers"
  7,45,"those who hindered ЋєothersЋЇ from AllahвАЩs Way, strived to make it ЋєappearЋЇ crooked, and disbelieved in the Hereafter.вАЭ"
  7,46,"There will be a barrier between Paradise and Hell. And on the heights Ћєof that barrierЋЇ will be people¬†who will recognize Ћєthe residents ofЋЇ both by their appearance.¬†They will call out to the residents of Paradise, вАЬPeace be upon you!вАЭ They will have not yet entered Paradise, but eagerly hope to"
  7,47,"When their eyes will turn towards the residents of Hell, they will pray, вАЬOur Lord! Do not join us with the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  7,48,"Those on the heights will call out to some Ћєtyrants in the FireЋЇ, who they will recognize by their appearance, saying, вАЬYour large numbers and arrogance are of no use ЋєtodayЋЇ"
  7,49,"Are these Ћєhumble believersЋЇ the ones you swore would never be shown AllahвАЩs mercy?вАЭ ЋєFinally, those on the heights will be told:ЋЇ вАЬEnter Paradise! There will be no fear for you, nor will you grieve.вАЭ"
  7,50,"The residents of the Fire will then cry out to the residents of Paradise, вАЬAid us with some water or any provision Allah has granted you.вАЭ They will reply, вАЬAllah has forbidden both to the disbelievers"
  7,51,"those who took this¬†faith Ћєof IslamЋЇ as mere amusement and play and were deluded by ЋєtheirЋЇ worldly life.вАЭ ЋєAllah will say,ЋЇ вАЬToday We will ignore them just as they ignored the coming of this Day of theirs and for rejecting Our revelations.вАЭ"
  7,52,We have certainly brought them a Book which We explained with knowledgeвАФa guide and mercy for those who believe
  7,53,"Do they only await the fulfilment Ћєof its warningЋЇ? The Day it will be fulfilled, those who ignored it before will say, вАЬThe messengers of our Lord certainly came with the truth. Are there any intercessors who can plead on our behalf? Or can we be sent back so we may do Ћєgood,ЋЇ unlike what we used to do?вАЭ They will have certainly ruined themselves, and whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ they fabricated will fail them"
  7,54,"Indeed your Lord is Allah Who created the heavens and the earth in six Days,¬†then established Himself on the Throne. He makes the day and night overlap in rapid succession. He created the sun, the moon, and the starsвАФall subjected by His command. The creation and the command belong to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. Blessed is AllahвАФLord of all worlds"
  7,55,Call upon your Lord humbly and secretly. Surely He does not like the transgressors
  7,56,"Do not spread corruption in the land after it has been set in order. And call upon Him with hope and fear. Indeed, AllahвАЩs mercy is always close to the good-doers"
  7,57,"He is the One Who sends the winds ushering in His mercy. When they bear heavy clouds, We drive them to a lifeless land and then cause rain to fall, producing every type of fruit. Similarly, We will bring the dead to life, so perhaps you will be mindful"
  7,58,"The fertile land produces abundantly by the Will of its Lord, whereas the infertile land hardly produces anything. This is how We vary ЋєOurЋЇ lessons to those who are thankful"
  7,59,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people. He said, вАЬO my people! Worship AllahвАФyou have no other god except Him. I truly fear for you the torment of a tremendous Day.вАЭ"
  7,60,"But the chiefs of his people said, вАЬWe surely see that you are clearly misguided.вАЭ"
  7,61,"He replied, вАЬO my people! I am not misguided! But I am a messenger from the Lord of all worlds"
  7,62,conveying to you my LordвАЩs messages and giving you ЋєsincereЋЇ advice. And I know from Allah what you do not know
  7,63,"Do you find it astonishing that a reminder should come to you from your Lord through one of your own, warning you, so you may beware and perhaps be shown mercy?вАЭ"
  7,64,"But they rejected him, so We saved him and those with him in the Ark, and drowned those who rejected Our signs. They were certainly a blind people"
  7,65,"And to the people of вАЩ√Вd We sent their brother H√їd. He said, вАЬO my people! Worship AllahвАФyou have no other god except Him. Will you not then fear Him?вАЭ"
  7,66,"The disbelieving chiefs of his people responded, вАЬWe surely see you as a fool, and we certainly think you are a liar.вАЭ"
  7,67,"H√їd replied, вАЬO my people! I am no fool! But I am a messenger from the Lord of all worlds"
  7,68,conveying to you my LordвАЩs messages. And I am your sincere advisor
  7,69,"Do you find it astonishing that a reminder should come to you from your Lord through one of your own so he may warn you? Remember that He made you successors after the people of Noah and increased you greatly in stature. So remember AllahвАЩs favours, so you may be successful.вАЭ"
  7,70,"They said, вАЬHave you come to us so that we would worship Allah alone and abandon what our forefathers used to worship? Then bring us what you threaten us with, if what you say is true!вАЭ"
  7,71,"He said, вАЬYou will certainly be subjected to your LordвАЩs torment and wrath. Do you dispute with me regarding the so-called gods which you and your forefathers have made upвАФa practice Allah has never authorized? Then wait! I too am waiting with you.вАЭ"
  7,72,So We saved him and those with him by Our mercy and uprooted those who denied Our signs. They were not believers
  7,73,"And to the people of Tham√їd We sent their brother бєҐ√ҐliбЄ•. He said, вАЬO my people! Worship AllahвАФyou have no other god except Him. A clear proof has come to you from your Lord: this is AllahвАЩs she-camel as a sign to you. So leave her to graze ЋєfreelyЋЇ on AllahвАЩs land and do not harm her, or else you will be overcome by a painful punishment"
  7,74,"Remember when He made you successors after вАЩ√Вd and established you in the landвАФЋєandЋЇ you built palaces on its plains and carved homes into mountains. So remember AllahвАЩs favours, and do not go about spreading corruption in the land.вАЭ"
  7,75,"The arrogant chiefs of his people asked the lowly who believed among them, вАЬAre you certain that бєҐ√ҐliбЄ• has been sent by his Lord?вАЭ They replied, вАЬWe certainly believe in what he has been sent with.вАЭ"
  7,76,"The arrogant said, вАЬWe surely reject what you believe in.вАЭ"
  7,77,"Then they killed the she-camelвАФdefying their LordвАЩs commandвАФand challenged ЋєбєҐ√ҐliбЄ•ЋЇ, вАЬBring us what you threaten us with, if you are ЋєtrulyЋЇ one of the messengers.вАЭ"
  7,78,"Then an ЋєoverwhelmingЋЇ earthquake struck them, and they fell lifeless in their homes"
  7,79,"So he turned away from them, saying, вАЬO my people! Surely I conveyed to you my LordвАЩs message and gave you ЋєsincereЋЇ advice, but you do not like ЋєsincereЋЇ advisors.вАЭ"
  7,80,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Lot scolded Ћєthe men ofЋЇ his people, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬDo you commit a shameful deed that no man has ever done before"
  7,81,You lust after men instead of women! You are certainly transgressors.вАЭ
  7,82,"But his peopleвАЩs only response was to say, вАЬExpel them from your land! They are a people who wish to remain chaste!вАЭ"
  7,83,"So We saved him and his family except his wife, who was one of the doomed"
  7,84,We poured upon them a rain Ћєof brimstoneЋЇ. See what was the end of the wicked
  7,85,"And to the people of Midian We sent their brother ShuвАЩaib. He said, вАЬO my people! Worship AllahвАФyou have no other god except Him. A clear proof has already come to you from your Lord. So give just measure and weight, do not defraud people of their property, nor spread corruption in the land after it has been set in order. This is for your own good, if you are ЋєtrulyЋЇ believers"
  7,86,"And do not lie in ambush on every roadвАФthreatening and hindering those who believe in Allah from His Path and striving to make it ЋєappearЋЇ crooked. Remember when you were few, then He increased you in number. And consider the fate of the corruptors"
  7,87,"If some of you do believe in what I have been sent with while others do not, then be patient until Allah judges between us. He is the Best of Judges.вАЭ"
  7,88,"The arrogant chiefs of his people threatened, вАЬO ShuвАЩaib! We will certainly expel you and your fellow believers from our land, unless you return to our faith.вАЭ He replied, вАЬEven if we hate it"
  7,89,"We would surely be fabricating a lie against Allah if we were to return to your faith after Allah has saved us from it. It does not befit us to return to it unless it is the Will of Allah, our Lord. Our Lord has encompassed everything in ЋєHisЋЇ knowledge. In Allah we trust. Our Lord! Judge between us and our people with truth. You are the best of those who judge.вАЭ"
  7,90,"The disbelieving chiefs of his people threatened, вАЬIf you follow ShuвАЩaib, you will surely be losers!вАЭ"
  7,91,Then an ЋєoverwhelmingЋЇ earthquake struck them and they fell lifeless in their homes
  7,92,Those who rejected ShuвАЩaib were Ћєwiped outЋЇ as if they had never lived there. Those who rejected ShuвАЩaib were the true losers
  7,93,"He turned away from them, saying, вАЬO my people! Indeed, I have delivered to you the messages of my Lord and gave you ЋєsincereЋЇ advice. How can I then grieve for those who chose to disbelieve?вАЭ"
  7,94,"Whenever We sent a prophet to a society, We afflicted its ЋєdisbelievingЋЇ people with suffering and adversity, so perhaps they would be humbled"
  7,95,"Then We changed their adversity to prosperity until they flourished and argued ЋєfalselyЋЇ, вАЬOur forefathers ЋєtooЋЇ had been visited by adversity and prosperity.вАЭ¬†So We seized them by surprise, while they were unaware"
  7,96,"Had the people of those societies been faithful and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, We would have overwhelmed them with blessings from heaven and earth. But they disbelieved, so We seized them for what they used to commit"
  7,97,Did the people of those societies feel secure that Our punishment would not come upon them by night while they were asleep
  7,98,Or did they feel secure that Our punishment would not come upon them by day while they were at play
  7,99,Did they feel secure against AllahвАЩs planning? None would feel secure from AllahвАЩs planning except the losers
  7,100,Is it not clear to those who take over the land after Ћєthe destruction ofЋЇ its former residents thatвАФif We willвАФWe can punish them ЋєtooЋЇ for their sins and seal their hearts so they will not hear Ћєthe truthЋЇ
  7,101,"We have narrated to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ some of the stories of those societies. Surely, their messengers came to them with clear proofs, but still they would not believe in what they had already denied. This is how Allah seals the hearts of the disbelievers"
  7,102,"We did not find most of them true to their covenant. Rather, We found most of them truly rebellious"
  7,103,"Then after them We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs, but they wrongfully rejected them. See what was the end of the corruptors"
  7,104,"And Moses said, вАЬO Pharaoh! I am truly a messenger from the Lord of all worlds"
  7,105,"obliged to say nothing about Allah except the truth. Indeed, I have come to you with clear proof from your Lord, so let the children of Israel go with me.вАЭ"
  7,106,"Pharaoh said, вАЬIf you have come with a sign, then bring it if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  7,107,So Moses threw down his staff andвАФbehold!вАФit became a real snake
  7,108,Then he drew his hand Ћєout of his collarЋЇ and it was ЋєshiningЋЇ white for all to see
  7,109,"The chiefs of PharaohвАЩs people said, вАЬHe is indeed a skilled magician"
  7,110,"who seeks to drive you from your land.вАЭ ЋєSo Pharaoh asked,ЋЇ вАЬWhat do you propose?вАЭ"
  7,111,"They replied, вАЬLet him and his brother wait and send mobilizers to all cities"
  7,112,to bring you every clever magician.вАЭ
  7,113,"The magicians came to Pharaoh, saying, вАЬShall we receive a ЋєsuitableЋЇ reward if we prevail?вАЭ"
  7,114,"He replied, вАЬYes, and you will certainly be among those closest to me.вАЭ"
  7,115,"They asked, вАЬO Moses! Will you cast, or shall we be the first to cast?вАЭ"
  7,116,"Moses said, вАЬYou first.вАЭ So when they did, they deceived the eyes of the people, stunned them, and made a great display of magic"
  7,117,"Then We inspired Moses, вАЬThrow down your staff,вАЭ andвАФbehold!вАФit devoured the objects of their illusion"
  7,118,So the truth prevailed and their illusions failed
  7,119,So Pharaoh and his people were defeated right there and put to shame
  7,120,"And the magicians fell down, prostrating"
  7,121,"They declared, вАЬWe ЋєnowЋЇ believe in the Lord of all worldsвАФ"
  7,122,the Lord of Moses and Aaron.вАЭ
  7,123,"Pharaoh threatened, вАЬHow dare you believe in him before I give you permission? This must be a conspiracy you devised in the city to drive out its people, but soon you will see"
  7,124,"I will certainly cut off your hands and feet on opposite sides, then crucify you all.вАЭ"
  7,125,"They responded, вАЬSurely to our Lord we will ЋєallЋЇ return"
  7,126,"Your rage towards us is only because we believed in the signs of our Lord when they came to us. Our Lord! Shower us with perseverance, and let us die while submitting Ћєto YouЋЇ.вАЭ"
  7,127,"The chiefs of PharaohвАЩs people protested, вАЬAre you going to leave Moses and his people free to spread corruption in the land and abandon you and your gods?вАЭ He responded, вАЬWe will kill their sons and keep their women.¬†We will completely dominate them.вАЭ"
  7,128,"Moses reassured his people, вАЬSeek AllahвАЩs help and be patient. Indeed, the earth belongs to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ. He grants it to whoever He chooses of His servants. The ultimate outcome belongs ЋєonlyЋЇ to the righteous.вАЭ"
  7,129,"They complained, вАЬWe have always been oppressedвАФbefore and after you came to us Ћєwith the messageЋЇ.вАЭ He replied, вАЬPerhaps your Lord will destroy your enemy and make you successors in the land to see what you will do.вАЭ"
  7,130,"Indeed, We afflicted PharaohвАЩs people with famine and shortage of crops so they might come back Ћєto their sensesЋЇ"
  7,131,"In times of prosperity, they said, вАЬThis is what we deserve,вАЭ but in adversity, they blamed it on Moses and those with him.¬†Surely all is destined by Allah. Yet most of them did not know"
  7,132,"They said, вАЬNo matter what sign you may bring to deceive us, we will never believe in you.вАЭ"
  7,133,"So We plagued them with floods, locusts, lice, frogs, and bloodвАФall as clear signs, but they persisted in arrogance and were a wicked people"
  7,134,"When tormented, they pleaded, вАЬO Moses! Pray to your Lord on our behalf, by virtue of the covenant He made with you. If you help remove this torment from us, we will certainly believe in you and let the Children of Israel go with you.вАЭ"
  7,135,But as soon as We removed the torment from themвАФuntil they met their inevitable fateвАФthey broke their promise
  7,136,"So We inflicted punishment upon them, drowning them in the sea for denying Our signs and being heedless of them"
  7,137,"And ЋєsoЋЇ We made the oppressed people successors of the eastern and western lands, which We had showered with blessings. ЋєIn this wayЋЇ the noble Word of your Lord was fulfilled for the Children of Israel for what they had endured. And We destroyed what Pharaoh and his people constructed and what they established"
  7,138,"We brought the Children of Israel across the sea and they came upon a people devoted to idols. They demanded, вАЬO Moses! Make for us a god like their gods.вАЭ He replied, вАЬIndeed, you are a people acting ignorantly"
  7,139,What they follow is certainly doomed to destruction and their deeds are in vain.вАЭ
  7,140,"He added, вАЬShall I seek for you a god other than Allah, while He has honoured you above the others?вАЭ"
  7,141,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We rescued you from the people of Pharaoh, who afflicted you with dreadful tormentвАФkilling your sons and keeping your women. That was a severe test from your Lord"
  7,142,"We appointed for Moses thirty nights then added another tenвАФcompleting his LordвАЩs term of forty nights. Moses commanded his brother Aaron, вАЬTake my place among my people, do what is right, and do not follow the way of the corruptors.вАЭ"
  7,143,"When Moses came at the appointed time and his Lord spoke to him, he asked, вАЬMy Lord! Reveal Yourself to me so I may see You.вАЭ Allah answered, вАЬYou cannot see Me! But look at the mountain. If it remains firm in its place, only then will you see Me.вАЭ When his Lord appeared to the mountain, He levelled it to dust and Moses collapsed unconscious. When he recovered, he cried, вАЬGlory be to You! I turn to You in repentance and I am the first of the believers.вАЭ"
  7,144,"Allah said, вАЬO Moses! I have ЋєalreadyЋЇ elevated you above all others by My messages and speech.¬†So hold firmly to what I have given you and be grateful.вАЭ"
  7,145,"We wrote for him on the Tablets Ћєthe fundamentalsЋЇ of everything; commandments and explanations of all things. ЋєWe commanded,ЋЇ вАЬHold to this firmly and ask your people to take the best of it.¬†I will soon show Ћєall ofЋЇ you the home of the rebellious"
  7,146,"I will turn away from My signs those who act unjustly with arrogance in the land. And even if they were to see every sign, they still would not believe in them. If they see the Right Path, they will not take it. But if they see a crooked path, they will follow it. This is because they denied Our signs and were heedless of them"
  7,147,The deeds of those who deny Our signs and the meeting Ћєwith AllahЋЇ in the Hereafter will be in vain. Will they be rewarded except for what they have done?вАЭ
  7,148,"In the absence of Moses, his people made from their ЋєgoldenЋЇ jewellery an idol of a calf that made a lowing sound. Did they not see that it could neither speak to them nor guide them to the ЋєRightЋЇ Path? Still they took it as a god and were wrongdoers"
  7,149,"Later, when they were filled with remorse and realized they had gone astray, they cried, вАЬIf our Lord does not have mercy on us and forgive us, we will certainly be losers.вАЭ"
  7,150,"Upon MosesвАЩ return to his people, ЋєtotallyЋЇ furious and sorrowful, he said, вАЬWhat an evil thing you committed in my absence! Did you want to hasten your LordвАЩs torment?вАЭ Then he threw down the Tablets and grabbed his brother by the hair, dragging him closer. Aaron pleaded, вАЬO son of my mother! The people overpowered me and were about to kill me. So do not Ћєhumiliate me andЋЇ make my enemies rejoice, nor count me among the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  7,151,"Moses prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Forgive me and my brother! And admit us into Your mercy. You are the Most Merciful of the merciful.вАЭ"
  7,152,Those who worshipped the calf will certainly be afflicted with AllahвАЩs wrath as well as disgrace in the life of this world. This is how We reward those who invent falsehood
  7,153,"But those who commit evil, then repent and become ЋєtrueЋЇ believers, your Lord will certainly be All-Forgiving, Most-Merciful"
  7,154,"When MosesвАЩ anger subsided, he took up the Tablets whose text contained guidance and mercy for those who stand in awe of their Lord"
  7,155,"Moses chose seventy men from among his people for Our appointment and, when they were seized by an earthquake,¬†he cried, вАЬMy Lord! Had You willed, You could have destroyed them long ago, and me as well. Will You destroy us for what the foolish among us have done? This is only a test from YouвАФby which You allow whoever you will to stray and guide whoever You will. You are our Guardian. So forgive us and have mercy on us. You are the best forgiver"
  7,156,"Ordain for us what is good in this life and the next. Indeed, we have turned to You Ћєin repentanceЋЇ.вАЭ Allah replied, вАЬI will inflict My torment on whoever I will. But My mercy encompasses everything. I will ordain mercy for those who shun evil, pay alms-tax, and believe in Our revelations"
  7,157,"вАЬЋєThey areЋЇ the ones who follow the Messenger, the unlettered Prophet, whose description they find in their Torah and the Gospel.¬†He commands them to do good and forbids them from evil, permits for them what is lawful and forbids to them what is impure, and relieves them from their burdens and the shackles that bound them. ЋєOnlyЋЇ those who believe in him, honour and support him, and follow the light sent down to him will be successful.вАЭ"
  7,158,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO humanity! I am AllahвАЩs Messenger to you all. To Him ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. He gives life and causes death.вАЭ So believe in Allah and His Messenger, the unlettered Prophet, who believes in Allah and His revelations. And follow him, so you may be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  7,159,There are some among the people of Moses who guide with the truth and establish justice accordingly
  7,160,"We divided them into twelve tribesвАФeach as a community. And We revealed to Moses, when his people asked for water, вАЬStrike the rock with your staff.вАЭ Then twelve springs gushed out. Each tribe knew its drinking place. We shaded them with clouds and sent down to them manna and quails,¬†ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬEat from the good things We have provided for you.вАЭ They ЋєcertainlyЋЇ did not wrong Us, but wronged themselves"
  7,161,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when it was said to them, вАЬEnter this city Ћєof JerusalemЋЇ and eat from wherever you please. Say, вАШAbsolve us,вАЩ and enter the gate with humility. We will forgive your sins, ЋєandЋЇ We will multiply the reward for the good-doers.вАЭ"
  7,162,But the wrongdoers among them changed the words they were commanded to say. So We sent down a punishment from the heavens upon them for their wrongdoing
  7,163,"Ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about Ћєthe people ofЋЇ the town which was by the sea, who broke the Sabbath.¬†During the Sabbath, ЋєabundantЋЇ fish would come to them clearly visible, but on other days the fish were never seen. In this way We tested them for their rebelliousness"
  7,164,"When some of Ћєthe righteous amongЋЇ them questioned Ћєtheir fellow Sabbath-keepersЋЇ, вАЬWhy do you Ћєbother toЋЇ warn those ЋєSabbath-breakersЋЇ who will either be destroyed or severely punished by Allah?вАЭ They replied, вАЬJust to be free from your LordвАЩs blame, and so perhaps they may abstain.вАЭ"
  7,165,"When they ignored the warning they were given, We rescued those who used to warn against evil and overtook the wrongdoers with a dreadful punishment for their rebelliousness"
  7,166,"But when they stubbornly persisted in violation, We said to them, вАЬBe disgraced apes!вАЭ"
  7,167,"And Ћєremember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when your Lord declared that He would send against them others who would make them suffer terribly until the Day of Judgment. Indeed, your Lord is swift in punishment, but He is certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  7,168,"We dispersed them through the land in groupsвАФsome were righteous, others were less so. We tested them with prosperity and adversity, so perhaps they would return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ"
  7,169,"Then they were succeeded by other generations who inherited the Scripture. They indulged in unlawful gains, claiming, вАЬWe will be forgiven Ћєafter allЋЇ.вАЭ And if similar gain came their way, they would seize it. Was a covenant not taken from them in the Scripture that they would not say anything about Allah except the truth? And they were already well-versed in its teachings. But the ЋєeternalЋЇ Home of the Hereafter is far better for those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ. Will you not then understand"
  7,170,As for those who firmly abide by the Scripture and establish prayerвАФsurely We never discount the reward of those acting righteously
  7,171,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We raised the mountain over them as if it were a cloud and they thought it would fall on them.¬†ЋєWe said,ЋЇ вАЬHold firmly to that ЋєScriptureЋЇ which¬†We have given you and observe its teachings so perhaps you will become mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ.вАЭ"
  7,172,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when your Lord brought forth from the loins of the children of Adam their descendants and had them testify regarding themselves. ЋєAllah asked,ЋЇ вАЬAm I not your Lord?вАЭ They replied, вАЬYes, You are! We testify.вАЭ ЋєHe cautioned,ЋЇ вАЬNow you have no right to say on Judgment Day, вАШWe were not aware of this.вАЩ"
  7,173,"Nor say, вАШIt was our forefathers who had associated others Ћєwith Allah in worshipЋЇ and we, as their descendants, followed in their footsteps. Will you then destroy us for the falsehood they invented?вАЩвАЭ"
  7,174,"This is how We make our signs clear, so perhaps they will return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ"
  7,175,"And relate to them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the story of the one to whom We gave Our signs, but he abandoned them, so Satan took hold of him, and he became a deviant"
  7,176,"If We had willed, We would have elevated him with Our signs, but he clung to this lifeвАФfollowing his evil desires. His example is that of a dog: if you chase it away, it pants, and if you leave it, it ЋєstillЋЇ pants. This is the example of the people who deny Our signs.¬†So narrate Ћєto themЋЇ stories Ћєof the pastЋЇ, so perhaps they will reflect"
  7,177,What an evil example of those who denied Our signs! They ЋєonlyЋЇ wronged their own souls
  7,178,"Whoever Allah guides is truly guided. And whoever He leaves to stray, they are the ЋєtrueЋЇ losers"
  7,179,"Indeed, We have destined many jinn and humans for Hell. They have hearts they do not understand with, eyes they do not see with, and ears they do not hear with. They are like cattle. In fact, they are even less guided! Such ЋєpeopleЋЇ are ЋєentirelyЋЇ heedless"
  7,180,"Allah has the Most Beautiful Names. So call upon Him by them, and keep away from those who abuse His Names.¬†They will be punished for what they used to do"
  7,181,And among those We created is a group that guides with the truth and establishes justice accordingly
  7,182,"As for those who deny Our signs, We will gradually draw them to destruction in ways they cannot comprehend"
  7,183,"I ЋєonlyЋЇ delay their end for a while, but My planning is flawless"
  7,184,Have they not ever given it a thought? Their fellow man¬†is not insane. He is only sent with a clear warning
  7,185,"Have they ever reflected on the wonders of the heavens and the earth, and everything Allah has created, and that perhaps their end is near? So what message after this ЋєQuranЋЇ would they believe in"
  7,186,"Whoever Allah allows to stray, none can guide, leaving them to wander blindly in their defiance"
  7,187,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ regarding the Hour, вАЬWhen will it be?вАЭ Say, вАЬThat knowledge is only with my Lord. He alone will reveal it when the time comes. It is too tremendous for the heavens and the earth and will only take you by surprise.вАЭ They ask you as if you had full knowledge of it. Say, вАЬThat knowledge is only with Allah, but most people do not know.вАЭ"
  7,188,"Say, вАЬI have no power to benefit or protect myself, except by the Will of Allah. If I had known the unknown, I would have benefited myself enormously, and no harm would have ever touched me. I am only a warner and deliverer of good news for those who believe.вАЭ"
  7,189,"He is the One Who created you from a single soul, then from it made its spouse so he may find comfort in her. After he had been united with her, she carried a light burden that developed gradually. When it grew heavy, they prayed to Allah, their Lord, вАЬIf you grant us good offspring, we will certainly be grateful.вАЭ"
  7,190,"But when He granted their descendants good offspring, they associated false gods in what He has given them. Exalted is Allah above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ"
  7,191,"Do they associate Ћєwith AllahЋЇ those ЋєidolsЋЇ which cannot create anything, but are in fact created"
  7,192,"which cannot help them, or even help themselves"
  7,193,"And if you ЋєidolatersЋЇ call upon them for guidance, they cannot respond to you. It is all the same whether you call them or remain silent"
  7,194,"Those ЋєidolsЋЇ you invoke besides Allah are created beings like yourselves. So call upon them and see if they will answer you, if your claims are true"
  7,195,"Do they have feet to walk with? Or hands to hold with? Or eyes to see with? Or ears to hear with? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬCall upon your associate-gods and conspire against me without delay"
  7,196,"вАЬIndeed, my Protector is Allah Who has revealed this Book. For He ЋєaloneЋЇ protects the righteous"
  7,197,But those Ћєfalse godsЋЇ you call besides Him can neither help you nor even themselves.вАЭ
  7,198,"If you ЋєidolatersЋЇ call them to guidance, they cannot hear. And you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ may see them facing towards you, but they cannot see"
  7,199,"Be gracious, enjoin what is right, and turn away from those who act ignorantly"
  7,200,"If you are tempted by Satan, then seek refuge with Allah. Surely He is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  7,201,"Indeed, when Satan whispers to those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, they remember Ћєtheir LordЋЇ then they start to see ЋєthingsЋЇ clearly"
  7,202,"But the devils persistently plunge their ЋєhumanЋЇ associates¬†deeper into wickedness, sparing no effort"
  7,203,"If you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ do not bring them a sign Ћєwhich they demandedЋЇ, they ask, вАЬWhy do you not make it yourself?вАЭ Say, вАЬI only follow what is revealed to me from my Lord. This ЋєQuranЋЇ is an insight from your LordвАФa guide and a mercy for those who believe.вАЭ"
  7,204,"When the Quran is recited, listen to it attentively and be silent, so you may be shown mercy"
  7,205,"Remember your Lord inwardly with humility and reverence and in a moderate tone of voice, both morning and evening. And do not be one of the heedless"
  7,206,Surely those ЋєangelsЋЇ nearest to your Lord are not too proud to worship Him. They glorify Him. And to Him they prostrate
  8,1,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ regarding the spoils of war. Say, вАЬTheir distribution is decided by Allah and His Messenger. So be mindful of Allah, settle your affairs, and obey Allah and His Messenger if you are ЋєtrueЋЇ believers.вАЭ"
  8,2,"The ЋєtrueЋЇ believers are only those whose hearts tremble at the remembrance of Allah, whose faith increases when His revelations are recited to them, and who put their trust in their Lord"
  8,3,ЋєThey areЋЇ those who establish prayer and donate from what We have provided for them
  8,4,"It is they who are the true believers. They will have elevated ranks, forgiveness, and an honourable provision from their Lord"
  8,5,"Similarly, when your Lord brought you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ out of your home for a just cause, a group of believers was totally against it"
  8,6,"They disputed with you about the truth after it had been made clear, as if they were being driven to death with their eyes wide open"
  8,7,"ЋєRemember, O believers,ЋЇ when Allah promised Ћєto giveЋЇ you the upper hand over either target, you wished to capture the unarmed party.¬†But it was AllahвАЩs Will¬†to establish the truth by His Words and uproot the disbelievers"
  8,8,to firmly establish the truth and wipe out falsehoodвАФeven to the dismay of the wicked
  8,9,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when you cried out to your Lord for help, He answered, вАЬI will reinforce you with a thousand angelsвАФfollowed by many others.вАЭ"
  8,10,"And Allah made this a sign of victory and reassurance to your hearts. Victory comes only from Allah. Surely Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,11,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when He caused drowsiness to overcome you, giving you serenity.¬†And He sent down rain from the sky to purify you, free you from SatanвАЩs whispers, strengthen your hearts, and make ЋєyourЋЇ steps firm"
  8,12,"ЋєRemember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when your Lord revealed to the angels, вАЬI am with you. So make the believers stand firm. I will cast horror into the hearts of the disbelievers. So strike their necks and strike their fingertips.вАЭ"
  8,13,"This is because they defied Allah and His Messenger. And whoever defies Allah and His Messenger, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ Allah is surely severe in punishment"
  8,14,"That Ћєworldly punishmentЋЇ is yours, so taste it! Then the disbelievers will suffer the torment of the Fire"
  8,15,"O believers! When you face the disbelievers in battle, never turn your backs to them"
  8,16,"And whoever does so on such an occasionвАФunless it is a manoeuvre or to join their own troopsвАФwill earn the displeasure of Allah, and their home will be Hell. What an evil destination"
  8,17,"It was not you ЋєbelieversЋЇ who killed them, but it was Allah Who did so. Nor was it you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who threw Ћєa handful of sand at the disbelieversЋЇ,¬†but it was Allah Who did so, rendering the believers a great favour. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,18,"As such, Allah frustrates the evil plans of the disbelievers"
  8,19,"If you ЋєMeccansЋЇ sought judgment, now it has come to you. And if you cease, it will be for your own good. But if you persist, We will persist. And your forcesвАФno matter how numerous they might beвАФwill not benefit you whatsoever. For Allah is certainly with the believers"
  8,20,O believers! Obey Allah and His Messenger and do not turn away from him while you hear Ћєhis callЋЇ
  8,21,"Do not be like those who say, вАЬWe hear,вАЭ but in fact they are not listening"
  8,22,"Indeed, the worst of all beings in the sight of Allah are the ЋєwilfullyЋЇ deaf and dumb, who do not understand"
  8,23,"Had Allah known any goodness in them, He would have certainly made them hear. ЋєButЋЇ even if He had made them hear, they would have surely turned away heedlessly"
  8,24,"O believers! Respond to Allah and His Messenger when he calls you to that which gives you life. And know that Allah stands between a person and their heart, and that to Him you will all be gathered"
  8,25,Beware of a trial that will not only affect the wrongdoers among you. And know that Allah is severe in punishment
  8,26,"Remember when you had been vastly outnumbered and oppressed in the land,¬†constantly in fear of attacks by your enemy, then He sheltered you, strengthened you with His help, and provided you with good things so perhaps you would be thankful"
  8,27,"O believers! Do not betray Allah and the Messenger, nor betray your trusts knowingly"
  8,28,And know that your wealth and your children are only a test and that with Allah is a great reward
  8,29,"O believers! If you are mindful of Allah, He will grant you a standard Ћєto distinguish between right and wrongЋЇ, absolve you of your sins, and forgive you. And Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty"
  8,30,"And Ћєremember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when the disbelievers conspired to capture, kill, or exile you. They planned, but Allah also planned. And Allah is the best of planners"
  8,31,"Whenever Our revelations are recited to them, they challenge ЋєyouЋЇ, вАЬWe have already heard Ћєthe recitationЋЇ. If we wanted, we could have easily produced something similar. This ЋєQuranЋЇ is nothing but ancient fables!вАЭ"
  8,32,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when they prayed, вАЬO Allah! If this is indeed the truth from You, then rain down stones upon us from the sky or overcome us with a painful punishment.вАЭ"
  8,33,But Allah would never punish them while you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ were in their midst. Nor would He ever punish them if they prayed for forgiveness
  8,34,"And why should Allah not punish them while they hinder pilgrims from the Sacred Mosque, claiming to be its rightful guardians? None has the right to guardianship except those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, but most pagans do not know"
  8,35,Their prayer at the Sacred House was nothing but whistling and clapping. So taste the punishment for your disbelief
  8,36,Surely the disbelievers spend their wealth to hinder others from the Path of Allah. They will continue to spend to the point of regret. Then they will be defeated and the disbelievers will be driven into Hell
  8,37,so Allah may separate the evil from the good. He will pile up the evil ones all together and then cast them into Hell. They are the ЋєtrueЋЇ losers
  8,38,"Tell the disbelievers that if they desist, their past will be forgiven. But if they persist, then they have an example in those destroyed before them"
  8,39,"Fight against them until there is no more persecutionвАФand ЋєyourЋЇ devotion will be entirely to Allah. But if they desist, then surely Allah is All-Seeing of what they do"
  8,40,"And if they do not comply, then know that Allah is your Protector. What an excellent Protector, and what an excellent Helper"
  8,41,"Know that whatever spoils you take, one-fifth is for Allah and the Messenger, his close relatives, orphans, the poor, and ЋєneedyЋЇ travellers, if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in Allah and what We revealed to Our servant on that decisive day when the two armies met Ћєat BadrЋЇ. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  8,42,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when you were on the near side of the valley, your enemy on the far side, and the caravan was below you. Even if the two armies had made an appointment Ћєto meetЋЇ, both would have certainly missed it.¬†Still it transpired so Allah may establish what He had destinedвАФthat those who were to perish and those who were to survive might do so after the truth had been made clear to both. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,43,"ЋєRemember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when Allah showed them in your dream as few in number. Had He shown them to you as many, you ЋєbelieversЋЇ would have certainly faltered and disputed in the matter. But Allah spared you Ћєfrom thatЋЇ. Surely He knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  8,44,"Then when your armies met, Allah made them appear as few in your eyes, and made you appear as few in theirs, so Allah may establish what He had destined. And to Allah ЋєallЋЇ matters will be returned Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ"
  8,45,"O believers! When you face an enemy, stand firm and remember Allah often so you may triumph"
  8,46,"Obey Allah and His Messenger and do not dispute with one another, or you would be discouraged and weakened. Persevere! Surely Allah is with those who persevere"
  8,47,"Do not be like those ЋєpagansЋЇ who left their homes arrogantly, only to be seen by people and to hinder others from AllahвАЩs Path. And Allah is Fully Aware of what they do"
  8,48,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Satan made their ЋєevilЋЇ deeds appealing to them, and said, вАЬNo one can overcome you today. I am surely by your side.вАЭ But when the two forces faced off, he cowered and said, вАЬI have absolutely nothing to do with you. I certainly see what you do not see. I truly fear Allah, for Allah is severe in punishment.вАЭ"
  8,49,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, вАЬThese ЋєbelieversЋЇ are deluded by their faith.вАЭ But whoever puts their trust in Allah, surely Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,50,"If only you could see when the angels take the souls of the disbelievers, beating their faces and backs, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬTaste the torment of burning"
  8,51,This is Ћєthe rewardЋЇ for what your hands have done. And Allah is never unjust to ЋєHisЋЇ creation.вАЭ
  8,52,"Their fate is that of the people of Pharaoh and those before themвАФthey all disbelieved in AllahвАЩs signs, so Allah seized them for their sins. Indeed, Allah is All-Powerful, severe in punishment"
  8,53,"This is because Allah would never discontinue His favour to a people until they discontinue their faith. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,54,"That was the case with PharaohвАЩs people and those before themвАФthey all rejected the signs of their Lord, so We destroyed them for their sins and drowned PharaohвАЩs people. They were all wrongdoers"
  8,55,"Indeed, the worst of all beings in the sight of Allah are those who persist in disbelief, never to have faithвАФ"
  8,56,"ЋєnamelyЋЇ those with whom you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ have entered into treaties, but they violate them every time, not fearing the consequences"
  8,57,"If you ever encounter them in battle, make a fearsome example of them, so perhaps those who would follow them may be deterred"
  8,58,"And if you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ see signs of betrayal by a people, respond by openly terminating your treaty with them. Surely Allah does not like those who betray"
  8,59,Do not let those disbelievers¬†think they are not within reach. They will have no escape
  8,60,Prepare against them what you ЋєbelieversЋЇ can of ЋєmilitaryЋЇ power and cavalry to deter AllahвАЩs enemies and your enemies as well as other enemies unknown to you but known to Allah. Whatever you spend in the cause of Allah will be paid to you in full and you will not be wronged
  8,61,"If the enemy is inclined towards peace, make peace with them. And put your trust in Allah. Indeed, He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,62,"But if their intention is only to deceive you, then Allah is certainly sufficient for you. He is the One Who has supported you with His help and with the believers"
  8,63,"He brought their hearts together. Had you spent all the riches in the earth, you could not have united their hearts. But Allah has united them. Indeed, He is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,64,O Prophet! Allah is sufficient for you and for the believers who follow you
  8,65,"O Prophet! Motivate the believers to fight. If there are twenty steadfast among you, they will overcome two hundred. And if there are one hundred of you, they will overcome one thousand of the disbelievers, for they are a people who do not comprehend"
  8,66,"Now Allah has lightened your burden, for He knows that there is weakness in you. So if there are a hundred steadfast among you, they will overcome two hundred. And if there be one thousand, they will overcome two thousand, by AllahвАЩs Will. And Allah is with the steadfast"
  8,67,"It is not fit for a prophet that he should take captives until he has thoroughly subdued the land. You ЋєbelieversЋЇ settled with the fleeting gains of this world,¬†while AllahвАЩs aim Ћєfor youЋЇ is the Hereafter. Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,68,"Had it not been for a prior decree from Allah,¬†you would have certainly been disciplined with a tremendous punishment for whatever ЋєransomЋЇ you have taken"
  8,69,"Now enjoy what you have taken, for it is lawful and good. And be mindful of Allah. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  8,70,"O Prophet! Tell the captives in your custody, вАЬIf Allah finds goodness in your hearts, He will give you better than what has been taken from you, and forgive you. For Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  8,71,"But if their intention is only to betray you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, they sought to betray Allah before. But He gave you power over them. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  8,72,"Those who believed, emigrated, and strived with their wealth and lives in the cause of Allah, as well as those who gave them shelter and helpвАФthey are truly guardians of one another. As for those who believed but did not emigrate, you have no obligations to them until they emigrate. But if they seek your help Ћєagainst persecutionЋЇ in faith, it is your obligation to help them, except against people bound with you in a treaty. Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  8,73,"As for the disbelievers, they are guardians of one another. And unless you ЋєbelieversЋЇ act likewise, there will be great oppression and corruption in the land"
  8,74,"Those who believed, migrated, and struggled in the cause of Allah, and those who gave ЋєthemЋЇ shelter and help, they are the true believers. They will have forgiveness and an honourable provision"
  8,75,"And those who later believed, migrated, and struggled alongside you, they are also with you. But only blood relatives are now entitled to inherit from one another,¬†as ordained by Allah. Surely Allah has ЋєfullЋЇ knowledge of everything"
  9,1,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a discharge from all obligations,¬†by Allah and His Messenger, to the polytheists you ЋєbelieversЋЇ have entered into treaties with"
  9,2,"вАЬYou ЋєpolytheistsЋЇ may travel freely through the land for four months, but know that you will have no escape from Allah, and that Allah will disgrace the disbelievers.вАЭ"
  9,3,"A declaration from Allah and His Messenger Ћєis madeЋЇ to all people on the day of the greater pilgrimage¬†that Allah and His Messenger are free of the polytheists. So if you ЋєpagansЋЇ repent, it will be better for you. But if you turn away, then know that you will have no escape from Allah. And give good news ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to the disbelievers of a painful punishment"
  9,4,"As for the polytheists who have honoured every term of their treaty with you and have not supported an enemy against you, honour your treaty with them until the end of its term. Surely Allah loves those who are mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ"
  9,5,"But once the Sacred Months have passed, kill the polytheists Ћєwho violated their treatiesЋЇ wherever you find them,¬†capture them, besiege them, and lie in wait for them on every way. But if they repent, perform prayers, and pay alms-tax, then set them free. Indeed, Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,6,"And if anyone from the polytheists asks for your protection ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, grant it to them so they may hear the Word of Allah, then escort them to a place of safety, for they are a people who have no knowledge"
  9,7,"How can such polytheists have a treaty with Allah and His Messenger, except those you have made a treaty with at the Sacred Mosque?¬†So, as long as they are true to you, be true to them. Indeed Allah loves those who are mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ"
  9,8,"How Ћєcan they have a treatyЋЇ? If they were to have the upper hand over you, they would have no respect for kinship or treaty. They only flatter you with their tongues, but their hearts are in denial, and most of them are rebellious"
  9,9,"They chose a fleeting gain over AllahвАЩs revelations, hindering ЋєothersЋЇ from His Way. Evil indeed is what they have done"
  9,10,They do not honour the bonds of kinship or treaties with the believers. It is they who are the transgressors
  9,11,"But if they repent, perform prayer, and pay alms-tax, then they are your brothers in faith. This is how We make the revelations clear for people of knowledge"
  9,12,"But if they break their oaths after making a pledge and attack your faith, then fight the champions of disbeliefвАФwho never honour their oathsвАФso perhaps they will desist"
  9,13,"Will you not fight those who have broken their oaths, conspired to expel the Messenger Ћєfrom MeccaЋЇ, and attacked you first? Do you fear them? Allah is more deserving of your fear, if you are ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  9,14,"ЋєSoЋЇ fight them and Allah will punish them at your hands, put them to shame, help you overcome them, and soothe the hearts of the believersвАФ"
  9,15,"removing rage from their hearts. And Allah pardons whoever He wills. For Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,16,"Do you ЋєbelieversЋЇ think that you will be left without Allah proving who among you ЋєtrulyЋЇ struggles Ћєin His causeЋЇ and never takes trusted allies other than Allah, His Messenger, or the believers? And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  9,17,"It is not for the polytheists to maintain the mosques of Allah while they openly profess disbelief. Their deeds are void, and they will be in the Fire forever"
  9,18,"The mosques of Allah should only be maintained by those who believe in Allah and the Last Day, establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and fear none but Allah. It is right to hope that they will be among the ЋєtrulyЋЇ guided"
  9,19,Do you ЋєpagansЋЇ consider providing the pilgrims with water and maintaining the Sacred Mosque as equal to believing in Allah and the Last Day and struggling in the cause of Allah? They are not equal in AllahвАЩs sight. And Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people
  9,20,"Those who have believed, emigrated, and strived in the cause of Allah with their wealth and their lives are greater in rank in the sight of Allah. It is they who will triumph"
  9,21,"Their Lord gives them good news of His mercy, pleasure, and Gardens with everlasting bliss"
  9,22,to stay there for ever and ever. Surely with Allah is a great reward
  9,23,"O believers! Do not take your parents and siblings as trusted allies if they choose disbelief over belief. And whoever of you does so, they are the ЋєtrueЋЇ wrongdoers"
  9,24,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf your parents and children and siblings and spouses and extended family and the wealth you have acquired and the trade you fear will decline and the homes you cherishвАФЋєif all theseЋЇ are more beloved to you than Allah and His Messenger and struggling in His Way, then wait until Allah brings about His Will. Allah does not guide the rebellious people.вАЭ"
  9,25,"Indeed Allah has given you ЋєbelieversЋЇ victory on many battlefields, even at the Battle of бЄ§unain¬†when you took pride in your great numbers, but they proved of no advantage to you. The earth, despite its vastness, seemed to close in on you, then you turned back in retreat"
  9,26,"Then Allah sent down His reassurance¬†upon His Messenger and the believers, and sent down forces¬†you could not see, and punished those who disbelieved. Such was the reward of the disbelievers"
  9,27,"Then afterwards Allah will turn in grace to whoever He wills.¬†And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,28,"O believers! Indeed, the polytheists are ЋєspirituallyЋЇ impure,¬†so they should not approach the Sacred Mosque after this year.¬†If you fear poverty, Allah will enrich you out of His bounty, if He wills. Surely, Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,29,"Fight those who do not believe in Allah and the Last Day, nor comply with what Allah and His Messenger have forbidden, nor embrace the religion of truth from among those who were given the Scripture,¬†until they pay the tax,¬†willingly submitting, fully humbled"
  9,30,"The Jews say, вАЬEzra is the son of Allah,вАЭ while the Christians say, вАЬThe Messiah is the son of Allah.вАЭ Such are their baseless assertions, only parroting the words of earlier disbelievers. May Allah condemn them! How can they be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  9,31,"They have taken their rabbis and monks as well as the Messiah, son of Mary, as lords besides Allah,¬†even though they were commanded to worship none but One God. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. Glorified is He above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ"
  9,32,"They wish to extinguish AllahвАЩs light¬†with their mouths, but Allah will only allow His light to be perfected, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  9,33,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others, even to the dismay of the polytheists"
  9,34,"O believers! Indeed, many rabbis and monks consume peopleвАЩs wealth wrongfully and hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah. Give good news of a painful torment to those who hoard gold and silver and do not spend it in AllahвАЩs cause"
  9,35,"The Day Ћєwill comeЋЇ when their treasure will be heated up in the Fire of Hell, and their foreheads, sides, and backs branded with it. ЋєIt will be said to them,ЋЇ вАЬThis is the treasure you hoarded for yourselves. Now taste what you hoarded!вАЭ"
  9,36,"Indeed, the number of months ordained by Allah is twelveвАФin AllahвАЩs Record¬†since the day He created the heavens and the earthвАФof which four are sacred. That is the Right Way. So do not wrong one another during these months. And together fight the polytheists as they fight against you together. And know that Allah is with those mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ"
  9,37,"Reallocating the sanctity of ЋєtheseЋЇ months¬†is an increase in disbelief, by which the disbelievers are led ЋєfarЋЇ astray. They adjust the sanctity one year and uphold it in another, only to maintain the number of months sanctified by Allah, violating the very months Allah has made sacred. Their evil deeds have been made appealing to them. And Allah does not guide the disbelieving people"
  9,38,"O believers! What is the matter with you that when you are asked to march forth in the cause of Allah, you cling firmly to ЋєyourЋЇ land?¬†Do you prefer the life of this world over the Hereafter? The enjoyment of this worldly life is insignificant compared to that of the Hereafter"
  9,39,"If you do not march forth, He will afflict you with a painful torment and replace you with other people. You are not harming Him in the least. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  9,40,"ЋєIt does not matterЋЇ if you ЋєbelieversЋЇ do not support him, for Allah did in fact support him when the disbelievers drove him out Ћєof MeccaЋЇ and he was only one of two. While they both were in the cave, he reassured his companion,¬†вАЬDo not worry; Allah is certainly with us.вАЭ So Allah sent down His serenity upon the Prophet, supported him with forces you ЋєbelieversЋЇ did not see, and made the word of the disbelievers lowest, while the Word of Allah is supreme. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  9,41,"ЋєO believers!ЋЇ March forth whether it is easy or difficult for you, and strive with your wealth and your lives in the cause of Allah. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  9,42,"Had the gain been within reach and the journey shorter, they would have followed you, but the distance seemed too long for them. And they will swear by Allah, вАЬHad we been able, we would have certainly joined you.вАЭ They are ruining themselves. And Allah knows that they are surely lying"
  9,43,May Allah pardon you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ! Why did you give them permission Ћєto stay behindЋЇ before those who told the truth were distinguished from those who were lying
  9,44,Those who believe in Allah and the Last Day do not ask for exemption from striving with their wealth and their lives. And Allah has perfect knowledge of those who are mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ
  9,45,"No one would ask for exemption except those who have no faith in Allah or the Last Day, and whose hearts are in doubt, so they are torn by their doubts"
  9,46,"Had they ЋєreallyЋЇ intended to march forth, they would have made preparations for it. But Allah disliked that they should go, so He let them lag behind, and it was said Ћєto themЋЇ, вАЬStay with those ЋєhelplessЋЇ who remain behind.вАЭ"
  9,47,"Had they gone forth with you ЋєbelieversЋЇ, they would have been nothing but trouble for you, and would have scrambled around, seeking to spread discord in your midst. And some of you would have eagerly listened to them. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of the wrongdoers"
  9,48,"They had already sought to spread discord before¬†and devised every ЋєpossibleЋЇ plot against you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, until the truth came and AllahвАЩs Will prevailedвАФmuch to their dismay"
  9,49,"There are some of them who say, вАЬExempt me and do not expose me to temptation.вАЭ¬†They have already fallen into temptation. And Hell will surely engulf the disbelievers"
  9,50,"If a blessing befalls you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, they grieve, but if a disaster befalls you, they say, вАЬWe took our precaution in advance,вАЭ and turn away, rejoicing"
  9,51,"Say, вАЬNothing will ever befall us except what Allah has destined for us. He is our Protector.вАЭ So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  9,52,"Say, вАЬAre you awaiting anything to befall us except one of the two best things: Ћєvictory or martyrdomЋЇ? But¬†We are awaiting Allah to afflict you with torment either from Him or at our hands. So keep waiting! We too are waiting with you.вАЭ"
  9,53,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєWhether youЋЇ donate willingly or unwillingly, it will never be accepted from you, for you have been a rebellious people.вАЭ"
  9,54,"And what prevented their donations from being accepted is that they have lost faith in Allah and His Messenger, they never come to prayer except half-heartedly, and they never donate except resentfully"
  9,55,"So let neither their wealth nor children impress you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Allah only intends to torment them through these things in this worldly life, then their souls will depart while they are disbelievers"
  9,56,"They swear by Allah that they are part of you, but they are not. They only say so out of fear"
  9,57,"If only they could find a refuge, or a cave, or any hiding-place, they would rush headlong towards it"
  9,58,"There are some of them who are critical of your distribution of alms ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. If they are given some of it they are pleased, but if not they are enraged"
  9,59,"If only they had been content with what Allah and His Messenger had given them and said, вАЬAllah is sufficient for us! Allah will grant us out of His bounty, and so will His Messenger. To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ we turn with hope.вАЭ"
  9,60,"Alms-tax is only for the poor and the needy, for those employed to administer it, for those whose hearts are attracted Ћєto the faithЋЇ, for ЋєfreeingЋЇ slaves, for those in debt, for AllahвАЩs cause, and for ЋєneedyЋЇ travellers. ЋєThis isЋЇ an obligation from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,61,"And there are others who hurt the Prophet by saying, вАЬHe listens to anyone.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHe listens to what is best for you. He believes in Allah, has faith in the believers, and is a mercy for those who believe among you.вАЭ Those who hurt AllahвАЩs Messenger will suffer a painful punishment"
  9,62,"They swear by Allah to you ЋєbelieversЋЇ in order to please you, while it is the pleasure of Allah and His Messenger they should seek, if they are ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  9,63,Do they not know that whoever opposes Allah and His Messenger will be in the Fire of Hell forever? That is the ultimate disgrace
  9,64,"The hypocrites fear that a s√їrah¬†should be revealed about them, exposing what is in their hearts. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬKeep mocking! Allah will definitely bring to light what you fear.вАЭ"
  9,65,"If you question them, they will certainly say, вАЬWe were only talking idly and joking around.вАЭ Say, вАЬWas it Allah, His revelations, and His Messenger that you ridiculed?вАЭ"
  9,66,"Make no excuses! You have lost faith after your belief. If We pardon a group of you,¬†We will punish others for their wickedness"
  9,67,"The hypocrites, both men and women, are all alike: they encourage what is evil, forbid what is good, and withhold Ћєwhat is inЋЇ their hands. They neglected Allah, so He neglected them. Surely the hypocrites are the rebellious"
  9,68,"Allah has promised the hypocrites, both men and women, and the disbelievers an everlasting stay in the Fire of HellвАФit is sufficient for them. Allah has condemned them, and they will suffer a never-ending punishment"
  9,69,"ЋєYou hypocrites areЋЇ like those ЋєdisbelieversЋЇ before you. They were far superior to you in might and more abundant in wealth and children. They enjoyed their share in this life. You have enjoyed your share, just as they did. And you have engaged in idle talk, just as they did. Their deeds have become void in this world and the Hereafter. And it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ losers"
  9,70,"Have they not received the stories of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them: the people of Noah, вАЩ√Вd, and Tham√їd, the people of Abraham, the residents of Midian, and the overturned cities Ћєof LotЋЇ?¬†Their messengers came to them with clear proofs. Allah would have never wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  9,71,"The believers, both men and women, are guardians of one another. They encourage good and forbid evil, establish prayer and pay alms-tax, and obey Allah and His Messenger. It is they who will be shown AllahвАЩs mercy. Surely Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  9,72,"Allah has promised the believers, both men and women, Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever, and splendid homes in the Gardens of Eternity, andвАФabove allвАФthe pleasure of Allah. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the ultimate triumph"
  9,73,"O Prophet! Struggle against the disbelievers and the hypocrites, and be firm with them. Hell will be their home. What an evil destination"
  9,74,"They swear by Allah that they never said anything ЋєblasphemousЋЇ, while they did in fact utter a blasphemy, lost faith after accepting Islam, and plotted what they could not carry out.¬†It is only through resentment that they pay Allah and His Messenger back for enriching them out of His bounty! If they repent, it will be better for them. But if they turn away, Allah will torment them with a painful punishment in this world and the Hereafter, and they will have no one on earth to protect or help them"
  9,75,"And there are some who had made a vow to Allah: вАЬIf He gives us from His bounty, we will surely spend in charity and be of the righteous.вАЭ"
  9,76,"But when He gave them out of His bounty, they withheld it and turned away indifferently"
  9,77,"So He caused hypocrisy to plague their hearts until the Day they will meet Him, for breaking their promise to Allah and for their lies"
  9,78,"Do they not know that Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows their ЋєevilЋЇ thoughts and secret talks, and that Allah is the Knower of all unseen"
  9,79,"ЋєThere areЋЇ those who slander Ћєsome ofЋЇ the believers for donating liberally and mock others for giving only the little they can afford. Allah will throw their mockery back at them, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  9,80,"ЋєIt does not matterЋЇ whether you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ pray for them to be forgiven or not. Even if you pray for their forgiveness seventy times, Allah will never forgive them. That is because they have lost faith in Allah and His Messenger. And Allah does not guide the rebellious people"
  9,81,"Those ЋєhypocritesЋЇ who remained behind rejoiced for doing so in defiance of the Messenger of Allah and hated Ћєthe prospect ofЋЇ striving with their wealth and their lives in the cause of Allah. They said Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬDo not march forth in the heat.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬThe Fire of Hell is far hotter!вАЭ If only they could comprehend"
  9,82,So let them laugh a littleвАФthey will weep much as a reward for what they have committed
  9,83,"If Allah returns you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to a group of them and they ask to go forth with you, say, вАЬYou will not ever go forth or fight an enemy along with me. You preferred to stay behind the first time, so stay with those ЋєhelplessЋЇ who remain behind.вАЭ"
  9,84,"And do not ever offer ЋєfuneralЋЇ prayers for any of their dead, nor stand by their grave Ћєat burialЋЇ, for they have lost faith in Allah and His Messenger and died rebellious"
  9,85,"And let neither their wealth nor children impress you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Allah only intends to torment them through these things in this world, and ЋєthenЋЇ their souls will depart while they are disbelievers"
  9,86,"Whenever a s√їrah¬†is revealed stating, вАЬBelieve in Allah and struggle along with His Messenger,вАЭ the rich among them would ask to be exempt, saying, вАЬLeave us with those who remain behind.вАЭ"
  9,87,"They preferred to stay behind with the helpless, and their hearts have been sealed so they do not comprehend"
  9,88,"But the Messenger and the believers with him strived with their wealth and their lives. They will have all the best, and it is they who will be successful"
  9,89,"Allah has prepared for them Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  9,90,"Some nomadic Arabs ЋєalsoЋЇ came with excuses, seeking exemption. And those who were untrue to Allah and His Messenger remained behind Ћєwith no excuseЋЇ. The unfaithful among them will be afflicted with a painful punishment"
  9,91,"There is no blame on the weak, the sick, or those lacking the means Ћєif they stay behindЋЇ, as long as they are true to Allah and His Messenger. There is no blame on the good-doers. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,92,"Nor Ћєis there any blame onЋЇ those who came to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ for mounts, then when you said, вАЬI can find no mounts for you,вАЭ they left with eyes overflowing with tears out of grief that they had nothing to contribute"
  9,93,"Blame is only on those who seek exemption from you although they have the means. They preferred to stay behind with the helpless, and Allah has sealed their hearts so they do not realize Ћєthe consequencesЋЇ"
  9,94,"They will make excuses to you ЋєbelieversЋЇ when you return to them. Say, вАЬMake no excuses, ЋєforЋЇ we will not believe you. Allah has already informed us about your ЋєtrueЋЇ state Ћєof faithЋЇ. Your ЋєfutureЋЇ deeds will be observed by Allah and His Messenger as well. And you will be returned to the Knower of the seen and unseen, then He will inform you of what you used to do.вАЭ"
  9,95,"When you return, they will swear to you by Allah so that you may leave them alone. So leave them aloneвАФthey are truly evil. Hell will be their home as a reward for what they have committed"
  9,96,"They will swear to you in order to please you. And even if you are pleased with them, Allah will never be pleased with the rebellious people"
  9,97,"The nomadic Arabs Ћєaround MedinaЋЇ are far worse in disbelief and hypocrisy, and less likely to know the laws revealed by Allah to His Messenger. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,98,"And among the nomads are those who consider what they donate to be a loss and await your misfortune. May ill-fortune befall them! And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  9,99,"However, among the nomadic Arabs are those who believe in Allah and the Last Day, and consider what they donate as a means of coming closer to Allah and ЋєreceivingЋЇ the prayers of the Messenger. It will certainly bring them closer. Allah will admit them into His mercy. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,100,"As for the foremostвАФthe first of the Emigrants¬†and the HelpersвАФand those who follow them in goodness, Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. And He has prepared for them Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  9,101,"Some of the nomads around you ЋєbelieversЋЇ are hypocrites, as are some of the people of Medina. They have mastered hypocrisy. They are not known to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ; they are known to Us. We will punish them twice Ћєin this worldЋЇ,¬†then they will be brought back Ћєto their LordЋЇ for a tremendous punishment"
  9,102,"Some others have confessed their wrongdoing: they have mixed goodness with evil.¬†It is right to hope that Allah will turn to them in mercy. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  9,103,"Take from their wealth ЋєO ProphetЋЇ charity to purify and bless them, and pray for themвАФsurely your prayer is a source of comfort for them. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  9,104,"Do they not know that Allah alone accepts the repentance of His servants and receives ЋєtheirЋЇ charity, and that Allah alone is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  9,105,"Tell Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬDo as you will. Your deeds will be observed by Allah, His Messenger, and the believers. And you will be returned to the Knower of the seen and unseen, then He will inform you of what you used to do.вАЭ"
  9,106,"And some others are left for AllahвАЩs decision, either to punish them or turn to them in mercy.¬†And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,107,"There are also those ЋєhypocritesЋЇ who set up a mosque ЋєonlyЋЇ to cause harm, promote disbelief, divide the believers, and as a base for those who had previously fought against Allah and His Messenger.¬†They will definitely swear, вАЬWe intended nothing but good,вАЭ but Allah bears witness that they are surely liars"
  9,108,"Do not ЋєO ProphetЋЇ ever pray in it. Certainly, a mosque founded on righteousness from the first day is more worthy of your prayers. In it are men who love to be purified.¬†And Allah loves those who purify themselves"
  9,109,"Which is better: those who laid the foundation of their building on the fear and pleasure of Allah, or those who did so on the edge of a crumbling cliff that tumbled down with them into the Fire of Hell? And Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  9,110,"The building which they erected will never cease to fuel hypocrisy in their hearts until their hearts are torn apart. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,111,"Allah has indeed purchased from the believers their lives and wealth in exchange for Paradise. They fight in the cause of Allah and kill or are killed. This is a true promise binding on Him in the Torah, the Gospel, and the Quran. And whose promise is truer than AllahвАЩs? So rejoice in the exchange you have made with Him. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the ultimate triumph"
  9,112,"ЋєIt is the believersЋЇ who repent, who are devoted to worship, who praise Ћєtheir LordЋЇ, who fast, who bow down and prostrate themselves, who encourage good and forbid evil, and who observe the limits set by Allah. And give good news to the believers"
  9,113,"It is not ЋєproperЋЇ for the Prophet and the believers to seek forgiveness for the polytheists, even if they were close relatives, after it has become clear to the believers that they are bound for the Hellfire"
  9,114,"As for AbrahamвАЩs prayer for his fatherвАЩs forgiveness, it was only in fulfilment of a promise he had made to him. But when it became clear to Abraham that his father was an enemy of Allah, he broke ties with him.¬†Abraham was truly tender-hearted, forbearing"
  9,115,"Allah would never consider a people deviant after He has guided them, until He makes clear to them what they must avoid. Surely Allah has ЋєfullЋЇ knowledge of everything"
  9,116,"Indeed, to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He gives life and causes death. And besides Allah you have no guardian or helper"
  9,117,"Allah has certainly turned in mercy to the Prophet¬†as well as the Emigrants and the Helpers who stood by him in the time of hardship, after the hearts of a group of them had almost faltered. He then accepted their repentance. Surely He is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to them"
  9,118,"And ЋєAllah has also turned in mercy toЋЇ the three who had remained behind, Ћєwhose guilt distressed themЋЇ until the earth, despite its vastness, seemed to close in on them, and their souls were torn in anguish. They knew there was no refuge from Allah except in Him. Then He turned to them in mercy so that they might repent. Surely Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  9,119,O believers! Be mindful of Allah and be with the truthful
  9,120,"It was not ЋєproperЋЇ for the people of Medina and the nomadic Arabs around them to avoid marching with the Messenger of Allah or to prefer their own lives above his. That is because whenever they suffer from thirst, fatigue, or hunger in the cause of Allah; or tread on a territory, unnerving the disbelievers; or inflict any loss on an enemyвАФit is written to their credit as a good deed. Surely Allah never discounts the reward of the good-doers"
  9,121,"And whenever they make a donation, small or large, or cross a valley Ћєin AllahвАЩs causeЋЇвАФit is written to their credit, so that Allah may grant them the best reward for what they used to do"
  9,122,"ЋєHowever,ЋЇ it is not necessary for the believers to march forth all at once. Only a party from each group should march forth, leaving the rest to gain religious knowledge then enlighten their people when they return to them, so that they ЋєtooЋЇ may beware Ћєof evilЋЇ"
  9,123,O believers! Fight the disbelievers around you and let them find firmness in you. And know that Allah is with those mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ
  9,124,"Whenever a s√їrah¬†is revealed, some of them ask ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhich of you has this increased in faith?вАЭ As for the believers, it has increased them in faith and they rejoice"
  9,125,"But as for those with sickness in their hearts,¬†it has increased them only in wickedness upon their wickedness, and they die as disbelievers"
  9,126,Do they not see that they are tried once or twice every year?¬†Yet they neither repent nor do they learn a lesson
  9,127,"Whenever a s√їrah¬†is revealed, they look at one another, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬIs anyone watching you?вАЭ Then they slip away. ЋєIt isЋЇ Allah ЋєWhoЋЇ has turned their hearts away because they are a people who do not comprehend"
  9,128,"There certainly has come to you a messenger from among yourselves. He is concerned by your suffering, anxious for your well-being, and gracious and merciful to the believers"
  9,129,"But if they turn away, then say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAllah is sufficient for me. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. In Him I put my trust. And He is the Lord of the Mighty Throne.вАЭ"
  10,1,"Alif-L√£m-Ra. These are the verses of the Book, rich in wisdom"
  10,2,"Is it astonishing to people that We have sent revelation to a man from among themselves, Ћєinstructing him,ЋЇ вАЬWarn humanity and give good news to the believers that they will have an honourable status with their Lord.вАЭ? Yet the disbelievers said, вАЬIndeed, this ЋєmanЋЇ is clearly a magician!вАЭ"
  10,3,"Surely your Lord is Allah Who created the heavens and the earth in six Days,¬†then established Himself on the Throne, conducting every affair. None can intercede except by His permission. That is AllahвАФyour Lord, so worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. Will you not then be mindful"
  10,4,"To Him is your return all together. AllahвАЩs promise is ЋєalwaysЋЇ true. Indeed, He originates the creation then resurrects it so that He may justly reward those who believe and do good. But those who disbelieve will have a boiling drink and a painful punishment for their disbelief"
  10,5,"He is the One Who made the sun a radiant source and the moon a reflected light, with precisely ordained phases, so that you may know the number of years and calculation Ћєof timeЋЇ. Allah did not create all this except for a purpose. He makes the signs clear for people of knowledge"
  10,6,"Surely in the alternation of the day and the night, and in all that Allah has created in the heavens and the earth, there are truly signs for those mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ"
  10,7,"Indeed, those who do not expect to meet Us, being pleased and content with this worldly life, and who are heedless of Our signs"
  10,8,they will have the Fire as a home because of what they have committed
  10,9,"Surely those who believe and do good, their Lord will guide them Ћєto ParadiseЋЇ through their faith, rivers will flow under their feet in the Gardens of Bliss"
  10,10,"in which their prayer will be, вАЬGlory be to You, O Allah!вАЭ and their greeting will be, вАЬPeace!вАЭ and their closing prayer will be, вАЬAll praise is for AllahвАФLord of all worlds!вАЭ"
  10,11,"If Allah were to hasten evil for people¬†as they wish to hasten good, they would have certainly been doomed. But We leave those who do not expect to meet Us to wander blindly in their defiance"
  10,12,"Whenever someone is touched by hardship, they cry out to Us, whether lying on their side, sitting, or standing. But when We relieve their hardship, they return to their old ways as if they had never cried to Us to remove any hardship! This is how the misdeeds of the transgressors have been made appealing to them"
  10,13,"We surely destroyed ЋєotherЋЇ peoples before you when they did wrong, and their messengers came to them with clear proofs but they would not believe! This is how We reward the wicked people"
  10,14,Then We made you their successors in the land to see how you would act
  10,15,"When Our clear revelations are recited to them, those who do not expect to meet Us say Ћєto the ProphetЋЇ, вАЬBring us a different Quran or make some changes in it.вАЭ Say Ћєto themЋЇ, вАЬIt is not for me to change it on my own. I only follow what is revealed to me. I fear, if I were to disobey my Lord, the punishment of a tremendous Day.вАЭ"
  10,16,"Say, вАЬHad Allah willed, I would not have recited it to you, nor would He have made it known to you. I had lived my whole life among you before this ЋєrevelationЋЇ. Do you not understand?вАЭ"
  10,17,"Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against Allah or deny His revelations? Indeed, the wicked will never succeed"
  10,18,"They worship besides Allah others who can neither harm nor benefit them, and say, вАЬThese are our intercessors with Allah.вАЭ Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬAre you informing Allah of something He does not know in the heavens or the earth? Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ!вАЭ"
  10,19,"Humanity was once nothing but a single community Ћєof believersЋЇ, but then they differed.¬†Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord,¬†their differences would have been settled Ћєat onceЋЇ"
  10,20,"They ask, вАЬWhy has no ЋєotherЋЇ sign been sent down to him from his Lord?вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєThe knowledge ofЋЇ the unseen is with Allah alone. So wait! I too am waiting with you.вАЭ"
  10,21,"When We give people a taste of mercy after being afflicted with a hardship, they swiftly devise plots against Our revelations! Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAllah is swifter in devising ЋєpunishmentЋЇ. Surely Our messenger-angels record whatever you devise.вАЭ"
  10,22,"He is the One Who enables you to travel through land and sea. And it so happens that you are on ships, sailing with a favourable wind, to the passengersвАЩ delight. Suddenly, the ships are overcome by a gale wind and those on board are overwhelmed by waves from every side, and they assume they are doomed. They cry out to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ in sincere devotion, вАЬIf You save us from this, we will certainly be grateful.вАЭ"
  10,23,"But as soon as He rescues them, they transgress in the land unjustly. O humanity! Your transgression is only against your own souls. ЋєThere is onlyЋЇ brief enjoyment in this worldly life, then to Us is your return, and then We will inform you of what you used to do"
  10,24,"The life of this world is just like rain We send down from the sky, producing a mixture of plants which humans and animals consume. Then just as the earth looks its best, perfectly beautified, and its people think they have full control over it, there comes to it Our command by night or by day, so We mow it down as if it never flourished yesterday! This is how We make the signs clear for people who reflect"
  10,25,And Allah invites ЋєallЋЇ to the Home of Peace and guides whoever He wills to the Straight Path
  10,26,Those who do good will have the finest reward¬†and ЋєevenЋЇ more.¬†Neither gloom nor disgrace will cover their faces. It is they who will be the residents of Paradise. They will be there forever
  10,27,"As for those who commit evil, the reward of an evil deed is its equivalent. Humiliation will cover themвАФwith no one to protect them from AllahвАФas if their faces were covered with patches of the nightвАЩs deep darkness. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  10,28,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ the Day We will gather them all together then say to those who associated others Ћєwith Allah in worshipЋЇ, вАЬStay in your placesвАФyou and your associate-gods.вАЭ We will separate them from each other, and their associate-gods will say, вАЬIt was not us that you worshipped"
  10,29,Allah is sufficient as a Witness between each of us that we were totally unaware of your worship.вАЭ
  10,30,Then and there every soul will face Ћєthe consequences ofЋЇ what it had done. They all will be returned to AllahвАФtheir True Master. And whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ they fabricated will fail them
  10,31,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWho provides for you from heaven and earth? Who owns ЋєyourЋЇ hearing and sight? Who brings forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living? And who conducts every affair?вАЭ They will ЋєsurelyЋЇ say, вАЬAllah.вАЭ Say, вАЬWill you not then fear ЋєHimЋЇ"
  10,32,That is AllahвАФyour True Lord. So what is beyond the truth except falsehood? How can you then be turned away?вАЭ
  10,33,And so your LordвАЩs decree has been proven true against the rebelliousвАФthat they will never believe
  10,34,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬCan any of your associate-gods originate creation and then resurrect it?вАЭ Say, вАЬЋєOnlyЋЇ Allah originates creation and then resurrects it. How can you then be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ?вАЭ"
  10,35,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬCan any of your associate-gods guide to the truth?вАЭ Say, вАЬЋєOnlyЋЇ Allah guides to the truth.вАЭ Who then is more worthy to be followed: the One Who guides to the truth or those who cannot find the way unless guided? What is the matter with you? How do you judge"
  10,36,Most of them follow nothing but ЋєinheritedЋЇ assumptions. ЋєAndЋЇ surely assumptions can in no way replace the truth. Allah is indeed All-Knowing of what they do
  10,37,"It is not ЋєpossibleЋЇ for this Quran to have been produced by anyone other than Allah. In fact, it is a confirmation of what came before, and an explanation of the Scripture. It is, without a doubt, from the Lord of all worlds"
  10,38,"Or do they claim, вАЬHe¬†made it up!вАЭ? Tell them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, вАЬProduce one s√їrah¬†like it then, and seek help from whoever you canвАФother than AllahвАФif what you say is true!вАЭ"
  10,39,"In fact, they ЋєhastilyЋЇ rejected the Book without comprehending it and before the fulfilment of its warnings. Similarly, those before them were in denial. See then what was the end of the wrongdoers"
  10,40,Some of them will ЋєeventuallyЋЇ believe in it; others will not. And your Lord knows best the corruptors
  10,41,"If they deny you, then say, вАЬMy deeds are mine and your deeds are yours. You are free of what I do and I am free of what you do!вАЭ"
  10,42,"Some of them listen to what you say, but can you make the deaf hear even though they do not understand"
  10,43,"And some of them look at you, but can you guide the blind even though they cannot see"
  10,44,"Indeed, Allah does not wrong people in the least, but it is people who wrong themselves"
  10,45,"On the Day He will gather them, it will be as if they had not stayed Ћєin the worldЋЇ except for an hour of a day,¬†Ћєas though they were onlyЋЇ getting to know one another. Lost indeed will be those who denied the meeting with Allah, and were not ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  10,46,"Whether We show you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ some of what We threaten them with, or cause you to die Ћєbefore thatЋЇ, to Us is their return and Allah is a Witness over what they do"
  10,47,"And for every community there is a messenger. After their messenger has come,¬†judgment is passed on them in all fairness, and they are not wronged"
  10,48,"They ask Ћєthe believersЋЇ, вАЬWhen will this threat come to pass if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  10,49,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI have no power to benefit or protect myself, except by the Will of Allah.вАЭ For each community there is an appointed term. When their time arrives, they cannot delay it for a moment, nor could they advance it"
  10,50,"Tell them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, вАЬImagine if His torment were to overcome you by night or dayвАФdo the wicked realize what they are ЋєreallyЋЇ asking Him to hasten"
  10,51,Will you believe in it only after it has overtaken you? Now? But you always wanted to hasten it!вАЭ
  10,52,"Then the wrongdoers will be told, вАЬTaste the torment of eternity! Are you not rewarded except for what you used to commit?вАЭ"
  10,53,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, вАЬIs this true?вАЭ Say, вАЬYes, by my Lord! Most certainly it is true! And you will have no escape.вАЭ"
  10,54,"If every wrongdoer were to possess everything in the world, they would surely ransom themselves with it. They will hide ЋєtheirЋЇ remorse when they see the torment. And they will be judged in all fairness, and none will be wronged"
  10,55,"Surely to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. Surely AllahвАЩs promise is ЋєalwaysЋЇ true, but most of them do not know"
  10,56,"He Ћєis the One WhoЋЇ gives life and causes death, and to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  10,57,"O humanity! Indeed, there has come to you a warning from your Lord, a cure for what is in the hearts, a guide, and a mercy for the believers"
  10,58,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIn AllahвАЩs grace and mercy let them rejoice. That is far better than whatever ЋєwealthЋЇ they amass.вАЭ"
  10,59,"Ask Ћєthe pagans, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬHave you seen that which Allah has sent down for you as a provision, of which you have made some lawful and some unlawful?вАЭ¬†Say, вАЬHas Allah given you authorization, or are you fabricating lies against Allah?вАЭ"
  10,60,"What do those who fabricate lies against Allah expect on Judgment Day? Surely Allah is ever Bountiful to humanity,¬†but most of them are ungrateful"
  10,61,"There is no activity you may be engaged in ЋєO ProphetЋЇ or portion of the Quran you may be reciting, nor any deed you ЋєallЋЇ may be doing except that We are a Witness over you while doing it. Not ЋєevenЋЇ an atomвАЩs weight is hidden from your Lord on earth or in heaven; nor anything smaller or larger than that, but is ЋєwrittenЋЇ in a perfect Record"
  10,62,"There will certainly be no fear for the close servants of Allah, nor will they grieve"
  10,63,ЋєThey areЋЇ those who are faithful and are mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ
  10,64,For them is good news in this worldly life and the Hereafter. There is no change in the promise of Allah. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the ultimate triumph
  10,65,"Do not let their words grieve you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Surely all honour and power belongs to Allah. He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  10,66,Certainly to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belong all those in the heavens and all those on the earth. And what do those who associate others with Allah really follow? They follow nothing but assumptions and do nothing but lie
  10,67,He is the One Who has made the night for you to rest in and the day bright. Surely in this are signs for people who listen
  10,68,"They¬†say, вАЬAllah has offspring.вАЭ¬†Glory be to Him! He is the Self-Sufficient. To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. You have no proof of this! Do you say about Allah what you do not know"
  10,69,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIndeed, those who fabricate lies against Allah will never succeed.вАЭ"
  10,70,"ЋєIt is onlyЋЇ a brief enjoyment in this world, then to Us is their return, then We will make them taste the severe punishment for their disbelief"
  10,71,"Relate to them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the story of Noah when he said to his people, вАЬO my People! If my presence and my reminders to you of AllahвАЩs signs are unbearable to you, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ I have put my trust in Allah. So devise a plot along with your associate-godsвАФand you do not have to be secretive about your plotвАФthen carry it out against me without delay"
  10,72,"And if you turn away, ЋєrememberЋЇ I have never demanded a reward from you Ћєfor delivering the messageЋЇ. My reward is only from Allah. And I have been commanded to be one of those who submit Ћєto AllahЋЇ.вАЭ"
  10,73,"But they still rejected him, so We saved him and those with him in the Ark and made them successors, and drowned those who rejected Our signs. See then what was the end of those who had been warned"
  10,74,Then after him We sent ЋєotherЋЇ messengers to their ЋєownЋЇ people and they came to them with clear proofs. But they would not believe in what they had rejected before. This is how We seal the hearts of the transgressors
  10,75,Then after these ЋєmessengersЋЇ We sent Moses and Aaron to Pharaoh and his chiefs with Our signs. But they behaved arrogantly and were a wicked people
  10,76,"When the truth came to them from Us, they said, вАЬThis is certainly pure magic!вАЭ"
  10,77,"Moses responded, вАЬIs this what you say about the truth when it has come to you? Is this magic? Magicians will never succeed.вАЭ"
  10,78,"They argued, вАЬHave you come to turn us away from the faith of our forefathers so that the two of you may become supreme in the land? We will never believe in you!вАЭ"
  10,79,"Pharaoh demanded, вАЬBring me every skilled magician.вАЭ"
  10,80,"When the magicians came, Moses said to them, вАЬCast whatever you wish to cast!вАЭ"
  10,81,"When they did, Moses said, вАЬWhat you have produced is mere magic, Allah will surely make it useless, for Allah certainly does not set right the work of the corruptors"
  10,82,And Allah establishes the truth by His WordsвАФeven to the dismay of the wicked.вАЭ
  10,83,"But no one believed in Moses except a few youths of his people, while fearing that Pharaoh and their own chiefs might persecute them. And certainly Pharaoh was a tyrant in the land, and he was truly a transgressor"
  10,84,"Moses said, вАЬO my people! If you do believe in Allah and submit Ћєto His WillЋЇ, then put your trust in Him.вАЭ"
  10,85,"They replied, вАЬIn Allah we trust. Our Lord! Do not subject us to the persecution of the oppressive people"
  10,86,and deliver us by Your mercy from the disbelieving people.вАЭ
  10,87,"We revealed to Moses and his brother, вАЬAppoint houses for your people in Egypt. Turn these houses into places of worship, establish prayer, and give good news to the believers!вАЭ"
  10,88,"Moses prayed, вАЬOur Lord! You have granted Pharaoh and his chiefs luxuries and riches in this worldly life, Ћєwhich they abusedЋЇ to lead people astray from Your Way! Our Lord, destroy their riches and harden their hearts so that they will not believe until they see the painful punishment.вАЭ"
  10,89,"Allah responded Ћєto Moses and AaronЋЇ,¬†вАЬYour prayer is answered! So be steadfast and do not follow the way of those who do not know.вАЭ"
  10,90,"We brought the Children of Israel across the sea. Then Pharaoh and his soldiers pursued them unjustly and oppressively. But as Pharaoh was drowning, he cried out, вАЬI believe that there is no god except that in whom the Children of Israel believe, and I am ЋєnowЋЇ one of those who submit.вАЭ"
  10,91,"ЋєHe was told,ЋЇ вАЬNow Ћєyou believeЋЇ? But you always disobeyed and were one of the corruptors"
  10,92,Today We will preserve your corpse so that you may become an example¬†for those who come after you. And surely most people are heedless of Our examples!вАЭ
  10,93,"Indeed, We settled the Children of Israel in a blessed land,¬†and granted them good, lawful provisions. They did not differ until knowledge came to them.¬†Surely your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their differences"
  10,94,"If you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are in doubt about Ћєthese storiesЋЇ that We have revealed to you, then ask those who read the Scripture before you. The truth has certainly come to you from your Lord, so do not be one of those who doubt"
  10,95,and do not be one of those who deny AllahвАЩs signs or you will be one of the losers
  10,96,"Indeed, those against whom AllahвАЩs decree Ћєof tormentЋЇ is justified will not believeвАФ"
  10,97,even if every sign were to come to themвАФuntil they see the painful punishment
  10,98,"If only there had been a society which believed Ћєbefore seeing the tormentЋЇ and, therefore, benefited from its belief, like the people of Jonah.¬†When they believed, We lifted from them the torment of disgrace in this world and allowed them enjoyment for a while"
  10,99,"Had your Lord so willed ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, all ЋєpeopleЋЇ on earth would have certainly believed, every single one of them! Would you then force people to become believers"
  10,100,"It is not for any soul to believe except by AllahвАЩs leave, and He will bring His wrath upon those who are unmindful"
  10,101,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬConsider all that is in the heavens and the earth!вАЭ Yet neither signs nor warners are of any benefit to those who refuse to believe"
  10,102,"Are they waiting for ЋєanythingЋЇ except the same torments that befell those before them? Say, вАЬKeep waiting then! I too am waiting with you.вАЭ"
  10,103,Then We saved Our messengers and those who believed. For it is Our duty to save the believers
  10,104,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO humanity! If you are in doubt of my faith, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ I do not worship those ЋєidolsЋЇ you worship instead of Allah. But I worship Allah, Who has the power to cause your death. And I have been commanded, вАШBe one of the believers,вАЩ"
  10,105,"and, вАШBe steadfast in faith in all uprightness, and do not be one of the polytheists,вАЩ"
  10,106,"and вАШDo not invoke, instead of Allah, what can neither benefit nor harm youвАФfor if you do, then you will certainly be one of the wrongdoers,вАЩ"
  10,107,"and вАШIf Allah touches you with harm, none can undo it except Him. And if He intends good for you, none can withhold His bounty. He grants it to whoever He wills of His servants. And He is the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЩвАЭ"
  10,108,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO humanity! The truth has surely come to you from your Lord. So whoever chooses to be guided, it is only for their own good. And whoever chooses to stray, it is only to their own loss. And I am not a keeper over you.вАЭ"
  10,109,"And follow what is revealed to you, and be patient until Allah passes His judgment. For He is the Best of Judges"
  11,1,"Alif-L√£m-Ra. ЋєThis isЋЇ a Book whose verses are well perfected and then fully explained. ЋєIt isЋЇ from the One ЋєWho isЋЇ All-Wise, All-Aware"
  11,2,"ЋєTell them, O Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWorship none but Allah. Surely I am a warner and deliverer of good news to you from Him"
  11,3,"And seek your LordвАЩs forgiveness and turn to Him in repentance. He will grant you a good provision for an appointed term and graciously reward the doers of good. But if you turn away, then I truly fear for you the torment of a formidable Day"
  11,4,To Allah is your return. And He is Most Capable of everything.вАЭ
  11,5,"Indeed, they¬†enfold Ћєwhat is inЋЇ their hearts, ЋєtryingЋЇ to hide it from Him! But even when they cover themselves with their clothes, He knows what they conceal and what they reveal. Surely He knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  11,6,There is no moving creature on earth whose provision is not guaranteed by Allah. And He knows where it lives and where it is laid to rest. All is ЋєwrittenЋЇ in a perfect Record
  11,7,"He is the One Who created the heavens and the earth in six DaysвАФand His Throne was upon the watersвАФin order to test which of you is best in deeds. And if you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ say, вАЬSurely you will ЋєallЋЇ be raised up after death,вАЭ the disbelievers will certainly say, вАЬThat is nothing but pure magic!вАЭ"
  11,8,"And if We delay their punishment until an appointed time, they will definitely say, вАЬWhat is holding it back?вАЭ Indeed, on the Day it overtakes them, it will not be averted from them, and they will be overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  11,9,"If We give people a taste of Our mercy then take it away from them, they become utterly desperate, ungrateful"
  11,10,"But if We give them a taste of prosperity after being touched with adversity, they say, вАЬMy ills are gone,вАЭ and become totally prideful and boastful"
  11,11,except those who patiently endure and do good. It is they who will have forgiveness and a mighty reward
  11,12,"Perhaps you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ may wish to give up some of what is revealed to you and may be distressed by it because they say, вАЬIf only a treasure had been sent down to him, or an angel had come with him!вАЭ You are only a warner, and Allah is the Trustee of All Affairs"
  11,13,"Or do they say, вАЬHe¬†has fabricated this ЋєQuranЋЇ!вАЭ? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬProduce ten fabricated s√їrahs like it and seek help from whoever you canвАФother than AllahвАФif what you say is true!вАЭ"
  11,14,"But if your helpers fail you, then know that it has been revealed with the knowledge of Allah, and that there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him! Will you ЋєnotЋЇ then submit Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  11,15,"Whoever desires ЋєonlyЋЇ this worldly life and its luxuries, We will pay them in full for their deeds in this lifeвАФnothing will be left out"
  11,16,It is they who will have nothing in the Hereafter except the Fire. Their efforts in this life will be fruitless and their deeds will be useless
  11,17,"ЋєCan these people be compared toЋЇ those ЋєbelieversЋЇ who stand on clear proof from their Lord, backed by Ћєthe Quran asЋЇ a witness from Him, and preceded by the Book of Moses Ћєwhich was revealedЋЇ as a guide and mercy? It is those ЋєbelieversЋЇ who have faith in it. But whoever from the ЋєdisbelievingЋЇ groups¬†rejects it, the Fire will be their destiny. So do not be in doubt of it. It is certainly the truth from your Lord, but most people do not believe"
  11,18,"Who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against Allah? They will be brought before their Lord, and the witnesses¬†will say, вАЬThese are the ones who lied against their Lord.вАЭ Surely AllahвАЩs condemnation is upon the wrongdoers"
  11,19,"who hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from AllahвАЩs Path, striving to make it ЋєappearЋЇ crooked, and disbelieve in the Hereafter"
  11,20,"They will never frustrate Allah on earth, and they will have no protector besides Allah. Their punishment will be multiplied, for they failed to hear or see Ћєthe truthЋЇ"
  11,21,"It is they who have ruined themselves, and whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ they fabricated will fail them"
  11,22,"Without a doubt, they will be the worst losers in the Hereafter"
  11,23,"Surely those who believe, do good, and humble themselves before their Lord will be the residents of Paradise. They will be there forever"
  11,24,"The example of these two parties is that of the blind and the deaf, compared to the seeing and the hearing. Can the two be equal? Will you not then be mindful"
  11,25,"Surely We sent Noah to his people. ЋєHe said,ЋЇ вАЬIndeed, I am sent to you with a clear warning"
  11,26,that you should worship none but Allah. I truly fear for you the torment of a painful Day.вАЭ
  11,27,"The disbelieving chiefs of his people said, вАЬWe see you only as a human being like ourselves, and we see that no one follows you except the lowliest among us, who do so ЋєhastilyЋЇ without thinking.¬†We do not see anything that makes Ћєall ofЋЇ you any better than us. In fact, we think you are liars.вАЭ"
  11,28,"He said, вАЬO my people! Consider if I stand on a clear proof from my Lord and He has blessed me with a mercy from Himself,¬†which you fail to see. Should we ЋєthenЋЇ force it on you against your will"
  11,29,"O my people! I do not ask you for a payment for this ЋєmessageЋЇ. My reward is only from Allah. And I will never dismiss the believers, for they will surely meet their Lord. But I can see that you are a people acting ignorantly"
  11,30,O my people! Who would protect me from Allah if I were to dismiss them? Will you not then be mindful
  11,31,"I do not say to you that I possess AllahвАЩs treasuries or know the unseen, nor do I claim to be an angel, nor do I say that Allah will never grant goodness to those you look down upon. Allah knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ within them. ЋєIf I did,ЋЇ then I would truly be one of the wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  11,32,"They protested, вАЬO Noah! You have argued with us far too much, so bring upon us what you threaten us with, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  11,33,"He responded, вАЬIt is Allah Who can bring it upon you if He wills, and then you will have no escape"
  11,34,"My advice will not benefit youвАФno matter how hard I tryвАФif Allah wills ЋєforЋЇ you to stray. He is your Lord, and to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned.вАЭ"
  11,35,"Or do they say, вАЬHe¬†has fabricated this ЋєQuranЋЇ!вАЭ? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf I have done so, then I bear the burden of that sin! But I am free from your sinful accusation.вАЭ"
  11,36,"And it was revealed to Noah, вАЬNone of your people will believe except those who already have. So do not be distressed by what they have been doing"
  11,37,"And build the Ark under Our ЋєwatchfulЋЇ Eyes and directions, and do not plead with Me for those who have done wrong, for they will surely be drowned.вАЭ"
  11,38,"So he began to build the Ark, and whenever some of the chiefs of his people passed by, they mocked him. He said, вАЬIf you laugh at us, we will ЋєsoonЋЇ laugh at you similarly"
  11,39,You will soon come to know who will be visited by a humiliating torment Ћєin this lifeЋЇ and overwhelmed by an everlasting punishment Ћєin the nextЋЇ.вАЭ
  11,40,"And when Our command came and the oven burst Ћєwith waterЋЇ,¬†We said Ћєto NoahЋЇ, вАЬTake into the Ark a pair from every species along with your familyвАФexcept those against whom the decree Ћєto drownЋЇ has already been passedвАФand those who believe.вАЭ But none believed with him except for a few"
  11,41,"And he said, вАЬBoard it! In the Name of Allah it will sail and cast anchor. Surely my Lord is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  11,42,"And ЋєsoЋЇ the Ark sailed with them through waves like mountains. Noah called out to his son, who stood apart, вАЬO my dear son! Come aboard with us and do not be with the disbelievers.вАЭ"
  11,43,"He replied, вАЬI will take refuge on a mountain, which will protect me from the water.вАЭ Noah cried, вАЬToday no one is protected from AllahвАЩs decree except those to whom He shows mercy!вАЭ And the waves came between them, and his son was among the drowned"
  11,44,"And it was said, вАЬO earth! Swallow up your water. And O sky! Withhold Ћєyour rainЋЇ.вАЭ The floodwater receded and the decree was carried out. The Ark rested on Mount Judi, and it was said, вАЬAway with the wrongdoing people!вАЭ"
  11,45,"Noah called out to his Lord, saying, вАЬMy Lord! Certainly my son is ЋєalsoЋЇ of my family, Your promise is surely true, and You are the most just of all judges!вАЭ"
  11,46,"Allah replied, вАЬO Noah! He is certainly not of your familyвАФhe was entirely of unrighteous conduct. So do not ask Me about what you have no knowledge of! I warn you so you do not fall into ignorance.вАЭ"
  11,47,"Noah pleaded, вАЬMy Lord, I seek refuge in You from asking You about what I have no knowledge of, and unless You forgive me and have mercy on me, I will be one of the losers.вАЭ"
  11,48,"It was said, вАЬO Noah! Disembark with Our peace and blessings on you and some of the descendants of those with you. As for the others, We will allow them Ћєa briefЋЇ enjoyment, then they will be touched with a painful punishment from Us.вАЭ"
  11,49,"This is one of the stories of the unseen, which we reveal to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Neither you nor your people knew it before this. So be patient! Surely the ultimate outcome belongs ЋєonlyЋЇ to the righteous"
  11,50,"And to the people of вАЩ√Вd We sent their brother H√їd. He said, вАЬO my people! Worship Allah. You have no god other than Him. You do nothing but fabricate lies Ћєagainst AllahЋЇ"
  11,51,O my people! I do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇ. My reward is only from the One Who created me. Will you not then understand
  11,52,"And O my people! Seek your LordвАЩs forgiveness and turn to Him in repentance. He will shower you with rain in abundance, and add strength to your strength. So do not turn away, persisting in wickedness.вАЭ"
  11,53,"They argued, вАЬO H√їd! You have not given us any clear proof, and we will never abandon our gods upon your word, nor will we believe in you"
  11,54,"All we can say is that some of our gods have possessed you with evil.вАЭ He said, вАЬI call Allah to witness, and you too bear witness, that I ЋєtotallyЋЇ reject whatever you associate"
  11,55,with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ. So let all of you plot against me without delay
  11,56,I have put my trust in AllahвАФmy Lord and your Lord. There is no living creature that is not completely under His control.¬†Surely my LordвАЩs Way is perfect justice
  11,57,"But if you turn away, I have already delivered to you what I have been sent with. My Lord will replace you with others. You are not harming Him in the least. Indeed, my Lord is a ЋєvigilantЋЇ Keeper over all things.вАЭ"
  11,58,"When Our command came, We rescued H√їd and those who believed with him by a mercy from Us, saving them from a harsh torment"
  11,59,"That was вАЩ√Вd. They denied the signs of their Lord, disobeyed His messengers, and followed the command of every stubborn tyrant"
  11,60,"They were followed by a curse in this world, as they will be on the Day of Judgment. Surely вАЩ√Вd denied their Lord. So away with вАЩ√Вd, the people of H√їd"
  11,61,"And to the people of Tham√їd We sent their brother бєҐ√ҐliбЄ•. He said, вАЬO my people! Worship Allah. You have no god other than Him. He Ћєis the One WhoЋЇ produced you from the earth and settled you on it. So seek His forgiveness and turn to Him in repentance. Surely my Lord is Ever Near, All-Responsive Ћєto prayersЋЇ.вАЭ"
  11,62,"They argued, вАЬO бєҐ√ҐliбЄ•! We truly had high hopes in you before this.¬†How dare you forbid us to worship what our forefathers had worshipped? We are certainly in alarming doubt about what you are inviting us to.вАЭ"
  11,63,"He responded, вАЬO my people! Consider if I stand on a clear proof from my Lord and He has blessed me with a mercy from Him. Who could help me against Allah if I were to disobey Him? You would only contribute to my doom"
  11,64,"And O my people! This she-camel of Allah is a sign for you.¬†So leave her to graze ЋєfreelyЋЇ on AllahвАЩs earth and do her no harm, or a swift punishment will overtake you!вАЭ"
  11,65,"But they killed her, so he warned ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬYou have ЋєonlyЋЇ three ЋєmoreЋЇ days to enjoy life in your homesвАФthis is an unfailing promise!вАЭ"
  11,66,"When Our command came, We saved бєҐ√ҐliбЄ• and those who believed with him by a mercy from Us and spared them the disgrace of that Day. Surely your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Powerful, Almighty"
  11,67,"And the ЋєmightyЋЇ blast overtook the wrongdoers, so they fell lifeless in their homes"
  11,68,"as if they had never lived there. Surely Tham√їd denied their Lord, so away with Tham√їd"
  11,69,"And surely Our messenger-angels came to Abraham with good news Ћєof a sonЋЇ. They greeted Ћєhim withЋЇ, вАЬPeace!вАЭ And he replied, вАЬPeace Ћєbe upon youЋЇ!вАЭ Then it was not long before he brought ЋєthemЋЇ a Ћєfat,ЋЇ roasted calf"
  11,70,"And when he saw that their hands did not reach for the food, he became suspicious and fearful of them.¬†They reassured ЋєhimЋЇ, вАЬDo not be afraid! We are ЋєangelsЋЇ sent ЋєonlyЋЇ against the people of Lot.вАЭ"
  11,71,"And his wife was standing by, so she laughed,¬†then We gave her good news of Ћєthe birth ofЋЇ Isaac, and, after him, Jacob"
  11,72,"She wondered, вАЬOh, my! How can I have a child in this old age, and my husband here is an old man? This is truly an astonishing thing!вАЭ"
  11,73,"They responded, вАЬAre you astonished by AllahвАЩs decree? May AllahвАЩs mercy and blessings be upon you, O people of this house. Indeed, He is Praiseworthy, All-Glorious.вАЭ"
  11,74,"Then after the fear had left Abraham, and the good news had reached him, he began to plead with Us for the people of Lot"
  11,75,"Truly, Abraham was forbearing, tender-hearted, and ever turning Ћєto his LordЋЇ"
  11,76,"ЋєThe angels said,ЋЇ вАЬO Abraham! Plead no more! Your LordвАЩs decree has already come, and they will certainly be afflicted with a punishment that cannot be averted!вАЭ"
  11,77,"When Our messenger-angels came to Lot, he was distressed and worried by their arrival.¬†He said, вАЬThis is a terrible day.вАЭ"
  11,78,"And Ћєthe men ofЋЇ his peopleвАФwho were used to shameful deedsвАФcame to him rushing. He pleaded, вАЬO my people! Here are my daughters¬†Ћєfor marriageЋЇвАФthey are pure for you. So fear Allah, and do not humiliate me by disrespecting my guests. Is there not ЋєevenЋЇ a single right-minded man among you?вАЭ"
  11,79,"They argued, вАЬYou certainly know that we have no need for your daughters. You already know what we desire!вАЭ"
  11,80,"He responded, вАЬIf only I had the strength Ћєto resist youЋЇ or could rely on a strong supporter.вАЭ"
  11,81,"The angels said, вАЬO Lot! We are the messengers of your Lord. They will never reach you. So travel with your family in the dark of night, and do not let any of you look back, except your wife. She will certainly suffer the fate of the others.¬†Their appointed time is the morning. Is the morning not near?вАЭ"
  11,82,"When Our command came, We turned the cities upside down and rained down on them clustered stones of baked clay"
  11,83,marked by your Lord ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. And these stones are not far from the ЋєpaganЋЇ wrongdoers
  11,84,"And to the people of Midian We sent their brother ShuвАЩaib. He said, вАЬO my people! Worship Allah. You have no god other than Him. And do not give short measure and weight. I do see you in prosperity now, but I truly fear for you the torment of an overwhelming Day"
  11,85,"O my people! Give full measure and weigh with justice. Do not defraud people of their property, nor go about spreading corruption in the land"
  11,86,What is left Ћєas a lawful gainЋЇ by Allah is far better for you if you are ЋєtrulyЋЇ believers. And I am not a keeper over you.вАЭ
  11,87,"They asked ЋєsarcasticallyЋЇ, вАЬO ShuвАЩaib! Does your prayer command you that we should abandon what our forefathers worshipped or give up managing our wealth as we please? Indeed, you are such a tolerant, sensible man!вАЭ"
  11,88,"He said, вАЬO my people! Consider if I stand on a clear proof from my Lord and He has blessed me with a good provision from Him. I do not want to do what I am forbidding you from. I only intend reform to the best of my ability. My success comes only through Allah. In Him I trust and to Him I turn"
  11,89,"O my people! Do not let your opposition to me lead you to a fate similar to that of the people of Noah, or H√їd, or бєҐ√ҐliбЄ•. And the people of Lot are not far from you"
  11,90,"So seek your LordвАЩs forgiveness and turn to Him in repentance. Surely my Lord is Most Merciful, All-Loving.вАЭ"
  11,91,"They threatened, вАЬO ShuвАЩaib! We do not comprehend much of what you say, and surely we see you powerless among us. Were it not for your clan, we would have certainly stoned you, for you are nothing to us.вАЭ"
  11,92,"He said, вАЬO my people! Do you have more regard for my clan than for Allah, turning your back on Him entirely? Surely my Lord is Fully Aware of what you do"
  11,93,"O my people! Persist in your ways, for I ЋєtooЋЇ will persist in mine. You will soon come to know who will be visited by a humiliating torment and is a liar! And watch! I too am watching with you!вАЭ"
  11,94,"When Our command came, We saved ShuвАЩaib and those who believed with him by a mercy from Us. And the ЋєmightyЋЇ blast overtook the wrongdoers, so they fell lifeless in their homes"
  11,95,as if they had never lived there. So away with Midian as it was with Tham√їd
  11,96,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs and compelling proof"
  11,97,"to Pharaoh and his chiefs, but they followed the command of Pharaoh, and PharaohвАЩs command was not well guided"
  11,98,He will be before his people on the Day of Judgment and will lead them into the Fire. What an evil place to be led into
  11,99,They were followed by a curse in this ЋєlifeЋЇ and Ћєwill receive anotherЋЇ on the Day of Judgment. What an evil gift to receive
  11,100,"These are accounts, We relate to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, of the ЋєdestroyedЋЇ cities. Some are still standing ЋєbarrenЋЇ, while others have been mowed down"
  11,101,"We did not wrong them, rather they wronged themselves. The gods they invoked beside Allah were of no help at all when the command of your Lord came, and only contributed to their ruin"
  11,102,"Such is the ЋєcrushingЋЇ grip of your Lord when He seizes the societies entrenched in wrongdoing. Indeed, His grip is ЋєterriblyЋЇ painful and severe"
  11,103,Surely in this is a sign for those who fear the torment of the Hereafter. That is a Day for which humanity will be gathered and a Day Ћєthat will beЋЇ witnessed Ћєby allЋЇ
  11,104,We only delay it for a fixed term
  11,105,"When that Day arrives, no one will dare speak except with His permission. Some of them will be miserable, others joyful"
  11,106,"As for those bound for misery, they will be in the Fire, where they will be sighing and gasping"
  11,107,"staying there forever, as long as the heavens and the earth will endure, except what your Lord wills.¬†Surely your Lord does what He intends"
  11,108,"And as for those destined to joy, they will be in Paradise, staying there forever, as long as the heavens and the earth will endure, except what your Lord willsвАФa ЋєgenerousЋЇ giving, without end"
  11,109,"So do not be in doubt ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about what those ЋєpagansЋЇ worship. They worship nothing except what their forefathers worshipped before ЋєthemЋЇ. And We will certainly give them their share Ћєof punishmentЋЇ in full, without any reduction"
  11,110,"Indeed, We had given Moses the Scripture, but differences arose regarding it. Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord,¬†their differences would have been settled Ћєat onceЋЇ. They are truly in alarming doubt about it"
  11,111,And surely your Lord will fully pay all for their deeds. He is certainly All-Aware of what they do
  11,112,"So be steadfast as you are commanded ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, along with those who turn Ћєin submission to AllahЋЇ with you. And do not transgress. Surely He is All-Seeing of what you ЋєbelieversЋЇ do"
  11,113,"And do not be inclined to the wrongdoers or you will be touched by the Fire. For then you would have no protectors other than Allah, nor would you be helped"
  11,114,Establish prayer ЋєO ProphetЋЇ at both ends of the day and in the early part of the night.¬†Surely good deeds wipe out evil deeds. That is a reminder for the mindful
  11,115,And be patient! Certainly Allah does not discount the reward of the good-doers
  11,116,"If only there had been among the ЋєdestroyedЋЇ peoples before you, ЋєO believers,ЋЇ virtuous individuals who forbade corruption in the landвАФother than the few We had saved Ћєfrom the tormentЋЇ. But the wrongdoers ЋєonlyЋЇ pursued their ЋєworldlyЋЇ pleasures, becoming wicked"
  11,117,And your Lord ЋєO ProphetЋЇ would never destroy a society unjustly while its people were acting rightly
  11,118,"Had your Lord so willed, He would have certainly made humanity one single community Ћєof believersЋЇ, but they will always Ћєchoose toЋЇ differвАФ"
  11,119,"except those shown mercy by your LordвАФand so He created them Ћєto choose freelyЋЇ. And so the Word of your Lord will be fulfilled: вАЬI will surely fill up Hell with jinn and humans all together.вАЭ"
  11,120,"And We relate to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the stories of the messengers to reassure your heart. And there has come to you in this Ћєs√їrahЋЇ the truth, a warning Ћєto the disbelieversЋЇ, and a reminder to the believers"
  11,121,"Say to those who disbelieve, вАЬPersist in your ways; we will certainly persist in ours"
  11,122,And wait! Surely we ЋєtooЋЇ are waiting.вАЭ
  11,123,To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the knowledge of what is hidden in the heavens and the earth. And to Him all matters are returned. So worship Him and put your trust in Him. And your Lord is never unaware of what you do
  12,1,Alif-L√£m-Ra. These are the verses of the clear Book
  12,2,"Indeed, We have sent it down as an Arabic Quran¬†so that you may understand"
  12,3,"We relate to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the best of stories through Our revelation of this Quran, though before this you were totally unaware Ћєof themЋЇ"
  12,4,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when Joseph said to his father, вАЬO my dear father! Indeed I dreamt of eleven stars, and the sun, and the moonвАФI saw them prostrating to me!вАЭ"
  12,5,"He replied, вАЬO my dear son! Do not relate your vision to your brothers, or they will devise a plot against you. Surely Satan is a sworn enemy to humankind"
  12,6,"And so will your Lord choose you ЋєO JosephЋЇ, and teach you the interpretation of dreams, and perfect His favour upon you and the descendants of JacobвАФЋєjustЋЇ as He once perfected it upon your forefathers, Abraham and Isaac. Surely your Lord is All-Knowing, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  12,7,"Indeed, in the story of Joseph and his brothers there are lessons for all who ask"
  12,8,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when they said Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬSurely Joseph and his brother ЋєBenjaminЋЇ are more beloved to our father than we, even though we are a group of so many.¬†Indeed, our father is clearly mistaken"
  12,9,"Kill Joseph or cast him out to some ЋєdistantЋЇ land so that our fatherвАЩs attention will be only ours, then after that you may Ћєrepent andЋЇ become righteous people!вАЭ"
  12,10,"One of them said, вАЬDo not kill Joseph. But if you must do something, throw him into the bottom of a well so perhaps he may be picked up by some travellers.вАЭ"
  12,11,"They said, вАЬO our father! Why do you not trust us with Joseph, although we truly wish him well"
  12,12,Send him out with us tomorrow so that he may enjoy himself and play. And we will really watch over him.вАЭ
  12,13,"He responded, вАЬIt would truly sadden me if you took him away with you, and I fear that a wolf may devour him while you are negligent of him.вАЭ"
  12,14,"They said, вАЬIf a wolf were to devour him, despite our strong group, then we would certainly be losers!вАЭ"
  12,15,"And so, when they took him away and decided to throw him into the bottom of the well, We inspired him: вАЬЋєOne dayЋЇ you will remind them of this deed of theirs while they are unaware Ћєof who you areЋЇ.вАЭ"
  12,16,"Then they returned to their father in the evening, weeping"
  12,17,"They cried, вАЬOur father! We went racing and left Joseph with our belongings, and a wolf devoured him! But you will not believe us, no matter how truthful we are.вАЭ"
  12,18,"And they brought his shirt, stained with false blood.¬†He responded, вАЬNo! Your souls must have tempted you to do something ЋєevilЋЇ. So ЋєI can only endure withЋЇ beautiful patience!¬†It is AllahвАЩs help that I seek to bear your claims.вАЭ"
  12,19,"And there came some travellers, and they sent their water-boy who let down his bucket into the well. He cried out, вАЬOh, what a great find! Here is a boy!вАЭ And they took him secretly Ћєto be soldЋЇ as merchandise, but Allah is All-Knowing of what they did"
  12,20,"They ЋєlaterЋЇ sold him for a cheap price, just a few silver coinsвАФonly wanting to get rid of him"
  12,21,"The man from Egypt¬†who bought him said to his wife, вАЬTake good care of him, perhaps he may be useful to us or we may adopt him as a son.вАЭ This is how We established Joseph in the land, so that We might teach him the interpretation of dreams. AllahвАЩs Will always prevails, but most people do not know"
  12,22,"And when he reached maturity, We gave him wisdom and knowledge. This is how We reward the good-doers"
  12,23,"And the lady, in whose house he lived, tried to seduce him. She locked the doors ЋєfirmlyЋЇ and said, вАЬCome to me!вАЭ He replied, вАЬAllah is my refuge! It is Ћєnot right to betrayЋЇ my master, who has taken good care of me. Indeed, the wrongdoers never succeed.вАЭ"
  12,24,"She advanced towards him, and he would have done likewise, had he not seen a sign from his Lord.¬†This is how We kept evil and indecency away from him, for he was truly one of Our chosen servants"
  12,25,"They raced for the door and she tore his shirt from the back, only to find her husband at the door. She cried, вАЬWhat is the penalty for someone who tried to violate your wife, except imprisonment or a painful punishment?вАЭ"
  12,26,"Joseph responded, вАЬIt was she who tried to seduce me.вАЭ And a witness from her own family testified: вАЬIf his shirt is torn from the front, then she has told the truth and he is a liar"
  12,27,"But if it is torn from the back, then she has lied and he is truthful.вАЭ"
  12,28,"So when her husband saw that JosephвАЩs shirt was torn from the back, he said Ћєto herЋЇ, вАЬThis must be Ћєan exampleЋЇ of the cunning of you ЋєwomenЋЇ! Indeed, your cunning is so shrewd"
  12,29,O Joseph! Forget about this. And you ЋєO wifeЋЇ! Seek forgiveness for your sin.¬†It certainly has been your fault.вАЭ
  12,30,"Some women of the city gossiped, вАЬThe Chief MinisterвАЩs wife is trying to seduce her slave-boy. Love for him has plagued her heart. Indeed, we see that she is clearly mistaken.вАЭ"
  12,31,"When she heard about their gossip,¬†she invited them and set a banquet for them. She gave each one a knife, then said Ћєto JosephЋЇ, вАЬCome out before them.вАЭ When they saw him, they were so stunned Ћєby his beautyЋЇ that they cut their hands,¬†and exclaimed, вАЬGood God! This cannot be human; this must be a noble angel!вАЭ"
  12,32,"She said, вАЬThis is the one for whose love you criticized me! I did try to seduce him but he ЋєfirmlyЋЇ refused. And if he does not do what I order him to, he will certainly be imprisoned and ЋєfullyЋЇ disgraced.вАЭ"
  12,33,"Joseph prayed, вАЬMy Lord! I would rather be in jail than do what they invite me to. And if You do not turn their cunning away from me, I might yield to them and fall into ignorance.вАЭ"
  12,34,"So his Lord responded to him, turning their cunning away from him. Surely He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  12,35,"And so it occurred to those in charge, despite seeing all the proofs Ћєof his innocenceЋЇ, that he should be imprisoned for a while"
  12,36,"And two other servants went to jail with Joseph. One of them said, вАЬI dreamt I was pressing wine.вАЭ The other said, вАЬI dreamt I was carrying ЋєsomeЋЇ bread on my head, from which birds were eating.вАЭ ЋєThen both said,ЋЇ вАЬTell us their interpretation, for we surely see you as one of the good-doers.вАЭ"
  12,37,"Joseph replied, вАЬI can even tell you what kind of meal you will be served before you receive it. This ЋєknowledgeЋЇ is from what my Lord has taught me. I have shunned the faith of a people who disbelieve in Allah and deny the Hereafter"
  12,38,"I follow the faith of my fathers: Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. It is not ЋєrightЋЇ for us to associate anything with Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇ. This is part of AllahвАЩs grace upon us and humanity, but most people are not grateful"
  12,39,"O my fellow-prisoners! Which is far better: many different lords or AllahвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  12,40,"Whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you worship instead of Him are mere names which you and your forefathers have made upвАФa practice Allah has never authorized. It is only Allah Who decides. He has commanded that you worship none but Him. That is the upright faith, but most people do not know"
  12,41,"вАЬO my fellow-prisoners! ЋєThe firstЋЇ one of you will serve wine to his master, and the other will be crucified and the birds will eat from his head. The matter about which you inquired has been decided.вАЭ"
  12,42,"Then he said to the one he knew would survive, вАЬMention me in the presence of your master.вАЭ But Satan made him forget to mention Joseph to his master, so he remained in prison for several years"
  12,43,"And Ћєone dayЋЇ the King¬†said, вАЬI dreamt of seven fat cows eaten up by seven skinny ones; and seven green ears of grain and ЋєsevenЋЇ others dry. O chiefs! Tell me the meaning of my dream if you can interpret dreams.вАЭ"
  12,44,"They replied, вАЬThese are confused visions and we do not know the interpretation of such dreams.вАЭ"
  12,45,"ЋєFinally,ЋЇ the surviving ex-prisoner remembered ЋєJosephЋЇ after a long time and said, вАЬI will tell you its interpretation, so send me forth Ћєto JosephЋЇ.вАЭ"
  12,46,"ЋєHe said,ЋЇ вАЬJoseph, O man of truth! Interpret for us Ћєthe dream ofЋЇ seven fat cows eaten up by seven skinny ones; and seven green ears of grain and ЋєsevenЋЇ others dry, so that I may return to the people and let them know.вАЭ"
  12,47,"Joseph replied, вАЬYou will plant ЋєgrainЋЇ for seven consecutive years, leaving in the ear whatever you will harvest, except for the little you will eat"
  12,48,"Then after that will come seven years of great hardship which will consume whatever you have saved, except the little you will store Ћєfor seedЋЇ"
  12,49,Then after that will come a year in which people will receive abundant rain and they will press Ћєoil and wineЋЇ.вАЭ
  12,50,"The King ЋєthenЋЇ said, вАЬBring him to me.вАЭ When the messenger came to him, Joseph said, вАЬGo back to your master and ask him about the case of the women who cut their hands. Surely my Lord has ЋєfullЋЇ knowledge of their cunning.вАЭ"
  12,51,"The King asked Ћєthe womenЋЇ, вАЬWhat did you get when you tried to seduce Joseph?вАЭ They replied, вАЬAllah forbid! We know nothing indecent about him.вАЭ Then the Chief MinisterвАЩs wife admitted, вАЬNow the truth has come to light. It was I who tried to seduce him, and he is surely truthful"
  12,52,"From this, Joseph should know that I did not speak dishonestly about him in his absence, for Allah certainly does not guide the scheming of the dishonest"
  12,53,"And I do not seek to free myself from blame, for indeed the soul is ever inclined to evil, except those shown mercy by my Lord. Surely my Lord is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  12,54,"The King said, вАЬBring him to me. I will employ him exclusively in my service.вАЭ And when Joseph spoke to him, the King said, вАЬToday you are highly esteemed and fully trusted by us.вАЭ"
  12,55,"Joseph proposed, вАЬPut me in charge of the store-houses of the land, for I am truly reliable and adept.вАЭ"
  12,56,"This is how We established Joseph in the land to settle wherever he pleased. We shower Our mercy on whoever We will, and We never discount the reward of the good-doers"
  12,57,And the reward of the Hereafter is far better for those who are faithful and are mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ
  12,58,And JosephвАЩs brothers came and entered his presence. He recognized them but they were unaware of who he really was
  12,59,"When he had provided them with their supplies, he demanded, вАЬBring me your brother on your fatherвАЩs side.¬†Do you not see that I give full measure and I am the best of hosts"
  12,60,"But if you do not bring him to me Ћєnext timeЋЇ, I will have no grain for you, nor will you ever come close to me again.вАЭ"
  12,61,"They promised, вАЬWe will try to convince his father to let him come. We will certainly do Ћєour bestЋЇ.вАЭ"
  12,62,Joseph ordered his servants to put his brothersвАЩ money back into their saddlebags so that they would find it when they returned to their family and perhaps they would come back
  12,63,"When JosephвАЩs brothers returned to their father, they pleaded, вАЬO our father! We have been denied ЋєfurtherЋЇ supplies. So send our brother with us so that we may receive our measure, and we will definitely watch over him.вАЭ"
  12,64,"He responded, вАЬShould I trust you with him as I once trusted you with his brother ЋєJosephЋЇ? But ЋєonlyЋЇ Allah is the best Protector, and He is the Most Merciful of the merciful.вАЭ"
  12,65,"When they opened their bags, they discovered that their money had been returned to them. They argued, вАЬO our father! What more can we ask for? Here is our money, fully returned to us. Now we can buy more food for our family. We will watch over our brother, and obtain an extra camel-load of grain. That load can be easily secured.вАЭ"
  12,66,"Jacob insisted, вАЬI will not send him with you until you give me a solemn oath by Allah that you will certainly bring him back to me, unless you are totally overpowered.вАЭ Then after they had given him their oaths, he concluded, вАЬAllah is a Witness to what we have said.вАЭ"
  12,67,"He then instructed ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬO my sons! Do not enter Ћєthe cityЋЇ all through one gate, but through separate gates.¬†I cannot help you against Ћєwhat is destined byЋЇ Allah in the least. It is only Allah Who decides. In Him I put my trust. And in Him let the faithful put their trust.вАЭ"
  12,68,"Then when they entered as their father had instructed them, this did not help them against Ћєthe Will ofЋЇ Allah whatsoever. It was just a desire in JacobвАЩs heart which he satisfied. He was truly blessed with ЋєgreatЋЇ knowledge because of what We had taught him, but most people have no knowledge"
  12,69,"When they entered JosephвАЩs presence, he called his brother ЋєBenjaminЋЇ aside, and confided Ћєto himЋЇ, вАЬI am indeed your brother ЋєJosephЋЇ! So do not feel distressed about what they have been doing.вАЭ"
  12,70,"When Joseph had provided them with supplies, he slipped the royal cup into his brotherвАЩs bag. Then a herald cried, вАЬO people of the caravan! You must be thieves!вАЭ"
  12,71,"They asked, turning back, вАЬWhat have you lost?вАЭ"
  12,72,"The herald Ћєalong with the guardsЋЇ replied, вАЬWe have lost the KingвАЩs measuring cup. And whoever brings it will be awarded a camel-load Ћєof grainЋЇ. I guarantee it.вАЭ"
  12,73,"JosephвАЩs brothers replied, вАЬBy Allah! You know well that we did not come to cause trouble in the land, nor are we thieves.вАЭ"
  12,74,"JosephвАЩs men asked, вАЬWhat should be the price for theft, if you are lying?вАЭ"
  12,75,"JosephвАЩs brothers responded, вАЬThe price will be Ћєthe enslavement ofЋЇ the one in whose bag the cup is found. That is how we punish the wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  12,76,"Joseph began searching their bags before that of his brother ЋєBenjaminЋЇ, then brought it out of BenjaminвАЩs bag. This is how We inspired Joseph to plan. He could not have taken his brother under the KingвАЩs law, but Allah had so willed. We elevate in rank whoever We will. But above those ranking in knowledge is the One All-Knowing"
  12,77,"ЋєTo distance themselves,ЋЇ JosephвАЩs brothers argued, вАЬIf he has stolen, so did his ЋєfullЋЇ brother before.вАЭ¬†But Joseph suppressed his outrageвАФrevealing nothing to themвАФand said Ћєto himselfЋЇ, вАЬYou are in such an evil position,¬†and Allah knows best Ћєthe truth ofЋЇ what you claim.вАЭ"
  12,78,"They appealed, вАЬO Chief Minister! He has a very old father, so take one of us instead. We surely see you as one of the good-doers.вАЭ"
  12,79,"Joseph responded, вАЬAllah forbid that we should take other than the one with whom we found our property. Otherwise, we would surely be unjust.вАЭ"
  12,80,"When they lost all hope in him, they spoke privately. The eldest of them said, вАЬDo you not know that your father had taken a solemn oath by Allah from you, nor how you failed him regarding Joseph before? So I am not leaving this land until my father allows me to, or Allah decides for me. For He is the Best of Judges"
  12,81,"Return to your father and say, вАШO our father! Your son committed theft. We testify only to what we know. We could not guard against the unforeseen"
  12,82,Ask Ћєthe people ofЋЇ the land where we were and the caravan we travelled with. We are certainly telling the truth.вАЩвАЭ
  12,83,"He cried, вАЬNo! Your souls must have tempted you to do something ЋєevilЋЇ. So ЋєI am left with nothing butЋЇ beautiful patience!¬†I trust Allah will return them all to me. Surely He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Knowing, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  12,84,"He turned away from them, lamenting, вАЬAlas, poor Joseph!вАЭ And his eyes turned white out of the grief he suppressed"
  12,85,"They said, вАЬBy Allah! You will not cease to remember Joseph until you lose your health or ЋєevenЋЇ your life.вАЭ"
  12,86,"He replied, вАЬI complain of my anguish and sorrow only to Allah, and I know from Allah what you do not know"
  12,87,"O my sons! Go and search ЋєdiligentlyЋЇ for Joseph and his brother. And do not lose hope in the mercy of Allah, for no one loses hope in AllahвАЩs mercy except those with no faith.вАЭ"
  12,88,"When they entered JosephвАЩs presence, they pleaded, вАЬO Chief Minister! We and our family have been touched with hardship, and we have brought only a few worthless coins, but ЋєpleaseЋЇ give us our supplies in full and be charitable to us. Indeed, Allah rewards the charitable.вАЭ"
  12,89,"He asked, вАЬDo you remember what you did to Joseph and his brother in your ignorance?вАЭ"
  12,90,"They replied Ћєin shockЋЇ, вАЬAre you really Joseph?вАЭ He said, вАЬI am Joseph, and here is my brother ЋєBenjaminЋЇ! Allah has truly been gracious to us. Surely whoever is mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ and patient, then certainly Allah never discounts the reward of the good-doers.вАЭ"
  12,91,"They admitted, вАЬBy Allah! Allah has truly preferred you over us, and we have surely been sinful.вАЭ"
  12,92,"Joseph said, вАЬThere is no blame on you today. May Allah forgive you! He is the Most Merciful of the merciful"
  12,93,"Go with this shirt of mine and cast it over my fatherвАЩs face, and he will regain his sight. Then come back to me with your whole family.вАЭ"
  12,94,"When the caravan departed Ћєfrom EgyptЋЇ, their father said Ћєto those around himЋЇ, вАЬYou may think I am senile, but I certainly sense the smell of Joseph.вАЭ"
  12,95,"They replied, вАЬBy Allah! You are definitely still in your old delusion.вАЭ"
  12,96,"But when the bearer of the good news arrived, he cast the shirt over JacobвАЩs face, so he regained his sight. Jacob then said Ћєto his childrenЋЇ, вАЬDid I not tell you that I truly know from Allah what you do not know?вАЭ"
  12,97,"They begged, вАЬO our father! Pray for the forgiveness of our sins. We have certainly been sinful.вАЭ"
  12,98,"He said, вАЬI will pray to my Lord for your forgiveness.¬†He ЋєaloneЋЇ is indeed the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  12,99,"When they entered JosephвАЩs presence, he received his parents ЋєgraciouslyЋЇ and said, вАЬEnter Egypt, Allah willing, in security.вАЭ"
  12,100,"Then he raised his parents to the throne, and they all fell down in prostration to Joseph,¬†who then said, вАЬO my dear father! This is the interpretation of my old dream. My Lord has made it come true. He was truly kind to me when He freed me from prison, and brought you all from the desert after Satan had ignited rivalry between me and my siblings.¬†Indeed my Lord is subtle in fulfilling what He wills. Surely He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Knowing, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  12,101,вАЬMy Lord! You have surely granted me authority and taught me the interpretation of dreams. ЋєOЋЇ Originator of the heavens and the earth! You are my Guardian in this world and the Hereafter. Allow me to die as one who submits¬†and join me with the righteous.вАЭ
  12,102,"That is from the stories of the unseen which We reveal to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. You were not present when they ЋєallЋЇ¬†made up their minds, and when they plotted Ћєagainst JosephЋЇ"
  12,103,And most people will not believeвАФno matter how keen you areвАФ
  12,104,even though you are not asking them for a reward for this ЋєQuranЋЇ. It is only a reminder to the whole world
  12,105,How many signs in the heavens and the earth do they pass by with indifference
  12,106,And most of them do not believe in Allah without associating others with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ
  12,107,"Do they feel secure that an overwhelming torment from Allah will not overtake them, or that the Hour will not take them by surprise when they least expect ЋєitЋЇ"
  12,108,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬThis is my way. I invite to Allah with insightвАФI and those who follow me. Glory be to Allah, and I am not one of the polytheists.вАЭ"
  12,109,We only sent before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ men inspired by Us from among the people of each society. Have the deniers not travelled through the land to see what was the end of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them? And surely the ЋєeternalЋЇ Home of the Hereafter is far better for those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ. Will you not then understand
  12,110,"And when the messengers despaired and their people thought the messengers had been denied help, Our help came to them Ћєat lastЋЇ. We then saved whoever We willed, and Our punishment is never averted from the wicked people"
  12,111,"In their stories there is truly a lesson for people of reason. This message cannot be a fabrication, rather Ћєit isЋЇ a confirmation of previous revelation, a detailed explanation of all things, a guide, and a mercy for people of faith"
  13,1,"Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m-Ra. These are the verses of the Book. What has been revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ from your Lord is the truth, but most people do not believe"
  13,2,"It is Allah Who has raised the heavens without pillarsвАФas you can seeвАФthen established Himself on the Throne. He has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. He conducts the whole affair. He makes the signs clear so that you may be certain of the meeting with your Lord"
  13,3,"And He is the One Who spread out the earth and placed firm mountains and rivers upon it, and created fruits of every kind in pairs.¬†He covers the day with night. Surely in this are signs for those who reflect"
  13,4,"And on the earth there are ЋєdifferentЋЇ neighbouring tracts, gardens of grapevines, ЋєvariousЋЇ crops, palm treesвАФsome stemming from the same root, others standing alone. They are all irrigated with the same water, yet We make some taste better than others. Surely in this are signs for those who understand"
  13,5,"ЋєNow,ЋЇ if anything should amaze you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, then it is their question: вАЬWhen we are reduced to dust, will we really be raised as a new creation?вАЭ It is they who have disbelieved in their Lord. It is they who will have shackles around their necks. And it is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever"
  13,6,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to hasten the torment rather than grace, though there have ЋєalreadyЋЇ been ЋєmanyЋЇ torments before them. Surely your Lord is full of forgiveness for people, despite their wrongdoing, and your Lord is truly severe in punishment"
  13,7,"The disbelievers say, вАЬIf only a sign could be sent down to him from his Lord.вАЭ You ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are only a warner. And every people had a guide"
  13,8,Allah knows what every female bears and what increases and decreases in the wombs.¬†And with Him everything is determined with precision
  13,9,"ЋєHe is theЋЇ Knower of the seen and the unseenвАФthe All-Great, Most Exalted"
  13,10,"It is the same Ћєto HimЋЇ whether any of you speaks secretly or openly, whether one hides in the darkness of night or goes about in broad daylight"
  13,11,"For each one there are successive angels before and behind, protecting them by AllahвАЩs command. Indeed, Allah would never change a peopleвАЩs state Ћєof favourЋЇ until they change their own state Ћєof faithЋЇ. And if it is AllahвАЩs Will to torment a people, it can never be averted, nor can they find a protector other than Him"
  13,12,"He is the One Who shows you lightning, inspiring Ћєyou withЋЇ hope and fear,¬†and produces heavy clouds"
  13,13,"The thunder glorifies His praises, as do the angels in awe of Him. He sends thunderbolts, striking with them whoever He wills. Yet they dispute about Allah. And He is tremendous in might"
  13,14,"Calling upon Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is the truth. But those ЋєidolsЋЇ the pagans invoke besides Him ЋєcanЋЇ never respond to them in any way. ЋєIt isЋЇ just like someone who stretches out their hands to water, Ћєasking itЋЇ to reach their mouths, but it can never do so. The calls of the disbelievers are only in vain"
  13,15,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ bow down Ћєin submissionЋЇ¬†all those in the heavens and the earthвАФwillingly or unwillinglyвАФas do their shadows, morning and evening"
  13,16,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWho is the Lord of the heavens and the earth?вАЭ Say, вАЬAllah!вАЭ Ask ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬWhy ЋєthenЋЇ have you taken besides Him lords who cannot even benefit or protect themselves?вАЭ Say, вАЬCan the blind and the sighted be equal? Or can darkness and light be equal?вАЭ¬†Or have they associated with Allah partners who ЋєsupposedlyЋЇ produced a creation like His, leaving them confused between the two creations? Say, вАЬAllah is the Creator of all things, and He is the One, the Supreme.вАЭ"
  13,17,"He sends down rain from the sky, causing the valleys to flow, each according to its capacity. The currents then carry along rising foam, similar to the slag produced from metal that people melt in the fire for ornaments or tools. This is how Allah compares truth to falsehood. The ЋєworthlessЋЇ residue is then cast away, but what benefits people remains on the earth. This is how Allah sets forth parables"
  13,18,"Those who respond to Ћєthe call ofЋЇ their Lord will have the finest reward. As for those who do not respond to Him, even if they were to possess everything in the world twice over, they would certainly offer it to ransom themselves. They will face strict judgment, and Hell will be their home. What an evil place to rest"
  13,19,Can the one who knows that your LordвАЩs revelation to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ is the truth be like the one who is blind? None will be mindful Ћєof thisЋЇ except people of reason
  13,20,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who honour AllahвАЩs covenant, never breaking the pledge"
  13,21,"and those who maintain whatever ЋєtiesЋЇ Allah has ordered to be maintained, stand in awe of their Lord, and fear strict judgment"
  13,22,"And Ћєthey areЋЇ those who endure patiently, seeking their LordвАЩs pleasure,¬†establish prayer, donate from what We have provided for themвАФsecretly and openlyвАФand respond to evil with good. It is they who will have the ultimate abode"
  13,23,"the Gardens of Eternity, which they will enter along with the righteous among their parents, spouses, and descendants. And the angels will enter upon them from every gate, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ"
  13,24,вАЬPeace be upon you for your perseverance. How excellent is the ultimate abode!вАЭ
  13,25,"And those who violate AllahвАЩs covenant after it has been affirmed, break whatever ЋєtiesЋЇ Allah has ordered to be maintained, and spread corruption in the landвАФit is they who will be condemned and will have the worst abode"
  13,26,"Allah gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills. And the disbelievers become prideful of Ћєthe pleasures ofЋЇ this worldly life. But the life of this world, compared to the Hereafter, is nothing but a fleeting enjoyment"
  13,27,"The disbelievers say, вАЬIf only a sign could be sent down to him from his Lord.вАЭ¬†Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIndeed, Allah leaves to stray whoever He wills, and guides to Himself whoever turns to HimвАФ"
  13,28,those who believe and whose hearts find comfort in the remembrance of Allah. Surely in the remembrance of Allah do hearts find comfort
  13,29,"Those who believe and do good, for them will be bliss and an honourable destination.вАЭ"
  13,30,"And so We have sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to a community, like ЋєWe did withЋЇ earlier communities, so that you may recite to them what We have revealed to you. Yet they deny the Most Compassionate.¬†Say, вАЬHe is my Lord! There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. In Him I put my trust, and to Him I turn Ћєin repentanceЋЇ.вАЭ"
  13,31,"If there were a recitation that could cause mountains to move, or the earth to split, or the dead to speak, Ћєit would have been this QuranЋЇ. But all matters are by AllahвАЩs Will. Have the believers not yet realized that had Allah willed, He could have guided all of humanity? And disasters will continue to afflict the disbelievers or strike close to their homes for their misdeeds, until AllahвАЩs promise comes to pass. Surely Allah never fails in His promise"
  13,32,"Other messengers had already been ridiculed before you, but I delayed the disbelievers Ћєfor a whileЋЇ then seized them. And how ЋєhorribleЋЇ was My punishment"
  13,33,"Is Ћєthere any equal toЋЇ the Vigilant One Who knows what every soul commits? Yet the pagans have associated others with Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇ. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬName them! Or do you Ћєmean toЋЇ inform Him of something He does not know on the earth? Or are these ЋєgodsЋЇ just empty words?вАЭ In fact, the disbelieversвАЩ falsehood has been made so appealing to them that they have been turned away from the Path. And whoever Allah leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  13,34,"For them is punishment in this worldly life, but the punishment of the Hereafter is truly far worse. And none can shield them from Allah"
  13,35,The description of the Paradise promised to the righteous is that under it rivers flow; eternal is its fruit as well as its shade. That is the ЋєultimateЋЇ outcome for the righteous. But the outcome for the disbelievers is the Fire
  13,36,"ЋєThe believers amongЋЇ those who were given the Scripture rejoice at what has been revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, while some ЋєdisbelievingЋЇ factions deny a portion of it. Say, вАЬI have only been commanded to worship Allah, associating none with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ. To Him I invite ЋєallЋЇ, and to Him is my return.вАЭ"
  13,37,"And so We have revealed it as an authority in Arabic. And if you were to follow their desires after ЋєallЋЇ the knowledge that has come to you, there would be none to protect or shield you from Allah"
  13,38,We have certainly sent messengers before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ and blessed them with wives and offspring. It was not for any messenger to bring a sign without AllahвАЩs permission. Every destined matter has a ЋєsetЋЇ time
  13,39,"Allah eliminates and confirms what He wills, and with Him is the Master Record"
  13,40,"Whether We show you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ some of what We threaten them with, or cause you to die Ћєbefore thatЋЇ, your duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ. Judgment is for Us"
  13,41,Do they not see that We gradually reduce their land from its borders? Allah decidesвАФnone can reverse His decision. And He is swift in reckoning
  13,42,"Those ЋєdisbelieversЋЇ before them ЋєsecretlyЋЇ planned, but Allah has the ultimate plan. He knows what every soul commits. And the disbelievers will soon know who will have the ultimate outcome"
  13,43,"The disbelievers say, вАЬYou ЋєMuбЄ•ammadЋЇ are no messenger.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAllah is sufficient as a Witness between me and you, as is whoever has knowledge of the Scripture.вАЭ"
  14,1,"Alif-L√£m-Ra. ЋєThis isЋЇ a Book which We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ so that you may lead people out of darkness and into light, by the Will of their Lord, to the Path of the Almighty, the PraiseworthyвАФ"
  14,2,"Allah, to Whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And woe to the disbelievers because of a severe torment"
  14,3,"ЋєThey areЋЇ the ones who favour the life of this world over the Hereafter and hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah, striving to make it ЋєappearЋЇ crooked. It is they who have gone far astray"
  14,4,"We have not sent a messenger except in the language of his people to clarify Ћєthe messageЋЇ for them. Then Allah leaves whoever He wills to stray and guides whoever He wills. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  14,5,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs, Ћєordering him,ЋЇ вАЬLead your people out of darkness and into light, and remind them of AllahвАЩs days Ћєof favourЋЇ.вАЭ Surely in this are signs for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  14,6,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ when Moses said to his people, вАЬRemember AllahвАЩs favour upon you when He rescued you from the people of Pharaoh, who afflicted you with dreadful tormentвАФslaughtering your sons and keeping your women. That was a severe test from your Lord"
  14,7,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when your Lord proclaimed, вАШIf you are grateful, I will certainly give you more. But if you are ungrateful, surely My punishment is severe.вАЩвАЭ"
  14,8,"Moses added, вАЬIf you along with everyone on earth were to be ungrateful, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ Allah is indeed Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy.вАЭ"
  14,9,"Have you not ЋєalreadyЋЇ received the stories of those who were before you: the people of Noah, вАЩ√Вd, Tham√їd, and those after them? Only Allah knows how many they were. Their messengers came to them with clear proofs, but they put their hands over their mouths¬†and said, вАЬWe totally reject what you have been sent with, and we are certainly in alarming doubt about what you are inviting us to.вАЭ"
  14,10,"Their messengers asked ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬIs there any doubt about Allah, the Originator of the heavens and the earth? He is inviting you in order to forgive your sins, and delay your end until your appointed term.вАЭ¬†They argued, вАЬYou are no more than humans like us! You ЋєonlyЋЇ wish to turn us away from what our forefathers worshipped. So bring us some compelling proof.вАЭ"
  14,11,"Their messengers said to them, вАЬWe are ЋєindeedЋЇ only humans like you, but Allah favours whoever He chooses of His servants. It is not for us to bring you any proof without AllahвАЩs permission. And in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  14,12,"Why should we not put our trust in Allah, when He has truly guided us to Ћєthe very best ofЋЇ ways? Indeed, we will patiently endure whatever harm you may cause us. And in Allah let the faithful put their trust.вАЭ"
  14,13,"The disbelievers then threatened their messengers, вАЬWe will certainly expel you from our land, unless you return to our faith.вАЭ So their Lord revealed to them, вАЬWe will surely destroy the wrongdoers"
  14,14,and make you reside in the land after them. This is for whoever is in awe of standing before Me and fears My warning.вАЭ
  14,15,"And both sides called for judgment, so every stubborn tyrant was doomed"
  14,16,"Awaiting them is Hell, and they will be left to drink oozing pus"
  14,17,"which they will sip with difficulty, and can hardly swallow. Death will overwhelm them from every side, yet they will not Ћєbe able toЋЇ die. Awaiting them still is harsher torment"
  14,18,The parable of the deeds of those who disbelieve in their Lord is that of ashes fiercely blown away by wind on a stormy day. They will gain nothing from what they have earned. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the farthest one can stray
  14,19,"Have you not seen that Allah created the heavens and the earth for a reason? If He wills, He can eliminate you and produce a new creation"
  14,20,And that is not difficult for Allah Ћєat allЋЇ
  14,21,"They will all appear before Allah, and the lowly ЋєfollowersЋЇ will appeal to the arrogant ЋєleadersЋЇ, вАЬWe were your ЋєdedicatedЋЇ followers, so will you ЋєthenЋЇ protect us from AllahвАЩs torment in any way?вАЭ They will reply, вАЬHad Allah guided us, we would have guided you. ЋєNowЋЇ it is all the same for us whether we suffer patiently or impatiently, there is no escape for us.вАЭ"
  14,22,"And Satan will say Ћєto his followersЋЇ after the judgment has been passed, вАЬIndeed, Allah has made you a true promise.¬†I too made you a promise, but I failed you. I did not have any authority over you. I only called you, and you responded to me. So do not blame me; blame yourselves. I cannot save you, nor can you save me. Indeed, I denounce your previous association of me with Allah Ћєin loyaltyЋЇ. Surely the wrongdoers will suffer a painful punishment.вАЭ"
  14,23,"Those who believe and do good will be admitted into Gardens, under which rivers flowвАФto stay there forever by the Will of their LordвАФwhere they will be greeted with вАЬPeace!вАЭ"
  14,24,Do you not see how Allah compares a good word to a good tree? Its root is firm and its branches reach the sky
  14,25,"ЋєalwaysЋЇ yielding its fruit in every season by the Will of its Lord. This is how Allah sets forth parables for the people, so perhaps they will be mindful"
  14,26,"And the parable of an evil word is that of an evil tree, uprooted from the earth, having no stability"
  14,27,Allah makes the believers steadfast with the firm Word Ћєof faithЋЇ¬†in this worldly life and the Hereafter. And Allah leaves the wrongdoers to stray. For Allah does what He wills
  14,28,Have you not seen those ЋєdisbelieversЋЇ who meet AllahвАЩs favours with ingratitude and lead their own people to their doom
  14,29,In Hell they will burn. What an evil place for settlement
  14,30,"They set up equals to Allah to mislead ЋєothersЋЇ from His Way. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬEnjoy yourselves! Surely your destination is the Fire.вАЭ"
  14,31,Tell My believing servants to establish prayer and donate from what We have provided for themвАФopenly and secretlyвАФbefore the arrival of a Day in which there will be no ransom or friendly connections
  14,32,"It is Allah Who created the heavens and the earth and sends down rain from the sky, causing fruits to grow as a provision for you. He has subjected the ships for your service, sailing through the sea by His command, and has subjected the rivers for you"
  14,33,"He has ЋєalsoЋЇ subjected for you the sun and the moon, both constantly orbiting, and has subjected the day and night for you"
  14,34,"And He has granted you all that you asked Him for. If you tried to count AllahвАЩs blessings, you would never be able to number them. Indeed humankind is truly unfair, ЋєtotallyЋЇ ungrateful"
  14,35,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when Abraham prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Make this city Ћєof MeccaЋЇ secure, and keep me and my children away from the worship of idols"
  14,36,"My Lord! They have caused many people to go astray. So whoever follows me is with me, and whoever disobeys meвАФthen surely You are ЋєstillЋЇ All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  14,37,"Our Lord! I have settled some of my offspring in a barren valley, near Your Sacred House, our Lord, so that they may establish prayer. So make the hearts of ЋєbelievingЋЇ people incline towards them and provide them with fruits, so perhaps they will be thankful"
  14,38,Our Lord! You certainly know what we conceal and what we reveal. Nothing on earth or in heaven is hidden from Allah
  14,39,All praise is for Allah who has blessed me with Ishmael and Isaac in my old age. My Lord is indeed the Hearer of ЋєallЋЇ prayers
  14,40,My Lord! Make me and those ЋєbelieversЋЇ of my descendants keep up prayer. Our Lord! Accept my prayers
  14,41,"Our Lord! Forgive me, my parents, and the believers on the Day when the judgment will come to pass.вАЭ"
  14,42,Do not think ЋєO ProphetЋЇ that Allah is unaware of what the wrongdoers do. He only delays them until a Day when ЋєtheirЋЇ eyes will stare in horrorвАФ
  14,43,"rushing forth, heads raised, never blinking, hearts void"
  14,44,"And warn the people of the Day when the punishment will overtake Ћєthe wicked amongЋЇ them, and the wrongdoers will cry, вАЬOur Lord! Delay us for a little while. We will respond to Your call and follow the messengers!вАЭ ЋєIt will be said,ЋЇ вАЬDid you not swear before that you would never be removed Ћєto the next lifeЋЇ?вАЭ"
  14,45,"You passed by the ruins of those Ћєdestroyed peoplesЋЇ who had wronged themselves.¬†It was made clear to you how We dealt with them, and We gave you ЋєmanyЋЇ examples"
  14,46,"They devised every plot, which was fully known to Allah, but their plotting was not enough to ЋєevenЋЇ overpower mountains Ћєlet alone AllahЋЇ"
  14,47,"So do not think ЋєO ProphetЋЇ that Allah will fail to keep His promise to His messengers. Allah is indeed Almighty, capable of punishment"
  14,48,"ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day ЋєwhenЋЇ the earth will be changed into a different earth and the heavens as well, and all will appear before AllahвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  14,49,On that Day you will see the wicked bound together in chains
  14,50,"with garments of tar, and their faces covered with flames"
  14,51,"As such, Allah will reward every soul for what it has committed. Surely Allah is swift in reckoning"
  14,52,"This ЋєQuranЋЇ is a ЋєsufficientЋЇ message for humanity so that they may take it as a warning and know that there is only One God, and so that people of reason may be mindful"
  15,1,Alif-L√£m-Ra. These are the verses of the Book; the clear Quran
  15,2,ЋєThe day will come whenЋЇ the disbelievers will certainly wish they had submitted Ћєto AllahЋЇ
  15,3,"ЋєSoЋЇ let them eat and enjoy themselves and be diverted by ЋєfalseЋЇ hope, for they will soon know"
  15,4,We have never destroyed a society without a destined term
  15,5,"No people can advance their doom, nor can they delay it"
  15,6,"They say, вАЬO you to whom the Reminder¬†is revealed! You must be insane"
  15,7,"Why do you not bring us the angels, if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  15,8,"We do not send the angels down except for a just cause, and then Ћєthe end ofЋЇ the disbelievers will not be delayed"
  15,9,"It is certainly We Who have revealed the Reminder, and it is certainly We Who will preserve it"
  15,10,"Indeed, We sent messengers before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ among the groups of early peoples"
  15,11,but no messenger ever came to them without being mocked
  15,12,This is how We allow disbelief Ћєto steepЋЇ into the hearts of the wicked
  15,13,They would not believe in this ЋєQuranЋЇ despite the ЋєmanyЋЇ examples of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before
  15,14,"And even if We opened for them a gate to heaven, through which they continued to ascend"
  15,15,"still they would say, вАЬOur eyes have truly been dazzled! In fact, we must have been bewitched.вАЭ"
  15,16,"Indeed, We have placed constellations in the sky, and adorned it for all to see"
  15,17,And We protected it from every accursed devil
  15,18,"except the one eavesdropping, who is then pursued by a visible flare"
  15,19,"As for the earth, We spread it out and placed upon it firm mountains, and caused everything to grow there in perfect balance"
  15,20,"And We made in it means of sustenance for you and others, who you do not provide for"
  15,21,"There is not any means Ћєof sustenanceЋЇ whose reserves We do not hold, only bringing it forth in precise measure"
  15,22,"We send fertilizing winds, and bring down rain from the sky for you to drink. It is not you who hold its reserves"
  15,23,Surely it is We Who give life and cause death. And We are the ЋєEternalЋЇ Successor
  15,24,We certainly know those who have gone before you and those who will come after ЋєyouЋЇ
  15,25,"Surely your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ will gather them together Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ. He is truly All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  15,26,"Indeed, We created man from sounding clay moulded from black mud"
  15,27,"As for the jinn, We created them earlier from smokeless fire"
  15,28,"ЋєRemember, O ProphetЋЇ when your Lord said to the angels, вАЬI am going to create a human being from sounding clay moulded from black mud"
  15,29,"So when I have fashioned him and had a spirit of My Own ЋєcreationЋЇ breathed into him, fall down in prostration to him.вАЭ"
  15,30,So the angels prostrated all togetherвАФ
  15,31,"but not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who refused to prostrate with the others"
  15,32,"Allah asked, вАЬO Ibl√Ѓs! What is the matter with you that you did not join others in prostration?вАЭ"
  15,33,"He replied, вАЬIt is not for me to prostrate to a human You created from sounding clay moulded from black mud.вАЭ"
  15,34,"Allah commanded, вАЬThen get out of Paradise, for you are truly cursed"
  15,35,And surely upon you is condemnation until the Day of Judgment.вАЭ
  15,36,"Satan appealed, вАЬMy Lord! Then delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.вАЭ"
  15,37,"Allah said, вАЬYou will be delayed"
  15,38,until the appointed Day.вАЭ
  15,39,"Satan responded, вАЬMy Lord! For allowing me to stray I will surely tempt them on earth and mislead them all together"
  15,40,except Your chosen servants among them.вАЭ
  15,41,"Allah said, вАЬThis is the Way, binding on Me"
  15,42,"you will certainly have no authority over My servants, except the deviant who follow you"
  15,43,"and surely Hell is their destined place, all together"
  15,44,"It has seven gates, to each a group of them is designated.вАЭ"
  15,45,"Indeed, the righteous will be amid Gardens and springs"
  15,46,"ЋєIt will be said to them,ЋЇ вАЬEnter in peace and security.вАЭ"
  15,47,"We will remove whatever bitterness they had in their hearts.¬†In a friendly manner, they will be on thrones, facing one another"
  15,48,"No fatigue will touch them there, nor will they ever be asked to leave"
  15,49,"Inform My servants ЋєO ProphetЋЇ that I am truly the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  15,50,and that My torment is indeed the most painful
  15,51,And inform them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about AbrahamвАЩs guests
  15,52,"who entered upon him and greeted Ћєhim withЋЇ, вАЬPeace!вАЭ He ЋєlaterЋЇ said, вАЬSurely we are afraid of you.вАЭ"
  15,53,"They reassured ЋєhimЋЇ, вАЬDo not be afraid! Surely we give you good news of a knowledgeable son.вАЭ"
  15,54,"He wondered, вАЬDo you give me good news despite my old age? What unlikely news!вАЭ"
  15,55,"They responded, вАЬWe give you good news in all truth, so do not be one of those who despair.вАЭ"
  15,56,"He exclaimed, вАЬWho would despair of the mercy of their Lord except the misguided?вАЭ"
  15,57,"He ЋєthenЋЇ added, вАЬWhat is your mission, O messenger-angels?вАЭ"
  15,58,"They replied, вАЬWe have actually been sent to a wicked people"
  15,59,"As for the family of Lot, we will certainly deliver them all"
  15,60,except his wife. We have determined that she will be one of the doomed.вАЭ
  15,61,So when the messengers came to the family of Lot
  15,62,"he said, вАЬYou are surely an unfamiliar people!вАЭ"
  15,63,"They responded, вАЬWe have come to you with that ЋєtormentЋЇ which they have doubted"
  15,64,"We come to you with the truth, and we are certainly truthful"
  15,65,"So travel with your family in the dark of night, and follow ЋєcloselyЋЇ behind them. Do not let any of you look back, and go where you are commanded.вАЭ"
  15,66,"We revealed to him this decree: вАЬThose ЋєsinnersЋЇ will be uprooted in the morning.вАЭ"
  15,67,"And there came the men of the city, rejoicing"
  15,68,"Lot pleaded, вАЬIndeed, these are my guests, so do not embarrass me"
  15,69,Fear Allah and do not humiliate me.вАЭ
  15,70,"They responded, вАЬHave we not forbidden you from protecting anyone?вАЭ"
  15,71,"He said, вАЬO my people! Here are my daughters¬†Ћєso marry themЋЇ if you wish to do so.вАЭ"
  15,72,"By your life ЋєO ProphetЋЇ,¬†they certainly wandered blindly, intoxicated Ћєby lustЋЇ"
  15,73,So the ЋєmightyЋЇ blast overtook them at sunrise
  15,74,And We turned the cities Ћєof Sodom and GomorrahЋЇ upside down and rained upon them stones of baked clay
  15,75,Surely in this are signs for those who contemplate
  15,76,Their ruins still lie along a known route
  15,77,Surely in this is a sign for those who believe
  15,78,And the residents of the Forest were truly wrongdoers
  15,79,so We inflicted punishment upon them. The ruins of both nations still lie on a well-known road
  15,80,"Indeed, the residents of the Stone Valley also denied the messengers"
  15,81,"We gave them Our signs, but they turned away from them"
  15,82,"They carved their homes in the mountains, feeling secure"
  15,83,But the ЋєmightyЋЇ blast overtook them in the morning
  15,84,and all they achieved was of no help to them
  15,85,"We have not created the heavens and the earth and everything in between except for a purpose. And the Hour is certain to come, so forgive graciously"
  15,86,"Surely your Lord is the Master Creator, All-Knowing"
  15,87,We have certainly granted you the seven often-repeated verses¬†and the great Quran
  15,88,"Do not let your eyes crave the ЋєfleetingЋЇ pleasures We have provided for some of the disbelievers, nor grieve for them. And be gracious to the believers"
  15,89,"And say, вАЬI am truly sent with a clear warningвАЭвАФ"
  15,90,Ћєa warningЋЇ similar to what We sent to those who divided Ћєthe ScripturesЋЇ
  15,91,"who ЋєnowЋЇ accept parts of the Quran, rejecting others"
  15,92,So by your Lord! We will certainly question them all
  15,93,about what they used to do
  15,94,"So proclaim what you have been commanded, and turn away from the polytheists"
  15,95,Surely We will be sufficient for you against the mockers
  15,96,who set up ЋєotherЋЇ gods with Allah. They will soon come to know
  15,97,We certainly know that your heart is truly distressed by what they say
  15,98,So glorify the praises of your Lord and be one of those who ЋєalwaysЋЇ pray
  15,99,and worship your Lord until the inevitable¬†comes your way
  16,1,"The command of Allah is at hand, so do not hasten it. Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate Ћєwith Him in worshipЋЇ"
  16,2,"He sends down the angels with revelation by His command to whoever He wills of His servants, Ћєstating:ЋЇ вАЬWarn ЋєhumanityЋЇ that there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Me, so be mindful of Me ЋєaloneЋЇ.вАЭ"
  16,3,He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. Exalted is He above what they associate with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ
  16,4,"He created humans from a sperm-drop, thenвАФbehold!вАФthey openly challenge ЋєHimЋЇ"
  16,5,"And He created the cattle for you as a source of warmth, food, and Ћєmany otherЋЇ benefits"
  16,6,They are also pleasing to you when you bring them home and when you take them out to graze
  16,7,"And they carry your loads to ЋєdistantЋЇ lands which you could not otherwise reach without great hardship. Surely your Lord is Ever Gracious, Most Merciful"
  16,8,"ЋєHe also createdЋЇ horses, mules, and donkeys for your transportation and adornment. And He creates what you do not know"
  16,9,"It is upon Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ to ЋєclearlyЋЇ show the Straight Way. Other ways are deviant. Had He willed, He would have easily imposed guidance upon all of you"
  16,10,"He is the One Who sends down rain from the sky, from which you drink and by which plants grow for your cattle to graze"
  16,11,"With it He produces for you ЋєvariousЋЇ crops, olives, palm trees, grapevines, and every type of fruit. Surely in this is a sign for those who reflect"
  16,12,"And He has subjected for your benefit the day and the night, the sun and the moon. And the stars have been subjected by His command. Surely in this are signs for those who understand"
  16,13,And ЋєHe subjectedЋЇ for you whatever He has created on earth of varying colours.¬†Surely in this is a sign for those who are mindful
  16,14,"And He is the One Who has subjected the sea, so from it you may eat tender seafood and extract ornaments to wear. And you see the ships ploughing their way through it, so you may seek His bounty and give thanks Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  16,15,"He has placed into the earth firm mountains, so it does not shake with you, as well as rivers, and pathways so you may find your way"
  16,16,Also by landmarks and stars do people find their way
  16,17,Can the One Who creates be equal to those who do not? Will you not then be mindful
  16,18,"If you tried to count AllahвАЩs blessings, you would never be able to number them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,19,And Allah knows what you conceal and what you reveal
  16,20,But those ЋєidolsЋЇ they invoke besides Allah cannot create anythingвАФthey themselves are created
  16,21,"They are dead, not aliveвАФnot even knowing when their followers will be resurrected"
  16,22,"Your God is ЋєonlyЋЇ One God. As for those who do not believe in the Hereafter, their hearts are in denial, and they are too proud"
  16,23,"Without a doubt, Allah knows what they conceal and what they reveal. He certainly does not like those who are too proud"
  16,24,"And when it is said to them, вАЬWhat has your Lord revealed?вАЭ They say, вАЬAncient fables!вАЭ"
  16,25,Let them bear their burdens in full on the Day of Judgment as well as some of the burdens of those they mislead without knowledge. Evil indeed is what they will bear
  16,26,"Indeed, those before them had plotted, but Allah struck at the ЋєveryЋЇ foundation of their structure, so the roof collapsed on top of them, and the torment came upon them from where they did not expect"
  16,27,"Then on the Day of Judgment He will humiliate them and say, вАЬWhere are My Ћєso-calledЋЇ associate-gods for whose sake you used to oppose Ћєthe believersЋЇ?вАЭ Those gifted with knowledge will say, вАЬSurely disgrace and misery today are upon the disbelievers.вАЭ"
  16,28,"Those whose souls the angels seize while they wrong themselves will then offer ЋєfullЋЇ submission Ћєand say falsely,ЋЇ вАЬWe did not do any evil.вАЭ ЋєThe angels will say,ЋЇ вАЬNo! Surely Allah fully knows what you used to do"
  16,29,"So enter the gates of Hell, to stay there forever. Indeed, what an evil home for the arrogant!вАЭ"
  16,30,"And ЋєwhenЋЇ it is said to those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, вАЬWhat has your Lord revealed?вАЭ They say, вАЬAll the best!вАЭ For those who do good in this world, there is goodness. But far better is the ЋєeternalЋЇ Home of the Hereafter. How excellent indeed is the home of the righteous"
  16,31,"the Gardens of Eternity which they will enter, under which rivers flow. In it they will have whatever they desire. This is how Allah rewards the righteousвАФ"
  16,32,"those whose souls the angels take while they are virtuous, saying Ћєto themЋЇ, вАЬPeace be upon you! Enter Paradise for what you used to do.вАЭ"
  16,33,"Are they only awaiting the coming of the angels or the command of your Lord ЋєO ProphetЋЇ? So were those before them. And Allah never wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  16,34,"Then the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds overtook them, and they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  16,35,"The polytheists argue, вАЬHad Allah willed, neither we nor our forefathers would have worshipped anything other than Him, nor prohibited anything without His command.вАЭ So did those before them. Is not the messengersвАЩ duty only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ clearly"
  16,36,"We surely sent a messenger to every community, saying, вАЬWorship Allah and shun false gods.вАЭ But some of them were guided by Allah, while others were destined to stray. So travel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers"
  16,37,"Even though you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are keen on their guidance, Allah certainly does not guide those He leaves to stray, and they will have no helpers"
  16,38,"They swear by Allah their most solemn oaths that Allah will never raise the dead to life. Yes ЋєHe willЋЇ! It is a true promise binding on Him, but most people do not know"
  16,39,"ЋєHe will do thatЋЇ to make clear to them what they disagreed on, and for the disbelievers to know that they were liars"
  16,40,"If We ever will something Ћєto existЋЇ, all We say is: вАЬBe!вАЭ And it is"
  16,41,"As for those who emigrated in Ћєthe cause ofЋЇ Allah after being persecuted, We will surely bless them with a good home in this world. But the reward of the Hereafter is far better, if only they knew"
  16,42,"ЋєIt isЋЇ they who have patiently endured, and in their Lord they put their trust"
  16,43,"We did not send ЋєmessengersЋЇ before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ except mere men inspired by Us. If you ЋєpolytheistsЋЇ do not know Ћєthis alreadyЋЇ, then ask those who have knowledge Ћєof the ScripturesЋЇ"
  16,44,"ЋєWe sent themЋЇ with clear proofs and divine Books. And We have sent down to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the Reminder, so that you may explain to people what has been revealed for them, and perhaps they will reflect"
  16,45,Do those who devise evil plots feel secure that Allah will not cause the earth to swallow them? Or that the torment will not come upon them in ways they cannot comprehend
  16,46,"Or that He will not seize them while they go about Ћєtheir dayЋЇ, for then they will have no escape"
  16,47,"Or that He will not destroy them gradually? But your Lord is truly Ever Gracious, Most Merciful"
  16,48,"Have they not considered how the shadows of everything Allah has created incline to the right and the left Ћєas the sun movesЋЇ, totally submitting to Allah in all humility"
  16,49,"And to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ bows down Ћєin submissionЋЇ¬†whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth of living creatures, as do the angelsвАФwho are not too proud Ћєto do soЋЇ"
  16,50,"They¬†fear their Lord above them, and do whatever they are commanded"
  16,51,"And Allah has said, вАЬDo not take two gods. There is only One God. So be in awe of Me ЋєaloneЋЇ.вАЭ"
  16,52,"To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth, and to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is the everlasting devotion. Will you then fear any other than Allah"
  16,53,"Whatever blessings you have are from Allah. Then whenever hardship touches you, to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ you cry Ћєfor helpЋЇ"
  16,54,"Then as soon as He removes the hardship from you, a group of you associates ЋєothersЋЇ with their Lord Ћєin worshipЋЇ"
  16,55,"only returning Our favours with ingratitude. So enjoy yourselves, for you will soon know"
  16,56,And they ЋєevenЋЇ assign to those ЋєidolsЋЇвАФwho know nothingвАФa share of what We have provided for them. By Allah! You will certainly be questioned about whatever ЋєliesЋЇ you used to fabricate Ћєagainst AllahЋЇ
  16,57,And they attribute Ћєangels asЋЇ daughters to AllahвАФglory be to Him!вАФthe opposite of what they desire for themselves
  16,58,"Whenever one of them is given the good news of a baby girl, his face grows gloomy, as he suppresses his rage"
  16,59,"He hides himself from the people because of the bad news he has received. Should he keep her in disgrace, or bury her ЋєaliveЋЇ in the ground? Evil indeed is their judgment"
  16,60,"To those who disbelieve in the Hereafter belong all evil qualities, whereas to Allah belong the finest attributes. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  16,61,"If Allah were to punish people ЋєimmediatelyЋЇ for their wrongdoing, He would not have left a single living being on earth. But He delays them for an appointed term. And when their time arrives, they cannot delay it for a moment, nor could they advance it"
  16,62,"They attribute to Allah what they hate Ћєfor themselvesЋЇ,¬†and their tongues utter the lie that they will have the finest reward. Without a doubt, for them is the Fire, where they will be abandoned"
  16,63,"By Allah! We have surely sent messengers to communities before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, but Satan made their misdeeds appealing to them. So he is their patron today, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  16,64,"We have revealed to you the Book only to clarify for them what they differed about, and as a guide and mercy for those who believe"
  16,65,"And Allah sends down rain from the sky, giving life to the earth after its death. Surely in this is a sign for those who listen"
  16,66,"And there is certainly a lesson for you in cattle: We give you to drink of what is in their bellies, from between digested food and blood: pure milk, pleasant to drink"
  16,67,And from the fruits of palm trees and grapevines you derive intoxicants¬†as well as wholesome provision. Surely in this is a sign for those who understand
  16,68,"And your Lord inspired the bees: вАЬMake ЋєyourЋЇ homes in the mountains, the trees, and in what people construct"
  16,69,"and feed from Ћєthe flower ofЋЇ any fruit Ћєyou pleaseЋЇ and follow the ways your Lord has made easy for you.вАЭ From their bellies comes forth liquid of varying colours, in which there is healing for people. Surely in this is a sign for those who reflect"
  16,70,"Allah has created you, and then causes you to die. And some of you are left to reach the most feeble stage of life so that they may know nothing after having known much. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  16,71,"And Allah has favoured some of you over others in provision. But those who have been much favoured would not share their wealth with those ЋєbondspeopleЋЇ in their possession, making them their equals.¬†Do they then deny AllahвАЩs favours"
  16,72,"And Allah has made for you spouses of your own kind, and given you through your spouses children and grandchildren.¬†And He has granted you good, lawful provisions. Are they then faithful to falsehood and ungrateful for AllahвАЩs favours"
  16,73,"Yet they worship besides Allah those ЋєidolsЋЇ who do not afford them any provision from the heavens and the earth, nor do they have the power to"
  16,74,"So do not set up equals to Allah, for Allah certainly knows and you do not know"
  16,75,"Allah sets forth a parable: a slave who lacks all means, compared to a ЋєfreeЋЇ man to whom We granted a good provision, of which he donates Ћєfreely,ЋЇ openly and secretly. Are they equal? Praise be to Allah. In fact, most of them do not know"
  16,76,"And Allah sets forth a parable of two men: one of them is dumb, incapable of anything. He is a burden on his master. Wherever he is sent, he brings no good. Can such a person be equal to the one who commands justice and is on the Straight Path"
  16,77,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs Ћєthe knowledge ofЋЇ the unseen in the heavens and the earth. Bringing about the Hour would only take the blink of an eye, or even less. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  16,78,"And Allah brought you out of the wombs of your mothers while you knew nothing, and gave you hearing, sight, and intellect so perhaps you would be thankful"
  16,79,Have they not seen the birds glide in the open sky? None holds them up except Allah. Surely in this are signs for those who believe
  16,80,"And Allah has made your homes a place to rest, and has given you tents from the hide of animals, light to handle when you travel and when you camp. And out of their wool, fur, and hair He has given you furnishings and goods for a while"
  16,81,"And Allah has provided you shade out of what He created, and has given you shelter in the mountains. He has also provided you with clothes protecting you from the heat Ћєand coldЋЇ, and armour shielding you in battle. This is how He perfects His favour upon you, so perhaps you will ЋєfullyЋЇ submit Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  16,82,"But if they turn away, then your duty ЋєO ProphetЋЇ is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ clearly"
  16,83,"They are aware of AllahвАЩs favours, but still deny them. And most of them are ЋєtrulyЋЇ ungrateful"
  16,84,"ЋєConsider, O Prophet,ЋЇ the Day We will call Ћєa prophet asЋЇ a witness from every faith-community. Then the disbelievers will neither be allowed to plead nor appease Ћєtheir LordЋЇ"
  16,85,"And when the wrongdoers face the punishment, it will not be lightened for them, nor will they be delayed Ћєfrom itЋЇ"
  16,86,"And when the polytheists see their associate-gods, they will say, вАЬOur Lord! These are our associate-gods that we used to invoke besides You.вАЭ Their gods will throw a rebuttal at them, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬYou are definitely liars.вАЭ"
  16,87,"They will offer ЋєfullЋЇ submission to Allah on that Day, and whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ they fabricated will fail them"
  16,88,"For those who disbelieve and hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah, We will add more punishment to their punishment for all the corruption they spread"
  16,89,"ЋєConsider, O Prophet,ЋЇ the Day We will call against every faith-community a witness of their own. And We will call you to be a witness against these Ћєpeople of yoursЋЇ. We have revealed to you the Book as an explanation of all things, a guide, a mercy, and good news for those who ЋєfullyЋЇ submit"
  16,90,"Indeed, Allah commands justice, grace, as well as courtesy to close relatives. He forbids indecency, wickedness, and aggression. He instructs you so perhaps you will be mindful"
  16,91,"Honour AllahвАЩs covenant when you make a pledge, and do not break your oaths after confirming them, having made Allah your guarantor. Surely Allah knows all you do"
  16,92,"Do not be like the woman who ЋєfoolishlyЋЇ unravels her yarn after it is firmly spun, by taking your oaths as a means of deceiving one another in favour of a stronger group. Surely Allah tests you through this. And on the Day of Judgment He will certainly make your differences clear to you"
  16,93,"Had Allah willed, He could have easily made you one community Ћєof believersЋЇ, but He leaves to stray whoever He wills and guides whoever He wills.¬†And you will certainly be questioned about what you used to do"
  16,94,"And do not take your oaths as a means of deceiving one another or your feet will slip after they have been firm. Then you will taste the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of hindering ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah, and you will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  16,95,"And do not trade AllahвАЩs covenant for a fleeting gain. What is with Allah is certainly far better for you, if only you knew"
  16,96,"Whatever you have will end, but whatever Allah has is everlasting. And We will certainly reward the steadfast according to the best of their deeds"
  16,97,"Whoever does good, whether male or female, and is a believer, We will surely bless them with a good life, and We will certainly reward them according to the best of their deeds"
  16,98,"When you recite the Quran, seek refuge with Allah from Satan, the accursed"
  16,99,He certainly has no authority over those who believe and put their trust in their Lord
  16,100,His authority is only over those who take him as a patron and whoвАФunder his influenceвАФassociate ЋєothersЋЇ with Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇ
  16,101,"When We replace a verse with anotherвАФand Allah knows best what He revealsвАФthey say, вАЬYou ЋєMuбЄ•ammadЋЇ are just a fabricator.вАЭ In fact, most of them do not know"
  16,102,"Say, вАЬThe holy spirit¬†has brought it down from your Lord with the truth to reassure the believers, and as a guide and good news for those who submit Ћєto AllahЋЇ.вАЭ"
  16,103,"And We surely know that they say, вАЬNo one is teaching him except a human.вАЭ But the man they refer to speaks a foreign tongue, whereas this ЋєQuranЋЇ is ЋєinЋЇ eloquent Arabic"
  16,104,"Surely those who do not believe in AllahвАЩs revelations will never be guided by Allah, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  16,105,"No one fabricates lies except those who disbelieve in AllahвАЩs revelations, and it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ liars"
  16,106,"Whoever disbelieves in Allah after their beliefвАФnot those who are forced while their hearts are firm in faith,¬†but those who embrace disbelief wholeheartedlyвАФthey will be condemned by Allah and suffer a tremendous punishment"
  16,107,This is because they prefer the life of this world over the Hereafter. Surely Allah never guides those who Ћєchoose toЋЇ disbelieve
  16,108,"They are the ones whose hearts, ears, and eyes are sealed by Allah, and it is they who are ЋєtrulyЋЇ heedless"
  16,109,"Without a doubt, they will be the losers in the Hereafter"
  16,110,"As for those who emigrated after being compelled Ћєto renounce IslamЋЇ, then struggled Ћєin AllahвАЩs causeЋЇ, and persevered, your Lord ЋєO ProphetЋЇ is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful after all"
  16,111,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ the Day ЋєwhenЋЇ every soul will come pleading for itself, and each will be paid in full for what it did, and none will be wronged"
  16,112,"And Allah sets forth the example of a society which was safe and at ease, receiving its provision in abundance from all directions. But its people met AllahвАЩs favours with ingratitude, so Allah made them taste the clutches of hunger and fear for their misdeeds"
  16,113,"A messenger of their own actually did come to them, but they denied him. So the torment overtook them while they persisted in wrongdoing"
  16,114,"So eat from the good, lawful things which Allah has provided for you, and be grateful for AllahвАЩs favours, if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  16,115,"He has only forbidden you Ћєto eatЋЇ carrion, blood, swine,¬†and what is slaughtered in the name of any other than Allah. But if someone is compelled by necessityвАФneither driven by desire nor exceeding immediate needвАФthen surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,116,"Do not falsely declare with your tongues, вАЬThis is lawful, and that is unlawful,вАЭ ЋєonlyЋЇ fabricating lies against Allah. Indeed, those who fabricate lies against Allah will never succeed"
  16,117,"ЋєIt is onlyЋЇ a brief enjoyment, then they will suffer a painful punishment"
  16,118,"To the Jews, We have forbidden what We related to you before.¬†We did not wrong them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  16,119,"As for those who commit evil ignorantly Ћєor recklesslyЋЇ, then repent afterwards and mend their ways, then your Lord is surely All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,120,"Indeed, Abraham was a model of excellence: devoted to Allah, ЋєperfectlyЋЇ uprightвАФnot a polytheistвАФ"
  16,121,ЋєutterlyЋЇ grateful for AllahвАЩs favours. ЋєSoЋЇ He chose him and guided him to the Straight Path
  16,122,"We blessed him with all goodness in this world,¬†and in the Hereafter he will certainly be among the righteous"
  16,123,"Then We revealed to you ЋєO Prophet, sayingЋЇ: вАЬFollow the faith of Abraham, the upright, who was not one of the polytheists.вАЭ"
  16,124,ЋєHonouringЋЇ the Sabbath was ordained only for those who disputed about Abraham.¬†And surely your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their disputes
  16,125,"Invite ЋєallЋЇ to the Way of your Lord with wisdom and kind advice, and only debate with them in the best manner. Surely your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ knows best who has strayed from His Way and who is ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  16,126,"If you retaliate, then let it be equivalent to what you have suffered. But if you patiently endure, it is certainly best for those who are patient"
  16,127,"Be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, for your patience is only with AllahвАЩs help. Do not grieve over those Ћєwho disbelieveЋЇ, nor be distressed by their schemes"
  16,128,Surely Allah is with those who shun evil and who do good ЋєdeedsЋЇ
  17,1,"Glory be to the One Who took His servant ЋєMuбЄ•ammadЋЇ by night from the Sacred Mosque to the Farthest Mosque whose surroundings We have blessed, so that We may show him some of Our signs.¬†Indeed, He¬†alone is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  17,2,"And We gave Moses the Scripture and made it a guide for the Children of Israel, Ћєstating:ЋЇ вАЬDo not take besides Me any other Trustee of Affairs"
  17,3,ЋєOЋЇ descendants of those We carried with Noah Ћєin the ArkЋЇ! He was indeed a grateful servant.вАЭ
  17,4,"And We warned the Children of Israel in the Scripture, вАЬYou will certainly cause corruption in the land twice, and you will become extremely arrogant"
  17,5,"When the first of the two warnings would come to pass, We would send against you some of Our servants of great might, who would ravage your homes. This would be a warning fulfilled"
  17,6,"Then Ћєafter your repentanceЋЇ We would give you the upper hand over them and aid you with wealth and offspring, causing you to outnumber them"
  17,7,"If you act rightly, it is for your own good, but if you do wrong, it is to your own loss. вАЬAnd when the second warning would come to pass, your enemies would Ћєbe left toЋЇ totally disgrace you and enter the Temple Ћєof JerusalemЋЇ as they entered it the first time, and utterly destroy whatever would fall into their hands"
  17,8,"Perhaps your Lord will have mercy on you Ћєif you repentЋЇ, but if you return Ћєto sinЋЇ, We will return Ћєto punishmentЋЇ. And We have made Hell a ЋєpermanentЋЇ confinement for the disbelievers.вАЭ"
  17,9,"Surely this Quran guides to what is most upright, and gives good news to the believersвАФwho do goodвАФthat they will have a mighty reward"
  17,10,And Ћєit warnsЋЇ those who do not believe in the Hereafter ЋєthatЋЇ We have prepared for them a painful punishment
  17,11,And humans ЋєswiftlyЋЇ pray for evil¬†as they pray for good. For humankind is ever hasty
  17,12,"We made the day and night as two signs. So We made the sign of the night devoid of light, and We made the sign of the day ЋєperfectlyЋЇ bright, so that you may seek the bounty of your Lord and know the number of years and calculation Ћєof timeЋЇ. And We have explained everything in detail"
  17,13,We have bound every humanвАЩs destiny to their neck.¬†And on the Day of Judgment We will bring forth to each ЋєpersonЋЇ a record which they will find laid open
  17,14,"ЋєAnd it will be said,ЋЇ вАЬRead your record. You ЋєaloneЋЇ are sufficient this Day to take account of yourself.вАЭ"
  17,15,"Whoever chooses to be guided, it is only for their own good. And whoever chooses to stray, it is only to their own loss. No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. And We would never punish Ћєa peopleЋЇ until We have sent a messenger Ћєto warn themЋЇ"
  17,16,"Whenever We intend to destroy a society, We command its elite Ћєto obey AllahЋЇ but they act rebelliously in it. So the decree Ћєof punishmentЋЇ is justified, and We destroy it utterly"
  17,17,ЋєImagineЋЇ how many peoples We have destroyed after Noah! And sufficient is your Lord as All-Aware and All-Seeing of the sins of His servants
  17,18,"Whoever desires this fleeting world ЋєaloneЋЇ, We hasten in it whatever We please to whoever We will; then We destine them for Hell, where they will burn, condemned and rejected"
  17,19,"But whoever desires the Hereafter and strives for it accordingly, and is a ЋєtrueЋЇ believer, it is they whose striving will be appreciated"
  17,20,We provide both the former and the latter from the bounty of your Lord. And the bounty of your Lord can never be withheld
  17,21,"See how We have favoured some over others Ћєin this lifeЋЇ, but the Hereafter is certainly far greater in rank and in favour"
  17,22,"Do not set up any other god with Allah, or you will end up condemned, abandoned"
  17,23,"For your Lord has decreed that you worship none but Him. And honour your parents. If one or both of them reach old age in your care, never say to them ЋєevenЋЇ вАШugh,вАЩ nor yell at them. Rather, address them respectfully"
  17,24,"And be humble with them out of mercy, and pray, вАЬMy Lord! Be merciful to them as they raised me when I was young.вАЭ"
  17,25,"Your Lord knows best what is within yourselves. If you are righteous, He is certainly All-Forgiving to those who ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turn to Him"
  17,26,"Give to close relatives their due, as well as the poor and ЋєneedyЋЇ travellers. And do not spend wastefully"
  17,27,Surely the wasteful are ЋєlikeЋЇ brothers to the devils. And the Devil is ever ungrateful to his Lord
  17,28,But if you must turn them down Ћєbecause you lack the means to giveЋЇвАФwhile hoping to receive your LordвАЩs bountyвАФthen Ћєat leastЋЇ give them a kind word
  17,29,"Do not be so tight-fisted, for you will be blameworthy; nor so open-handed, for you will end up in poverty"
  17,30,"Surely your Lord gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills. He is certainly All-Aware, All-Seeing of His servants"
  17,31,Do not kill your children for fear of poverty. We provide for them and for you. Surely killing them is a heinous sin
  17,32,Do not go near adultery. It is truly a shameful deed and an evil way
  17,33,"Do not take a ЋєhumanЋЇ lifeвАФmade sacred by AllahвАФexcept with ЋєlegalЋЇ right.¬†If anyone is killed unjustly, We have given their heirs¬†the authority, but do not let them exceed limits in retaliation,¬†for they are already supported Ћєby lawЋЇ"
  17,34,"Do not come near the wealth of the orphanвАФunless intending to enhance itвАФuntil they attain maturity. Honour ЋєyourЋЇ pledges, for you will surely be accountable for them"
  17,35,"Give in full when you measure, and weigh with an even balance. That is fairest and best in the end"
  17,36,"Do not follow what you have no ЋєsureЋЇ knowledge of. Indeed, all will be called to account for ЋєtheirЋЇ hearing, sight, and intellect"
  17,37,And do not walk on the earth arrogantly. Surely you can neither crack the earth nor stretch to the height of the mountains
  17,38,The violation of any of these ЋєcommandmentsЋЇ is detestable to your Lord
  17,39,"This is part of the wisdom which your Lord has revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. And do not set up any other god with Allah ЋєO humanityЋЇ, or you will be cast into Hell, blameworthy, rejected"
  17,40,Has your Lord favoured you ЋєpagansЋЇ with sons and taken angels as ЋєHisЋЇ daughters?¬†You are truly making an outrageous claim
  17,41,"We have surely varied Ћєthe signsЋЇ in this Quran so perhaps they may be mindful, but it only drives them farther away"
  17,42,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHad there been other gods besides HimвАФas they claimвАФthen they would have certainly sought a way to ЋєchallengeЋЇ the Lord of the Throne.вАЭ"
  17,43,Glorified and Highly Exalted is He above what they claim
  17,44,"The seven heavens, the earth, and all those in them glorify Him. There is not a single thing that does not glorify His praisesвАФbut you ЋєsimplyЋЇ cannot comprehend their glorification. He is indeed Most Forbearing, All-Forgiving"
  17,45,"When you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ recite the Quran, We put a hidden barrier between you and those who do not believe in the Hereafter"
  17,46,"We have cast veils over their heartsвАФleaving them unable to comprehend itвАФand deafness in their ears. And when you mention your Lord alone in the Quran, they turn their backs in aversion"
  17,47,"We know best how they listen to your recitation and what they say privatelyвАФwhen the wrongdoers say, вАЬYou would only be following a bewitched man.вАЭ"
  17,48,See how they call you names ЋєO ProphetЋЇ!¬†So they have gone so ЋєfarЋЇ astray that they cannot find the ЋєRightЋЇ Way
  17,49,"And they say ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhen we are reduced to bones and ashes, will we really be raised as a new creation?вАЭ"
  17,50,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєYes, even ifЋЇ you become stones, or iron"
  17,51,"or whatever you think is harder to bring to life!вАЭ Then they will ask ЋєyouЋЇ, вАЬWho will bring us back Ћєto lifeЋЇ?вАЭ Say, вАЬThe One Who created you the first time.вАЭ They will then shake their heads at you and ask, вАЬWhen will that be?вАЭ Say, вАЬPerhaps it is soon!вАЭ"
  17,52,"On the Day He will call you, you will ЋєinstantlyЋЇ respond by praising Him,¬†thinking you had remained Ћєin the worldЋЇ only for a little while"
  17,53,Tell My ЋєbelievingЋЇ servants to say only what is best. Satan certainly seeks to sow discord among them. Satan is indeed a sworn enemy to humankind
  17,54,"Your Lord knows you best. He may have mercy on you if He wills, or punish you if He wills. We have not sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as a keeper over them"
  17,55,"Your Lord knows best all those in the heavens and the earth. And We have surely favoured some prophets above others, and to David We gave the Psalms"
  17,56,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬInvoke those you claim Ћєto be divineЋЇ¬†besides HimвАФthey do not have the power to undo harm from you or transfer it Ћєto someone elseЋЇ.вАЭ"
  17,57,"ЋєEvenЋЇ the closest Ћєto AllahЋЇ of those invoked would be seeking a way to their Lord, hoping for His mercy, and fearing His punishment. Indeed, your LordвАЩs torment is fearsome"
  17,58,There is not a ЋєwickedЋЇ society that We will not destroy or punish with a severe torment before the Day of Judgment. That is written in the Record
  17,59,"Nothing keeps Us from sending the ЋєdemandedЋЇ signs except that they had ЋєalreadyЋЇ been denied by earlier peoples. And We gave Tham√їd the she-camel as a clear sign, but they wrongfully rejected it.¬†We only send the signs as a warning"
  17,60,"And Ћєremember, O ProphetЋЇ when We told you, вАЬCertainly your Lord encompasses the people.вАЭ And We have made what We brought you to see¬†as well as the cursed tree ЋєmentionedЋЇ in the Quran¬†only as a test for the people. We keep warning them, but it only increases them greatly in defiance"
  17,61,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We said to the angels, вАЬProstrate before Adam,вАЭ so they all didвАФbut not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who protested, вАЬShould I prostrate to the one You have created from mud?вАЭ"
  17,62,"Adding, вАЬDo you see this one you honoured above me? If you delay my end until the Day of Judgment, I will certainly take hold of his descendants, except for a few.вАЭ"
  17,63,"Allah responded, вАЬBe gone! Whoever of them follows you, Hell will surely be the reward for all of youвАФan ample reward"
  17,64,"And incite whoever you can of them with your voice, mobilize against them all your cavalry and infantry, manipulate them in their wealth and children, and make them promises.вАЭ But Satan promises them nothing but delusion"
  17,65,"ЋєAllah added,ЋЇ вАЬYou will truly have no authority over My ЋєfaithfulЋЇ servants.вАЭ And sufficient is your Lord as a Guardian"
  17,66,"It is your Lord Who steers the ships for you through the sea, so that you may seek His bounty. Surely He is ever Merciful to you"
  17,67,"When you are touched with hardship at sea, you ЋєtotallyЋЇ forget all Ћєthe godsЋЇ you ЋєnormallyЋЇ invoke, except Him. But when He delivers you ЋєsafelyЋЇ to shore, you turn away. Humankind is ever ungrateful"
  17,68,"Do you feel secure that He will not cause the land to swallow you up, or unleash upon you a storm of stones? Then you will find none to protect you"
  17,69,"Or do you feel secure that He will not send you back to sea once again, and send upon you a violent storm, drowning you for your denial? Then you will find none to avenge you against Us"
  17,70,"Indeed, We have dignified the children of Adam, carried them on land and sea, granted them good and lawful provisions, and privileged them far above many of Our creatures"
  17,71,ЋєBeware ofЋЇ the Day We will summon every people with their leader.¬†So whoever will be given their record in their right hand will read it ЋєhappilyЋЇ and will not be wronged Ћєeven by the width ofЋЇ the thread of a date stone
  17,72,"But whoever is blind Ћєto the truthЋЇ in this ЋєworldЋЇ will be blind in the Hereafter, and ЋєevenЋЇ far more astray from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way"
  17,73,"They definitely Ћєthought theyЋЇ were about to lure you away from what We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, hoping that you would attribute something else to Us falselyвАФand then they would have certainly taken you as a close friend"
  17,74,"Had We not made you steadfast, you probably would have inclined to them a little"
  17,75,"and then We truly would have made you taste double ЋєpunishmentЋЇ both in this life and after death, and you would have found no helper against Us"
  17,76,"They were about to intimidate you to drive you out of the land Ћєof MeccaЋЇ, but then they would not have survived after you Ћєhad leftЋЇ except for a little while"
  17,77,ЋєThis has beenЋЇ Our way with the messengers We sent before you. And you will never find any change in Our way
  17,78,"Observe the prayer from the decline of the sun until the darkness of the night and the dawn prayer, for certainly the dawn prayer is witnessed Ћєby angelsЋЇ"
  17,79,"And rise at Ћєthe lastЋЇ part of the night, offering additional prayers, so your Lord may raise you to a station of praise"
  17,80,"And say, вАЬMy Lord! Grant me an honourable entrance and an honourable exit¬†and give me a supporting authority from Yourself.вАЭ"
  17,81,"And declare, вАЬThe truth has come and falsehood has vanished. Indeed, falsehood is bound to vanish.вАЭ"
  17,82,"We send down the Quran as a healing and mercy for the believers, but it only increases the wrongdoers in loss"
  17,83,"When We grant people Our favours, they turn away, acting arrogantly. But when touched with evil, they lose all hope"
  17,84,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬEveryone acts in their own way. But your Lord knows best whose way is rightly guided.вАЭ"
  17,85,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about the spirit. Say, вАЬIts nature is known only to my Lord, and you ЋєO humanityЋЇ have been given but little knowledge.вАЭ"
  17,86,"If We willed, We could have certainly taken away what We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФthen you would find none to guarantee its return from UsвАФ"
  17,87,"had it not been for the mercy of your Lord. Indeed, His favour upon you is immense"
  17,88,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf ЋєallЋЇ humans and jinn were to come together to produce the equivalent of this Quran, they could not produce its equal, no matter how they supported each other.вАЭ"
  17,89,"And We have truly set forth every Ћєkind ofЋЇ lesson for humanity in this Quran, yet most people persist in disbelief"
  17,90,"They challenge Ћєthe ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWe will never believe in you until you cause a spring to gush forth from the earth for us"
  17,91,"or until you have a garden of palm trees and vineyards, and cause rivers to flow abundantly in it"
  17,92,"or cause the sky to fall upon us in pieces, as you have claimed, or bring Allah and the angels before us, face to face"
  17,93,"or until you have a house of gold, or you ascend into heavenвАФand even then we will not believe in your ascension until you bring down to us a book that we can read.вАЭ Say, вАЬGlory be to my Lord! Am I not only a human messenger?вАЭ"
  17,94,"And nothing has prevented people from believing when guidance comes to them except their protest: вАЬHas Allah sent a human as a messenger?вАЭ"
  17,95,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHad there been angels walking the earth, well settled, We would have surely sent down for them an angel from heaven as a messenger.вАЭ"
  17,96,"Say, вАЬSufficient is Allah as a Witness between me and you. He is certainly All-Knowing, All-Seeing of His servants.вАЭ"
  17,97,"Whoever Allah guides is truly guided. And whoever He leaves to stray, you will find no guardians for them besides Him. And We will drag them on their faces on the Day of JudgmentвАФdeaf, dumb, and blind. Hell will be their home. Whenever it dies down, We will flare it up for them"
  17,98,"That is their reward for rejecting Our signs and asking ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhen we are reduced to bones and ashes, will we really be raised as a new creation?вАЭ"
  17,99,"Have they not realized that Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth, can ЋєeasilyЋЇ re-create them? He has ЋєalreadyЋЇ set for them a time, about which there is no doubt. But the wrongdoers persist in denial"
  17,100,"Say Ћєto them, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬEven if you were to possess the ЋєinfiniteЋЇ treasuries of my LordвАЩs mercy, then you would certainly withhold ЋєthemЋЇ, fearing they would run outвАФfor humankind is ever stingy!вАЭ"
  17,101,"We surely gave Moses nine clear signs.¬†ЋєYou, O Prophet, canЋЇ ask the Children of Israel. When Moses came to them, Pharaoh said to him, вАЬI really think that you, O Moses, are bewitched.вАЭ"
  17,102,"Moses replied, вАЬYou know well that none has sent these ЋєsignsЋЇ down except the Lord of the heavens and the earth as insights. And I really think that you, O Pharaoh, are doomed.вАЭ"
  17,103,"So Pharaoh wanted to scare the Israelites out of the land Ћєof EgyptЋЇ, but We drowned him and all of those with him"
  17,104,"And We said to the Children of Israel after Pharaoh, вАЬReside in the land, but when the promise of the Hereafter comes to pass,¬†We will bring you all together.вАЭ"
  17,105,"We have sent down the Quran in truth, and with the truth it has come down. We have sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ only as a deliverer of good news and a warner"
  17,106,ЋєIt isЋЇ a Quran We have revealed in stages so that you may recite it to people at a deliberate pace. And We have sent it down in successive revelations
  17,107,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬBelieve in this ЋєQuranЋЇ, or do not. Indeed, when it is recited to those who were gifted with knowledge¬†before it Ћєwas revealedЋЇ, they fall upon their faces in prostration"
  17,108,"and say, вАШGlory be to our Lord! Surely the promise of our Lord has been fulfilled.вАЩ"
  17,109,"And they fall down upon their faces weeping, and it increases them in humility.вАЭ"
  17,110,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬCall upon Allah or call upon the Most CompassionateвАФwhichever you call, He has the Most Beautiful Names.вАЭ Do not recite your prayers too loudly or silently, but seek a way between"
  17,111,"And say, вАЬAll praise is for Allah, Who has never had ЋєanyЋЇ offspring;¬†nor does He have a partner in ЋєgoverningЋЇ the kingdom;¬†nor is He pathetic, needing a protector.¬†And revere Him immensely.вАЭ"
  18,1,"All praise is for Allah Who has revealed the Book to His servant,¬†allowing no crookedness in it"
  18,2,"Ћєmaking itЋЇ perfectly upright, to warn Ћєthe disbelieversЋЇ of a severe torment from Him; to give good news to the believersвАФwho do goodвАФthat they will have a fine reward"
  18,3,in which they will remain forever
  18,4,"and to warn those who claim, вАЬAllah has offspring.вАЭ"
  18,5,"They have no knowledge of this, nor did their forefathers. What a terrible claim that comes out of their mouths! They say nothing but lies"
  18,6,"Now, perhaps you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ will grieve yourself to death over their denial, if they Ћєcontinue toЋЇ disbelieve in this message"
  18,7,"We have indeed made whatever is on earth as an adornment for it, in order to test which of them is best in deeds"
  18,8,And We will certainly reduce whatever is on it to barren ground
  18,9,Have you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ thought that the people of the cave¬†and the plaque¬†were Ћєthe onlyЋЇ wonders of Our signs
  18,10,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when those youths took refuge in the cave, and said, вАЬOur Lord! Grant us mercy from Yourself and guide us rightly through our ordeal.вАЭ"
  18,11,So We caused them to fall into a dead sleep¬†in the cave for many years
  18,12,then We raised them so We may show which of the two groups would make a better estimation of the length of their stay
  18,13,"We relate to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ their story in truth. They were youths who truly believed in their Lord, and We increased them in guidance"
  18,14,"And We strengthened their hearts when they stood up and declared, вАЬOur Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth. We will never call upon any god besides Him, or we would truly be uttering an outrageous lie.вАЭ"
  18,15,"ЋєThen they said to one another,ЋЇ вАЬThese people of ours have taken gods besides Him. Why do they not produce a clear proof of them? Who then does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against Allah"
  18,16,"Since you have distanced yourselves from them and what they worship besides Allah, take refuge in the cave. Your Lord will extend His mercy to you and accommodate you in your ordeal.вАЭ"
  18,17,"And you would have seen the sun, as it rose, inclining away from their cave to the right, and as it set, declining away from them to the left, while they lay in its open space.¬†That is one of the signs of Allah. Whoever Allah guides is truly guided. But whoever He leaves to stray, you will never find for them a guiding mentor"
  18,18,"And you would have thought they were awake,¬†though they were asleep. We turned them over, to the right and left, while their dog stretched his forelegs at the entrance. Had you looked at them, you would have certainly fled away from them, filled with horror"
  18,19,"And so We awakened them so that they might question one another. One of them exclaimed, вАЬHow long have you remained ЋєasleepЋЇ?вАЭ Some replied, вАЬPerhaps a day, or part of a day.вАЭ They said Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬYour Lord knows best how long you have remained. So send one of you with these silver coins of yours to the city, and let him find which food is the purest, and then bring you provisions from it. Let him be ЋєexceptionallyЋЇ cautious, and do not let him give you away"
  18,20,"For, indeed, if they find out about you, they will stone you Ћєto deathЋЇ, or force you back into their faith, and then you will never succeed.вАЭ"
  18,21,"That is how We caused them to be discovered so that their people might know that AllahвАЩs promise Ћєof resurrectionЋЇ is true and that there is no doubt about the Hour.¬†When the people disputed with each other about the case of the youth Ћєafter their deathЋЇ,¬†some proposed, вАЬBuild a structure around them. Their Lord knows best about them.вАЭ Those who prevailed in the matter said, вАЬWe will surely build a place of worship over them.вАЭ"
  18,22,"Some will say, вАЬThey were three, their dog was the fourth,вАЭ while others will say, вАЬThey were five, their dog was the sixth,вАЭ ЋєonlyЋЇ guessing blindly. And others will say, вАЬThey were seven and their dog was the eighth.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬMy Lord knows best their ЋєexactЋЇ number. Only a few people know as well.вАЭ So do not argue about them except with sure knowledge,¬†nor consult any of those Ћєwho debateЋЇ about them"
  18,23,"And never say of anything, вАЬI will definitely do this tomorrow,вАЭ"
  18,24,"without adding, вАЬif Allah so wills!вАЭ But if you forget, then remember your Lord, and say, вАЬI trust my Lord will guide me to what is more right than this.вАЭ"
  18,25,"They had remained in their cave for three hundred years, adding nine"
  18,26,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAllah knows best how long they stayed. With Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is Ћєthe knowledge ofЋЇ the unseen of the heavens and the earth. How perfectly He hears and sees! They have no guardian besides Him, and He shares His command with none.вАЭ"
  18,27,"Recite what has been revealed to you from the Book of your Lord. None can change His Words, nor can you find any refuge besides Him"
  18,28,"And patiently stick with those who call upon their Lord morning and evening, seeking His pleasure.¬†Do not let your eyes look beyond them, desiring the luxuries of this worldly life. And do not obey those whose hearts We have made heedless of Our remembrance, who follow ЋєonlyЋЇ their desires and whose state is ЋєtotalЋЇ loss"
  18,29,"And say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєThis isЋЇ the truth from your Lord. Whoever wills let them believe, and whoever wills let them disbelieve.вАЭ Surely We have prepared for the wrongdoers a Fire whose walls will ЋєcompletelyЋЇ surround them. When they cry for aid, they will be aided with water like molten metal, which will burn ЋєtheirЋЇ faces. What a horrible drink! And what a terrible place to rest"
  18,30,"As for those who believe and do good, We certainly never deny the reward of those who are best in deeds"
  18,31,"It is they who will have the Gardens of Eternity, with rivers flowing under their feet. There they will be adorned with bracelets of gold, and wear green garments of fine silk and rich brocade, reclining there on ЋєcanopiedЋЇ couches. What a marvellous reward! And what a fabulous place to rest"
  18,32,"Give them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ an example of two men. To Ћєthe disbelievingЋЇ one We gave two gardens of grapevines, which We surrounded with palm trees and placed ЋєvariousЋЇ crops in between"
  18,33,"Each garden yielded ЋєallЋЇ its produce, never falling short. And We caused a river to flow between them"
  18,34,"And he had other resources¬†Ћєas wellЋЇ. So he boasted to a ЋєpoorЋЇ companion of his, while conversing with him, вАЬI am greater than you in wealth and superior in manpower.вАЭ"
  18,35,"And he entered his property, while wronging his soul, saying, вАЬI do not think this will ever perish"
  18,36,"nor do I think the Hour will ЋєeverЋЇ come. And if in fact I am returned to my Lord, I will definitely get a far better outcome than ЋєallЋЇ this.вАЭ"
  18,37,"His ЋєbelievingЋЇ companion replied, while conversing with him, вАЬDo you disbelieve in the One Who created you from dust,¬†then Ћєdeveloped youЋЇ from a sperm-drop, then formed you into a man"
  18,38,"But as for me: He is Allah, my Lord, and I will never associate anyone with my Lord Ћєin worshipЋЇ"
  18,39,"If only you had said, upon entering your property, вАШThis is what Allah has willed! There is no power except with Allah!вАЩ Even though you see me inferior to you in wealth and offspring"
  18,40,"perhaps my Lord will grant me ЋєsomethingЋЇ better than your garden, and send down upon your garden a thunderbolt from the sky, turning it into a barren waste"
  18,41,"Or its water may sink Ћєinto the earthЋЇ, and then you will never be able to seek it out.вАЭ"
  18,42,"And so all his produce was ЋєtotallyЋЇ ruined, so he started to wring his hands for all he had spent on it, while it had collapsed on its trellises. He cried, вАЬAlas! I wish I had never associated anyone with my Lord Ћєin worshipЋЇ!вАЭ"
  18,43,"And he had no manpower to help him against Allah, nor could he ЋєevenЋЇ help himself"
  18,44,"At this time, support comes ЋєonlyЋЇ from AllahвАФthe True ЋєLordЋЇ. He is best in reward and best in outcome"
  18,45,"And give them a parable of this worldly life. ЋєIt isЋЇ like the plants of the earth, thriving when sustained by the rain We send down from the sky. Then they ЋєsoonЋЇ turn into chaff scattered by the wind. And Allah is fully capable of ЋєdoingЋЇ all things"
  18,46,"Wealth and children are the adornment of this worldly life, but the everlasting good deeds are far better with your Lord in reward and in hope"
  18,47,"ЋєBeware ofЋЇ the Day We will blow the mountains away, and you will see the earth laid bare. And We will gather all ЋєhumankindЋЇ, leaving none behind"
  18,48,"They will be presented before your Lord in rows, Ћєand the deniers will be told,ЋЇ вАЬYou have surely returned to Us Ћєall aloneЋЇ as We created you the first time, although you ЋєalwaysЋЇ claimed that We would never appoint a time for your return.вАЭ"
  18,49,"And the record Ћєof deedsЋЇ will be laid ЋєopenЋЇ, and you will see the wicked in fear of what is ЋєwrittenЋЇ in it. They will cry, вАЬWoe to us! What kind of record is this that does not leave any sin, small or large, unlisted?вАЭ They will find whatever they did present Ћєbefore themЋЇ. And your Lord will never wrong anyone"
  18,50,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We said to the angels, вАЬProstrate before Adam,вАЭ so they all didвАФbut not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who was one of the jinn, but he rebelled against the command of his Lord. Would you then take him and his descendants as patrons instead of Me, although they are your enemy? What an evil alternative for the wrongdoers Ћєto chooseЋЇ"
  18,51,"I never called them to witness the creation of the heavens and the earth or ЋєevenЋЇ their own creation, nor would I take the misleaders as helpers"
  18,52,"And Ћєbeware ofЋЇ the Day He will say, вАЬCall upon those you claimed were My associate-gods.вАЭ So they will call them, but will receive no response. And We will make them ЋєallЋЇ share in the same doom"
  18,53,"The wicked will see the Fire and realize that they are bound to fall into it, and will find no way to avoid it"
  18,54,"We have surely set forth in this Quran every Ћєkind ofЋЇ lesson for people, but humankind is the most argumentative of all beings"
  18,55,And nothing prevents people from believing when guidance comes to them and from seeking their LordвАЩs forgiveness except Ћєtheir demandЋЇ to meet the same fate of earlier deniers or that the torment would confront them face to face
  18,56,"We do not send the messengers except as deliverers of good news and warners. But the disbelievers argue in falsehood, ЋєhopingЋЇ to discredit the truth with it, and make a mockery of My revelations and warnings"
  18,57,"And who does more wrong than those who, when reminded of their LordвАЩs revelations, turn away from them and forget what their own hands have done? We have certainly cast veils over their heartsвАФleaving them unable to comprehend this ЋєQuranЋЇвАФand deafness in their ears. And if you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ invite them to ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance, they will never be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  18,58,"Your Lord is the All-Forgiving, Full of Mercy. If He were to seize them ЋєimmediatelyЋЇ for what they commit, He would have certainly hastened their punishment. But they have an appointed time, from which they will find no refuge"
  18,59,"Those Ћєare theЋЇ societies We destroyed when they persisted in wrong,¬†and We had set a time for their destruction"
  18,60,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Moses said to his young assistant, вАЬI will never give up until I reach the junction of the two seas, even if I travel for ages.вАЭ"
  18,61,"But when they ЋєfinallyЋЇ reached the point where the seas met, they forgot their ЋєsaltedЋЇ fish, and it made its way into the sea, slipping away ЋєwondrouslyЋЇ"
  18,62,"When they had passed further, he said to his assistant, вАЬBring us our meal! We have certainly been exhausted by todayвАЩs journey.вАЭ"
  18,63,"He replied, вАЬDo you remember when we rested by the rock? ЋєThat is whenЋЇ I forgot the fish. None made me forget to mention this except Satan. And the fish made its way into the sea miraculously.вАЭ"
  18,64,"Moses responded, вАЬThat is ЋєexactlyЋЇ what we were looking for.вАЭ¬†So they returned, retracing their footsteps"
  18,65,"There they found a servant of Ours, to whom We had granted mercy from Us and enlightened with knowledge of Our Own"
  18,66,"Moses said to him, вАЬMay I follow you, provided that you teach me some of the right guidance you have been taught?вАЭ"
  18,67,"He said, вАЬYou certainly cannot be patient ЋєenoughЋЇ with me"
  18,68,And how can you be patient with what is beyond your Ћєrealm ofЋЇ knowledge?вАЭ
  18,69,"Moses assured ЋєhimЋЇ, вАЬYou will find me patient, Allah willing, and I will not disobey any of your orders.вАЭ"
  18,70,"He responded, вАЬThen if you follow me, do not question me about anything until I ЋєmyselfЋЇ clarify it for you.вАЭ"
  18,71,"So they set out, but after they had boarded a ship, the man made a hole in it. Moses protested, вАЬHave you done this to drown its people? You have certainly done a terrible thing!вАЭ"
  18,72,"He replied, вАЬDid I not say that you cannot have patience with me?вАЭ"
  18,73,"Moses pleaded, вАЬExcuse me for forgetting, and do not be hard on me.вАЭ"
  18,74,"So they proceeded until they came across a boy, and the man killed him. Moses protested, вАЬHave you killed an innocent soul, who killed no one? You have certainly done a horrible thing.вАЭ"
  18,75,"He answered, вАЬDid I not tell you that you cannot have patience with me?вАЭ"
  18,76,"Moses replied, вАЬIf I ever question you about anything after this, then do not keep me in your company, for by then I would have given you enough of an excuse.вАЭ"
  18,77,"So they moved on until they came to the people of a town. They asked them for food, but the people refused to give them hospitality. There they found a wall ready to collapse, so the man set it right. Moses protested, вАЬIf you wanted, you could have demanded a fee for this.вАЭ"
  18,78,"He replied, вАЬThis is the parting of our ways. I will explain to you what you could not bear patiently"
  18,79,"вАЬAs for the ship, it belonged to some poor people, working at sea. So I intended to damage it, for there was a ЋєtyrantЋЇ king ahead of them who seizes every ЋєgoodЋЇ ship by force"
  18,80,"вАЬAnd as for the boy, his parents were ЋєtrueЋЇ believers, and we¬†feared that he would pressure them into defiance and disbelief"
  18,81,"So we hoped that their Lord would give them another, more virtuous and caring in his place"
  18,82,"вАЬAnd as for the wall, it belonged to two orphan boys in the city, and under the wall was a treasure that belonged to them, and their father had been a righteous man. So your Lord willed that these children should come of age and retrieve their treasure, as a mercy from your Lord. I did not do it ЋєallЋЇ on my own. This is the explanation of what you could not bear patiently.вАЭ"
  18,83,"They ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about в±Ђul-Qarnain. Say, вАЬI will relate to you something of his narrative.вАЭ"
  18,84,"Surely We established him in the land, and gave him the means to all things"
  18,85,So he travelled a course
  18,86,"until he reached the setting ЋєpointЋЇ of the sun, which appeared to him to be setting in a spring of murky water, where he found some people. We said, вАЬO в±Ђul-Qarnain! Either punish them or treat them kindly.вАЭ"
  18,87,"He responded, вАЬWhoever does wrong will be punished by us, then will be returned to their Lord, Who will punish them with a horrible torment"
  18,88,"As for those who believe and do good, they will have the finest reward, and we will assign them easy commands.вАЭ"
  18,89,Then he travelled a ЋєdifferentЋЇ course
  18,90,until he reached the rising ЋєpointЋЇ of the sun. He found it rising on a people for whom We had provided no shelter from it
  18,91,So it was. And We truly had full knowledge of him
  18,92,Then he travelled a ЋєthirdЋЇ course
  18,93,until he reached Ћєa passЋЇ between two mountains. He found in front of them a people who could hardly understand ЋєhisЋЇ language
  18,94,"They pleaded, вАЬO в±Ђul-Qarnain! Surely Gog and Magog¬†are spreading corruption throughout the land. Should we pay you tribute, provided that you build a wall between us and them?вАЭ"
  18,95,"He responded, вАЬWhat my Lord has provided for me is far better. But assist me with resources, and I will build a barrier between you and them"
  18,96,"Bring me blocks of iron!вАЭ Then, when he had filled up Ћєthe gapЋЇ between the two mountains, he ordered, вАЬBlow!вАЭ When the iron became red hot, he said, вАЬBring me molten copper to pour over it.вАЭ"
  18,97,And so the enemies could neither scale nor tunnel through it
  18,98,"He declared, вАЬThis is a mercy from my Lord. But when the promise of my Lord comes to pass, He will level it to the ground. And my LordвАЩs promise is ever true.вАЭ"
  18,99,"On that Day, We will let them¬†surge Ћєlike wavesЋЇ over one another. Later, the Trumpet will be blown,¬†and We will gather all ЋєpeopleЋЇ together"
  18,100,On that Day We will display Hell clearly for the disbelievers
  18,101,those who turned a blind eye to My Reminder¬†and could not stand listening Ћєto itЋЇ
  18,102,Do the disbelievers think they can ЋєsimplyЋЇ take My servants¬†as lords instead of Me? We have surely prepared Hell as an accommodation for the disbelievers
  18,103,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬShall we inform you of who will lose the most deeds"
  18,104,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those whose efforts are in vain in this worldly life, while they think they are doing good!вАЭ"
  18,105,"It is they who reject the signs of their Lord and their meeting with Him, rendering their deeds void, so We will not give their deeds any weight on Judgment Day"
  18,106,"That is their reward: Hell, for their disbelief and mockery of My signs and messengers"
  18,107,"Indeed, those who believe and do good will have the Gardens of Paradise¬†as an accommodation"
  18,108,"where they will be forever, never desiring anywhere else"
  18,109,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf the ocean were ink for ЋєwritingЋЇ the Words of my Lord, it would certainly run out before the Words of my Lord were finished, even if We refilled it with its equal.вАЭ"
  18,110,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI am only a man like you, ЋєbutЋЇ it has been revealed to me that your God is only One God. So whoever hopes for the meeting with their Lord, let them do good deeds and associate none in the worship of their Lord.вАЭ"
  19,1,K√£f-Ha-Ya-вАЩAƒ©n- бєҐ√£d
  19,2,ЋєThis isЋЇ a reminder of your LordвАЩs mercy to His servant Zachariah
  19,3,when he cried out to his Lord privately
  19,4,"saying, вАЬMy Lord! Surely my bones have become brittle, and grey hair has spread across my head, but I have never been disappointed in my prayer to You, my Lord"
  19,5,"And I am concerned about Ћєthe faith ofЋЇ my relatives after me, since my wife is barren. So grant me, by Your grace, an heir"
  19,6,"who will inherit ЋєprophethoodЋЇ from me and the family of Jacob, and make him, O Lord, pleasing Ћєto YouЋЇ!вАЭ"
  19,7,"ЋєThe angels announced,ЋЇ вАЬO Zachariah! Indeed, We give you the good news of Ћєthe birth ofЋЇ a son, whose name will be JohnвАФa name We have not given to anyone before.вАЭ"
  19,8,"He wondered, вАЬMy Lord! How can I have a son when my wife is barren, and I have become extremely old?вАЭ"
  19,9,"An angel replied, вАЬSo will it be! Your Lord says, вАШIt is easy for Me, just as I created you before, when you were nothing!вАЩвАЭ"
  19,10,"Zachariah said, вАЬMy Lord! Grant me a sign.вАЭ He responded, вАЬYour sign is that you will not Ћєbe able toЋЇ speak to people for three nights, despite being healthy.вАЭ"
  19,11,"So he came out to his people from the sanctuary, signalling to them to glorify ЋєAllahЋЇ morning and evening"
  19,12,"ЋєIt was later said,ЋЇ вАЬO John! Hold firmly to the Scriptures.вАЭ And We granted him wisdom while Ћєhe was stillЋЇ a child"
  19,13,as well as purity and compassion from Us. And he was God-fearing
  19,14,and kind to his parents. He was neither arrogant nor disobedient
  19,15,"Peace be upon him the day he was born, and the day of his death, and the day he will be raised back to life"
  19,16,"And mention in the Book ЋєO Prophet, the story ofЋЇ Mary when she withdrew from her family to a place in the east"
  19,17,"screening herself off from them. Then We sent to her Our angel, ЋєGabriel,ЋЇ appearing before her as a man, perfectly formed"
  19,18,"She appealed, вАЬI truly seek refuge in the Most Compassionate from you! ЋєSo leave me aloneЋЇ if you are God-fearing.вАЭ"
  19,19,"He responded, вАЬI am only a messenger from your Lord, ЋєsentЋЇ to bless you with a pure son.вАЭ"
  19,20,"She wondered, вАЬHow can I have a son when no man has ever touched me, nor am I unchaste?вАЭ"
  19,21,"He replied, вАЬSo will it be! Your Lord says, вАШIt is easy for Me. And so will We make him a sign for humanity and a mercy from Us.вАЩ It is a matter ЋєalreadyЋЇ decreed.вАЭ"
  19,22,So she conceived him and withdrew with him to a remote place
  19,23,"Then the pains of labour drove her to the trunk of a palm tree. She cried, вАЬAlas! I wish I had died before this, and was a thing long forgotten!вАЭ"
  19,24,"So a voice¬†reassured her from below her, вАЬDo not grieve! Your Lord has provided a stream at your feet"
  19,25,"And shake the trunk of this palm tree towards you, it will drop fresh, ripe dates upon you"
  19,26,"So eat and drink, and put your heart at ease. But if you see any of the people, say, вАШI have vowed silence¬†to the Most Compassionate, so I am not talking to anyone today.вАЩвАЭ"
  19,27,"Then she returned to her people, carrying him. They said Ћєin shockЋЇ, вАЬO Mary! You have certainly done a horrible thing"
  19,28,"O sister of Aaron!¬†Your father was not an indecent man, nor was your mother unchaste.вАЭ"
  19,29,"So she pointed to the baby. They exclaimed, вАЬHow can we talk to someone who is an infant in the cradle?вАЭ"
  19,30,"ЋєJesusЋЇ declared, вАЬI am truly a servant of Allah. He has destined me to be given the Scripture and to be a prophet"
  19,31,"He has made me a blessing wherever I go, and bid me to establish prayer and give alms-tax as long as I live"
  19,32,and to be kind to my mother. He has not made me arrogant or defiant
  19,33,"Peace be upon me the day I was born, the day I die, and the day I will be raised back to life!вАЭ"
  19,34,"That is Jesus, son of Mary. ЋєAnd this isЋЇ a word of truth, about which they dispute"
  19,35,"It is not for Allah to take a son! Glory be to Him. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, вАЬBe!вАЭ And it is"
  19,36,"ЋєJesus also declared,ЋЇ вАЬSurely Allah is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. This is the Straight Path.вАЭ"
  19,37,"Yet their ЋєvariousЋЇ groups have differed among themselves Ћєabout himЋЇ, so woe to the disbelievers when they face a tremendous Day"
  19,38,How clearly will they hear and see on the Day they will come to Us! But today the wrongdoers are clearly astray
  19,39,"And warn them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ of the Day of Regret, when all matters will be settled, while they are ЋєengrossedЋЇ in heedlessness and disbelief"
  19,40,"Indeed, it is We Who will succeed the earth and whoever is on it. And to Us they will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  19,41,"And mention in the Book ЋєO Prophet, the story ofЋЇ Abraham. He was surely a man of truth and a prophet"
  19,42,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when he said to his father, вАЬO dear father! Why do you worship what can neither hear nor see, nor benefit you at all"
  19,43,"O dear father! I have certainly received some knowledge which you have not received, so follow me and I will guide you to the Straight Path"
  19,44,O dear father! Do not worship Satan. Surely Satan is ever rebellious against the Most Compassionate
  19,45,"O dear father! I truly fear that you will be touched by a torment from the Most Compassionate, and become SatanвАЩs companion Ћєin HellЋЇ.вАЭ"
  19,46,"He threatened, вАЬHow dare you reject my idols, O Abraham! If you do not desist, I will certainly stone you Ћєto deathЋЇ. So be gone from me for a long time!вАЭ"
  19,47,"Abraham responded, вАЬPeace be upon you! I will pray to my Lord for your forgiveness. He has truly been Most Gracious to me"
  19,48,"As I distance myself from Ћєall ofЋЇ you and from whatever you invoke besides Allah, I will Ћєcontinue toЋЇ call upon my Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ, trusting that I will never be disappointed in invoking my Lord.вАЭ"
  19,49,"So after he had left them and what they worshipped besides Allah, We granted him Isaac and Jacob, and made each of them a prophet"
  19,50,"We showered them with Our mercy, and blessed them with honourable mention"
  19,51,"And mention in the Book ЋєO Prophet, the story ofЋЇ Moses. He was truly a chosen man, and was a messenger and a prophet"
  19,52,"We called him from the right side of Mount бєђ√їr, and drew him near, speaking Ћєwith himЋЇ directly"
  19,53,"And We appointed for himвАФout of Our graceвАФhis brother, Aaron, as a prophet"
  19,54,"And mention in the Book ЋєO Prophet, the story ofЋЇ Ishmael. He was truly a man of his word, and was a messenger and a prophet"
  19,55,He used to urge his people to pray and give alms-tax. And his Lord was well pleased with him
  19,56,"And mention in the Book ЋєO Prophet, the story ofЋЇ Enoch. He was surely a man of truth and a prophet"
  19,57,And We elevated him to an honourable status
  19,58,"Those were Ћєsome ofЋЇ the prophets who Allah has blessed from among the descendants of Adam, and of those We carried with Noah Ћєin the ArkЋЇ, and of the descendants of Abraham and Israel,¬†and of those We ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided and chose. Whenever the revelations of the Most Compassionate were recited to them, they fell down, prostrating and weeping"
  19,59,But they were succeeded by generations who neglected prayer and followed their lusts and so will soon face the evil consequences
  19,60,"As for those who repent, believe, and do good, it is they who will be admitted into Paradise, never being denied any reward"
  19,61,"ЋєThey will be inЋЇ the Gardens of Eternity, promised in trust by the Most Compassionate to His servants. Surely His promise will be fulfilled"
  19,62,There they will never hear any idle talkвАФonly Ћєgreetings ofЋЇ peace. And there they will have their provisions morning and evening
  19,63,"That is Paradise, which We will grant to whoever is devout among Our servants"
  19,64,"вАЬWe only descend by the command of your Lord. To Him belongs whatever is before us, and whatever is behind us, and everything in between. And your Lord is never forgetful"
  19,65,"ЋєHe is theЋЇ Lord of the heavens, and the earth, and everything in between. So worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ, and be steadfast in His worship. Do you know of anyone equal to Him Ћєin His attributesЋЇ?вАЭ"
  19,66,"Yet ЋєsomeЋЇ people ask ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬAfter I die, will I really be raised to life again?вАЭ"
  19,67,"Do ЋєsuchЋЇ people not remember that We created them before, when they were nothing"
  19,68,"By your Lord ЋєO ProphetЋЇ! We will surely gather them along with the devils, and then set them around Hell on their knees"
  19,69,Then We will certainly begin by dragging out of every group the ones most defiant to the Most Compassionate
  19,70,And We truly know best who is most deserving of burning in it
  19,71,There is none of you who will not pass over it.¬†ЋєThis isЋЇ a decree your Lord must fulfil
  19,72,"Then We will deliver those who were devout, leaving the wrongdoers there on their knees"
  19,73,"When Our clear revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers ask the believers ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhich of the two of us is better in status and superior in assembly?вАЭ"
  19,74,"ЋєImagine, O ProphetЋЇ how many peoples We have destroyed before them, who were far better in luxury and splendour"
  19,75,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWhoever is ЋєentrenchedЋЇ in misguidance, the Most Compassionate will allow them plenty of time, untilвАФbehold!вАФthey face what they are threatened with: either the torment or the Hour. Only then will they realize who is worse in position and inferior in manpower.вАЭ"
  19,76,And Allah increases in guidance those who are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided. And the everlasting good deeds are far better with your Lord in reward and in outcome
  19,77,"Have you seen ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the one¬†who rejects Our revelations yet boasts, вАЬI will definitely be granted Ћєplenty ofЋЇ wealth and children Ћєif there is an afterlifeЋЇ.вАЭ"
  19,78,Has he looked into the unseen or taken a pledge from the Most Compassionate
  19,79,Not at all! We certainly record whatever he claims and will increase his punishment extensively
  19,80,"And We will inherit what he boasts of, and he will come before Us all by himself"
  19,81,"They have taken other gods, instead of Allah, seeking strength Ћєand protectionЋЇ through them"
  19,82,But no! Those ЋєgodsЋЇ will deny their worship and turn against them
  19,83,"Do you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not see that We have sent the devils against the disbelievers, constantly inciting them"
  19,84,"So do not be in haste against them, for indeed We are ЋєcloselyЋЇ counting down their days"
  19,85,ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day We will gather the righteous before the Most Compassionate as an honoured delegation
  19,86,and drive the wicked to Hell like a thirsty herd
  19,87,"None will have the right to intercede, except those who have taken a covenant from the Most Compassionate"
  19,88,"They¬†say, вАЬThe Most Compassionate has offspring.вАЭ"
  19,89,You have certainly made an outrageous claim
  19,90,"by which the heavens are about to burst, the earth to split apart, and the mountains to crumble to pieces"
  19,91,in protest of attributing children to the Most Compassionate
  19,92,It does not befit Ћєthe majesty ofЋЇ the Most Compassionate to have children
  19,93,There is none in the heavens or the earth who will not return to the Most Compassionate in full submission
  19,94,"Indeed, He fully knows them and has counted them precisely"
  19,95,And each of them will return to Him on the Day of Judgment all alone
  19,96,"As for those who believe and do good, the Most Compassionate will ЋєcertainlyЋЇ bless them with ЋєgenuineЋЇ love"
  19,97,"Indeed, We have made this ЋєQuranЋЇ easy in your own language ЋєO ProphetЋЇ so with it you may give good news to the righteous and warn those who are contentious"
  19,98,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many peoples We have destroyed before them! Do you ЋєstillЋЇ see any of them, or ЋєevenЋЇ hear from them the slightest sound"
  20,1,бєђ√Ґ-H√Ґ
  20,2,We have not revealed the Quran to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to cause you distress
  20,3,but as a reminder to those in awe Ћєof AllahЋЇ
  20,4,ЋєIt isЋЇ a revelation from the One Who created the earth and the high heavensвАФ
  20,5,"the Most Compassionate, ЋєWho isЋЇ established on the Throne"
  20,6,To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth and whatever is in between and whatever is underground
  20,7,"Whether you speak openly Ћєor notЋЇ, He certainly knows what is secret and what is even more hidden"
  20,8,AllahвАФthere is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. He has the Most Beautiful Names
  20,9,Has the story of Moses reached you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ
  20,10,"When he saw a fire, he said to his family, вАЬWait here, ЋєforЋЇ I have spotted¬†a fire. Perhaps I can bring you a torch from it, or find some guidance at the fire.вАЭ"
  20,11,"But when he approached it, he was called, вАЬO Moses"
  20,12,"It is truly I. I am your Lord! So take off your sandals, for you are in the sacred valley of бєђuwa"
  20,13,"I have chosen you, so listen to what is revealed"
  20,14,"вАШIt is truly I. I am Allah! There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Me. So worship Me ЋєaloneЋЇ, and establish prayer for My remembrance"
  20,15,"The Hour is sure to come. My Will is to keep it hidden, so that every soul may be rewarded according to their efforts"
  20,16,"So do not let those who disbelieve in it and follow their desires distract you from it, or you will be doomed.вАЩвАЭ"
  20,17,"ЋєAllah added,ЋЇ вАЬAnd what is that in your right hand, O Moses?вАЭ"
  20,18,"He replied, вАЬIt is my staff! I lean on it, and with it I beat down ЋєbranchesЋЇ for my sheep, and have other uses for it.вАЭ"
  20,19,"Allah said, вАЬThrow it down, O Moses!вАЭ"
  20,20,"So he did, thenвАФbehold!вАФit became a serpent, slithering"
  20,21,"Allah said, вАЬTake it, and have no fear. We will return it to its former state"
  20,22,"And put your hand under your armpit, it will come out ЋєshiningЋЇ white, unblemished,¬†as another sign"
  20,23,so that We may show you some of Our greatest signs
  20,24,"Go to Pharaoh, for he has truly transgressed Ћєall boundsЋЇ.вАЭ"
  20,25,"Moses prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Uplift my heart for me"
  20,26,and make my task easy
  20,27,and remove the impediment from my tongue
  20,28,so people may understand my speech
  20,29,and grant me a helper from my family
  20,30,"Aaron, my brother"
  20,31,Strengthen me through him
  20,32,and let him share my task
  20,33,so that we may glorify You much
  20,34,and remember You much
  20,35,for truly You have ЋєalwaysЋЇ been overseeing us.вАЭ
  20,36,"Allah responded, вАЬAll that you requested has been granted, O Moses"
  20,37,And surely We had shown You favour before
  20,38,when We inspired your mother with this
  20,39,"вАШPut him into a chest, then put it into the river. The river will wash it ashore, and he will be taken by ЋєPharaoh,ЋЇ an enemy of Mine and his.вАЩ And I blessed you with lovability from Me¬†ЋєO MosesЋЇ so that you would be brought up under My ЋєwatchfulЋЇ Eye"
  20,40,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when your sister came along and proposed, вАШShall I direct you to someone who will nurse him?вАЩ¬†So We reunited you with your mother so that her heart would be put at ease, and she would not grieve. ЋєLaterЋЇ you killed a man Ћєby mistakeЋЇ, but We saved you from sorrow, as well as other tests We put you through. Then you stayed for a number of years among the people of Midian. Then you came here as pre-destined, O Moses"
  20,41,And I have selected you for My service
  20,42,"Go forth, you and your brother, with My signs and never falter in remembering Me"
  20,43,"Go, both of you, to Pharaoh, for he has truly transgressed Ћєall boundsЋЇ"
  20,44,"Speak to him gently, so perhaps he may be mindful Ћєof MeЋЇ or fearful Ћєof My punishmentЋЇ.вАЭ"
  20,45,"They both pleaded, вАЬOur Lord! We fear that he may be quick to harm us or act tyrannically.вАЭ"
  20,46,"Allah reassured ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬHave no fear! I am with you, hearing and seeing"
  20,47,"So go to him and say, вАШIndeed we are both messengers from your Lord, so let the Children of Israel go with us, and do not oppress them. We have come to you with a sign from your Lord. And salvation will be for whoever follows the ЋєrightЋЇ guidance"
  20,48,It has indeed been revealed to us that the punishment will be upon whoever denies Ћєthe truthЋЇ and turns away.вАЩвАЭ
  20,49,"Pharaoh asked, вАЬWho then is the Lord of you two, O Moses?вАЭ"
  20,50,"He answered, вАЬOur Lord is the One Who has given everything its ЋєdistinctiveЋЇ form, then guided ЋєitЋЇ.вАЭ"
  20,51,"Pharaoh asked, вАЬAnd what about previous peoples?вАЭ"
  20,52,"He replied, вАЬThat knowledge is with my Lord in a Record. My Lord neither falters¬†nor forgets ЋєanythingЋЇ.вАЭ"
  20,53,"ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who has laid out the earth for Ћєall ofЋЇ you, and set in it pathways for you, and sends down rain from the sky, causing various types of plants to grow"
  20,54,ЋєsoЋЇ eat and graze your cattle. Surely in this are signs for people of sound judgment
  20,55,"From the earth We created you, and into it We will return you, and from it We will bring you back again"
  20,56,"And We certainly showed Pharaoh all of Our signs,¬†but he denied them and refused Ћєto believeЋЇ"
  20,57,"He said, вАЬHave you come to drive us out of our land with your magic, O Moses"
  20,58,"We can surely meet you with similar magic. So set for us an appointment that neither of us will fail to keep, in a central place.вАЭ"
  20,59,"Moses said, вАЬYour appointment is on the Day of the Festival, and let the people be gathered mid-morning.вАЭ"
  20,60,"Pharaoh then withdrew, orchestrated his scheme, then returned"
  20,61,"Moses warned the magicians, вАЬWoe to you! Do not fabricate a lie against Allah,¬†or He will wipe you out with a torment. Whoever fabricates ЋєliesЋЇ is bound to fail.вАЭ"
  20,62,"So the magicians disputed the matter among themselves, conversing privately"
  20,63,"They concluded, вАЬThese two are only magicians who want to drive you out of your land with their magic, and do away with your most cherished traditions"
  20,64,"So orchestrate your plan, then come forward in ЋєperfectЋЇ ranks. And whoever prevails today will certainly be successful.вАЭ"
  20,65,"They said, вАЬO Moses! Either you cast, or let us be the first to cast.вАЭ"
  20,66,"Moses responded, вАЬNo, you go first.вАЭ And suddenly their ropes and staffs appeared to himвАФby their magicвАФto be slithering"
  20,67,So Moses concealed fear within himself
  20,68,"We reassured ЋєhimЋЇ, вАЬDo not fear! It is certainly you who will prevail"
  20,69,"Cast what is in your right hand, and it will swallow up what they have made, for what they have made is no more than a magic trick. And magicians can never succeed wherever they go.вАЭ"
  20,70,"So the magicians fell down in prostration, declaring, вАЬWe believe in the Lord of Aaron and Moses.вАЭ"
  20,71,"Pharaoh threatened, вАЬHow dare you believe in him before I give you permission? He must be your master who taught you magic. I will certainly cut off your hands and feet on opposite sides, and crucify you on the trunks of palm trees. You will really see whose punishment is more severe and more lasting.вАЭ"
  20,72,"They responded, вАЬBy the One Who created us! We will never prefer you over the clear proofs that have come to us. So do whatever you want! Your authority only covers the ЋєfleetingЋЇ life of this world"
  20,73,"Indeed, we have believed in our Lord so He may forgive our sins and that magic you have forced us to practice. And Allah is far superior Ћєin rewardЋЇ and more lasting Ћєin punishmentЋЇ.вАЭ"
  20,74,"Whoever comes to their Lord as an evildoer will certainly have Hell, where they can neither live nor die"
  20,75,"But whoever comes to Him as a believer, having done good, they will have the highest ranks"
  20,76,"the Gardens of Eternity, under which rivers flow, where they will stay forever. That is the reward of those who purify themselves"
  20,77,"And We surely inspired Moses, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬLeave with My servants Ћєat nightЋЇ and strike a dry passage for them across the sea. Have no fear of being overtaken, nor be concerned Ћєof drowningЋЇ.вАЭ"
  20,78,Then Pharaoh pursued them with his soldiersвАФbut how overwhelming were the waters that submerged them
  20,79,"And ЋєsoЋЇ Pharaoh led his people astray, and did not guide Ћєthem rightlyЋЇ"
  20,80,"O Children of Israel! We saved you from your enemy, and made an appointment with you¬†on the right side of Mount бєђ√їr, and sent down to you manna and quails"
  20,81,"Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬEat from the good things We have provided for you, but do not transgress in them, or My wrath will befall you. And whoever My wrath befalls is certainly doomed"
  20,82,"But I am truly Most Forgiving to whoever repents, believes, and does good, then persists on ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance.вАЭ"
  20,83,"ЋєAllah asked,ЋЇ вАЬWhy have you come with such haste ahead of your people, O Moses?вАЭ"
  20,84,"He replied, вАЬThey are close on my tracks. And I have hastened to You, my Lord, so You will be pleased.вАЭ"
  20,85,"Allah responded, вАЬWe have indeed tested your people in your absence, and the S√Ґmiri¬†has led them astray.вАЭ"
  20,86,"So Moses returned to his people, furious and sorrowful. He said, вАЬO my people! Had your Lord not made you a good promise?¬†Has my absence been too long for you? Or have you wished for wrath from your Lord to befall you, so you broke your promise to me?вАЭ"
  20,87,"They argued, вАЬWe did not break our promise to you of our own free will, but we were made to carry the burden of the peopleвАЩs ЋєgoldenЋЇ jewellery,¬†then we threw it Ћєinto the fireЋЇ, and so did the S√Ґmiri.вАЭ"
  20,88,"Then he moulded for them an idol of a calf that made a lowing sound. They said, вАЬThis is your god and the god of Moses, but Moses forgot Ћєwhere it wasЋЇ!вАЭ"
  20,89,"Did they not see that it did not respond to them, nor could it protect or benefit them"
  20,90,"Aaron had already warned them beforehand, вАЬO my people! You are only being tested by this, for indeed your Ћєone trueЋЇ Lord is the Most Compassionate. So follow me and obey my orders.вАЭ"
  20,91,"They replied, вАЬWe will not cease to worship it until Moses returns to us.вАЭ"
  20,92,"Moses scolded Ћєhis brotherЋЇ, вАЬO Aaron! What prevented you, when you saw them going astray"
  20,93,from following after me? How could you disobey my orders?вАЭ
  20,94,"Aaron pleaded, вАЬO son of my mother! Do not seize me by my beard or Ћєthe hair ofЋЇ my head. I really feared that you would say, вАШYou have caused division among the Children of Israel, and did not observe my word.вАЩвАЭ"
  20,95,"Moses then asked, вАЬWhat did you think you were doing, O S√Ґmiri?вАЭ"
  20,96,"He said, вАЬI saw what they did not see, so I took a handful Ћєof dustЋЇ from the hoof-prints of Ћєthe horse ofЋЇ the messenger-angel ЋєGabrielЋЇ then cast it Ћєon the moulded calfЋЇ. This is what my lower-self tempted me into.вАЭ"
  20,97,"Moses said, вАЬGo away then! And for Ћєthe rest of yourЋЇ life you will surely be crying, вАШDo not touch ЋєmeЋЇ!вАЩ¬†Then you will certainly have a fate¬†that you cannot escape. Now look at your god to which you have been devoted: we will burn it up, then scatter it in the sea completely.вАЭ"
  20,98,"ЋєThen Moses addressed his people,ЋЇ вАЬYour only god is Allah, there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. He encompasses everything in ЋєHisЋЇ knowledge.вАЭ"
  20,99,This is how We relate to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ some of the stories of the past. And We have certainly granted you a Reminder¬†from Us
  20,100,Whoever turns away from it will surely bear the burden Ћєof sinЋЇ on the Day of Judgment
  20,101,suffering its consequences forever. What an evil burden they will carry on Judgment Day
  20,102,"ЋєBeware ofЋЇ the Day the Trumpet will be blown,¬†and We will gather the wicked on that Day blue-faced Ћєfrom horror and thirstЋЇ"
  20,103,"They will whisper among themselves, вАЬYou stayed no more than ten days Ћєon the earthЋЇ.вАЭ"
  20,104,"We know best what they will sayвАФthe most reasonable of them will say, вАЬYou stayed no more than a day.вАЭ"
  20,105,"And ЋєifЋЇ they ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about the mountains, ЋєthenЋЇ say, вАЬMy Lord will wipe them out completely"
  20,106,leaving the earth level and bare
  20,107,with neither depressions nor elevations to be seen.вАЭ
  20,108,"On that Day all will follow the caller Ћєfor assemblyЋЇ, ЋєandЋЇ none will dare to deviate. All voices will be hushed before the Most Compassionate. Only whispers¬†will be heard"
  20,109,"On that Day no intercession will be of any benefit, except by those granted permission by the Most Compassionate and whose words are agreeable to Him"
  20,110,"He ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what is ahead of them and what is behind them,¬†but they cannot encompass Him in ЋєtheirЋЇ knowledge"
  20,111,"And all faces will be humbled before the Ever-Living, All-Sustaining. And those burdened with wrongdoing will be in loss"
  20,112,But whoever does good and is a believer will have no fear of being wronged or denied Ћєtheir rewardЋЇ
  20,113,"And so We have sent it down as an Arabic Quran and varied the warnings in it, so perhaps they will shun evil or it may cause them to be mindful"
  20,114,"Exalted is Allah, the True King! Do not rush to recite Ћєa revelation ofЋЇ the Quran ЋєO ProphetЋЇ before it is ЋєproperlyЋЇ conveyed to you,¬†and pray, вАЬMy Lord! Increase me in knowledge.вАЭ"
  20,115,"And indeed, We once made a covenant with Adam, but he forgot, and ЋєsoЋЇ We did not find determination in him"
  20,116,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We said to the angels, вАЬProstrate before Adam,вАЭ so they all didвАФbut not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who refused ЋєarrogantlyЋЇ"
  20,117,"So We cautioned, вАЬO Adam! This is surely an enemy to you and to your wife. So do not let him drive you both out of Paradise, for you ЋєO AdamЋЇ would then suffer ЋєhardshipЋЇ"
  20,118,Here it is guaranteed that you will never go hungry or unclothed
  20,119,nor will you ЋєeverЋЇ suffer from thirst or Ћєthe sunвАЩsЋЇ heat.вАЭ
  20,120,"But Satan whispered to him, saying, вАЬO Adam! Shall I show you the Tree of Immortality and a kingdom that does not fade away?вАЭ"
  20,121,"So they both ate from the tree and then their nakedness was exposed to them, prompting them to cover themselves with leaves from Paradise. So Adam disobeyed his Lord, and ЋєsoЋЇ lost his way"
  20,122,"Then his Lord chose him Ћєfor His graceЋЇ, accepted his repentance, and guided him ЋєrightlyЋЇ"
  20,123,"Allah said, вАЬDescend, both of you, from here together Ћєwith SatanЋЇ as enemies to each other. Then when guidance comes to you from Me, whoever follows My guidance will neither go astray Ћєin this lifeЋЇ nor suffer Ћєin the nextЋЇ"
  20,124,"But whoever turns away from My Reminder will certainly have a miserable life,¬†then We will raise them up blind on the Day of Judgment.вАЭ"
  20,125,"They will cry, вАЬMy Lord! Why have you raised me up blind, although I used to see?вАЭ"
  20,126,"Allah will respond, вАЬIt is so, just as Our revelations came to you and you neglected them, so Today you are neglected.вАЭ"
  20,127,This is how We reward whoever transgresses and does not believe in the revelations of their Lord. And the punishment of the Hereafter is far more severe and more lasting
  20,128,"Is it not yet clear to them how many peoples We destroyed before them, whose ruins they still pass by? Surely in this are signs for people of sound judgment"
  20,129,"Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord¬†ЋєO ProphetЋЇ and a term already set, their ЋєinstantЋЇ doom would have been inevitable"
  20,130,"So be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ with what they say. And glorify the praises of your Lord before sunrise and before sunset, and glorify Him in the hours of the night and at both ends of the day,¬†so that you may be pleased Ћєwith the rewardЋЇ"
  20,131,"Do not let your eyes crave what We have allowed some of the disbelievers to enjoy; the ЋєfleetingЋЇ splendour of this worldly life, which We test them with. But your LordвАЩs provision Ћєin the HereafterЋЇ is far better and more lasting"
  20,132,"Bid your people to pray, and be diligent in ЋєobservingЋЇ it. We do not ask you to provide. It is We Who provide for you. And the ultimate outcome is ЋєonlyЋЇ for Ћєthe people ofЋЇ righteousness"
  20,133,"They demand, вАЬIf only he could bring us a sign from his Lord!вАЭ¬†Have they not ЋєalreadyЋЇ received a confirmation of what is in earlier Scriptures"
  20,134,"Had We destroyed them with a torment before this ЋєProphet cameЋЇ, they would have surely argued, вАЬOur Lord! If only You had sent us a messenger, we would have followed Your revelations before being humiliated and put to shame.вАЭ"
  20,135,"Say Ћєto them, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬEach Ћєof usЋЇ is waiting, so keep waiting! You will soon know who is on the Straight Path and is ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided.вАЭ"
  21,1,"ЋєThe time ofЋЇ peopleвАЩs judgment has drawn near, yet they are heedlessly turning away"
  21,2,"Whatever new reminder comes to them from their Lord, they only listen to it jokingly"
  21,3,"with their hearts ЋєtotallyЋЇ distracted. The evildoers would converse secretly, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬIs this ЋєoneЋЇ not human like yourselves? Would you fall for ЋєthisЋЇ witchcraft, even though you can ЋєclearlyЋЇ see?вАЭ"
  21,4,"The Prophet responded, вАЬMy Lord ЋєfullyЋЇ knows every word spoken in the heavens and the earth. For He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing.вАЭ"
  21,5,"Yet they say, вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ is a set of confused dreams! No, he has fabricated it! No, he must be a poet! So let him bring us a ЋєtangibleЋЇ sign like those ЋєprophetsЋЇ sent before.вАЭ"
  21,6,Not a ЋєsingleЋЇ society We destroyed before them ever believed Ћєafter receiving the signsЋЇ. Will these ЋєpagansЋЇ then believe
  21,7,"We did not send ЋєmessengersЋЇ before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ except mere men inspired by Us. If you ЋєpolytheistsЋЇ do not know Ћєthis alreadyЋЇ, then ask those who have knowledge Ћєof the ScripturesЋЇ"
  21,8,"We did not give those messengers ЋєsupernaturalЋЇ bodies that did not need food, nor were they immortal"
  21,9,"Then We fulfilled Our promise to them, saving them along with whoever We willed and destroying the transgressors"
  21,10,"We have surely revealed to you a Book, in which there is glory for you. Will you not then understand"
  21,11,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many societies of wrongdoers We have destroyed, raising up other people after them"
  21,12,"When the wrongdoers sensed Ћєthe arrival ofЋЇ Our torment, they started to run away from their cities"
  21,13,"ЋєThey were told,ЋЇ вАЬDo not run away! Return to your luxuries and your homes, so you may be questioned Ћєabout your fateЋЇ.вАЭ"
  21,14,"They cried, вАЬWoe to us! We have surely been wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  21,15,"They kept repeating their cry until We mowed them down, Ћєleaving themЋЇ lifeless"
  21,16,We did not create the heavens and the earth and everything in between for sport
  21,17,"Had We intended to take ЋєsomeЋЇ amusement, We could have found it in Our presence, if that had been Our Will"
  21,18,"In fact, We hurl the truth against falsehood, leaving it crushed, and it quickly vanishes. And woe be to you for what you claim"
  21,19,"To Him belong all those in the heavens and the earth. And those nearest to Him are not too proud to worship Him, nor do they tire"
  21,20,"They glorify ЋєHimЋЇ day and night, never wavering"
  21,21,"Or have they taken gods from the earth, who can raise the dead"
  21,22,"Had there been other gods besides Allah in the heavens or the earth, both ЋєrealmsЋЇ would have surely been corrupted. So Glorified is Allah, Lord of the Throne, far above what they claim"
  21,23,"He cannot be questioned about what He does, but they will ЋєallЋЇ be questioned"
  21,24,"Or have they taken other gods besides Him? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬShow ЋєmeЋЇ your proof. Here is Ћєthe Quran,ЋЇ the Reminder for those with me; along with Ћєearlier Scriptures,ЋЇ the Reminder for those before me.вАЭ¬†But most of them do not know the truth, so they turn away"
  21,25,"We never sent a messenger before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ without revealing to him: вАЬThere is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Me, so worship Me ЋєaloneЋЇ.вАЭ"
  21,26,"And they say, вАЬThe Most Compassionate has offspring!вАЭ¬†Glory be to Him! In fact, those ЋєangelsЋЇ are only ЋєHisЋЇ honoured servants"
  21,27,"who do not speak until He has spoken, ЋєonlyЋЇ acting at His command"
  21,28,"He ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what is ahead of them and what is behind them. They do not intercede except for whom He approves, and they tremble in awe of Him"
  21,29,"Whoever of them were to say, вАЬI am a god besides Him,вАЭ they would be rewarded with Hell by Us. This is how We reward the wrongdoers"
  21,30,Do the disbelievers not realize that the heavens and earth were ЋєonceЋЇ one mass then We split them apart?¬†And We created from water every living thing. Will they not then believe
  21,31,"And We have placed firm mountains upon the earth so it does not shake with them, and made in it broad pathways so they may find their way"
  21,32,"And We have made the sky a well-protected canopy, still they turn away from its signs"
  21,33,"And He is the One Who created the day and the night, the sun and the moonвАФeach travelling in an orbit"
  21,34,"We have not granted immortality to any human before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ: so if you die, will they live forever"
  21,35,"Every soul will taste death. And We test you ЋєO humanityЋЇ with good and evil as a trial, then to Us you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  21,36,"When the disbelievers see you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, they only make fun of you, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬIs this the one who speaks ЋєillЋЇ of your gods?вАЭ while they disbelieve at the mention of the Most Compassionate"
  21,37,"Humankind is made of haste. I will soon show you My signs, so do not ask Me to hasten them"
  21,38,"They ask Ћєthe believersЋЇ, вАЬWhen will this threat come to pass if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  21,39,"If only the disbelievers knew that a time will come when they will not be able to keep the Fire off their faces or backs, nor will they be helped"
  21,40,"In fact, the Hour will take them by surprise, leaving them stunned. So they will not be able to avert it, nor will it be delayed from them"
  21,41,"ЋєOtherЋЇ messengers had already been ridiculed before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, but those who mocked them were overtaken by what they used to ridicule"
  21,42,"Ask Ћєthem, O Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWho can defend you by day or by night against the Most Compassionate?вАЭ Still they turn away from the remembrance of their Lord"
  21,43,"Or do they have godsвАФother than UsвАФthat can protect them? They cannot ЋєevenЋЇ protect themselves, nor will they be aided against Us"
  21,44,"In fact, We have allowed enjoyment for these ЋєMeccansЋЇ and their forefathers for such a long time Ћєthat they took it for grantedЋЇ. Do they not see that We gradually reduce ЋєtheirЋЇ land from its borders? Is it they who will then prevail"
  21,45,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI warn you only by revelation.вАЭ But the deaf cannot hear the call when they are warned"
  21,46,"If they were touched by even a breath of your LordвАЩs torment, they would certainly cry, вАЬWoe to us! We have really been wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  21,47,"We will set up the scales of justice on the Day of Judgment, so no soul will be wronged in the least. And ЋєevenЋЇ if a deed is the weight of a mustard seed, We will bring it forth. And sufficient are We as a ЋєvigilantЋЇ Reckoner"
  21,48,"Indeed, We granted Moses and Aaron the standard Ћєto distinguish between right and wrongЋЇвАФa light and a reminder for the righteous"
  21,49,"who are in awe of their Lord without seeing Him,¬†and are fearful of the Hour"
  21,50,And this ЋєQuranЋЇ is a blessed reminder which We have revealed. Will you ЋєpagansЋЇ then deny it
  21,51,"And indeed, We had granted Abraham sound judgment early on, for We knew him well Ћєto be worthy of itЋЇ"
  21,52,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when he questioned his father and his people, вАЬWhat are these statues to which you are so devoted?вАЭ"
  21,53,"They replied, вАЬWe found our forefathers worshipping them.вАЭ"
  21,54,"He responded, вАЬIndeed, you and your forefathers have been clearly astray.вАЭ"
  21,55,"They asked, вАЬHave you come to us with the truth, or is this a joke?вАЭ"
  21,56,"He replied, вАЬIn fact, your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, Who created them ЋєbothЋЇ. And to that I bear witness.вАЭ"
  21,57,"ЋєThen he said to himself,ЋЇ вАЬBy Allah! I will surely plot against your idols after you have turned your backs and gone away.вАЭ"
  21,58,"So he smashed them into pieces, except the biggest of them, so they might turn to it Ћєfor answersЋЇ"
  21,59,"They protested, вАЬWho dared do this to our gods? It must be an evildoer!вАЭ"
  21,60,"Some said, вАЬWe heard a young man, called Abraham, speaking ЋєillЋЇ of them.вАЭ"
  21,61,"They demanded, вАЬBring him before the eyes of the people, so that they may witness Ћєhis trialЋЇ.вАЭ"
  21,62,"They asked, вАЬWas it you who did this to our gods, O Abraham?вАЭ"
  21,63,"He replied ЋєsarcasticallyЋЇ, вАЬNo, this oneвАФthe biggest of themвАФdid it! So ask them, if they can talk!вАЭ"
  21,64,"So they came back to their senses, saying Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬYou yourselves are truly the wrongdoers!вАЭ"
  21,65,"Then they ЋєquicklyЋЇ regressed to their ЋєoriginalЋЇ mind-set, Ћєarguing,ЋЇ вАЬYou already know that those ЋєidolsЋЇ cannot talk.вАЭ"
  21,66,"He rebuked ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬDo you then worshipвАФinstead of AllahвАФwhat can neither benefit nor harm you in any way"
  21,67,Shame on you and whatever you worship instead of Allah! Do you not have any sense?вАЭ
  21,68,"They concluded, вАЬBurn him up to avenge your gods, if you must act.вАЭ"
  21,69,"We ordered, вАЬO fire! Be cool and safe for Abraham!вАЭ"
  21,70,"They had sought to harm him, but We made them the worst losers"
  21,71,"Then We delivered him, along with Lot, to the land We had showered with blessings for all people"
  21,72,"And We blessed him with Isaac Ћєas a sonЋЇ and Jacob Ћєas a grandsonЋЇ, as an additional favourвАФmaking all of them righteous"
  21,73,"We ЋєalsoЋЇ made them leaders, guiding by Our command, and inspired them to do good deeds, establish prayer, and pay alms-tax. And they were devoted to Our worship"
  21,74,"And to Lot We gave wisdom and knowledge, and delivered him from the society engrossed in shameful practices. They were certainly an evil, rebellious people"
  21,75,"And We admitted him into Our mercy, ЋєforЋЇ he was truly one of the righteous"
  21,76,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Noah had cried out to Us earlier, so We responded to him and delivered him and his family¬†from the great distress"
  21,77,"And We made him prevail over those who had rejected Our signs. They were truly an evil people, so We drowned them all"
  21,78,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when David and Solomon passed judgment regarding the crops ruined Ћєat nightЋЇ by someoneвАЩs sheep, and We were witness to their judgments"
  21,79,"We guided ЋєyoungЋЇ Solomon to a fairer settlement,¬†and granted each of them wisdom and knowledge. We subjected the mountains as well as the birds to hymn ЋєOur praisesЋЇ along with David. It is We Who did Ћєit allЋЇ"
  21,80,We taught him the art of making body armour to protect you in battle. Will you then be grateful
  21,81,"And to Solomon We subjected the raging winds, blowing by his command to the land We had showered with blessings. It is We Who know everything"
  21,82,"And ЋєWe subjectedЋЇ some jinn¬†that dived for him,¬†and performed other duties. It is We Who kept them in check"
  21,83,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Job cried out to his Lord, вАЬI have been touched with adversity,¬†and You are the Most Merciful of the merciful.вАЭ"
  21,84,"So We answered his prayer and removed his adversity, and gave him back his family, twice as many, as a mercy from Us and a lesson for the ЋєdevotedЋЇ worshippers"
  21,85,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ Ishmael, Enoch, and в±Ђul-Kifl.¬†They were all steadfast"
  21,86,"We admitted them into Our mercy, for they were truly of the righteous"
  21,87,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when the Man of the Whale stormed off Ћєfrom his cityЋЇ in a rage, thinking We would not restrain him.¬†Then in the Ћєveils ofЋЇ darkness¬†he cried out, вАЬThere is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except You. Glory be to You! I have certainly done wrong.вАЭ"
  21,88,So We answered his prayer and rescued him from anguish. And so do We save the ЋєtrueЋЇ believers
  21,89,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Zachariah cried out to his Lord, вАЬMy Lord! Do not leave me childless, though You are the Best of Successors.вАЭ"
  21,90,"So We answered his prayer, granted him John, and made his wife fertile. Indeed, they used to race in doing good, and call upon Us with hope and fear, totally humbling themselves before Us"
  21,91,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ the one who guarded her chastity, so We breathed into her through Our angel, ЋєGabriel,ЋЇ¬†making her and her son a sign for all peoples"
  21,92,"ЋєO prophets!ЋЇ Indeed, this religion of yours is ЋєonlyЋЇ one, and I am your Lord, so worship Me ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  21,93,Yet the people have divided it into sects. But to Us they will all return
  21,94,"So whoever does good and is a believer will never be denied Ћєthe reward forЋЇ their striving, for We are recording it all"
  21,95,It is impossible for a society which We have destroyed to ever rise again
  21,96,"until ЋєafterЋЇ Gog and Magog have broken loose Ћєfrom the barrierЋЇ,¬†swarming down from every hill"
  21,97,"ushering in the True Promise.¬†ThenвАФbehold!вАФthe disbelievers will stare Ћєin horror, crying,ЋЇ вАЬOh, woe to us! We have truly been heedless of this. In fact, we have been wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  21,98,Certainly you ЋєdisbelieversЋЇ and whatever you worship instead of Allah will be the fuel of Hell.¬†You are ЋєallЋЇ bound to enter it
  21,99,"Had those idols been ЋєtrueЋЇ gods, they would not have entered it. And they will be there forever"
  21,100,"In it they will groan, and will not be able to hear"
  21,101,Surely those for whom We have destined the finest reward will be kept far away from Hell
  21,102,not even hearing the slightest hissing from it. And they will delight forever in what their souls desire
  21,103,"The Supreme Horror Ћєof that DayЋЇ will not disturb them, and the angels will greet them, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬThis is your Day, which you have been promised.вАЭ"
  21,104,"On that Day We will roll up the heavens like a scroll of writings. Just as We produced the first creation, ЋєsoЋЇ shall We reproduce it. That is a promise binding on Us. We truly uphold ЋєOur promisesЋЇ"
  21,105,"Surely, following the ЋєheavenlyЋЇ Record, We decreed in the Scriptures: вАЬMy righteous servants shall inherit the land.вАЭ"
  21,106,Surely this ЋєQuranЋЇ is sufficient Ћєas a reminderЋЇ for those devoted to worship
  21,107,We have sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ only as a mercy for the whole world
  21,108,"Say, вАЬWhat has been revealed to me is this: вАШYour God is only One God.вАЩ Will you then submit?вАЭ"
  21,109,"If they turn away, then say, вАЬI have warned you all equally. I do not know if what you are threatened with is near or far"
  21,110,Allah surely knows what you say openly and whatever you hide
  21,111,I do not know if this ЋєdelayЋЇ is possibly a test for you and an enjoyment for a while.вАЭ
  21,112,"ЋєIn the end,ЋЇ the Prophet said, вАЬMy Lord! Judge Ћєbetween usЋЇ in truth. And our Lord is the Most Compassionate, Whose help is sought against what you claim.вАЭ"
  22,1,"O humanity! Fear your Lord, for the ЋєviolentЋЇ quaking at the Hour is surely a dreadful thing"
  22,2,"The Day you see it, every nursing mother will abandon what she is nursing, and every pregnant woman will deliver her burden ЋєprematurelyЋЇ. And you will see people Ћєas if they wereЋЇ drunk, though they will not be drunk; but the torment of Allah is ЋєterriblyЋЇ severe"
  22,3,"ЋєStillЋЇ there are some who dispute about Allah without knowledge, and follow every rebellious devil"
  22,4,It has been decreed for such devils that whoever takes them as a guide will be misguided and led by them into the torment of the Blaze
  22,5,"O humanity! If you are in doubt about the Resurrection, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ We did create you¬†from dust, then from a sperm-drop,¬†then Ћєdeveloped you intoЋЇ a clinging clot Ћєof bloodЋЇ,¬†then a lump of fleshвАФfully formed or unformedвАФin order to demonstrate ЋєOur powerЋЇ to you. ЋєThenЋЇ We settle whatever ЋєembryoЋЇ We will in the womb for an appointed term, then bring you forth as infants, so that you may reach your prime. Some of you ЋєmayЋЇ die ЋєyoungЋЇ, while others are left to reach the most feeble stage of life so that they may know nothing after having known much. And you see the earth lifeless, but as soon as We send down rain upon it, it begins to stir Ћєto lifeЋЇ and swell, producing every type of pleasant plant"
  22,6,"That is because Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Truth, He ЋєaloneЋЇ gives life to the dead, and He ЋєaloneЋЇ is Most Capable of everything"
  22,7,"And certainly the Hour is coming, there is no doubt about it. And Allah will surely resurrect those in the graves"
  22,8,"ЋєStillЋЇ there are some who dispute about Allah without knowledge, guidance, or an enlightening scripture"
  22,9,"turning away Ћєin prideЋЇ to lead ЋєothersЋЇ astray from AllahвАЩs Way. They will suffer disgrace in this world, and on the Day of Judgment We will make them taste the torment of burning"
  22,10,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬThis is Ћєthe rewardЋЇ for what your hands have done. And Allah is never unjust to ЋєHisЋЇ creation.вАЭ"
  22,11,"And there are some who worship Allah on the verge Ћєof faithЋЇ: if they are blessed with something good, they are content with it; but if they are afflicted with a trial, they relapse Ћєinto disbeliefЋЇ,¬†losing this world and the Hereafter. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the clearest loss"
  22,12,They call besides Allah what can neither harm nor benefit them. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the farthest one can stray
  22,13,"They invoke those whose worship leads to harm, not benefit. What an evil patron and what an evil associate"
  22,14,"Indeed, Allah will admit those who believe and do good into Gardens, under which rivers flow. Surely Allah does what He wills"
  22,15,"Whoever thinks that Allah will not help His Prophet in this world and the Hereafter, let them stretch out a rope to the ceiling and strangle themselves, then let them see if this plan will do away with Ћєthe cause ofЋЇ their rage"
  22,16,And so We revealed this ЋєQuranЋЇ as clear verses. And Allah certainly guides whoever He wills
  22,17,"Indeed, the believers, Jews, Sabians,¬†Christians, Magi,¬†and the polytheistsвАФAllah will judge between them ЋєallЋЇ on Judgment Day. Surely Allah is a Witness over all things"
  22,18,"Do you not see that to Allah bow down Ћєin submissionЋЇ¬†all those in the heavens and all those on the earth, as well as the sun, the moon, the stars, the mountains, the trees, and ЋєallЋЇ living beings, as well as many humans, while many are deserving of punishment. And whoever Allah disgraces, none can honour. Surely Allah does what He wills"
  22,19,"These are two opposing groups that disagree about their Lord: as for the disbelievers, garments of Fire will be cut out for them and boiling water will be poured over their heads"
  22,20,"melting whatever is in their bellies, along with their skin"
  22,21,And awaiting them are maces of iron
  22,22,"Whenever they try to escape from HellвАФout of anguishвАФthey will be forced back into it, Ћєand will be told,ЋЇ вАЬTaste the torment of burning!вАЭ"
  22,23,"ЋєButЋЇ Allah will surely admit those who believe and do good into Gardens, under which rivers flow, where they will be adorned with bracelets of gold and pearls, and their clothing will be silk"
  22,24,"for they have been guided to the best of speech, and they have been guided to the Commendable Path"
  22,25,"Indeed, those who persist in disbelief and hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah and from the Sacred MosqueвАФwhich We have appointed for all people, residents and visitors alikeвАФalong with whoever intends to deviate by doing wrong in it,¬†We will cause them to taste a painful punishment"
  22,26,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We assigned to Abraham the site of the House, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬDo not associate anything with Me Ћєin worshipЋЇ and purify My House for those who circle Ћєthe KaвАЩbahЋЇ, stand Ћєin prayerЋЇ, and bow and prostrate themselves"
  22,27,Call ЋєallЋЇ people to the pilgrimage.¬†They will come to you on foot and on every lean camel from every distant path
  22,28,"so they may obtain the benefits Ћєin storeЋЇ for them,¬†and pronounce the Name of Allah on appointed days over the sacrificial animals He has provided for them. So eat from their meat and feed the desperately poor"
  22,29,"Then let them groom themselves,¬†fulfil their vows, and circle the Ancient House.вАЭ"
  22,30,"That is so. And whoever honours the rituals of Allah, it is best for them in the sight of their Lord. The Ћєmeat ofЋЇ cattle has been made lawful for you, except what has ЋєalreadyЋЇ been recited to you.¬†So shun the impurity of idolatry, and shun words of falsehood"
  22,31,"Be upright Ћєin devotionЋЇ to Allah, associating none with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ. For whoever associates ЋєothersЋЇ with Allah is like someone who has fallen from the sky and is either snatched away by birds or swept by the wind to a remote place"
  22,32,"That is so. And whoever honours the symbols of Allah, it is certainly out of the piety of the heart"
  22,33,"You may benefit from sacrificial animals for an appointed term,¬†then their place of sacrifice is at the Ancient House"
  22,34,"For every community We appointed a rite of sacrifice so that they may pronounce the Name of Allah over the sacrificial animals He has provided for them. For your God is only One God, so submit yourselves to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. And give good news ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to the humble"
  22,35,"those whose hearts tremble at the remembrance of Allah, who patiently endure whatever may befall them, and who establish prayer and donate from what We have provided for them"
  22,36,"We have made sacrificial camels Ћєand cattleЋЇ among the symbols of Allah, in which there is ЋєmuchЋЇ good for you. So pronounce the Name of Allah over them when they are lined up Ћєfor sacrificeЋЇ. Once they have fallen ЋєlifelessЋЇ on their sides, you may eat from their meat, and feed the needyвАФthose who do not beg, and those who do. In this way We have subjected these ЋєanimalsЋЇ to you so that you may be grateful"
  22,37,"Neither their meat nor blood reaches Allah. Rather, it is your piety that reaches Him. This is how He has subjected them to you so that you may proclaim the greatness of Allah for what He has guided you to, and give good news to the good-doers"
  22,38,"Indeed, Allah defends those who believe. Surely Allah does not like whoever is deceitful, ungrateful"
  22,39,"Permission Ћєto fight backЋЇ is ЋєherebyЋЇ granted to those being fought, for they have been wronged.¬†And Allah is truly Most Capable of helping them ЋєprevailЋЇ"
  22,40,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who have been expelled from their homes for no reason other than proclaiming: вАЬOur Lord is Allah.вАЭ Had Allah not repelled Ћєthe aggression ofЋЇ some people by means of others, destruction would have surely claimed monasteries, churches, synagogues, and mosques in which AllahвАЩs Name is often mentioned. Allah will certainly help those who stand up for Him. Allah is truly All-Powerful, Almighty"
  22,41,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who, if established in the land by Us, would perform prayer, pay alms-tax, encourage what is good, and forbid what is evil. And with Allah rests the outcome of all affairs"
  22,42,"If they deny you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, so did the people of Noah before them, as well as Ћєthe tribes ofЋЇ вАЩ»Вd and Tham√їd"
  22,43,"the people of Abraham, the people of Lot"
  22,44,and the residents of Midian. And Moses was denied ЋєtooЋЇ. But I delayed Ћєthe fate ofЋЇ the disbelievers Ћєuntil their appointed timeЋЇ then seized them. And how severe was My response
  22,45,"Many are the societies We have destroyed for persisting in wrongdoing, leaving them in total ruin. ЋєMany areЋЇ also the abandoned wells and lofty palaces"
  22,46,"Have they not travelled throughout the land so their hearts may reason, and their ears may listen? Indeed, it is not the eyes that are blind, but it is the hearts in the chests that grow blind"
  22,47,They challenge you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to hasten the torment. And Allah will never fail in His promise. But a day with your Lord is indeed like a thousand years by your counting
  22,48,"Many are the societies whose end We delayed while they did wrong, then seized them. And to Me is the final return"
  22,49,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO humanity! I am only sent to you with a clear warning"
  22,50,So those who believe and do good will have forgiveness and an honourable provision
  22,51,"But those who strive to discredit Our revelations, they will be the residents of the Hellfire.вАЭ"
  22,52,"Whenever We sent a messenger or a prophet before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ and he recited ЋєOur revelationsЋЇ, Satan would influence ЋєpeopleвАЩs understanding ofЋЇ his recitation. But ЋєeventuallyЋЇ Allah would eliminate SatanвАЩs influence. Then Allah would ЋєfirmlyЋЇ establish His revelations. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  22,53,All that so He may make SatanвАЩs influence a trial for those ЋєhypocritesЋЇ whose hearts are sick and those ЋєdisbelieversЋЇ whose hearts are hardened. Surely the wrongdoers are totally engrossed in opposition
  22,54,"ЋєThis isЋЇ also so that those gifted with knowledge would know that this ЋєrevelationЋЇ is the truth from your Lord, so they have faith in it, and so their hearts would submit humbly to it. And Allah surely guides the believers to the Straight Path"
  22,55,"Yet the disbelievers will persist in doubt about this ЋєrevelationЋЇ until the Hour takes them by surprise, or the torment of a terminating¬†Day comes to them"
  22,56,All authority on that Day is for Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ.¬†He will judge between them. So those who believe and do good will be in the Gardens of Bliss
  22,57,"But those who disbelieve and deny Our revelations, it is they who will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  22,58,"As for those who emigrate in the cause of Allah and then are martyred or die, Allah will indeed grant them a good provision. Surely Allah is the Best Provider"
  22,59,"He will certainly admit them into a place they will be pleased with. For Allah is truly All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  22,60,"That is so. And whoever retaliates in equivalence to the injury they have received, and then are wronged ЋєagainЋЇ, Allah will certainly help them. Surely Allah is Ever-Pardoning, All-Forgiving"
  22,61,"That is because Allah causes the night to merge into the day, and the day into the night. Indeed, Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  22,62,"That is because Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Truth and what they invoke besides Him is falsehood, and Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is truly the Most High, All-Great"
  22,63,"Do you not see that Allah sends down rain from the sky, then the earth becomes green? Surely Allah is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  22,64,"To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is truly the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  22,65,Do you not see that Allah has subjected to you¬†whatever is in the earth as well as the ships ЋєthatЋЇ sail through the sea by His command? He keeps the sky from falling down on the earth except by His permission. Surely Allah is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to humanity
  22,66,"And He is the One Who gave you life, then will cause you to die, and then will bring you back to life. ЋєButЋЇ surely humankind is ever ungrateful"
  22,67,"For every community We appointed a code¬†of life to follow.¬†So do not let them dispute with you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in this matter. And invite ЋєallЋЇ to your Lord, for you are truly on the Right Guidance"
  22,68,"But if they argue with you, then say, вАЬAllah knows best what you do.вАЭ"
  22,69,Allah will judge between you ЋєallЋЇ on Judgment Day regarding your differences
  22,70,Do you not know that Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth? Surely it is all ЋєwrittenЋЇ in a Record. That is certainly easy for Allah
  22,71,"Yet they worship besides Allah that for which He has sent down no authority, and of which they have no knowledge. The wrongdoers will have no helper"
  22,72,"Whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ recognize rage on the faces of the disbelievers, as if they are going to snap at those who recite Our revelations to them. Say, вАЬShall I inform you of something far more enraging than that? ЋєIt isЋЇ the Fire with which Allah has threatened those who disbelieve. What an evil destination!вАЭ"
  22,73,"O humanity! A lesson is set forth, so listen to it ЋєcarefullyЋЇ: those ЋєidolsЋЇ you invoke besides Allah can never create Ћєso much asЋЇ a fly, even if they ЋєallЋЇ were to come together for that. And if a fly were to snatch anything away from them, they cannot ЋєevenЋЇ retrieve it from the fly. How powerless are those who invoke and those invoked"
  22,74,"They have not shown Allah the reverence He deserves. Surely Allah is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  22,75,"Allah selects messengers from both angels and people, for Allah is truly All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  22,76,He knows what is ahead of them and what is behind them. And to Allah ЋєallЋЇ matters will be returned Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ
  22,77,"O believers! Bow down, prostrate yourselves, worship your Lord, and do Ћєwhat isЋЇ good so that you may be successful"
  22,78,"Strive for Ћєthe cause ofЋЇ Allah in the way He deserves, for Ћєit isЋЇ He ЋєWhoЋЇ has chosen you, and laid upon you no hardship in the religionвАФthe way of your forefather Abraham. ЋєIt is AllahЋЇ Who named you вАШthe ones who submitвАЩ¬†Ћєin theЋЇ earlier ЋєScripturesЋЇ and in this ЋєQuranЋЇ, so that the Messenger may be a witness over you, and that you may be witnesses over humanity. So establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and hold fast to Allah. He ЋєaloneЋЇ is your Guardian. What an excellent Guardian, and what an excellent Helper"
  23,1,Successful indeed are the believers
  23,2,those who humble themselves in prayer
  23,3,those who avoid idle talk
  23,4,those who pay alms-tax
  23,5,those who guard their chastity
  23,6,"except with their wives or those ЋєbondwomenЋЇ in their possession,¬†for then they are free from blame"
  23,7,but whoever seeks beyond that are the transgressors
  23,8,Ћєthe believers are alsoЋЇ those who are true to their trusts and covenants
  23,9,and those who are ЋєproperlyЋЇ observant of their prayers
  23,10,These are the ones who will be awarded
  23,11,Paradise as their own.¬†They will be there forever
  23,12,"And indeed, We created humankind¬†from an extract of clay"
  23,13,then placed each ЋєhumanЋЇ as a sperm-drop¬†in a secure place
  23,14,"then We developed the drop into a clinging clot Ћєof bloodЋЇ, then developed the clot into a lump Ћєof fleshЋЇ, then developed the lump into bones, then clothed the bones with flesh, then We brought it into being as a new creation.¬†So Blessed is Allah, the Best of Creators"
  23,15,After that you will surely die
  23,16,then on the Day of Judgment you will be resurrected
  23,17,"And indeed, We created above you seven levels Ћєof heavenЋЇ. We are never unmindful of ЋєOurЋЇ creation"
  23,18,"We send down rain from the sky in perfect measure, causing it to soak into the earth. And We are surely able to take it away"
  23,19,"With it We produce for you gardens of palm trees and grapevines, in which there are abundant fruits, and from which you may eat"
  23,20,"as well as ЋєoliveЋЇ trees which grow at Mount Sinai, providing oil and a condiment to eat"
  23,21,"And there is certainly a lesson for you in cattle, from whose bellies We give you ЋєmilkЋЇ to drink, and in them are many other benefits for you, and from them you may eat"
  23,22,And you are carried upon Ћєsome ofЋЇ them and upon ships
  23,23,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people. He declared, вАЬO my people! Worship Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ. You have no god other than Him. Will you not then fear ЋєHimЋЇ?вАЭ"
  23,24,"But the disbelieving chiefs of his people said Ћєto the massesЋЇ, вАЬThis is only a human like you, who wants to be superior to you. Had Allah willed, He could have easily sent down angels ЋєinsteadЋЇ. We have never heard of this in Ћєthe history ofЋЇ our forefathers"
  23,25,"He is simply insane, so bear with him for a while.вАЭ"
  23,26,"Noah prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Help me, because they have denied ЋєmeЋЇ.вАЭ"
  23,27,"So We inspired him: вАЬBuild the Ark under Our ЋєwatchfulЋЇ Eyes and directions. Then when Our command comes and the oven bursts Ћєwith waterЋЇ,¬†take on board a pair from every species along with your familyвАФexcept those against whom the decree Ћєto drownЋЇ has already been passed. And do not plead with Me for those who have done wrong, for they will surely be drowned.вАЭ"
  23,28,"Then when you and those with you have settled in the Ark, say, вАЬAll praise is for Allah, Who saved us from the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  23,29,"And pray, вАЬMy Lord! Allow me a blessed landing, for You are the best accommodator.вАЭ"
  23,30,Surely in this are lessons.¬†And We ЋєalwaysЋЇ put ЋєpeopleЋЇ to the test
  23,31,Then We raised another generation after them
  23,32,"and sent to them a messenger from among themselves, Ћєdeclaring,ЋЇ вАЬWorship Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ. You have no god other than Him. Will you not then fear ЋєHimЋЇ?вАЭ"
  23,33,"But the chiefs of his peopleвАФwho disbelieved, denied the meeting Ћєwith AllahЋЇ in the Hereafter, and were spoiled by the worldly luxuries We had provided for themвАФsaid Ћєto the massesЋЇ, вАЬThis is only a human like you. He eats what you eat, and drinks what you drink"
  23,34,"And if you ЋєeverЋЇ obey a human like yourselves, then you would certainly be losers"
  23,35,"Does he promise you that once you are dead and reduced to dust and bones, you will be brought forth ЋєaliveЋЇ"
  23,36,"Impossible, simply impossible is what you are promised"
  23,37,"There is nothing beyond our worldly life. We die, others are born, and none will be resurrected"
  23,38,"He is no more than a man who has fabricated a lie about Allah, and we will never believe in him.вАЭ"
  23,39,"The messenger prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Help me, because they have denied ЋєmeЋЇ.вАЭ"
  23,40,"Allah responded, вАЬSoon they will be truly regretful.вАЭ"
  23,41,"Then the ЋєmightyЋЇ blast overtook them with justice, and We reduced them to rubble. So away with the wrongdoing people"
  23,42,Then We raised other generations after them
  23,43,"No people can advance their doom, nor can they delay it"
  23,44,"Then We sent Our messengers in succession: whenever a messenger came to his people, they denied him. So We destroyed them, one after the other, reducing them to ЋєcautionaryЋЇ tales. So away with the people who refuse to believe"
  23,45,Then We sent Moses and his brother Aaron with Our signs¬†and compelling proof
  23,46,"to Pharaoh and his chiefs, but they behaved arrogantly and were a tyrannical people"
  23,47,"They argued, вАЬWill we believe in two humans, like ourselves, whose people are slaves to us?вАЭ"
  23,48,"So they rejected them both, and ЋєsoЋЇ were among those destroyed"
  23,49,"And We certainly gave Moses the Scripture, so perhaps his people would be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  23,50,"And We made the son of Mary and his mother a sign, and gave them refuge on high groundвАФa ЋєsuitableЋЇ place for rest with flowing water"
  23,51,"O messengers! Eat from what is good and lawful, and act righteously. Indeed, I fully know what you do"
  23,52,"Surely this religion of yours is ЋєonlyЋЇ one, and I am your Lord, so fear Me ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  23,53,"Yet the people have divided it into different sects, each rejoicing in what they have"
  23,54,So leave them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in their heedlessness for a while
  23,55,"Do they think, since We provide them with wealth and children"
  23,56,that We hasten to ЋєhonourЋЇ them ЋєwithЋЇ all kinds of good? No! They are not aware
  23,57,Surely those who tremble in awe of their Lord
  23,58,and who believe in the revelations of their Lord
  23,59,and who associate none with their Lord
  23,60,"and who do whatever ЋєgoodЋЇ they do with their hearts fearful, ЋєknowingЋЇ that they will return to their LordвАФ"
  23,61,"it is they who race to do good deeds, always taking the lead"
  23,62,We never require of any soul more than what it can afford. And with Us is a record which speaks the truth. None will be wronged
  23,63,"But the hearts of those Ћєwho disbelieveЋЇ are oblivious to Ћєall ofЋЇ this,¬†and they have other ЋєevilЋЇ deeds, opposite to this, in which they are engrossed"
  23,64,"But as soon as We seize their elite with torment, they start to cry for help"
  23,65,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬDo not cry for help today. Surely you will never be saved from Us"
  23,66,"Indeed, My revelations were recited to you, but you used to back away Ћєin disgustЋЇ"
  23,67,"boasting of the Sacred House, and babbling Ћєnonsense about the QuranЋЇ by night.вАЭ"
  23,68,Is it because they have never contemplated the Word Ћєof AllahЋЇ? Or ЋєbecauseЋЇ there has come to them something that did not come to their forefathers
  23,69,"Or ЋєbecauseЋЇ they failed to recognize their Messenger, and so they denied him"
  23,70,"Or ЋєbecauseЋЇ they say, вАЬHe is insane?вАЭ In fact, he has come to them with the truth, but most of them are resentful of the truth"
  23,71,"Had the truth followed their desires,¬†the heavens, the earth, and all those in them would have certainly been corrupted. In fact, We have brought them Ћєthe means toЋЇ their glory, but they turn away from it"
  23,72,"Or Ћєis it becauseЋЇ you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are asking them for tribute? But the reward of your Lord is best, for He is the Best Provider"
  23,73,And surely you are calling them to the Straight Path
  23,74,but those who disbelieve in the Hereafter are certainly deviating from that Path
  23,75,"ЋєEvenЋЇ if We had mercy on them and removed their affliction,¬†they would still persist in their transgression, wandering blindly"
  23,76,"And We have already seized them with torment, but they never humbled themselves to their Lord, nor did they ЋєsubmissivelyЋЇ appeal Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  23,77,"But as soon as We open for them a gate of severe punishment, they will be utterly desperate"
  23,78,"He is the One Who created for you hearing, sight, and intellect. ЋєYetЋЇ you hardly give any thanks"
  23,79,"And He is the One Who has dispersed you ЋєallЋЇ over the earth, and to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be gathered"
  23,80,"And He is the One Who gives life and causes death, and to Him belongs the alternation of the day and night. Will you not then understand"
  23,81,But they ЋєjustЋЇ say what their predecessors said
  23,82,"They said, вАЬOnce we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be resurrected"
  23,83,"We have already been promised this, as well as our forefathers earlier. This is nothing but ancient fables!вАЭ"
  23,84,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬTo whom belong the earth and all those on it, if you ЋєreallyЋЇ know?вАЭ"
  23,85,"They will reply, вАЬTo Allah!вАЭ Say, вАЬWhy are you not then mindful?вАЭ"
  23,86,"ЋєAndЋЇ ask ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬWho is the Lord of the seven heavens and the Lord of the Mighty Throne?вАЭ"
  23,87,"They will reply, вАЬAllah.вАЭ Say, вАЬWill you not then fear ЋєHimЋЇ?вАЭ"
  23,88,"Ask Ћєthem also,ЋЇ вАЬIn Whose Hands is the authority over all things, protecting ЋєallЋЇ while none can protect against Him, if you ЋєreallyЋЇ know?вАЭ"
  23,89,"They will reply, вАЬAllah.вАЭ Say, вАЬHow are you then so deluded?вАЭ"
  23,90,"In fact, We have brought them the truth, and they are certainly liars"
  23,91,"Allah has never had ЋєanyЋЇ offspring, nor is there any god besides Him. Otherwise, each god would have taken away what he created, and they would have tried to dominate one another. Glorified is Allah above what they claim"
  23,92,ЋєHe is theЋЇ Knower of the seen and unseen. Exalted is He above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ
  23,93,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬMy Lord! Should You show me what they¬†are threatened with"
  23,94,"then, my Lord, do not count me among the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  23,95,We are indeed able to show you what We have threatened them with
  23,96,Respond to evil with what is best. We know well what they claim
  23,97,"And say, вАЬMy Lord! I seek refuge in You from the temptations of the devils"
  23,98,"And I seek refuge in You, my Lord, that they ЋєevenЋЇ come near me.вАЭ"
  23,99,"When death approaches any of them, they cry, вАЬMy Lord! Let me go back"
  23,100,so I may do good in what I left behind.вАЭ Never! It is only a ЋєuselessЋЇ appeal they make. And there is a barrier behind them until the Day they are resurrected
  23,101,"Then, when the Trumpet will be blown,¬†there will be no kinship between them on that Day, nor will they Ћєeven care toЋЇ ask about one another"
  23,102,"As for those whose scale is heavy Ћєwith good deedsЋЇ, it is they who will be successful"
  23,103,"But those whose scale is light, they will have doomed themselves, staying in Hell forever"
  23,104,"The Fire will burn their faces, leaving them deformed"
  23,105,"ЋєIt will be said,ЋЇ вАЬWere My revelations not recited to you, but you used to deny them?вАЭ"
  23,106,"They will cry, вАЬOur Lord! Our ill-fate took hold of us, so we became a misguided people"
  23,107,"Our Lord! Take us out of this ЋєFireЋЇ. Then if we ever return Ћєto denialЋЇ, we will truly be wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  23,108,"Allah will respond, вАЬBe despised in there! Do not ЋєeverЋЇ plead with Me ЋєagainЋЇ"
  23,109,"Indeed, there was a group of My servants who used to pray, вАШOur Lord! We have believed, so forgive us and have mercy on us, for You are the best of those who show mercy,вАЩ"
  23,110,but you were Ћєso busyЋЇ making fun of them that it made you forget My remembrance. And you used to laugh at them
  23,111,"Today I have indeed rewarded them for their perseverance: they are certainly the triumphant.вАЭ"
  23,112,"He will ask ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬHow many years did you remain on earth?вАЭ"
  23,113,"They will reply, вАЬWe remained ЋєonlyЋЇ a day or part of a day.¬†But ask those who kept count.вАЭ"
  23,114,"He will say, вАЬYou only remained for a little while, if only you knew"
  23,115,"Did you then think that We had created you without purpose, and that you would never be returned to Us?вАЭ"
  23,116,"Exalted is Allah, the True King! There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him, the Lord of the Honourable Throne"
  23,117,"Whoever invokes, besides Allah, another godвАФfor which they can have no proofвАФthey will surely find their penalty with their Lord. Indeed, the disbelievers will never succeed"
  23,118,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬMy Lord! Forgive and have mercy, for You are the best of those who show mercy.вАЭ"
  24,1,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a s√їrah¬†which We have revealed and made Ћєits rulingsЋЇ obligatory, and revealed in it clear commandments so that you may be mindful"
  24,2,"As for female and male fornicators, give each of them one hundred lashes,¬†and do not let pity for them make you lenient in ЋєenforcingЋЇ the law of Allah, if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in Allah and the Last Day. And let a number of believers witness their punishment"
  24,3,A male fornicator would only marry a female fornicator or idolatress. And a female fornicator would only be married to a fornicator or idolater. This is ЋєallЋЇ forbidden to the believers
  24,4,"Those who accuse chaste women Ћєof adulteryЋЇ and fail to produce four witnesses, give them eighty lashes ЋєeachЋЇ. And do not ever accept any testimony from themвАФfor they are indeed the rebelliousвАФ"
  24,5,"except those who repent afterwards and mend their ways, then surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  24,6,"And those who accuse their wives Ћєof adulteryЋЇ but have no witness except themselves, the accuser must testify,¬†swearing four times by Allah that he is telling the truth"
  24,7,and a fifth oath that Allah may condemn him if he is lying
  24,8,"For her to be spared the punishment, she must swear four times by Allah that he is telling a lie"
  24,9,and a fifth oath that Allah may be displeased with her if he is telling the truth
  24,10,"ЋєYou would have suffered,ЋЇ had it not been for AllahвАЩs grace and mercy upon you, and had Allah not been Accepting of Repentance, All-Wise"
  24,11,"Indeed, those who came up with that ЋєoutrageousЋЇ slander are a group of you. Do not think this is bad for you. Rather, it is good for you.¬†They will be punished, each according to their share of the sin. As for their mastermind,¬†he will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  24,12,"If only the believing men and women had thought well of one another, when you heard this ЋєrumourЋЇ, and said, вАЬThis is clearly Ћєan outrageousЋЇ slander!вАЭ"
  24,13,"Why did they not produce four witnesses? Now, since they have failed to produce witnesses, they are ЋєtrulyЋЇ liars in the sight of Allah"
  24,14,"Had it not been for AllahвАЩs grace and mercy upon you in this world and the Hereafter, you would have certainly been touched with a tremendous punishment for what you plunged intoвАФ"
  24,15,"when you passed it from one tongue to the other, and said with your mouths what you had no knowledge of, taking it lightly while it is ЋєextremelyЋЇ serious in the sight of Allah"
  24,16,"If only you had said upon hearing it, вАЬHow can we speak about such a thing! Glory be to You ЋєO LordЋЇ! This is a heinous slander!вАЭ"
  24,17,"Allah forbids you from ever doing something like this again, if you are ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  24,18,"And Allah makes ЋєHisЋЇ commandments clear to you, for Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  24,19,"Indeed, those who love to see indecency spread among the believers will suffer a painful punishment in this life and the Hereafter. Allah knows and you do not know"
  24,20,"ЋєYou would have suffered,ЋЇ had it not been for AllahвАЩs grace and mercy upon you, and had Allah not been Ever Gracious, Most Merciful"
  24,21,"O believers! Do not follow the footsteps of Satan. Whoever follows SatanвАЩs footsteps, then Ћєlet them know thatЋЇ he surely bids Ћєall toЋЇ immorality and wickedness. Had it not been for AllahвАЩs grace and mercy upon you, none of you would have ever been purified. But Allah purifies whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  24,22,"Do not let the people of virtue and affluence among you swear to suspend donations to their relatives, the needy, and the emigrants in the cause of Allah. Let them pardon and forgive. Do you not love to be forgiven by Allah? And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  24,23,"Surely those who accuse chaste, unsuspecting,¬†believing women are cursed in this life and the Hereafter. And they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  24,24,"on the Day their tongues, hands, and feet will testify against them for what they used to do"
  24,25,"On that Day, Allah will give them their just penalty in full, and they will Ћєcome toЋЇ know that Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Ultimate Truth"
  24,26,"Wicked women are for wicked men, and wicked men are for wicked women. And virtuous women are for virtuous men, and virtuous men are for virtuous women. The virtuous are innocent of what the wicked say. They will have forgiveness and an honourable provision"
  24,27,"O believers! Do not enter any house other than your own until you have asked for permission and greeted its occupants. This is best for you, so perhaps you will be mindful"
  24,28,"If you find no one at home, do not enter it until you have been given permission. And if you are asked to leave, then leave. That is purer for you. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of what you do"
  24,29,There is no blame on you if you enter public places¬†where there is something of benefit for you. And Allah knows what you reveal and what you conceal
  24,30,ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Tell the believing men to lower their gaze and guard their chastity. That is purer for them. Surely Allah is All-Aware of what they do
  24,31,"And tell the believing women to lower their gaze and guard their chastity, and not to reveal their adornments¬†except what normally appears.¬†Let them draw their veils over their chests, and not reveal their ЋєhiddenЋЇ adornments¬†except to their husbands, their fathers, their fathers-in-law, their sons, their stepsons, their brothers, their brothersвАЩ sons or sistersвАЩ sons, their fellow women, those ЋєbondwomenЋЇ in their possession, male attendants with no desire, or children who are still unaware of womenвАЩs nakedness. Let them not stomp their feet, drawing attention to their hidden adornments. Turn to Allah in repentance all together, O believers, so that you may be successful"
  24,32,"Marry off the ЋєfreeЋЇ singles among you, as well as the righteous of your bondmen and bondwomen. If they are poor, Allah will enrich them out of His bounty. For Allah is All-Bountiful, All-Knowing"
  24,33,"And let those who do not have the means to marry keep themselves chaste until Allah enriches them out of His bounty. And if any of those ЋєbondspeopleЋЇ in your possession desires a deed of emancipation, make it possible for them, if you find goodness in them. And give them some of AllahвАЩs wealth which He has granted you. Do not force your ЋєslaveЋЇ girls into prostitution for your own worldly gains while they wish to remain chaste. And if someone coerces them, then after such a coercion Allah is certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful Ћєto themЋЇ"
  24,34,"Indeed, We have sent down to you clear revelations, along with examples of those who had gone before you, and a lesson to the God-fearing"
  24,35,"Allah is the Light of the heavens and the earth. His light¬†is like a niche in which there is a lamp, the lamp is in a crystal, the crystal is like a shining star, lit from Ћєthe oil ofЋЇ a blessed olive tree, ЋєlocatedЋЇ neither to the east nor the west,¬†whose oil would almost glow, even without being touched by fire. Light upon light! Allah guides whoever He wills to His light. And Allah sets forth parables for humanity. For Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  24,36,"ЋєThat light shinesЋЇ through houses Ћєof worshipЋЇ which Allah has ordered to be raised, and where His Name is mentioned. He is glorified there morning and evening"
  24,37,"by men¬†who are not distractedвАФeither by buying or sellingвАФfrom AllahвАЩs remembrance, or performing prayer, or paying alms-tax. They fear a Day when hearts and eyes will tremble"
  24,38,"ЋєhopingЋЇ that Allah may reward them according to the best of their deeds, and increase them out of His grace. And Allah provides for whoever He wills without limit"
  24,39,"As for the disbelievers, their deeds are like a mirage in a desert, which the thirsty perceive as water, but when they approach it, they find it to be nothing. Instead, they find Allah there Ћєin the Hereafter, readyЋЇ to settle their account. And Allah is swift in reckoning"
  24,40,"Or Ћєtheir deeds areЋЇ like the darkness in a deep sea, covered by waves upon waves,¬†topped by ЋєdarkЋЇ clouds. Darkness upon darkness! If one stretches out their hand, they can hardly see it. And whoever Allah does not bless with light will have no light"
  24,41,"Do you not see that Allah is glorified by all those in the heavens and the earth, even the birds as they soar? Each ЋєinstinctivelyЋЇ knows their manner of prayer and glorification. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all they do"
  24,42,To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And to Allah is the final return
  24,43,"Do you not see that Allah gently drives the clouds, then joins them together, piling them up into masses, from which you see raindrops come forth? And He sends down from the sky mountains Ћєof cloudsЋЇ loaded with hail, pouring it on whoever He wills and averting it from whoever He wills. The flash of the cloudsвАЩ lightning nearly takes away eyesight"
  24,44,Allah alternates the day and night. Surely in this is a lesson for people of insight
  24,45,"And Allah has created from water every living creature. Some of them crawl on their bellies, some walk on two legs, and some walk on four. Allah creates whatever He wills. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  24,46,We have indeed sent down revelations clarifying Ћєthe truthЋЇ. But Allah ЋєonlyЋЇ guides whoever He wills to the Straight Path
  24,47,"And the hypocrites say, вАЬWe believe in Allah and the Messenger, and we obey.вАЭ Then a group of them turns away soon after that. These are not ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  24,48,"And as soon as they are called to Allah and His Messenger so he may judge between them, a group of them¬†turns away"
  24,49,"But if the truth is in their favour, they come to him, fully submitting"
  24,50,"Is there a sickness in their hearts? Or are they in doubt? Or do they fear that Allah and His Messenger will be unjust to them? In fact, it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ wrongdoers"
  24,51,"The only response of the ЋєtrueЋЇ believers, when they are called to Allah and His Messenger so he may judge between them, is to say, вАЬWe hear and obey.вАЭ It is they who will ЋєtrulyЋЇ succeed"
  24,52,"For whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger, and fears Allah and is mindful of Him, then it is they who will ЋєtrulyЋЇ triumph"
  24,53,"They swear by Allah their most solemn oaths that if you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ were to command them, they would certainly march forth Ћєin AllahвАЩs causeЋЇ. Say, вАЬЋєYouЋЇ do not Ћєhave toЋЇ swear; your obedience is well known!вАЭ¬†Surely Allah is All-Aware of what you do.вАЭ"
  24,54,"Say, вАЬObey Allah and obey the Messenger. But if you turn away, then he is only responsible for his duty¬†and you are responsible for yours.¬†And if you obey him, you will be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided. The MessengerвАЩs duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ clearly.вАЭ"
  24,55,"Allah has promised those of you who believe and do good that He will certainly make them successors in the land, as He did with those before them; and will surely establish for them their faith which He has chosen for them; and will indeed change their fear into securityвАФЋєprovided thatЋЇ they worship Me, associating nothing with Me. But whoever disbelieves after this ЋєpromiseЋЇ, it is they who will be the rebellious"
  24,56,"Moreover, establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and obey the Messenger, so you may be shown mercy"
  24,57,"Do not think ЋєO ProphetЋЇ that the disbelievers can escape in the land. The Fire will be their home. Indeed, what an evil destination"
  24,58,"O believers! Let those ЋєbondspeopleЋЇ in your possession and those of you who are still under age ask for your permission Ћєto come inЋЇ at three times: before dawn prayer, when you take off your ЋєouterЋЇ clothes at noon, and after the late evening prayer. ЋєThese areЋЇ three times of privacy for you. Other than these times, there is no blame on you or them to move freely, attending to one another. This is how Allah makes the revelations clear to you, for Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  24,59,"And when your children reach the age of puberty, let them seek permission Ћєto come inЋЇ, as their seniors do. This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, for Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  24,60,"As for elderly women past the age of marriage, there is no blame on them if they take off their ЋєouterЋЇ garments, without revealing their adornments. But it is better for them if they avoid this ЋєaltogetherЋЇ. And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  24,61,"There is no restriction on the blind, or the disabled, or the sick.¬†Nor on yourselves if you eat from your homes,¬†or the homes of your fathers, or your mothers, or your brothers, or your sisters, or your paternal uncles, or your paternal aunts, or your maternal uncles, or your maternal aunts, or from the homes in your trust, or Ћєthe homes ofЋЇ your friends. There is no blame on you eating together or separately. However, when you enter houses, greet one another with a greeting Ћєof peaceЋЇ from Allah, blessed and good.¬†This is how Allah makes His revelations clear to you, so perhaps you will understand"
  24,62,"The ЋєtrueЋЇ believers are only those who believe in Allah and His Messenger, and when they are with him on a public matter, they do not leave without his permission. Indeed, those who ask your permission ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are the ones who ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in Allah and His Messenger. So when they ask your permission for a private matter, grant permission to whoever you wish and ask AllahвАЩs forgiveness for them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  24,63,"Do not treat the MessengerвАЩs summons to you Ћєas lightlyЋЇ as your summons to one another.¬†Allah certainly knows those of you who slip away, hiding behind others.¬†So let those who disobey his orders beware, for an affliction may befall them, or a painful torment may overtake them"
  24,64,"Surely to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. He knows well what you stand for. And ЋєonЋЇ the Day all will be returned to Him, He will inform them of what they did. For Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  25,1,"Blessed is the One Who sent down the Standard¬†to His servant,¬†so that he may be a warner to the whole world"
  25,2,"ЋєAllah isЋЇ the One to Whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, Who has never had ЋєanyЋЇ offspring, nor does He have a partner in ЋєgoverningЋЇ the kingdom. He has created everything, ordaining it precisely"
  25,3,"Yet they have taken besides Him gods who cannot create anything but are themselves created. Nor can they protect or benefit themselves. Nor can they control life, death, or resurrection"
  25,4,"The disbelievers say, вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ is nothing but a fabrication which he¬†made up with the help of others.вАЭ Their claim is totally unjustified and untrue"
  25,5,"And they say, вАЬЋєThese revelations are onlyЋЇ ancient fables which he has had written down, and they are rehearsed to him morning and evening.вАЭ"
  25,6,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ has been revealed by the One Who knows the secrets of the heavens and the earth. Surely He is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  25,7,"And they say ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhat kind of messenger is this who eats food and goes about in market-places Ћєfor a livingЋЇ? If only an angel had been sent down with him to be his co-warner"
  25,8,"or a treasure had been cast down to him, or he had had a garden from which he may eat!вАЭ And the wrongdoers say Ћєto the believersЋЇ, вАЬYou are only following a bewitched man.вАЭ"
  25,9,See ЋєO ProphetЋЇ how they call you names!¬†So they have gone so ЋєfarЋЇ astray that they cannot find the ЋєRightЋЇ Way
  25,10,"Blessed is the One WhoвАФif He willsвАФcan give you far better than ЋєallЋЇ that: gardens under which rivers flow, and palaces as well"
  25,11,"In fact, they deny the Hour.¬†And for the deniers of the Hour, We have prepared a blazing Fire"
  25,12,"Once it sees them from a distance, they will hear it fuming and growling"
  25,13,"And when they are tossed into a narrow place inside ЋєHellЋЇ, chained together, then and there they will cry out for ЋєinstantЋЇ destruction"
  25,14,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬDo not cry only once for destruction, but cry many times over!вАЭ"
  25,15,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIs this better or the Garden of Eternity which the righteous have been promised, as a reward and Ћєan ultimateЋЇ destination"
  25,16,"There they will have whatever they wish for, forever. That is a promise Ћєto be sought afterЋЇ, binding on your Lord.вАЭ"
  25,17,"ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day He will gather them along with what they used to worship besides Allah, and ask Ћєthe objects of worshipЋЇ,¬†вАЬWas it you who misled these servants of Mine, or did they stray from the Way Ћєon their ownЋЇ?вАЭ"
  25,18,"They will say, вАЬGlory be to You! It was not right for Ћєothers likeЋЇ us to take any lords besides You,¬†but You allowed enjoyment for them and their forefathers Ћєfor so longЋЇ that they forgot ЋєYourЋЇ remembrance and became a doomed people.вАЭ"
  25,19,"ЋєThe doomed will be toldЋЇ, вАЬYour gods have clearly denied your claims. So now you can neither ward off Ћєthe punishmentЋЇ nor get any help.вАЭ And whoever of you does wrong, We will make them taste a horrible punishment"
  25,20,"We never sent any messenger before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, who did not eat food and go about in market-places. We have made some of you a trial for others. Will you Ћєnot thenЋЇ be patient? And your Lord is All-Seeing"
  25,21,"Those who do not expect to meet Us say, вАЬIf only the angels were sent down to us, or we could see our Lord!вАЭ They have certainly been carried away by their arrogance and have entirely exceeded all limits"
  25,22,"ЋєButЋЇ on the Day they will see the angels, there will be no good news for the wicked, who will cry, вАЬKeep away! Away Ћєfrom usЋЇ!вАЭ"
  25,23,"Then We will turn to whatever ЋєgoodЋЇ deeds they did, reducing them to scattered dust"
  25,24,ЋєButЋЇ on that Day the residents of Paradise will have the best settlement and the finest place to rest
  25,25,"ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day the heavens will burst with clouds, and the angels will be sent down in successive ranks"
  25,26,True authority on that Day will belong ЋєonlyЋЇ to the Most Compassionate.¬†And it will be a hard day for the disbelievers
  25,27,"And Ћєbeware ofЋЇ the Day the wrongdoer will bite his nails Ћєin regretЋЇ and say, вАЬOh! I wish I had followed the Way along with the Messenger"
  25,28,Woe to me! I wish I had never taken so-and-so as a close friend
  25,29,It was he who truly made me stray from the Reminder after it had reached me.вАЭ And Satan has always betrayed humanity
  25,30,"The Messenger has cried, вАЬO my Lord! My people have indeed received this Quran with neglect.вАЭ"
  25,31,"Similarly, We made enemies for every prophet from among the wicked, but sufficient is your Lord as a Guide and Helper"
  25,32,"The disbelievers say, вАЬIf only the Quran had been sent down to him all at once!вАЭ ЋєWe have sent itЋЇ as such Ћєin stagesЋЇ so We may reassure your heart with it. And We have revealed it at a deliberate pace"
  25,33,"Whenever they bring you an argument, We come to you with the right refutation and the best explanation"
  25,34,"Those who will be dragged into Hell on their faces will be in the worst place, and are ЋєnowЋЇ farthest from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way"
  25,35,We certainly gave Moses the Book and appointed his brother Aaron as his helper
  25,36,"We had ordered ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬGo to the people who would deny Our signs.вАЭ Then We annihilated the deniers entirely"
  25,37,"And when the people of Noah rejected the messengers,¬†We drowned them, making them an example to humanity. And We have prepared a painful punishment for the wrongdoers"
  25,38,"Also ЋєWe destroyedЋЇ вАЩ»Вd, Tham√їd, and the people of the Water-pit,¬†as well as many peoples in between"
  25,39,"For each We set forth ЋєvariousЋЇ lessons, and We ultimately destroyed each"
  25,40,"They have certainly passed by the city Ћєof SodomЋЇ, which had been showered with a dreadful rain Ћєof stonesЋЇ. Have they not seen its ruins? But they do not expect to be resurrected"
  25,41,"When they see you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, they only make fun of you, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬIs this the one that Allah has sent as a messenger"
  25,42,"He would have almost tricked us away from our gods, had we not been so devoted to them.вАЭ ЋєButЋЇ soon they will know, when they face the punishment, who is far astray from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way"
  25,43,Have you seen ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the one who has taken their own desires as their god? Will you then be a keeper over them
  25,44,"Or do you think that most of them listen or understand?¬†They are only like cattleвАФno, more than that, they are astray from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way"
  25,45,Have you not seen how your Lord extends the shadeвАФHe could have simply made it ЋєremainЋЇ still if He so willedвАФthen We make the sun its guide
  25,46,causing the shade to retreat gradually
  25,47,"He is the One Who has made the night for you as a cover, and ЋєmadeЋЇ sleep for resting, and the day for rising"
  25,48,"And He is the One Who sends the winds ushering in His mercy, and We send down pure rain from the sky"
  25,49,"giving life to a lifeless land, and providing water for countless animals and humans of Our Own creation"
  25,50,"We certainly disperse it among them so they may be mindful, but most people persist in ungratefulness"
  25,51,"Had We willed, We could have easily sent a warner to every society"
  25,52,"So do not yield to the disbelievers, but strive diligently against them with this ЋєQuranЋЇ"
  25,53,"And He is the One Who merges the two bodies of water: one fresh and palatable and the other salty and bitter, placing between them a barrier they cannot cross"
  25,54,"And He is the One Who creates human beings from a ЋєhumbleЋЇ liquid,¬†then establishes for them bonds of kinship and marriage. For your Lord is Most Capable"
  25,55,Yet they worship besides Allah what can neither benefit nor harm them. And the disbeliever always collaborates against their Lord
  25,56,And We have sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ only as a deliverer of good news and a warner
  25,57,"Say, вАЬI do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇ, but whoever wishes, let them pursue the Way to their Lord.вАЭ"
  25,58,"Put your trust in the Ever-Living, Who never dies, and glorify His praises. Sufficient is He as All-Aware of the sins of His servants"
  25,59,"ЋєHe isЋЇ the One Who created the heavens and the earth and everything in between in six Days,¬†then established Himself on the Throne. ЋєHe isЋЇ the Most Compassionate! Ask Ћєnone other thanЋЇ the All-Knowledgeable about Himself"
  25,60,"When it is said to them, вАЬProstrate to the Most Compassionate,вАЭ they ask Ћєin disgustЋЇ, вАЬWhat is вАШthe Most CompassionateвАЩ? Will we prostrate to whatever you order us to?вАЭ And it only drives them farther away"
  25,61,"Blessed is the One Who has placed constellations in the sky, as well as a ЋєradiantЋЇ lamp¬†and a luminous moon"
  25,62,"And He is the One Who causes the day and the night to alternate, Ћєas a signЋЇ for whoever desires to be mindful or to be grateful"
  25,63,"The ЋєtrueЋЇ servants of the Most Compassionate are those who walk on the earth humbly, and when the foolish address them ЋєimproperlyЋЇ, they only respond with peace"
  25,64,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who spend Ћєa good portion ofЋЇ the night, prostrating themselves and standing before their Lord"
  25,65,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who pray, вАЬOur Lord! Keep the punishment of Hell away from us, for its punishment is indeed unrelenting"
  25,66,It is certainly an evil place to settle and reside.вАЭ
  25,67,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who spend neither wastefully nor stingily, but moderately in between"
  25,68,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who do not invoke any other god besides Allah, nor take a ЋєhumanЋЇ lifeвАФmade sacred by AllahвАФexcept with ЋєlegalЋЇ right,¬†nor commit fornication. And whoever does Ћєany ofЋЇ this will face the penalty"
  25,69,"Their punishment will be multiplied on the Day of Judgment, and they will remain in it forever, in disgrace"
  25,70,"As for those who repent, believe, and do good deeds, they are the ones whose evil deeds Allah will change into good deeds. For Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  25,71,And whoever repents and does good has truly turned to Allah properly
  25,72,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who do not bear false witness, and when they come across falsehood, they pass ЋєitЋЇ by with dignity"
  25,73,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who, when reminded of the revelation of their Lord, do not turn a blind eye or a deaf ear to it"
  25,74,"ЋєThey areЋЇ those who pray, вАЬOur Lord! Bless us with ЋєpiousЋЇ spouses and offspring who will be the joy of our hearts, and make us models for the righteous.вАЭ"
  25,75,"It is they who will be rewarded with ЋєelevatedЋЇ mansions Ћєin ParadiseЋЇ for their perseverance, and will be received with salutations and Ћєgreetings ofЋЇ peace"
  25,76,staying there forever. What an excellent place to settle and reside
  25,77,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYou ЋєallЋЇ would not ЋєevenЋЇ matter to my Lord were it not for your faith Ћєin HimЋЇ. But now you ЋєdisbelieversЋЇ have denied Ћєthe truthЋЇ, so the torment is bound to come.вАЭ"
  26,1,бєђ√Ґ-Sƒ©n-Mƒ©m
  26,2,These are the verses of the clear Book
  26,3,Perhaps you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ will grieve yourself to death over their disbelief
  26,4,"If We willed, We could send down upon them a ЋєcompellingЋЇ sign from the heavens, leaving their necks bent in ЋєutterЋЇ submission to it"
  26,5,"Whatever new reminder comes to them from the Most Compassionate, they always turn away from it"
  26,6,"They have certainly denied Ћєthe truthЋЇ, so they will soon face the consequences of their ridicule"
  26,7,"Have they failed to look at the earth, Ћєto seeЋЇ how many types of fine plants We have caused to grow in it"
  26,8,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,9,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,10,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when your Lord called out to Moses, вАЬGo to the wrongdoing peopleвАФ"
  26,11,the people of Pharaoh. Will they not fear ЋєAllahЋЇ?вАЭ
  26,12,"He replied, вАЬMy Lord! I fear that they will reject me"
  26,13,And ЋєsoЋЇ my heart will be broken and my tongue will be tied. So send Aaron along Ћєas a messengerЋЇ
  26,14,"Also, they have a charge against me,¬†so I fear they may kill me.вАЭ"
  26,15,"Allah responded, вАЬCertainly not! So go, both of you, with Our signs. We will be with you, listening"
  26,16,"Go to Pharaoh and say, вАШWe are messengers from the Lord of all worlds"
  26,17,"Ћєcommanded to say:ЋЇ вАШLet the Children of Israel go with us.вАЩвАЩвАЭ"
  26,18,"Pharaoh protested, вАЬDid we not raise you among us as a child, and you stayed several years of your life in our care"
  26,19,"Then you did what you did,¬†being ЋєutterlyЋЇ ungrateful!вАЭ"
  26,20,"Moses replied, вАЬI did it then, lacking guidance"
  26,21,So I fled from you when I feared you. Then my Lord granted me wisdom and made me one of the messengers
  26,22,"How can that be a вАШfavour,вАЩ of which you remind me, when Ћєit was only becauseЋЇ you ЋєhaveЋЇ enslaved the Children of Israel?вАЭ"
  26,23,"Pharaoh asked, вАЬAnd what is вАШthe Lord of all worldsвАЩ?вАЭ"
  26,24,"Moses replied, вАЬЋєHe isЋЇ the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, if only you had sure faith.вАЭ"
  26,25,"Pharaoh said to those around him, вАЬDid you hear Ћєwhat he saidЋЇ?вАЭ"
  26,26,"Moses added, вАЬЋєHe isЋЇ your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers.вАЭ"
  26,27,"Pharaoh said ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬYour messenger, who has been sent to you, must be insane.вАЭ"
  26,28,"Moses responded: вАЬЋєHe isЋЇ the Lord of the east and west, and everything in between, if only you had any sense.вАЭ"
  26,29,"Pharaoh threatened, вАЬIf you take any other god besides me, I will certainly have you imprisoned.вАЭ"
  26,30,"Moses responded, вАЬEven if I bring you a clear proof?вАЭ"
  26,31,"Pharaoh demanded, вАЬBring it then, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  26,32,So he threw down his staff andвАФbehold!вАФit became a real snake
  26,33,Then he drew his hand Ћєout of his collarЋЇ and it was ЋєshiningЋЇ white for all to see
  26,34,"Pharaoh said to the chiefs around him, вАЬHe is indeed a skilled magician"
  26,35,who seeks to drive you from your land by his magic. So what do you propose?вАЭ
  26,36,"They replied, вАЬLet him and his brother wait and dispatch mobilizers to all cities"
  26,37,to bring you every skilled magician.вАЭ
  26,38,So the magicians were assembled at the set time on the appointed day
  26,39,"And the people were asked, вАЬWill you join the gathering"
  26,40,so that we may follow the magicians if they prevail?вАЭ
  26,41,"When the magicians came, they asked Pharaoh, вАЬShall we have a ЋєsuitableЋЇ reward if we prevail?вАЭ"
  26,42,"He replied, вАЬYes, and you will then certainly be among those closest to me.вАЭ"
  26,43,"Moses said to them, вАЬCast whatever you wish to cast.вАЭ"
  26,44,"So they cast down their ropes and staffs, saying, вАЬBy PharaohвАЩs might, it is we who will surely prevail.вАЭ"
  26,45,"Then Moses threw down his staff, andвАФbehold!вАФit devoured the objects of their illusion"
  26,46,"So the magicians fell down, prostrating"
  26,47,"They declared, вАЬWe ЋєnowЋЇ believe in the Lord of all worldsвАФ"
  26,48,the Lord of Moses and Aaron.вАЭ
  26,49,"Pharaoh threatened, вАЬHow dare you believe in him before I give you permission? He must be your master who taught you magic, but soon you will see. I will certainly cut off your hands and feet on opposite sides, then crucify you all.вАЭ"
  26,50,"They responded, вАЬЋєThat would beЋЇ no harm! Surely to our Lord we will ЋєallЋЇ return"
  26,51,"We really hope that our Lord will forgive our sins, as we are the first to believe.вАЭ"
  26,52,"And We inspired Moses, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬLeave with My servants at night, for you will surely be pursued.вАЭ"
  26,53,Then Pharaoh sent mobilizers to all cities
  26,54,"Ћєand said,ЋЇ вАЬThese ЋєoutcastsЋЇ are just a handful of people"
  26,55,who have really enraged us
  26,56,but we are all on the alert.вАЭ
  26,57,"So We lured the tyrants¬†out of ЋєtheirЋЇ gardens, springs"
  26,58,"treasures, and splendid residences"
  26,59,So it was. And We awarded it ЋєallЋЇ to the Children of Israel
  26,60,And so they pursued them at sunrise
  26,61,"When the two groups came face to face, the companions of Moses cried out, вАЬWe are overtaken for sure.вАЭ"
  26,62,"Moses reassured ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬAbsolutely not! My Lord is certainly with meвАФHe will guide me.вАЭ"
  26,63,"So We inspired Moses: вАЬStrike the sea with your staff,вАЭ and the sea was split, each part was like a huge mountain"
  26,64,We drew the pursuers to that place
  26,65,and delivered Moses and those with him all together
  26,66,Then We drowned the others
  26,67,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,68,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,69,Relate to them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the story of Abraham
  26,70,"when he questioned his father and his people, вАЬWhat is that you worship Ћєbesides AllahЋЇ?вАЭ"
  26,71,"They replied, вАЬWe worship idols, to which we are fully devoted.вАЭ"
  26,72,"Abraham asked, вАЬCan they hear you when you call upon them"
  26,73,Or can they benefit or harm you?вАЭ
  26,74,"They replied, вАЬNo! But we found our forefathers doing the same.вАЭ"
  26,75,"Abraham responded, вАЬHave you ЋєreallyЋЇ considered what you have been worshippingвАФ"
  26,76,you and your ancestors
  26,77,"They are ЋєallЋЇ enemies to me, except the Lord of all worlds"
  26,78,"ЋєHe isЋЇ the One Who created me, and He ЋєaloneЋЇ guides me"
  26,79,ЋєHe isЋЇ the One Who provides me with food and drink
  26,80,And He ЋєaloneЋЇ heals me when I am sick
  26,81,"And He Ћєis the One WhoЋЇ will cause me to die, and then bring me back to life"
  26,82,"And He is Ћєthe OneЋЇ Who, I hope, will forgive my flaws¬†on Judgment Day.вАЭ"
  26,83,"вАЬMy Lord! Grant me wisdom, and join me with the righteous"
  26,84,Bless me with honourable mention among later generations
  26,85,Make me one of those awarded the Garden of Bliss
  26,86,"Forgive my father, for he is certainly one of the misguided"
  26,87,And do not disgrace me on the Day all will be resurrectedвАФ
  26,88,the Day when neither wealth nor children will be of any benefit
  26,89,Only those who come before Allah with a pure heart Ћєwill be savedЋЇ.вАЭ
  26,90,ЋєOn that DayЋЇ Paradise will be brought near to the God-fearing
  26,91,and the Hellfire will be displayed to the deviant
  26,92,"And it will be said to them, вАЬWhere are those you used to worship"
  26,93,besides Allah? Can they help you or even help themselves?вАЭ
  26,94,"Then the idols will be hurled headlong into Hell, along with the deviant"
  26,95,"and the soldiers of Ibl√Ѓs,¬†all together"
  26,96,There the deviant will cry while disputing with their idols
  26,97,вАЬBy Allah! We were clearly mistaken
  26,98,when we made you equal to the Lord of all worlds
  26,99,And none led us astray other than the wicked
  26,100,Now we have none to intercede for us
  26,101,nor a close friend
  26,102,"If only we could have a second chance, then we would be believers.вАЭ"
  26,103,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,104,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,105,The people of Noah rejected the messengers
  26,106,"when their brother Noah said to them, вАЬWill you not fear ЋєAllahЋЇ"
  26,107,I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,108,"So fear Allah, and obey me"
  26,109,I do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇ. My reward is only from the Lord of all worlds
  26,110,"So fear Allah, and obey me.вАЭ"
  26,111,"They argued, вАЬHow can we believe in you, when you are followed ЋєonlyЋЇ by the lowest of the low?вАЭ"
  26,112,"He responded, вАЬAnd what knowledge do I have of what they do"
  26,113,"Their judgment is with my Lord, if you had any sense"
  26,114,I am not going to expel the believers
  26,115,I am only sent with a clear warning.вАЭ
  26,116,"They threatened, вАЬIf you do not desist, O Noah, you will surely be stoned Ћєto deathЋЇ.вАЭ"
  26,117,"Noah prayed, вАЬMy Lord! My people have truly rejected me"
  26,118,"So judge between me and them decisively, and save me and the believers with me.вАЭ"
  26,119,So We saved him and those with him in the fully loaded Ark
  26,120,Then afterwards We drowned the rest
  26,121,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,122,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,123,The people of вАЩ√Вd rejected the messengers
  26,124,"when their brother H√їd said to them, вАЬWill you not fear ЋєAllahЋЇ"
  26,125,I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,126,"So fear Allah, and obey me"
  26,127,I do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇ. My reward is only from the Lord of all worlds
  26,128,ЋєWhyЋЇ do you build a landmark on every high place in vanity
  26,129,"and construct castles, as if you are going to live forever"
  26,130,and act so viciously when you attack ЋєothersЋЇ
  26,131,"So fear Allah, and obey me"
  26,132,Fear the One Who has provided you with Ћєthe goodЋЇ things you know
  26,133,"He provided you with cattle, and children"
  26,134,"and gardens, and springs"
  26,135,I truly fear for you the torment of a tremendous day.вАЭ
  26,136,"They responded, вАЬIt is all the same to us whether you warn ЋєusЋЇ or not"
  26,137,This is simply the tradition of our predecessors
  26,138,And we will never be punished.вАЭ
  26,139,"So they rejected him, and ЋєsoЋЇ We destroyed them. Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe"
  26,140,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,141,The people of Tham√їd rejected the messengers
  26,142,"when their brother бєҐ√ҐliбЄ• said to them, вАЬWill you not fear ЋєAllahЋЇ"
  26,143,I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,144,"So fear Allah, and obey me"
  26,145,I do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇ. My reward is only from the Lord of all worlds
  26,146,Do you think you will be ЋєforeverЋЇ left secure in what you have here
  26,147,amid gardens and springs
  26,148,"and ЋєvariousЋЇ crops, and palm trees ЋєloadedЋЇ with tender fruit"
  26,149,to carve homes in the mountains with great skill
  26,150,"So fear Allah, and obey me"
  26,151,And do not follow the command of the transgressors
  26,152,"who spread corruption throughout the land, never setting things right.вАЭ"
  26,153,"They replied, вАЬYou are simply bewitched"
  26,154,"You are only a human being like us, so bring forth a sign if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  26,155,"бєҐ√ҐliбЄ• said, вАЬHere is a camel. She will have her turn to drink as you have yours, each on an appointed day"
  26,156,"And do not ever touch her with harm, or you will be overtaken by the torment of a tremendous day.вАЭ"
  26,157,"But they killed her, becoming regretful"
  26,158,So the punishment overtook them. Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,159,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,160,The people of Lot rejected the messengers
  26,161,"when their brother Lot said to them, вАЬWill you not fear ЋєAllahЋЇ"
  26,162,I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,163,"So fear Allah, and obey me"
  26,164,I do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇ. My reward is only from the Lord of all worlds
  26,165,Why do you ЋєmenЋЇ lust after fellow men
  26,166,"leaving the wives that your Lord has created for you? In fact, you are a transgressing people.вАЭ"
  26,167,"They threatened, вАЬIf you do not desist, O Lot, you will surely be expelled.вАЭ"
  26,168,"Lot responded, вАЬI am truly one of those who despise your ЋєshamefulЋЇ practice"
  26,169,My Lord! Save me and my family from Ћєthe consequences ofЋЇ what they do.вАЭ
  26,170,So We saved him and all of his family
  26,171,"except an old woman,¬†who was one of the doomed"
  26,172,Then We utterly destroyed the rest
  26,173,pouring upon them a rain Ћєof brimstoneЋЇ. How evil was the rain of those who had been warned
  26,174,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,175,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,176,The residents of the Forest rejected the messengers
  26,177,"when ShuвАЩaib said to them,¬†вАЬWill you not fear ЋєAllahЋЇ"
  26,178,I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,179,"So fear Allah, and obey me"
  26,180,I do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇ. My reward is only from the Lord of all worlds
  26,181,"Give full measure, and cause no loss Ћєto othersЋЇ"
  26,182,Weigh with an even balance
  26,183,and do not defraud people of their property. Nor go about spreading corruption in the land
  26,184,And fear the One Who created you and ЋєallЋЇ earlier peoples.вАЭ
  26,185,"They replied, вАЬYou are simply bewitched"
  26,186,"Also, you are only a human being like us, and we think you are indeed a liar"
  26,187,"So cause ЋєdeadlyЋЇ pieces of the sky to fall upon us, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  26,188,"ShuвАЩaib responded, вАЬMy Lord knows best whatever you do.вАЭ"
  26,189,"So they rejected him, and ЋєsoЋЇ were overtaken by the torment of the day of the ЋєdeadlyЋЇ cloud.¬†That was really a torment of a tremendous day"
  26,190,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,191,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,192,This is certainly a revelation from the Lord of all worlds
  26,193,which the trustworthy spirit ЋєGabrielЋЇ brought down
  26,194,into your heart ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФso that you may be one of the warnersвАФ
  26,195,in a clear Arabic tongue
  26,196,And it has indeed been ЋєforetoldЋЇ in the Scriptures of those before
  26,197,Was it not sufficient proof for the deniers that it has been recognized by the knowledgeable among the Children of Israel
  26,198,Had We revealed it to a non-Arab
  26,199,"who would then recite it to the deniers Ћєin fluent ArabicЋЇ, still they would not have believed in it"
  26,200,This is how We allow denial Ћєto steepЋЇ into the hearts of the wicked
  26,201,They will not believe in it until they see the painful punishment
  26,202,which will take them by surprise when they least expect ЋєitЋЇ
  26,203,"Then they will cry, вАЬCan we be allowed more time?вАЭ"
  26,204,Do they ЋєreallyЋЇ seek to hasten Our torment
  26,205,Imagine ЋєO ProphetЋЇ if We allowed them enjoyment for years
  26,206,then there came to them what they had been threatened with
  26,207,would that enjoyment be of any benefit to them Ћєat allЋЇ
  26,208,We have never destroyed a society without warners
  26,209,"to remind ЋєthemЋЇ, for We would never wrong ЋєanyoneЋЇ"
  26,210,It was not the devils who brought this ЋєQuranЋЇ down
  26,211,"it is not for them Ћєto do soЋЇ, nor can they"
  26,212,for they are strictly barred from ЋєevenЋЇ overhearing ЋєitЋЇ
  26,213,"So do not ever call upon any other god besides Allah, or you will be one of the punished"
  26,214,"And warn Ћєall, starting withЋЇ your closest relatives"
  26,215,and be gracious to the believers who follow you
  26,216,"But if they disobey you, say, вАЬI am certainly free of what you do.вАЭ"
  26,217,"Put your trust in the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,218,Who sees you when you rise Ћєfor prayer at nightЋЇ
  26,219,as well as your movements Ћєin prayerЋЇ along with ЋєfellowЋЇ worshippers
  26,220,"He ЋєaloneЋЇ is indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  26,221,Shall I inform you of whom the devils ЋєactuallyЋЇ descend upon
  26,222,They descend upon every sinful liar
  26,223,"who gives an ЋєattentiveЋЇ ear Ћєto half-truthsЋЇ, mostly passing on sheer lies"
  26,224,"As for poets, they are followed ЋєmerelyЋЇ by deviants"
  26,225,Do you not see how they rant in every field
  26,226,only saying what they never do
  26,227,"Except those who believe, do good, remember Allah often, and ЋєpoeticallyЋЇ avenge Ћєthe believersЋЇ after being wrongfully slandered. The wrongdoers will come to know what ЋєevilЋЇ end they will meet"
  27,1,бєђ√Ґ-Sƒ©n. These are the verses of the Quran; the clear Book
  27,2,ЋєIt isЋЇ a guide and good news for the believers
  27,3,"ЋєthoseЋЇ who establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  27,4,"As for those who do not believe in the Hereafter, We have certainly made their ЋєevilЋЇ deeds appealing to them, so they wander blindly"
  27,5,"It is they who will suffer a dreadful torment, and in the Hereafter they will ЋєtrulyЋЇ be the greatest losers"
  27,6,"And indeed, you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are receiving the Quran from the One ЋєWho isЋЇ All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  27,7,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when Moses said to his family, вАЬI have spotted a fire. I will either bring you some directions¬†from there, or a burning torch so you may warm yourselves.вАЭ"
  27,8,"But when he came to it, he was called Ћєby AllahЋЇ, вАЬBlessed is the one at the fire, and whoever is around it!¬†Glory be to Allah, the Lord of all worlds"
  27,9,"O Moses! It is truly I. I am AllahвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  27,10,"Now, throw down your staff!вАЭ But when he saw it slithering like a snake, he ran away without looking back. ЋєAllah reassured him,ЋЇ вАЬO Moses! Do not be afraid! Messengers should have no fear in My presence"
  27,11,"ЋєFear isЋЇ only for those who do wrong. But if they later mend ЋєtheirЋЇ evil ЋєwaysЋЇ with good, then I am certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  27,12,"Now put your hand through Ћєthe opening ofЋЇ your collar, it will come out ЋєshiningЋЇ white, unblemished.¬†ЋєThese are twoЋЇ of nine signs for Pharaoh and his people.¬†They have truly been a rebellious people.вАЭ"
  27,13,"But when Our enlightening signs came to them, they said, вАЬThis is pure magic.вАЭ"
  27,14,"And, although their hearts were convinced the signs were true, they still denied them wrongfully and arrogantly. See then what was the end of the corruptors"
  27,15,"Indeed, We granted knowledge to David and Solomon. And they said Ћєin acknowledgmentЋЇ, вАЬAll praise is for Allah Who has privileged us over many of His faithful servants.вАЭ"
  27,16,"And David was succeeded by Solomon, who said, вАЬO people! We have been taught the language of birds, and been given everything Ћєwe needЋЇ. This is indeed a great privilege.вАЭ"
  27,17,"SolomonвАЩs forces of jinn, humans, and birds were rallied for him, perfectly organized"
  27,18,"And when they came across a valley of ants, an ant warned, вАЬO ants! Go quickly into your homes so Solomon and his armies do not crush you, unknowingly.вАЭ"
  27,19,"So Solomon smiled in amusement at her words, and prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Inspire me to ЋєalwaysЋЇ be thankful for Your favours which You have blessed me and my parents with, and to do good deeds that please you. Admit me, by Your mercy, into Ћєthe company ofЋЇ Your righteous servants.вАЭ"
  27,20,"ЋєOne dayЋЇ he inspected the birds, and wondered, вАЬWhy is it that I cannot see the hoopoe? Or could he be absent"
  27,21,"I will surely subject him to a severe punishment, or ЋєevenЋЇ slaughter him, unless he brings me a compelling excuse.вАЭ"
  27,22,"It was not long before the bird came and said, вАЬI have found out something you do not know. I have just come to you from Sheba with sure news"
  27,23,"Indeed, I found a woman ruling over them,¬†who has been given everything Ћєshe needsЋЇ, and who has a magnificent throne"
  27,24,I found her and her people prostrating to the sun instead of Allah. For Satan has made their deeds appealing to themвАФhindering them from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way and leaving them unguidedвАФ
  27,25,"so they do not prostrate to Allah, Who brings forth what is hidden in the heavens and the earth, and knows what you ЋєallЋЇ conceal and what you reveal"
  27,26,"ЋєHe isЋЇ Allah! There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him, the Lord of the Mighty Throne.вАЭ"
  27,27,"Solomon said, вАЬWe will see whether you are telling the truth or lying"
  27,28,"Go with this letter of mine and deliver it to them, then stand aside and see how they will respond.вАЭ"
  27,29,"The Queen ЋєlaterЋЇ announced, вАЬO chiefs! Indeed, a noble letter has been delivered to me"
  27,30,"It is from Solomon, and it reads: вАШIn the Name of AllahвАФthe Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  27,31,"Do not be arrogant with me, but come to me, fully submitting Ћєto AllahЋЇ.вАЩвАЭ"
  27,32,"She said, вАЬO chiefs! Advise me in this matter of mine, for I would never make any decision without you.вАЭ"
  27,33,"They responded, вАЬWe are a people of strength and great ЋєmilitaryЋЇ might, but the decision is yours, so decide what you will command.вАЭ"
  27,34,"She reasoned, вАЬIndeed, when kings invade a land, they ruin it and debase its nobles. They really do so"
  27,35,"But I will certainly send him a gift, and see what ЋєresponseЋЇ my envoys will return with.вАЭ"
  27,36,"When the chief-envoy came to him, Solomon said, вАЬDo you offer me wealth? What Allah has granted me is far greater than what He has granted you. No! It is you who rejoice in ЋєreceivingЋЇ gifts"
  27,37,"Go back to them, for we will certainly mobilize against them forces which they can never resist, and we will drive them out from there in disgrace, fully humbled.вАЭ"
  27,38,"Solomon asked, вАЬO chiefs! Which of you can bring me her throne before they come to me in ЋєfullЋЇ submission?вАЭ"
  27,39,"One mighty jinn responded, вАЬI can bring it to you before you rise from this council of yours. And I am quite strong and trustworthy for this ЋєtaskЋЇ.вАЭ"
  27,40,"But the one who had knowledge of the Scripture said,¬†вАЬI can bring it to you in the blink of an eye.вАЭ So when Solomon saw it placed before him, he exclaimed, вАЬThis is by the grace of my Lord to test me whether I am grateful or ungrateful. And whoever is grateful, it is only for their own good. But whoever is ungrateful, surely my Lord is Self-Sufficient, Most Generous.вАЭ"
  27,41,"ЋєThenЋЇ Solomon said, вАЬDisguise her throne for her so we may see whether she will recognize ЋєitЋЇ or she will not be able to.вАЭ"
  27,42,"So when she arrived, it was said Ћєto herЋЇ, вАЬIs your throne like this?вАЭ She replied, вАЬIt looks to be the same. We have ЋєalreadyЋЇ received knowledge Ћєof SolomonвАЩs prophethoodЋЇ¬†before this ЋєmiracleЋЇ,¬†and have submitted Ћєto AllahЋЇ.вАЭ"
  27,43,"But she had been hindered by what she used to worship instead of Allah, for she was indeed from a disbelieving people"
  27,44,"Then she was told, вАЬEnter the palace.вАЭ But when she saw the hall, she thought it was a body of water, so she bared her legs. Solomon said. вАЬIt is just a palace paved with crystal.вАЭ ЋєAt lastЋЇ she declared, вАЬMy Lord! I have certainly wronged my soul. Now I ЋєfullyЋЇ submit myself along with Solomon to Allah, the Lord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  27,45,"And We certainly sent to the people of Tham√їd their brother бєҐ√ҐliбЄ•, proclaiming, вАЬWorship Allah,вАЭ but they suddenly split into two opposing groups"
  27,46,"He urged Ћєthe disbelieving groupЋЇ, вАЬO my people! Why do you Ћєseek toЋЇ hasten the torment¬†rather than grace?¬†If only you sought AllahвАЩs forgiveness so you may be shown mercy!вАЭ"
  27,47,"They replied, вАЬYou and your followers are a bad omen for us.вАЭ¬†He responded, вАЬYour omens are destined by Allah. In fact, you are ЋєonlyЋЇ a people being tested.вАЭ"
  27,48,"And there were in the city nine ЋєeliteЋЇ men who spread corruption in the land, never doing what is right"
  27,49,"They vowed, вАЬLet us swear by Allah that we will take him and his family down by night. Then we will certainly say to his ЋєclosestЋЇ heirs, вАШWe did not witness the murder of his family. We are definitely telling the truth.вАЩвАЭ"
  27,50,"And ЋєsoЋЇ they made a plan, but We too made a plan, while they were unaware"
  27,51,"See then what the consequences of their plan were: We ЋєutterlyЋЇ destroyed them and their people all together"
  27,52,"So their homes are there, Ћєbut completelyЋЇ ruined because of their wrongdoing. Surely in this is a lesson for people of knowledge"
  27,53,And We delivered those who were faithful and were mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ
  27,54,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ Lot, when he rebuked Ћєthe men ofЋЇ his people, вАЬDo you commit that shameful deed while you can see Ћєone anotherЋЇ"
  27,55,"Do you really lust after men instead of women? In fact, you are ЋєonlyЋЇ a people acting ignorantly.вАЭ"
  27,56,"But his peopleвАЩs only response was to say, вАЬExpel LotвАЩs followers from your land! They are a people who wish to remain chaste!вАЭ"
  27,57,"So We delivered him and his family, except his wife. We had destined her to be one of the doomed"
  27,58,And We poured upon them a rain Ћєof brimstoneЋЇ. How evil was the rain of those who had been warned
  27,59,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬPraise be to Allah, and peace be upon the servants He has chosen.вАЭ ЋєAsk the disbelievers,ЋЇ вАЬWhich is better: Allah or whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ?вАЭ"
  27,60,"Or Ћєask them,ЋЇ вАЬWho created the heavens and the earth, and sends down rain for you from the sky, by which We cause delightful gardens to grow? You could never cause their trees to grow. Was it another god besides Allah?вАЭ Absolutely not! But they are a people who set up equals Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  27,61,"Or Ћєask them,ЋЇ вАЬWho made the earth a place of settlement, caused rivers to flow through it, placed firm mountains upon it, and set a barrier between Ћєfresh and saltЋЇ bodies of water?¬†Was it another god besides Allah?вАЭ Absolutely not! But most of them do not know"
  27,62,"Or Ћєask them,ЋЇ вАЬWho responds to the distressed when they cry to Him, relieving ЋєtheirЋЇ affliction, and ЋєWhoЋЇ makes you successors in the earth? Is it another god besides Allah? Yet you are hardly mindful!вАЭ"
  27,63,"Or Ћєask them,ЋЇ вАЬWho guides you in the darkness of the land and sea,¬†and sends the winds ushering in His mercy?¬†Is it another god besides Allah? Exalted is Allah above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ"
  27,64,"Or Ћєask them,ЋЇ вАЬWho originates the creation then resurrects it, and gives you provisions from the heavens and the earth? Is it another god besides Allah?вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬShow ЋєmeЋЇ your proof, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  27,65,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬNone in the heavens and the earth has knowledge of the unseen except Allah. Nor do they know when they will be resurrected"
  27,66,"No! Their knowledge of the Hereafter amounts to ignorance. In fact, they are in doubt about it. In truth, they are ЋєtotallyЋЇ blind to it"
  27,67,"The disbelievers ask, вАЬWhen we and our fathers are reduced to dust, will we really be brought forth ЋєaliveЋЇ"
  27,68,"We have already been promised this, as well as our forefathers earlier. This is nothing but ancient fables!вАЭ"
  27,69,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬTravel throughout the land and see the fate of the wicked.вАЭ"
  27,70,"Do not grieve for them, nor be distressed by their schemes"
  27,71,"They ask Ћєthe believersЋЇ, вАЬWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  27,72,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬPerhaps some of what you seek to hasten is close at hand.вАЭ"
  27,73,"Surely your Lord is ever Bountiful to humanity,¬†but most of them are ungrateful"
  27,74,And surely your Lord knows what their hearts conceal and what they reveal
  27,75,For there is nothing hidden in the heavens or the earth without being ЋєwrittenЋЇ in a perfect Record
  27,76,"Indeed, this Quran clarifies for the Children of Israel most of what they differ over"
  27,77,And it is truly a guide and mercy for the believers
  27,78,"Your Lord will certainly judge between them by His justice, for He is the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  27,79,"So put your trust in Allah, for you are surely upon the ЋєPath ofЋЇ clear truth"
  27,80,You certainly cannot make the dead hear Ћєthe truthЋЇ. Nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and walk away
  27,81,"Nor can you lead the blind out of their misguidance. You can make none hear Ћєthe truthЋЇ except those who believe in Our revelations, ЋєfullyЋЇ submitting Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  27,82,"And when the decree Ћєof the HourЋЇ comes to pass against them, We will bring forth for them a beast from the earth,¬†telling them that the people had no sure faith in Our revelations"
  27,83,"ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day We will gather from every faith-community a group of those who denied Our revelations, and they will be driven in ranks"
  27,84,"When they ЋєfinallyЋЇ come before their Lord, He will ask ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬDid you deny My revelations without ЋєevenЋЇ comprehending them? Or what ЋєexactlyЋЇ did you do?вАЭ"
  27,85,"And the decree Ћєof tormentЋЇ will be justified against them for their wrongdoing, leaving them speechless"
  27,86,Do they not see that We made the night for them to rest in and the day bright?¬†Surely in this are signs for those who believe
  27,87,"And Ћєbeware ofЋЇ the Day the Trumpet will be blown, and all those in the heavens and all those on the earth will be horrified Ћєto the point of deathЋЇ,¬†except those Allah wills Ћєto spareЋЇ. And all will come before Him, fully humbled"
  27,88,"Now you see the mountains, thinking they are firmly fixed, but they are travelling ЋєjustЋЇ like clouds. ЋєThat isЋЇ the design of Allah, Who has perfected everything. Surely He is All-Aware of what you do"
  27,89,"Whoever comes with a good deed will be rewarded with what is better, and they will be secure from the horror on that Day"
  27,90,And whoever comes with an evil deed will be hurled face-first into the Fire. Are you rewarded except for what you used to do
  27,91,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI have only been commanded to worship the Lord of this city Ћєof MeccaЋЇ, Who has made it sacred, and to Him belongs everything. And I am commanded to be one of those who ЋєfullyЋЇ submit Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  27,92,"and to recite the Quran.вАЭ Then whoever chooses to be guided, it is only for their own good. But whoever chooses to stray, say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI am only a warner.вАЭ"
  27,93,"And say, вАЬAll praise is for Allah! He will show you His signs, and you will recognize them. And your Lord is never unaware of what you do.вАЭ"
  28,1,бєђ√Ґ-Sƒ©n-Mƒ©m
  28,2,These are the verses of the clear Book
  28,3,We narrate to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ part of the story of Moses and Pharaoh in truth for people who believe
  28,4,"Indeed, Pharaoh ЋєarrogantlyЋЇ elevated himself in the land and divided its people into ЋєsubservientЋЇ groups, one of which he persecuted, slaughtering their sons and keeping their women. He was truly one of the corruptors"
  28,5,"But it was Our Will to favour those who were oppressed in the land, making them models Ћєof faithЋЇ as well as successors"
  28,6,"and to establish them in the land; and through them show Pharaoh, Ham√Ґn,¬†and their soldiers Ћєthe fulfilment ofЋЇ what they feared"
  28,7,"We inspired the mother of Moses: вАЬNurse him, but when you fear for him, put him then into the river, and do not fear or grieve. We will certainly return him to you, and make him one of the messengers.вАЭ"
  28,8,"And Ћєit so happened thatЋЇ PharaohвАЩs people picked him up, only to become their enemy and source of grief. Surely Pharaoh, Ham√Ґn, and their soldiers were sinful"
  28,9,"PharaohвАЩs wife said Ћєto himЋЇ, вАЬЋєThis baby isЋЇ a source of joy for me and you. Do not kill him. Perhaps he may be useful to us or we may adopt him as a son.вАЭ They were unaware Ћєof what was to comeЋЇ"
  28,10,"And the heart of MosesвАЩ mother ached so much that she almost gave away his identity, had We not reassured her heart in order for her to have faith Ћєin AllahвАЩs promiseЋЇ"
  28,11,"And she said to his sister, вАЬKeep track of him!вАЭ So she watched him from a distance, while they were unaware"
  28,12,"And We had caused him to refuse all wet-nurses at first, so his sister suggested, вАЬShall I direct you to a family who will bring him up for you and take good care of him?вАЭ"
  28,13,"This is how We returned him to his mother so that her heart would be put at ease, and not grieve, and that she would know that AllahвАЩs promise is ЋєalwaysЋЇ true. But most people do not know"
  28,14,"And when he reached full strength and maturity, We gave him wisdom and knowledge. This is how We reward the good-doers"
  28,15,"ЋєOne dayЋЇ he entered the city unnoticed by its people.¬†There he found two men fighting: one of his own people, and the other of his enemies. The man from his people called to him for help against his foe. So Moses punched him, causing his death. Moses cried, вАЬThis is from SatanвАЩs handiwork. He is certainly a sworn, misleading enemy.вАЭ"
  28,16,"He pleaded, вАЬMy Lord! I have definitely wronged my soul, so forgive me.вАЭ So He forgave him, ЋєforЋЇ He is indeed the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  28,17,"Moses pledged, вАЬMy Lord! For all Your favours upon me, I will never side with the wicked.вАЭ"
  28,18,"And so Moses became fearful, watching out in the city, when suddenly the one who sought his help the day before cried out to him again for help. Moses rebuked him, вАЬIndeed, you are clearly a trouble-maker.вАЭ"
  28,19,"Then when Moses was about to lay his hands on their foe,¬†the enemy said, вАЬO Moses! Do you intend to kill me as you killed a man yesterday? You only want to be a tyrant in the land. You do not intend to make peace!вАЭ"
  28,20,"And there came a man, rushing from the farthest end of the city. He said, вАЬO Moses! The chiefs are actually conspiring against you to put you to death, so leave Ћєthe cityЋЇ. I really advise you Ћєto do soЋЇ.вАЭ"
  28,21,"So Moses left the city in a state of fear and caution, praying, вАЬMy Lord! Deliver me from the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  28,22,"And as he made his way towards Midian, he said, вАЬI trust my Lord will guide me to the right way.вАЭ"
  28,23,"When he arrived at the well of Midian, he found a group of people watering Ћєtheir herdsЋЇ. Apart from them, he noticed two women holding back Ћєtheir herdЋЇ. He asked ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬWhat is the problem?вАЭ They replied, вАЬWe cannot water Ћєour animalsЋЇ until the ЋєotherЋЇ shepherds are done, for our father is a very old man.вАЭ"
  28,24,"So he watered Ћєtheir herdЋЇ for them, then withdrew to the shade and prayed, вАЬMy Lord! I am truly in ЋєdesperateЋЇ need of whatever provision You may have in store for me.вАЭ"
  28,25,"Then one of the two women came to him, walking bashfully. She said, вАЬMy father is inviting you so he may reward you for watering Ћєour animalsЋЇ for us.вАЭ When Moses came to him and told him his whole story, the old man said, вАЬHave no fear! You are ЋєnowЋЇ safe from the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  28,26,"One of the two daughters suggested, вАЬO my dear father! Hire him. The best man for employment is definitely the strong and trustworthy ЋєoneЋЇ.вАЭ"
  28,27,"The old man proposed, вАЬI wish to marry one of these two daughters of mine to you, provided that you stay in my service for eight years. If you complete ten, it will be Ћєa favourЋЇ from you, but I do not wish to make it difficult for you. Allah willing, you will find me an agreeable man.вАЭ"
  28,28,"Moses responded, вАЬЋєThenЋЇ it is ЋєsettledЋЇ between you and I. Whichever term I fulfill, there will be no ЋєfurtherЋЇ obligation on me. And Allah is a Witness to what we say.вАЭ"
  28,29,"When Moses had completed the term and was travelling with his family, he spotted a fire on the side of Mount бєђ√їr. He said to his family, вАЬStay here, ЋєforЋЇ I have spotted a fire. Perhaps from there I can bring you some directions¬†or a torch from the fire so you may warm yourselves.вАЭ"
  28,30,"But when he came to it, he was called from the bush in the sacred ground to the right side of the valley: вАЬO Moses! It is truly I. I am AllahвАФthe Lord of all worlds"
  28,31,"Now, throw down your staff!вАЭ But when he saw it slithering like a snake, he ran away without looking back. ЋєAllah reassured him,ЋЇ вАЬO Moses! Draw near, and have no fear. You are perfectly secure"
  28,32,"Now put your hand through Ћєthe opening ofЋЇ your collar, it will come out ЋєshiningЋЇ white, unblemished.¬†And cross your arms tightly to calm your fears.¬†These are two proofs from your Lord to Pharaoh and his chiefs. They have truly been a rebellious people.вАЭ"
  28,33,"Moses appealed, вАЬMy Lord! I have indeed killed a man from them, so I fear they may kill me"
  28,34,"And my brother Aaron is more eloquent than I, so send him with me as a helper to support what I say, for I truly fear they may reject me.вАЭ"
  28,35,"Allah responded, вАЬWe will assist you with your brother and grant you both authority, so they cannot harm you. With Our signs, you and those who follow you will ЋєcertainlyЋЇ prevail.вАЭ"
  28,36,"But when Moses came to them with Our clear signs, they said ЋєarrogantlyЋЇ, вАЬThis is nothing but conjured magic ЋєtricksЋЇ. We have never heard of this in Ћєthe history ofЋЇ our forefathers.вАЭ"
  28,37,"Moses responded, вАЬMy Lord knows best who has come with ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance from Him and will fare best in the end. Indeed, the wrongdoers will never succeed.вАЭ"
  28,38,"Pharaoh declared, вАЬO chiefs! I know of no other god for you but myself. So bake bricks out of clay for me, O Ham√Ґn, and build a high tower so I may look at the God of Moses, although I am sure he is a liar.вАЭ"
  28,39,"And so he and his soldiers behaved arrogantly in the land with no right, thinking they would never be returned to Us"
  28,40,"So We seized him and his soldiers, casting¬†them into the sea. See then what was the end of the wrongdoers"
  28,41,We made them leaders inviting ЋєothersЋЇ to the Fire. And on the Day of Judgment they will not be helped
  28,42,We caused a curse to follow them in this world. And on the Day of Judgment they will be among the outcasts
  28,43,"Indeed, We gave Moses the ScriptureвАФafter destroying earlier nationsвАФas an insight for the people, a guide, and mercy so perhaps they would be mindful"
  28,44,"You were not there ЋєO ProphetЋЇ on the western side of the mountain when We entrusted the Commandments to Moses, nor were you present Ћєin his timeЋЇ"
  28,45,"But We ЋєlaterЋЇ raised ЋєseveralЋЇ generations, and the ages took their toll on them.¬†Nor were you living among the people of Midian, rehearsing Our revelations with them. But it is We Who have sent Ћєthis¬†revelation to youЋЇ"
  28,46,"And you were not at the side of Mount бєђ√їr when We called out Ћєto MosesЋЇ. But Ћєyou have been sentЋЇ as a mercy from your Lord to warn a people to whom no warner has come before you, so perhaps they may be mindful"
  28,47,"Also so they would not say, if struck by an affliction for what their hands have done: вАЬOur Lord! If only You had sent us a messenger, we would have followed Your revelations and become believers.вАЭ"
  28,48,"But when the truth came to them from Us, they said, вАЬIf only he was given the like of what Moses had been given.вАЭ¬†Did they not deny what had been given to Moses earlier? They claimed, вАЬBoth ЋєScripturesЋЇ are works of magic, supporting each other!вАЭ¬†Adding, вАЬWe truly deny both.вАЭ"
  28,49,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬBring then a scripture from Allah which is a better guide than these two so I may follow it, if your claim is true.вАЭ"
  28,50,"So if they fail to respond to you, then know that they only follow their desires. And who could be more astray than those who follow their desires with no guidance from Allah? Surely Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  28,51,"Indeed, We have steadily delivered the Word Ћєof AllahЋЇ to the people so they may be mindful"
  28,52,"ЋєAs forЋЇ those ЋєfaithfulЋЇ to whom We had given the Scripture before this ЋєQuranЋЇ, they do believe in it"
  28,53,"When it is recited to them, they declare, вАЬWe believe in it. This is definitely the truth from our Lord. We had already submitted¬†ЋєevenЋЇ before this.вАЭ"
  28,54,"These ЋєbelieversЋЇ will be given a double reward for their perseverance, responding to evil with good, and for donating from what We have provided for them"
  28,55,"When they hear slanderous talk, they turn away from it, saying, вАЬWe are accountable for our deeds and you for yours. Peace Ћєis our only responseЋЇ to you! We want nothing to do with those who act ignorantly.вАЭ"
  28,56,"You surely cannot guide whoever you like ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, but it is Allah Who guides whoever He wills, and He knows best who are Ћєfit to beЋЇ guided"
  28,57,"They say Ћєto the ProphetЋЇ, вАЬIf we were to follow ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance with you, we would certainly be snatched away from our land.вАЭ Have We not established for them a safe haven Ћєin MeccaЋЇ to which fruits of all kinds are brought as a provision from Us? But most of them do not know Ћєthis favourЋЇ"
  28,58,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many societies We have destroyed that had been spoiled by their ЋєcomfortableЋЇ living! Those are their residences, never inhabited after them except passingly.¬†And We ЋєaloneЋЇ were the Successor"
  28,59,"Your Lord would never destroy a society until He had sent to its capital a messenger, reciting Our revelations to them. Nor would We ever destroy a society unless its people persisted in wrongdoing"
  28,60,Whatever ЋєpleasureЋЇ you have been given is no more than Ћєa fleetingЋЇ enjoyment and adornment of this worldly life. But what is with Allah is far better and more lasting. Will you not then understand
  28,61,"Can those to whom We have made a fine promiseвАФwhich they will see fulfilledвАФbe like those who We have allowed to enjoy the pleasures of this worldly life, but on the Day of Judgment will be brought Ћєfor punishmentЋЇ"
  28,62,"ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day He will call to them, вАЬWhere are those you claimed were My associate-gods?вАЭ"
  28,63,"Those ЋєmisleadersЋЇ against whom the decree Ћєof tormentЋЇ is justified will cry, вАЬOur Lord! These ЋєfollowersЋЇ are the ones we caused to deviate. We led them into deviance, for we ourselves were deviant. We disassociate ourselves Ћєfrom themЋЇ before You. It was not us that they used to worship.вАЭ"
  28,64,"It will be said Ћєto the disbelieversЋЇ, вАЬCall upon your associate-gods Ћєfor helpЋЇ.вАЭ So they will call them, but will receive no response. And they will face the punishment, wishing they had been ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  28,65,"And Ћєwatch forЋЇ the Day He will call to them, asking, вАЬWhat response did you give to the messengers?вАЭ"
  28,66,They will be too dumbstruck on that Day to ask one another Ћєfor answersЋЇ
  28,67,"As for those who repent, believe, and do good Ћєin this worldЋЇ, it is right to hope that they will be among the successful"
  28,68,Your Lord creates and chooses whatever He willsвАФthe choice is not theirs. Glorified and Exalted is Allah above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ
  28,69,And your Lord knows what their hearts conceal and what they reveal
  28,70,He is Allah. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. All praise belongs to Him in this life and the next. All authority is His. And to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned
  28,71,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬImagine if Allah were to make the night perpetual for you until the Day of Judgment, which god other than Allah could bring you sunlight? Will you not then listen?вАЭ"
  28,72,"Ask Ћєthem alsoЋЇ, вАЬImagine if Allah were to make the day perpetual for you until the Day of Judgment, which god other than Allah could bring you night to rest in? Will you not then see?вАЭ"
  28,73,"It is out of His mercy that He has made for you the day and night so that you may rest Ћєin the latterЋЇ and seek His bounty Ћєin the formerЋЇ, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  28,74,"And Ћєwatch forЋЇ the Day He will call to them, вАЬWhere are those you claimed were My associate-gods?вАЭ"
  28,75,"And We will bring forth a witness¬†from every faith-community and ask Ћєthe polytheistsЋЇ, вАЬShow ЋєUsЋЇ your proof.вАЭ Then they will Ћєcome toЋЇ know that the truth is with Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ. And whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ they fabricated will fail them"
  28,76,"Indeed, Korah¬†was from the people of Moses, but he behaved arrogantly towards them. We had granted him such treasures that even their keys would burden a group of strong men. ЋєSome ofЋЇ his people advised him, вАЬDo not be prideful! Surely Allah does not like the prideful"
  28,77,"Rather, seek the ЋєrewardЋЇ of the Hereafter by means of what Allah has granted you, without forgetting your share of this world. And be good Ћєto othersЋЇ as Allah has been good to you. Do not seek to spread corruption in the land, for Allah certainly does not like the corruptors.вАЭ"
  28,78,"He replied, вАЬI have been granted all this because of some knowledge I have.вАЭ¬†Did he not know that Allah had already destroyed some from the generations before him who were far superior to him in power and greater in accumulating ЋєwealthЋЇ? There will be no need for the wicked to be asked about their sins"
  28,79,"Then he came out before his people in all his glamour. Those who desired the life of this world wished, вАЬIf only we could have something like what Korah has been given. He is truly a man of great fortune!вАЭ"
  28,80,"But those gifted with knowledge said, вАЬShame on you! AllahвАЩs reward is far better for those who believe and do good. But none will attain this except the steadfast.вАЭ"
  28,81,"Then We caused the earth to swallow him up, along with his home. There was no one to help him against Allah, nor could he even help himself"
  28,82,"And those who had craved his position the previous day began to say, вАЬAh! It is certainly Allah Who gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. Had it not been for the grace of Allah, He could have surely caused the earth to swallow us up! Oh, indeed! The disbelievers will never succeed.вАЭ"
  28,83,That ЋєeternalЋЇ Home in the Hereafter We reserve ЋєonlyЋЇ for those who seek neither tyranny nor corruption on the earth. The ultimate outcome belongs ЋєonlyЋЇ to the righteous
  28,84,"Whoever comes with a good deed will be rewarded with what is better. And whoever comes with an evil deed, then the evildoers will only be rewarded for what they used to do"
  28,85,"Most certainly, the One Who has ordained the Quran for you will ЋєultimatelyЋЇ bring you back home Ћєto MeccaЋЇ.¬†Say, вАЬMy Lord knows best who has come with ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance and who is clearly astray.вАЭ"
  28,86,"You never expected this Book to be revealed to you, but Ћєit cameЋЇ only ЋєasЋЇ a mercy from your Lord. So never side with the disbelievers Ћєin their disbeliefЋЇ"
  28,87,"Do not let them turn you away from the revelations of Allah after they have been sent down to you. Rather, invite ЋєallЋЇ to Ћєthe Way ofЋЇ your Lord, and never be one of the polytheists"
  28,88,And do not invoke any other god with Allah. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. Everything is bound to perish except He Himself.¬†All authority belongs to Him. And to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned
  29,1,Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m
  29,2,"Do people think once they say, вАЬWe believe,вАЭ that they will be left without being put to the test"
  29,3,We certainly tested those before them. And Ћєin this wayЋЇ Allah will clearly distinguish between those who are truthful and those who are liars
  29,4,Or do the evildoers ЋєsimplyЋЇ think that they will escape Us? How wrong is their judgment
  29,5,"Whoever hopes for the meeting with Allah, Ћєlet them know thatЋЇ AllahвАЩs appointed time is sure to come. He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  29,6,"And whoever strives Ћєin AllahвАЩs causeЋЇ, only does so for their own good. Surely Allah is not in need of Ћєany ofЋЇ His creation"
  29,7,"As for those who believe and do good, We will certainly absolve them of their sins, and reward them according to the best of what they used to do"
  29,8,"We have commanded people to honour their parents. But if they urge you to associate with Me what you have no knowledge of,¬†then do not obey them. To Me you will ЋєallЋЇ return, and then I will inform you of what you used to do"
  29,9,Those who believe and do good will surely be admitted by Us into Ћєthe company ofЋЇ the righteous
  29,10,"There are some who say, вАЬWe believe in Allah,вАЭ but when they suffer in the cause of Allah, they mistake ЋєthisЋЇ persecution at the hands of people for the punishment of Allah. But when victory comes from your Lord, they surely say Ћєto the believersЋЇ, вАЬWe have always been with you.вАЭ Does Allah not know best what is in the hearts of all beings"
  29,11,Allah will certainly distinguish between those who have ЋєsureЋЇ faith and the hypocrites
  29,12,"The disbelievers say to the believers, вАЬЋєJustЋЇ follow our way, and we will bear Ћєthe burden ofЋЇ your sins.вАЭ But they would never Ћєwant toЋЇ bear any of the believersвАЩ sins. They are simply lying"
  29,13,"Yet they will certainly Ћєbe made toЋЇ carry their own burdens, as well as other burdens along with their own.¬†And they will surely be questioned on Judgment Day about what they used to fabricate"
  29,14,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people, and he remained among them for a thousand years, less fifty. Then the Flood overtook them, while they persisted in wrongdoing"
  29,15,"But We delivered him and those in the Ark, making it a sign for all people"
  29,16,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Abraham said to his people, вАЬWorship Allah, and fear Him. This is better for you, if only you knew"
  29,17,"You worship besides Allah nothing but idols, simply creating lies Ћєabout themЋЇ. Those you worship besides Allah certainly cannot give you any provision. So seek provision from Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ, worship Him, and be grateful to Him. To Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  29,18,"If you ЋєMeccansЋЇ persist in denial, so did ЋєmanyЋЇ communities before you. The MessengerвАЩs duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ clearly.вАЭ"
  29,19,Have they not seen how Allah originates the creation then resurrects it? That is certainly easy for Allah
  29,20,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬTravel throughout the land and see how He originated the creation, then Allah will bring it into being one more time. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  29,21,"He punishes whoever He wills, and shows mercy to whoever He wills. And you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned to Him"
  29,22,And you cannot escape Him on earth or in heaven. Nor have you any protector or helper besides Allah.вАЭ
  29,23,"As for those who disbelieve in AllahвАЩs signs and the meeting with Him, it is they who will have no hope in His mercy.¬†And it is they who will suffer a painful punishment"
  29,24,"But the only response of AbrahamвАЩs people was to say: вАЬKill him or burn him!вАЭ But Allah saved him from the fire.¬†Surely in this are signs for people who believe"
  29,25,"He said Ћєto his peopleЋЇ, вАЬYou have taken idols Ћєfor worshipЋЇ instead of Allah, only to keep Ћєthe bond ofЋЇ harmony among yourselves in this worldly life. But on the Day of Judgment you will disown and curse one another. Your home will be the Fire, and you will have no helper!вАЭ"
  29,26,"So Lot believed in him. And Abraham said, вАЬI am emigrating Ћєin obedienceЋЇ to my Lord. He ЋєaloneЋЇ is indeed the Almighty, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  29,27,"We blessed him with Isaac and ЋєlaterЋЇ Jacob, and reserved prophethood and revelation for his descendants. We gave him his reward in this life,¬†and in the Hereafter he will certainly be among the righteous"
  29,28,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Lot rebuked Ћєthe men ofЋЇ his people: вАЬYou certainly commit a shameful deed that no man has ever done before you"
  29,29,"Do you really lust after ЋєotherЋЇ men, abuse the travellers, and practice immorality ЋєopenlyЋЇ in your gatherings?вАЭ His peopleвАЩs only response was to say ЋєmockinglyЋЇ: вАЬBring AllahвАЩs punishment upon us, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  29,30,"Lot prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Help me against the people of corruption.вАЭ"
  29,31,"When Our messenger-angels came to Abraham with the good news Ћєof the birth of IsaacЋЇ, they said, вАЬWe are going to destroy the people of this city Ћєof SodomЋЇ, for its people have persisted in wrongdoing.вАЭ"
  29,32,"He said, вАЬBut Lot is there!вАЭ They responded, вАЬWe know best who is there. We will certainly save him and his familyвАФexcept his wife, who is one of the doomed.вАЭ"
  29,33,"And when Our messenger-angels came to Lot, he was distressed and worried by their arrival.¬†They reassured ЋєhimЋЇ, вАЬDo not fear, nor grieve. We will surely deliver you and your familyвАФexcept your wife, who is one of the doomed"
  29,34,We are certainly bringing down a punishment from heaven upon the people of this city for their rebelliousness.вАЭ
  29,35,And We did leave Ћєsome ofЋЇ its ruins as a clear lesson for people of understanding
  29,36,"And to the people of Midian ЋєWe sentЋЇ their brother ShuвАЩaib. He said, вАЬO my people! Worship Allah, and hope for Ћєthe reward ofЋЇ the Last Day. And do not go about spreading corruption in the land.вАЭ"
  29,37,"But they rejected him, so an ЋєoverwhelmingЋЇ earthquake struck them and they fell lifeless in their homes"
  29,38,"And the people of вАЩ»Вd and Tham√їd Ћєmet a similar fateЋЇ, which must be clear to you ЋєMeccansЋЇ from their ruins.¬†Satan made their ЋєevilЋЇ deeds appealing to them, hindering them from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way, although they were capable of reasoning"
  29,39,"ЋєWeЋЇ also ЋєdestroyedЋЇ Korah, Pharaoh, and Ham√Ґn. Indeed, Moses had come to them with clear proofs, but they behaved arrogantly in the land. Yet they could not escape ЋєUsЋЇ"
  29,40,"So We seized each ЋєpeopleЋЇ for their sin: against some of them We sent a storm of stones, some were overtaken by a ЋєmightyЋЇ blast, some We caused the earth to swallow, and some We drowned. Allah would not have wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  29,41,"The parable of those who take protectors other than Allah is that of a spider spinning a shelter. And the flimsiest of all shelters is certainly that of a spider, if only they knew"
  29,42,"Allah surely knows that whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ they invoke besides Him are ЋєsimplyЋЇ nothing. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  29,43,"These are the parables We set forth for humanity, but none will understand them except the people of knowledge"
  29,44,Allah created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. Surely in this is a sign for the people of faith
  29,45,"Recite what has been revealed to you of the Book and establish prayer. Indeed, ЋєgenuineЋЇ prayer should deter ЋєoneЋЇ from indecency and wickedness. The remembrance of Allah is ЋєanЋЇ even greater ЋєdeterrentЋЇ. And Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what you ЋєallЋЇ do"
  29,46,"Do not argue with the People of the Book unless gracefully, except with those of them who act wrongfully. And say, вАЬWe believe in what has been revealed to us and what was revealed to you. Our God and your God is ЋєonlyЋЇ One. And to Him we ЋєfullyЋЇ submit.вАЭ"
  29,47,"Similarly Ћєto earlier messengersЋЇ, We have revealed to you a Book ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. ЋєThe faithful ofЋЇ those to whom We gave the Scriptures believe in it, as do some of these Ћєpagan ArabsЋЇ. And none denies Our revelations except the ЋєstubbornЋЇ disbelievers"
  29,48,"You ЋєO ProphetЋЇ could not read any writing ЋєevenЋЇ before this ЋєrevelationЋЇ, nor could you write at all. Otherwise, the people of falsehood would have been suspicious"
  29,49,But this ЋєQuranЋЇ is Ћєa set ofЋЇ clear revelations ЋєpreservedЋЇ in the hearts of those gifted with knowledge. And none denies Our revelations except the ЋєstubbornЋЇ wrongdoers
  29,50,"They say, вАЬIf only ЋєsomeЋЇ signs had been sent down to him from his Lord!вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬSigns are only with Allah. And I am only sent with a clear warning.вАЭ"
  29,51,"Is it not enough for them that We have sent down to you the Book, Ћєwhich isЋЇ recited to them. Surely in this ЋєQuranЋЇ is a mercy and reminder for people who believe"
  29,52,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬSufficient is Allah as a Witness between me and you. He ЋєfullyЋЇ knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And those who believe in falsehood and disbelieve in Allah, it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ losers.вАЭ"
  29,53,"They challenge you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to hasten the punishment. Had it not been for a time already set, the punishment would have certainly come to them Ћєat onceЋЇ. But it will definitely take them by surprise when they least expect it"
  29,54,They urge you to hasten the punishment. And Hell will certainly encompass the disbelievers
  29,55,"on the Day the punishment will overwhelm them from above them and from below their feet. And it will be said, вАЬReap what you sowed.вАЭ"
  29,56,"O My believing servants! My earth is truly spacious, so worship Me ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  29,57,"Every soul will taste death, then to Us you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  29,58,"ЋєAs forЋЇ those who believe and do good, We will certainly house them in ЋєelevatedЋЇ mansions in Paradise, under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. How excellent is the reward for those who work Ћєrighteousness!ЋЇвАФ"
  29,59,"those who patiently endure, and put their trust in their Lord"
  29,60,"How many are the creatures that cannot secure their provisions! ЋєIt isЋЇ Allah ЋєWhoЋЇ provides for them and you Ћєas wellЋЇ. He is indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  29,61,"If you ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who created the heavens and the earth and subjected the sun and the moon Ћєfor your benefitЋЇ, they will certainly say, вАЬAllah!вАЭ How can they then be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  29,62,Allah gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. Surely Allah has ЋєfullЋЇ knowledge of everything
  29,63,"And if you ask them who sends down rain from the sky, giving life to the earth after its death, they will surely say, вАЬAllah!вАЭ Say, вАЬPraise be to Allah!вАЭ In fact, most of them do not understand"
  29,64,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement. But the Hereafter is indeed the real life, if only they knew"
  29,65,"If they happen to be aboard a ship Ћєcaught in a stormЋЇ, they cry out to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ in sincere devotion. But as soon as He delivers them ЋєsafelyЋЇ to shore, they associate Ћєothers with Him once againЋЇ"
  29,66,"So let them be ungrateful for all We have given them, and Ћєlet themЋЇ enjoy themselves Ћєfor nowЋЇ! For they will soon know"
  29,67,"Have they not seen how We have made ЋєMeccaЋЇ a safe haven, whereas people ЋєallЋЇ around them are snatched away?¬†How can they then believe in falsehood¬†and deny AllahвАЩs favours"
  29,68,And who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against Allah or reject the truth after it has reached them? Is Hell not a ЋєfittingЋЇ home for the disbelievers
  29,69,"As for those who struggle in Our cause, We will surely guide them along Our Way. And Allah is certainly with the good-doers"
  30,1,Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m
  30,2,The Romans have been defeated
  30,3,"in a nearby land.¬†Yet following their defeat, they will triumph"
  30,4,within three to nine years.¬†The ЋєwholeЋЇ matter rests with Allah before and after ЋєvictoryЋЇ. And on that day the believers will rejoice
  30,5,"at the victory willed by Allah. He gives victory to whoever He wills. For He is the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  30,6,ЋєThis isЋЇ the promise of Allah. ЋєAndЋЇ Allah never fails in His promise. But most people do not know
  30,7,"They ЋєonlyЋЇ know the worldly affairs of this life, but are ЋєtotallyЋЇ oblivious to the Hereafter"
  30,8,Have they not reflected upon their own being? Allah only created the heavens and the earth and everything in between for a purpose and an appointed term. Yet most people are truly in denial of the meeting with their Lord
  30,9,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them? They were far superior in might; they cultivated the land and developed it more than these ЋєMeccansЋЇ ever have. Their messengers came to them with clear proofs. Allah would have never wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  30,10,Then most evil was the end of the evildoers for denying and mocking the signs of Allah
  30,11,"It is Allah Who originates the creation, and will resurrect it. And then to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  30,12,"On the Day the Hour will arrive, the wicked will be dumbstruck"
  30,13,"There will be no intercessors for them from among their associate-gods, and they will ЋєtotallyЋЇ deny their associate-gods"
  30,14,"And on the Day the Hour will arrive, the people will then be split Ћєinto two groupsЋЇ"
  30,15,"As for those who believed and did good, they will be rejoicing in a Garden"
  30,16,"And as for those who disbelieved, and denied Our signs and the meeting Ћєwith AllahЋЇ in the Hereafter, they will be confined in punishment"
  30,17,So glorify Allah in the evening and in the morningвАФ
  30,18,"all praise is for Him in the heavens and the earthвАФas well as in the afternoon, and at noon"
  30,19,He brings forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living. And He gives life to the earth after its death. And so will you be brought forth Ћєfrom the graveЋЇ
  30,20,"One of His signs is that He created you from dust, thenвАФbehold!вАФyou are human beings spreading over Ћєthe earthЋЇ"
  30,21,And one of His signs is that He created for you spouses from among yourselves so that you may find comfort in them. And He has placed between you compassion and mercy. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect
  30,22,"And one of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the diversity of your languages and colours. Surely in this are signs for those of ЋєsoundЋЇ knowledge"
  30,23,And one of His signs is your sleep by night and by day Ћєfor restЋЇ as well as your seeking His bounty Ћєin bothЋЇ. Surely in this are signs for people who listen
  30,24,"And one of His signs is that He shows you lightning, inspiring Ћєyou withЋЇ hope and fear.¬†And He sends down rain from the sky, reviving the earth after its death. Surely in this are signs for people who understand"
  30,25,"And one of His signs is that the heavens and the earth persist by His command. Then when He calls you out of the earth just once, you will instantly come forth"
  30,26,And to Him belong all those in the heavens and the earthвАФall are subject to His Will
  30,27,"And He is the One Who originates the creation then will resurrect itвАФwhich is even easier for Him.¬†To Him belong the finest attributes in the heavens and the earth. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  30,28,"He sets forth for you an example ЋєdrawnЋЇ from your own lives: would you allow some of those ЋєbondspeopleЋЇ in your possession to be your equal partners in whatever ЋєwealthЋЇ We have provided you, keeping them in mind as you are mindful of your peers?¬†This is how We make the signs clear for people who understand"
  30,29,"In fact, the wrongdoers merely follow their desires with no knowledge. Who then can guide those Allah has left to stray? They will have no helpers"
  30,30,"So be steadfast in faith in all uprightness ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФthe natural Way of Allah which He has instilled in ЋєallЋЇ people. Let there be no change in this creation of Allah. That is the Straight Way, but most people do not know"
  30,31,"ЋєO believers!ЋЇ Always turn to Him Ћєin repentanceЋЇ, be mindful of Him, and establish prayers. And do not be polytheistsвАФ"
  30,32,"ЋєlikeЋЇ those who have divided their faith and split into sects, each rejoicing in what they have"
  30,33,"When people are touched with hardship, they cry out to their Lord, turning to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. But as soon as He gives them a taste of His mercy, a group of them associates ЋєothersЋЇ with their Lord Ћєin worshipЋЇ"
  30,34,"becoming ungrateful for whatever ЋєfavoursЋЇ We have given them. So enjoy yourselves, for soon you will know"
  30,35,Or have We sent down to them an authority which attests to what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ
  30,36,"If We give people a taste of mercy, they become prideful ЋєbecauseЋЇ of it. But if they are afflicted with an evil for what their hands have done, they instantly fall into despair"
  30,37,Have they not seen that Allah gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills? Surely in this are signs for people who believe
  30,38,"So give your close relatives their due, as well as the poor and the ЋєneedyЋЇ traveller. That is best for those who seek the pleasure of Allah,¬†and it is they who will be successful"
  30,39,"Whatever loans you give, ЋєonlyЋЇ seeking interest at the expense of peopleвАЩs wealth¬†will not increase with Allah. But whatever charity you give, ЋєonlyЋЇ seeking the pleasure of AllahвАФit is they whose reward will be multiplied"
  30,40,"It is Allah Who created you, then gives you provisions, then will cause you to die, and then will bring you back to life. Can any of your associate-gods do any of this? Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ"
  30,41,"Corruption has spread on land and sea as a result of what peopleвАЩs hands have done, so that Allah may cause them to taste Ћєthe consequences ofЋЇ some of their deeds and perhaps they might return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ"
  30,42,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬTravel throughout the land and see what was the end of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before ЋєyouЋЇвАФmost of them were polytheists.вАЭ"
  30,43,"So be steadfast in the Upright Faith ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, before the coming of a Day from Allah that cannot be averted. On that Day the people will be divided"
  30,44,those who disbelieved will bear Ћєthe burden ofЋЇ their own disbelief; and those who did good will have prepared for themselves Ћєeternal homesЋЇ
  30,45,"so that He may ЋєgenerouslyЋЇ reward those who believe and do good, out of His grace. He truly does not like the disbelievers"
  30,46,"And one of His signs is that He sends the winds, ushering in good news Ћєof rainЋЇ so that He may give you a taste of His mercy, and that ships may sail by His command, and that you may seek His bounty, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  30,47,"Indeed, We sent before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ messengers, each to their own people, and they came to them with clear proofs. Then We inflicted punishment upon those who persisted in wickedness. For it is Our duty to help the believers"
  30,48,"It is Allah Who sends the winds, which then stir up Ћєvapour, formingЋЇ clouds, which He then spreads out in the sky or piles up into masses as He wills, from which you see rain come forth. Then as soon as He causes it to fall on whoever He wills of His servants, they rejoice"
  30,49,although they had utterly lost hope just before it was sent down to them
  30,50,"See then the impact of AllahвАЩs mercy: how He gives life to the earth after its death! Surely That Ћєsame GodЋЇ can raise the dead. For He is Most Capable of everything"
  30,51,"Then if We send a ЋєharshЋЇ wind which they see withering ЋєtheirЋЇ crops, they will definitely deny Ћєold favoursЋЇ right after"
  30,52,So you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ certainly cannot make the dead hear Ћєthe truthЋЇ. Nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and walk away
  30,53,"Nor can you lead the blind out of their misguidance. You can make none hear Ћєthe truthЋЇ except those who believe in Our revelations, ЋєfullyЋЇ submitting Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  30,54,"It is Allah Who created you in a state of weakness, then developed ЋєyourЋЇ weakness into strength, then developed ЋєyourЋЇ strength into weakness and old age.¬†He creates whatever He wills. For He is the All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  30,55,"And on the Day the Hour will arrive, the wicked will swear that they did not stay Ћєin this worldЋЇ more than an hour. In this way they were always deluded Ћєin the worldЋЇ"
  30,56,"But those gifted with knowledge and faith will say Ћєto themЋЇ, вАЬYou did actually stayвАФas destined by AllahвАФuntil the Day of Resurrection. So here is the Day of Resurrection Ћєwhich you deniedЋЇ! But you did not know Ћєit was trueЋЇ.вАЭ"
  30,57,"So on that Day the wrongdoersвАЩ excuses will not benefit them, nor will they be allowed to appease Ћєtheir LordЋЇ"
  30,58,"We have certainly set forth every Ћєkind ofЋЇ lesson for people in this Quran. And no matter what sign you bring to them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, the disbelievers will definitely say Ћєto the believersЋЇ, вАЬYou are only a people of falsehood.вАЭ"
  30,59,This is how Allah seals the hearts of those unwilling to know Ћєthe truthЋЇ
  30,60,"So be patient, for the promise of Allah certainly is true. And do not be disturbed by those who have no sure faith"
  31,1,Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m
  31,2,"These are the verses of the Book, rich in wisdom"
  31,3,ЋєIt isЋЇ a guide and mercy for the good-doersвАФ
  31,4,"those who establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  31,5,"It is they who are ЋєtrulyЋЇ guided by their Lord, and it is they who will be successful"
  31,6,"But there are some who employ theatrics,¬†only to lead others away from AllahвАЩs WayвАФwithout any knowledgeвАФand to make a mockery of it. They will suffer¬†a humiliating punishment"
  31,7,"Whenever Our revelations are recited to them, they turn away in arrogance as if they did not hear them, as if there is deafness in their ears. So give them good news ЋєO ProphetЋЇ of a painful punishment"
  31,8,Surely those who believe and do good will have the Gardens of Bliss
  31,9,"staying there forever. AllahвАЩs promise is true. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  31,10,"He created the heavens without pillarsвАФas you can seeвАФand placed firm mountains upon the earth so it does not shake with you, and scattered throughout it all types of creatures. And We send down rain from the sky, causing every type of fine plant to grow on earth"
  31,11,"This is AllahвАЩs creation. Now show Me what those ЋєgodsЋЇ other than Him have created. In fact, the wrongdoers are clearly astray"
  31,12,"Indeed, We blessed Luqm√Ґn with wisdom, ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬBe grateful to Allah, for whoever is grateful, it is only for their own good. And whoever is ungrateful, then surely Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy.вАЭ"
  31,13,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Luqm√Ґn said to his son, while advising him, вАЬO my dear son! Never associate ЋєanythingЋЇ with Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇ, for associating Ћєothers with HimЋЇ is truly the worst of all wrongs.вАЭ"
  31,14,"And We have commanded people to ЋєhonourЋЇ their parents. Their mothers bore them through hardship upon hardship, and their weaning takes two years. So be grateful to Me and your parents.¬†To Me is the final return"
  31,15,"But if they pressure you to associate with Me what you have no knowledge of,¬†do not obey them. Still keep their company in this world courteously, and follow the way of those who turn to Me Ћєin devotionЋЇ. Then to Me you will ЋєallЋЇ return, and then I will inform you of what you used to do"
  31,16,"ЋєLuqm√Ґn added,ЋЇ вАЬO my dear son! ЋєEvenЋЇ if a deed were the weight of a mustard seedвАФbe it ЋєhiddenЋЇ in a rock or in the heavens or the earthвАФAllah will bring it forth. Surely Allah is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  31,17,"вАЬO my dear son! Establish prayer, encourage what is good and forbid what is evil, and endure patiently whatever befalls you. Surely this is a resolve to aspire to"
  31,18,"вАЬAnd do not turn your nose up to people, nor walk pridefully upon the earth. Surely Allah does not like whoever is arrogant, boastful"
  31,19,"Be moderate in your pace. And lower your voice, for the ugliest of all voices is certainly the braying of donkeys.вАЭ"
  31,20,"Have you not seen that Allah has subjected for you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth, and has lavished His favours upon you, both seen and unseen? ЋєStillЋЇ there are some who dispute about Allah without knowledge, or guidance, or an enlightening scripture"
  31,21,"When it is said to them, вАЬFollow what Allah has revealed,вАЭ they reply, вАЬNo! We ЋєonlyЋЇ follow what we found our forefathers practicing.вАЭ ЋєWould they still do soЋЇ even if Satan is inviting them to the torment of the Blaze"
  31,22,"Whoever fully submits themselves to Allah and is a good-doer, they have certainly grasped the firmest hand-hold. And with Allah rests the outcome of ЋєallЋЇ affairs"
  31,23,"But whoever disbelieves, do not let their disbelief grieve you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. To Us is their return, and We will inform them of all they did. Surely Allah knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  31,24,"We allow them enjoyment for a little while, then Ћєin timeЋЇ We will force them into a harsh torment"
  31,25,"And if you ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will definitely say, вАЬAllah!вАЭ Say, вАЬPraise be to Allah!вАЭ In fact, most of them do not know"
  31,26,"To Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. Allah is truly the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  31,27,"If all the trees on earth were pens and the ocean Ћєwere inkЋЇ, refilled by seven other oceans, the Words of Allah would not be exhausted. Surely Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  31,28,"The creation and resurrection of you ЋєallЋЇ is as simple Ћєfor HimЋЇ as that of a single soul. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  31,29,"Do you not see that Allah causes the night to merge into the day and the day into the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term, and that Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  31,30,"That is because Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Truth and what they invoke besides Him is falsehood, and ЋєbecauseЋЇ Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Most High, All-Great"
  31,31,"Do you not see that the ships sail ЋєsmoothlyЋЇ through the sea by the grace of Allah so that He may show you some of His signs? Surely in this are signs for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  31,32,"And as soon as they are overwhelmed by waves like mountains, they cry out to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ in sincere devotion. But when He delivers them ЋєsafelyЋЇ to shore, only some become relatively grateful. And none rejects Our signs except whoever is deceitful, ungrateful"
  31,33,"O humanity! Be mindful of your Lord, and beware of a Day when no parent will be of any benefit to their child, nor will a child be of any benefit to their parent. Surely AllahвАЩs promise is true. So do not let the life of this world deceive you, nor let the Chief Deceiver¬†deceive you about Allah"
  31,34,"Indeed, Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ has the knowledge of the Hour. He sends down the rain,¬†and knows what is in the wombs.¬†No soul knows what it will earn for tomorrow, and no soul knows in what land it will die. Surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  32,1,Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m
  32,2,The revelation of this Book isвАФbeyond doubtвАФfrom the Lord of all worlds
  32,3,"Or do they say, вАЬHe has fabricated it!вАЭ? No! It is the truth from your Lord in order for you to warn a people to whom no warner has come before you, so they may be ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  32,4,"It is Allah Who has created the heavens and the earth and everything in between in six Days,¬†then established Himself on the Throne. You have no protector or intercessor besides Him. Will you not then be mindful"
  32,5,"He conducts every affair from the heavens to the earth, then it all ascends to Him on a Day whose length is a thousand years by your counting"
  32,6,"That is the Knower of the seen and unseenвАФthe Almighty, Most Merciful"
  32,7,Who has perfected everything He created. And He originated the creation of humankind from clay
  32,8,Then He made his descendants from an extract of a humble fluid
  32,9,"then He fashioned them and had a spirit of His Own ЋєcreationЋЇ breathed into them. And He gave you hearing, sight, and intellect. ЋєYetЋЇ you hardly give any thanks"
  32,10,"ЋєStillЋЇ they ask ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhen we are disintegrated into the earth, will we really be raised as a new creation?вАЭ In fact, they are in denial of the meeting with their Lord"
  32,11,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYour soul will be taken by the Angel of Death, who is in charge of you. Then to your Lord you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned.вАЭ"
  32,12,"If only you could see the wicked hanging their heads Ћєin shameЋЇ before their Lord, Ћєcrying:ЋЇ вАЬOur Lord! We have now seen and heard, so send us back and we will do good. We truly have sure faith ЋєnowЋЇ!вАЭ"
  32,13,"Had We willed, We could have easily imposed guidance on every soul. But My Word will come to pass: I will surely fill up Hell with jinn and humans all together"
  32,14,So taste Ћєthe punishmentЋЇ for neglecting the meeting of this Day of yours. We ЋєtooЋЇ will certainly neglect you. And taste the torment of eternity for what you used to do
  32,15,The only ЋєtrueЋЇ believers in Our revelation are those whoвАФwhen it is recited to themвАФfall into prostration and glorify the praises of their Lord and are not too proud
  32,16,"They abandon their beds, invoking their Lord with hope and fear, and donate from what We have provided for them"
  32,17,No soul can imagine what delights are kept in store for them as a reward for what they used to do
  32,18,Is the one who is a believer equal Ћєbefore AllahЋЇ to the one who is rebellious? They are not equal
  32,19,"As for those who believe and do good, they will have the Gardens of ЋєEternalЋЇ ResidenceвАФas an accommodation for what they used to do"
  32,20,"But as for those who are rebellious, the Fire will be their home. Whenever they try to escape from it, they will be forced back into it, and will be told, вАЬTaste the FireвАЩs torment, which you used to deny.вАЭ"
  32,21,"We will certainly make them taste some of the minor torment Ћєin this lifeЋЇ before the major torment Ћєof the HereafterЋЇ, so perhaps they will return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ"
  32,22,And who does more wrong than the one who is reminded of AllahвАЩs revelations then turns away from them? We will surely inflict punishment upon the wicked
  32,23,"Indeed, We gave the Scripture to MosesвАФso let there be no doubt ЋєO ProphetЋЇ that you ЋєtooЋЇ are receiving revelationsвАФand We made it a guide for the Children of Israel"
  32,24,"We raised from among them leaders,¬†guiding by Our command, when they patiently endured and firmly believed in Our signs"
  32,25,"Indeed, your Lord will decide between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their differences"
  32,26,"Is it not yet clear to them how many peoples We destroyed before them, whose ruins they still pass by? Surely in this are signs. Will they not then listen"
  32,27,"Do they not see how We drive rain to parched land, producing ЋєvariousЋЇ crops from which they and their cattle eat? Will they not then see"
  32,28,"They ask ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhen is this ЋєDay of finalЋЇ Decision, if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  32,29,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬOn the Day of Decision it will not benefit the disbelievers to believe then, nor will they be delayed Ћєfrom punishmentЋЇ.вАЭ"
  32,30,"So turn away from them, and wait! They too are waiting"
  33,1,"O Prophet! ЋєAlwaysЋЇ be mindful of Allah, and do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  33,2,Follow what is revealed to you from your Lord. Surely Allah is All-Aware of what you ЋєallЋЇ do
  33,3,"And put your trust in Allah, for Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,4,"Allah does not place two hearts in any personвАЩs chest. Nor does He regard your wives as Ћєunlawful for you likeЋЇ your real mothers, ЋєevenЋЇ if you say they are.¬†Nor does He regard your adopted children as your real children.¬†These are only your baseless assertions. But Allah declares the truth, and He ЋєaloneЋЇ guides to the ЋєRightЋЇ Way"
  33,5,"Let your adopted children keep their family names. That is more just in the sight of Allah. But if you do not know their fathers, then they are ЋєsimplyЋЇ your fellow believers and close associates. There is no blame on you for what you do by mistake, but ЋєonlyЋЇ for what you do intentionally. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,6,"The Prophet has a stronger affinity to the believers than they do themselves. And his wives are their mothers. As ordained by Allah, blood relatives are more entitled Ћєto inheritanceЋЇ than ЋєotherЋЇ believers and immigrants, unless you Ћєwant toЋЇ show kindness to your ЋєcloseЋЇ associates Ћєthrough bequestЋЇ.¬†This is decreed in the Record"
  33,7,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when We took a covenant from the prophets, as well as from you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, and from Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, son of Mary. We did take a solemn covenant from Ћєall ofЋЇ them"
  33,8,so that He may question these men of truth about their Ћєdelivery of theЋЇ truth. And He has prepared a painful punishment for the disbelievers
  33,9,"O believers! Remember AllahвАЩs favour upon you when ЋєenemyЋЇ forces came to ЋєbesiegeЋЇ you Ћєin MedinaЋЇ,¬†so We sent against them a ЋєbitterЋЇ wind and forces you could not see.¬†And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  33,10,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when they came at you from east and west,¬†when your eyes grew wild Ћєin horrorЋЇ and your hearts jumped into your throats, and you entertained ЋєconflictingЋЇ thoughts about Allah"
  33,11,"Then and there the believers were put to the test, and were violently shaken"
  33,12,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, вАЬAllah and His Messenger have promised us nothing but delusion!вАЭ"
  33,13,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when a group of them said, вАЬO people of Yathrib!¬†There is no point in you staying ЋєhereЋЇ, so retreat!вАЭ Another group of them asked the ProphetвАЩs permission Ћєto leaveЋЇ, saying, вАЬOur homes are vulnerable,вАЭ while Ћєin factЋЇ they were not vulnerable. They only wished to flee"
  33,14,"Had their city been sacked from all sides and they had been asked to abandon faith, they would have done so with little hesitation"
  33,15,They had already pledged to Allah earlier never to turn their backs Ћєin retreatЋЇ. And a pledge to Allah must be answered for
  33,16,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬFleeing will not benefit you if you Ћєtry toЋЇ escape a natural or violent death. ЋєIf it is not your time,ЋЇ you will only be allowed enjoyment for a little while.вАЭ"
  33,17,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWho can put you out of AllahвАЩs reach if He intends to harm you or show you mercy?вАЭ They can never find any protector or helper besides Allah"
  33,18,"Allah knows well those among you who discourage Ћєothers from fightingЋЇ, saying ЋєsecretlyЋЇ to their brothers, вАЬStay with us,вАЭ and who themselves hardly take part in fighting"
  33,19,"ЋєThey areЋЇ totally unwilling to assist you. When danger comes, you see them staring at you with their eyes rolling like someone in the throes of death. But once the danger is over, they slash you with razor-sharp tongues, ravenous for ЋєworldlyЋЇ gains. Such people have not ЋєtrulyЋЇ believed, so Allah has rendered their deeds void. And that is easy for Allah"
  33,20,"They ЋєstillЋЇ think that the enemy alliance has not ЋєyetЋЇ withdrawn. And if the allies were to come ЋєagainЋЇ, the hypocrites would wish to be away in the desert among nomadic Arabs, ЋєonlyЋЇ asking for news about you ЋєbelieversЋЇ. And if the hypocrites were in your midst, they would hardly take part in the fight"
  33,21,"Indeed, in the Messenger of Allah you have an excellent example for whoever has hope in Allah and the Last Day, and remembers Allah often"
  33,22,"When the believers saw the enemy alliance, they said, вАЬThis is what Allah and His Messenger had promised us. The promise of Allah and His Messenger has come true.вАЭ And this only increased them in faith and submission"
  33,23,"Among the believers are men who have proven true to what they pledged to Allah.¬†Some of them have fulfilled their pledge Ћєwith their livesЋЇ, others are waiting Ћєtheir turnЋЇ. They have never changed Ћєtheir commitmentЋЇ in the least"
  33,24,"ЋєIt all happenedЋЇ so Allah may reward the faithful for their faithfulness, and punish the hypocrites if He wills or turn to them Ћєin mercyЋЇ. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,25,"And Allah drove back the disbelievers in their rage, totally empty-handed. And Allah spared the believers from fighting. For Allah is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  33,26,"And He brought down those from the People of the Book¬†who supported the enemy alliance from their own strongholds, and cast horror into their hearts. You ЋєbelieversЋЇ killed some, and took others captive"
  33,27,"He has also caused you to take over their lands, homes, and wealth, as well as lands you have not yet set foot on. And Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  33,28,"O Prophet! Say to your wives, вАЬIf you desire the life of this world and its luxury, then come, I will give you a ЋєsuitableЋЇ compensation Ћєfor divorceЋЇ and let you go graciously"
  33,29,"But if you desire Allah and His Messenger and the ЋєeverlastingЋЇ Home of the Hereafter, then Surely Allah has prepared a great reward for those of you who do good.вАЭ"
  33,30,"O wives of the Prophet! If any of you were to commit a blatant misconduct, the punishment would be doubled for her. And that is easy for Allah"
  33,31,"And whoever of you devoutly obeys Allah and His Messenger and does good, We will grant her double the reward, and We have prepared for her an honourable provision"
  33,32,"O wives of the Prophet! You are not like any other women: if you are mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, then do not be overly effeminate in speech Ћєwith menЋЇ or those with sickness in their hearts may be tempted, but speak in a moderate tone"
  33,33,"Settle in your homes, and do not display yourselves as women did in the days of Ћєpre-IslamicЋЇ ignorance. Establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and obey Allah and His Messenger. Allah only intends to keep Ћєthe causes ofЋЇ evil away from you and purify you completely, O members of the ЋєProphetвАЩsЋЇ family"
  33,34,"ЋєAlwaysЋЇ remember what is recited in your homes of AllahвАЩs revelations and ЋєpropheticЋЇ wisdom.¬†Surely Allah is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  33,35,"Surely ЋєforЋЇ Muslim men and women, believing men and women,¬†devout men and women, truthful men and women, patient men and women, humble men and women, charitable men and women, fasting men and women, men and women who guard their chastity, and men and women who remember Allah oftenвАФfor Ћєall ofЋЇ them Allah has prepared forgiveness and a great reward"
  33,36,"It is not for a believing man or womanвАФwhen Allah and His Messenger decree a matterвАФto have any other choice in that matter.¬†Indeed, whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger has clearly gone ЋєfarЋЇ astray"
  33,37,"And Ћєremember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when you said to the one¬†for whom Allah has done a favour and you ЋєtooЋЇ have done a favour,¬†вАЬKeep your wife and fear Allah,вАЭ while concealing within yourself what Allah was going to reveal. And ЋєsoЋЇ you were considering the people, whereas Allah was more worthy of your consideration. So when Zaid totally lost interest in ЋєkeepingЋЇ his wife, We gave her to you in marriage, so that there would be no blame on the believers for marrying the ex-wives of their adopted sons after their divorce. And AllahвАЩs command is totally binding"
  33,38,There is no blame on the Prophet for doing what Allah has ordained for him. That has been the way of Allah with those ЋєprophetsЋЇ who had gone before. And AllahвАЩs command has been firmly decreed
  33,39,"ЋєThat is His way withЋЇ those ЋєprophetsЋЇ who deliver the messages of Allah, and consider Him, and none but Allah. And sufficient is Allah as a ЋєvigilantЋЇ Reckoner"
  33,40,"MuбЄ•ammad is not the father of any of your men,¬†but is the Messenger of Allah and the seal of the prophets. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  33,41,O believers! Always remember Allah often
  33,42,and glorify Him morning and evening
  33,43,He is the One Who showers His blessings upon youвАФand His angels pray for youвАФso that He may bring you out of darkness and into light. For He is ever Merciful to the believers
  33,44,"Their greeting on the Day they meet Him will be, вАЬPeace!вАЭ And He has prepared for them an honourable reward"
  33,45,"O Prophet! We have sent you as a witness, and a deliverer of good news, and a warner"
  33,46,"and a caller to Ћєthe Way ofЋЇ Allah by His command, and a beacon of light"
  33,47,Give good news to the believers that they will have a great bounty from Allah
  33,48,"Do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Overlook their annoyances, and put your trust in Allah. For Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,49,"O believers! If you marry believing women and then divorce them before you touch them,¬†they will have no waiting period for you to count,¬†so give them a ЋєsuitableЋЇ compensation, and let them go graciously"
  33,50,"O Prophet! We have made lawful for you your wives to whom you have paid their ЋєfullЋЇ dowries as well as those ЋєbondwomenЋЇ in your possession, whom Allah has granted you.¬†And Ћєyou are allowed to marryЋЇ the daughters of your paternal uncles and aunts, and the daughters of your maternal uncles and aunts, who have emigrated like you. Also Ћєallowed for marriage isЋЇ a believing woman who offers herself to the Prophet Ћєwithout dowryЋЇ if he is interested in marrying herвАФЋєthis isЋЇ exclusively for you, not for the rest of the believers.¬†We know well what ЋєrulingsЋЇ We have ordained for the believers in relation to their wives and those ЋєbondwomenЋЇ in their possession. As such, there would be no blame on you. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,51,"It is up to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to delay or receive whoever you please of your wives. There is no blame on you if you call back any of those you have set aside.¬†That is more likely that they will be content, not grieved, and satisfied with what you offer them all. Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what is in your hearts. And Allah is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  33,52,"It is not lawful for you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to marry more women after this, nor can you replace any of your present wives with another, even if her beauty may attract youвАФexcept those ЋєbondwomenЋЇ in your possession. And Allah is ever Watchful over all things"
  33,53,"O believers! Do not enter the homes of the Prophet without permission Ћєand if invitedЋЇ for a meal, do not Ћєcome too early andЋЇ linger until the meal is ready. But if you are invited, then enter Ћєon timeЋЇ. Once you have eaten, then go on your way, and do not stay for casual talk. Such behaviour is truly annoying to the Prophet, yet he is too shy to ask you to leave. But Allah is never shy of the truth. And when you ЋєbelieversЋЇ ask his wives for something, ask them from behind a barrier. This is purer for your hearts and theirs. And it is not right for you to annoy the Messenger of Allah, nor ever marry his wives after him. This would certainly be a major offence in the sight of Allah"
  33,54,"Whether you reveal something or conceal it, surely Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  33,55,"There is no blame on the ProphetвАЩs wives Ћєif they appear unveiledЋЇ before their fathers,¬†their sons, their brothers, their brothersвАЩ sons, their sistersвАЩ sons, their fellow ЋєMuslimЋЇ women, and those ЋєbondspeopleЋЇ in their possession. And be mindful of Allah ЋєO wives of the Prophet!ЋЇ Surely Allah is a Witness over all things"
  33,56,"Indeed, Allah showers His blessings upon the Prophet, and His angels pray for him. O believers! Invoke AllahвАЩs blessings upon him, and salute him with worthy greetings of peace"
  33,57,Surely those who offend Allah¬†and His Messenger¬†are condemned by Allah in this world and the Hereafter. And He has prepared for them a humiliating punishment
  33,58,"As for those who abuse believing men and women¬†unjustifiably, they will definitely bear the guilt of slander and blatant sin"
  33,59,"O Prophet! Ask your wives, daughters, and believing women to draw their cloaks over their bodies. In this way it is more likely that they will be recognized Ћєas virtuousЋЇ and not be harassed. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,60,"If the hypocrites, and those with sickness in their hearts, and rumour-mongers in Medina do not desist, We will certainly incite you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ against them, and then they will not be your neighbours there any longer"
  33,61,"ЋєThey deserve to beЋЇ condemned. ЋєIf they were to persist,ЋЇ they would get themselves seized and killed relentlessly wherever they are found"
  33,62,That was AllahвАЩs way with those ЋєhypocritesЋЇ who have gone before. And you will find no change in AllahвАЩs way
  33,63,"People ask you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ about the Hour. Say, вАЬThat knowledge is only with Allah. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near.вАЭ"
  33,64,"Surely Allah condemns the disbelievers, and has prepared for them a blazing Fire"
  33,65,to stay there for ever and everвАФnever will they find any protector or helper
  33,66,"On the Day their faces are ЋєconstantlyЋЇ flipped in the Fire, they will cry, вАЬOh! If only we had obeyed Allah and obeyed the Messenger!вАЭ"
  33,67,"And they will say, вАЬOur Lord! We obeyed our leaders and elite, but they led us astray from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way"
  33,68,"Our Lord! Give them double ЋєourЋЇ punishment, and condemn them tremendously.вАЭ"
  33,69,"O believers! Do not be like those who slandered Moses, but Allah cleared him of what they said. And he was honourable in the sight of Allah"
  33,70,"O believers! Be mindful of Allah, and say what is right"
  33,71,"He will bless your deeds for you, and forgive your sins. And whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger, has truly achieved a great triumph"
  33,72,"Indeed, We offered the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they ЋєallЋЇ declined to bear it, being fearful of it. But humanity assumed it, ЋєforЋЇ they are truly wrongful Ћєto themselvesЋЇ and ignorant Ћєof the consequencesЋЇ"
  33,73,"so that Allah will punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, and Allah will turn in mercy to believing men and women. For Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  34,1,"All praise is for Allah, to Whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And praise be to Him in the Hereafter. He is the All-Wise, All-Aware"
  34,2,"He knows whatever goes into the earth and whatever comes out of it, and whatever descends from the sky and whatever ascends into it. And He is the Most Merciful, All-Forgiving"
  34,3,"The disbelievers say, вАЬThe Hour will never come to us.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYesвАФby my Lord, the Knower of the unseenвАФit will certainly come to you!вАЭ Not ЋєevenЋЇ an atomвАЩs weight is hidden from Him in the heavens or the earth; nor anything smaller or larger than that, but is ЋєwrittenЋЇ in a perfect Record"
  34,4,So He may reward those who believe and do good. It is they who will have forgiveness and an honourable provision
  34,5,"As for those who strive to discredit Our revelations, it is they who will suffer the ЋєworstЋЇ torment of agonizing pain"
  34,6,"Those gifted with knowledge ЋєclearlyЋЇ see that what has been revealed to you from your Lord ЋєO ProphetЋЇ is the truth, and that it guides to the Path of the Almighty, the Praiseworthy"
  34,7,"The disbelievers say Ћєmockingly to one anotherЋЇ, вАЬShall we show you a man who claims that when you have been utterly disintegrated you will be raised as a new creation"
  34,8,"Has he fabricated a lie against Allah or is he insane?вАЭ In fact, those who do not believe in the Hereafter are bound for torment and have strayed farthest Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  34,9,"Have they not then seen all that surrounds them of the heavens and the earth? If We willed, We could cause the earth to swallow them up, or cause ЋєdeadlyЋЇ pieces of the sky to fall upon them. Surely in this is a sign for every servant who turns Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  34,10,"Indeed, We granted David a ЋєgreatЋЇ privilege from Us, Ћєcommanding:ЋЇ вАЬO mountains! Echo his hymns! And the birds as well.вАЭ We made iron mouldable for him"
  34,11,"instructing: вАЬMake full-length armour, ЋєperfectlyЋЇ balancing the links. And work righteousness ЋєO family of David!ЋЇ. Indeed, I am All-Seeing of what you do.вАЭ"
  34,12,"And to Solomon ЋєWe subjectedЋЇ the wind: its morning stride was a monthвАЩs journey and so was its evening stride. And We caused a stream of molten copper to flow for him, and ЋєWe subjectedЋЇ some of the jinn to work under him by his LordвАЩs Will. And whoever of them deviated from Our command, We made them taste the torment of the blaze"
  34,13,"They made for him whatever he desired of sanctuaries, statues,¬†basins as large as reservoirs, and cooking pots fixed Ћєinto the groundЋЇ. ЋєWe ordered:ЋЇ вАЬWork gratefully, O family of David!вАЭ ЋєOnlyЋЇ a few of My servants are ЋєtrulyЋЇ grateful"
  34,14,"When We decreed SolomonвАЩs death, nothing indicated to the ЋєsubjectedЋЇ jinn that he was dead except the termites eating away his staff.¬†So when he collapsed, the jinn realized that if they had ЋєreallyЋЇ known the unseen, they would not have remained in ЋєsuchЋЇ humiliating servitude"
  34,15,"Indeed, there was a sign for Ћєthe tribe ofЋЇ Sheba in their homeland: two orchardsвАФone to the right and the other to the left. ЋєThey were told:ЋЇ вАЬEat from the provision of your Lord, and be grateful to Him. ЋєYours isЋЇ a good land and a forgiving Lord.вАЭ"
  34,16,"But they turned away. So We sent against them a devastating flood, and replaced their orchards with two others producing bitter fruit, fruitless bushes,¬†and a few ЋєsparseЋЇ thorny trees"
  34,17,This is how We rewarded them for their ingratitude. Would We ever punish Ћєanyone in such a wayЋЇ except the ungrateful
  34,18,"We had also placed between them and the cities¬†We showered with blessings Ћєmany smallЋЇ towns within sight of one another. And We set moderate travel distances in between, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬTravel between them by day and night safely.вАЭ"
  34,19,"But they said, вАЬOur Lord! Make Ћєthe distances ofЋЇ our journeys longer,вАЭ wronging themselves.¬†So We reduced them to ЋєcautionaryЋЇ tales, and scattered them utterly. Surely in this are lessons for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  34,20,"Indeed, Ibl√ЃsвАЩ assumption about them has come true,¬†so they ЋєallЋЇ follow him, except a group of ЋєtrueЋЇ believers"
  34,21,"He does not have any authority over them, but ЋєOur Will isЋЇ only to distinguish those who believe in the Hereafter from those who are in doubt about it. And your Lord is a ЋєvigilantЋЇ Keeper over all things.вАЭ"
  34,22,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬCall upon those you claim Ћєto be divineЋЇ besides Allah. They do not possess ЋєevenЋЇ an atomвАЩs weight either in the heavens or the earth, nor do they have any share in ЋєgoverningЋЇ them. Nor is any of them a helper to Him.вАЭ"
  34,23,"No intercession will be of any benefit with Him, except by those granted permission by Him. ЋєAt last,ЋЇ when the dread Ћєof Judgment DayЋЇ is relieved from their hearts Ћєbecause they are permitted to intercedeЋЇ, they will ЋєexcitedlyЋЇ ask Ћєthe angelsЋЇ, вАЬWhat has your Lord ЋєjustЋЇ said?вАЭ The angels will reply, вАЬThe truth! And He is the Most High, All-Great.вАЭ"
  34,24,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWho provides for you from the heavens and the earth?вАЭ Say, вАЬAllah! Now, certainly one of our two groups¬†is ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided; the other is clearly astray.вАЭ"
  34,25,"Say, вАЬYou will not be accountable for our misdeeds, nor will we be accountable for your deeds.вАЭ"
  34,26,"Say, вАЬOur Lord will gather us together, then He will judge between us with the truth. For He is the All-Knowing Judge.вАЭ"
  34,27,"Say, вАЬShow me those ЋєidolsЋЇ you have joined with Him as partners. No! In fact, He ЋєaloneЋЇ is AllahвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  34,28,"We have sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ only as a deliverer of good news and a warner to all of humanity, but most people do not know"
  34,29,"And they ask Ћєthe believersЋЇ, вАЬWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  34,30,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬA Day has ЋєalreadyЋЇ been appointed for you, which you can neither delay nor advance by a ЋєsingleЋЇ moment.вАЭ"
  34,31,"The disbelievers vow, вАЬWe will never believe in this Quran, nor in those ЋєScripturesЋЇ before it.вАЭ If only you could see when the wrongdoers will be detained before their Lord, throwing blame at each other! The lowly ЋєfollowersЋЇ will say to the arrogant ЋєleadersЋЇ, вАЬHad it not been for you, we would certainly have been believers.вАЭ"
  34,32,"The arrogant will respond to the lowly, вАЬDid we ever hinder you from guidance after it came to you? In fact, you were wicked Ћєon your ownЋЇ.вАЭ"
  34,33,"The lowly will say to the arrogant, вАЬNo! It was your plotting by day and nightвАФwhen you ordered us to disbelieve in Allah and to set up equals with Him.вАЭ They will ЋєallЋЇ hide ЋєtheirЋЇ remorse when they see the torment. And We will put shackles around the necks of the disbelievers. Will they be rewarded except for what they used to do"
  34,34,"Whenever We sent a warner to a society, its elite would say, вАЬWe truly reject what you have been sent with.вАЭ"
  34,35,"Adding, вАЬWe are far superior Ћєto the believersЋЇ in wealth and children, and we will never be punished.вАЭ"
  34,36,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬSurely Ћєit isЋЇ my Lord ЋєWhoЋЇ gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills. But most people do not know.вАЭ"
  34,37,"It is not your wealth or children that bring you closer to Us. But those who believe and do goodвАФit is they who will have a multiplied reward for what they did, and they will be secure in ЋєelevatedЋЇ mansions"
  34,38,"As for those who strive to discredit Our revelations, it is they who will be confined in punishment"
  34,39,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬSurely Ћєit isЋЇ my Lord ЋєWhoЋЇ gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. And whatever you spend in charity, He will compensate ЋєyouЋЇ for it. For He is the Best Provider.вАЭ"
  34,40,"And ЋєconsiderЋЇ the Day He will gather them all together, and then ask the angels, вАЬWas it you that these ЋєpolytheistsЋЇ used to worship?вАЭ"
  34,41,"They will say, вАЬGlory be to You! Our loyalty is to You, not them. In fact, they ЋєonlyЋЇ followed the Ћєtemptations of evilЋЇ jinn,¬†in whom most of them had faith.вАЭ"
  34,42,"So Today neither of you can benefit or protect each other. And We will say to the wrongdoers, вАЬTaste the torment of the Fire, which you used to deny.вАЭ"
  34,43,"When Our clear revelations are recited to them, they say, вАЬThis is only a man who wishes to hinder you from what your forefathers used to worship.вАЭ They also say, вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ is no more than a fabricated lie.вАЭ And the disbelievers say of the truth when it has come to them, вАЬThis is nothing but pure magic.вАЭ"
  34,44,"ЋєThey say so even thoughЋЇ We had never given them any scriptures to study, nor did We ever send them a warner before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ"
  34,45,"Those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them denied as wellвАФand these ЋєMeccansЋЇ have not attained even one-tenth of what We had given their predecessors.¬†Yet ЋєwhenЋЇ they denied My messengers, how severe was My response"
  34,46,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI advise you to do ЋєonlyЋЇ one thing: stand up for Ћєthe sake ofЋЇ AllahвАФindividually or in pairsвАФthen reflect. Your fellow man¬†is not insane. He is only a warner to you before Ћєthe coming ofЋЇ a severe punishment.вАЭ"
  34,47,"Say, вАЬIf I had ever asked you for a reward, you could keep it. My reward is only from Allah. And He is a Witness over all things.вАЭ"
  34,48,"Say, вАЬSurely my Lord hurls the truth Ћєagainst falsehoodЋЇ. ЋєHe isЋЇ the Knower of all unseen.вАЭ"
  34,49,"Say, вАЬThe truth has come, and falsehood will vanish, never to return.вАЭ"
  34,50,"Say, вАЬIf I am astray, the loss is only mine. And if I am guided, it is ЋєonlyЋЇ because of what my Lord reveals to me. He is indeed All-Hearing, Ever Near.вАЭ"
  34,51,If only you could see when they will be horrified with no escape Ћєon Judgment DayЋЇ! And they will be seized from a nearby place
  34,52,"They will ЋєthenЋЇ cry, вАЬWe do ЋєnowЋЇ believe in it ЋєallЋЇ.вАЭ But how could they ЋєpossiblyЋЇ attain faith from a place so far-off Ћєfrom the worldЋЇ"
  34,53,"while they had already rejected it before, guessing blindly from a place ЋєequallyЋЇ far-away Ћєfrom the HereafterЋЇ"
  34,54,"They will be sealed off from whatever they desire, as was done to their counterparts before. Indeed, they were ЋєallЋЇ in alarming doubt"
  35,1,"All praise is for Allah, the Originator of the heavens and the earth, Who made angels Ћєas HisЋЇ messengers with wingsвАФtwo, three, or four. He increases in creation whatever He wills. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  35,2,"Whatever mercy Allah opens up for people, none can withhold it. And whatever He withholds, none but Him can release it. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  35,3,O humanity! Remember AllahвАЩs favours upon you. Is there any creator other than Allah who provides for you from the heavens and the earth? There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. How can you then be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ
  35,4,"If you are rejected by them, so too were messengers before you. And to Allah ЋєallЋЇ matters will be returned Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ"
  35,5,"O humanity! Indeed, AllahвАЩs promise is true. So do not let the life of this world deceive you, nor let the Chief Deceiver¬†deceive you about Allah"
  35,6,"Surely Satan is an enemy to you, so take him as an enemy. He only invites his followers to become inmates of the Blaze"
  35,7,Those who disbelieve will have a severe punishment. But those who believe and do good will have forgiveness and a great reward
  35,8,"Are those whose evil-doing is made so appealing to them that they deem it good Ћєlike those who are rightly guidedЋЇ? ЋєIt isЋЇ certainly Allah ЋєWhoЋЇ leaves to stray whoever He wills, and guides whoever He wills. So do not grieve yourself to death over them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Surely Allah is All-Knowing of what they do"
  35,9,"And it is Allah Who sends the winds, which then stir up Ћєvapour, formingЋЇ clouds, and then We drive them to a lifeless land, giving life to the earth after its death. Similar is the Resurrection"
  35,10,"Whoever seeks honour and power, then Ћєlet them know thatЋЇ all honour and power belongs to Allah. To Him ЋєaloneЋЇ good words ascend, and righteous deeds are raised up by Him. As for those who plot evil, they will suffer a severe punishment. And the plotting of such ЋєpeopleЋЇ is doomed Ћєto failЋЇ"
  35,11,"And Ћєit isЋЇ Allah ЋєWhoЋЇ created you from dust,¬†then Ћєdeveloped youЋЇ from a sperm-drop, then made you into pairs.¬†No female ever conceives or delivers without His knowledge. And no oneвАЩs life is made long or cut short but is ЋєwrittenЋЇ in a Record.¬†That is certainly easy for Allah"
  35,12,"The two bodies of water are not alike: one is fresh, palatable, and pleasant to drink and the other is salty and bitter. Yet from them both you eat tender seafood and extract ornaments to wear. And you see the ships ploughing their way through both, so you may seek His bounty and give thanks Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  35,13,"He merges the night into the day and the day into the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. That is AllahвАФyour Lord! All authority belongs to Him. But those ЋєidolsЋЇ you invoke besides Him do not possess even the skin of a date stone"
  35,14,"If you call upon them, they cannot hear your calls. And if they were to hear, they could not respond to you. On the Day of Judgment they will disown your worship Ћєof themЋЇ. And no one can inform you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ like the All-Knowledgeable"
  35,15,"O humanity! It is you who stand in need of Allah, but Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  35,16,"If He willed, He could eliminate you and produce a new creation"
  35,17,And that is not difficult for Allah Ћєat allЋЇ
  35,18,"No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. And if a sin-burdened soul cries for help with its burden, none of it will be carriedвАФeven by a close relative. You ЋєO ProphetЋЇ can only warn those who stand in awe of their Lord without seeing Him¬†and establish prayer. Whoever purifies themselves, they only do so for their own good. And to Allah is the final return"
  35,19,Those blind Ћєto the truthЋЇ and those who can see are not equal
  35,20,nor are the darkness and the light
  35,21,nor the ЋєscorchingЋЇ heat and the ЋєcoolЋЇ shade
  35,22,"Nor are the dead and the living equal. Indeed, Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ makes whoever He wills hear, but you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ can never make those in the graves hear Ћєyour callЋЇ"
  35,23,You are only a warner
  35,24,We have surely sent you with the truth as a deliverer of good news and a warner. There is no community that has not had a warner
  35,25,"If they deny you, so did those before them. Their messengers came to them with clear proofs, divine Books, and enlightening Scriptures"
  35,26,Then I seized those who persisted in disbelief. How severe was My response
  35,27,"Do you not see that Allah sends down rain from the sky with which We bring forth fruits of different colours? And in the mountains are streaks of varying shades of white, red, and raven black"
  35,28,"just as people, living beings, and cattle are of various colours as well. Of all of AllahвАЩs servants, only the knowledgeable Ћєof His mightЋЇ are ЋєtrulyЋЇ in awe of Him. Allah is indeed Almighty, All-Forgiving"
  35,29,"Surely those who recite the Book of Allah, establish prayer, and donate from what We have provided for themвАФsecretly and openlyвАФЋєcanЋЇ hope for an exchange that will never fail"
  35,30,"so that He will reward them in full and increase them out of His grace. He is truly All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  35,31,"The Book We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ is the truth, confirming what came before it.¬†Surely Allah is All-Aware, All-Seeing of His servants"
  35,32,"Then We granted the Book to those We have chosen from Our servants. Some of them wrong themselves, some follow a middle course, and some are foremost in good deeds by AllahвАЩs Will. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the greatest bounty"
  35,33,"They will enter the Gardens of Eternity, where they will be adorned with bracelets of gold and pearls, and their clothing will be silk"
  35,34,"And they will say, вАЬPraise be to Allah, Who has kept away from us all Ћєcauses ofЋЇ sorrow. Our Lord is indeed All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  35,35,"ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ WhoвАФout of His graceвАФhas settled us in the Home of Everlasting Stay, where we will be touched by neither fatigue nor weariness.вАЭ"
  35,36,"As for the disbelievers, they will have the Fire of Hell, where they will not be Ћєallowed to beЋЇ finished by death, nor will its torment be lightened for them. This is how We reward every ЋєstubbornЋЇ disbeliever"
  35,37,"There they will be ЋєferventlyЋЇ screaming, вАЬOur Lord! Take us out Ћєand send us backЋЇ. We will do good, unlike what we used to do.вАЭ ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬDid We not give you lives long enough so that whoever wanted to be mindful could have done so? And the warner came to you. So taste Ћєthe punishmentЋЇ, for the wrongdoers have no helper.вАЭ"
  35,38,"Indeed, Allah is the Knower of the unseen of the heavens and the earth. He surely knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  35,39,"He is the One Who has placed you as successors on earth. So whoever disbelieves will bear Ћєthe burden ofЋЇ their own disbelief. The disbelieversвАЩ denial only increases them in contempt in the sight of their Lord, and it will only contribute to their loss"
  35,40,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬHave you considered your associate-gods which you invoke besides Allah? Show me what they have created on earth! Or do they have a share in Ћєthe creation ofЋЇ the heavens? Or have We given the polytheists a Book, which serves as a clear proof for them? In fact, the wrongdoers promise each other nothing but delusion.вАЭ"
  35,41,"Indeed, Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ keeps the heavens and the earth from falling apart. If they were to fall apart, none but Him could hold them up. He is truly Most Forbearing, All-Forgiving"
  35,42,"They swore by Allah their most solemn oaths that if a warner were to come to them, they would certainly be better guided than any other community. Yet when a warner did come to them, it only drove them farther awayвАФ"
  35,43,"behaving arrogantly in the land and plotting evil. But evil plotting only backfires on those who plot. Are they awaiting anything but the fate of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before? You will find no change in the way of Allah, nor will you find it diverted Ћєto someone elseЋЇ"
  35,44,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them? They were far superior in might. But there is nothing that can escape Allah in the heavens or the earth. He is certainly All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  35,45,"If Allah were to punish people ЋєimmediatelyЋЇ for what they have committed, He would not have left a single living being on earth. But He delays them for an appointed term. And when their time arrives, then surely Allah is All-Seeing of His servants"
  36,1,Y√Ґ-Sƒ©n
  36,2,"By the Quran, rich in wisdom"
  36,3,You ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are truly one of the messengers
  36,4,upon the Straight Path
  36,5,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a revelation from the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  36,6,"so that you may warn a people whose forefathers were not warned, and so are heedless"
  36,7,"The decree Ћєof tormentЋЇ has already been justified against most of them, for they will never believe"
  36,8,"ЋєIt is as ifЋЇ We have put shackles around their necks up to their chins, so their heads are forced up"
  36,9,"and have placed a barrier before them and a barrier behind them and covered them ЋєallЋЇ up, so they fail to see Ћєthe truthЋЇ"
  36,10,It is the same whether you warn them or notвАФthey will never believe
  36,11,You can only warn those who follow the Reminder¬†and are in awe of the Most Compassionate without seeing Him.¬†So give them good news of forgiveness and an honourable reward
  36,12,"It is certainly We Who resurrect the dead, and write what they send forth and what they leave behind. Everything is listed by Us in a perfect Record"
  36,13,"Give them an example ЋєO ProphetЋЇ of the residents of a town, when the messengers came to them"
  36,14,"We sent them two messengers, but they rejected both. So We reinforced Ћєthe twoЋЇ with a third, and they declared, вАЬWe have indeed been sent to you Ћєas messengersЋЇ.вАЭ"
  36,15,"The people replied, вАЬYou are only humans like us, and the Most Compassionate has not revealed anything. You are simply lying!вАЭ"
  36,16,"The messengers responded, вАЬOur Lord knows that we have truly been sent to you"
  36,17,And our duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ clearly.вАЭ
  36,18,"The people replied, вАЬWe definitely see you as a bad omen for us. If you do not desist, we will certainly stone you Ћєto deathЋЇ and you will be touched with a painful punishment from us.вАЭ"
  36,19,"The messengers said, вАЬYour bad omen lies within yourselves. Are you saying this because you are reminded Ћєof the truthЋЇ? In fact, you are a transgressing people.вАЭ"
  36,20,"Then from the farthest end of the city a man came, rushing. He advised, вАЬO my people! Follow the messengers"
  36,21,"Follow those who ask no reward of you, and are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"
  36,22,"And why should I not worship the One Who has originated me, and to Whom you will be returned"
  36,23,"How could I take besides Him other gods whose intercession would not be of any benefit to me, nor could they save me if the Most Compassionate intended to harm me"
  36,24,"Indeed, I would then be clearly astray"
  36,25,"I do believe in your Lord, so listen to me.вАЭ"
  36,26,"ЋєBut they killed him, thenЋЇ he was told Ћєby the angelsЋЇ, вАЬEnter Paradise!вАЭ He said, вАЬIf only my people knew"
  36,27,"of how my Lord has forgiven me, and made me one of the honourable.вАЭ"
  36,28,"We did not send any soldiers from the heavens against his people after his death, nor did We need to"
  36,29,"All it took was one ЋєmightyЋЇ blast, and they were extinguished at once"
  36,30,"Oh pity, such beings! No messenger ever came to them without being mocked"
  36,31,Have the deniers not considered how many peoples We destroyed before them who never came back to life again
  36,32,Yet they will all be brought before Us
  36,33,"There is a sign for them in the dead earth: We give it life, producing grain from it for them to eat"
  36,34,"And We have placed in it gardens of palm trees and grapevines, and caused springs to gush forth in it"
  36,35,"so that they may eat from its fruit, which they had no hand in making. Will they not then give thanks"
  36,36,"Glory be to the One Who created all Ћєthings inЋЇ pairsвАФЋєbe itЋЇ what the earth produces, their genders, or what they do not know"
  36,37,"There is also a sign for them in the night: We strip from it daylight, thenвАФbehold!вАФthey are in darkness"
  36,38,"The sun travels for its fixed term. That is the design of the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  36,39,"As for the moon, We have ordained ЋєpreciseЋЇ phases for it, until it ends up like an old, curved palm stalk"
  36,40,"It is not for the sun to catch up with the moon,¬†nor does the night outrun the day. Each is travelling in an orbit of their own"
  36,41,Another sign for them is that We carried their ancestors Ћєwith NoahЋЇ in the fully loaded Ark
  36,42,and created for them similar things to ride in
  36,43,"If We willed, We could drown them: then no one would respond to their cries, nor would they be rescuedвАФ"
  36,44,"except by mercy from Us, allowing them enjoyment for a ЋєlittleЋЇ while"
  36,45,"ЋєStill they turn awayЋЇ when it is said to them, вАЬBeware of what is ahead of you Ћєin the HereafterЋЇ and what is behind you Ћєof destroyed nationsЋЇ so you may be shown mercy.вАЭ"
  36,46,"Whenever a sign comes to them from their Lord, they turn away from it"
  36,47,"And when it is said to them, вАЬDonate from what Allah has provided for you,вАЭ the disbelievers say to the believers, вАЬWhy should we feed those whom Allah could have fed if He wanted to? You are clearly astray!вАЭ"
  36,48,"And they ask Ћєthe believersЋЇ, вАЬWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  36,49,"They must be awaiting a single Blast,¬†which will seize them while they are ЋєentrenchedЋЇ in ЋєworldlyЋЇ disputes"
  36,50,"Then they will not be able to make a ЋєlastЋЇ will, nor can they return to their own people"
  36,51,"The Trumpet will be blown Ћєa second timeЋЇ, thenвАФbehold!вАФthey will rush from the graves to their Lord"
  36,52,"They will cry, вАЬWoe to us! Who has raised us up from our place of rest? This must be what the Most Compassionate warned us of; the messengers told the truth!вАЭ"
  36,53,"It will only take one Blast, then at once they will all be brought before Us"
  36,54,"On that Day no soul will be wronged in the least, nor will you be rewarded except for what you used to do"
  36,55,"Indeed, on that Day the residents of Paradise will be busy enjoying themselves"
  36,56,"They and their spouses will be in ЋєcoolЋЇ shade, reclining on ЋєcanopiedЋЇ couches"
  36,57,There they will have fruits and whatever they desire
  36,58,And вАЬPeace!вАЭ will be ЋєtheirЋЇ greeting from the Merciful Lord
  36,59,"ЋєThen the disbelievers will be told,ЋЇ вАЬStep away Ћєfrom the believersЋЇ this Day, O wicked ones"
  36,60,"Did I not command you, O Children of Adam, not to follow Satan, for he is truly your sworn enemy"
  36,61,but to worship Me ЋєaloneЋЇ? This is the Straight Path
  36,62,Yet he already misled great multitudes of you. Did you not have any sense
  36,63,This is the Hell you were warned of
  36,64,Burn in it Today for your disbelief.вАЭ
  36,65,"On this Day We will seal their mouths, their hands will speak to Us, and their feet will testify to what they used to commit"
  36,66,"Had We willed, We could have easily blinded their eyes, so they would struggle to find their way. How then could they see"
  36,67,"And had We willed, We could have transfigured them on the spot,¬†so they could neither progress forward nor turn back"
  36,68,"And whoever We grant a long life, We reverse them in development.¬†Will they not then understand"
  36,69,"We have not taught him poetry, nor is it fitting for him. This ЋєBookЋЇ is only a Reminder and a clear Quran"
  36,70,to warn whoever is ЋєtrulyЋЇ alive and fulfil the decree Ћєof tormentЋЇ against the disbelievers
  36,71,"Do they not see that We singlehandedly¬†created for them, among other things, cattle which are under their control"
  36,72,"And We have subjected these ЋєanimalsЋЇ to them, so they may ride some and eat others"
  36,73,And they derive from them other benefits and drinks. Will they not then give thanks
  36,74,"Still they have taken other gods besides Allah, hoping to be helped Ћєby themЋЇ"
  36,75,"They cannot help the pagans, even though they serve the idols as dedicated guards"
  36,76,"So do not let their words grieve you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Indeed, We ЋєfullyЋЇ know what they conceal and what they reveal"
  36,77,"Do people not see that We have created them from a sperm-drop, thenвАФbehold!вАФthey openly challenge ЋєUsЋЇ"
  36,78,"And they argue with UsвАФforgetting they were createdвАФsaying, вАЬWho will give life to decayed bones?вАЭ"
  36,79,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬThey will be revived by the One Who produced them the first time, for He has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of every created being"
  36,80,"ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who gives you fire from green trees, andвАФbehold!вАФyou kindle ЋєfireЋЇ from them"
  36,81,"Can the One Who created the heavens and the earth not ЋєeasilyЋЇ resurrect these ЋєdeniersЋЇ?вАЭ Yes ЋєHe canЋЇ! For He is the Master Creator, All-Knowing"
  36,82,"All it takes, when He wills something Ћєto beЋЇ, is simply to say to it: вАЬBe!вАЭ And it is"
  36,83,"So glory be to the One in Whose Hands is the authority over all things, and to Whom ЋєaloneЋЇ you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  37,1,By those ЋєangelsЋЇ lined up in ranks
  37,2,and those who diligently drive Ћєthe cloudsЋЇ
  37,3,and those who recite the Reminder
  37,4,Surely your God is One
  37,5,"ЋєHe isЋЇ the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, and the Lord of all points of sunrise"
  37,6,"Indeed, We have adorned the lowest heaven with the stars for decoration"
  37,7,and ЋєforЋЇ protection from every rebellious devil
  37,8,They cannot listen to the highest assembly Ћєof angelsЋЇ for they are pelted from every side
  37,9,ЋєfiercelyЋЇ driven away. And they will suffer an everlasting torment
  37,10,But whoever manages to stealthily eavesdrop is ЋєinstantlyЋЇ pursued by a piercing flare
  37,11,"So ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, which is harder to create: them or other marvels of Our creation?¬†Indeed, We created them from a sticky clay"
  37,12,"In fact, you are astonished Ћєby their denialЋЇ, while they ridicule ЋєyouЋЇ"
  37,13,"When they are reminded, they are never mindful"
  37,14,"And whenever they see a sign, they make fun of it"
  37,15,"saying, вАЬThis is nothing but pure magic"
  37,16,"When we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be resurrected"
  37,17,And our forefathers as well?вАЭ
  37,18,"Say, вАЬYes! And you will be fully humbled.вАЭ"
  37,19,"It will only take one Blast,¬†then at once they will see Ћєit allЋЇ"
  37,20,"They will cry, вАЬOh, woe to us! This is the Day of Judgment!вАЭ"
  37,21,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬThis is the Day of ЋєFinalЋЇ Decision which you used to deny.вАЭ"
  37,22,"ЋєAllah will say to the angels,ЋЇ вАЬGather ЋєallЋЇ the wrongdoers along with their peers, and whatever they used to worship"
  37,23,"instead of Allah, then lead them ЋєallЋЇ to the path of Hell"
  37,24,"And detain them, for they must be questioned.вАЭ"
  37,25,"ЋєThen they will be asked,ЋЇ вАЬWhat is the matter with you that you can no longer help each other?вАЭ"
  37,26,"In fact, on that Day they will be ЋєfullyЋЇ submissive"
  37,27,"They will turn on each other, throwing blame"
  37,28,"The misled will say, вАЬIt was you who deluded us away from what is right.вАЭ"
  37,29,"The misleaders will reply, вАЬNo! You disbelieved on your own"
  37,30,"We had no authority over you. In fact, you yourselves were a transgressing people"
  37,31,"The decree of our Lord has come to pass against us ЋєallЋЇ: we will certainly taste Ћєthe punishmentЋЇ"
  37,32,"We caused you to deviate, for we ourselves were deviant.вАЭ"
  37,33,Surely on that Day they will ЋєallЋЇ share in the punishment
  37,34,That is certainly how We deal with the wicked
  37,35,"For whenever it was said to them Ћєin the worldЋЇ, вАЬThere is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Allah,вАЭ they acted arrogantly"
  37,36,"and argued, вАЬShould we really abandon our gods for a mad poet?вАЭ"
  37,37,"In fact, he came with the truth, confirming ЋєearlierЋЇ messengers"
  37,38,You will certainly taste the painful torment
  37,39,and will only be rewarded for what you used to do
  37,40,But not the chosen servants of Allah
  37,41,They will have a known provision
  37,42,fruits Ћєof every typeЋЇ.¬†And they will be honoured
  37,43,in the Gardens of Bliss
  37,44,facing each other on thrones
  37,45,A drink Ћєof pure wineЋЇ will be passed around to them from a flowing stream
  37,46,"crystal-white, delicious to drink"
  37,47,"It will neither harm ЋєthemЋЇ, nor will they be intoxicated by it"
  37,48,And with them will be maidens of modest gaze and gorgeous eyes
  37,49,as if they were pristine pearls
  37,50,Then they will turn to one another inquisitively
  37,51,"One of them will say, вАЬI once had a companion Ћєin the worldЋЇ"
  37,52,"who used to ask ЋєmeЋЇ, вАШDo you actually believe Ћєin resurrectionЋЇ"
  37,53,"When we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be brought to judgment?вАЩвАЭ"
  37,54,"He will ЋєthenЋЇ ask, вАЬWould you care to see Ћєhis fateЋЇ?вАЭ"
  37,55,Then he Ћєand the othersЋЇ will look and spot him in the midst of the Hellfire
  37,56,"He will ЋєthenЋЇ say, вАЬBy Allah! You nearly ruined me"
  37,57,"Had it not been for the grace of my Lord, I ЋєtooЋЇ would have certainly been among those brought Ћєto HellЋЇ.вАЭ"
  37,58,"ЋєThen he will ask his fellow believers,ЋЇ вАЬCan you imagine that we will never die"
  37,59,"except our first death, nor be punished Ћєlike the othersЋЇ?вАЭ"
  37,60,This is truly the ultimate triumph
  37,61,For such ЋєhonourЋЇ all should strive
  37,62,Is this ЋєblissЋЇ a better accommodation or the tree of Zaqq√їm
  37,63,We have surely made it a test for the wrongdoers
  37,64,"Indeed, it is a tree that grows in the depths of Hell"
  37,65,bearing fruit like devilsвАЩ heads
  37,66,"The evildoers will certainly Ћєbe left toЋЇ eat from it, filling up their bellies with it"
  37,67,Then on top of that they will be given a blend of boiling drink
  37,68,Then they will ultimately return to Ћєtheir place inЋЇ Hell
  37,69,"Indeed, they found their forefathers astray"
  37,70,so they rushed in their footsteps
  37,71,And surely most of the earlier generations had strayed before them
  37,72,although We had certainly sent warners among them
  37,73,See then what was the end of those who had been warned
  37,74,But not the chosen servants of Allah
  37,75,"Indeed, Noah cried out to Us, and how excellent are We in responding"
  37,76,We delivered him and his family¬†from the great distress
  37,77,and made his descendants the sole survivors
  37,78,And We blessed him Ћєwith honourable mentionЋЇ among later generations
  37,79,вАЬPeace be upon Noah among all peoples.вАЭ
  37,80,"Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,81,ЋєForЋЇ he was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,82,Then We drowned the others
  37,83,"And indeed, one of those who followed his way was Abraham"
  37,84,ЋєRememberЋЇ when he came to his Lord with a pure heart
  37,85,"and said to his father and his people, вАЬWhat are you worshipping"
  37,86,Is it false gods that you desire instead of Allah
  37,87,What then do you expect from the Lord of all worlds?вАЭ
  37,88,He later looked up to the stars Ћєin contemplationЋЇ
  37,89,"then said, вАЬI am really sick.вАЭ"
  37,90,So they turned their backs on him and went away
  37,91,"Then he ЋєstealthilyЋЇ advanced towards their gods, and said ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWill you not eat Ћєyour offeringsЋЇ"
  37,92,What is wrong with you that you cannot speak?вАЭ
  37,93,"Then he swiftly turned on them, striking ЋєthemЋЇ with his right hand"
  37,94,"Later, his people came rushing towards him ЋєfuriouslyЋЇ"
  37,95,"He argued, вАЬHow can you worship what you carve Ћєwith your own handsЋЇ"
  37,96,when it is Allah Who created you and whatever you do?вАЭ
  37,97,"They said Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬBuild him a furnace and cast him into the blazing fire.вАЭ"
  37,98,"And so they sought to harm him, but We made them inferior"
  37,99,"He later said, вАЬI am leaving Ћєin obedienceЋЇ to my Lord. He will guide me"
  37,100,My Lord! Bless me with righteous offspring.вАЭ
  37,101,So We gave him good news of a forbearing son
  37,102,"Then when the boy reached the age to work with him, Abraham said, вАЬO my dear son! I have seen in a dream that I ЋєmustЋЇ sacrifice you. So tell me what you think.вАЭ He replied, вАЬO my dear father! Do as you are commanded. Allah willing, you will find me steadfast.вАЭ"
  37,103,"Then when they submitted Ћєto AllahвАЩs WillЋЇ, and Abraham laid him on the side of his forehead Ћєfor sacrificeЋЇ"
  37,104,"We called out to him, вАЬO Abraham"
  37,105,"You have already fulfilled the vision.вАЭ Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,106,That was truly a revealing test
  37,107,And We ransomed his son with a great sacrifice
  37,108,and blessed Abraham Ћєwith honourable mentionЋЇ among later generations
  37,109,вАЬPeace be upon Abraham.вАЭ
  37,110,This is how We reward the good-doers
  37,111,He was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,112,"We ЋєlaterЋЇ gave him good news of IsaacвАФa prophet, and one of the righteous"
  37,113,"We blessed him¬†and Isaac as well. Some of their descendants did good, while others clearly wronged themselves"
  37,114,And We certainly showed favour to Moses and Aaron
  37,115,and delivered them and their people from the great distress
  37,116,We helped them so it was they who prevailed
  37,117,We gave them the clear Scripture
  37,118,and guided them to the Straight Path
  37,119,And We blessed them Ћєwith honourable mentionЋЇ among later generations
  37,120,вАЬPeace be upon Moses and Aaron.вАЭ
  37,121,"Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,122,They were truly ЋєtwoЋЇ of Our faithful servants
  37,123,And Elias was indeed one of the messengers
  37,124,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when he said to his people, вАЬWill you not fear ЋєAllahЋЇ"
  37,125,Do you call upon Ћєthe idol ofЋЇ BaвАЩl¬†and abandon the Best of CreatorsвАФ
  37,126,"Allah, your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers?вАЭ"
  37,127,"But they rejected him, so they will certainly be brought Ћєfor punishmentЋЇ"
  37,128,But not the chosen servants of Allah
  37,129,We blessed him Ћєwith honourable mentionЋЇ among later generations
  37,130,вАЬPeace be upon Elias.вАЭ
  37,131,"Indeed, this is how We reward the good-doers"
  37,132,He was truly one of Our faithful servants
  37,133,And Lot was indeed one of the messengers
  37,134,ЋєRememberЋЇ when We delivered him and all of his family
  37,135,"except an old woman,¬†who was one of the doomed"
  37,136,Then We ЋєutterlyЋЇ destroyed the rest
  37,137,You ЋєMeccansЋЇ certainly pass by their ruins day
  37,138,and night. Will you not then understand
  37,139,And Jonah was indeed one of the messengers
  37,140,ЋєRememberЋЇ when he fled to the overloaded ship
  37,141,"Then Ћєto save it from sinking,ЋЇ he drew straws Ћєwith other passengersЋЇ. He lost Ћєand was thrown overboardЋЇ"
  37,142,Then the whale engulfed him while he was blameworthy
  37,143,Had he not ЋєconstantlyЋЇ glorified ЋєAllahЋЇ
  37,144,he would have certainly remained in its belly until the Day of Resurrection
  37,145,"But We cast him onto the open ЋєshoreЋЇ, ЋєtotallyЋЇ worn out"
  37,146,and caused a squash plant to grow over him
  37,147,We ЋєlaterЋЇ sent him ЋєbackЋЇ to Ћєhis city ofЋЇ at least one hundred thousand people
  37,148,"who then believed Ћєin himЋЇ, so We allowed them enjoyment for a while"
  37,149,"Ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ if your Lord has daughters,¬†while the pagans Ћєprefer toЋЇ have sons"
  37,150,Or Ћєask themЋЇ if We created the angels as females right before their eyes
  37,151,"Indeed, it is one of their ЋєoutrageousЋЇ fabrications to say"
  37,152,вАЬAllah has children.вАЭ They are simply liars
  37,153,Has He chosen daughters over sons
  37,154,What is the matter with you? How do you judge
  37,155,Will you not then be mindful
  37,156,Or do you have ЋєanyЋЇ compelling proof
  37,157,"Then bring ЋєusЋЇ your scripture, if what you say is true"
  37,158,They have also established a ЋєmaritalЋЇ relationship between Him and the jinn. Yet the jinn ЋєthemselvesЋЇ know well that such people will certainly be brought Ћєfor punishmentЋЇ
  37,159,Glorified is Allah far above what they claim
  37,160,But not the chosen servants of Allah
  37,161,Surely you ЋєpagansЋЇ and whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you worship
  37,162,can never lure ЋєanyoneЋЇ away from Him
  37,163,except those ЋєdestinedЋЇ to burn in Hell
  37,164,"ЋєThe angels respond,ЋЇ вАЬThere is not one of us without an assigned station Ћєof worshipЋЇ"
  37,165,We are indeed the ones lined up in ranks Ћєfor AllahЋЇ
  37,166,And we are indeed the ones ЋєconstantlyЋЇ glorifying ЋєHis praiseЋЇ.вАЭ
  37,167,They certainly used to say
  37,168,вАЬIf only we had a Reminder like Ћєthose ofЋЇ earlier peoples
  37,169,we would have truly been AllahвАЩs devoted servants.вАЭ
  37,170,"But ЋєnowЋЇ they reject it, so they will soon know"
  37,171,"Our Word has already gone forth to Our servants, the messengers"
  37,172,that they would surely be helped
  37,173,and that Our forces will certainly prevail
  37,174,So turn away from the deniers for a while ЋєO ProphetЋЇ
  37,175,"You will see Ћєwhat will happen toЋЇ them, and they too will see"
  37,176,Do they ЋєreallyЋЇ wish to hasten Our punishment
  37,177,"Yet when it descends upon them:¬†how evil will that morning be for those who had been warned"
  37,178,And turn away from them for a while
  37,179,"You will see, and they too will see"
  37,180,Glorified is your LordвАФthe Lord of Honour and PowerвАФabove what they claim
  37,181,Peace be upon the messengers
  37,182,And praise be to AllahвАФLord of all worlds
  38,1,"бєҐ√£d. By the Quran, full of reminders"
  38,2,"ЋєThis is the truth,ЋЇ yet the disbelievers are ЋєentrenchedЋЇ in arrogance and opposition"
  38,3,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many peoples We destroyed before them, and they cried out when it was too late to escape"
  38,4,"Now, the pagans are astonished that a warner has come to them from among themselves.¬†And the disbelievers say, вАЬThis is a magician, a total liar"
  38,5,"Has he reduced ЋєallЋЇ the gods to One God? Indeed, this is something totally astonishing.вАЭ"
  38,6,"The chiefs among them went forth saying, вАЬCarry on, and stand firm in devotion to your gods. Certainly this is just a scheme Ћєfor powerЋЇ"
  38,7,We have never heard of this in the previous faith.¬†This is nothing but a fabrication
  38,8,"Has the Reminder been revealed ЋєonlyЋЇ to him out of Ћєall ofЋЇ us?вАЭ In fact, they are ЋєonlyЋЇ in doubt of My ЋєrevealedЋЇ Reminder.¬†In fact, Ћєthey do so becauseЋЇ they have not yet tasted My punishment"
  38,9,"Or Ћєis it becauseЋЇ they possess the treasuries of the mercy of your LordвАФthe Almighty, the Giver Ћєof all bountiesЋЇ"
  38,10,"Or Ћєis it becauseЋЇ the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between belongs to them? Let them then climb their way Ћєto heaven, if their claim is trueЋЇ"
  38,11,This is just another ЋєenemyЋЇ force bound for defeat out there
  38,12,"Before them, the people of Noah denied Ћєthe truthЋЇ, as did вАЩ√Вd, Pharaoh of the mighty structures"
  38,13,"Tham√їd, the people of Lot, and the residents of the Forest.¬†These were ЋєallЋЇ enemy forces"
  38,14,"Each rejected their messenger, so My punishment was justified"
  38,15,These ЋєpagansЋЇ are awaiting nothing but a single Blast that cannot be stopped
  38,16,"They say ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬOur Lord! Hasten for us our share Ћєof the punishmentЋЇ before the Day of Reckoning.вАЭ"
  38,17,"Be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ with what they say. And remember Our servant, David, the man of strength. Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  38,18,We truly subjected the mountains to hymn ЋєOur praisesЋЇ along with him in the evening and after sunrise
  38,19,"And ЋєWe subjectedЋЇ the birds, flocking together. All turned to him Ћєechoing his hymnsЋЇ"
  38,20,"We strengthened his kingship, and gave him wisdom and sound judgment"
  38,21,"Has the story of the two plaintiffs, who scaled the Ћєwall of DavidвАЩsЋЇ sanctuary, reached you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ"
  38,22,"When they came into DavidвАЩs presence, he was startled by them. They said, вАЬHave no fear. ЋєWe are merelyЋЇ two in a dispute: one of us has wronged the other. So judge between us with truthвАФdo not go beyond ЋєitЋЇвАФand guide us to the right way"
  38,23,"This is my brother.¬†He has ninety-nine sheep while I have ЋєonlyЋЇ one. ЋєStillЋЇ he asked me to give it up to him, overwhelming me with ЋєhisЋЇ argument.вАЭ"
  38,24,"David ЋєeventuallyЋЇ ruled, вАЬHe has definitely wronged you in demanding Ћєto addЋЇ your sheep to his. And certainly many partners wrong each other, except those who believe and do goodвАФbut how few are they!вАЭ Then David realized that We had tested him so he asked for his LordвАЩs forgiveness, fell down in prostration, and turned Ћєto Him in repentanceЋЇ"
  38,25,So We forgave that for him. And he will indeed have Ћєa status ofЋЇ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,26,"ЋєWe instructed him:ЋЇ вАЬO David! We have surely made you an authority in the land, so judge between people with truth. And do not follow ЋєyourЋЇ desires or they will lead you astray from AllahвАЩs Way. Surely those who go astray from AllahвАЩs Way will suffer a severe punishment for neglecting the Day of Reckoning.вАЭ"
  38,27,We have not created the heavens and earth and everything in between without purposeвАФas the disbelievers think. So woe to the disbelievers because of the Fire
  38,28,Or should We treat those who believe and do good like those who make mischief throughout the land? Or should We treat the righteous like the wicked
  38,29,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a blessed Book which We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ so that they may contemplate its verses, and people of reason may be mindful"
  38,30,"And We blessed David with SolomonвАФwhat an excellent servant Ћєhe wasЋЇ! Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  38,31,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the well-trained, swift horses were paraded before him in the evening"
  38,32,"He then proclaimed, вАЬI am truly in love with ЋєtheseЋЇ fine things out of remembrance for Allah,вАЭ until they went out of sight"
  38,33,"ЋєHe ordered,ЋЇ вАЬBring them back to me!вАЭ Then he began to rub down their legs and necks"
  38,34,"And indeed, We tested Solomon, placing a ЋєdeformedЋЇ body on his throne,¬†then he turned Ћєto Allah in repentanceЋЇ"
  38,35,"He prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Forgive me, and grant me an authority that will never be matched by anyone after me. You are indeed the Giver Ћєof all bountiesЋЇ.вАЭ"
  38,36,"So We subjected to him the wind, blowing gently at his command to wherever he pleased"
  38,37,And ЋєWe subjected to himЋЇ every builder and diver¬†of the jinn
  38,38,and others bound together in chains
  38,39,"ЋєAllah said,ЋЇ вАЬThis is Our gift, so give or withhold Ћєas you wishЋЇ, never to be called to account.вАЭ"
  38,40,And he will indeed have Ћєa status ofЋЇ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,41,"And remember Our servant Job, when he cried out to his Lord, вАЬSatan has afflicted me with distress and suffering.вАЭ"
  38,42,"ЋєWe responded,ЋЇ вАЬStomp your foot: ЋєnowЋЇ here is a cool Ћєand refreshingЋЇ spring for washing and drinking.вАЭ"
  38,43,"And We gave him back his family, twice as many, as a mercy from Us and a lesson for people of reason"
  38,44,"ЋєAnd We said to him,ЋЇ вАЬTake in your hand a bundle of grass, and strike Ћєyour wifeЋЇ with it, and do not break your oath.вАЭ¬†We truly found him patient. What an excellent servant Ћєhe wasЋЇ! Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  38,45,"And remember Our servants: Abraham, Isaac, and JacobвАФthe men of strength and insight"
  38,46,We truly chose them for the honour of proclaiming the Hereafter
  38,47,And in Our sight they are truly among the chosen and the finest
  38,48,"Also remember Ishmael, Elisha, and в±Ђul-Kifl.¬†All are among the best"
  38,49,This is ЋєallЋЇ a reminder. And the righteous will certainly have an honourable destination
  38,50,"the Gardens of Eternity, whose gates will be open for them"
  38,51,"There they will recline, calling for abundant fruit and drink"
  38,52,And with them will be maidens of modest gaze and equal age
  38,53,This is what you are promised for the Day of Reckoning
  38,54,This is indeed Our provision that will never end
  38,55,That is that. And the transgressors will certainly have the worst destination
  38,56,"Hell, where they will burn. What an evil place to rest"
  38,57,"Let them then taste this: boiling water and ЋєoozingЋЇ pus"
  38,58,and other torments of the same sort
  38,59,"ЋєThe misleaders will say to one another,ЋЇ вАЬHere is a crowd Ћєof followersЋЇ being thrown in with us. They are not welcome, ЋєforЋЇ they ЋєtooЋЇ will burn in the Fire.вАЭ"
  38,60,"The followers will respond, вАЬNo! You are not welcome! You brought this upon us. What an evil place for settlement!вАЭ"
  38,61,"Adding, вАЬOur Lord! Whoever brought this upon us, double their punishment in the Fire.вАЭ"
  38,62,"The tyrants will ask Ћєone anotherЋЇ, вАЬBut why do we not see those we considered to be lowly"
  38,63,Were we wrong in mocking them Ћєin the worldЋЇ?¬†Or do our eyes ЋєjustЋЇ fail to see them Ћєin the FireЋЇ?вАЭ
  38,64,This dispute between the residents of the Fire will certainly come to pass
  38,65,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI am only a warner. And there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except AllahвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  38,66,"ЋєHe is theЋЇ Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in betweenвАФthe Almighty, Most Forgiving.вАЭ"
  38,67,"Say, вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ is momentous news"
  38,68,from which you ЋєpagansЋЇ are turning away.вАЭ
  38,69,"ЋєAnd say,ЋЇ вАЬI had no knowledge of the highest assembly Ћєin heavenЋЇ when they differed Ћєconcerning AdamЋЇ"
  38,70,What is revealed to me is that I am only sent with a clear warning.вАЭ
  38,71,"ЋєRemember, O ProphetЋЇ when your Lord said to the angels, вАЬI am going to create a human being from clay"
  38,72,"So when I have fashioned him and had a spirit of My Own ЋєcreationЋЇ breathed into him, fall down in prostration to him.вАЭ"
  38,73,So the angels prostrated all togetherвАФ
  38,74,"but not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who acted arrogantly,¬†becoming unfaithful"
  38,75,"Allah asked, вАЬO Ibl√Ѓs! What prevented you from prostrating to what I created with My Own Hands? Did you ЋєjustЋЇ become proud? Or have you always been arrogant?вАЭ"
  38,76,"He replied, вАЬI am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.вАЭ"
  38,77,"Allah commanded, вАЬThen get out of Paradise, for you are truly cursed"
  38,78,And surely upon you is My condemnation until the Day of Judgment.вАЭ
  38,79,"Satan appealed, вАЬMy Lord! Then delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.вАЭ"
  38,80,"Allah said, вАЬYou will be delayed"
  38,81,until the appointed Day.вАЭ
  38,82,"Satan said, вАЬBy Your Glory! I will certainly mislead them all"
  38,83,except Your chosen servants among them.вАЭ
  38,84,"Allah concluded, вАЬThe truth isвАФand I ЋєonlyЋЇ say the truthвАФ"
  38,85,"I will surely fill up Hell with you and whoever follows you from among them, all together.вАЭ"
  38,86,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєQuranЋЇ, nor do I pretend to be someone I am not"
  38,87,It is only a reminder to the whole world
  38,88,And you will certainly know its truth before long.вАЭ
  39,1,"The revelation of this Book is from AllahвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  39,2,"Indeed, We have sent down the Book to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in truth, so worship Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ, being sincerely devoted to Him"
  39,3,"Indeed, sincere devotion is due ЋєonlyЋЇ to Allah. As for those who take other lords besides Him, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬWe worship them only so they may bring us closer to Allah,вАЭ surely Allah will judge between all¬†regarding what they differed about. Allah certainly does not guide whoever persists in lying and disbelief"
  39,4,"Had it been AllahвАЩs Will to have offspring, He could have chosen whatever He willed of His creation. Glory be to Him! He is AllahвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. He wraps the night around the day, and wraps the day around the night. And He has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. He is truly the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  39,6,"He created you ЋєallЋЇ from a single soul,¬†then from it He made its mate.¬†And He produced for you four pairs of cattle.¬†He creates you in the wombs of your mothers Ћєin stagesЋЇ, one development after another, in three layers of darkness.¬†That is AllahвАФyour Lord! All authority belongs to Him. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. How can you then be turned away"
  39,7,"If you disbelieve, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ Allah is truly not in need of you, nor does He approve of disbelief from His servants. But if you become grateful Ћєthrough faithЋЇ, He will appreciate that from you. No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. Then to your Lord is your return, and He will inform you of what you used to do. He certainly knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  39,8,"When one is touched with hardship, they cry out to their Lord, turning to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. But as soon as He showers them with blessings from Him, they ЋєtotallyЋЇ forget the One they had cried to earlier, and set up equals to Allah to mislead ЋєothersЋЇ from His Way. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬEnjoy your disbelief for a little while! You will certainly be one of the inmates of the Fire.вАЭ"
  39,9,"ЋєAre they betterЋЇ or those who worship Ћєtheir LordЋЇ devoutly in the hours of the night, prostrating and standing, fearing the Hereafter and hoping for the mercy of their Lord? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAre those who know equal to those who do not know?вАЭ None will be mindful Ћєof thisЋЇ except people of reason"
  39,10,"Say ЋєO Prophet, that Allah saysЋЇ, вАЬO My servants who believe! Be mindful of your Lord. Those who do good in this world will have a good reward. And AllahвАЩs earth is spacious. Only those who endure patiently will be given their reward without limit.вАЭ"
  39,11,"Say, вАЬI am commanded to worship Allah, being sincerely devoted to Him ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  39,12,And I am commanded to be the first of those who submit Ћєto His WillЋЇ.вАЭ
  39,13,"Say, вАЬI truly fearвАФif I were to disobey my LordвАФthe torment of a tremendous Day.вАЭ"
  39,14,"Say, вАЬIt is ЋєonlyЋЇ Allah that I worship, being sincere in my devotion to Him"
  39,15,"Worship then whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ you want instead of Him.вАЭ Say, вАЬThe ЋєtrueЋЇ losers are those who will lose themselves and their families on Judgment Day. That is indeed the clearest loss.вАЭ"
  39,16,"They will have layers of fire above and below them. That is what Allah warns His servants with. So fear Me, O My servants"
  39,17,"And those who shun the worship of false gods, turning to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ, will have good news. So give good news to My servants ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФ"
  39,18,"those who listen to what is said and follow the best of it.¬†These are the ones ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided by Allah, and these are ЋєtrulyЋЇ the people of reason"
  39,19,What about those against whom the decree of torment has been justified? Is it you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who will then save those bound for the Fire
  39,20,"But those mindful of their Lord will have ЋєelevatedЋЇ mansions, built one above the other, under which rivers flow. ЋєThat isЋЇ the promise of Allah. ЋєAndЋЇ Allah never fails in ЋєHisЋЇ promise"
  39,21,"Do you not see that Allah sends down rain from the skyвАФchannelling it through streams in the earthвАФthen produces with it crops of various colours, then they dry up and you see them wither, and then He reduces them to chaff? Surely in this is a reminder for people of reason"
  39,22,"Can Ћєthe misguided be likeЋЇ those whose hearts Allah has opened to Islam, so they are enlightened by their Lord? So woe to those whose hearts are hardened at the remembrance of Allah! It is they who are clearly astray"
  39,23,"ЋєIt isЋЇ Allah ЋєWhoЋЇ has sent down the best messageвАФa Book of perfect consistency and repeated lessonsвАФwhich causes the skin Ћєand heartsЋЇ of those who fear their Lord to tremble, then their skin and hearts soften at the mention of Ћєthe mercy ofЋЇ Allah. That is the guidance of Allah, through which He guides whoever He wills. But whoever Allah leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  39,24,"Are those who will only have their ЋєbareЋЇ faces to shield themselves from the awful torment on Judgment Day Ћєbetter than those in ParadiseЋЇ? It will ЋєthenЋЇ be said to the wrongdoers: вАЬReap what you sowed!вАЭ"
  39,25,"Those before them ЋєalsoЋЇ rejected Ћєthe truthЋЇ, then the torment came upon them from where they least expected"
  39,26,"So Allah made them taste humiliation in this worldly life, but far worse is the punishment of the Hereafter, if only they knew"
  39,27,"We have certainly set forth every Ћєkind ofЋЇ lesson for people in this Quran, so perhaps they will be mindful"
  39,28,"ЋєIt isЋЇ a Quran ЋєrevealedЋЇ in Arabic without any crookedness, so perhaps they will be conscious Ћєof AllahЋЇ"
  39,29,"Allah sets forth the parable of a slave owned by several quarrelsome masters, and a slave owned by only one master. Are they equal in condition?¬†Praise be to Allah! In fact, most of them do not know"
  39,30,"You ЋєO ProphetЋЇ will certainly die, and they will die too"
  39,31,Then on the Day of Judgment you will Ћєall settle yourЋЇ dispute before your Lord
  39,32,Who then does more wrong than those who lie about Allah and reject the truth after it has reached them? Is Hell not a ЋєfittingЋЇ home for the disbelievers
  39,33,And the one who has brought the truth and those who embrace itвАФit is they who are the righteous
  39,34,They will have whatever they desire with their Lord. That is the reward of the good-doers
  39,35,"As such, Allah will absolve them of ЋєevenЋЇ the worst of what they did and reward them according to the best of what they used to do"
  39,36,Is Allah not sufficient for His servant? Yet they threaten you with other ЋєpowerlessЋЇ gods besides Him! Whoever Allah leaves to stray will be left with no guide
  39,37,"And whoever Allah guides, none can lead astray. Is Allah not Almighty, capable of punishment"
  39,38,"If you ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who created the heavens and the earth, they will certainly say, вАЬAllah!вАЭ Ask ЋєthemЋЇ, вАЬConsider then whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you invoke besides Allah: if it was AllahвАЩs Will to harm me, could they undo that harm? Or if He willed ЋєsomeЋЇ mercy for me, could they withhold His mercy?вАЭ Say, вАЬAllah is sufficient for me. In Him ЋєaloneЋЇ the faithful put their trust.вАЭ"
  39,39,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO my people! Persist in your ways, for I ЋєtooЋЇ will persist in mine. You will soon come to know"
  39,40,who will be visited by a humiliating torment Ћєin this lifeЋЇ and overwhelmed by an everlasting punishment Ћєin the nextЋЇ.вАЭ
  39,41,"Surely We have revealed to you the Book ЋєO ProphetЋЇ with the truth for humanity. So whoever chooses to be guided, it is for their own good. And whoever chooses to stray, it is only to their own loss. You are not a keeper over them"
  39,42,"ЋєIt isЋЇ Allah ЋєWhoЋЇ calls back the souls Ћєof peopleЋЇ upon their death as well as Ћєthe soulsЋЇ of the living during their sleep. Then He keeps those for whom He has ordained death, and releases the others until ЋєtheirЋЇ appointed time. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect"
  39,43,"Or have they taken others besides Allah as intercessors? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєWould they do so,ЋЇ even though those ЋєidolsЋЇ have neither authority nor intelligence?вАЭ"
  39,44,"Say, вАЬAll intercession belongs to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ. To Him belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. Then to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned.вАЭ"
  39,45,"Yet when Allah alone is mentioned, the hearts of those who disbelieve in the Hereafter are filled with disgust. But as soon as those ЋєgodsЋЇ other than Him are mentioned, they are filled with joy"
  39,46,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO AllahвАФOriginator of the heavens and the earth, Knower of the seen and unseen! You will judge between Your servants regarding their differences.вАЭ"
  39,47,"Even if the wrongdoers were to possess everything in the world twice over, they would certainly offer it to ransom themselves from the horrible punishment on Judgment Day, for they will see from Allah what they had never expected"
  39,48,"And the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds will unfold before them, and they will be overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  39,49,"When one is touched with hardship, they cry out to Us ЋєaloneЋЇ. Then when We shower Our blessings upon them, they say, вАЬI have been granted all this only because of ЋєmyЋЇ knowledge.вАЭ Not at all! It is Ћєno more thanЋЇ a test. But most of them do not know"
  39,50,"The same had already been said by those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them,¬†but their ЋєworldlyЋЇ gains were of no benefit to them"
  39,51,So the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds overtook them. And the wrongdoers among these ЋєpagansЋЇ will be overtaken by the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds. And they will have no escape
  39,52,Do they not know that Allah gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills? Surely in this are signs for people who believe
  39,53,"Say, ЋєO Prophet, that Allah says,ЋЇ вАЬO My servants who have exceeded the limits against their souls! Do not lose hope in AllahвАЩs mercy, for Allah certainly forgives all sins.¬†He is indeed the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  39,54,"Turn to your Lord Ћєin repentanceЋЇ, and ЋєfullyЋЇ submit to Him before the punishment reaches you, ЋєforЋЇ then you will not be helped"
  39,55,"Follow Ћєthe Quran,ЋЇ the best of what has been revealed to you from your Lord, before the punishment takes you by surprise while you are unaware"
  39,56,"so that no ЋєsinfulЋЇ soul will say Ћєon Judgment DayЋЇ, вАШWoe to me for neglecting Ћєmy duties towardsЋЇ Allah, while ridiculing Ћєthe truthЋЇ.вАЩ"
  39,57,"Or Ћєa soul willЋЇ say, вАШIf only Allah had guided me, I would have certainly been one of the righteous.вАЩ"
  39,58,"Or say, upon seeing the torment, вАШIf only I had a second chance, I would have been one of the good-doers.вАЩ"
  39,59,"Not at all! My revelations had already come to you, but you rejected them, acted arrogantly, and were one of the disbelievers.вАЭ"
  39,60,On the Day of Judgment you will see those who lied about Allah with their faces gloomy. Is Hell not a ЋєfittingЋЇ home for the arrogant
  39,61,"And Allah will deliver those who were mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ to their place of ЋєultimateЋЇ triumph. No evil will touch them, nor will they grieve"
  39,62,"Allah is the Creator of all things, and He is the Maintainer of everything"
  39,63,"To Him belong the keys Ћєof the treasuriesЋЇ¬†of the heavens and the earth. As for those who rejected the signs of Allah, it is they who will be the ЋєtrueЋЇ losers"
  39,64,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬAre you urging me to worship ЋєanyoneЋЇ other than Allah, O ignorant ones?вАЭ"
  39,65,"It has already been revealed to youвАФand to those ЋєprophetsЋЇ before youвАФthat if you associate others Ћєwith AllahЋЇ, your deeds will certainly be void and you will truly be one of the losers"
  39,66,"Rather, worship Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ and be one of the grateful"
  39,67,"They have not shown Allah His proper reverenceвАФwhen on the Day of Judgment the ЋєwholeЋЇ earth will be in His Grip, and the heavens will be rolled up in His Right Hand. Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ"
  39,68,"The Trumpet will be blown and all those in the heavens and all those on the earth will fall dead, except those Allah wills Ћєto spareЋЇ. Then it will be blown again and they will rise up at once, looking on Ћєin anticipationЋЇ"
  39,69,"The earth¬†will shine with the light of its Lord, the record Ћєof deedsЋЇ will be laid ЋєopenЋЇ, the prophets and the witnesses will be brought forwardвАФand judgment will be passed on all with fairness. None will be wronged"
  39,70,"Every soul will be paid in full for its deeds, for Allah knows best what they have done"
  39,71,"Those who disbelieved will be driven to Hell in ЋєsuccessiveЋЇ groups. When they arrive there, its gates will be opened and its keepers will ask them: вАЬDid messengers not come to you from among yourselves, reciting to you the revelations of your Lord and warning you of the coming of this Day of yours?вАЭ The disbelievers will cry, вАЬYes ЋєindeedЋЇ! But the decree of torment has come to pass against the disbelievers.вАЭ"
  39,72,"It will be said to them, вАЬEnter the gates of Hell, to stay there forever.вАЭ What an evil home for the arrogant"
  39,73,"And those who were mindful of their Lord will be led to Paradise in ЋєsuccessiveЋЇ groups. When they arrive at its ЋєalreadyЋЇ open gates, its keepers will say, вАЬPeace be upon you! You have done well, so come in, to stay forever.вАЭ"
  39,74,"The righteous will say, вАЬPraise be to Allah Who has fulfilled His promise to us, and made us inherit the ЋєeverlastingЋЇ land¬†to settle in Paradise wherever we please.вАЭ How excellent is the reward of those who work ЋєrighteousnessЋЇ"
  39,75,"You will see the angels all around the Throne, glorifying the praises of their Lord, for judgment will have been passed on all with fairness. And it will be said,¬†вАЬPraise be to AllahвАФLord of all worlds!вАЭ"
  40,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  40,2,"The revelation of this Book is from AllahвАФthe Almighty, All-Knowing"
  40,3,"the Forgiver of sin and Accepter of repentance, the Severe in punishment, and Infinite in bounty. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. To Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is the final return"
  40,4,"None disputes the signs of Allah except the disbelievers, so do not be deceived by their prosperity throughout the land"
  40,5,"Before them, the people of Noah denied Ћєthe truthЋЇ, as did ЋєotherЋЇ enemy forces afterwards. Every community plotted against its prophet to seize him, and argued in falsehood, ЋєhopingЋЇ to discredit the truth with it. So I seized them. And how ЋєhorribleЋЇ was My punishment"
  40,6,And so your LordвАЩs decree has been proven true against the disbelieversвАФthat they will be the inmates of the Fire
  40,7,"Those ЋєangelsЋЇ who carry the Throne and those around it glorify the praises of their Lord, have faith in Him, and seek forgiveness for the believers, Ћєpraying:ЋЇ вАЬOur Lord! You encompass everything in ЋєYourЋЇ mercy and knowledge. So forgive those who repent and follow Your Way, and protect them from the torment of the Hellfire"
  40,8,"Our Lord! Admit them into the Gardens of Eternity which You have promised them, along with the righteous among their parents, spouses, and descendants. You ЋєaloneЋЇ are truly the Almighty, All-Wise"
  40,9,And protect them from Ћєthe consequences of theirЋЇ evil deeds. For whoever You protect from the evil of their deeds on that Day will have been shown Your mercy. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the ultimate triumph.вАЭ
  40,10,"Indeed, it will be announced to the disbelievers, вАЬAllahвАЩs contempt for youвАФas you disbelieved when invited to beliefвАФwas far worse than your contempt for one another ЋєTodayЋЇ.вАЭ"
  40,11,"They will plead, вАЬOur Lord! You made us lifeless twice, and gave us life twice.¬†Now we confess our sins. So is there any way out?вАЭ"
  40,12,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬЋєNo!ЋЇ This is because when Allah alone was invoked, you ЋєstaunchlyЋЇ disbelieved. But when others were associated with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ, you ЋєreadilyЋЇ believed. So ЋєTodayЋЇ judgment belongs to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇвАФthe Most High, All-Great.вАЭ"
  40,13,He is the One Who shows you His signs and sends down Ћєrain asЋЇ a provision for you from the sky. ЋєButЋЇ none will be mindful except those who turn Ћєto HimЋЇ
  40,14,"So call upon Allah with sincere devotion, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  40,15,"ЋєHe isЋЇ Highly Exalted in rank, Lord of the Throne. He sends down the revelation by His command to whoever He wills of His servants to warn ЋєallЋЇ of the Day of MeetingвАФ"
  40,16,"the Day all will appear Ћєbefore AllahЋЇ. Nothing about them will be hidden from Him. ЋєHe will ask,ЋЇ вАЬWho does all authority belong to this Day? To AllahвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  40,17,Today every soul will be rewarded for what it has done. No injustice Today! Surely Allah is swift in reckoning.вАЭ
  40,18,"Warn them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ of the approaching Day when the hearts will jump into the throats, suppressing distress. The wrongdoers will have neither a close friend nor intercessor to be heard"
  40,19,Allah ЋєevenЋЇ knows the sly glances of the eyes and whatever the hearts conceal
  40,20,"And Allah judges with the truth, while those ЋєidolsЋЇ they invoke besides Him cannot judge at all. Indeed, Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,21,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them? They were far superior in might and Ћєricher inЋЇ monuments throughout the land. But Allah seized them for their sins, and they had no protector from Allah"
  40,22,"That was because their messengers used to come to them with clear proofs, but they persisted in disbelief. So Allah seized them. Surely He is All-Powerful, severe in punishment"
  40,23,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs and compelling proof"
  40,24,"to Pharaoh, Ham√Ґn, and Korah. But they responded: вАЬMagician! Total liar!вАЭ"
  40,25,"Then, when he came to them with the truth from Us, they said, вАЬKill the sons of those who believe with him and keep their women.вАЭ But the plotting of the disbelievers was only in vain"
  40,26,"And Pharaoh said, вАЬLet me kill Moses, and let him call upon his Lord! I truly fear that he may change your traditions or cause mischief in the land.вАЭ"
  40,27,"Moses replied, вАЬI seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every arrogant person who does not believe in the Day of Reckoning.вАЭ"
  40,28,"A believing man from PharaohвАЩs people, who was hiding his faith, argued, вАЬWill you kill a man¬†ЋєonlyЋЇ for saying: вАШMy Lord is Allah,вАЩ while he has in fact come to you with clear proofs from your Lord? If he is a liar, it will be to his own loss. But if he is truthful, then you will be afflicted with some of what he is threatening you with. Surely Allah does not guide whoever is a transgressor, a total liar"
  40,29,"O my people! Authority belongs to you today, reigning supreme in the land. But who would help us against the torment of Allah, if it were to befall us?вАЭ Pharaoh assured Ћєhis peopleЋЇ, вАЬI am telling you only what I believe, and I am leading you only to the way of guidance.вАЭ"
  40,30,"And the man who believed cautioned, вАЬO my people! I truly fear for you the doom of ЋєearlierЋЇ enemy forcesвАФ"
  40,31,"like the fate of the people of Noah, вАЩ»Вd, Tham√їd, and those after them. For Allah would never will to wrong ЋєHisЋЇ servants"
  40,32,O my people! I truly fear for you the Day all will be crying out Ћєto each otherЋЇвАФ
  40,33,"the Day you will Ћєtry in vain toЋЇ turn your backs and run away, with no one to protect you from Allah. And whoever Allah leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  40,34,"Joseph already came to you¬†earlier with clear proofs, yet you never ceased to doubt what he came to you with. When he died you said, вАШAllah will never send a messenger after him.вАЩ This is how Allah leaves every transgressor and doubter to strayвАФ"
  40,35,those who dispute AllahвАЩs signs with no proof given to them. How despicable is that for Allah and the believers! This is how Allah seals the heart of every arrogant tyrant.вАЭ
  40,36,"Pharaoh ordered, вАЬO Ham√Ґn! Build me a high tower so I may reach the pathways"
  40,37,"leading up to the heavens and look for the God of Moses, although I am sure he is a liar.вАЭ¬†And so PharaohвАЩs evil deeds were made so appealing to him that he was hindered from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way. But the plotting of Pharaoh was only in vain"
  40,38,"And the man who believed urged, вАЬO my people! Follow me, ЋєandЋЇ I will lead you to the Way of Guidance"
  40,39,"O my people! This worldly life is only Ћєa fleetingЋЇ enjoyment, whereas the Hereafter is truly the home of settlement"
  40,40,"Whoever does an evil deed will only be paid back with its equivalent. And whoever does good, whether male or female, and is a believer, they will enter Paradise, where they will be provided for without limit"
  40,41,"O my people! How is it that I invite you to salvation, while you invite me to the Fire"
  40,42,"You invite me to disbelieve in Allah and associate with Him what I have no knowledge of, while I invite you to the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  40,43,"There is no doubt that whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you invite me to ЋєworshipЋЇ are not worthy to be invoked either in this world or the Hereafter.¬†ЋєUndoubtedly,ЋЇ our return is to Allah, and the transgressors will be the inmates of the Fire"
  40,44,"You will remember what I say to you, and I entrust my affairs to Allah. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of all ЋєHisЋЇ servants.вАЭ"
  40,45,So Allah protected him from the evil of their schemes. And PharaohвАЩs people were overwhelmed by an evil punishment
  40,46,"they are exposed to the Fire Ћєin their gravesЋЇ morning and evening. And on the Day the Hour will be established Ћєit will be saidЋЇ, вАЬAdmit PharaohвАЩs people into the harshest punishment Ћєof HellЋЇ.вАЭ"
  40,47,"ЋєConsider the DayЋЇ when they will dispute in the Fire, and the lowly ЋєfollowersЋЇ will appeal to the arrogant ЋєleadersЋЇ, вАЬWe were your ЋєdedicatedЋЇ followers, will you then shield us from a portion of the Fire?вАЭ"
  40,48,"The arrogant will say, вАЬWe are all in it! ЋєForЋЇ Allah has already passed judgment over ЋєHisЋЇ servants.вАЭ"
  40,49,"And those in the Fire will cry out to the keepers of Hell,¬†вАЬPray to your Lord to lighten the torment for us ЋєevenЋЇ for one day!вАЭ"
  40,50,"The keepers will reply, вАЬDid your messengers not ЋєconstantlyЋЇ come to you with clear proofs?вАЭ They will say, вАЬYes Ћєthey didЋЇ.вАЭ The keepers will say, вАЬThen pray! Though the prayer of the disbelievers is only in vain.вАЭ"
  40,51,"We certainly help Our messengers and the believers, ЋєbothЋЇ in this worldly life and on the Day the witnesses will stand forth Ћєfor testimonyЋЇвАФ"
  40,52,"the Day the wrongdoersвАЩ excuses will be of no benefit to them. They will be condemned, and will have the worst outcome"
  40,53,"And indeed, We gave Moses ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance, and made the Children of Israel inherit the ScriptureвАФ"
  40,54,a guide and a reminder to people of reason
  40,55,"So be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, ЋєforЋЇ AllahвАЩs promise is certainly true. Seek forgiveness for your shortcomings.¬†And glorify the praises of your Lord morning and evening"
  40,56,"Surely those who dispute AllahвАЩs signsвАФwith no proof given to themвАФhave nothing in their hearts but greed for dominance, which they will never attain. So seek refuge in Allah. Indeed, He alone is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,57,"The creation of the heavens and the earth is certainly greater than the re-creation of humankind, but most people do not know"
  40,58,"Those blind Ћєto the truthЋЇ and those who can see are not equal, nor are those who believe and do good ЋєequalЋЇ to those who do evil. Yet you are hardly mindful"
  40,59,"The Hour is certainly coming, there is no doubt about it. But most people do not believe"
  40,60,"Your Lord has proclaimed, вАЬCall upon Me, I will respond to you. Surely those who are too proud to worship Me will enter Hell, fully humbled.вАЭ"
  40,61,"It is Allah Who has made the night for you to rest in and the day bright. Surely Allah is ever Bountiful to humanity, but most people are ungrateful"
  40,62,"That is Allah, your Lord, the Creator of all things. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. How can you then be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  40,63,This is how those who used to reject AllahвАЩs signs were ЋєalsoЋЇ deluded
  40,64,"It is Allah Who made the earth a place of settlement for you and the sky a canopy. He shaped you Ћєin the wombЋЇ, perfecting your form. And He has provided you with what is good and lawful. That is AllahвАФyour Lord. So Blessed is Allah, Lord of all worlds"
  40,65,"He is the Ever-Living. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. So call upon Him with sincere devotion, Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬAll praise is for AllahвАФLord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  40,66,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI have been forbidden to worship those ЋєidolsЋЇ you worship besides Allah, since clear proofs have come to me from my Lord. And I have been commanded to ЋєfullyЋЇ submit to the Lord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  40,67,"He is the One Who created you¬†from dust, then from a sperm-drop,¬†then Ћєdeveloped you intoЋЇ a clinging clot Ћєof bloodЋЇ,¬†then He brings you forth as infants, so that you may reach your prime, and become oldвАФthough some of you ЋєmayЋЇ die soonerвАФreaching an appointed time, so perhaps you may understand ЋєAllahвАЩs powerЋЇ"
  40,68,"He is the One Who gives life and causes death. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, вАЬBe!вАЭ And it is"
  40,69,Have you not seen how those who dispute AllahвАЩs signs are turned away
  40,70,ЋєThey areЋЇ the ones who reject this Book and all ЋєscripturesЋЇ We sent Our messengers with. So they will know Ћєthe consequencesЋЇ
  40,71,when shackles will be around their necks and chains Ћєon their legsЋЇ. They will be dragged
  40,72,"through boiling water, then burned in the Fire Ћєas fuelЋЇ"
  40,73,"Then they will be asked, вАЬWhere are those ЋєidolsЋЇ you used to associate"
  40,74,"with Allah?вАЭ They will cry, вАЬThey have ЋєallЋЇ failed us. In fact, we did not invoke anything ЋєrealЋЇ before.вАЭ This is how Allah leaves the disbelievers to stray"
  40,75,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬThis ЋєpunishmentЋЇ is for being prideful on earth unjustly and for acting arrogantly"
  40,76,"Enter the gates of Hell, to stay there forever. What an evil home for the arrogant!вАЭ"
  40,77,"So be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. Surely AllahвАЩs promise is true. Whether We show you some of what We threaten them with, or cause you to die Ћєbefore thatЋЇ, to Us they will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  40,78,"We already sent messengers before you. We have told you the stories of some of them, while others We have not. It was not for any messenger to bring a sign without AllahвАЩs permission. But when AllahвАЩs decree comes, judgment will be passed with fairness, and the people of falsehood will then be in ЋєtotalЋЇ loss"
  40,79,It is Allah Who made cattle for you so that you may ride some and eat others
  40,80,"Also, you find in them ЋєotherЋЇ benefits.¬†And by means of them you may reach destinations you desire. And you are carried upon Ћєsome ofЋЇ them and upon ships"
  40,81,And He shows you His signs. Now which of AllahвАЩs signs will you deny
  40,82,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those who were ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before them? They were far superior in might and Ћєricher inЋЇ monuments throughout the land, but their ЋєworldlyЋЇ gains were of no benefit to them"
  40,83,"When their messengers came to them with clear proofs, they were prideful in whatever ЋєworldlyЋЇ knowledge they had,¬†and were ЋєultimatelyЋЇ overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  40,84,"When they saw Our punishment, they cried, вАЬЋєNowЋЇ we believe in Allah alone and reject what we had been associating with Him!вАЭ"
  40,85,But their faith was of no benefit to them when they saw Our torment. This has ЋєalwaysЋЇ been AllahвАЩs way Ћєof dealingЋЇ with His ЋєwickedЋЇ servants. Then and there the disbelievers were in ЋєtotalЋЇ loss
  41,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  41,2,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a revelation from the Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  41,3,ЋєIt isЋЇ a Book whose verses are perfectly explainedвАФa Quran in Arabic for people who know
  41,4,"delivering good news and warning. Yet most of them turn away, so they do not hear"
  41,5,"They say, вАЬOur hearts are veiled against what you are calling us to, there is deafness in our ears, and there is a barrier between us and you. So do Ћєwhatever you wantЋЇ and so shall we!вАЭ"
  41,6,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI am only a man like you, ЋєbutЋЇ it has been revealed to me that your God is only One God. So take the Straight Way towards Him, and seek His forgiveness. And woe to the polytheistsвАФ"
  41,7,those who do not pay alms-tax and are in denial of the Hereafter
  41,8,ЋєButЋЇ those who believe and do good will certainly have a never-ending reward
  41,9,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬHow can you disbelieve in the One Who created the earth in two Days? And how can you set up equals with Him? That is the Lord of all worlds"
  41,10,"He placed on the earth firm mountains, standing high, showered His blessings upon it, and ordained ЋєallЋЇ its means of sustenanceвАФtotaling four Days exactlyвАФfor all who ask"
  41,11,"Then He turned towards the heaven when it was Ћєstill likeЋЇ smoke, saying to it and to the earth, вАШSubmit, willingly or unwillingly.вАЩ They both responded, вАШWe submit willingly.вАЩ"
  41,12,"So He formed the heaven into seven heavens in two Days, assigning to each its mandate. And We adorned the lowest heaven with Ћєstars likeЋЇ lamps Ћєfor beautyЋЇ and for protection. That is the design of the Almighty, All-Knowing.вАЭ"
  41,13,"If they turn away, then say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI warn you of a ЋєmightyЋЇ blast, like the one that befell вАЩ»Вd and Tham√їd.вАЭ"
  41,14,"The messengers had come to them from all angles, Ћєproclaiming,ЋЇ вАЬWorship none but Allah.вАЭ They responded, вАЬHad our Lord willed, He could have easily sent down angels ЋєinsteadЋЇ. So we totally reject what you have been sent with.вАЭ"
  41,15,"As for вАЩ»Вd, they acted arrogantly throughout the land with no right, boasting, вАЬWho is superior to us in might?вАЭ Did they not see that Allah ЋєHimselfЋЇ, Who created them, was far superior to them in might? Still they persisted in denying Our signs"
  41,16,"So We sent against them a furious wind,¬†for ЋєseveralЋЇ miserable days, to make them taste a humiliating punishment in this worldly life. But far more humiliating will be the punishment of the Hereafter. And they will not be helped"
  41,17,"As for Tham√їd, We showed them guidance, but they preferred blindness over guidance. So the blast of a disgracing punishment overtook them for what they used to commit"
  41,18,And We delivered those who were faithful and were mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ
  41,19,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ the Day ЋєwhenЋЇ the enemies of Allah will be gathered for the Fire, all driven in ranks"
  41,20,"When they reach it, their ears, eyes, and skin will testify against what they used to do"
  41,21,"They will ask their skin ЋєfuriouslyЋЇ, вАЬWhy have you testified against us?вАЭ It will say, вАЬWe have been made to speak by Allah, Who causes all things to speak. He Ћєis the One WhoЋЇ created you the first time, and to Him you were bound to return"
  41,22,"You did not Ћєbother toЋЇ hide yourselves from your ears, eyes, and skin to prevent them from testifying against you. Rather, you assumed that Allah did not know much of what you used to do"
  41,23,"It was that ЋєfalseЋЇ assumption you entertained about your Lord that has brought about your doom, so you have become losers.вАЭ"
  41,24,"Even if they endure patiently, the Fire will ЋєalwaysЋЇ be their home. And if they Ћєbeg toЋЇ appease Ћєtheir LordЋЇ, they will never be allowed to"
  41,25,"We placed at their disposal ЋєevilЋЇ associates who made their past and future ЋєmisdeedsЋЇ appealing to them.¬†ЋєSoЋЇ the fate of earlier communities of jinn and humans has been justified against them Ћєas wellЋЇ, ЋєforЋЇ they were truly losers"
  41,26,"The disbelievers advised Ћєone anotherЋЇ, вАЬDo not listen to this Quran but drown it out so that you may prevail.вАЭ"
  41,27,"So We will certainly make the disbelievers taste a severe punishment, and We will surely repay them according to the worst of their deeds"
  41,28,"That is the reward of AllahвАЩs enemies: the Fire, which will be their eternal homeвАФa ЋєfittingЋЇ reward for their denial of Our revelations"
  41,29,"The disbelievers will ЋєthenЋЇ cry, вАЬOur Lord! Show us those jinn and humans who led us astray: we will put them under our feet so that they will be among the lowest Ћєin HellЋЇ.вАЭ"
  41,30,"Surely those who say, вАЬOur Lord is Allah,вАЭ and then remain steadfast, the angels descend upon them,¬†Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬDo not fear, nor grieve. Rather, rejoice in the good news of Paradise, which you have been promised"
  41,31,"We are your supporters in this worldly life and in the Hereafter. There you will have whatever your souls desire, and there you will have whatever you ask for"
  41,32,"an accommodation from the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful ЋєLordЋЇ.вАЭ"
  41,33,"And whose words are better than someone who calls ЋєothersЋЇ to Allah, does good, and says, вАЬI am truly one of those who submit.вАЭ"
  41,34,"Good and evil cannot be equal. Respond Ћєto evilЋЇ with what is best, then the one you are in a feud with will be like a close friend"
  41,35,But this cannot be attained except by those who are patient and who are truly fortunate
  41,36,"And if you are tempted by Satan, then seek refuge with Allah. Indeed, He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  41,37,"Among His signs are the day and the night, the sun and the moon. Do not prostrate to the sun or the moon, but prostrate to Allah, Who created them ЋєallЋЇ, if you ЋєtrulyЋЇ worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ"
  41,38,"But if the pagans are too proud, then Ћєlet them know thatЋЇ those ЋєangelsЋЇ nearest to your Lord glorify Him day and night, and never grow weary"
  41,39,"And among His signs is that you see the earth devoid of life, but as soon as We send down rain upon it, it begins to stir Ћєto lifeЋЇ and swell. Indeed, the One Who revives it can easily revive the dead. He is certainly Most Capable of everything"
  41,40,"Indeed, those who abuse Our revelations¬†are not hidden from Us. Who is better: the one who will be cast into the Fire or the one who will be secure on Judgment Day? Do whatever you want. He is certainly All-Seeing of what you do"
  41,41,"Indeed, those who deny the Reminder¬†after it has come to them Ћєare doomedЋЇ, for it is truly a mighty Book"
  41,42,"It cannot be proven false from any angle. ЋєIt isЋЇ a revelation from the ЋєOne Who isЋЇ All-Wise, Praiseworthy"
  41,43,ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Nothing is said to you Ћєby the deniersЋЇ except what was already said to the messengers before you. Surely your Lord is Ћєthe LordЋЇ of forgiveness and painful punishment
  41,44,"Had We revealed it as a non-Arabic Quran, they would have certainly argued, вАЬIf only its verses were made clear Ћєin our languageЋЇ. What! A non-Arabic revelation for an Arab audience!вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIt is a guide and a healing to the believers. As for those who disbelieve, there is deafness in their ears and blindness to it Ћєin their heartsЋЇ. It is as if they are being called from a faraway place.вАЭ"
  41,45,"Indeed, We had given Moses the Scripture, but differences arose regarding it. Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord,¬†their differences would have been settled Ћєat onceЋЇ. They are truly in alarming doubt about it"
  41,46,"Whoever does good, it is to their own benefit. And whoever does evil, it is to their own loss. Your Lord is never unjust to ЋєHisЋЇ creation"
  41,47,"With Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is the knowledge of the Hour. No fruit comes out of its husk, nor does a female conceive or deliver without His knowledge. And ЋєconsiderЋЇ the Day He will call to them, вАЬWhere are My Ћєso-calledЋЇ associate-gods?вАЭ They will cry, вАЬWe declare before you that none of us testifies to that Ћєany longerЋЇ.вАЭ"
  41,48,Whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ they used to invoke besides Allah will fail them. And they will realize that they will have no escape
  41,49,"One never tires of praying for good. And if touched with evil, they become desperate and hopeless"
  41,50,"And if We let them taste a mercy from Us after being touched with adversity, they will certainly say, вАЬThis is what I deserve. I do not think the Hour will ЋєeverЋЇ come. And if in fact I am returned to my Lord, the finest reward with Him will definitely be mine.вАЭ But We will surely inform the disbelievers of what they used to do. And We will certainly make them taste a harsh torment"
  41,51,"When We show favour to someone, they turn away, acting arrogantly. And when touched with evil, they make endless prayers Ћєfor goodЋЇ"
  41,52,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬImagine if this ЋєQuranЋЇ is ЋєtrulyЋЇ from Allah and you deny it: who can be more astray than those who have gone too far in opposition Ћєto the truthЋЇ?вАЭ"
  41,53,We will show them Our signs in the universe and within themselves until it becomes clear to them that this ЋєQuranЋЇ is the truth. Is it not enough that your Lord is a Witness over all things
  41,54,They are truly in doubt of the meeting with their Lord! ЋєButЋЇ He is indeed Fully Aware of everything
  42,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  42,2,вАЩAƒ©n-Sƒ©n-Q√£f
  42,3,"And so you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are sent revelation, just like those before you, by AllahвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  42,4,"To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And He is the Most High, the Greatest"
  42,5,"The heavens¬†nearly burst, one above the other, Ћєin awe of HimЋЇ. And the angels glorify the praises of their Lord, and seek forgiveness for those on earth. Surely Allah alone is the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  42,6,"As for those who take other protectors besides Him, Allah is Watchful over them. And you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are not a keeper over them"
  42,7,"And so We have revealed to you a Quran in Arabic, so you may warn the Mother of Cities¬†and everyone around it, and warn of the Day of GatheringвАФabout which there is no doubtвАФЋєwhenЋЇ a group will be in Paradise and another in the Blaze"
  42,8,"Had Allah willed, He could have easily made all ЋєhumanityЋЇ into a single community Ћєof believersЋЇ. But He admits into His mercy whoever He wills. And the wrongdoers will have no protector or helper"
  42,9,How can they take protectors besides Him? Allah alone is the Protector. He ЋєaloneЋЇ gives life to the dead. And He ЋєaloneЋЇ is Most Capable of everything
  42,10,"ЋєSay to the believers, O Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWhatever you may differ about, its judgment rests with Allah. That is AllahвАФmy Lord. In Him I put my trust, and to Him I ЋєalwaysЋЇ turn.вАЭ"
  42,11,"ЋєHe isЋЇ the Originator of the heavens and the earth. He has made for you spouses from among yourselves, and ЋєmadeЋЇ mates for cattle Ћєas wellЋЇвАФmultiplying you ЋєbothЋЇ. There is nothing like Him, for He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  42,12,"To Him belong the keys Ћєof the treasuriesЋЇ of the heavens and the earth. He gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills. Indeed, He has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  42,13,"He has ordained for you ЋєbelieversЋЇ the Way which He decreed for Noah, and what We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ and what We decreed for Abraham, Moses, and Jesus,¬†Ћєcommanding:ЋЇ вАЬUphold the faith, and make no divisions in it.вАЭ What you call the polytheists to is unbearable for them. Allah chooses for Himself whoever He wills, and guides to Himself whoever turns Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  42,14,"They did not split Ћєinto sectsЋЇ out of mutual envy until knowledge came to them.¬†Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord for an appointed term,¬†the matter would have certainly been settled between them Ћєat onceЋЇ. And surely those who were made to inherit the Scripture¬†after them are truly in alarming doubt about this ЋєQuranЋЇ"
  42,15,"Because of that, you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ will invite ЋєallЋЇ. Be steadfast as you are commanded, and do not follow their desires. And say, вАЬI believe in every Scripture Allah has revealed. And I am commanded to judge fairly among you. Allah is our Lord and your Lord. We will be accountable for our deeds and you for yours. There is no Ћєneed forЋЇ contention between us. Allah will gather us together Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ. And to Him is the final return.вАЭ"
  42,16,"As for those who dispute about Allah after He is ЋєalreadyЋЇ acknowledged Ћєby manyЋЇ, their argument is futile in the sight of their Lord. Upon them is wrath, and they will suffer a severe punishment"
  42,17,"It is Allah Who has revealed the Book with the truth and the balance Ћєof justiceЋЇ. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near"
  42,18,"Those who disbelieve in it Ћєask toЋЇ hasten it ЋєmockinglyЋЇ. But the believers are fearful of it, knowing that it is the truth. Surely those who dispute about the Hour have gone far astray"
  42,19,"Allah is Ever Kind to His servants. He provides ЋєabundantlyЋЇ to whoever He wills. And He is the All-Powerful, Almighty"
  42,20,"Whoever desires the harvest of the Hereafter, We will increase their harvest. And whoever desires ЋєonlyЋЇ the harvest of this world, We will give them some of it, but they will have no share in the Hereafter"
  42,21,"Or do they have associate-gods who have ordained for them some ЋєpolytheisticЋЇ beliefs, which Allah has not authorized? Had it not been for ЋєpriorЋЇ decree on Judgment, the matter would have certainly been settled between them Ћєat onceЋЇ. And surely the wrongdoers will suffer a painful punishment"
  42,22,"You will see the wrongdoers fearful Ћєof the punishmentЋЇ for what they committed but it will be inevitable for them, whereas those who believe and do good will be in the lush Gardens of Paradise. They will have whatever they desire from their Lord. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the greatest bounty"
  42,23,"That ЋєrewardЋЇ is the good news which Allah gives to His servants who believe and do good. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI do not ask you for a reward for this ЋєmessageЋЇвАФonly honour for ЋєourЋЇ kinship.вАЭ¬†Whoever earns a good deed, We will increase it in goodness for them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  42,24,"Or do they say, вАЬHe has fabricated a lie about Allah!вАЭ? ЋєIf you had,ЋЇ Allah would have sealed your heart, if He willed. And Allah wipes out falsehood and establishes the truth by His Words. He certainly knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart"
  42,25,He is the One Who accepts repentance from His servants and pardons ЋєtheirЋЇ sins. And He knows whatever you do
  42,26,"He responds to those who believe and do good, and increases their reward out of His grace. As for the disbelievers, they will suffer a severe punishment"
  42,27,"Had Allah given abundant provisions to ЋєallЋЇ His servants, they would have certainly transgressed throughout the land. But He sends down whatever He wills in perfect measure. He is truly All-Aware, All-Seeing of His servants"
  42,28,"He is the One Who sends down rain after people have given up hope, spreading out His mercy. He is the Guardian, the Praiseworthy"
  42,29,"And among His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and all living beings He dispersed throughout both. And He is Most Capable of bringing all together whenever He wills"
  42,30,Whatever affliction befalls you is because of what your own hands have committed. And He pardons much
  42,31,"You can never escape ЋєHimЋЇ on earth, nor do you have any protector or helper besides Allah"
  42,32,And among His signs are the ships like mountains ЋєsailingЋЇ in the sea
  42,33,"If He wills, He can calm the wind, leaving the ships motionless on the water. Surely in this are signs for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  42,34,Or He can wreck the ships for what the people have committedвАФthough He forgives muchвАФ
  42,35,so those who dispute about Our signs may know that they have no refuge
  42,36,Whatever ЋєpleasureЋЇ you have been given is Ћєno more than a fleetingЋЇ enjoyment of this worldly life. But what is with Allah is far better and more lasting for those who believe and put their trust in their Lord
  42,37,"who avoid major sins and shameful deeds, and forgive when angered"
  42,38,"who respond to their Lord, establish prayer, conduct their affairs by mutual consultation, and donate from what We have provided for them"
  42,39,and who enforce justice when wronged
  42,40,"The reward of an evil deed is its equivalent. But whoever pardons and seeks reconciliation, then their reward is with Allah. He certainly does not like the wrongdoers"
  42,41,There is no blame on those who enforce justice after being wronged
  42,42,Blame is only on those who wrong people and transgress in the land unjustly. It is they who will suffer a painful punishment
  42,43,And whoever endures patiently and forgivesвАФsurely this is a resolve to aspire to
  42,44,"And whoever Allah leaves to stray will have no guide after Him. You will see the wrongdoers, when they face the torment, pleading, вАЬIs there any way back Ћєto the worldЋЇ?вАЭ"
  42,45,"And you will see them exposed to the Fire, fully humbled out of disgrace, stealing glances Ћєat itЋЇ. And the believers will say, вАЬThe ЋєtrueЋЇ losers are those who have lost themselves and their families on Judgment Day.вАЭ The wrongdoers will certainly be in everlasting torment"
  42,46,"They will have no protectors to help them against Allah. And whoever Allah leaves to stray, for them there is no way"
  42,47,"Respond to your Lord before the coming of a Day from Allah that cannot be averted. There will be no refuge for you then, nor Ћєgrounds forЋЇ denial Ћєof sinsЋЇ"
  42,48,"But if they turn away, We have not sent you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ as a keeper over them. Your duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ. And indeed, when We let someone taste a mercy from Us, they become prideful ЋєbecauseЋЇ of it. But when afflicted with evil because of what their hands have done, then one becomes totally ungrateful"
  42,49,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He creates whatever He wills. He blesses whoever He wills with daughters, and blesses whoever He wills with sons"
  42,50,"or grants both, sons and daughters, Ћєto whoever He willsЋЇ, and leaves whoever He wills infertile. He is indeed All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  42,51,"It is not ЋєpossibleЋЇ for a human being to have Allah communicate with them, except through inspiration, or from behind a veil, or by sending a messenger-angel to reveal whatever He wills by His permission. He is surely Most High, All-Wise"
  42,52,"And so We have sent to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ a revelation by Our command. You did not know of ЋєthisЋЇ Book and faith ЋєbeforeЋЇ. But We have made it a light, by which We guide whoever We will of Our servants. And you are truly leading ЋєallЋЇ to the Straight PathвАФ"
  42,53,"the Path of Allah, to Whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Surely to Allah all matters will return Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ"
  43,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  43,2,By the clear Book
  43,3,"Certainly, We have made it a Quran in Arabic so perhaps you will understand"
  43,4,"And indeed, it isвАФin the Master Record¬†with UsвАФhighly esteemed, rich in wisdom"
  43,5,Should We then turn the ЋєQuranicЋЇ Reminder away from you ЋєsimplyЋЇ because you have been a transgressing people
  43,6,ЋєImagineЋЇ how many prophets We sent to those ЋєdestroyedЋЇ before
  43,7,But no prophet ever came to them without being mocked
  43,8,So We destroyed those who were far mightier than these ЋєMeccansЋЇ. The examples of ЋєtheirЋЇ predecessors have ЋєalreadyЋЇ been related
  43,9,"If you ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who created the heavens and the earth, they will certainly say, вАЬThe Almighty, All-Knowing did.вАЭ"
  43,10,"ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who has laid out the earth for you, and set in it pathways for you so that you may find your way"
  43,11,"And ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who sends down rain from the sky in perfect measure, with which We give life to a lifeless land. And so will you be brought forth Ћєfrom the graveЋЇ"
  43,12,"And ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who created all Ћєthings inЋЇ pairs,¬†and made for you ships and animals to ride"
  43,13,"so that you may sit firmly on their backs, and remember your LordвАЩs blessings once you are settled on them, saying, вАЬGlory be to the One Who has subjected these for us, for we could have never done so Ћєon our ownЋЇ"
  43,14,And surely to our Lord we will ЋєallЋЇ return.вАЭ
  43,15,"Still the pagans have made some of His creation out to be a part of Him.¬†Indeed, humankind is clearly ungrateful"
  43,16,"Has He taken Ћєangels as HisЋЇ daughters from what He created, and favoured you ЋєO pagansЋЇ with sons"
  43,17,"Whenever one of them is given the good news of what they attribute to the Most Compassionate,¬†his face grows gloomy, as he suppresses his rage"
  43,18,ЋєDo they attribute to HimЋЇ those who are brought up in fineries and are not commanding in disputes
  43,19,"Still they have labelled the angels, who are servants of the Most Compassionate, as female. Did they witness their creation? Their statement will be recorded, and they will be questioned"
  43,20,"And they argue, вАЬHad the Most Compassionate willed, we would have never worshipped them.вАЭ They have no knowledge Ћєin supportЋЇ of this ЋєclaimЋЇ. They do nothing but lie"
  43,21,"Or have We given them a Book Ћєfor proofЋЇ, before this ЋєQuranЋЇ, to which they are holding firm"
  43,22,"In fact, they say, вАЬWe found our forefathers following a ЋєparticularЋЇ way, and we are following in their footsteps.вАЭ"
  43,23,"Similarly, whenever We sent a warner to a society before you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, its ЋєspoiledЋЇ elite would say, вАЬWe found our forefathers following a ЋєparticularЋЇ way, and we are walking in their footsteps.вАЭ"
  43,24,"Each ЋєwarnerЋЇ asked, вАЬEven if what I brought you is better guidance than what you found your forefathers practicing?вАЭ They replied, вАЬWe totally reject whatever you have been sent with.вАЭ"
  43,25,So We inflicted punishment upon them. See then what was the fate of the deniers
  43,26,"ЋєRemember, O ProphetЋЇ when Abraham declared to his father and his people, вАЬI am totally free of whatever ЋєgodsЋЇ you worship"
  43,27,"except the One Who originated me, and He will surely guide me.вАЭ"
  43,28,"And he left this enduring declaration among his descendants, so they may ЋєalwaysЋЇ turn back Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  43,29,"In fact, I had allowed enjoyment for these ЋєMeccansЋЇ and their forefathers, until the truth came to them along with a messenger making things clear"
  43,30,"ЋєButЋЇ when the truth came to them, they said, вАЬThis is magic, and we totally reject it.вАЭ"
  43,31,"And they exclaimed, вАЬIf only this Quran was revealed to a great man from Ћєone ofЋЇ the two cities!вАЭ"
  43,32,Is it they who distribute your LordвАЩs mercy? We ЋєaloneЋЇ have distributed their ЋєveryЋЇ livelihood among them in this worldly life and raised some of them in rank above others so that some may employ others in service. ЋєButЋЇ your LordвАЩs mercy is far better than whatever ЋєwealthЋЇ they amass
  43,33,"Were it not that people might Ћєbe tempted toЋЇ become one community Ћєof disbelieversЋЇ, We would have supplied the homes of ЋєonlyЋЇ those who disbelieve in the Most Compassionate with silver roofs and ЋєsilverЋЇ stairways to ascend"
  43,34,as well as ЋєsilverЋЇ gates and thrones to recline on
  43,35,and ornaments Ћєof goldЋЇ. Yet all this is no more than a ЋєfleetingЋЇ enjoyment in this worldly life. ЋєButЋЇ the Hereafter with your Lord is ЋєonlyЋЇ for those mindful Ћєof HimЋЇ
  43,36,"And whoever turns a blind eye to the Reminder of the Most Compassionate, We place at the disposal of each a devilish one as their close associate"
  43,37,who will certainly hinder them from the ЋєRightЋЇ Way while they think they are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  43,38,"But when such a person comes to Us, one will say Ћєto their associateЋЇ, вАЬI wish you were as distant from me as the east is from the west! What an evil associate Ћєyou wereЋЇ!вАЭ"
  43,39,"ЋєIt will be said to both,ЋЇ вАЬSince you all did wrong, sharing in the punishment will be of no benefit to you this Day.вАЭ"
  43,40,"Can you make the deaf hear, or guide the blind or those clearly astray"
  43,41,"Even if We take you away Ћєfrom this worldЋЇ, We will surely inflict punishment upon them"
  43,42,"Or if We show you what We threaten them with, We certainly have full power over them"
  43,43,So hold firmly to what has been revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. You are truly on the Straight Path
  43,44,Surely this ЋєQuranЋЇ is a glory for you and your people. And you will ЋєallЋЇ be questioned Ћєabout itЋЇ
  43,45,Ask Ћєthe followers ofЋЇ the messengers that We already sent before you if We ЋєeverЋЇ appointed ЋєotherЋЇ gods to be worshipped besides the Most Compassionate
  43,46,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs, and he said: вАЬI am a messenger of the Lord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  43,47,"But as soon as he came to them with Our signs, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"although every sign We showed them was greater than the one before.¬†Ultimately, We seized them with torments so that they might return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ"
  43,49,"ЋєThenЋЇ they pleaded, вАЬO ЋєmightyЋЇ magician! Pray to your Lord on our behalf, by virtue of the covenant He made with you.¬†We will certainly accept guidance.вАЭ"
  43,50,"But as soon as We removed the torments from them, they broke their promise"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh called out to his people, boasting, вАЬO my people! Am I not sovereign over Egypt as well as ЋєallЋЇ these streams¬†flowing at my feet? Can you not see"
  43,52,Am I not better than this nobody who can hardly express himself
  43,53,Why then have no golden bracelets Ћєof kingshipЋЇ been granted to him or angels come with him as escorts!вАЭ
  43,54,"And so he fooled his people, and they obeyed him. They were truly a rebellious people"
  43,55,"So when they enraged Us, We inflicted punishment upon them, drowning them all"
  43,56,And We made them an example and a lesson for those after them
  43,57,"When the son of Mary was cited as an example Ћєin argumentЋЇ, your people ЋєO ProphetЋЇ broke into ЋєjoyfulЋЇ applause"
  43,58,"They exclaimed, вАЬWhich is better: our gods or Jesus?вАЭ They cite him only to argue. In fact, they are a people prone to dispute"
  43,59,"He was only a servant We showed favour to, and made as an example for the Children of Israel"
  43,60,"Had We willed, We could have easily replaced you ЋєallЋЇ with angels,¬†succeeding one another on earth"
  43,61,"And his ЋєsecondЋЇ coming is truly a sign for the Hour. So have no doubt about it, and follow me. This is the Straight Path"
  43,62,"And do not let Satan hinder you, ЋєforЋЇ he is certainly your sworn enemy"
  43,63,"When Jesus came with clear proofs, he declared, вАЬI have come to you with wisdom, and to clarify to you some of what you differ about. So fear Allah, and obey me"
  43,64,"Surely Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him ЋєaloneЋЇ. This is the Straight Path.вАЭ"
  43,65,"Yet their ЋєvariousЋЇ groups have differed among themselves Ћєabout himЋЇ, so woe to the wrongdoers when they face the torment of a painful Day"
  43,66,Are they waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise when they least expect ЋєitЋЇ
  43,67,"Close friends will be enemies to one another on that Day, except the righteous"
  43,68,"Ћєwho will be told,ЋЇ вАЬO My servants! There is no fear for you Today, nor will you grieveвАФ"
  43,69,ЋєthoseЋЇ who believed in Our signs and ЋєfullyЋЇ submitted Ћєto UsЋЇ
  43,70,"Enter Paradise, you and your spouses, rejoicing.вАЭ"
  43,71,Golden trays and cups will be passed around to them. There will be whatever the souls desire and the eyes delight in. And you will be there forever
  43,72,That is the Paradise which you will be awarded for what you used to do
  43,73,There you will have abundant fruit¬†to eat from
  43,74,"Indeed, the wicked will be in the torment of Hell forever"
  43,75,"It will never be lightened for them, and there they will be overwhelmed with despair"
  43,76,"We did not wrong them, but it was they who were the wrongdoers"
  43,77,"They will cry, вАЬO M√Ґlik!¬†Let your Lord finish us off.вАЭ He will answer, вАЬYou are definitely here to stay.вАЭ"
  43,78,"We certainly brought the truth to you, but most of you were resentful of the truth"
  43,79,Or have they mastered some ЋєevilЋЇ plan? Then We ЋєtooЋЇ are surely planning
  43,80,"Or do they think that We do not hear their ЋєevilЋЇ thoughts and secret talks? Yes ЋєWe doЋЇ! And Our messenger-angels are in their presence, recording Ћєit allЋЇ"
  43,81,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf the Most Compassionate ЋєreallyЋЇ had offspring, I would be the first worshipper.вАЭ"
  43,82,"Glorified is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, far above what they claim"
  43,83,"So let them indulge Ћєin falsehoodЋЇ and amuse ЋєthemselvesЋЇ until they face their Day, which they have been warned of"
  43,84,"It is He Who is Ћєthe onlyЋЇ God in the heavens and Ћєthe onlyЋЇ God on the earth. For He is the All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  43,85,And Blessed is the One to Whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between! With Him ЋєaloneЋЇ is the knowledge of the Hour. And to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned
  43,86,"ЋєButЋЇ those Ћєobjects of worshipЋЇ they invoke besides Him have no power to intercede, except those who testify to the truth knowingly"
  43,87,"If you ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ who created them, they will certainly say, вАЬAllah!вАЭ How can they then be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  43,88,"ЋєAllah is Aware ofЋЇ the ProphetвАЩs cry: вАЬO my Lord! Indeed, these are a people who persist in disbelief.вАЭ"
  43,89,So bear with them and respond with peace. They will soon come to know
  44,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  44,2,By the clear Book
  44,3,"Indeed, We sent it down on a blessed night,¬†for We always warn Ћєagainst evilЋЇ"
  44,4,On that night every matter of wisdom is ordained
  44,5,"by a command from Us, for We have always sent ЋєmessengersЋЇ"
  44,6,"as a mercy from your Lord. He ЋєaloneЋЇ is truly the All-Hearing, All-KnowingвАФ"
  44,7,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, if only you had sure faith"
  44,8,"There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. He ЋєaloneЋЇ gives life and causes death. ЋєHe isЋЇ your Lord, and the Lord of your forefathers"
  44,9,"In fact, they are in doubt, amusing themselves"
  44,10,"Wait then ЋєO ProphetЋЇ for the day ЋєwhenЋЇ the sky will be veiled in haze,¬†clearly visible"
  44,11,"overwhelming the people. ЋєThey will cry,ЋЇ вАЬThis is a painful torment"
  44,12,"Our Lord! Remove ЋєthisЋЇ torment from us, ЋєandЋЇ we will certainly believe.вАЭ"
  44,13,"How can they be reminded when a messenger has already come to them, making things clear"
  44,14,"then they turned away from him, saying, вАЬA madman, taught by others!вАЭ"
  44,15,"Indeed, We will remove ЋєthatЋЇ torment for a while, and you ЋєMeccansЋЇ will return Ћєto disbeliefЋЇ"
  44,16,"ЋєThenЋЇ on the Day We will deal ЋєyouЋЇ the fiercest blow, We will surely inflict punishment"
  44,17,"Indeed, before them We tested PharaohвАЩs people: a noble messenger came to them"
  44,18,"Ћєproclaiming,ЋЇ вАЬHand over the servants of Allah to me.¬†I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you"
  44,19,And do not be arrogant with Allah. I have certainly come to you with a compelling proof
  44,20,"And indeed, I seek refuge with my Lord and your Lord so you do not stone me Ћєto deathЋЇ"
  44,21,"ЋєButЋЇ if you do not believe me, then let me be.вАЭ"
  44,22,"Ultimately, he cried out to his Lord, вАЬThese are a wicked people!вАЭ"
  44,23,"ЋєAllah responded,ЋЇ вАЬLeave with My servants at night, for you will surely be pursued"
  44,24,"And leave the sea parted, for they are certainly an army bound to drown.вАЭ"
  44,25,ЋєImagineЋЇ how many gardens and springs the tyrants¬†left behind
  44,26,as well as ЋєvariousЋЇ crops and splendid residences
  44,27,and luxuries which they fully enjoyed
  44,28,So it was. And We awarded it ЋєallЋЇ to another people
  44,29,"Neither heaven nor earth wept over them, nor was their fate delayed"
  44,30,And We certainly delivered the Children of Israel from the humiliating torment
  44,31,"of Pharaoh. He was truly a tyrant, a transgressor"
  44,32,"And indeed, We chose the Israelites knowingly above the others"
  44,33,And We showed them signs in which there was a clear test
  44,34,"Indeed, these ЋєMeccansЋЇ say"
  44,35,"вАЬThere is nothing beyond our first death, and we will never be resurrected"
  44,36,"Bring ЋєbackЋЇ our forefathers, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  44,37,"Are they superior to the people of TubbaвАЩ¬†and those before them? We destroyed them ЋєallЋЇ, ЋєforЋЇ they were truly wicked"
  44,38,We did not create the heavens and the earth and everything in between for sport
  44,39,"We only created them for a purpose, but most of these ЋєpagansЋЇ do not know"
  44,40,Surely the Day of ЋєFinalЋЇ Decision is the time appointed for allвАФ
  44,41,"the Day no kith or kin will be of benefit to another whatsoever, nor will they be helped"
  44,42,"except those shown mercy by Allah. He is truly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  44,43,Surely Ћєthe fruit ofЋЇ the tree of Zaqq√їm
  44,44,will be the food of the evildoer
  44,45,"Like molten metal, it will boil in the bellies"
  44,46,like the boiling of hot water
  44,47,"ЋєIt will be said,ЋЇ вАЬSeize them and drag them into the depths of the Hellfire"
  44,48,Then pour over their heads the torment of boiling water.вАЭ
  44,49,"ЋєThe wicked will be told,ЋЇ вАЬTaste this. You mighty, noble one"
  44,50,This is truly what you ЋєallЋЇ used to doubt.вАЭ
  44,51,"Indeed, the righteous will be in a secure place"
  44,52,amid Gardens and springs
  44,53,"dressed in fine silk and rich brocade, facing one another"
  44,54,So it will be. And We will pair them to maidens with gorgeous eyes
  44,55,There they will call for every fruit in serenity
  44,56,"There they will never taste death, beyond the first death. And He will protect them from the punishment of the HellfireвАФ"
  44,57,as Ћєan act ofЋЇ grace from your Lord. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the ultimate triumph
  44,58,"Indeed, We have made this ЋєQuranЋЇ easy in your own language ЋєO ProphetЋЇ so perhaps they will be mindful"
  44,59,Wait then! They too are certainly waiting
  45,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  45,2,"The revelation of this Book is from AllahвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  45,3,Surely in Ћєthe creation ofЋЇ the heavens and the earth are signs for the believers
  45,4,"And in your own creation, and whatever living beings He dispersed, are signs for people of sure faith"
  45,5,"And ЋєinЋЇ the alternation of the day and the night, the provision¬†sent down from the skies by AllahвАФreviving the earth after its deathвАФand the shifting of the winds, are signs for people of understanding"
  45,6,These are AllahвАЩs revelations which We recite to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in truth. So what message will they believe in after ЋєdenyingЋЇ Allah and His revelations
  45,7,Woe to every sinful liar
  45,8,"They hear AllahвАЩs revelations recited to them, then persist Ћєin denialЋЇ arrogantly as if they did not hear them. So give them good news of a painful punishment"
  45,9,"And whenever they learn anything of Our revelations, they make a mockery of it. It is they who will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  45,10,"Awaiting them is Hell. Their ЋєworldlyЋЇ gains will not be of any benefit to them whatsoever, nor will those protectors they have taken besides Allah. And they will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  45,11,This ЋєQuranЋЇ is ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance. And those who deny their LordвАЩs revelations will suffer the ЋєworstЋЇ torment of agonizing pain
  45,12,"Allah is the One Who has subjected the sea for you so that ships may sail upon it by His command, and that you may seek His bounty, and that perhaps you will be grateful"
  45,13,He ЋєalsoЋЇ subjected for you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earthвАФall by His grace. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect
  45,14,"ЋєO Prophet!ЋЇ Tell the believers to forgive those who do not fear AllahвАЩs days Ћєof tormentЋЇ, so that He will reward each group for what they used to commit"
  45,15,"Whoever does good, it is to their own benefit. And whoever does evil, it is to their own loss. Then to your Lord you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
  45,16,"Indeed, We gave the Children of Israel the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood; granted them good, lawful provisions; and favoured them above the others"
  45,17,We ЋєalsoЋЇ gave them clear commandments regarding ЋєtheirЋЇ faith. But it was not until knowledge came to them that they differed out of mutual envy.¬†Surely your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their differences
  45,18,"Now We have set you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ on the ЋєclearЋЇ Way of faith. So follow it, and do not follow the desires of those who do not know Ћєthe truthЋЇ"
  45,19,"They certainly can be of no benefit to you against Allah whatsoever. Surely the wrongdoers are patrons of each other, whereas Allah is the Patron of the righteous"
  45,20,This ЋєQuranЋЇ is an insight for humanityвАФa guide and mercy for people of sure faith
  45,21,Or do those who commit evil deeds ЋєsimplyЋЇ think that We will make them equalвАФin their life and after their deathвАФto those who believe and do good? How wrong is their judgment
  45,22,"For Allah created the heavens and the earth for a purpose, so that every soul may be paid back for what it has committed. And none will be wronged"
  45,23,"Have you seen ЋєO ProphetЋЇ those who have taken their own desires as their god? ЋєAnd soЋЇ Allah left them to stray knowingly, sealed their hearing and hearts, and placed a cover on their sight. Who then can guide them after Allah? Will you ЋєallЋЇ not then be mindful"
  45,24,"And they argue, вАЬThere is nothing beyond our worldly life. We die;¬†others are born. And nothing destroys us but Ћєthe passage ofЋЇ time.вАЭ Yet they have no knowledge Ћєin supportЋЇ of this ЋєclaimЋЇ. They only speculate"
  45,25,"And whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, their only argument is to say: вАЬBring our forefathers back, if what you say is true!вАЭ"
  45,26,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬЋєIt isЋЇ Allah ЋєWhoЋЇ gives you life, then causes you to die, then will gather you ЋєallЋЇ on the Day of Judgment, about which there is no doubt. But most people do not know.вАЭ"
  45,27,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. On the Day the Hour will be established, the people of falsehood will then be in ЋєtotalЋЇ loss"
  45,28,"And you will see every faith-community on its knees. Every community will be summoned to its record Ћєof deedsЋЇ. ЋєThey all will be told,ЋЇ вАЬThis Day you will be rewarded for what you used to do"
  45,29,"This record of Ours speaks the truth about you. Indeed, We always had your deeds recorded Ћєby the angelsЋЇ.вАЭ"
  45,30,"As for those who believed and did good, their Lord will admit them into His mercy. That is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the absolute triumph"
  45,31,"And as for those who disbelieved, Ћєthey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬWere My revelations not recited to you, yet you acted arrogantly and were a wicked people"
  45,32,"And whenever it was said Ћєto youЋЇ, вАШSurely AllahвАЩs promise Ћєof judgmentЋЇ is true and there is no doubt about the Hour,вАЩ you said ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАШWe do not know what the Hour is! We think it is no more than speculation, and we are not convinced Ћєthat it will ever comeЋЇ.вАЩвАЭ"
  45,33,"And the evil ЋєconsequencesЋЇ of their deeds will unfold before them, and they will be overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  45,34,"It will be said, вАЬThis Day We will neglect you as you neglected the meeting of this Day of yours! Your home will be the Fire, and you will have no helpers"
  45,35,"This is because you made a mockery of AllahвАЩs revelations, and were deluded by ЋєyourЋЇ worldly life.вАЭ So ЋєfromЋЇ that Day ЋєonЋЇ they will not be taken out of the Fire, nor will they be allowed to appease Ћєtheir LordЋЇ"
  45,36,"So all praise is for AllahвАФLord of the heavens and Lord of the earth, Lord of all worlds"
  45,37,"To Him belongs ЋєallЋЇ Majesty in the heavens and the earth. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  46,1,бЄ§√Ґ-Mƒ©m
  46,2,"The revelation of this Book is from AllahвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  46,3,We only created the heavens and the earth and everything in between for a purpose and an appointed term. Yet the disbelievers are turning away from what they have been warned about
  46,4,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬHave you considered whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you invoke besides Allah? Show me what they have created on earth! Or do they have a share in Ћєthe creation ofЋЇ the heavens? Bring me a scripture ЋєrevealedЋЇ before this ЋєQuranЋЇ or a shred of knowledge, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  46,5,"And who could be more astray than those who call upon others besides AllahвАФЋєothersЋЇ that cannot respond to them until the Day of Judgment, and are ЋєevenЋЇ unaware of their calls"
  46,6,"And when ЋєsuchЋЇ people will be gathered together, those ЋєgodsЋЇ will be their enemies and will disown their worship"
  46,7,"Whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers say of the truth when it has come to them, вАЬThis is pure magic.вАЭ"
  46,8,"Or do they say, вАЬHe¬†has fabricated this ЋєQuranЋЇ!вАЭ? Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIf I have done so, then there is nothing whatsoever you can do to save me from Allah. He knows best what ЋєslursЋЇ you indulge about it. Sufficient is He as a Witness between you and me. And He is the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  46,9,"Say, вАЬI am not the first messenger ever sent, nor do I know what will happen to me or you. I only follow what is revealed to me. And I am only sent with a clear warning.вАЭ"
  46,10,"Ask Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬConsider if this ЋєQuranЋЇ is ЋєtrulyЋЇ from Allah and you deny it, and a witness from the Children of Israel attests to it and then believes,¬†whereas you act arrogantly. Surely Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  46,11,"The disbelievers say of the believers, вАЬHad it been ЋєsomethingЋЇ good, they¬†would not have beaten us to it.вАЭ Now since they reject its guidance, they will say, вАЬЋєThis isЋЇ an ancient fabrication!вАЭ"
  46,12,"And before this ЋєQuranЋЇ the Book of Moses was Ћєrevealed asЋЇ a guide and mercy. And this Book is a confirmation, in the Arabic tongue, to warn those who do wrong, and as good news to those who do good"
  46,13,"Surely those who say, вАЬOur Lord is Allah,вАЭ and then remain steadfastвАФthere will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  46,14,"It is they who will be the residents of Paradise, staying there forever, as a reward for what they used to do"
  46,15,"We have commanded people to honour their parents. Their mothers bore them in hardship and delivered them in hardship. Their Ћєperiod ofЋЇ bearing and weaning is thirty months. In time, when the child reaches their prime at the age of forty, they pray, вАЬMy Lord! Inspire me to ЋєalwaysЋЇ be thankful for Your favours which You blessed me and my parents with, and to do good deeds that please You. And instil righteousness in my offspring. I truly repent to You, and I truly submit Ћєto Your WillЋЇ.вАЭ"
  46,16,"It is from these ЋєpeopleЋЇ that We will accept the good they did, and overlook their misdeedsвАФalong with the residents of Paradise, Ћєin fulfilment ofЋЇ the true promise they have been given"
  46,17,"But some scold their parents, вАЬEnough with you! Are you warning me that I will be brought forth Ћєfrom the graveЋЇ, while many generations had already perished before me Ћєfor goodЋЇ?вАЭ The parents cry to Allah for help, Ћєand warn their child,ЋЇ вАЬPity you. Have faith! Surely AllahвАЩs promise is true.вАЭ But the deniers insist, вАЬThis is nothing but ancient fables.вАЭ"
  46,18,"These are the ones against whom the fate of earlier communities of jinn and humans has been justified, ЋєforЋЇ they were truly losers"
  46,19,Each Ћєof the two groupsЋЇ will be ranked according to what they have done so He may fully reward all. And none will be wronged
  46,20,"ЋєWatch forЋЇ the Day ЋєwhenЋЇ the disbelievers will be exposed to the Fire. ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬYou ЋєalreadyЋЇ exhausted your Ћєshare ofЋЇ pleasures during your worldly life, and ЋєfullyЋЇ enjoyed them. So Today you will be rewarded with the torment of disgrace for your arrogance throughout the land with no right, and for your rebelliousness.вАЭ"
  46,21,"And remember the brother of вАЩ»Вd, when he warned his people, who inhabited the sand-hillsвАФthere were certainly warners before and after himвАФЋєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬWorship none but Allah. I truly fear for you the torment of a tremendous day.вАЭ"
  46,22,"They argued, вАЬHave you come to turn us away from our gods? Bring us then whatever you threaten us with, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  46,23,"He responded, вАЬThe knowledge Ћєof its timeЋЇ is only with Allah. I only convey to you what I have been sent with. But I can see that you are a people acting ignorantly.вАЭ"
  46,24,"Then when they saw the torment as a ЋєdenseЋЇ cloud approaching their valleys, they said ЋєhappilyЋЇ, вАЬThis is a cloud bringing us rain.вАЭ ЋєBut H√їd replied,ЋЇ вАЬNo, it is what you sought to hasten: a ЋєfierceЋЇ wind carrying a painful punishment!вАЭ"
  46,25,"It destroyed everything by the command of its Lord, leaving nothing visible except their ruins. This is how We reward the wicked people"
  46,26,"Indeed, We had established them¬†in a way We have not established you ЋєMeccansЋЇ. And We gave them hearing, sight, and intellect. But neither their hearing, sight, nor intellect were of any benefit to them whatsoever, since they persisted in denying AllahвАЩs signs. And ЋєsoЋЇ they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  46,27,We certainly destroyed the societies around you after having varied the signs so perhaps they would return Ћєto the Right PathЋЇ
  46,28,"Why then did those ЋєidolsЋЇ they took as godsвАФhoping to get closer Ћєto HimЋЇвАФnot come to their aid? Instead, they failed them. That is Ћєthe result ofЋЇ their lies and their fabrications"
  46,29,"ЋєRemember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when We sent a group of jinn your way to listen to the Quran. Then, upon hearing it, they said Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬListen quietly!вАЭ Then when it was over, they returned to their fellow jinn as warners"
  46,30,"They declared, вАЬO our fellow jinn! We have truly heard a scripture revealed after Moses, confirming what came before it. It guides to the truth and the Straight Way"
  46,31,"O our fellow jinn! Respond to the caller of Allah and believe in him, He will forgive your sins and protect you from a painful punishment"
  46,32,"And whoever does not respond to the caller of Allah will have no escape on earth, nor will they have any protectors against Him. It is they who are clearly astray.вАЭ"
  46,33,"Do they not realize that Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth and did not tire in creating them,¬†is able to give life to the dead? Yes ЋєindeedЋЇ! He is certainly Most Capable of everything"
  46,34,"And on the Day the disbelievers will be exposed to the Fire, Ћєthey will be asked,ЋЇ вАЬIs this ЋєHereafterЋЇ not the truth?вАЭ They will cry, вАЬAbsolutely, by our Lord!вАЭ It will be said, вАЬThen taste the punishment for your disbelief.вАЭ"
  46,35,"So endure patiently, as did the Messengers of Firm Resolve.¬†And do not Ћєseek toЋЇ hasten Ћєthe tormentЋЇ for the deniers. On the Day they see what they have been threatened with, it will be as if they had only stayed Ћєin this worldЋЇ for an hour of a day.¬†ЋєThis isЋЇ a ЋєsufficientЋЇ warning! Then, will anyone be destroyed except the rebellious people"
  47,1,"Those who disbelieve and hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah, He will render their deeds void"
  47,2,"As for those who believe, do good, and have faith in what has been revealed to MuбЄ•ammadвАФwhich is the truth from their LordвАФHe will absolve them of their sins and improve their condition"
  47,3,"This is because the disbelievers follow falsehood, while the believers follow the truth from their Lord. This is how Allah shows people their true state Ћєof faithЋЇ"
  47,4,"So when you meet the disbelievers Ћєin battleЋЇ, strike ЋєtheirЋЇ necks until you have thoroughly subdued them, then bind them firmly. Later Ћєfree them either asЋЇ an act of grace or by ransom until the war comes to an end. So will it be. Had Allah willed, He ЋєHimselfЋЇ could have inflicted punishment on them. But He does Ћєthis only toЋЇ test some of you by means of others. And those who are martyred in the cause of Allah,¬†He will never render their deeds void"
  47,5,"He will guide them Ћєto their rewardЋЇ, improve their condition"
  47,6,"and admit them into Paradise, having made it known to them"
  47,7,"O believers! If you stand up for Allah, He will help you and make your steps firm"
  47,8,"As for the disbelievers, may they be doomed and may He render their deeds void"
  47,9,"That is because they detest what Allah has revealed, so He has rendered their deeds void"
  47,10,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those before them? Allah annihilated them, and a similar fate awaits the disbelievers"
  47,11,This is because Allah is the Patron of the believers while the disbelievers have no patron
  47,12,"Surely Allah will admit those who believe and do good into Gardens under which rivers flow. As for the disbelievers, they enjoy themselves and feed like cattle.¬†But the Fire will be their home"
  47,13,"ЋєImagine, O Prophet,ЋЇ how many societies We destroyed that were far superior in might than your societyвАФwhich drove you outвАФand there was none to help them"
  47,14,Can those ЋєbelieversЋЇ who stand on clear proof from their Lord be like those whose evil deeds are made appealing to them and ЋєonlyЋЇ follow their desires
  47,15,"The description of the Paradise promised to the righteous is that in it are rivers of fresh water, rivers of milk that never changes in taste, rivers of wine delicious to drink, and rivers of pure honey. There they will ЋєalsoЋЇ have all kinds of fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord. ЋєCan they beЋЇ like those who will stay in the Fire forever, left to drink boiling water that will tear apart their insides"
  47,16,"There are some of them who listen to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, but when they depart from you, they say ЋєmockinglyЋЇ to those ЋєbelieversЋЇ gifted with knowledge, вАЬWhat did he just say?вАЭ These are the ones whose hearts Allah has sealed and who ЋєonlyЋЇ follow their desires"
  47,17,"As for those who are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided, He increases them in guidance and blesses them with righteousness"
  47,18,"Are they only waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise? Yet Ћєsome ofЋЇ its signs have already come.¬†Once it actually befalls them, will it not be too late to be mindful"
  47,19,"So, know Ћєwell, O Prophet,ЋЇ that there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Allah. And seek forgiveness for your shortcomings¬†and for Ћєthe sins ofЋЇ the believing men and women. For Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows your movements and places of rest ЋєO peopleЋЇ"
  47,20,"And the believers say, вАЬIf only a s√їrah¬†was revealed Ћєallowing self-defenceЋЇ!вАЭ Yet when a precise s√їrah¬†is revealed, in which fighting is ЋєexplicitlyЋЇ mentioned, you see those with sickness in their hearts staring at you like someone in the throes of death. It would have been better for them"
  47,21,"to obey and speak rightly. Then when fighting was ordained, it surely would have been better for them if they were true to Allah"
  47,22,"Now if you ЋєhypocritesЋЇ turn away, perhaps you would then spread corruption throughout the land and sever your Ћєties ofЋЇ kinship"
  47,23,"These are the ones who Allah has condemned, deafening them and blinding their eyes"
  47,24,Do they not then reflect on the Quran? Or are there locks upon their hearts
  47,25,"Indeed, those who relapse Ћєinto disbeliefЋЇ after ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance has become clear to them, Ћєit isЋЇ Satan ЋєthatЋЇ has tempted them, luring them with false hopes"
  47,26,"That is because they said ЋєprivatelyЋЇ to those who ЋєalsoЋЇ detest what Allah has revealed, вАЬWe will obey you in some matters.вАЭ¬†But Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows what they are hiding"
  47,27,"Then how ЋєhorribleЋЇ will it be when the angels take their souls, beating their faces and backs"
  47,28,"This is because they follow whatever displeases Allah and hate whatever pleases Him, so He has rendered their deeds void"
  47,29,Or do those with sickness in their hearts think that Allah will not Ћєbe able toЋЇ expose their malice
  47,30,"Had We willed, We could have truly shown them to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, and you would have certainly recognized them by their appearance. But you will surely recognize them by their tone of speech. And Allah ЋєfullyЋЇ knows your doings ЋєO peopleЋЇ"
  47,31,"We will certainly test you ЋєbelieversЋЇ until We prove those of you who ЋєtrulyЋЇ struggle Ћєin AllahвАЩs causeЋЇ and remain steadfast, and reveal how you conduct yourselves"
  47,32,"Indeed, those who disbelieve, hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah, and defy the Messenger after ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance has become clear to them; they will not harm Allah in the least, but He will render their deeds void"
  47,33,"O believers! Obey Allah and obey the Messenger, and do not let your deeds be in vain"
  47,34,"Surely those who disbelieve, hinder ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah, and then die as disbelievers; Allah will never forgive them"
  47,35,"So do not falter or cry for peace, for you will have the upper hand and Allah is with you. And He will never let your deeds go to waste"
  47,36,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement. But if you are faithful and mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ, He will grant you your ЋєfullЋЇ reward, and will not ask you Ћєto donate allЋЇ your wealth"
  47,37,"If He were to do so and pressure you, you would withhold and He would bring out your resentment"
  47,38,"Here you are, being invited to donate Ћєa littleЋЇ in the cause of Allah. Still some of you withhold. And whoever does so, it is only to their own loss. For Allah is the Self-Sufficient, whereas you stand in need Ћєof HimЋЇ. If you ЋєstillЋЇ turn away, He will replace you with another people. And they will not be like you"
  48,1,"Indeed, We have granted you a clear triumph ЋєO ProphetЋЇ"
  48,2,"so that Allah may forgive you for your past and future shortcomings,¬†perfect His favour upon you, guide you along the Straight Path"
  48,3,and so that Allah will help you tremendously
  48,4,"He is the One Who sent down serenity upon the hearts of the believers so that they may increase even more in their faith. To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belong the forces of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  48,5,So He may admit believing men and women¬†into Gardens under which rivers flowвАФto stay there foreverвАФand absolve them of their sins. And that is a supreme achievement in the sight of Allah
  48,6,"Also Ћєso thatЋЇ He may punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, who harbour evil thoughts of Allah.¬†May ill-fate befall them! Allah is displeased with them. He has condemned them and prepared for them Hell. What an evil destination"
  48,7,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belong the forces of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  48,8,"Indeed, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ We have sent you as a witness, a deliverer of good news, and a warner"
  48,9,"so that you ЋєbelieversЋЇ may have faith in Allah and His Messenger, support and honour him, and glorify Allah morning and evening"
  48,10,"Surely those who pledge allegiance to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are actually pledging allegiance to Allah. AllahвАЩs Hand is over theirs. Whoever breaks their pledge, it will only be to their own loss. And whoever fulfils their pledge to Allah, He will grant them a great reward"
  48,11,"The nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, will say to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, вАЬWe were preoccupied with our wealth and families, so ask for forgiveness for us.вАЭ They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts. Say, вАЬWho then can stand between you and Allah in any way, if He intends harm or benefit for you? In fact, Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  48,12,"The truth is: you thought that the Messenger and the believers would never return to their families again. And that was made appealing in your hearts. You harboured evil thoughts Ћєabout AllahЋЇ, and ЋєsoЋЇ became a doomed people.вАЭ"
  48,13,"And whoever does not believe in Allah and His Messenger, then We surely have prepared for the disbelievers a blazing Fire"
  48,14,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  48,15,"Those who stayed behind will say, when you ЋєbelieversЋЇ set out to take the spoils of war, вАЬLet us accompany you.вАЭ They wish to change AllahвАЩs promise.¬†Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYou will not accompany us. This is what Allah has said before.вАЭ They will then say, вАЬIn fact, you are driven by jealousy against us!вАЭ¬†The truth is: they can hardly comprehend"
  48,16,"Say to nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, вАЬYou will be called Ћєto fightЋЇ against a people of great might,¬†who you will fight unless they submit. If you then obey, Allah will grant you a fine reward. But if you turn away as you did before, He will inflict upon you a painful punishment.вАЭ"
  48,17,"There is no blame on the blind, or the disabled, or the sick Ћєfor staying behindЋЇ. And whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger will be admitted by Him into Gardens under which rivers flow. But whoever turns away will be subjected by Him to a painful punishment"
  48,18,"Indeed, Allah was pleased with the believers when they pledged allegiance to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ under the tree. He knew what was in their hearts, so He sent down serenity upon them and rewarded them with a victory at hand"
  48,19,"and many spoils of war they will gain. For Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  48,20,"Allah has promised you ЋєbelieversЋЇ abundant spoils, which you will gain, so He hastened this ЋєtruceЋЇ¬†for you. And He has held peopleвАЩs hands back from ЋєharmingЋЇ you, so it may be a sign for the believers, and so He may guide you along the Straight Path"
  48,21,And Ћєthere areЋЇ other gains which are beyond your reach that Allah is keeping in store Ћєfor youЋЇ. For Allah is Most Capable of everything
  48,22,"If the disbelievers were to fight you, they would certainly flee.¬†Then they would never find any protector or helper"
  48,23,"ЋєThis isЋЇ AllahвАЩs way, already long established Ћєin the pastЋЇ. And you will find no change in AllahвАЩs way"
  48,24,"He is the One Who held back their hands from you and your hands from them in the valley of ЋєбЄ§udaibiyah, nearЋЇ Mecca, after giving you the upper hand over Ћєa group ofЋЇ them.¬†And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  48,25,"They are the ones who persisted in disbelief and hindered you from the Sacred Mosque, preventing the sacrificial animals from reaching their destination.¬†ЋєWe would have let you march through Mecca,ЋЇ had there not been believing men and women, unknown to you. You might have trampled them underfoot, incurring guilt for Ћєwhat you did toЋЇ them unknowingly. That was so Allah may admit into His mercy whoever He wills.¬†Had those ЋєunknownЋЇ believers stood apart, We would have certainly inflicted a painful punishment on the disbelievers"
  48,26,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the disbelievers had filled their hearts with prideвАФthe pride of Ћєpre-IslamicЋЇ ignoranceвАФthen Allah sent down His serenity upon His Messenger and the believers, inspiring them to uphold the declaration of faith,¬†for they were better entitled and more worthy of it. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  48,27,"Indeed, Allah will fulfil His MessengerвАЩs vision in all truth: Allah willing, you will surely enter the Sacred Mosque, in securityвАФЋєsome withЋЇ heads shaved and Ћєothers withЋЇ hair shortenedвАФwithout fear.¬†He knew what you did not know, so He first granted you the triumph at hand"
  48,28,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ЋєrightЋЇ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others. And sufficient is Allah as a Witness"
  48,29,"MuбЄ•ammad is the Messenger of Allah. And those with him are firm with the disbelievers¬†and compassionate with one another. You see them bowing and prostrating¬†Ћєin prayerЋЇ, seeking AllahвАЩs bounty and pleasure. The sign Ћєof brightness can be seenЋЇ on their faces from the trace of prostrating Ћєin prayerЋЇ. This is their description in the Torah.¬†And their parable in the Gospel is that of a seed that sprouts its ЋєtinyЋЇ branches, making it strong. Then it becomes thick, standing firmly on its stem, to the delight of the plantersвАФin this way Allah makes the believers a source of dismay for the disbelievers.¬†To those of them who believe and do good, Allah has promised forgiveness and a great reward"
  49,1,"O believers! Do not proceed Ћєin any matterЋЇ before Ћєa decree fromЋЇ Allah and His Messenger. And fear Allah. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  49,2,"O believers! Do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet, nor speak loudly to him as you do to one another,¬†or your deeds will become void while you are unaware"
  49,3,"Indeed, those who lower their voices in the presence of AllahвАЩs Messenger are the ones whose hearts Allah has refined for righteousness. They will have forgiveness and a great reward"
  49,4,"Indeed, most of those who call out to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ from outside ЋєyourЋЇ private quarters have no understanding Ћєof mannersЋЇ"
  49,5,"Had they been patient until you could come out to them, it would have certainly been better for them. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  49,6,"O believers, if an evildoer brings you any news, verify ЋєitЋЇ so you do not harm people unknowingly, becoming regretful for what you have done"
  49,7,"And keep in mind that AllahвАЩs Messenger is ЋєstillЋЇ in your midst. If he were to yield to you in many matters, you would surely suffer Ћєthe consequencesЋЇ.¬†But Allah has endeared faith to you, making it appealing in your hearts. And He has made disbelief, rebelliousness, and disobedience detestable to you. Those are the ones rightly guided"
  49,8,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a bounty and a blessing from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  49,9,"And if two groups of believers fight each other, then make peace between them. But if one of them transgresses against the other, then fight against the transgressing group until they Ћєare willing toЋЇ submit to the rule of Allah. If they do so, then make peace between both ЋєgroupsЋЇ in all fairness and act justly. Surely Allah loves those who uphold justice"
  49,10,"The believers are but one brotherhood, so make peace between your brothers. And be mindful of Allah so you may be shown mercy"
  49,11,"O believers! Do not let some ЋєmenЋЇ ridicule others, they may be better than them, nor let ЋєsomeЋЇ women ridicule other women, they may be better than them. Do not defame one another, nor call each other by offensive nicknames. How evil it is to act rebelliously after having faith! And whoever does not repent, it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ wrongdoers"
  49,12,"O believers! Avoid many suspicions, ЋєforЋЇ indeed, some suspicions are sinful. And do not spy, nor backbite one another. Would any of you like to eat the flesh of their dead brother? You would despise that!¬†And fear Allah. Surely Allah is ЋєtheЋЇ Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  49,13,"O humanity! Indeed, We created you from a male and a female, and made you into peoples and tribes so that you may Ћєget toЋЇ know one another. Surely the most noble of you in the sight of Allah is the most righteous among you. Allah is truly All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  49,14,"ЋєSome ofЋЇ the nomadic Arabs say, вАЬWe believe.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYou have not believed. But say, вАШWe have submitted,вАЩ for faith has not yet entered your hearts.¬†But if you obey Allah and His Messenger ЋєwholeheartedlyЋЇ, He will not discount anything from Ћєthe reward ofЋЇ your deeds. Allah is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  49,15,The ЋєtrueЋЇ believers are only those who believe in Allah and His MessengerвАФnever doubtingвАФand strive with their wealth and their lives in the cause of Allah. They are the ones true in faith
  49,16,"Say, вАЬDo you inform Allah of your faith, when Allah ЋєalreadyЋЇ knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth? And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things.вАЭ"
  49,17,"They regard their acceptance of Islam as a favour to you. Tell Ћєthem, O ProphetЋЇ, вАЬDo not regard your Islam as a favour to me. Rather, it is Allah Who has done you a favour by guiding you to the faith, if ЋєindeedЋЇ you are faithful"
  49,18,Surely Allah knows the unseen of the heavens and earth. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do.вАЭ
  50,1,Q√£f. By the glorious Quran
  50,2,"ЋєAll will be resurrected,ЋЇ yet the deniers are astonished that a warner has come to them from among themselves Ћєwarning of resurrectionЋЇ. So the disbelievers say, вАЬThis is an astonishing thing"
  50,3,"ЋєWill we be returned to life,ЋЇ when we are dead and reduced to dust? Such a return is impossible.вАЭ"
  50,4,"We certainly know what the earth consumes of them Ћєafter their deathЋЇ, and with us is a well-preserved Record"
  50,5,"In fact, they reject the truth when it has come to them, so they are in a confused state"
  50,6,"Have they not then looked at the sky above them: how We built it and adorned it Ћєwith starsЋЇ, leaving it flawless"
  50,7,"As for the earth, We spread it out and placed upon it firm mountains, and produced in it every type of pleasant plantвАФ"
  50,8,Ћєall asЋЇ an insight and a reminder to every servant who turns Ћєto AllahЋЇ
  50,9,"And We send down blessed rain from the sky, bringing forth gardens and grains for harvest"
  50,10,and towering palm trees ЋєloadedЋЇ with clustered fruit
  50,11,ЋєasЋЇ a provision for ЋєOurЋЇ servants. And with this ЋєrainЋЇ We revive a lifeless land. Similar is the emergence Ћєfrom the gravesЋЇ
  50,12,"Before them, the people of Noah denied Ћєthe truth,ЋЇ as did the people of the Water-pit,¬†Tham√їd"
  50,13,"вАЩ»Вd, Pharaoh, the kinfolk of Lot"
  50,14,"the residents of the Forest,¬†and the people of TubbaвАЩ.¬†Each rejected ЋєtheirЋЇ messenger, so My warning was fulfilled"
  50,15,"Were We incapable of creating ЋєthemЋЇ the first time? In fact, they are in doubt about ЋєtheirЋЇ re-creation"
  50,16,"Indeed, Ћєit isЋЇ We ЋєWhoЋЇ created humankind and ЋєfullyЋЇ know what their souls whisper to them, and We are closer to them than ЋєtheirЋЇ jugular vein"
  50,17,"As the two recording-angelsвАФЋєoneЋЇ sitting to the right, and Ћєthe other toЋЇ the leftвАФnote ЋєeverythingЋЇ"
  50,18,not a word does a person utter without having a ЋєvigilantЋЇ observer ready Ћєto write it downЋЇ
  50,19,"ЋєUltimately,ЋЇ with the throes of death will come the truth.¬†This is what you were trying to escape"
  50,20,And the Trumpet will be blown.¬†This is the Day Ћєyou wereЋЇ warned of
  50,21,Each soul will come forth with an angel to drive it and another to testify
  50,22,"ЋєIt will be said to the denier,ЋЇ вАЬYou were totally heedless of this. Now We have lifted this veil of yours, so Today your sight is sharp!вАЭ"
  50,23,"And oneвАЩs accompanying-angel will say, вАЬHere is the record ready with me.вАЭ"
  50,24,"ЋєIt will be said to both angels,ЋЇ вАЬThrow into Hell every stubborn disbeliever"
  50,25,"withholder of good, transgressor, and doubter"
  50,26,who set up another god with Allah. So cast them into the severe punishment.вАЭ
  50,27,"OneвАЩs ЋєdevilishЋЇ associate will say, вАЬOur Lord! I did not make them transgress. Rather, they were far astray Ћєon their ownЋЇ.вАЭ"
  50,28,"Allah will respond, вАЬDo not dispute in My presence, since I had already given you a warning"
  50,29,"My Word cannot be changed,¬†nor am I unjust to ЋєMyЋЇ creation.вАЭ"
  50,30,"ЋєBeware ofЋЇ the Day We will ask Hell, вАЬAre you full ЋєyetЋЇ?вАЭ And it will respond, вАЬAre there any more?вАЭ"
  50,31,"And Paradise will be brought near to the righteous, not far off"
  50,32,"ЋєAnd it will be said to them,ЋЇ вАЬThis is what you were promised, for whoever ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto AllahЋЇ and kept up ЋєHis commandmentsЋЇвАФ"
  50,33,"who were in awe of the Most Compassionate without seeing ЋєHimЋЇ,¬†and have come with a heart turning Ћєonly to HimЋЇ"
  50,34,Enter it in peace. This is the Day of eternal life!вАЭ
  50,35,"There they will have whatever they desire, and with Us is ЋєevenЋЇ more"
  50,36,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many peoples We destroyed before them, who were far mightier than them. Then Ћєwhen the torment came,ЋЇ they ЋєdesperatelyЋЇ sought refuge in the land. ЋєButЋЇ was there any escape"
  50,37,Surely in this is a reminder for whoever has a ЋєmindfulЋЇ heart and lends an attentive ear
  50,38,"Indeed, We created the heavens and the earth and everything in between in six Days,¬†and We were not ЋєevenЋЇ touched with fatigue"
  50,39,So be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ with what they say. And glorify the praises of your Lord before sunrise and before sunset
  50,40,And glorify Him during part of the night¬†and after the prayers
  50,41,And listen! On the Day the caller will call out from a near place
  50,42,"the Day all will hear the ЋєmightyЋЇ Blast in ЋєallЋЇ truth,¬†that will be the Day of emergence Ћєfrom the gravesЋЇ"
  50,43,It is certainly We Who give life and cause death. And to Us is the final return
  50,44,"ЋєBeware ofЋЇ the Day the earth will split open, letting them rush forth. That will be an easy gathering for Us"
  50,45,We know best what they say. And you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are not ЋєthereЋЇ to compel them Ћєto believeЋЇ. So remind with the Quran ЋєonlyЋЇ those who fear My warning
  51,1,By the winds scattering ЋєdustЋЇ
  51,2,and Ћєthe cloudsЋЇ loaded with rain
  51,3,and Ћєthe shipsЋЇ gliding with ease
  51,4,and Ћєthe angelsЋЇ administering affairs by ЋєAllahвАЩsЋЇ command
  51,5,"Indeed, what you are promised is true"
  51,6,And the Judgment will certainly come to pass
  51,7,ЋєAndЋЇ by the heavens in their marvellous design
  51,8,Surely you are ЋєlostЋЇ in conflicting views Ћєregarding the truthЋЇ
  51,9,Only those Ћєdestined to beЋЇ deluded are turned away from it
  51,10,Condemned are the liarsвАФ
  51,11,"those who are ЋєsteepedЋЇ in ignorance, totally heedless"
  51,12,"They ask ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhen is this Day of Judgment?вАЭ"
  51,13,ЋєIt isЋЇ the Day they will be tormented over the Fire
  51,14,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬTaste your torment! This is what you sought to hasten.вАЭ"
  51,15,"Indeed, the righteous will be amid Gardens and springs"
  51,16,ЋєjoyfullyЋЇ receiving what their Lord will grant them. Before this ЋєrewardЋЇ they were truly good-doers Ћєin the worldЋЇ
  51,17,they used to sleep only little in the night
  51,18,and pray for forgiveness before dawn
  51,19,And in their wealth there was a rightful share ЋєfulfilledЋЇ for the beggar and the poor
  51,20,There are ЋєcountlessЋЇ signs on earth for those with sure faith
  51,21,as there are within yourselves. Can you not see
  51,22,In heaven is your sustenance and whatever you are promised
  51,23,Then by the Lord of heaven and earth! ЋєAllЋЇ this is certainly as true as Ћєthe fact thatЋЇ you can speak
  51,24,Has the story of AbrahamвАЩs honoured guests reached you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ
  51,25,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when they entered his presence and greeted Ћєhim withЋЇ, вАЬPeace!вАЭ He replied, вАЬPeace Ћєbe upon youЋЇ!вАЭ ЋєThen he said to himself,ЋЇ вАЬЋєThese areЋЇ an unfamiliar people.вАЭ"
  51,26,Then he slipped off to his family and brought a fat ЋєroastedЋЇ calf
  51,27,"and placed it before them, asking, вАЬWill you not eat?вАЭ"
  51,28,"ЋєThey did not eat,ЋЇ so he grew fearful of them.¬†They reassured ЋєhimЋЇ, вАЬDo not be afraid,вАЭ and gave him good news of a knowledgeable son"
  51,29,"Then his wife came forward with a cry, clasping her forehead Ћєin astonishmentЋЇ, exclaiming, вАЬЋєA baby fromЋЇ a barren, old woman!вАЭ"
  51,30,"They replied, вАЬSuch has your Lord decreed. He is truly the All-Wise, All-Knowing.вАЭ"
  51,31,"ЋєLater,ЋЇ Abraham asked, вАЬWhat is your mission, O messengers?вАЭ"
  51,32,"They replied, вАЬWe have actually been sent to a wicked people"
  51,33,to send upon them stones of ЋєbakedЋЇ clay
  51,34,marked by your Lord for the transgressors.вАЭ
  51,35,Then Ћєbefore the tormentЋЇ We evacuated the believers from the city
  51,36,But We only found one family that had submitted Ћєto AllahЋЇ
  51,37,And We have left a sign there¬†Ћєas a lessonЋЇ for those who fear the painful punishment
  51,38,"And in Ћєthe story ofЋЇ Moses Ћєwas another lesson,ЋЇ when We sent him to Pharaoh with compelling proof"
  51,39,"but Pharaoh was carried away by his power, saying Ћєof MosesЋЇ, вАЬA magician or a madman!вАЭ"
  51,40,"So We seized him and his soldiers, casting them into the sea while he was blameworthy"
  51,41,"And in Ћєthe story ofЋЇ вАЩ√Вd Ћєwas another lesson,ЋЇ when We sent against them the devastating wind"
  51,42,There was nothing it came upon that it did not reduce to ashes
  51,43,"And in Ћєthe story ofЋЇ Tham√їd Ћєwas another lesson,ЋЇ when they were told, вАЬEnjoy yourselves ЋєonlyЋЇ for a ЋєshortЋЇ while.вАЭ"
  51,44,"Still they persisted in defying the commands of their Lord, so they were overtaken by a ЋєmightyЋЇ blast while they were looking on"
  51,45,"Then they were not able to rise up, nor were they helped"
  51,46,And the people of Noah Ћєhad also been destroyedЋЇ earlier. They were truly a rebellious people
  51,47,"We built the universe with ЋєgreatЋЇ might, and We are certainly expanding ЋєitЋЇ"
  51,48,"As for the earth, We spread it out. How superbly did We smooth it out"
  51,49,And We created pairs of all things¬†so perhaps you would be mindful
  51,50,"So Ћєproclaim, O ProphetЋЇ: вАЬFlee to Allah! I am truly sent by Him with a clear warning to you"
  51,51,And do not set up another god with Allah. I am truly sent by Him with a clear warning to you.вАЭ
  51,52,"Similarly, no messenger came to those before them without being told: вАЬA magician or a madman!вАЭ"
  51,53,"Have they passed this Ћєclich√©ЋЇ down to one another? In fact, they have ЋєallЋЇ been a transgressing people"
  51,54,"So ЋєnowЋЇ turn away from them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, for you will not be blamed"
  51,55,But Ћєcontinue toЋЇ remind. For certainly reminders benefit the believers
  51,56,I did not create jinn and humans except to worship Me
  51,57,"I seek no provision from them, nor do I need them to feed Me"
  51,58,"Indeed, Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Supreme ProviderвАФLord of all Power, Ever Mighty"
  51,59,The wrongdoers will certainly have a share Ћєof the tormentЋЇ like that of their predecessors. So do not let them ask Me to hasten ЋєitЋЇ
  51,60,Woe then to the disbelievers when they face their Day which they are warned of
  52,1,By Mount бєђ√їr
  52,2,And by the Book written
  52,3,on open pages Ћєfor all to readЋЇ
  52,4,And by the ЋєSacredЋЇ House frequently visited
  52,5,And by the canopy raised ЋєhighЋЇ
  52,6,And by the seas set on fire
  52,7,"Indeed, the punishment of your Lord will come to passвАФ"
  52,8,none will avert itвАФ
  52,9,on the Day the heavens will be shaken violently
  52,10,and the mountains will be blown away entirely
  52,11,Then woe on that Day to the deniersвАФ
  52,12,those who amuse themselves with falsehood
  52,13,ЋєIt isЋЇ the Day they will be fiercely shoved into the Fire of Hell
  52,14,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬThis is the Fire which you used to deny"
  52,15,"Is this magic, or do you not see"
  52,16,Burn in it! It is the same whether you endure ЋєitЋЇ patiently or not.¬†You are only rewarded for what you used to do.вАЭ
  52,17,"Indeed, the righteous will be in Gardens and bliss"
  52,18,enjoying whatever their Lord will have granted them. And their Lord will have protected them from the torment of the Hellfire
  52,19,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬEat and drink happily for what you used to do.вАЭ"
  52,20,"They will be reclining on thrones, ЋєneatlyЋЇ lined up Ћєfacing each otherЋЇ. And We will pair them to maidens with gorgeous eyes"
  52,21,"As for those who believe and whose descendants follow them in faith, We will elevate their descendants to their rank, never discounting anything Ћєof the rewardЋЇ of their deeds. Every person will reap only what they sowed"
  52,22,And We will ЋєcontinuallyЋЇ provide them with whatever fruit or meat they desire
  52,23,"They will pass around to each other a drink Ћєof pure wine,ЋЇ which leads to no idle talk or sinfulness"
  52,24,And they will be waited on by their youthful servants like spotless pearls
  52,25,They will turn to one another inquisitively
  52,26,"They will say, вАЬBefore Ћєthis rewardЋЇ we used to be in awe Ћєof AllahЋЇ in the midst of our people"
  52,27,So Allah has graced us and protected us from the torment of ЋєHellвАЩsЋЇ scorching heat
  52,28,"Indeed, we used to call upon Him ЋєaloneЋЇ before. He is truly the Most Kind, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  52,29,"So Ћєcontinue toЋЇ remind Ћєall, O ProphetЋЇ. For you, by the grace of your Lord, are not a fortune-teller or a madman"
  52,30,"Or do they say, вАЬЋєHe isЋЇ a poet, for whom we ЋєeagerlyЋЇ await an ill-fate!вАЭ"
  52,31,"Say, вАЬKeep waiting! I too am waiting with you.вАЭ"
  52,32,Or do their ЋєintelligentЋЇ minds prompt them to this ЋєparadoxЋЇ?¬†Or are they ЋєjustЋЇ a transgressing people
  52,33,"Or do they say, вАЬHe made this ЋєQuranЋЇ up!вАЭ? In fact, they have no faith"
  52,34,"Let them then produce something like it, if what they say is true"
  52,35,"Or were they created by nothing, or are they Ћєtheir ownЋЇ creators"
  52,36,"Or did they create the heavens and the earth? In fact, they have no firm belief Ћєin AllahЋЇ"
  52,37,"Or do they possess the treasuries of your Lord, or are they in control Ћєof everythingЋЇ"
  52,38,"Or do they have a stairway, by which they eavesdrop Ћєon the heavensЋЇ? Then let those who do so bring a compelling proof"
  52,39,"Or does He have daughters Ћєas you claimЋЇ, while you Ћєprefer toЋЇ have sons"
  52,40,Or are you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ asking them for a reward Ћєfor the messageЋЇ so that they are overburdened by debt
  52,41,"Or do they have access to Ћєthe Record inЋЇ the unseen, so they copy it Ћєfor all to seeЋЇ"
  52,42,Or do they intend to scheme Ћєagainst the ProphetЋЇ? Then it is the disbelievers who will fall victim to ЋєtheirЋЇ schemes
  52,43,Or do they have a god other than Allah? Glorified is Allah far above what they associate Ћєwith HimЋЇ
  52,44,"If they were to see a ЋєdeadlyЋЇ piece of the sky fall down Ћєupon themЋЇ, still they would say, вАЬЋєThis is justЋЇ a pile of clouds.вАЭ"
  52,45,So leave them until they face their Day in which they will be struck deadвАФ
  52,46,"the Day their scheming will be of no benefit to them whatsoever, nor will they be helped"
  52,47,"Also, the wrongdoers will certainly have another torment before that ЋєDayЋЇ, but most of them do not know"
  52,48,"So be patient with your LordвАЩs decree, for you are truly under Our ЋєwatchfulЋЇ Eyes. And glorify the praises of your Lord when you rise"
  52,49,And glorify Him during part of the night and at the fading of the stars
  53,1,By the stars when they fade away
  53,2,Your fellow man¬†is neither misguided nor astray
  53,3,Nor does he speak of his own whims
  53,4,It is only a revelation sent down Ћєto himЋЇ
  53,5,He has been taught by one ЋєangelЋЇ of mighty power
  53,6,"and great perfection, who once rose to ЋєhisЋЇ true form"
  53,7,while on the highest point above the horizon
  53,8,"then he approached Ћєthe ProphetЋЇ, coming so close"
  53,9,that he was only two arms-lengths away or even less
  53,10,Then Allah revealed to His servant what He revealed Ћєthrough GabrielЋЇ
  53,11,The ЋєProphetвАЩsЋЇ heart did not doubt what he saw
  53,12,How can you ЋєO pagansЋЇ then dispute with him regarding what he saw
  53,13,And he certainly saw that Ћєangel descendЋЇ a second time
  53,14,at the Lote Tree of the most extreme limit Ћєin the seventh heavenЋЇвАФ
  53,15,near which is the Garden of ЋєEternalЋЇ ResidenceвАФ
  53,16,while the Lote Tree was overwhelmed with ЋєheavenlyЋЇ splendours
  53,17,"The ЋєProphetвАЩsЋЇ sight never wandered, nor did it overreach"
  53,18,He certainly saw some of his LordвАЩs greatest signs
  53,19,"Now, have you considered Ћєthe idols ofЋЇ L√Ґt¬†and вАЩUzza"
  53,20,"and the third one, Man√Ґt,¬†as well"
  53,21,Do you Ћєprefer toЋЇ have sons while Ћєyou attributeЋЇ to Him daughters
  53,22,Then this is ЋєtrulyЋЇ a biased distribution
  53,23,"These ЋєidolsЋЇ are mere names that you and your forefathers have made upвАФa practice Allah has never authorized. They follow nothing but ЋєinheritedЋЇ assumptions and whatever ЋєtheirЋЇ souls desire, although ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance has already come to them from their Lord"
  53,24,Or should every person ЋєsimplyЋЇ have whatever ЋєintercessorsЋЇ they desire
  53,25,"In fact, to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs this world and the next"
  53,26,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many ЋєnobleЋЇ angels are in the heavens! ЋєEvenЋЇ their intercession would be of no benefit whatsoever, until Allah gives permission to whoever He wills and Ћєonly for the people HeЋЇ approves"
  53,27,"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter label angels as female"
  53,28,although they have no knowledge Ћєin supportЋЇ of this. They follow nothing but ЋєinheritedЋЇ assumptions. And surely assumptions can in no way replace the truth
  53,29,"So turn away ЋєO ProphetЋЇ from whoever has shunned Our Reminder,¬†only seeking the ЋєfleetingЋЇ life of this world"
  53,30,This is the extent of their knowledge. Surely your Lord knows best who has strayed from His Way and who is ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  53,31,"To Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth so that He may reward the evildoers according to what they did, and reward the good-doers with the finest rewardвАФ"
  53,32,"those who avoid major sins and shameful deeds, despite Ћєstumbling onЋЇ minor sins. Surely your Lord is infinite in forgiveness. He knew well what would become of you as He created you from the earth¬†and while you were ЋєstillЋЇ fetuses in the wombs of your mothers.¬†So do not ЋєfalselyЋЇ elevate yourselves. He knows best who is ЋєtrulyЋЇ righteous"
  53,33,"Have you seen the one who turned away Ћєfrom Islam,ЋЇ"
  53,34,"and ЋєinitiallyЋЇ paid a little Ћєfor his salvationЋЇ, and then stopped"
  53,35,Does he have the knowledge of the unseen so that he sees Ћєthe HereafterЋЇ
  53,36,Or has he not been informed of what is in the Scripture of Moses
  53,37,"and Ћєthat ofЋЇ Abraham, who ЋєperfectlyЋЇ fulfilled Ћєhis covenantЋЇ"
  53,38,ЋєThey stateЋЇ that no soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another
  53,39,and that each person will only have what they endeavoured towards
  53,40,and that Ћєthe outcome ofЋЇ their endeavours will be seen Ћєin their recordЋЇ
  53,41,then they will be fully rewarded
  53,42,and that to your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ is the ultimate return Ћєof all thingsЋЇ
  53,43,"Moreover, He is the One Who brings about joy and sadness"
  53,44,And He is the One Who gives life and causes death
  53,45,And He created the pairsвАФmales and femalesвАФ
  53,46,from a sperm-drop when it is emitted
  53,47,And it is upon Him to bring about re-creation
  53,48,And He is the One Who enriches and impoverishes
  53,49,And He alone is the Lord of Sirius
  53,50,And He destroyed the first Ћєpeople ofЋЇ вАЩ»Вd
  53,51,"and ЋєthenЋЇ Tham√їd,¬†sparing no one"
  53,52,"And before Ћєthat He destroyedЋЇ the people of Noah, who were truly far worse in wrongdoing and transgression"
  53,53,And Ћєit wasЋЇ He ЋєWhoЋЇ turned the cities Ћєof Sodom and GomorrahЋЇ upside down
  53,54,How overwhelming was what covered ЋєthemЋЇ
  53,55,"Now, which of your LordвАЩs favours will you dispute"
