  54,1,The Hour has drawn near and the moon was split Ћєin twoЋЇ
  54,2,"Yet, whenever they see a sign, they turn away,¬†saying, вАЬSame old magic!вАЭ"
  54,3,They rejected Ћєthe truthЋЇ and followed their own desiresвАФand every matter will be settledвАФ
  54,4,even though the stories Ћєof destroyed nationsЋЇ that have already come to them are a sufficient deterrent
  54,5,"ЋєThis Quran isЋЇ profound ЋєinЋЇ wisdom, but warnings are of no benefit Ћєto themЋЇ"
  54,6,So turn away from them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ. ЋєAnd wait forЋЇ the Day ЋєwhenЋЇ the caller¬†will summon ЋєthemЋЇ for something horrifying
  54,7,"With eyes downcast, they will come forth from the graves as if they were swarming locusts"
  54,8,"rushing towards the caller. The disbelievers will cry, вАЬThis is a difficult Day!вАЭ"
  54,9,"Before them, the people of Noah denied Ћєthe truthЋЇ and rejected Our servant, calling ЋєhimЋЇ insane. And he was intimidated"
  54,10,"So he cried out to his Lord, вАЬI am helpless, so help ЋєmeЋЇ!вАЭ"
  54,11,So We opened the gates of the sky with pouring rain
  54,12,"and caused the earth to burst with springs, so the waters met for a fate already set"
  54,13,We carried him on that ЋєArk madeЋЇ of planks and nails
  54,14,sailing under Our ЋєwatchfulЋЇ EyesвАФa ЋєfairЋЇ punishment on behalf of the one ЋєtheyЋЇ denied
  54,15,We certainly left this¬†as a sign. So is there anyone who will be mindful
  54,16,Then how ЋєdreadfulЋЇ were My punishment and warnings
  54,17,And We have certainly made the Quran easy to remember. So is there anyone who will be mindful
  54,18,вАЩ»Вd ЋєalsoЋЇ rejected Ћєthe truthЋЇ. Then how ЋєdreadfulЋЇ were My punishment and warnings
  54,19,"Indeed, We sent against them a furious wind,¬†on a day of unrelenting misery"
  54,20,"that snatched people up, leaving them like trunks of uprooted palm trees"
  54,21,Then how ЋєdreadfulЋЇ were My punishment and warnings
  54,22,And We have certainly made the Quran easy to remember. So is there anyone who will be mindful
  54,23,Tham√їd rejected the warnings Ћєas wellЋЇ
  54,24,"arguing, вАЬHow can we follow one ЋєaverageЋЇ human being from among us? We would then truly be misguided and insane"
  54,25,"Has the revelation been sent down ЋєonlyЋЇ to him out of Ћєall ofЋЇ us? In fact, he is a boastful liar.вАЭ"
  54,26,"ЋєIt was revealed to бєҐ√ҐliбЄ•,ЋЇ вАЬThey will soon know who the boastful liar is"
  54,27,"We are sending the she-camel as a test for them. So watch them ЋєcloselyЋЇ, and have patience"
  54,28,"And tell them that the ЋєdrinkingЋЇ water must be divided between them Ћєand herЋЇ, each taking a turn to drink Ћєevery other dayЋЇ.вАЭ"
  54,29,"But they roused a companion of theirs, so he dared to kill ЋєherЋЇ"
  54,30,Then how ЋєdreadfulЋЇ were My punishment and warnings
  54,31,"Indeed, We sent against them ЋєonlyЋЇ one ЋєmightyЋЇ blast, leaving them like the twigs of fence-builders"
  54,32,And We have certainly made the Quran easy to remember. So is there anyone who will be mindful
  54,33,The people of Lot ЋєalsoЋЇ rejected the warnings
  54,34,"We unleashed upon them a storm of stones. As for Ћєthe believers ofЋЇ LotвАЩs family, We delivered them before dawn"
  54,35,as a blessing from Us. This is how We reward whoever gives thanks
  54,36,He had already warned them of Our ЋєcrushingЋЇ blow but they disputed the warnings
  54,37,"And they even demanded his angel-guests from him,¬†so We blinded their eyes. ЋєAnd they were told,ЋЇ вАЬTaste then My punishment and warnings!вАЭ"
  54,38,"And indeed, by the early morning they were overwhelmed by an unrelenting torment"
  54,39,"ЋєAgain they were told,ЋЇ вАЬTaste now My punishment and warnings!вАЭ"
  54,40,And We have certainly made the Quran easy to remember. So is there anyone who will be mindful
  54,41,"And indeed, the warnings ЋєalsoЋЇ came to the people of Pharaoh"
  54,42,"ЋєButЋЇ they rejected all of Our signs, so We seized them with the ЋєcrushingЋЇ grip of the Almighty, Most Powerful"
  54,43,"Now, are you ЋєMeccanЋЇ disbelievers superior to those Ћєdestroyed peoplesЋЇ? Or have you Ћєbeen grantedЋЇ immunity Ћєfrom punishmentЋЇ in divine Books"
  54,44,"Or do they say, вАЬWe are all ЋєaЋЇ united ЋєfrontЋЇ, bound to prevail.вАЭ"
  54,45,ЋєSoonЋЇ their united front will be defeated and Ћєforced toЋЇ flee
  54,46,"Better yet, the Hour is their appointed timeвАФand the Hour will be most catastrophic and most bitter"
  54,47,"Indeed, the wicked are ЋєentrenchedЋЇ in misguidance, and Ћєare bound forЋЇ blazes"
  54,48,"On the Day they will be dragged into the Fire on their faces, Ћєthey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬTaste the touch of Hell!вАЭ"
  54,49,"Indeed, We have created everything, perfectly preordained"
  54,50,"Our command¬†is but a single word,¬†done in the blink of an eye"
  54,51,We have already destroyed the likes of you. So will any Ћєof youЋЇ be mindful
  54,52,Everything they have done is ЋєlistedЋЇ in ЋєtheirЋЇ records
  54,53,"Every matter, small and large, is written ЋєpreciselyЋЇ"
  54,54,"Indeed, the righteous will be amid Gardens and rivers"
