  57,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and the earth glorifies Allah, for He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  57,2,To Him belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He gives life and causes death. And He is Most Capable of everything
  57,3,"He is the First and the Last, the Most High and Most Near,¬†and He has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  57,4,"He is the One Who created the heavens and the earth in six Days,¬†then established Himself on the Throne. He knows whatever goes into the earth and whatever comes out of it, and whatever descends from the sky and whatever ascends into it. And He is with you wherever you are.¬†For Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  57,5,To Him belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And to Allah all matters are returned
  57,6,He merges the night into day and the day into night. And He knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart
  57,7,"Believe in Allah and His Messenger, and donate from what He has entrusted you with. So those of you who believe and donate will have a mighty reward"
  57,8,"Why do you not believe in Allah while the Messenger is inviting you to have faith in your Lord, although He has already taken your covenant,¬†if you will ever believe"
  57,9,He is the One Who sends down clear revelations to His servant to bring you out of darkness and into light. For indeed Allah is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to you
  57,10,"And why should you not spend in the cause of Allah, while Allah is the ЋєsoleЋЇ inheritor of the heavens and the earth? Those of you who donated and fought before the victory Ћєover MeccaЋЇ are unparalleled. They are far greater in rank than those who donated and fought afterwards.¬†Yet Allah has promised each a fine reward. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  57,11,"Who is it that will lend to Allah a good loan which Allah will multiply Ћєmany times overЋЇ for them, and they will have an honourable reward"
  57,12,"On that Day you will see believing men and women with their light shining ahead of them and on their right. ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬToday you have good news of Gardens, under which rivers flow, Ћєfor youЋЇ to stay in forever. This is ЋєtrulyЋЇ the ultimate triumph.вАЭ"
  57,13,"On that Day hypocrite men and women will beg the believers, вАЬWait for us so that we may have some of your light.вАЭ It will be said ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬGo back Ћєto the worldЋЇ and seek a light ЋєthereЋЇ!вАЭ Then a ЋєseparatingЋЇ wall with a gate will be erected between them. On the near side will be grace and on the far side will be torment"
  57,14,"The tormented will cry out to those graced, вАЬWere we not with you?вАЭ They will reply, вАЬYes Ћєyou wereЋЇ. But you chose to be tempted Ћєby hypocrisyЋЇ, ЋєeagerlyЋЇ awaited Ћєour demiseЋЇ, doubted Ћєthe truthЋЇ, and were deluded by false hopes until AllahвАЩs decree Ћєof your deathЋЇ came to pass. And ЋєsoЋЇ the Chief Deceiver¬†deceived you about Allah"
  57,15,"So Today no ransom will be accepted from you ЋєhypocritesЋЇ, nor from the disbelievers. Your home is the FireвАФit is the ЋєonlyЋЇ fitting place for you. What an evil destination!вАЭ"
  57,16,"Has the time not yet come for believersвАЩ hearts to be humbled at the remembrance of Allah and what has been revealed of the truth, and not be like those given the Scripture beforeвАФЋєthoseЋЇ who were spoiled for so long that their hearts became hardened. And many of them are ЋєstillЋЇ rebellious"
  57,17,Know that Allah revives the earth after its death.¬†We have certainly made the signs clear for you so perhaps you will understand
  57,18,"Indeed, those men and women who give in charity and lend to Allah a good loan will have it multiplied for them, and they will have an honourable reward"
  57,19,"ЋєAs forЋЇ those who believe in Allah and His messengers, it is they who are ЋєtrulyЋЇ the people of truth. And the martyrs, with their Lord, will have their reward and their light. But Ћєas forЋЇ those who disbelieve and reject Our signs, it is they who will be the residents of the Hellfire"
  57,20,"Know that this worldly life is no more than play, amusement, luxury, mutual boasting, and competition in wealth and children. This is like rain that causes plants to grow, to the delight of the planters. But later the plants dry up and you see them wither, then they are reduced to chaff. And in the Hereafter there will be either severe punishment or forgiveness and pleasure of Allah, whereas the life of this world is no more than the delusion of enjoyment"
  57,21,"ЋєSoЋЇ compete with one another for forgiveness from your Lord and a Paradise as vast as the heavens and the earth, prepared for those who believe in Allah and His messengers. This is the favour of Allah. He grants it to whoever He wills. And Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty"
  57,22,No calamity Ћєor blessingЋЇ occurs on earth or in yourselves without being ЋєwrittenЋЇ in a Record before We bring it into being. This is certainly easy for Allah
  57,23,"ЋєWe let you know thisЋЇ so that you neither grieve over what you have missed nor boast over what He has granted you. For Allah does not like whoever is arrogant, boastfulвАФ"
  57,24,"those who are stingy and promote stinginess among people. And whoever turns away Ћєshould know thatЋЇ Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is truly the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  57,25,"Indeed, We sent Our messengers with clear proofs, and with them We sent down the Scripture and the balance Ћєof justiceЋЇ so that people may administer justice. And We sent down iron with its great might, benefits for humanity, and means for Allah to prove who Ћєis willing toЋЇ stand up for Him and His messengers without seeing Him. Surely Allah is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  57,26,"And indeed, We sent Noah and Abraham and reserved prophethood and revelation for their descendants. Some of them are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided, while most are rebellious"
  57,27,"Then in the footsteps of these ЋєprophetsЋЇ, We sent Our messengers, and Ћєafter themЋЇ We sent Jesus, son of Mary, and granted him the Gospel, and instilled compassion and mercy into the hearts of his followers. As for monasticism, they made it upвАФWe never ordained it for themвАФonly seeking to please Allah, yet they did not ЋєevenЋЇ observe it strictly. So We rewarded those of them who were faithful. But most of them are rebellious"
  57,28,"O people of faith! Fear Allah and believe in His Messenger. ЋєAndЋЇ He will grant you a double share of His mercy, provide you with a light to walk in Ћєon Judgment DayЋЇ, and forgive you. For Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  57,29,"ЋєThis is soЋЇ that the People of the Book Ћєwho deny the ProphetЋЇ may know that they do not have any control over AllahвАЩs grace, and that all grace is in AllahвАЩs Hands. He grants it to whoever He wills. For Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty"
  58,1,"Indeed, Allah has heard the argument of the woman who pleaded with you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ concerning her husband, and appealed to Allah. Allah has heard your exchange.¬†Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  58,2,"Those of you who ЋєsinfullyЋЇ divorce their wives by comparing them to their mothers Ћєshould know thatЋЇ their wives are in no way their mothers. None can be their mothers except those who gave birth to them. What they say is certainly detestable and false. Yet Allah is truly Ever-Pardoning, All-Forgiving"
  58,3,"Those who divorce their wives in this manner, then Ћєwish toЋЇ retract what they said, must free a slave before they touch each other. This ЋєpenaltyЋЇ is meant to deter you. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,4,"But if the husband cannot afford this, let him then fast two consecutive months before the couple touch each other. But if he is unable Ћєto fastЋЇ, then let him feed sixty poor people. This is to re-affirm your faith in Allah and His Messenger. These are the limits set by Allah. And the disbelievers will suffer a painful punishment"
  58,5,"Indeed, those who defy Allah and His Messenger will be debased, just like those before them. We have certainly sent down clear revelations. And the disbelievers will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  58,6,"On the Day Allah resurrects them all together, He will then inform them of what they have done. Allah has kept account of it all, while they have forgotten it. For Allah is a Witness over all things"
  58,7,"Do you not see that Allah knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth? If three converse privately, He is their fourth. If five, He is their sixth. Whether fewer or more, He is with them¬†wherever they may be. Then, on the Day of Judgment, He will inform them of what they have done. Surely Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  58,8,"Have you not seen those who were forbidden from secret talks, yet they ЋєalwaysЋЇ return to what they were forbidden from, conspiring in sin, aggression, and disobedience to the Messenger? And when they come to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, they greet you not as Allah greets you,¬†and say to one another, вАЬWhy does Allah not punish us for what we say?вАЭ Hell is enough for themвАФthey will burn in it. And what an evil destination"
  58,9,"O believers! When you converse privately, let it not be for sin, aggression, or disobedience to the Messenger, but let it be for goodness and righteousness. And fear Allah, to Whom you will ЋєallЋЇ be gathered"
  58,10,Secret talks are only inspired by Satan to grieve the believers. Yet he cannot harm them whatsoever except by AllahвАЩs Will. So in Allah let the believers put their trust
  58,11,"O believers! When you are told to make room in gatherings, then do so. Allah will make room for you Ћєin His graceЋЇ. And if you are told to rise, then do so. Allah will elevate those of you who are faithful, and ЋєraiseЋЇ those gifted with knowledge in rank. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,12,"O believers! When you consult the Messenger privately, give something in charity before your consultation. That is better and purer for you. But if you lack the means, then Allah is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  58,13,"Are you afraid of spending in charity before your private consultations Ћєwith himЋЇ? Since you are unable to do so, and Allah has turned to you in mercy, then Ћєcontinue toЋЇ establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and obey Allah and His Messenger. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,14,Have you not seen those ЋєhypocritesЋЇ who ally themselves with a people with whom Allah is displeased? They are neither with you nor with them. And they swear to lies knowingly
  58,15,Allah has prepared for them a severe punishment. Evil indeed is what they do
  58,16,"They have made their ЋєfalseЋЇ oaths as a shield, hindering ЋєothersЋЇ from the cause of Allah. So they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  58,17,Neither their wealth nor children will be of any help to them against Allah whatsoever. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever
  58,18,"On the Day Allah resurrects them all, they will ЋєfalselyЋЇ swear to Him as they swear to you, thinking they have something to stand on. Indeed, it is they who are the ЋєtotalЋЇ liars"
  58,19,"Satan has taken hold of them, causing them to forget the remembrance of Allah. They are the party of Satan. Surely SatanвАЩs party is bound to lose"
  58,20,"ЋєAs forЋЇ those who defy Allah and His Messenger, they will definitely be among the most debased"
  58,21,"Allah has decreed, вАЬI and My messengers will certainly prevail.вАЭ Surely Allah is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  58,22,"You will never find a people who ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in Allah and the Last Day loyal to those who defy Allah and His Messenger, even if they were their parents, children, siblings, or extended family. For those ЋєbelieversЋЇ, Allah has instilled faith in their hearts and strengthened them with a spirit from Him.¬†He will admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. They are the party of Allah. Indeed, AllahвАЩs party is bound to succeed"
  59,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth glorifies Allah. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  59,2,"He is the One Who expelled the disbelievers of the People of the Book from their homes for ЋєtheirЋЇ first banishment ЋєeverЋЇ. You never thought they would go. And they thought their strongholds would put them out of AllahвАЩs reach. But Ћєthe decree ofЋЇ Allah came upon them from where they never expected. And He cast horror into their hearts so they destroyed their houses with their own hands and the hands of the believers.¬†So take a lesson Ћєfrom thisЋЇ, O people of insight"
  59,3,"Had Allah not decreed exile for them, He would have certainly punished them in this world. And in the Hereafter they will suffer the punishment of the Fire"
  59,4,"This is because they defied Allah and His Messenger. And whoever defies Allah, then Allah is truly severe in punishment"
  59,5,"Whatever palm trees you ЋєbelieversЋЇ cut down or left standing intact, it was ЋєallЋЇ by AllahвАЩs Will, so that He might disgrace the rebellious"
  59,6,As for the gains Allah has turned over to His Messenger from themвАФyou did not ЋєevenЋЇ spur on any horse or camel for such gains. But Allah gives authority to His messengers over whoever He wills. For Allah is Most Capable of everything
  59,7,"As for gains granted by Allah to His Messenger from the people of ЋєotherЋЇ lands, they are for Allah and the Messenger, his close relatives, orphans, the poor, and ЋєneedyЋЇ travellers so that wealth may not merely circulate among your rich. Whatever the Messenger gives you, take it. And whatever he forbids you from, leave it. And fear Allah. Surely Allah is severe in punishment"
  59,8,"ЋєSome of the gains will beЋЇ for poor emigrants who were driven out of their homes and wealth, seeking AllahвАЩs bounty and pleasure, and standing up for Allah and His Messenger. They are the ones true in faith"
  59,9,"As for those who had settled in the city and ЋєembracedЋЇ the faith before Ћєthe arrival ofЋЇ the emigrants, they love whoever immigrates to them, never having a desire in their hearts for whatever Ћєof the gainsЋЇ is given to the emigrants. They give Ћєthe emigrantsЋЇ preference over themselves even though they may be in need. And whoever is saved from the selfishness of their own souls, it is they who are ЋєtrulyЋЇ successful"
  59,10,"And those who come after them will pray, вАЬOur Lord! Forgive us and our fellow believers who preceded us in faith, and do not allow bitterness into our hearts towards those who believe. Our Lord! Indeed, You are Ever Gracious, Most Merciful.вАЭ"
  59,11,"Have you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ not seen the hypocrites who say to their fellow disbelievers from the People of the Book,¬†вАЬIf you are expelled, we will certainly leave with you, and We will never obey anyone against you. And if you are fought against, we will surely help you.вАЭ? But Allah bears witness that they are truly liars"
  59,12,"Indeed, if they are expelled, the hypocrites will never leave with them. And if they are fought against, the hypocrites will never help them. And even if the hypocrites did so, they would certainly flee, then the disbelievers would be left with no help"
  59,13,"Indeed, there is more fear in their hearts for you ЋєbelieversЋЇ than for Allah. That is because they are a people who do not comprehend"
  59,14,"Even united, they would not ЋєdareЋЇ fight against you except ЋєfromЋЇ within fortified strongholds or from behind walls. Their malice for each other is intense: you think they are united, yet their hearts are divided. That is because they are a people with no ЋєrealЋЇ understanding"
  59,15,"They are Ћєboth justЋЇ like those who recently went down before them:¬†they tasted the evil consequences of their doings. And they will suffer a painful punishment"
  59,16,"ЋєThey areЋЇ like Satan when he lures someone to disbelieve. Then after they have done so, he will say Ћєon Judgment DayЋЇ, вАЬI have absolutely nothing to do with you. I truly fear AllahвАФthe Lord of all worlds.вАЭ"
  59,17,"So they will both end up in the Fire, staying there forever. That is the reward of the wrongdoers"
  59,18,"O believers! Be mindful of Allah and let every soul look to what ЋєdeedsЋЇ it has sent forth for tomorrow.¬†And fear Allah, ЋєforЋЇ certainly Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  59,19,"And do not be like those who forgot Allah, so He made them forget themselves. It is they who are ЋєtrulyЋЇ rebellious"
  59,20,The residents of the Fire cannot be equal to the residents of Paradise. ЋєOnlyЋЇ the residents of Paradise will be successful
  59,21,"Had We sent down this Quran upon a mountain, you would have certainly seen it humbled and torn apart in awe of Allah. We set forth such comparisons for people, ЋєsoЋЇ perhaps they may reflect"
  59,22,"He is AllahвАФthere is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him: Knower of the seen and unseen. He is the Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  59,23,"He is AllahвАФthere is no god except Him: the King, the Most Holy, the All-Perfect, the Source of Serenity, the Watcher Ћєof allЋЇ, the Almighty, the Supreme in Might,¬†the Majestic. Glorified is Allah far above what they associate with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ"
  59,24,"He is Allah: the Creator, the Inventor, the Shaper. He ЋєaloneЋЇ has the Most Beautiful Names. Whatever is in the heavens and the earth ЋєconstantlyЋЇ glorifies Him. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  60,1,"O believers! Do not take My enemies and yours as trusted allies, showing them affection even though they deny what has come to you of the truth. They drove the Messenger and yourselves out Ћєof MeccaЋЇ, simply for your belief in Allah, your Lord. If you ЋєtrulyЋЇ emigrated¬†to struggle in My cause and seek My pleasure, Ћєthen do not take them as allies,ЋЇ disclosing secrets Ћєof the believersЋЇ to the pagans out of affection for them, when I know best whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal. And whoever of you does this has truly strayed from the Right Way"
  60,2,"If they gain the upper hand over you, they would be your ЋєopenЋЇ enemies, unleashing their hands and tongues to harm you, and wishing that you would abandon faith"
  60,3,Neither your relatives nor children will benefit you on Judgment DayвАФHe will decide between you ЋєallЋЇ. For Allah is All-Seeing of what you do
  60,4,"You already have an excellent example in Abraham and those with him, when they said to their people, вАЬWe totally dissociate ourselves from you and ЋєshunЋЇ whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you worship besides Allah. We reject you. The enmity and hatred that has arisen between us and you will last until you believe in Allah alone.вАЭ The only exception is when Abraham said to his father, вАЬI will seek forgiveness for you,ЋєвАЭ adding, вАЬbutЋЇ I cannot protect you from Allah at all.вАЭ ЋєThe believers prayed,ЋЇ вАЬOur Lord! In You we trust. And to You we ЋєalwaysЋЇ turn. And to You is the final return"
  60,5,"Our Lord! Do not subject us to the persecution of the disbelievers. Forgive us, our Lord! You ЋєaloneЋЇ are truly the Almighty, All-Wise.вАЭ"
  60,6,"You certainly have an excellent example in them for whoever has hope in Allah and the Last Day. But whoever turns away, then surely Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  60,7,"ЋєIn time,ЋЇ Allah may bring about goodwill between you and those of them you ЋєnowЋЇ hold as enemies. For Allah is Most Capable. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,8,Allah does not forbid you from dealing kindly and fairly with those who have neither fought nor driven you out of your homes. Surely Allah loves those who are fair
  60,9,"Allah only forbids you from befriending those who have fought you for ЋєyourЋЇ faith, driven you out of your homes, or supported ЋєothersЋЇ in doing so. And whoever takes them as friends, then it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ wrongdoers"
  60,10,"O believers! When the believing women come to you as emigrants,¬†test their intentionsвАФtheir faith¬†is best known to AllahвАФand if you find them to be believers, then do not send them back to the disbelievers. These ЋєwomenЋЇ are not lawful ЋєwivesЋЇ for the disbelievers, nor are the disbelievers lawful ЋєhusbandsЋЇ for them. ЋєButЋЇ repay the disbelievers whatever ЋєdowriesЋЇ they had paid. And there is no blame on you if you marry these ЋєwomenЋЇ as long as you pay them their dowries. And do not hold on to marriage with polytheistic women.¬†ЋєButЋЇ demand Ћєrepayment ofЋЇ whatever ЋєdowriesЋЇ you had paid, and let the disbelievers do the same. That is the judgment of AllahвАФHe judges between you. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  60,11,"And if any of your wives desert you to the disbelievers, and later you take spoils from them, then pay those whose wives have gone, the equivalent of whatever ЋєdowryЋЇ they had paid. And be mindful of Allah, in Whom you believe"
  60,12,"O Prophet! When the believing women come to you, pledging to you that they will neither associate anything with Allah Ћєin worshipЋЇ, nor steal, nor fornicate, nor kill their children, nor falsely attribute ЋєillegitimateЋЇ children to their husbands,¬†nor disobey you in what is right, then accept their pledge, and ask Allah to forgive them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,13,"O believers! Do not ally yourselves with a people Allah is displeased with. They already have no hope for the Hereafter, just like the disbelievers lying in ЋєtheirЋЇ graves"
  61,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth glorifies Allah. For He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  61,2,O believers! Why do you say what you do not do
  61,3,How despicable it is in the sight of Allah that you say what you do not do
  61,4,Surely Allah loves those who fight in His cause in ЋєsolidЋЇ ranks as if they were one concrete structure
  61,5,"ЋєRemember, O Prophet,ЋЇ when Moses said to his people, вАЬO my people! Why do you hurt me when you already know I am AllahвАЩs messenger to you?вАЭ So when they ЋєpersistentlyЋЇ deviated, Allah caused their hearts to deviate. For Allah does not guide the rebellious people"
  61,6,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Jesus, son of Mary, said, вАЬO children of Israel! I am truly AllahвАЩs messenger to you, confirming the Torah which came before me, and giving good news of a messenger after me whose name will be AбЄ•mad.вАЭ¬†Yet when the Prophet came to them with clear proofs, they said, вАЬThis is pure magic.вАЭ"
  61,7,Who does more wrong than the one who fabricates lies about Allah when invited to submit Ћєto HimЋЇ?¬†For Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people
  61,8,"They wish to extinguish AllahвАЩs light with their mouths, but Allah will ЋєcertainlyЋЇ perfect His light, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  61,9,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others, even to the dismay of the polytheists"
  61,10,O believers! Shall I guide you to an exchange that will save you from a painful punishment
  61,11,"ЋєIt is toЋЇ have faith in Allah and His Messenger, and strive in the cause of Allah with your wealth and your lives. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  61,12,"He will forgive your sins, and admit you into Gardens under which rivers flow, and Ћєhouse you inЋЇ splendid homes in the Gardens of Eternity. That is the ultimate triumph"
  61,13,"ЋєHe will also give youЋЇ another favour that you long for: help from Allah and an imminent victory. ЋєSoЋЇ give good news ЋєO ProphetЋЇ to the believers"
  61,14,"O believers! Stand up for Allah, as Jesus, son of Mary, asked the disciples, вАЬWho will stand up with me for Allah?вАЭ The disciples replied, вАЬWe will stand up for Allah.вАЭ Then a group from the Children of Israel believed while another disbelieved. We then supported the believers against their enemies, so they prevailed"
  62,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth ЋєconstantlyЋЇ glorifies AllahвАФthe King, the Most Holy, the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  62,2,"He is the One Who raised for the illiterate ЋєpeopleЋЇ a messenger from among themselvesвАФreciting to them His revelations, purifying them, and teaching them the Book and wisdom, for indeed they had previously been clearly astrayвАФ"
  62,3,"along with others of them who have not yet joined them Ћєin faithЋЇ. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  62,4,This is the favour of Allah. He grants it to whoever He wills. And Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty
  62,5,"The example of those who were entrusted with ЋєobservingЋЇ the Torah but failed to do so, is that of a donkey carrying books.¬†How evil is the example of those who reject AllahвАЩs signs! For Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  62,6,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬO Jews! If you claim to be AllahвАЩs chosen ЋєpeopleЋЇ out of all humanity, then wish for death, if what you say is true.вАЭ"
  62,7,But they will never wish for that because of what their hands have done.¬†And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of the wrongdoers
  62,8,"Say, вАЬThe death you are running away from will inevitably come to you. Then you will be returned to the Knower of the seen and unseen, and He will inform you of what you used to do.вАЭ"
  62,9,"O believers! When the call to prayer is made on Friday, then proceed ЋєdiligentlyЋЇ to the remembrance of Allah and leave off ЋєyourЋЇ business. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  62,10,"Once the prayer is over, disperse throughout the land and seek the bounty of Allah. And remember Allah often so you may be successful"
  62,11,"When they saw the fanfare along with the caravan, they Ћєalmost allЋЇ flocked to it, leaving you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ standing Ћєon the pulpitЋЇ. Say, вАЬWhat is with Allah is far better than amusement and merchandise. And Allah is the Best Provider.вАЭ"
  63,1,"When the hypocrites come to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ, they say, вАЬWe bear witness that you are certainly the Messenger of AllahвАЭвАФand surely Allah knows that you are His MessengerвАФbut Allah bears witness that the hypocrites are truly liars"
  63,2,"They have made their ЋєfalseЋЇ oaths as a shield, hindering ЋєothersЋЇ from the Way of Allah. Evil indeed is what they do"
  63,3,"This is because they believed and then abandoned faith. Therefore, their hearts have been sealed, so they do not comprehend"
  63,4,"When you see them, their appearance impresses you. And when they speak, you listen to their ЋєimpressiveЋЇ speech. But they are ЋєjustЋЇ like ЋєworthlessЋЇ planks of wood leaned Ћєagainst a wallЋЇ. They think every cry is against them. They are the enemy, so beware of them. May Allah condemn them! How can they be deluded Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ"
  63,5,"When it is said to them, вАЬCome! The Messenger of Allah will pray for you to be forgiven,вАЭ they turn their heads Ћєin disgustЋЇ, and you see them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ turn away in arrogance"
  63,6,"It is the same whether you pray for their forgiveness or not, Allah will not forgive them. Surely Allah does not guide the rebellious people"
  63,7,"They are the ones who say Ћєto one anotherЋЇ, вАЬDo not spend ЋєanythingЋЇ on those ЋєemigrantsЋЇ with the Messenger of Allah so that they will break away Ћєfrom himЋЇ.вАЭ But to Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ belong the treasuries of the heavens and the earth, yet the hypocrites do not comprehend"
  63,8,"They say, вАЬIf we return to Medina, the honourable will definitely expel the inferior.вАЭ But all honour and power belongs to Allah, His Messenger, and the believers, yet the hypocrites do not know"
  63,9,"O believers! Do not let your wealth or your children divert you from the remembrance of Allah. For whoever does so, it is they who are the ЋєtrueЋЇ losers"
  63,10,"And donate from what We have provided for you before death comes to one of you, and you cry, вАЬMy Lord! If only You delayed me for a short while, I would give in charity and be one of the righteous.вАЭ"
  63,11,But Allah never delays a soul when its appointed time comes. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do
  64,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth ЋєconstantlyЋЇ glorifies Allah. The kingdom is His, and all praise is for Him. For He is Most Capable of everything"
  64,2,"He is the One Who created you, yet some of you are disbelievers while some are believers. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  64,3,"He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. He shaped you Ћєin the wombЋЇ, perfecting your form. And to Him is the final return"
  64,4,He knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And He knows whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal. For Allah knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart
  64,5,"Have the stories of those who disbelieved before not reached you ЋєpagansЋЇ? They tasted the evil consequences of their doings, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  64,6,"That was because their messengers used to come to them with clear proofs, but they said ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬHow can humans be our guides?вАЭ So they persisted in disbelief and turned away. And Allah was not in need Ћєof their faithЋЇ. For Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  64,7,"The disbelievers claim they will not be resurrected. Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬYes, by my Lord, you will surely be resurrected, then you will certainly be informed of what you have done. And that is easy for Allah.вАЭ"
  64,8,So believe in Allah and His Messenger and in the Light¬†We have revealed. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do
  64,9,"ЋєConsiderЋЇ the Day He will gather you ЋєallЋЇ for the Day of GatheringвАФthat will be the Day of mutual loss and gain. So whoever believes in Allah and does good, He will absolve them of their sins and admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  64,10,"As for those who disbelieve and reject Our revelations, they will be the residents of the Fire, staying there forever. What an evil destination"
  64,11,"No calamity befalls ЋєanyoneЋЇ except by AllahвАЩs Will. And whoever has faith in Allah, He will ЋєrightlyЋЇ guide their hearts Ћєthrough adversityЋЇ. And Allah has ЋєperfectЋЇ knowledge of all things"
  64,12,"Obey Allah and obey the Messenger! But if you turn away, then Our MessengerвАЩs duty is only to deliver Ћєthe messageЋЇ clearly"
  64,13,AllahвАФthere is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. So in Allah let the believers put their trust
  64,14,"O believers! Indeed, some of your spouses and children are enemies to you,¬†so beware of them. But if you pardon, overlook, and forgive Ћєtheir faultsЋЇ, then Allah is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  64,15,"Your wealth and children are only a test, but Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ has a great reward"
  64,16,"So be mindful of Allah to the best of your ability, hear and obey, and spend in charityвАФthat will be best for you. And whoever is saved from the selfishness of their own souls, it is they who are ЋєtrulyЋЇ successful"
  64,17,"If you lend to Allah a good loan, He will multiply it for you and forgive you. For Allah is Most Appreciative, Most Forbearing"
  64,18,"ЋєHe is theЋЇ Knower of the seen and unseenвАФthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  65,1,"O Prophet! ЋєInstruct the believers:ЋЇ When you Ћєintend toЋЇ divorce women, then divorce them with concern for their waiting period,¬†and count it accurately. And¬†fear Allah, your Lord. Do not force them out of their homes, nor should they leaveвАФunless they commit a blatant misconduct. These are the limits set by Allah. And whoever transgresses AllahвАЩs limits has truly wronged his own soul. You never know, perhaps Allah will bring about a change Ћєof heartЋЇ later"
  65,2,"Then when they have ЋєalmostЋЇ reached the end of their waiting period, either retain them honourably or separate from them honourably.¬†And call two of your reliable men to witness Ћєeither wayЋЇвАФand Ћєlet the witnessesЋЇ bear true testimony for Ћєthe sake ofЋЇ Allah. This is enjoined on whoever has faith in Allah and the Last Day. And whoever is mindful of Allah, He will make a way out for them"
  65,3,"and provide for them from sources they could never imagine. And whoever puts their trust in Allah, then He ЋєaloneЋЇ is sufficient for them. Certainly Allah achieves His Will. Allah has already set a destiny for everything"
  65,4,"As for your women past the age of menstruation, in case you do not know, their waiting period is three months, and those who have not menstruated as well. As for those who are pregnant, their waiting period ends with delivery.¬†And whoever is mindful of Allah, He will make their matters easy for them"
  65,5,"This is the commandment of Allah, which He has revealed to you. And whoever is mindful of Allah, He will absolve them of their sins and reward them immensely"
  65,6,"Let them live where you live Ћєduring their waiting periodЋЇ, according to your means. And do not harass them to make their stay unbearable. If they are pregnant, then maintain them until they deliver. And if they nurse your child,¬†compensate them, and consult together courteously. But if you fail to reach an agreement, then another woman will nurse Ћєthe childЋЇ for the father"
  65,7,"Let the man of wealth provide according to his means. As for the one with limited resources, let him provide according to whatever Allah has given him. Allah does not require of any soul beyond what He has given it. After hardship, Allah will bring about ease"
  65,8,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many societies rebelled against the commandments of their Lord and His messengers, so We called each ЋєsocietyЋЇ to a severe account and subjected them to a horrible punishment"
  65,9,"So they tasted the evil consequences of their doings, and the outcome of their doings was ЋєtotalЋЇ loss"
  65,10,"Allah has ЋєalsoЋЇ prepared for them a severe punishment. So fear Allah, O people of reason and faith. Allah has indeed revealed to you a Reminder"
  65,11,"Ћєand sentЋЇ a messenger reciting to you AllahвАЩs revelations, making things clear so that He may bring those who believe and do good out of darkness and into light. And whoever believes in Allah and does good will be admitted by Him into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. Allah will have indeed granted them an excellent provision"
  65,12,"Allah is the One Who created seven heavens Ћєin layersЋЇ, and likewise for the earth. The ЋєdivineЋЇ command descends between them so you may know that Allah is Most Capable of everything and that Allah certainly encompasses all things in ЋєHisЋЇ knowledge"
  66,1,"O Prophet! Why do you prohibit ЋєyourselfЋЇ from what Allah has made lawful to you, seeking to please your wives? And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  66,2,"Allah has already ordained for you ЋєbelieversЋЇ the way to absolve yourselves from your oaths.¬†For Allah is your Guardian. And He is the All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  66,3,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the Prophet had ЋєonceЋЇ confided something to one of his wives, then when she disclosed it Ћєto another wifeЋЇ and Allah made it known to him, he presented Ћєto herЋЇ part of what was disclosed and overlooked a part. So when he informed her of it, she exclaimed, вАЬWho told you this?вАЭ He replied, вАЬI was informed by the All-Knowing, All-Aware.вАЭ"
  66,4,"ЋєIt will be betterЋЇ if you ЋєwivesЋЇ both turn to Allah in repentance, for your hearts have certainly faltered. But if you Ћєcontinue toЋЇ collaborate against him, then Ћєknow thatЋЇ Allah Himself is his Guardian. And Gabriel, the righteous believers, and the angels are ЋєallЋЇ his supporters as well"
  66,5,"Perhaps, if he were to divorce you ЋєallЋЇ, his Lord would replace you with better wives who are submissive Ћєto AllahЋЇ, faithful Ћєto HimЋЇ, devout, repentant, dedicated to worship and fastingвАФpreviously married or virgins"
  66,6,"O believers! Protect yourselves and your families from a Fire whose fuel is people and stones, overseen by formidable and severe angels, who never disobey whatever Allah ordersвАФalways doing as commanded"
  66,7,"ЋєThe deniers will then be told,ЋЇ вАЬO disbelievers! Make no excuses this Day! You are only rewarded for what you used to do.вАЭ"
  66,8,"O believers! Turn to Allah in sincere repentance, so your Lord may absolve you of your sins and admit you into Gardens, under which rivers flow, on the Day Allah will not disgrace the Prophet or the believers with him. Their light will shine ahead of them and on their right. They will say, вАЬOur Lord! Perfect our light for us, and forgive us. ЋєForЋЇ You are truly Most Capable of everything.вАЭ"
  66,9,"O Prophet! Struggle against the disbelievers and the hypocrites, and be firm with them. Hell will be their home. What an evil destination"
  66,10,"Allah sets forth an example for the disbelievers: the wife of Noah and the wife of Lot. Each was married to one of Our righteous servants, yet betrayed them.¬†So their husbands were of no benefit to them against Allah whatsoever. Both were told, вАЬEnter the Fire, along with the others!вАЭ"
  66,11,"And Allah sets forth an example for the believers: the wife of Pharaoh, who prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Build me a house in Paradise near You, deliver me from Pharaoh and his ЋєevilЋЇ doing, and save me from the wrongdoing people.вАЭ"
  66,12,"ЋєThere isЋЇ also Ћєthe example ofЋЇ Mary, the daughter of вАЩImr√Ґn, who guarded her chastity, so We breathed into her ЋєwombЋЇ through Our angel ЋєGabrielЋЇ.¬†She testified to the words of her Lord and His Scriptures, and was one of the ЋєsincerelyЋЇ devout"
  67,1,Blessed is the One in Whose Hands rests all authority. And He is Most Capable of everything
  67,2,"ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who created death and life in order to test which of you is best in deeds. And He is the Almighty, All-Forgiving"
  67,3,"ЋєHe is the OneЋЇ Who created seven heavens, one above the other. You will never see any imperfection in the creation of the Most Compassionate.¬†So look again: do you see any flaws"
  67,4,Then look again and againвАФyour sight will return frustrated and weary
  67,5,"And indeed, We adorned the lowest heaven with Ћєstars likeЋЇ lamps, and made them Ћєas missilesЋЇ for stoning ЋєeavesdroppingЋЇ devils, for whom We have also prepared the torment of the Blaze"
  67,6,Those who disbelieve in their Lord will suffer the punishment of Hell. What an evil destination
  67,7,"When they are tossed into it, they will hear its roaring as it boils over"
  67,8,"almost bursting in fury. Every time a group is cast into it, its keepers will ask them, вАЬDid a warner not come to you?вАЭ"
  67,9,"They will reply, вАЬYes, a warner did come to us, but we denied and said, вАШAllah has revealed nothing. You are extremely astray.вАЩвАЭ"
  67,10,"And they will lament, вАЬIf only we had listened and reasoned, we would not be among the residents of the Blaze!вАЭ"
  67,11,And so they will confess their sins. So away with the residents of the Blaze
  67,12,"Indeed, those in awe of their Lord without seeing Him¬†will have forgiveness and a mighty reward"
  67,13,Whether you speak secretly or openlyвАФHe surely knows best what is ЋєhiddenЋЇ in the heart
  67,14,"How could He not know His Own creation? For He ЋєaloneЋЇ is the Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  67,15,"He is the One Who smoothed out the earth for you, so move about in its regions and eat from His provisions. And to Him is the resurrection Ћєof allЋЇ"
  67,16,Do you feel secure that the One Who is in heaven will not cause the earth to swallow you up as it quakes violently
  67,17,Or do you feel secure that the One Who is in heaven will not unleash upon you a storm of stones. Only then would you know how ЋєseriousЋЇ My warning was
  67,18,"And certainly those before them denied Ћєas wellЋЇ, then how severe was My response"
  67,19,"Have they not seen the birds above them, spreading and folding their wings? None holds them up except the Most Compassionate. Indeed, He is All-Seeing of everything"
  67,20,"Also, which ЋєpowerlessЋЇ force will come to your help instead of the Most Compassionate? Indeed, the disbelievers are only ЋєlostЋЇ in delusion"
  67,21,"Or who is it that will provide for you if He withholds His provision? In fact, they persist in arrogance and aversion Ћєto the truthЋЇ"
  67,22,"Who is ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided: the one who crawls facedown or the one who walks upright on the Straight Path"
  67,23,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHe is the One Who brought you into being and gave you hearing, sight, and intellect. ЋєYetЋЇ you hardly give any thanks.вАЭ"
  67,24,"ЋєAlsoЋЇ say, вАЬHe is the One Who has dispersed you ЋєallЋЇ over the earth, and to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be gathered.вАЭ"
  67,25,"ЋєStillЋЇ they ask Ћєthe believersЋЇ, вАЬWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?вАЭ"
  67,26,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬThat knowledge is with Allah alone, and I am only sent with a clear warning.вАЭ"
  67,27,"Then when they see the torment drawing near, the faces of the disbelievers will become gloomy, and it will be said Ћєto themЋЇ, вАЬThis is what you claimed would never come.вАЭ"
  67,28,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬConsider this: whether Allah causes me and those with me to die or shows us mercy, who will save the disbelievers from a painful punishment?вАЭ"
  67,29,"Say, вАЬHe is the Most CompassionateвАФin Him ЋєaloneЋЇ we believe, and in Him ЋєaloneЋЇ we trust. You will soon know who is clearly astray.вАЭ"
  67,30,"Say, вАЬConsider this: if your water were to sink Ћєinto the earthЋЇ, then who ЋєelseЋЇ could bring you flowing water?вАЭ"
  68,1,N≈©n. By the pen and what everyone writes
  68,2,"By the grace of your Lord, you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ are not insane"
  68,3,You will certainly have a never-ending reward
  68,4,And you are truly Ћєa manЋЇ of outstanding character
  68,5,Soon you and the pagans will see
  68,6,which of you is mad
  68,7,Surely your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ knows best who has strayed from His Way and who is ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  68,8,So do not give in to the deniers
  68,9,They wish you would compromise so they would yield Ћєto youЋЇ
  68,10,"And do not obey the despicable, vain oath-taker"
  68,11,"slanderer, gossip-monger"
  68,12,"withholder of good, transgressor, evildoer"
  68,13,"brute, andвАФon top of all thatвАФan illegitimate child"
  68,14,"Now, ЋєsimplyЋЇ because he has been blessed with ЋєabundantЋЇ wealth and children"
  68,15,"whenever Our revelations are recited to him, he says, вАЬAncient fables!вАЭ"
  68,16,We will soon mark his snout
  68,17,"Indeed, We have tested those ЋєMeccansЋЇ as We tested the owners of the gardenвАФwhen they swore they would surely harvest ЋєallЋЇ its fruit in the early morning"
  68,18,leaving no thought for AllahвАЩs Will
  68,19,Then it was struck by a torment from your Lord while they slept
  68,20,so it was reduced to ashes
  68,21,Then by daybreak they called out to each other
  68,22,"Ћєsaying,ЋЇ вАЬGo early to your harvest, if you want to pick ЋєallЋЇ the fruit.вАЭ"
  68,23,"So they went off, whispering to one another"
  68,24,вАЬDo not let any poor person enter your garden today.вАЭ
  68,25,"And they proceeded early, totally fixated on their purpose"
  68,26,"But when they saw it ЋєdevastatedЋЇ, they cried, вАЬWe must have lost ЋєourЋЇ way"
  68,27,"In fact, we have been deprived Ћєof our livelihoodЋЇ.вАЭ"
  68,28,"The most sensible of them said, вАЬDid I not urge you to say, вАШAllah willing.вАЩ?вАЭ"
  68,29,"They replied, вАЬGlory be to our Lord! We have truly been wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  68,30,"Then they turned on each other, throwing blame"
  68,31,"They said, вАЬWoe to us! We have certainly been transgressors"
  68,32,"We trust our Lord will give us a better garden than this, ЋєforЋЇ we are indeed turning to our Lord with hope.вАЭ"
  68,33,"That is the Ћєway of OurЋЇ punishment Ћєin this worldЋЇ. But the punishment of the Hereafter is certainly far worse, if only they knew"
  68,34,"Indeed, the righteous will have the Gardens of Bliss with their Lord"
  68,35,Should We then treat those who have submitted like the wicked
  68,36,What is the matter with you? How do you judge
  68,37,"Or do you have a scripture, in which you read"
  68,38,that you will have whatever you choose
  68,39,Or do you have oaths binding on Us until the Day of Judgment that you will have whatever you decide
  68,40,Ask them ЋєO ProphetЋЇ which of them can guarantee all that
  68,41,"Or do they have associate-gods Ћєsupporting this claimЋЇ? Then let them bring forth their associate-gods, if what they say is true"
  68,42,"ЋєBeware ofЋЇ the Day the Shin Ћєof AllahЋЇ will be bared,¬†and the wicked will be asked to prostrate, but they will not be able to do so"
  68,43,"with eyes downcast, totally covered with disgrace. For they were ЋєalwaysЋЇ called to prostrate Ћєin the worldЋЇ when they were fully capable Ћєbut they chose not toЋЇ"
  68,44,So leave to Me ЋєO ProphetЋЇ those who reject this message. We will gradually draw them to destruction in ways they cannot comprehend
  68,45,"I ЋєonlyЋЇ delay their end for a while, but My planning is flawless"
  68,46,Or are you asking them for a reward Ћєfor the messageЋЇ so that they are overburdened by debt
  68,47,"Or do they have access to Ћєthe Record inЋЇ the unseen, so they copy it Ћєfor all to seeЋЇ"
  68,48,"So be patient with your LordвАЩs decree, and do not be like ЋєJonah,ЋЇ the Man of the Whale, who cried out Ћєto AllahЋЇ, in total distress"
  68,49,"Had he not been shown grace by his Lord, he would have certainly been cast onto the open ЋєshoreЋЇ, still blameworthy"
  68,50,"Then his Lord chose him, making him one of the righteous"
  68,51,"The disbelievers would almost cut you down with their eyes when they hear Ћєyou reciteЋЇ the Reminder,¬†and say, вАЬHe is certainly a madman.вАЭ"
  68,52,But it is simply a reminder to the whole world
  69,1,The Inevitable Hour
  69,2,What is the Inevitable Hour
  69,3,And what will make you realize what the Inevitable Hour is
  69,4,ЋєBothЋЇ Tham√їd and вАЩ»Вd denied the Striking Disaster
  69,5,"As for Tham√їd, they were destroyed by an overwhelming blast"
  69,6,"And as for вАЩ»Вd, they were destroyed by a furious, bitter wind"
  69,7,"which Allah unleashed on them non-stop for seven nights and eight days, so that you would have seen its people lying dead like trunks of uprooted palm trees"
  69,8,Do you see any of them left alive
  69,9,"Also, Pharaoh and those before him, and Ћєthe people ofЋЇ the overturned cities Ћєof LotЋЇ indulged in sin"
  69,10,"each disobeying their LordвАЩs messenger, so He seized them with a crushing grip"
  69,11,"Indeed, when the floodwater had overflowed, We carried you¬†in the floating Ark Ћєwith NoahЋЇ"
  69,12,"so that We may make this a reminder to you, and that attentive ears may grasp it"
  69,13,"At last, when the Trumpet will be blown with one blast"
  69,14,and the earth and mountains will be lifted up and crushed with one blow
  69,15,on that Day the Inevitable Event will have come to pass
  69,16,The sky will then be so torn that it will be frail
  69,17,with the angels on its sides. On that Day eight Ћєmighty angelsЋЇ will bear the Throne of your Lord above them
  69,18,"You will then be presented Ћєbefore Him for judgmentЋЇ, and none of your secrets will stay hidden"
  69,19,"As for those given their records in their right hand, they will cry ЋєhappilyЋЇ, вАЬHere ЋєeveryoneЋЇ! Read my record"
  69,20,I surely knew I would face my reckoning.вАЭ
  69,21,They will be in a life of bliss
  69,22,in an elevated Garden
  69,23,whose fruit will hang within reach
  69,24,"ЋєThey will be told,ЋЇ вАЬEat and drink joyfully for what you did in the days gone by.вАЭ"
  69,25,"And as for those given their record in their left hand, they will cry ЋєbitterlyЋЇ, вАЬI wish I had not been given my record"
  69,26,nor known anything of my reckoning
  69,27,I wish death was the end
  69,28,My wealth has not benefited me
  69,29,My authority has been stripped from me.вАЭ
  69,30,"ЋєIt will be said,ЋЇ вАЬSeize and shackle them"
  69,31,then burn them in Hell
  69,32,then tie them up with chains seventy arms long
  69,33,"For they never had faith in Allah, the Greatest"
  69,34,nor encouraged the feeding of the poor
  69,35,So this Day they will have no close friend here
  69,36,nor any food except ЋєoozingЋЇ pus
  69,37,which none will eat except the evildoers.вАЭ
  69,38,"Now, I do swear by whatever you see"
  69,39,and whatever you cannot see
  69,40,"Indeed, this ЋєQuranЋЇ is the recitation of a noble Messenger"
  69,41,"It is not the prose of a poet Ћєas you claimЋЇ, ЋєyetЋЇ you hardly have any faith"
  69,42,"Nor is it the mumbling of a fortune-teller, ЋєyetЋЇ you are hardly mindful"
  69,43,ЋєIt isЋЇ a revelation from the Lord of all worlds
  69,44,Had the Messenger made up something in Our Name
  69,45,We would have certainly seized him by his right hand
  69,46,then severed his aorta
  69,47,and none of you could have shielded him Ћєfrom UsЋЇ
  69,48,"Indeed, this ЋєQuranЋЇ is a reminder to those mindful Ћєof AllahЋЇ"
  69,49,And We certainly know that some of you will persist in denial
  69,50,and it will surely be a source of regret for the disbelievers
  69,51,"And indeed, this ЋєQuranЋЇ is the absolute truth"
  69,52,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Greatest"
  70,1,A challenger¬†has demanded a punishment bound to come
  70,2,for the disbelieversвАФto be averted by noneвАФ
  70,3,"from Allah, Lord of pathways of ЋєheavenlyЋЇ ascent"
  70,4,Ћєthrough whichЋЇ the angels and the ЋєholyЋЇ spirit¬†will ascend to Him on a Day fifty thousand years in length
  70,5,"So endure Ћєthis denial, O Prophet,ЋЇ with beautiful patience"
  70,6,They truly see this ЋєDayЋЇ as impossible
  70,7,but We see it as inevitable
  70,8,On that Day the sky will be like molten brass
  70,9,and the mountains like Ћєtufts ofЋЇ wool
  70,10,And no close friend will ask ЋєaboutЋЇ their friends
  70,11,ЋєalthoughЋЇ they will be made to see each other. The wicked will wish to ransom themselves from the punishment of that Day by their children
  70,12,"their spouses, their siblings"
  70,13,their clan that sheltered them
  70,14,"and everyone on earth altogether, just to save themselves"
  70,15,But no! There will certainly be a raging Flame
  70,16,ripping off scalps
  70,17,It will summon whoever turned their backs Ћєon AllahЋЇ and turned away Ћєfrom the truthЋЇ
  70,18,and gathered and hoarded ЋєwealthЋЇ
  70,19,"Indeed, humankind was created impatient"
  70,20,distressed when touched with evil
  70,21,and withholding when touched with goodвАФ
  70,22,except those who pray
  70,23,consistently performing their prayers
  70,24,and who give the rightful share of their wealth
  70,25,to the beggar and the poor
  70,26,and who ЋєfirmlyЋЇ believe in the Day of Judgment
  70,27,and those who fear the punishment of their LordвАФ
  70,28,Ћєknowing thatЋЇ none should feel secure from their LordвАЩs punishmentвАФ
  70,29,and those who guard their chastity
  70,30,"except with their wives or those ЋєbondwomenЋЇ in their possession,¬†for then they are free from blame"
  70,31,but whoever seeks beyond that are the transgressors
  70,32,ЋєThe faithful areЋЇ also those who are true to their trusts and covenants
  70,33,and who are honest in their testimony
  70,34,and who are ЋєproperlyЋЇ observant of their prayers
  70,35,"These will be in Gardens, held in honour"
  70,36,So what is the matter with the disbelievers that they rush Ћєhead-longЋЇ towards you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ
  70,37,"from the right and the left, in groups Ћєto mock youЋЇ"
  70,38,Does every one of them expect to be admitted into a Garden of Bliss
  70,39,"But no! Indeed, they ЋєalreadyЋЇ know what We created them from"
  70,40,"So, I do swear by the Lord of ЋєallЋЇ the points of sunrise and sunset¬†that We are truly capable"
  70,41,"of replacing them with ЋєothersЋЇ better than them, and We cannot be prevented Ћєfrom doing soЋЇ"
  70,42,"So let them indulge Ћєin falsehoodЋЇ and amuse ЋєthemselvesЋЇ until they face their Day, which they have been threatened withвАФ"
  70,43,"the Day they will come forth from the graves swiftly, as if racing to an idol Ћєfor a blessingЋЇ"
  70,44,"with eyes downcast, utterly covered with disgrace. That is the Day they have ЋєalwaysЋЇ been warned of"
  71,1,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people Ћєsaying to himЋЇ, вАЬWarn your people before a painful punishment comes to them.вАЭ"
  71,2,"Noah proclaimed, вАЬO my people! I am truly sent to you with a clear warning"
  71,3,"worship Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ, fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive your sins, and delay your end until the appointed time.¬†Indeed, when the time set by Allah comes, it cannot be delayed, if only you knew!вАЭ"
  71,5,"He cried, вАЬMy Lord! I have surely called my people day and night"
  71,6,but my calls only made them run farther away
  71,7,"And whenever I invite them to be forgiven by You, they press their fingers into their ears, cover themselves with their clothes, persist Ћєin denialЋЇ, and act very arrogantly"
  71,8,Then I certainly called them openly
  71,9,then I surely preached to them publicly and privately
  71,10,"saying, вАШSeek your LordвАЩs forgiveness, ЋєforЋЇ He is truly Most Forgiving"
  71,11,He will shower you with abundant rain
  71,12,"supply you with wealth and children, and give you gardens as well as rivers"
  71,13,What is the matter with you that you are not in awe of the Majesty of Allah
  71,14,when He truly created you in stages Ћєof developmentЋЇ
  71,15,"Do you not see how Allah created seven heavens, one above the other"
  71,16,"placing the moon within them as a ЋєreflectedЋЇ light, and the sun as a ЋєradiantЋЇ lamp"
  71,17,Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ caused you¬†to grow from the earth like a plant
  71,18,"Then He will return you to it, and then simply bring you forth ЋєagainЋЇ"
  71,19,And Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ spread out the earth for you
  71,20,to walk along its spacious pathways.вАЩвАЭ
  71,21,"ЋєEventually,ЋЇ Noah cried, вАЬMy Lord! They have certainly persisted in disobeying me, and followed ЋєinsteadЋЇ those ЋєeliteЋЇ whose ЋєabundantЋЇ wealth and children only increase them in loss"
  71,22,and who have devised a tremendous plot
  71,23,"urging Ћєtheir followersЋЇ, вАШDo not abandon your idolsвАФespecially Wadd, Suw√ҐвАЩ, Yagh√їth, YaвАЩ√їq, and Nasr.вАЩ"
  71,24,"Those ЋєeliteЋЇ have already led many astray. So ЋєO LordЋЇ, only allow the wrongdoers to stray farther away.вАЭ"
  71,25,"So because of their sins, they were drowned, then admitted into the Fire. And they found none to help them against Allah"
  71,26,"Noah had prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Do not leave a single disbeliever on earth"
  71,27,"For if You spare Ћєany ofЋЇ them, they will certainly mislead Your servants, and give birth only to ЋєwickedЋЇ sinners, staunch disbelievers"
  71,28,"My Lord! Forgive me, my parents, and whoever enters my house in faith, and ЋєallЋЇ believing men and women. And increase the wrongdoers only in destruction.вАЭ"
  72,1,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬIt has been revealed to me that a group of jinn listened Ћєto the Quran,ЋЇ and said Ћєto their fellow jinnЋЇ: вАШIndeed, we have heard a wondrous recitation"
  72,2,"It leads to Right Guidance so we believed in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord Ћєin worshipЋЇ"
  72,3,"ЋєNow, we believe thatЋЇ our LordвАФExalted is His MajestyвАФhas neither taken a mate nor offspring"
  72,4,and that the foolish of us used to utter ЋєoutrageousЋЇ falsehoods about Allah
  72,5,We certainly thought that humans and jinn would never speak lies about Allah
  72,6,And some men used to seek refuge with some jinnвАФso they increased each other in wickedness
  72,7,"And those ЋєhumansЋЇ thought, just like you ЋєjinnЋЇ, that Allah would not resurrect anyone Ћєfor judgmentЋЇ"
  72,8,"ЋєEarlierЋЇ we tried to reach heaven Ћєfor newsЋЇ, only to find it filled with stern guards and shooting stars"
  72,9,"We used to take up positions there for eavesdropping, but whoever dares eavesdrop now will find a flare¬†lying in wait for them"
  72,10,"Now, we have no clue whether evil is intended for those on earth, or their Lord intends for them what is right"
  72,11,Among us are those who are righteous and those who are less so. We have been of different factions
  72,12,"ЋєNow,ЋЇ we truly know that we cannot frustrate Allah on earth, nor can we escape from Him Ћєinto heavenЋЇ"
  72,13,"When we heard the guidance Ћєof the QuranЋЇ, we ЋєreadilyЋЇ believed in it. For whoever believes in their Lord will have no fear of being denied Ћєa rewardЋЇ or wronged"
  72,14,"And among us are those who have submitted Ћєto AllahЋЇ and those who are deviant. So Ћєas forЋЇ those who submitted, it is they who have attained Right Guidance"
  72,15,"And as for the deviant, they will be fuel for Hell.вАЩвАЭ"
  72,16,"Had the deniers followed the Right Way, We would have certainly granted them abundant rain to drinkвАФ"
  72,17,as a test for them.¬†And whoever turns away from the remembrance of their Lord will be admitted by Him into an overwhelming punishment
  72,18,"The places of worship are ЋєonlyЋЇ for Allah, so do not invoke anyone besides Him"
  72,19,"Yet when the servant of Allah¬†stood up calling upon Him ЋєaloneЋЇ, the pagans almost swarmed over him"
  72,20,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI call only upon my Lord, associating none with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ.вАЭ"
  72,21,"Say, вАЬIt is not in my power to harm or benefit you.вАЭ"
  72,22,"Say, вАЬNo one can protect me from Allah Ћєif I were to disobey HimЋЇ, nor can I find any refuge other than Him"
  72,23,"ЋєMy duty isЋЇ only to convey Ћєthe truthЋЇ from Allah and ЋєdeliverЋЇ His messages.вАЭ And whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger will certainly be in the Fire of Hell, to stay there for ever and ever"
  72,24,Only when they see what they have been threatened with will they know who is weaker in helpers and inferior in manpower
  72,25,"Say, вАЬI do not know if what you are promised is near or my Lord has set a distant time for it"
  72,26,"ЋєHe is theЋЇ Knower of the unseen, disclosing none of it to anyone"
  72,27,except messengers of His choice. Then He appoints angel-guards before and behind them
  72,28,"to ensure that the messengers fully deliver the messages of their LordвАФthough He ЋєalreadyЋЇ knows all about them, and keeps account of everything.вАЭ"
  73,1,O you wrapped Ћєin your clothesЋЇ
  73,2,Stand all night Ћєin prayerЋЇ except a littleвАФ
  73,3,"ЋєprayЋЇ half the night, or a little less"
  73,4,or a little moreвАФand recite the Quran ЋєproperlyЋЇ in a measured way
  73,5,ЋєForЋЇ We will soon send upon you a weighty revelation
  73,6,"Indeed, worship in the night is more impactful and suitable for recitation"
  73,7,For during the day you are over-occupied Ћєwith worldly dutiesЋЇ
  73,8,"ЋєAlwaysЋЇ remember the Name of your Lord, and devote yourself to Him wholeheartedly"
  73,9,"ЋєHe is theЋЇ Lord of the east and the west. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him, so take Him ЋєaloneЋЇ as a Trustee of Affairs"
  73,10,"Be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ with what they say, and depart from them courteously"
  73,11,And leave to Me the deniersвАФthe people of luxuryвАФand bear with them for a little while
  73,12,"ЋєForЋЇ We certainly have shackles, a ЋєragingЋЇ Fire"
  73,13,"choking food, and a painful punishment Ћєin store for themЋЇ"
  73,14,"on the Day the earth and mountains will shake ЋєviolentlyЋЇ, and mountains will be Ћєreduced toЋЇ dunes of shifting sand"
  73,15,"Indeed, We have sent to you a messenger as a witness over you, just as We sent a messenger to Pharaoh"
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the messenger, so We seized him with a stern grip"
  73,17,"If you ЋєpagansЋЇ persist in disbelief, then how will you guard yourselves against Ћєthe horrors ofЋЇ a Day which will turn childrenвАЩs hair grey"
  73,18,It will ЋєevenЋЇ cause the sky to split apart. His promise Ћєof judgmentЋЇ must be fulfilled
  73,19,Surely this is a reminder. So let whoever wills take the ЋєRightЋЇ Way to their Lord
  73,20,"Surely your Lord knows that you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ stand Ћєin prayerЋЇ for nearly two-thirds of the night, or ЋєsometimesЋЇ half of it, or a third, as do some of those with you. Allah ЋєaloneЋЇ keeps a ЋєpreciseЋЇ measure of the day and night. He knows that you ЋєbelieversЋЇ are unable to endure this, and has turned to you in mercy.¬†So recite Ћєin prayerЋЇ whatever you can from the Quran. He knows that some of you will be sick, some will be travelling throughout the land seeking AllahвАЩs bounty, and some fighting in the cause of Allah. So recite whatever you can from it. And Ћєcontinue toЋЇ perform ЋєregularЋЇ prayers, pay alms-tax, and lend to Allah a good loan.¬†Whatever good you send forth for yourselves, you will find it with Allah far better and more rewarding.¬†And seek AllahвАЩs forgiveness. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  74,1,O you covered up Ћєin your clothesЋЇ
  74,2,Arise and warn ЋєallЋЇ
  74,3,Revere your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ
  74,4,Purify your garments
  74,5,ЋєContinue toЋЇ shun idols
  74,6,Do not do a favour expecting more Ћєin returnЋЇ
  74,7,And persevere for Ћєthe sake ofЋЇ your Lord
  74,8,ЋєForЋЇ when the Trumpet will be sounded
  74,9,that will ЋєtrulyЋЇ be a difficult DayвАФ
  74,10,far from easy for the disbelievers
  74,11,And leave to me ЋєO ProphetЋЇ the one I created all by Myself
  74,12,and granted him abundant wealth
  74,13,and children always by his side
  74,14,and made life very¬†easy for him
  74,15,Yet he is hungry for more
  74,16,But no! ЋєForЋЇ he has been truly stubborn with Our revelations
  74,17,I will make his fate unbearable
  74,18,for he contemplated and determined Ћєa degrading label for the QuranЋЇ
  74,19,May he be condemned! How evil was what he determined
  74,20,May he be condemned even more! How evil was what he determined
  74,21,Then he re-contemplated Ћєin frustrationЋЇ
  74,22,then frowned and scowled
  74,23,then turned his back Ћєon the truthЋЇ and acted arrogantly
  74,24,"saying, вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ is nothing but magic from the ancients"
  74,25,This is no more than the word of a man.вАЭ
  74,26,Soon I will burn him in Hell
  74,27,And what will make you realize what Hell is
  74,28,It does not let anyone live or die
  74,29,scorching the skin
  74,30,It is overseen by nineteen ЋєkeepersЋЇ
  74,31,"We have appointed only ЋєsternЋЇ angels as wardens of the Fire. And We have made their number only as a test for the disbelievers,¬†so that the People of the Book will be certain, and the believers will increase in faith, and neither the People of the Book nor the believers will have any doubts, and so that those ЋєhypocritesЋЇ with sickness in their hearts and the disbelievers will argue, вАЬWhat does Allah mean by such a number?вАЭ In this way Allah leaves whoever He wills to stray and guides whoever He wills. And none knows the forces of your Lord except He. And this Ћєdescription of HellЋЇ is only a reminder to humanity"
  74,32,But no! By the moon
  74,33,and the night as it retreats
  74,34,and the day as it breaks
  74,35,Surely Hell is one of the mightiest catastrophesвАФ
  74,36,a warning to humankind
  74,37,to whichever of you chooses to take the lead or lag behind
  74,38,Every soul will be detained for what it has done
  74,39,except the people of the right
  74,40,"who will be in Gardens, asking one another"
  74,41,about the wicked Ћєwho will then be askedЋЇ
  74,42,вАЬWhat has landed you in Hell?вАЭ
  74,43,"They will reply, вАЬWe were not of those who prayed"
  74,44,nor did we feed the poor
  74,45,We used to indulge Ћєin falsehoodЋЇ along with others
  74,46,and deny the Day of Judgment
  74,47,until the inevitable came to us.вАЭ
  74,48,So the pleas of intercessors will be of no benefit to them
  74,49,"Now, what is the matter with them that they are turning away from the reminder"
  74,50,as if they were spooked zebras
  74,51,fleeing from a lion
  74,52,"In fact, each one of them wishes to be given a ЋєpersonalЋЇ letter Ћєfrom AllahЋЇ for all Ћєto readЋЇ"
  74,53,"But no! In fact, they do not fear the Hereafter"
  74,54,Enough! Surely this ЋєQuranЋЇ is a reminder
  74,55,So let whoever wills be mindful of it
  74,56,But they cannot do so unless Allah wills. He ЋєaloneЋЇ is worthy to be feared and entitled to forgive
  75,1,I do swear by the Day of Judgment
  75,2,And I do swear by the self-reproaching soul
  75,3,Do people think We cannot reassemble their bones
  75,4,Yes ЋєindeedЋЇ! We are ЋєmostЋЇ capable of restoring ЋєevenЋЇ their very fingertips
  75,5,Still people want to deny what is yet to come
  75,6,"asking ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬWhen is this Day of Judgment?вАЭ"
  75,7,But when the sight is stunned
  75,8,and the moon is dimmed
  75,9,and the sun and the moon are brought together
  75,10,"on that Day one will cry, вАЬWhere is the escape?вАЭ"
  75,11,But no! There will be no refuge
