  75,13,All will then be informed of what they have sent forth and left behind
  75,14,"In fact, people will testify against their own souls"
  75,15,despite the excuses they come up with
  75,16,Do not rush your tongue trying to memorize Ћєa revelation ofЋЇ the Quran
  75,17,It is certainly upon Us to Ћєmake youЋЇ memorize and recite it
  75,18,"So once We have recited a revelation Ћєthrough GabrielЋЇ, follow its recitation ЋєcloselyЋЇ"
  75,19,Then it is surely upon Us to make it clear Ћєto youЋЇ
  75,20,"But no! In fact, you love this fleeting world"
  75,21,and neglect the Hereafter
  75,22,On that Day ЋєsomeЋЇ faces will be bright
  75,23,looking at their Lord
  75,24,And ЋєotherЋЇ faces will be gloomy
  75,25,anticipating something devastating to befall them
  75,26,But no! ЋєBeware of the dayЋЇ when the soul reaches the collar bone Ћєas it leavesЋЇ
  75,27,"and it will be said, вАЬIs there any healer Ћєwho can save this lifeЋЇ?вАЭ"
  75,28,And the dying person realizes it is ЋєtheirЋЇ time to depart
  75,29,and ЋєthenЋЇ their feet are tied together Ћєin a shroudЋЇ
  75,30,On that day they will be driven to your Lord ЋєaloneЋЇ
  75,31,This denier neither believed nor prayed
  75,32,but persisted in denial and turned away
  75,33,"then went to their own people, walking boastfully"
  75,34,"Woe to you, and more woe"
  75,35,"Again, woe to you, and even more woe"
  75,36,Do people think they will be left without purpose
  75,37,Were they not ЋєonceЋЇ a sperm-drop emitted
  75,38,"Then they became a clinging clot Ћєof bloodЋЇ,¬†then He developed and perfected their form"
  75,39,"producing from it both sexes, male and female"
  75,40,Is such Ћєa CreatorЋЇ unable to bring the dead back to life
  76,1,Is there not a period of time when each human is nothing yet worth mentioning
  76,2,"ЋєForЋЇ indeed, We ЋєaloneЋЇ created humans from a drop of mixed fluids,¬†Ћєin orderЋЇ to test them, so We made them hear and see"
  76,3,"We already showed them the Way, whether they Ћєchoose toЋЇ be grateful or ungrateful"
  76,4,"Indeed, We have prepared for the disbelievers chains, shackles, and a blazing Fire"
  76,5,"Indeed, the virtuous will have a drink Ћєof pure wineЋЇвАФflavoured with camphorвАФ"
  76,6,"ЋєfromЋЇ a spring where AllahвАЩs servants will drink, flowing at their will"
  76,7,They Ћєare those whoЋЇ fulfil ЋєtheirЋЇ vows and fear a Day of sweeping horror
  76,8,"and give foodвАФdespite their desire for itвАФto the poor, the orphan, and the captive"
  76,9,"Ћєsaying to themselves,ЋЇ вАЬWe feed you only for the sake of Allah, seeking neither reward nor thanks from you"
  76,10,We fear from our Lord a horribly distressful Day.вАЭ
  76,11,"So Allah will deliver them from the horror of that Day, and grant them radiance and joy"
  76,12,and reward them for their perseverance with a Garden Ћєin ParadiseЋЇ and Ћєgarments ofЋЇ silk
  76,13,"There they will be reclining on ЋєcanopiedЋЇ couches, never seeing scorching heat or bitter cold"
  76,14,"The GardenвАЩs shade will be right above them, and its fruit will be made very easy to reach"
  76,15,They will be waited on with silver vessels and cups of crystalвАФ
  76,16,"crystalline silver, filled precisely as desired"
  76,17,And they will be given a drink Ћєof pure wineЋЇ flavoured with ginger
  76,18,"from a spring there, called Salsab√Ѓl"
  76,19,"They will be waited on by eternal youths. If you saw them, you would think they were scattered pearls"
  76,20,"And if you looked around, you would see ЋєindescribableЋЇ bliss and a vast kingdom"
  76,21,"The virtuous will be ЋєdressedЋЇ in garments of fine green silk and rich brocade, and adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them a purifying drink"
  76,22,"ЋєAnd they will be told,ЋЇ вАЬAll this is surely a reward for you. Your striving has been appreciated.вАЭ"
  76,23,"Indeed, it is We Who have revealed the Quran to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in stages"
  76,24,"So be patient with your LordвАЩs decree, and do not yield to any evildoer or ЋєstaunchЋЇ disbeliever from among them"
  76,25,ЋєAlwaysЋЇ remember the Name of your Lord morning and evening
  76,26,"and prostrate before Him during part of the night,¬†and glorify Him long at night"
  76,27,"Surely those ЋєpagansЋЇ love this fleeting world, ЋєtotallyЋЇ neglecting a weighty Day ahead of them"
  76,28,"It is We Who created them and perfected their ЋєphysicalЋЇ form. But if We will, We can easily replace them with others"
  76,29,Surely this is a reminder. So let whoever wills take the ЋєRightЋЇ Way to their Lord
  76,30,"But you cannot will Ћєto do soЋЇ unless Allah wills. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  76,31,"He admits whoever He wills into His mercy. As for the wrongdoers, He has prepared for them a painful punishment"
  77,1,By those ЋєwindsЋЇ sent forth successively
  77,2,and those blowing violently
  77,3,and those scattering ЋєraincloudsЋЇ widely
  77,4,And ЋєbyЋЇ those ЋєangelsЋЇ fully distinguishing Ћєtruth from falsehoodЋЇ
