  78,36,a ЋєfittingЋЇ reward as a generous gift from your Lord
  78,37,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, the Most Compassionate. No one will dare speak to Him"
  78,38,"on the Day the ЋєholyЋЇ spirit¬†and the angels will stand in ranks. None will talk, except those granted permission by the Most Compassionate and whose words are true"
  78,39,That Day is the ЋєultimateЋЇ truth. So let whoever wills take the path leading back to their Lord
  78,40,"Indeed, We have warned you of an imminent punishmentвАФthe Day every person will see Ћєthe consequences ofЋЇ what their hands have done, and the disbelievers will cry, вАЬI wish I were dust.вАЭ"
  79,1,By those ЋєangelsЋЇ stripping out Ћєevil soulsЋЇ harshly
